(window["webpackJsonp"]=window["webpackJsonp"]||[]).push([["chunk-2d0e4a70"],{"90ad":function(a){a.exports=JSON.parse('{"title":"Śrī Śrī Prema-vivarta","code":"en-ŚrīŚrīPrema-vivarta","chapters":[{"title":"শ্রীশ্রীপ্রেমবিবর্ত্ত","paragraphs":[{"class":"b34","text":"\\r"},{"class":"b42","text":" All glory to Śrī Guru and Śrī Gaurāṅga"},{"class":"b115","text":" শ্রীশ্রীপ্রেমবিবর্ত্ত"},{"class":"b36","text":" Śrī Śrī Prema-vivarta"},{"class":"b37","text":" Composed by<br />the intimate associate of Śrī Gaurāṅga Mahāprabhu"},{"class":"b73","text":" Śrīla Jagadānanda Paṇḍit"},{"class":"b37","text":" Published in Bengali by<br />the pre-eminent modern Vaiṣṇava Āchārya"},{"class":"b73","text":" Śrīla Sachchidānanda Bhakti Vinod Ṭhākur"},{"class":"b37","text":" Edited by<br />the self-effulgent guardian<br />of the Brahma–Mādhva–Gauḍīya sampradāya"},{"class":"b73","text":" Śrīla Bhakti Siddhānta Saraswatī Ṭhākur"},{"class":"b37","text":" whose ideal of pure devotion in Śrī Rūpa’s line<br />was protected and developed by"},{"class":"b73","text":" Śrīla Bhakti Rakṣak Śrīdhar Dev-Goswāmī Mahārāj"},{"class":"b37","text":" and spread to the hearts of fortunate souls<br />all over the world by"},{"class":"b73","text":" Śrīla Bhakti Sundar Govinda Dev-Goswāmī Mahārāj"},{"class":"b37","text":" Translated into English at the merciful request<br />of the present Sevāite-President-Āchārya<br />of Śrī Chaitanya Sāraswat Maṭh"},{"class":"b73","text":" Śrīla Bhakti Nirmal Āchārya Mahārāj"},{"class":"b37","text":" and published from"},{"class":"b38","text":" Śrī Chaitanya Sāraswat Maṭh<br />Nabadwīp"}]},{"title":"Contents","paragraphs":[{"class":"b46","text":"\\r"},{"class":"b47","text":" Contents"},{"class":"b48","text":" <span class=\\"e1\\">Translator’s Note</span>"},{"class":"b48","text":" <span class=\\"e1\\">Introduction</span>"},{"class":"b48","text":" <span class=\\"e1\\">In Praise of Sri Sri Prema-vivarta</span>"},{"class":"b48","text":" <span class=\\"e1\\">Sri Sri Prema-vivarta</span>"},{"class":"b57","text":" <span class=\\"e1\\">1 Invocation of Auspiciousness</span>"},{"class":"b57","text":" <span class=\\"e1\\">2 The Composition of this Book</span>"},{"class":"b57","text":" <span class=\\"e1\\">3 First Obeisances</span>"},{"class":"b57","text":" <span class=\\"e1\\">4 Gaura’s Greatness</span>"},{"class":"b57","text":" <span class=\\"e1\\">5 Transformations of Ecstasy in Service</span>"},{"class":"b57","text":" <span class=\\"e1\\">6 The Journey of the Soul</span>"},{"class":"b57","text":" <span class=\\"e1\\">7 The Name is for Everyone</span>"},{"class":"b57","text":" <span class=\\"e1\\">8 Give up Deceit</span>"},{"class":"b57","text":" <span class=\\"e1\\">9 Proper Renunciation</span>"},{"class":"b57","text":" <span class=\\"e1\\">10 Caste and Class</span>"},{"class":"b57","text":" <span class=\\"e1\\">11 The Light of Nabadwip</span>"},{"class":"b57","text":" <span class=\\"e1\\">12 Glories of the Vaisnavas</span>"},{"class":"b57","text":" <span class=\\"e1\\">13 Eagerness to see Sri Gaura</span>"},{"class":"b57","text":" <span class=\\"e1\\">14 Contradictory Transformations</span>"},{"class":"b57","text":" <span class=\\"e1\\">15 Morning Pastimes in Nabadwip</span>"},{"class":"b57","text":" <span class=\\"e1\\">16 What is Love?</span>"},{"class":"b57","text":" <span class=\\"e1\\">17 Different Practices for Different Devotees</span>"},{"class":"b57","text":" <span class=\\"e1\\">18 Sri Ekadasi</span>"},{"class":"b57","text":" <span class=\\"e1\\">19 A Collection of Hidden Truths about the Name</span>"},{"class":"b57","text":" <span class=\\"e1\\">20 The Glories of the Name</span>"},{"class":"b48","text":" <span class=\\"e1\\">The Ten Offences to the Holy Name</span>"},{"class":"b49","text":" <span class=\\"e1\\">Glossary</span>"}]},{"title":"Translator’s Note","paragraphs":[{"class":"b46","text":"\\r"},{"class":"b47","text":" Translator’s Note"},{"class":"b71","text":" I bow at the feet of Śrī Gurudev, the Vaiṣṇavas, Śrī Gaurasundar, and all the Lord’s exalted associates. They are our eternal shelter. With hope and joy, I present this offering to them, praying that it is satisfying to their hearts."},{"class":"b70","text":" Content"},{"class":"b71","text":" This edition of <span class=\\"e3\\">Śrī Śrī Prema-vivarta</span> has been prepared from the Bengali version of the text edited by Śrīla Bhakti Siddhānta Saraswatī Ṭhākur and published by Śrī Gauḍīya Maṭh. Reference has also been made to the original publication of the text by Śrīla Bhakti Vinod Ṭhākur in <span class=\\"e3\\">Śrī Sajjana-toṣaṇī</span>. An introduction to the author and his message precedes the text, as does an article in praise of <span class=\\"e3\\">Śrī Śrī Prema-vivarta</span> compiled from lectures by Śrīla Bhakti Rakṣak Śrīdhar Dev-Goswāmī Mahārāj. Following the text, a glossary summarises important terms, references, persons, and places that are mentioned throughout the book."},{"class":"b70","text":" Translation"},{"class":"b43","text":" The text of <span class=\\"e3\\">Śrī Śrī Prema-vivarta</span> is presented in a four-fold format: 1) the Bengali text of each verse, 2) its Roman transliteration, 3) its English prose-ordered phrase-by-phrase gloss, and 4) its English prose translation."},{"class":"b51","text":" In this edition, punctuation marks to indicate grammatical compounds, speech, and past active participles have been inserted into the Bengali text and its transliteration to aid comprehension. When reading the prose-ordered phrase-by-phrase gloss, a style of translation known as <span class=\\"e3\\">anvaya</span> which is common in Bengali translation of Sanskrit, please note:"},{"class":"b88","text":" 1) Past active participles are often conjugated in tandem with the finite verb they accompany."},{"class":"b88","text":" 2) Verb tenses are often translated to suit idiomatic usage in English (e.g. present tense and present perfect tense are often translated as simple past tense)."},{"class":"b88","text":" 3) Idiomatic uses of the passive voice in Bengali are translated in the active voice in English."},{"class":"b88","text":" 4) Correlative pronouns and prepositional cases are typically translated in the simplest grammatically equivalent forms possible."},{"class":"b67","text":" 5) Grammatically inferred and thematically implied prepositions and pronouns are set in square brackets."},{"class":"b71","text":" It is our hope that this method of presentation, combined with a minimalistic approach to the translation, will aid readers in appreciating Śrīla Jagadānanda Paṇḍit’s Bengali itself, which is delightfully bold, vivid, and sweet."},{"class":"b70","text":" Origin"},{"class":"b43","text":" This book has been prepared at the express request of Śrī Chaitanya Sāraswat Maṭh’s present Sevāite-President-Āchārya Om Viṣṇupād Śrīla Bhakti Nirmal Āchārya Mahārāj. It is his desire that Śrīla Jagadānanda Paṇḍit’s bright and concise instructions guide devotees in their practice and preaching."},{"class":"b44","text":" Numerous devotees collaborated on this publication. Śrīpād Bhakti Prapanna Tīrtha Mahārāj assisted with the translation of the text, Jagadānanda Dās Adhikārī, Viśākhā Devī Dāsī, and others provided valuable editorial assistance, and Śrīpād Bhakti Rañjan Madhusūdan Mahārāj checked over the publication as a whole. We are deeply grateful for the selfless contributions they have all made."},{"class":"b69","text":" Should any errors or shortcomings be found within the text, we pray the swan-like Vaiṣṇavas will overlook them, forgive us, and relish the essence of <span class=\\"e3\\">Śrī Śrī Prema-vivarta</span>."},{"class":"b44","text":" Śrī Gaura-jana-kiṅkar,<br />Bhakti Kamal Tyāgī<br />Śrī Chaitanya Sāraswat Maṭh<br />Śrī Dhām Nabadwīp"},{"class":"b52","text":" The divine appearance day of<br />Bhagavān Śrīla Bhakti Siddhānta <br />Saraswatī Goswāmī Ṭhākur,<br />9 February 2015"}]},{"title":"Introduction","paragraphs":[{"class":"b46","text":"\\r"},{"class":"b47","text":" Introduction"},{"class":"b70","text":" The author"},{"class":"b43","text":" The place and time of Śrīla Jagadānanda Paṇḍit’s appearance and disappearance are generally considered unknown. On the basis of <span class=\\"e3\\">Prema-vivarta</span>, in which Jagadānanda Paṇḍit refers to Kavi Karṇapūr as a ‘resident of my village’ (Pv: 8.15), it is understood that he spent his early life in Kāñchan Pallī, a town seventy kilometres south of Nabadwīp (now known as Kanchrapara). He further explains that Śivānanda Sen, Kavi Karṇapūr’s father, taught him <span class=\\"e3\\">Bhagavad-gītā</span> in his youth and brought him to Nadia (Pv: 8.17–8). It appears that this took place while Jagadānanda was still quite young, as elsewhere he sweetly describes having a quarrel with Śrī Gaurasundar as a schoolboy in Nadia (Pv: 2.18). From this time on, Jagadānanda Paṇḍit spent his entire life in the Lord’s association. Through descriptions in <span class=\\"e3\\">Śrī Chaitanya-charitāmṛta</span> and <span class=\\"e3\\">Śrī Chaitanya-bhāgavat</span>, it is known that Jagadānanda was present throughout the Lord’s Pastimes in Nadia, accompanied the Lord to Purī after His sannyās, and, apart from once visiting Vṛndāvan and making periodic trips to Bengal on the Lord’s order, lived and served in the Lord’s close association for the remainder of His Pastimes."},{"class":"b51","text":" <span class=\\"e3\\">Śrī Gaura-gaṇoddeśa-dīpikā</span> (51) identifies Śrīla Jagadānanda Paṇḍit as a manifestation of Satyabhāmā, and in <span class=\\"e3\\">Śrī Chaitanya-charitāmṛta</span> Śrīla Jagadānanda Paṇḍit’s extraordinary character and unique relationship with Śrīman Mahāprabhu are glorified profusely:"},{"class":"b59","text":" paṇḍita jagadānanda prabhura prāṇa-rūpa<br />loke khyāta ye̐ho satyabhāmāra svarūpa"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Śrī Chaitanya-charitāmṛta: Ādi-līlā, 10.21)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “Jagadānanda Paṇḍit is the life of the Lord. He is known everywhere as a manifestation of Satyabhāmā.”"},{"class":"b59","text":" prabhura atyanta priya paṇḍita-jagadānanda<br />yāhāra charitre prabhu pāyena ānanda"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Śrī Chaitanya-charitāmṛta: Antya-līlā, 19.4)"},{"class":"b43","text":" “Jagadānanda Paṇḍit was extremely dear to the Lord. The Lord derived great pleasure from his character.”"},{"class":"b51","text":" Jagadānanda Paṇḍit’s relationship with the Lord was on the highest platform of intimacy—madhura-rasa."},{"class":"b62","text":" purīra vātsalya mukhya\\trāmānandera śuddha-sakhya<br />\\tgovindādyera śuddha-dāsya-rasa<br />gadādhara jagadānanda\\tsvarūpera (mukhya) rasānanda<br />\\tei chāri-bhāve prabhu vaśa"},{"class":"b63","text":" (Śrī Chaitanya-charitāmṛta: Madhya-līlā, 2.78)"},{"class":"b43","text":" “The vātsalya of Paramānanda Purī, pure sakhya of Rāmānanda Rāy, pure dāsya of Govinda, and the joy of the madhura rasa of Gadādhar, Jagadānanda, and Svarūp Damodar—the Lord was captivated by these four moods.”"},{"class":"b51","text":" Jagadānanda Paṇḍit’s love was characterised by vāmya-bhāva, the mood predominant in Vṛndāvan amongst Śrīmatī Rādhārāṇī and Her entourage (as well as their expansions in Dvārakā—Satyabhāmā and her attendants)."},{"class":"b59","text":" jagadānanda-paṇḍitera śuddha gāḍha bhāva<br />satyabhāmā-prāya prema “vāmya-svabhāva”<br />bāra bāra praṇaya kalaha kare prabhu-sane<br />anyo ’nye khaṭmaṭi chale dui-jane"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Śrī Chaitanya-charitāmṛta: Antya-līlā, 7.138–9)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “Jagadānanda Paṇḍit has deep, pure devotion, and, like Satyabhāmā, his love is ‘leftist’. Again and again, he lovingly quarrels with the Lord. There are always disagreements between them.”"},{"class":"b59","text":" prītye karite chāhe prabhura lālana-pālana<br />vairāgya-loka-bhaye prabhu nā māne kakhana<br />dui-jane khaṭmaṭi lāgāya kondala"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Śrī Chaitanya-charitāmṛta: Ādi-līlā, 10.22–3)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “Out of love, Jagadānanda desires to comfort the Lord, but because the Lord is a renunciant and thus concerned about public opinion, He never accepts this. Thus, they disagree and quarrel.”"},{"class":"b59","text":" jagadānande-prabhute prema chale ei-mate<br />satyabhāmā-kṛṣṇe yaichhe śuni bhāgavate<br />jagadānandera saubhāgyera ke kahibe sīmā?<br />jagadānandera saubhāgyera te̐ha se upamā"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Śrī Chaitanya-charitāmṛta: Antya-līlā, 12.152–3)"},{"class":"b43","text":" “Divine love flowed between Jagadānanda and the Lord as we hear in <span class=\\"e3\\">Śrīmad Bhāgavatam </span>that it did between Satyabhāmā and Kṛṣṇa. Who can describe the extent of Jagadānanda’s fortune? He is the only comparison that there is for his fortune (his fortune is incomparable).”"},{"class":"b51","text":" Jagadānanda Paṇḍit not only had profoundly intimate Pastimes with the Lord, he also had the deepest form of association with the Lord’s devotees—he would relieve them of their sorrow in separation from the Lord."},{"class":"b59","text":" prati-vatsara prabhu tā̐re pāṭhāna nadīyāte<br />vichchheda-duḥkhitā jāni’ jananī āśvāsite<br />nadīyāra bhakta-gaṇe sabāre mililā<br />jagadānande pāñā sabe ānandita hailā<br />chaitanyera marma-kathā śune tā̐ra mukhe<br />āpanā pāsare sabe chaitanya-kathā-sukhe<br />jagadānanda milite yāya yei bhakta-ghare<br />sei sei bhakta sukhe āpanā pāsare"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Śrī Chaitanya-charitāmṛta: Antya-līlā, 12.5, 96, 99–100)"},{"class":"b43","text":" “Knowing His mother to be sorrowful in separation, the Lord sent Jagadānanda Paṇḍit to Nadia every year to console her. Jagadānanda would also meet with all the other devotees in Nadia, and they would all be overjoyed to meet him. They would hear confidential discussion of Śrī Chaitanya from his mouth and forget themselves in the joy of the discussions. In every home Jagadānanda visited, the devotees forgot themselves out of joy.”"},{"class":"b51","text":" Jagadānanda Paṇḍit is thus most dear to the Lord and all His devotees. May his service and teachings be worshipped eternally."},{"class":"b59","text":" chaitanyera prema-pātra jagadānanda dhanya<br />yāre mile sei māne, “pāilu̐ chaitanya”"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Śrī Chaitanya-charitāmṛta: Antya-līlā, 12.101)"},{"class":"b71","text":" “All glory to Jagadānanda, the carrier of Śrī Chaitanya’s love! Whoever meets him feels, ‘I have met Śrī Chaitanya!’”"},{"class":"b70","text":" The composition"},{"class":"b50","text":" Śrīla Jagadānanda Paṇḍit explains in <span class=\\"e3\\">Prema-vivarta</span> how he came to compose this book:"},{"class":"b88","text":" “I prostrate myself at the feet of my beloved Gaura and write this <span class=\\"e3\\">Prema-vivarta</span>, having received the order of the devotees.” (Pv: 3.7)"},{"class":"b88","text":" “I write whatever comes to my mind about Gaurāṅga’s Pastimes, whenever it does, even if it is out of sequence.” (Pv: 15.1)"},{"class":"b89","text":" “Svarūp Dāmodar asked me, ‘O Paṇḍit, what are you writing?’ I replied, ‘I am writing about whom I love.’ (Pv: 2.4)"},{"class":"b89","text":" “Svarūp Dāmodar said, ‘Then write about the Pastimes of the Lord that the world will be greatly benefitted by reading about.’ (Pv: 2.6)"},{"class":"b174","text":" “I replied, ‘I don’t know what is beneficial for the world. I simply write whatever I like.’ Svarūp left, considering me mad. Sitting alone, I write, meditating on the Lord. My mind cries, my heart cries, my eyes cry, and whenever something comes to mind, I write it down.” (Pv: 2.7, 8, 10)"},{"class":"b70","text":" The name"},{"class":"b50","text":" In <span class=\\"e3\\">Śrī Chaitanya-charitāmṛta</span>, Śrīla Kṛṣṇadās Kavirāj Goswāmī writes,"},{"class":"b59","text":" jagadānandera ‘prema-vivarta’ śune yei jana<br />premera ‘svarūpa’ jāne, pāya prema-dhana"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Śrī Chaitanya-charitāmṛta: Antya-līlā, 12.154)"},{"class":"b43","text":" “Anyone who hears of Jagadānanda Paṇḍit’s <span class=\\"e3\\">prema-vivarta</span> understands the nature of divine love and attains its wealth.”"},{"class":"b44","text":" In his commentary on <span class=\\"e3\\">Śrī Chaitanya-charitāmṛta</span>, Śrīla Bhakti Vinod Ṭhākur explains the meaning of ‘<span class=\\"e3\\">prema-vivarta</span>’: “One meaning intended is (Jagadānanda Paṇḍit’s) transformations of love (<span class=\\"e3\\">premera vivarta</span>)—his indignant behaviour during loving affairs. A second meaning is the book entitled ‘<span class=\\"e3\\">Prema-vivarta</span>’ written by Jagadānanda Paṇḍit himself about Śrīman Mahāprabhu.”"},{"class":"b51","text":" Throughout <span class=\\"e3\\">Prema-vivarta</span>, Śrīla Jagadānanda Paṇḍit describes the reveries, emotions, and ecstasies he experiences:"},{"class":"b88","text":" “The pangs and transformations of love constantly dance within my mind. I quarrel with Gaura every day, and thus I am known as ‘Angry Jagāi’.” (Pv: 5.1)"},{"class":"b89","text":" “I cannot tolerate a moment of separation as Gaura dances in my heart. He does not let me die, but when I live, we quarrel. How does my life go on?” (Pv: 13.10)"},{"class":"b89","text":" “Transformations of love make me dance, but, not understanding them, I am dying.” (Pv: 13.4)"},{"class":"b174","text":" “Those who have love for Gorā undergo distress: that love pulls their hearts in opposite directions simultaneously.” (Pv: 13.13)"},{"class":"b70","text":" The substance"},{"class":"b43","text":" Śrīla Jagadānanda Paṇḍit’s only known writing, <span class=\\"e3\\">Śrī Śrī Prema-vivarta</span>, is immensely valuable to the followers of Śrīman Mahāprabhu. Śrīla Jagadānanda Paṇḍit describes his Pastimes with the Lord in a sweet, loving manner as though he is reminiscing with an intimate friend, adding details that deepen the meaning of many of the Pastimes recorded in <span class=\\"e3\\">Śrī Chaitanya-charitāmṛta, </span>such as his travelling to Vṛndāvan, his conversations with Śrīla Sanātan Goswāmī, and his quarrel with the Lord over a pot of sandalwood oil. He also recounts Pastimes of the Lord that are not recorded anywhere else, such as his quarrelling with the Lord as a schoolboy (Pv: 2.18) and the Lord showing affection to the cowherd boys of Nadia by liberating a croco­dile (Pv: 12.15). Weaved throughout these narrations are profound expressions of union in separation that reveal the mood and ideal with which the Lord’s intimate associates serve Him."},{"class":"b51","text":" Throughout <span class=\\"e3\\">Śrī Śrī Prema-vivarta</span>, prominent teachings of the Gauḍīya–Vaiṣṇavas as given in <span class=\\"e3\\">Śrī Chaitanya-charitāmṛta</span> are highlighted:"},{"class":"b50","text":" Śrī Gaurasundar is Śrī Rādhā and Śrī Kṛṣṇa combined (Cc: Ādi, 1.5):"},{"class":"b67","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">“</span>The Absolute is sometimes two, as Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa, and sometimes one, as Śrī Chaitanya, the Supreme Being.” (Pv: 1.2)"},{"class":"b43","text":" Svayam Bhagavān Śrī Kṛṣṇa appeared as Śrī Gaurasundar to explore the mystery of Śrī Rādhā’s love for Him (Cc: Ādi, 1.6):"},{"class":"b67","text":" [The Lord decided:] “I will take Rādhā’s heart and halo, become Gaura, and relish Kṛṣṇa’s sweetness in the mood of a devotee.” (Pv: 11.10)"},{"class":"b43","text":" Śrī Gaurasundar’s Pastimes are superior to all other līlās and forms of the Lord (Cc: Madhya, 25.264):"},{"class":"b67","text":" “Golden Kṛṣṇa appeared to fulfil His desires, and feels more joy in Nabadwīp Dhām than He does in Vraja.” (Pv: 1.39)"},{"class":"b43","text":" Rādhā-dāsyam is the essence of Śrī Gaurasundar’s ideal and gift (Cc: Madhya, 8.97):"},{"class":"b67","text":" [Jagadānanda Paṇḍit:] “I am a maidservant of Rādhā’s feet, and I love the form of the Lord that is adorned with Her halo (Śrī Gaurāṅga).” (Pv: 1.53)"},{"class":"b43","text":" The Lord appeared both as Śrī Gaurāṅga and as His Name to deliver the souls of Kali-yuga (Cc: Ādi, 1.4, 17.22):"},{"class":"b67","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">“</span>Being merciful to the conditioned souls, Kṛṣṇa appeared as His Name, and being compassionate to the souls of Kali-yuga, He appeared as Gaura.” (Pv: 7.17)"},{"class":"b43","text":" Śrī Hari-nām-saṅkīrtan is the dharma of the modern age (Cc: Ādi, 7.74):"},{"class":"b67","text":" “O devotees, hear about the dharma in the Age of Kali: there is no duty other than chanting the Name of Śrī Kṛṣṇa.” (Pv: 19.3)"},{"class":"b43","text":" True devotees of the Name always avoid the association of non-devotees and those attached to the pleasures of the world (Cc: Madhya, 22.84):"},{"class":"b67","text":" “Brother, the Name of Kṛṣṇa never appears in bad association: the letters of the Name may appear, but the Name never does.” (Pv: 7.1)"},{"class":"b43","text":" The Name must be chanted without offence (Cc: Ādi, 8.24):"},{"class":"b67","text":" “Only by very carefully avoiding the offences to the Name does the soul attain all perfection and reach the Lord. Those who understand the offences but are unconcerned about avoiding them are foolish and suffer forever.” (Pv: 19.115, 124)"},{"class":"b43","text":" Surrender is the essence of avoiding offences, chanting the Name, and the practice of devotion itself (Cc: Madhya, 22.33, 99):"},{"class":"b67","text":" “When you sincerely take shelter of the Lord, all your offences are destroyed, you never again have any taste for sin and suffering, your piety and sins disappear, and you conquer the illusory environment.” (Pv: 19.108–9)"},{"class":"b43","text":" Only detachment produced by devotion is natural (Cc: Madhya, 16.238–9):"},{"class":"b67","text":" “Service to Kṛṣṇa and the sādhus is relishable to the soul. By simply opposing material nature, you end up completely disheartened.” (Pv: 9.7)"},{"class":"b43","text":" The soul, a part and parcel of Kṛṣṇa’s energy, is Kṛṣṇa’s eternal servant and naturally serves Him under the spell of His all-attractive nature (Cc: Madhya, 20.108–9, 21.102):"},{"class":"b67","text":" “The soul is a spiritual spark, and Kṛṣṇa is the spiritual sun. Seeing eternal Kṛṣṇa, the soul adores Him.” (Pv: 6.1)"},{"class":"b43","text":" The only qualification for devotion is faith (Cc: Madhya, 22.64):"},{"class":"b67","text":" “Every human being—if they have faith—is qualified to chant the Name. The arguments and brashness of speculators about caste and class do not count for anything.” (Pv: 10.1)"},{"class":"b43","text":" Having desires contrary to the Lord’s will is the one and only cause of the soul’s fall, illusion, and suffering (Cc: Madhya, 20.117):"},{"class":"b67","text":" “When the soul becomes averse to Kṛṣṇa and desires enjoyment, nearby Māyā seizes them.<span class=\\"e2\\"> </span>Forgetting, ‘I am an eternal servant of Kṛṣṇa’, the soul becomes a slave of Māyā and wanders indefinitely (suffering the consequences of their actions in the material world).” (Pv: 6.2, 4)"},{"class":"b43","text":" Sādhu-saṅga is the fundamental basis of deliverance and devotion (Cc: Madhya, 22.45, 80):"},{"class":"b67","text":" “When the souls’ wandering throughout saṁsāra comes to an end, then, according to their fortune, they attain the association of the sādhus. Brother, as a result of association with the sādhus, devotion to Kṛṣṇa, the Lord of all Lords, appears within their hearts.” (Pv: 12.3–4)"},{"class":"b43","text":" The combination of service to the devotees and service to the Name is the essence of the practice given by Śrī Gaurasundar (Cc: Madhya, 22.124):"},{"class":"b67","text":" “I want only to chant the Name of Kṛṣṇa in the association of the sādhus—there is no other way to conquer saṁsāra.” (Pv: 6.13)"},{"class":"b43","text":" Serving Vaiṣṇavas is real service to the Lord (Cc: Madhya, 16.70):"},{"class":"b67","text":" “Serve Gaura’s devotees with perfect sincerity, and then, brother, you will reach Śrī Kṛṣṇa’s feet.” (Pv: 7.18)"},{"class":"b43","text":" Divine love is the supreme goal of devotional practice (Cc: Madhya, 19.164):"},{"class":"b67","text":" “Be free from offences and chant the Name of Kṛṣṇa. Then divine love will come with the Name and reside within your heart.” (Pv: 19.156)"},{"class":"b43","text":" Divine love captivates the Lord Himself (Cc: Madhya, 8.88):"},{"class":"b67","text":" “The Lord never leaves the sincere hearts of those who have bound His lotus feet with the rope of divine love.” (Pv: 12.25)"},{"class":"b43","text":" Divine love is the supreme fulfilment (Cc: Madhya, 2.49):"},{"class":"b67","text":" “Love for Kṛṣṇa is perfectly pure, like the pure water of the Ganges; it is an ocean of nectar. Within such pure love, there is not even a trace of mundanity. It is like a white cloth free from even one spot of ink. Pure love is an ocean of joy. I have received one drop of it, and this drop floods the world.” (Pv: 16.15–6)"},{"class":"b71","text":" <span class=\\"e3\\">Śrī Śrī Prema-vivarta</span> thus serves as a comprehensive companion to <span class=\\"e3\\">Śrī Chaitanya-charitāmṛta</span>. In a text less than one-tenth of <span class=\\"e3\\">Śrī Chaitanya-charitāmṛta’s </span>length, Śrīla Jagadānanda Paṇḍit has presented the gist of Gauḍīya–Vaiṣṇava theology—sambandha, abhidheya, and prayojan—in clear-cut, energetic summaries composed in sweet vernacular rhyme. Those whose hearts are thrilled to hear the essential principles of sincerity, surrender, and devotion propounded with emphatic conviction are nourished in full by <span class=\\"e3\\">Śrī Śrī Prema-vivarta.</span> Bearing in mind that our Guru-varga reveres <span class=\\"e3\\">Śrī Chaitanya-charitāmṛta</span> as the most revolutionary theological literature to have ever seen the light of day, when we read and reflect on <span class=\\"e3\\">Śrī Śrī Prema-vivarta</span>, which presents <span class=\\"e3\\">Śrī Chaitanya-charitāmṛta’s</span> wealth in a condensed and vibrant form, we can only marvel at the profundity of this simple gift. What will we not attain by taking its substance to heart?"},{"class":"b70","text":" Prayer"},{"class":"b50","text":" Holding on our heads the ideal of unconditional devotion to Śrī Gurudev, the Vaiṣṇavas, Śrī Gaurasundar, and the Lord’s eternal associates, we invoke the blessings of Śrīla Jagadānanda Paṇḍit and pray that the words of Śrīla Kṛṣṇadās Kavirāj Goswāmī may soon shine true in the hearts of all the readers:"},{"class":"b60","text":" jagadānandera ‘prema-vivarta’ śune yei jana<br />premera ‘svarūpa’ jāne, pāya prema-dhana"},{"class":"b55","text":" “Anyone who hears Jagadānanda’s <span class=\\"e3\\">Prema-vivarta</span> understands the nature of divine love and attains its wealth.”"}]},{"title":"In Praise of Śrī Śrī Prema-vivarta","paragraphs":[{"class":"b46","text":"\\r"},{"class":"b47","text":" In Praise of <span class=\\"e31\\">Śrī Śrī Prema-vivarta</span>"},{"class":"b42","text":" Compiled from the talks of"},{"class":"b73","text":" Śrīla Bhakti Rakṣak Śrīdhar Dev-Goswāmī Mahārāj"},{"class":"b50","text":" Śrīla Jagadānanda Paṇḍit collected his notes on Śrīman Mahāprabhu’s Pastimes and teachings, and presented them in the form of a book named <span class=\\"e3\\">Prema-vivarta</span>. This book was published by Śrīla Bhakti Vinod Ṭhākur and is full of Gauḍīya siddhānta."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Student:</span> Some people say <span class=\\"e3\\">Prema-vivarta</span> was written by Śrīla Bhakti Vinod Ṭhākur, not Jagadānanda Paṇḍit."},{"class":"b43","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Śrīla Śrīdhar Mahārāj:</span> If we can understand that <span class=\\"e3\\">Śrīmad Bhāgavatam</span> is the highest development of theism and the teachings of Śrī Chaitanyadev are the highest, full-fledged form of that theism, then anything that correlates with them has value and cannot but be true. Some claim that <span class=\\"e3\\">Śrī Brahma-saṁhitā</span> was written by Śrī Chaitanyadev. Śrīla Jīva Goswāmī has shown that there really was a <span class=\\"e3\\">Brahma-saṁhitā</span> with one hundred chapters and that the <span class=\\"e3\\">Brahma-saṁhitā</span> given by Śrī Chaitanyadev is one chapter from that book. Śrīla Bhakti Vinod Ṭhākur, however, also wrote, “We do not find any book by Śrī Chaitanyadev Himself anywhere. If <span class=\\"e3\\">Brahma-saṁhitā</span> comes from Him, then we are very proud and satisfied that He has left us at least one book.” We may see <span class=\\"e3\\">Prema-vivarta</span> in this way."},{"class":"b51","text":" There are many things mentioned in <span class=\\"e3\\">Prema-vivarta</span> that greatly help the Gauḍīya Maṭh’s propaganda. A particular opposition camp of the Gauḍīya Maṭh says that Śrīla Bhakti Vinod Ṭhākur has written <span class=\\"e3\\">Prema-vivarta</span> in the name of Jagadānanda Paṇḍit because the book supports the Gauḍīya Maṭh’s position very well. For example, a section of sahajiyās say that there is no Ekādaśī in Purī. They say that when Mahāprabhu lived in Purī, He did not follow Ekādaśī because in <span class=\\"e3\\">Śrī Chaitanya-charitāmṛta</span> He is always found to be taking mahāprasād. They say that in Purī even on Ekādaśī we should not fast because there is always mahāprasād present, and there mahāprasād cannot be refused. It is, however, clearly stated in Jagadānanda Paṇḍit’s <span class=\\"e3\\">Prema-vivarta</span> that when Mahāprabhu was offered mahāprasād on Ekādaśī, He touched it to His head, kept it respectfully nearby, performed kīrtan the whole day and night, and then took the prasād the next morning. Many similar points that are very helpful for the preaching of the Gauḍīya Maṭh are found in <span class=\\"e3\\">Prema-vivarta</span>."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Student:</span> Was Jagadānanda Paṇḍit in the mood of Satyabhāmā or was he an incarnation of Satyabhāmā?"},{"class":"b43","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Śrīla Śrīdhar Mahārāj:</span> He was an incarnation of Satyabhāmā. Satyabhāmā’s mood is known as vāmya-bhāva, opposition. She is very sentimental. She apparently opposes the Lord and behaves insistently. Ostentatiously, she opposes the Lord, but from the heart she has no opposition to Him, only loving emotions. Jagadānanda Paṇḍit sometimes played with the Lord in a way that might seem sinful. He was full of sentiments, but he has the highest qualification of having the greatest attraction to Mahāprabhu."},{"class":"b51","text":" Once, Jagadānanda Paṇḍit asked Mahāprabhu for permission to go to Vṛndāvan. Mahāprabhu granted him permission but gave him instructions to follow while he was there."},{"class":"b59","text":" mathurā gele sanātana-saṅgei rahibā<br />mathurāra svāmī sabera charaṇa vandibā<br />dūre rahi’ bhakti kariha saṅge nā rahibā<br />tā̐-sabāra āchāra-cheṣṭā la-ite nāribā<br />sanātana-saṅge kariha vana daraśana<br />sanātanera saṅga nā chhāḍibā eka-kṣaṇa<br />śīghra āsiha, tāhā̐ nā rahiha chira-kāla<br />govardhane nā chaḍiha dekhite ‘gopāla’"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Śrī Chaitanya-charitāmṛta: Antya-līlā, 13.36–39)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “You may go to Vṛndāvan, but do not remain there for a long time and do not climb on top of Govardhan to see Mādhavendra Purī’s Gopāl. Offer respect to the Vraja-vāsīs, but do not imitate their practices. And as long as you are there, stay under the guidance of Sanātan.”"},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Student:</span> Why did the Lord tell Jagadānanda Paṇḍit not to come too close to the Vraja-vāsīs?"},{"class":"b43","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Śrīla Śrīdhar Mahārāj:</span> Although the Lord was advising Jagadānanda, these instructions are really for us. They are to warn us that the Vraja-vāsīs may not be scrupulous about following physical practices, and that we should not imitate their external behaviour. Also, in Vraja at that time, everyone was not a follower of Chaitanyadev. They were followers of Nimbārka Āchārya, Viṣṇu Swāmī, and others. Furthermore, it was a period of Mohammedan rule. Under those circumstances, Mahāprabhu did not want Jagadānanda’s sentiments to be publicly exposed in Vraja Maṇḍal. Sanātan Goswāmī was the most sober and respected follower of Mahāprabhu there, and he could deal with things in the locality well. Jagadānanda was very intolerant of anyone who did not follow Mahāprabhu. He had many eccentricities, and he could create havoc. Mahāprabhu thought, “He quarrels even with Me here. He won’t care for anyone there. For his own interest, he may create quarrel there. So, he should always be under the guidance of Sanātan. Sanātan is a sober man and knows how to deal with the people in that place. He is My trusted leader there. Jagadānanda must remain under his guidance and should not mix closely with the Vraja-vāsīs. Because of his intolerance, he may quarrel with them.” Mahāprabhu knew Jagadānanda was very sentimental, and He did not want that Jagadānanda would go there and freely display intense sentiments for Him. Still, Jagadānanda did so."},{"class":"b44","text":" One day, while Jagadānanda Paṇḍit was cooking, Sanātan Goswāmī came to visit him just as he was placing a cooking pot on the oven. Sanātan Goswāmī was wearing a turban made of red cloth. Jagadānanda Prabhu was delighted to see the red cloth and said, “That must be Mahāprabhu’s cloth! Did He give it to you?”"},{"class":"b44","text":" Sanātan Goswāmī replied, “No, no. I received this cloth from another sannyāsī, Mukunda Saraswatī, who stays in this area.”"},{"class":"b44","text":" Jagadānanda said, “Oh! Is it? You are the leading follower of Mahāprabhu but you wear on your head the cloth of another sannyāsī!”"},{"class":"b44","text":" Jagadānanda rushed toward Sanātan to strike Sanātan with the cooking pot in his hand. “Who can tolerate this?” he exclaimed."},{"class":"b44","text":" “Yes, Paṇḍitjī!” Sanātan Goswāmī joined his palms, “I have now found the jewel I have been searching for. I wanted to see your exclusive love for Mahāprabhu, and today, by Mahāprabhu’s grace, I have seen it. I wore this turban only with the hope that I would see your exclusive devotion to Mahāprabhu and the extreme intolerance produced by your love. Seeing the intensity of your love for Mahāprabhu, my life is fulfilled. I am very fortunate.”"},{"class":"b44","text":" Jagadānanda was nonplussed by Sanātan’s words and felt that his excitement was quite abrupt and awkward. He felt shy and fell silent. Then he said, “No, no, no. I am mistaken. But who can tolerate this? You are one of the main followers of Mahāprabhu, but you have such respect for another sannyāsī, a māyāvādī, that you wear his cloth on your head as a turban? I cannot tolerate this, but please forgive me for coming to strike you.”"},{"class":"b44","text":" On another occasion, when Sanātan Goswāmī came to Purī, he asked for Jagadānanda’s advice as to whether he should remain there with Mahāprabhu or return to Vṛndāvan. Jagadānanda advised him to return to Vṛndāvan, and later Śrīman Mahāprabhu heard that Jagadānanda had given this advice to Sanātan Goswāmī, who was his senior. Mahāprabhu chastised Jagadānanda and then praised Sanātan Goswāmī, but Sanātan Goswāmī replied to Mahāprabhu, “Oh! This is my misfortune. You are feeding me so much bitterness coated with praise. Jagadānanda’s fortune is higher. You blame him and punish him with ill words—that means that You think of him as Your own, but You keep me at a respectful distance. This shows his good fortune and my bad fortune. It is my bad fate that You praise me and keep me at a respectful distance. That You punish Jagadānanda shows that You favour him, and that he is Your own. You are actually treating him most affectionately.”"},{"class":"b44","text":" Through Sanātan’s glorification, we can understand the exalted position of Jagadānanda Paṇḍit and his intimate relationship with Mahāprabhu."},{"class":"b44","text":" In another instance, Jagadānanda Paṇḍit carried a large clay pot full of sandalwood oil from Bengal to Purī, a distance of more than three hundred miles. He came to Govinda, Mahāprabhu’s personal servant, and modestly offered it: “With great trouble, I have carried this pot full of sandalwood oil here for Mahāprabhu. May the Lord graciously accept it. Please keep it here. You can massage Mahāprabhu’s head with this oil; it has a cooling effect. Sometimes the Lord cannot sleep, and sometimes He speaks deliriously. This oil will help Him greatly at those times. I have taken the oil from Śivānanda Sen, and it is pure. Please keep it here and use it for the Lord.”"},{"class":"b44","text":" Mahāprabhu overheard Jagadānanda saying this to Govinda. “What is this?” He asked."},{"class":"b44","text":" “Jagadānanda Paṇḍit has brought a full pot of sandalwood oil for You, and his request is that You smear it on Your head now and then so that You will sleep soundly and remain in good health”, said Govinda."},{"class":"b44","text":" “No, no, no. Sandalwood oil is very fragrant. What will people say about Me? I am a sannyāsī. If I smear this oil on My head and go to see Jagannāth, the public will smell it and say, ‘Such luxury for a sannyāsī? Does He also keep a woman with Him?’ I cannot use this oil at all. I will get a bad name.”"},{"class":"b44","text":" Mahāprabhu turned to Jagadānanda, “Would that please you? I advise you to take the oil to the Temple of Jagannāth. There it can be burned in the lamps, and Jagannāth will enjoy its scent. In that way, your labour of carrying the oil here will be successful. You will be greatly benefitted by offering the oil in that way.”"},{"class":"b44","text":" “Remove the oil from My room”, Mahāprabhu said to Govinda."},{"class":"b44","text":" Hearing this, Jagadānanda took the pot of oil from Govinda, came in front of Mahāprabhu, and smashed it on the floor. The oil spilled everywhere, and Jagadānanda ran straight to his room. He locked the door from the inside and did not come out for three days. When Mahāprabhu heard that Jagadānanda had been fasting for three days, He could not contain Himself, and He personally went to Jagadānanda’s door. “O Jagadānanda! What is the matter? Arise and open the door. Today, I shall take prasādam prepared by your hands. I will not take prasādam from anyone else. I am going now, and at noon time I will return to take lunch here, prepared by you.”"},{"class":"b44","text":" Jagadānanda thought, “Oh! Mahāprabhu will accept my cooking today!” He got out of bed and began to cook. Mahāprabhu came with Govinda to take prasādam, and He remarked, “Oh! All the dishes are very, very sweet today. Perhaps your cooking with a hot temper has made them extra sweet.”"},{"class":"b44","text":" After eating, Mahāprabhu stood and said, “Now you eat. Before I leave, I want to see you eat.”"},{"class":"b44","text":" Jagadānanda replied, “Oh no, no, no. My Lord, You go and take rest. I shall take later. Certainly I will eat.”"},{"class":"b44","text":" Mahāprabhu said, “Govinda, you remain here. Once Jagadānanda has eaten, come and inform Me.” Finally, Jagadānanda took prasādam."},{"class":"b44","text":" Jagadānanda Paṇḍit has a very sentimental character like that of Satyabhāmā. He cannot give up his tendency of being reactionary towards Mahāprabhu. He is abhimānyu, very sensitive about subtle things, and known for his prema-vivarta, the peculiar charac­teristics of the reactions produced by his divine love. They are of a peculiar type and are described in the science of divine love. Like Satyabhāmā, he has vāmya-bhāva, which is the nature of the highest class of heroines (nāyikās). They instantly refuse whatever is offered to them by their lover (nāyaka). In the science of love, we are told that this nature is the most valuable: it increases the lover’s earnestness."},{"class":"b44","text":" Rādhārāṇī’s nature is also of that type: always in opposition (nirantara vāmya). This spirit of opposition is a peculiar thing, and the experts in rasa say that it is the highest mood because it enhances the intensity of the other side. This mood is found in Jagadānanda and Satyabhāmā."},{"class":"b51","text":" After Kṛṣṇa went to Mathurā, His Vṛndāvan-līlā continued underground, that is, outside of ordinary vision. During that time, parts (aṁśas) of the gopīs went to Dvārakā. Satyabhāmā appeared from a portion of Rādhārāṇī’s lustre and Rukmiṇī from Chandrāvalī’s. Chandrāvalī is more judicious, Rādhārāṇī more sentimental. Senti­ment has the upper hand in Vṛndāvan: it is above judiciousness in matters of love. In Dvārakā, however, judiciousness gets the upper hand, and sentimentalism goes into the lower position. So, Satyabhāmā—Rādhārāṇī’s connection, or shadow—is considered of lower value there, and the judiciousness and cleverness of Chandrāvalī—Rukmiṇī—comes into the first rank. The mood that has its highest glory in Vṛndāvan cannot play fully in Dvārakā. It goes into a secondary position there. These are the peculiarities in the līlā."},{"class":"b59","text":" yathā yathā gaura-padāravinde<br />vindeta bhaktiṁ kṛta-puṇya-rāśiḥ<br />tathā tathotsarpati hṛdy akasmād<br />rādhā-padāmbhoja-sudhāmburāśiḥ"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Śrī Chaitanya-chandrāmṛta: 88)"},{"class":"b55","text":" As much as one engages in the service of Gaura-līlā, automatically one finds oneself within the inner development of the service of Śrī Rādhikā in Vraja-līlā. One’s service begins here and reaches there. Automatically, spontaneously, one will be led there to the service of the highest value and quality. So, begin properly with Gaura-līlā, begin with Nityānanda and Gaura-Gadādhar, and then find yourself in the midst of Vṛndāvan-lilā. Unknowingly, you will find, “I have attained a good position in Vṛndāvan-līlā.”"}]},{"title":"শ্রীশ্রীপ্রেমবিবর্ত্ত","paragraphs":[{"class":"b46","text":"\\r"},{"class":"b115","text":" শ্রীশ্রীপ্রেমবিবর্ত্ত"},{"class":"b36","text":" Śrī Śrī Prema-vivarta"}]},{"title":"Invocation of Auspiciousness","paragraphs":[{"class":"b46","text":"\\r"},{"class":"b58","text":" Chapter One"},{"class":"b120","text":" মঙ্গলাচরণ"},{"class":"b121","text":" Maṅgalācharaṇa"},{"class":"b175","text":" Invocation of Auspiciousness"},{"class":"b97","text":" রাধাকৃষ্ণপ্রণয়বিকৃতির্হ্লাদিনী শক্তিরস্মাদ্<br />একাত্মানাবপি ভুবি পুরা দেহভেদং গতৌ তৌ<br />চৈতন্যাখ্যং প্রকটমধুনা তদ্দ্বয়ং চৈক্যমাপ্তং<br />রাধাভাবদ্যুতিসুবলিতং নৌমি কৃষ্ণস্বরূপম্"},{"class":"b53","text":" rādhā-kṛṣṇa-praṇaya-vikṛtir hlādinī-śaktir asmād<br />ekātmānāv api bhuvi purā deha-bhedaṁ gatau tau<br />chaitanyākhyaṁ prakaṭam adhunā tad-dvayaṁ chaikyam āptaṁ<br />rādhā-bhāva-dyuti-suvalitaṁ naumi kṛṣṇa-svarūpam"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Śrī Chaitanya-charitāmṛta: Ādi-līlā, 1.5)"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">api</span>–Although <span class=\\"e2\\">tau</span>–They [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">eka-ātmānau</span>–by nature one, <span class=\\"e2\\">asmāt</span>–through <span class=\\"e2\\">hlādinī-śaktiḥ</span>–the pleasure potency, <span class=\\"e2\\">rādhā-kṛṣṇa-praṇaya-vikṛtiḥ</span>–a transformation of Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa’s love, [They] <span class=\\"e2\\">purā</span>–eternally <span class=\\"e2\\">gatau</span>–possess <span class=\\"e2\\">deha-bhedam</span>–separate bodies <span class=\\"e2\\">bhuvi</span>–within the world. <span class=\\"e2\\">adhunā</span>–Now, <span class=\\"e2\\">tad-dvayam</span>–these two <span class=\\"e2\\">āptam</span>–have become <span class=\\"e2\\">prakaṭam</span>–manifest <span class=\\"e2\\">aikyam</span>–as one <span class=\\"e2\\">cha</span>–and [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">ākhyam</span>–known as <span class=\\"e2\\">chaitanya</span>–‘Chaitanya’. <span class=\\"e2\\">naumi</span>–I bow <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-svarūpam</span>–to Kṛṣṇa’s form <span class=\\"e2\\">suvalitam</span>–adorned with <span class=\\"e2\\">rādhā-bhāva-dyuti</span>–the heart and halo of Śrī Rādhā."},{"class":"b71","text":" Although Śrī Rādhā and Śrī Kṛṣṇa are by nature one, through the hlādinī-śakti, a transformation of Their love, They exist eternally in separate forms. Now, They have manifested in one combined form as Śrī Chaitanya. I bow to Him, Kṛṣṇa Himself adorned with the heart and halo of Śrī Rādhā."},{"class":"b176","text":" শ্রীরাধাকৃষ্ণতত্ত্ব"},{"class":"b177","text":" śrī-rādhā-kṛṣṇa-tattva"},{"class":"b70","text":" The nature of Śrī Rādhā and Śrī Kṛṣṇa"},{"class":"b97","text":" অখণ্ড-অদ্বয়-জ্ঞান সর্ব্বতত্ত্বসার ।<br />সেই তত্ত্বে দণ্ড-পরণাম বার বার ॥১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" akhaṇḍa-advaya-jñāna sarva-tattva-sāra<br />sei tattve daṇḍa-paraṇāma bāra bāra [1]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">daṇḍa-paraṇāma</span>–I bow <span class=\\"e2\\">bāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bāra</span>–again and again <span class=\\"e2\\">sei khaṇḍa-advaya-jñāna tattve</span>–to the indivisible, nondual Absolute, <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-tattva-sāra</span>–the essence of all truths."},{"class":"b50","text":" I bow again and again to the indivisible, nondual Absolute, the essence of all truths."},{"class":"b97","text":" সেই তত্ত্ব কভু দুই রাধাকৃষ্ণরূপে ।<br />কভু এক পরাৎপর চৈতন্যস্বরূপে ॥২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sei tattva kabhu dui rādhā-kṛṣṇa-rūpe<br />kabhu eka parātpara chaitanya-svarūpe [2]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">tattva</span>–The Absolute [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu</span>–sometimes <span class=\\"e2\\">dui</span>–two <span class=\\"e2\\">rādhā-kṛṣṇa-rūpe</span>–as Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu</span>–sometimes <span class=\\"e2\\">eka</span>–one <span class=\\"e2\\">chaitanya-svarūpe</span>–as Śrī Chaitanya, <span class=\\"e2\\">parātpara</span>–the Supreme Being."},{"class":"b50","text":" The Absolute is sometimes two, as Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa, and sometimes one, as Śrī Chaitanya, the Supreme Being."},{"class":"b97","text":" তত্ত্ব-বস্তু এক সদা অদ্বিতীয় ভায় ।<br />বস্তু বস্তুশক্তি মাঝে কিছু ভেদ নাই ॥৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" tattva-vastu eka sadā advitīya bhāya<br />vastu vastu-śakti mājhe kichhu bheda nāi [3]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">tattva-vastu</span>–The Absolute [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">sadā</span>–eternally <span class=\\"e2\\">eka</span>–one <span class=\\"e2\\">advitīya bhāya</span>–without a second, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">kichhu</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāi</span>–there is no <span class=\\"e2\\">bheda</span>–difference <span class=\\"e2\\">mājhe</span>–between <span class=\\"e2\\">vastu</span>–the Absolute [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">vastu-śakti</span>–the Absolute’s energy."},{"class":"b50","text":" The Absolute is eternally one without a second, and there is no difference between the Absolute and the Absolute’s energy."},{"class":"b97","text":" ভেদ নাই বটে, কিন্তু সদা ভেদ তায় ।<br />“ভেদাভেদ অবিচিন্ত্য” সর্ব্ব-বেদে গায় ॥৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" bheda nāi vaṭe, kintu sadā bheda tāya<br />“bhedābheda avichintya” sarva-vede gāya [4]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">vaṭe</span>–Truly, <span class=\\"e2\\">nāi</span>–there is no <span class=\\"e2\\">bheda</span>–difference [between them], <span class=\\"e2\\">kintu</span>–yet [there is] <span class=\\"e2\\">sadā</span>–always <span class=\\"e2\\">bheda</span>–a difference <span class=\\"e2\\">tāya</span>–between them. <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-vede</span>–All the Vedas <span class=\\"e2\\">gāya</span>–glorify <span class=\\"e2\\">“bhedābheda</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">avichintya”</span>–this “inconceivable difference and nondifference”."},{"class":"b50","text":" Truly, there is no difference between them, yet there is always a difference between them. All the Vedas glorify this “inconceivable difference and nondifference”."},{"class":"b97","text":" বস্তুশক্তি চিৎ-স্বরূপ ভাবেতে সন্ধিনী ।<br />ক্রিয়াতে হ্লাদিনী তাই ত্রিভাবধারিণী ॥৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" vastu-śakti chit-svarūpa bhāvete sandhinī<br />kriyāte hlādinī tāi tribhāva-dhāriṇī [5]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">vastu-śakti</span>–The Absolute’s energy [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">chit-svarūpa</span>–spirit by nature, <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāvete</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sandhinī</span>–existence in form, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">kriyāte</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">hlādinī</span>–pleasure in action, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">tāi</span>–thus <span class=\\"e2\\">tribhāva-dhāriṇī</span>–possesses three aspects."},{"class":"b50","text":" The Absolute’s energy is spirit by nature, existence in form, and pleasure in action. The Absolute’s energy thus possesses three aspects."},{"class":"b97","text":" বস্তুশক্তিদ্বারে বস্তু দেয় পরিচয় ।<br />বস্তুশক্তি ক্রিয়াযোগে সর্ব্ব সিদ্ধ হয় ॥৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" vastu-śakti-dvāre vastu deya parichaya<br />vastu-śakti kriyā-yoge sarva siddha haya [6]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">vastu</span>–The Absolute <span class=\\"e2\\">parichaya deya</span>–reveals Himself <span class=\\"e2\\">vastu-śakti-dvāre</span>–through the Absolute’s energy; <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva</span>–everything <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–is <span class=\\"e2\\">siddha</span>–effected <span class=\\"e2\\">kriyā-yoge</span>–by the action <span class=\\"e2\\">vastu-śakti</span>–of the Absolute’s energy."},{"class":"b50","text":" The Absolute reveals Himself through His energy; everything is effected by the action of the Absolute’s energy."},{"class":"b97","text":" অখণ্ড বস্তুতে ভাব ক্রিয়া নিত্য হয় ।<br />শক্তি শক্তিমান্ বস্তু তবু পৃথক্ নয় ॥৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" akhaṇḍa vastute bhāva kriyā nitya haya<br />śakti śaktimān vastu tabu pṛthak naya [7]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāva</span>–Feeling [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">kriyā</span>–action <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–happen <span class=\\"e2\\">nitya</span>–constantly <span class=\\"e2\\">akhaṇḍa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">vastute</span>–within the indivisible Absolute. <span class=\\"e2\\">vastu</span>–The Absolute [is]<span class=\\"e2\\"> śakti</span>–energy [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">śaktimān</span>–the possessor of all energy. <span class=\\"e2\\">tabu</span>–Still, <span class=\\"e2\\">naya</span>–the Absolute is not <span class=\\"e2\\">pṛthak</span>–differentiated."},{"class":"b50","text":" Feeling and action happen constantly within the indivisible Absolute. The Absolute is energy and the possessor of all energy. Still, the Absolute is not differentiated."},{"class":"b97","text":" হ্লাদিনী বস্তুকে দিয়া দুইটী স্বরূপ ।<br />ব্রজে রাধাকৃষ্ণলীলা করায় অপরূপ ॥৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" hlādinī vastuke diyā duiṭī svarūpa<br />vraje rādhā-kṛṣṇa-līlā karāya aparūpa [8]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">hlādinī</span>–The pleasure potency <span class=\\"e2\\">vastuke</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">duiṭī</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">svarūpa diyā</span>–separates the Absolute into two [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">karāya</span>–makes <span class=\\"e2\\">rādhā-kṛṣṇa-līlā</span>–Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa’s Pastimes <span class=\\"e2\\">vraje</span>–in Vraja <span class=\\"e2\\">aparūpa</span>–sublime."},{"class":"b50","text":" The hlādinī-śakti separates the Absolute into two and makes Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa’s Pastimes in Vraja sublime."},{"class":"b97","text":" রাধাকৃষ্ণ-প্রণয়ের বিকৃতি হ্লাদিনী ।<br />অবিচিন্ত্য শক্তি রাধাকৃষ্ণ-উন্মাদিনী ॥৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" rādhā-kṛṣṇa-praṇayera vikṛti hlādinī<br />avichintya śakti rādhā-kṛṣṇa-unmādinī [9]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">hlādinī</span>–The pleasure potency [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">vikṛti</span>–a transformation<span class=\\"e2\\"> rādhā-kṛṣṇa-praṇayera</span>–of Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa’s love, <span class=\\"e2\\">avichintya śakti</span>–an inconceivable energy [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">rādhā-kṛṣṇa-unmādinī</span>–delights Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa."},{"class":"b50","text":" The hlādinī-śakti is a transformation of Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa’s love, an inconceivable energy that delights Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa."},{"class":"b97","text":" অঘটন ঘটাইতে ধরে মহাশক্তি ।<br />নির্ব্বিকারে করিয়াছে বিকার অনুরক্তি ॥১০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" aghaṭana ghaṭāite dhare mahāśakti<br />nirvikāre kariyāchhe vikāra anurakti [10]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">dhare</span>–She has <span class=\\"e2\\">mahāśakti</span>–immense power <span class=\\"e2\\">aghaṭana</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ghaṭāite</span>–to make the impossible possible: <span class=\\"e2\\">kariyāchhe</span>–she has made <span class=\\"e2\\">vikāra</span>–transformations <span class=\\"e2\\">anurakti</span>–of love <span class=\\"e2\\">nirvikāre</span>–within that which is non-transformable."},{"class":"b71","text":" The hlādinī-śakti has immense power to make the impossible possible: she has made transformations of love within the non-transformable Absolute."},{"class":"b176","text":" তত্ত্ববস্তু তার্কিকের অগোচর; কৃষ্ণকৃপাসাপেক্ষ"},{"class":"b177","text":" tattva-vastu tārkikera agochara; kṛṣṇa-kṛpā-sāpekṣa"},{"class":"b70","text":" The Absolute is incomprehensible to speculators; realisation is dependent on Kṛṣṇa’s grace"},{"class":"b97","text":" এবে এক উঠিল অপূর্ব্ব পূর্ব্বপক্ষ ।<br />তার্কিক না বুঝে যদি চিন্তে বর্ষ লক্ষ ॥১১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ebe eka uṭhila apūrva pūrva-pakṣa<br />tārkika nā bujhe yadi chinte varṣa lakṣa [11]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">ebe</span>–Now, <span class=\\"e2\\">eka</span>–an <span class=\\"e2\\">apūrva</span>–unprecedented <span class=\\"e2\\">pūrva-pakṣa</span>–proposition <span class=\\"e2\\">uṭhila</span>–has arisen [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">tārkika</span>–speculators <span class=\\"e2\\">bujhe nā</span>–do not understand [even] <span class=\\"e2\\">yadi</span>–if <span class=\\"e2\\">chinte</span>–they think [about it] <span class=\\"e2\\">lakṣa varṣa</span>–for hundreds of thousands of years."},{"class":"b50","text":" Now, an unprecedented proposition has arisen that speculators do not understand, even if they think about it for hundreds of thousands of years."},{"class":"b97","text":" কৃষ্ণ যারে কৃপা করে সেই মাত্র জানে ।<br />লক্ষবর্ষ চিন্তি তাহা না বুঝিবে আনে ॥১২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kṛṣṇa yāre kṛpā kare sei mātra jāne<br />lakṣa-varṣa chinti’ tāhā nā bujhibe āne [12]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">mātra</span>–Only <span class=\\"e2\\">sei</span>–those <span class=\\"e2\\">yāre</span>–whom <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span>–Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛpā kare</span>–blesses <span class=\\"e2\\">jāne</span>–understand [it]. <span class=\\"e2\\">āne</span>–Others <span class=\\"e2\\">bujhibe nā</span>–will not understand <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhā</span>–it [even] <span class=\\"e2\\">chinti’</span>–after thinking [about it] <span class=\\"e2\\">lakṣa-varṣa</span>–for hundreds of thousands of years."},{"class":"b50","text":" Only those whom Kṛṣṇa blesses understand it. Others will not understand it, even after thinking about it for hundreds of thousands of years."},{"class":"b97","text":" রাধাকৃষ্ণ-প্রণয়ের বিকার হ্লাদিনী ।<br />প্রণয়ের পরে জন্মে চিত্ত-উন্মাদিনী ॥১৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" rādhā-kṛṣṇa-praṇayera vikāra hlādinī<br />praṇayera pare janme chitta-unmādinī [13]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">hlādinī</span>–The pleasure potency, <span class=\\"e2\\">vikāra</span>–a transformation<span class=\\"e2\\"> rādhā-kṛṣṇa-praṇayera</span>–of Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa’s love, <span class=\\"e2\\">janme</span>–manifests <span class=\\"e2\\">pare</span>–after [Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa’s] <span class=\\"e2\\">praṇayera</span>–love [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">chitta-unmādinī</span>–delights [Their] hearts."},{"class":"b50","text":" The hlādinī-śakti, a transformation of Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa’s love, manifests after Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa’s love and delights Their hearts."},{"class":"b97","text":" রাধা-কৃষ্ণ দুই হলে হয় ত প্রণয় ।<br />প্রণয় হৈলে তবে বিকার ঘটয় ॥১৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" rādhā-kṛṣṇa dui hale haya ta’ praṇaya<br />praṇaya ha-ile tabe vikāra ghaṭaya [14]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [When] <span class=\\"e2\\">rādhā-kṛṣṇa</span>–Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">hale</span>–become <span class=\\"e2\\">dui</span>–two, <span class=\\"e2\\">praṇaya</span>–love <span class=\\"e2\\">ta’ haya</span>–manifests, [and when] <span class=\\"e2\\">praṇaya</span>–love <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-ile</span>–manifests, <span class=\\"e2\\">tabe</span>–then <span class=\\"e2\\">vikāra</span>–transformations <span class=\\"e2\\">ghaṭaya</span>–occur."},{"class":"b50","text":" When Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa become two, love manifests, and when love manifests, transformations occur."},{"class":"b97","text":" দুই দেহ হবার আগে বিকার না ছিল ।<br />তবে এক রূপ দুই কেমনে হৈল ॥১৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" dui deha habāra āge vikāra nā chhila<br />tabe eka-rūpa dui kemane ha-ila [15]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">āge</span>–Before <span class=\\"e2\\">habāra</span>–Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa assumed <span class=\\"e2\\">dui</span>–two <span class=\\"e2\\">deha</span>–bodies, <span class=\\"e2\\">chhila nā</span>–there were no <span class=\\"e2\\">vikāra</span>–transformations. <span class=\\"e2\\">tabe</span>–So, <span class=\\"e2\\">kemane</span>–how [did] <span class=\\"e2\\">eka-rūpa</span>–one form <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-ila</span>–become <span class=\\"e2\\">dui</span>–two?"},{"class":"b50","text":" Before Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa assumed two bodies, there were no transformations. So, how did one form become two?"},{"class":"b97","text":" হ্লাদিনী হইতে হয় দুই দেহ ভেদ ।<br />কোথা বা হ্লাদিনী ছিল হইল প্রভেদ ॥১৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" hlādinī ha-ite haya dui deha bheda<br />kothā vā hlādinī chhila ha-ila prabheda [16]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bheda haya</span>–One form separated [into] <span class=\\"e2\\">dui</span>–two <span class=\\"e2\\">deha</span>–bodies <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-ite</span>–because of <span class=\\"e2\\">hlādinī</span>–the hlādinī-śakti. [But] <span class=\\"e2\\">kothā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">vā</span>–where <span class=\\"e2\\">chhila</span>–was <span class=\\"e2\\">hlādinī</span>–the hlādinī-śakti [when] <span class=\\"e2\\">prabheda ha-ila</span>–they separated?"},{"class":"b50","text":" One form separated into two because of the hlādinī-śakti. But where was the hlādinī-śakti when they separated?"},{"class":"b97","text":" এই প্রশ্নের এক মাত্র আছে ত’ উত্তর ।<br />দেশকালাতীত কৃষ্ণতত্ত্ব নিরন্তর ॥১৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ei praśnera eka-mātra āchhe ta’ uttara<br />deśa-kālātīta kṛṣṇa-tattva nirantara [17]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">eka-mātra</span>–The only <span class=\\"e2\\">uttara</span>–answer <span class=\\"e2\\">ta’ āchhe</span>–there is <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">praśnera</span>–to this question [is that] <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-tattva</span>–Kṛṣṇa, by nature, [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">nirantara</span>–eternally <span class=\\"e2\\">deśa-kālātīta</span>–beyond time and space."},{"class":"b71","text":" The only answer to this question is that Kṛṣṇa, by nature, is eternally transcendental to time and space."},{"class":"b176","text":" অপ্রাকৃত-তত্ত্বে দেশকালাদির বিচার নাই"},{"class":"b177","text":" aprākṛta-tattve deśa-kālādira vichāra nāi"},{"class":"b70","text":" There is no consideration of time and space in divinity"},{"class":"b97","text":" প্রকৃতির মধ্যে দেখ কালের প্রভাব ।<br />ভূত-ভবিষ্যতের বুদ্ধি তাহার স্বভাব ॥১৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" prakṛtira madhye dekha kālera prabhāva<br />bhūta-bhaviṣyatera buddhi tāhāra svabhāva [18]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">prakṛtira</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">madhye</span>–Within material existence, <span class=\\"e2\\">dekha</span>–you see <span class=\\"e2\\">prabhāva</span>–the influence <span class=\\"e2\\">kālera</span>–of time; <span class=\\"e2\\">buddhi</span>–awareness <span class=\\"e2\\">bhūta-bhaviṣyatera</span>–of past and future [is part of] <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhāra</span>–its <span class=\\"e2\\">svabhāva</span>–nature."},{"class":"b50","text":" Within material existence, you see the influence of time; awareness of past and future are natural within material existence."},{"class":"b97","text":" অপ্রাকৃত-তত্ত্বে ভূত ভবিষ্যৎ নাই ।<br />নিত্য-বর্ত্তমান তথা বলিহারি যাই ॥১৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" aprākṛta-tattve bhūta bhaviṣyat nāi<br />nitya-vartamāna tathā balihāri yāi [19]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">aprākṛta-tattve</span>–In divinity, [however,] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāi</span>–there is no <span class=\\"e2\\">bhūta</span>–past [or] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaviṣyat</span>–future. <span class=\\"e2\\">tathā</span>–There, [there is] <span class=\\"e2\\">nitya-vartamāna</span>–the eternal present, [which] <span class=\\"e2\\">balihāri</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">yāi</span>–"},{"class":"b101","text":" is indescribable."},{"class":"b50","text":" In divinity, however, there is no past or future; there is only the eternal present, which is indescribable."},{"class":"b97","text":" বাঙ্মনের অগোচর অপ্রাকৃত-তত্ত্ব ।<br />বর্ণিতে আইসে দোষ এই মাত্র সত্য ॥২০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" vāṅmanera agochara aprākṛta-tattva<br />varṇite āise doṣa ei mātra satya [20]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">aprākṛta-tattva</span>–Divinity [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">vāṅmanera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">agochara</span>–beyond the mind and words. <span class=\\"e2\\">varṇite</span>–Describing [it] <span class=\\"e2\\">āise</span>–brings about <span class=\\"e2\\">doṣa</span>–error. <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span>–This <span class=\\"e2\\">mātra</span>–alone [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">satya</span>–true."},{"class":"b50","text":" Divinity is beyond thought and description. Describing it leads to error. This alone is the truth."},{"class":"b97","text":" অপ্রাকৃত-তত্ত্বে কভু দোষ নাহি পাই ।<br />অচিন্ত্য-শক্তিতে সব সমাধান ভাই ॥২১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" aprākṛta-tattve kabhu doṣa nāhi pāi<br />achintya-śaktite saba samādhāna bhāi [21]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāhi</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">pāi</span>–We never find <span class=\\"e2\\">doṣa</span>–faults <span class=\\"e2\\">aprākṛta-tattve</span>–in divinity. <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāi</span>–Brother, <span class=\\"e2\\">saba</span>–everything [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">samādhāna</span>–harmonised <span class=\\"e2\\">achintya-śaktite</span>–by [the Absolute’s] inconceivable energy."},{"class":"b50","text":" We never find faults in divinity. Brother, everything is harmonised by the Absolute’s inconceivable energy."},{"class":"b97","text":" পূর্ব্বাপর হেন কথা কভু নাহি তায় ।<br />সর্ব্বদা নূতন সব আনন্দে মাতায় ॥২২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" pūrvāpara hena kathā kabhu nāhi tāya<br />sarvadā nūtana saba ānande mātāya [22]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāhi</span>–There is never <span class=\\"e2\\">hena</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kathā</span>–such notion <span class=\\"e2\\">pūrvāpara</span>–of before and after <span class=\\"e2\\">tāya</span>–there. <span class=\\"e2\\">saba</span>–Everything [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">sarvadā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nūtana</span>–ever-new [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">mātāya</span>–overflows <span class=\\"e2\\">ānande</span>–with joy."},{"class":"b50","text":" There is never any sense of before and after in the Absolute. Everything is ever-new and overflows with joy."},{"class":"b97","text":" অতএব তত্ত্বে যে অখণ্ড-খণ্ড-ভাব ।<br />সমকালে দেখি সেও তত্ত্বের স্বভাব ॥২৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ataeva tattve ye akhaṇḍa-khaṇḍa-bhāva<br />sama-kāle dekhi seo tattvera svabhāva [23]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">ataeva</span>–Thus, <span class=\\"e2\\">seo ye</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">akhaṇḍa-khaṇḍa-bhāva</span>–the states of being divided and undivided, [which] <span class=\\"e2\\">dekhi</span>–we see <span class=\\"e2\\">tattve</span>–in the Absolute <span class=\\"e2\\">sama-kāle</span>–simultaneously, [are both part of] <span class=\\"e2\\">tattvera</span>–the Absolute’s <span class=\\"e2\\">svabhāva</span>–nature."},{"class":"b50","text":" Thus, the states of being divided and undivided, which we see within the Absolute simultaneously, are both part of the Absolute’s nature."},{"class":"b97","text":" বিরুদ্ধ-ধর্ম্মাশ্রয় তত্ত্ব আশ্চর্য তার গুণ ।<br />জন্মে নাই হ্লাদিনী তবু ক্রিয়াতে নিপুণ ॥২৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" viruddha-dharmāśraya tattva āścharya tāra guṇa<br />janme nāi hlādinī tabu kriyāte nipuṇa [24]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">tattva</span>–The Absolute [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">viruddha-dharmāśraya</span>–the shelter of contradictory natures. [This is] <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra</span>–His <span class=\\"e2\\">āścharya</span>–astonishing <span class=\\"e2\\">guṇa</span>–quality: <span class=\\"e2\\">janme</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāi</span>–without having manifest, <span class=\\"e2\\">hlādinī</span>–the hlādinī-śaktī [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">tabu</span>–still <span class=\\"e2\\">nipuṇa</span>–adept <span class=\\"e2\\">kriyāte</span>–in action."},{"class":"b50","text":" The Absolute has contradictory natures. This is one of the Absolute’s astonishing qualities: without having manifest, the hlādinī-śakti still acts expertly."},{"class":"b97","text":" জন্মিবার পূর্ব্বে রাধা-কৃষ্ণে দুই করে ।<br />দুঁহে প্রেমের বিকার হয়ে নিজে জন্ম ধরে ॥২৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" janmibāra pūrve rādhā-kṛṣṇe dui kare<br />du̐he premera vikāra haye nije janma dhare [25]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">pūrve</span>–Prior <span class=\\"e2\\">janmibāra</span>–to [her] manifestation, <span class=\\"e2\\">kare</span>–she makes <span class=\\"e2\\">rādhā-kṛṣṇe</span>–Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">dui</span>–two [and then] <span class=\\"e2\\">janma</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">dhare</span>–she manifests <span class=\\"e2\\">nije</span>–herself <span class=\\"e2\\">haye</span>–as <span class=\\"e2\\">vikāra</span>–the transformations <span class=\\"e2\\">premera</span>–of love <span class=\\"e2\\">du̐he</span>–between Them."},{"class":"b50","text":" Prior to her manifestation, she makes Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa two, and then manifests herself as the transformations of love between Them."},{"class":"b97","text":" নিত্য-বর্ত্তমান তত্ত্ব কালদোষহীন ।<br />কালদোষ-বিচার প্রাকৃতে সমীচীন ॥২৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" nitya-vartamāna tattva kāla-doṣa-hīna<br />kāla-doṣa-vichāra prākṛte samīchīna [26]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">tattva</span>–The Absolute, <span class=\\"e2\\">nitya-vartamāna</span>–eternally present, [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">kāla-doṣa-hīna</span>–free from the fault of time. <span class=\\"e2\\">kāla-doṣa-vichāra</span>–Consideration of the fault of time [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">samīchīna</span>–appropriate <span class=\\"e2\\">prākṛte</span>–for material existence."},{"class":"b50","text":" The eternally present Absolute is free from the fault of time. Consideration of time applies only to material existence."},{"class":"b97","text":" শ্রীঅদ্বয়তত্ত্ব আর রাধাকৃষ্ণতত্ত্ব ।<br />সমকাল সত্য নিত্য আর শুদ্ধ সত্ত্ব ॥২৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" śrī-advaya-tattva āra rādhā-kṛṣṇa-tattva<br />sama-kāla satya nitya āra śuddha sattva [27]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-advaya-tattva</span>–The nondual Absolute <span class=\\"e2\\">āra</span>–and <span class=\\"e2\\">rādhā-kṛṣṇa-tattva</span>–Rādhā-Kṛṣṇa [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">sama-kāla</span>–simultaneously <span class=\\"e2\\">satya</span>–true, <span class=\\"e2\\">nitya</span>–eternal, <span class=\\"e2\\">āra</span>–and <span class=\\"e2\\">śuddha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sattva</span>–pure in nature."},{"class":"b71","text":" The nondual Absolute and Rādhā-Kṛṣṇa are simultaneously existent, eternal, and spiritual."},{"class":"b176","text":" শ্রীরাধাকৃষ্ণই শ্রীচৈতন্য"},{"class":"b177","text":" śrī-rādhā-kṛṣṇa-i śrī-chaitanya"},{"class":"b70","text":" Śrī Rādhā and Śrī Kṛṣṇa are Śrī Chaitanya"},{"class":"b97","text":" অতএব রাধাকৃষ্ণ দুই এক হঞা ।<br />অধুনা প্রকট মোর চৈতন্য গোসাঞাঁ ॥২৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ataeva rādhā-kṛṣṇa dui eka hañā<br />adhunā prakaṭa mora chaitanya gosāñā̐ [28]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">ataeva</span>–Thus, <span class=\\"e2\\">dui</span>–the two, <span class=\\"e2\\">rādhā-kṛṣṇa</span>–Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa, <span class=\\"e2\\">hañā</span>–have become <span class=\\"e2\\">eka</span>–one <span class=\\"e2\\">adhunā</span>–now [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">prakaṭa</span>–manifest [as] <span class=\\"e2\\">mora</span>–my <span class=\\"e2\\">gosāñā̐</span>–Lord, <span class=\\"e2\\">chaitanya</span>–Śrī Chaitanya."},{"class":"b50","text":" Thus, the two, Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa, have now become one and manifest as my Lord, Śrī Chaitanya."},{"class":"b97","text":" “অধুনা” বলিতে কালভেদ নাহি কর ।<br />অপ্রাকৃতে কালভেদ নাহি তাহা স্মর ॥২৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" “adhunā” balite kāla-bheda nāhi kara<br />aprākṛte kāla-bheda nāhi tāhā smara [29]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">balite</span>–As I say, <span class=\\"e2\\">“adhunā”</span>–“now”, <span class=\\"e2\\">kara nāhi</span>–do not make <span class=\\"e2\\">kāla-bheda</span>–a temporal distinction. <span class=\\"e2\\">smara</span>–Remember <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhā</span>–that <span class=\\"e2\\">nāhi</span>–there are no <span class=\\"e2\\">kāla-bheda</span>–temporal distinctions <span class=\\"e2\\">aprākṛte</span>–in divinity."},{"class":"b50","text":" I said, “now”, but do not make a temporal distinction. Remember that there are no such distinctions in divinity."},{"class":"b97","text":" “রাধাকৃষ্ণ ছিল, ভেল চৈতন্য গোসাঞি” ।<br />এ বলিলে কালদোষ সত্যবস্তু হারাই ॥৩০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" “rādhā-kṛṣṇa chhila, bhela chaitanya gosāñi”<br />e balile kāla-doṣa satya-vastu hārāi [30]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">“rādhā-kṛṣṇa</span>–“Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">chhila</span>–existed, [and then] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhela</span>–became <span class=\\"e2\\">chaitanya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">gosāñi</span>–Lord Chaitanya”— <span class=\\"e2\\">e</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">balile</span>–if you say this, <span class=\\"e2\\">kāla-doṣa</span>–the fault of time [occurs, and] <span class=\\"e2\\">hārāi</span>–you misunderstand <span class=\\"e2\\">satya-vastu</span>–the true Absolute."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa existed, and then became Lord Chaitanya”—if you say this, you make a temporal distinction and misunderstand the Absolute."},{"class":"b97","text":" ‘একাত্মা’ শব্দেতে যদি শ্রীচৈতন্য মান ।<br />রাধাকৃষ্ণে হবে ভাই আধুনিক জ্ঞান ॥৩১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ‘ekātmā’ śabdete yadi śrī-chaitanya māna<br />rādhā-kṛṣṇe habe bhāi ādhunika jñāna [31]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāi</span>–Brother, <span class=\\"e2\\">yadi</span>–if <span class=\\"e2\\">māna</span>–you consider <span class=\\"e2\\">‘ekātmā’ śabdete</span>–the word <span class=\\"e33\\">ekātmā</span> [means] <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-chaitanya</span>–Śrī Chaitanya, [and that] <span class=\\"e2\\">habe</span>–He will become <span class=\\"e2\\">rādhā-kṛṣṇe</span>–Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa, [then] <span class=\\"e2\\">ādhunika</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">jñāna</span>–a temporal distinction [is made]."},{"class":"b50","text":" Brother, if you consider that the word <span class=\\"e3\\">ekātmā</span> means Śrī Chaitanya and that He will become Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa, then you make a temporal distinction between Them."},{"class":"b97","text":" “অগ্রে রাধাকৃষ্ণ কিবা শচীর নন্দন” ।<br />এ বিচারে বৃথা কাল না কর কর্ত্তন ॥৩২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" “agre rādhā-kṛṣṇa kibā śachīra nandana”<br />e vichāre vṛthā kāla nā kara kartana [32]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">“kibā</span>–“Who [was] <span class=\\"e2\\">agre</span>–first: <span class=\\"e2\\">rādhā-kṛṣṇa</span>–Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa [or] <span class=\\"e2\\">śachīra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nandana”</span>–the son of Śachī?” <span class=\\"e2\\">kāla</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kartana kara nā</span>–Do not spend [your] time <span class=\\"e2\\">vṛthā</span>–uselessly <span class=\\"e2\\">e</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">vichāre</span>–with such analysis."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Who was first: Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa or Śrī Chaitanya?” Do not waste your time analysing this."},{"class":"b97","text":" বলিয়াছি অপ্রাকৃতে সব বর্ত্তমান ।<br />চৈতন্য কৃষ্ণেতে তর্কে হও সাবধান ॥৩৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" baliyāchhi aprākṛte saba vartamāna<br />chaitanye kṛṣṇete tarke hao sāvadhāna [33]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">baliyāchhi</span>–I have said [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">saba</span>–everything <span class=\\"e2\\">aprākṛte</span>–within divinity [exists] <span class=\\"e2\\">vartamāna</span>–in the present. <span class=\\"e2\\">sāvadhāna hao</span>–Be cautious <span class=\\"e2\\">tarke</span>–in arguing [over] <span class=\\"e2\\">chaitanye</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇete</span>–Chaitanya and Kṛṣṇa."},{"class":"b50","text":" I have already said that everything within divinity exists in the present, so be cautious about arguing over Śrī Chaitanya and Śrī Kṛṣṇa."},{"class":"b97","text":" সমকাল নিত্যকাল দুই তত্ত্ব সত্য ।<br />অখণ্ড অদ্বয় লীলা তত্ত্বের মহত্ত্ব ॥৩৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sama-kāla nitya-kāla dui tattva satya<br />akhaṇḍa advaya līlā tattvera mahattva [34]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">dui</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">tattva</span>–The two of Them <span class=\\"e2\\">satya</span>–exist <span class=\\"e2\\">sama-kāla</span>–simultaneously [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">nitya-kāla</span>–eternally, [and Their] <span class=\\"e2\\">akhaṇḍa</span>–indivisible, <span class=\\"e2\\">advaya</span>–nondual <span class=\\"e2\\">līlā</span>–Pastimes [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">mahattva</span>–the glory <span class=\\"e2\\">tattvera</span>–of the Absolute."},{"class":"b50","text":" Śrī Chaitanya and Śrī Kṛṣṇa exist simultaneously and eternally, and Their indivisible, nondual Pastimes are Their glory."},{"class":"b97","text":" প্রণয়-বিকার-শক্তি সেই আহ্লাদিনী ।<br />দুই তত্ত্বে সমকাল রাখে এই জানি ॥৩৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" praṇaya-vikāra-śakti sei āhlādinī<br />dui tattve sama-kāla rākhe ei jāni [35]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">jāni</span>–We understand <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span>–that <span class=\\"e2\\">praṇaya-vikāra-śakti</span>–this energy, the transformation of [Their] love, <span class=\\"e2\\">sei āhlādinī</span>–the hlādinī-śakti, <span class=\\"e2\\">sama-kāla</span>–simultaneously <span class=\\"e2\\">rākhe</span>–maintains <span class=\\"e2\\">dui</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">tattve</span>–the two of Them."},{"class":"b50","text":" We understand that the transformation of Their love, the hlādinī-śakti, simultaneously maintains Them both."},{"class":"b97","text":" সেই ত’ চৈতন্য এবে প্রপঞ্চ-প্রকটে ।<br />সঙ্কীর্ত্তন করি’ বুলে গঙ্গাসিন্ধুতটে ॥৩৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sei ta’ chaitanya ebe prapañcha-prakaṭe<br />saṅkīrtana kari’ bule gaṅgā-sindhu-taṭe [36]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ta’</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">chaitanya</span>–This Śrī Chaitanya [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">ebe</span>–now <span class=\\"e2\\">prapañcha-prakaṭe</span>–manifest in the material world. <span class=\\"e2\\">bule</span>–He walks <span class=\\"e2\\">gaṅgā-sindhu-taṭe</span>–along the shore of the Gaṅgā and the ocean <span class=\\"e2\\">saṅkīrtana kari’</span>–chanting [His Name]."},{"class":"b50","text":" Śrī Chaitanya is now manifest in the material world. He walks along the shore of the Gaṅgā and the ocean performing saṅkīrtan."},{"class":"b97","text":" কৃষ্ণলীলার অধিক এই শ্রীচৈতন্যলীলা ।<br />প্রণয়-বিকার যাতে উৎকট হইলা ॥৩৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kṛṣṇa-līlāra adhika ei śrī-chaitanya-līlā<br />praṇaya-vikāra yāte utkaṭa ha-ilā [37]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-chaitanya-līlā</span>–Śrī Chaitanya’s Pastimes [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">adhika</span>–more <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-līlāra</span>–than Śrī Kṛṣṇa’s Pastimes: <span class=\\"e2\\">praṇaya-vikāra</span>–the transformations of love <span class=\\"e2\\">yāte</span>–within them <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-ilā</span>–have become <span class=\\"e2\\">utkaṭa</span>–extreme."},{"class":"b50","text":" Śrī Chaitanya’s Pastimes are more than Śrī Kṛṣṇa’s Pastimes: the transformations of love within them are the most intense."},{"class":"b97","text":" উৎকট হইয়া কৃষ্ণে রাধাভাবদ্যুতি ।<br />মাখাইল প্রেমভরে আহ্লাদিনী সতী ॥৩৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" utkaṭa ha-iyā kṛṣṇe rādhā-bhāva-dyuti<br />mākhāila prema-bhare āhlādinī satī [38]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">utkaṭa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-iyā</span>–Intensifying, <span class=\\"e2\\">satī āhlādinī</span>–the chaste pleasure potency <span class=\\"e2\\">prema-bhare</span>–lovingly <span class=\\"e2\\">mākhāila</span>–enveloped <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇe</span>–Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">rādhā-bhāva-dyuti</span>–with the heart and halo of Rādhā."},{"class":"b50","text":" Intensifying, the chaste hlādinī-śakti lovingly enveloped Kṛṣṇa with the heart and halo of Rādhā."},{"class":"b97","text":" ব্রজের অধিক সুখ নবদ্বীপধামে ।<br />পাইল পুরট কৃষ্ণ আসি’ নিজ কামে ॥৩৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" vrajera adhika sukha navadvīpa-dhāme<br />pāila puraṭa kṛṣṇa āsi’ nija kāme [39]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">puraṭa</span>–Golden <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span>–Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">āsi’</span>–came <span class=\\"e2\\">nija</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kāme</span>–to fulfil His desires, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">pāila</span>–felt <span class=\\"e2\\">adhika</span>–more <span class=\\"e2\\">sukha</span>–joy <span class=\\"e2\\">navadvīpa-dhāme</span>–in Nabadwīp Dhām <span class=\\"e2\\">vrajera</span>–than [in] Vraja."},{"class":"b71","text":" Then Golden Kṛṣṇa appeared to fulfil His desires, and felt more joy in Nabadwīp Dhām than He does in Vraja."},{"class":"b176","text":" শ্রীচৈতন্যের স্বরূপ"},{"class":"b177","text":" śrī-chaitanyera svarūpa"},{"class":"b70","text":" Śrī Chaitanya’s nature"},{"class":"b97","text":" চৈতন্যমুরতি কৃষ্ণের অপূর্ব্বস্বরূপ ।<br />কৃষ্ণমূর্ত্তি চৈতন্যের স্বরূপ অপরূপ ॥৪০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" chaitanya-murati kṛṣṇera apūrva-svarūpa<br />kṛṣṇa-mūrti chaitanyera svarūpa aparūpa [40]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">chaitanya-murati</span>–The form of Śrī Chaitanya [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">apūrva-svarūpa</span>–an extraordinary form <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇera</span>–of Śrī Kṛṣṇa, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-mūrti</span>–the form of Śrī Kṛṣṇa [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">aparūpa svarūpa</span>–a wonderful form <span class=\\"e2\\">chaitanyera</span>–of Śrī Chaitanya."},{"class":"b50","text":" Śrī Chaitanya is an extraordinary form of Śrī Kṛṣṇa, and Śrī Kṛṣṇa is a wonderful form of Śrī Chaitanya."},{"class":"b97","text":" হ্লাদিনীর দুই সাজ পরম মধুর ।<br />মধু হৈতে মধু, তাহা হৈতে সুমধুর ॥৪১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" hlādinīra dui sāja parama madhura<br />madhu haite madhu, tāhā haite sumadhura [41]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">dui</span>–These two <span class=\\"e2\\">sāja</span>–arrangements <span class=\\"e2\\">hlādinīra</span>–of the pleasure potency [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">parama</span>–supremely <span class=\\"e2\\">madhura</span>–sweet. [They are] <span class=\\"e2\\">madhu</span>–sweeter <span class=\\"e2\\">haite</span>–than <span class=\\"e2\\">madhu</span>–sweetness, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">sumadhura</span>–even sweeter <span class=\\"e2\\">haite</span>–than <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhā</span>–that."},{"class":"b50","text":" Both of these arrangements of the hlādinī-śakti are supremely sweet. They are sweeter than sweetness, and even sweeter still."},{"class":"b97","text":" সুমধুর স্বরূপ কৃষ্ণের চৈতন্য মুরতি ।<br />নিরন্তর করি তাঁতে দণ্ডবন্নতি ॥৪২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sumadhura svarūpa kṛṣṇera chaitanya-murati<br />nirantara kari tā̐te daṇḍavan-nati [42]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">nirantara</span>–Eternally, <span class=\\"e2\\">daṇḍavan-nati kari</span>–I bow <span class=\\"e2\\">tā̐te</span>–to Him, <span class=\\"e2\\">svarūpa</span>–the embodiment <span class=\\"e2\\">sumadhura</span>–of the supreme sweetness, <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">chaitanya-murati</span>–Śrī Kṛṣṇa’s form as Śrī Chaitanya."},{"class":"b50","text":" Eternally, I bow to the embodiment of the supreme sweetness, Śrī Kṛṣṇa’s form as Śrī Chaitanya."},{"class":"b97","text":" যদি বল ‘একাত্মা’ শব্দে ব্রহ্ম নির্ব্বিকার ।<br />যাহা হৈতে রাধাকৃষ্ণস্বরূপ সাকার ॥৪৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" yadi bala ‘ekātmā’ śabde brahma nirvikāra<br />yāhā haite rādhā-kṛṣṇa-svarūpa sākāra [43]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">yadi</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bala</span>–You may say <span class=\\"e2\\">‘ekātmā’ śabde</span>–the word <span class=\\"e33\\">ekātmā</span> [means] <span class=\\"e2\\">nirvikāra brahma</span>–nondifferentiated Brahma, <span class=\\"e2\\">haite</span>–from <span class=\\"e2\\">yāhā</span>–which <span class=\\"e2\\">rādhā-kṛṣṇa-svarūpa</span>–Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa [became] <span class=\\"e2\\">sākāra</span>–embodied."},{"class":"b50","text":" You may say that <span class=\\"e3\\">ekātmā</span> means nondifferentiated Brahma, from which Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa assumed forms."},{"class":"b97","text":" এ সিদ্ধান্ত হৈতে নারে শ্লোকের আভাসে ।<br />সেই দুই এক আত্মা চৈতন্যপ্রকাশে ॥৪৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" e siddhānta haite nāre ślokera ābhāse<br />sei dui eka ātmā chaitanya-prakāśe [44]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">e</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">siddhānta</span>–This conclusion <span class=\\"e2\\">haite</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāre</span>–cannot be <span class=\\"e2\\">ābhāse</span>–the intention <span class=\\"e2\\">ślokera</span>–of the verse. <span class=\\"e2\\">sei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">dui</span>–The two [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">eka</span>–one <span class=\\"e2\\">ātmā</span>–entity <span class=\\"e2\\">chaitanya-prakāśe</span>–in the form of Śrī Chaitanya."},{"class":"b71","text":" Such a conclusion, however, cannot be the intended meaning of the verse. The two, Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa, are one entity (ātmā) as Śrī Chaitanya."},{"class":"b176","text":" ব্রহ্ম শ্রীচৈতন্যের অঙ্গকান্তি"},{"class":"b177","text":" brahma śrī-chaitanyera aṅga-kānti"},{"class":"b70","text":" Brahma is Śrī Chaitanya’s bodily lustre"},{"class":"b97","text":" চৈতন্য নহেন কভু ব্রহ্ম নির্ব্বিকার ।<br />আনন্দবিকারপূর্ণ বিশুদ্ধ সাকার ॥৪৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" chaitanya nahena kabhu brahma nirvikāra<br />ānanda-vikāra-pūrṇa viśuddha sākāra [45]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">chaitanya</span>–Śrī Chaitanya <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu nahena</span>–is never <span class=\\"e2\\">nirvikāra brahma</span>–nondifferentiated Brahma. [He has] <span class=\\"e2\\">viśuddha</span>–a pure <span class=\\"e2\\">sākāra</span>–form <span class=\\"e2\\">ānanda-vikāra-pūrṇa</span>–filled with transformations of ecstasy."},{"class":"b50","text":" Śrī Chaitanya is never nondifferentiated Brahma. He has a spiritual form and is filled with transformations of ecstasy."},{"class":"b97","text":" ব্রহ্ম তাঁর শ্রীঅঙ্গের জ্যোতি নির্ব্বিশেষ ।<br />ব্রহ্মের প্রতিষ্ঠা কৃষ্ণচৈতন্যবিশেষ ॥৪৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" brahma tā̐ra śrī-aṅgera jyoti nirviśeṣa<br />brahmera pratiṣṭhā kṛṣṇa-chaitanya-viśeṣa [46]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-chaitanya-viśeṣa</span>–Śrī Kṛṣṇa Chaitanya Himself [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">pratiṣṭhā</span>–the origin <span class=\\"e2\\">brahmera</span>–of Brahma; <span class=\\"e2\\">brahma</span>–Brahma [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">nirviśeṣa jyoti</span>–the nondifferentiated lustre <span class=\\"e2\\">tā̐ra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-aṅgera</span>–of His divine form."},{"class":"b50","text":" Śrī Kṛṣṇa Chaitanya Himself is the origin of Brahma; Brahma is the nondifferentiated lustre of His divine form."},{"class":"b97","text":" অতএব ‘একাত্মা’ শব্দেতে শ্রীচৈতন্য ।<br />বুঝেন পণ্ডিতগণ স্বরূপাদি ধন্য ॥৪৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ataeva ‘ekātmā’ śabdete śrī-chaitanya<br />bujhena paṇḍita-gaṇa svarūpādi dhanya [47]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">ataeva</span>–Thus, <span class=\\"e2\\">svarūpādi dhanya paṇḍita-gaṇa</span>–Svarūp Dāmodar and other renowned scholars <span class=\\"e2\\">bujhena</span>–understand <span class=\\"e2\\">śabdete</span>–the word <span class=\\"e2\\">‘ekātmā’</span>–<span class=\\"e33\\">ekātmā</span> [to mean] <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-chaitanya</span>–Śrī Chaitanya."},{"class":"b50","text":" Thus, Svarūp Dāmodar and other renowned scholars understand <span class=\\"e3\\">ekātmā</span> to mean Śrī Chaitanya."},{"class":"b97","text":" সেই ত’ ‘একাত্মা’-তত্ত্বে কর পরণাম ।<br />রাধাকৃষ্ণসেবা পাবে, সিদ্ধ হবে কাম ॥৪৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sei ta’ ‘ekātmā’-tattve kara paraṇāma<br />rādhā-kṛṣṇa-sevā pābe, siddha habe kāma [48]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">paraṇāma kara</span>–Bow <span class=\\"e2\\">sei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ta’</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">‘ekātmā’-tattve</span>–to that <span class=\\"e33\\">ekātmā</span> (‘one being’). <span class=\\"e2\\">pābe</span>–You will attain <span class=\\"e2\\">rādhā-kṛṣṇa-sevā</span>–Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa’s service, [and your] <span class=\\"e2\\">kāma</span>–desires <span class=\\"e2\\">siddha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">habe</span>–will be fulfilled."},{"class":"b71","text":" Bow down to that <span class=\\"e3\\">ekātmā</span> (‘one being’). You will attain Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa’s service, and all your desires will be fulfilled."},{"class":"b176","text":" পরমাত্মা শ্রীচৈতন্যের অংশ"},{"class":"b177","text":" paramātmā śrī-chaitanyera aṁśa"},{"class":"b70","text":" The Supersoul is Śrī Chaitanya’s expansion"},{"class":"b97","text":" যদি বল ‘একাত্মা’ শব্দে হয় পরমাত্মা ।<br />যাহা হইতে রাধাকৃষ্ণ হয় দুই আত্মা ॥৪৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" yadi bala ‘ekātmā’ śabde haya paramātmā<br />yāhā ha-ite rādhā-kṛṣṇa haya dui ātmā [49]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">yadi</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bala</span>–You may say [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">śabde</span>–the word <span class=\\"e2\\">‘ekātmā’</span>–<span class=\\"e33\\">ekātmā</span> (‘one being’) <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–means <span class=\\"e2\\">paramātmā</span>–the Supersoul (the all-pervading Soul of all beings), <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-ite</span>–from <span class=\\"e2\\">yāhā</span>–which <span class=\\"e2\\">rādhā-kṛṣṇa</span>–Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–have become <span class=\\"e2\\">dui</span>–two <span class=\\"e2\\">ātmā</span>–beings."},{"class":"b50","text":" You may say that <span class=\\"e3\\">ekātmā</span> (‘one being’) means the Supersoul, from which Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa have become two beings."},{"class":"b97","text":" শ্লোকের আভাসে তাহা কভু নহে সিদ্ধ ।<br />“চৈতন্যাখ্য”-শব্দে হয় বড়ই বিরুদ্ধ ॥৫০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ślokera ābhāse tāhā kabhu nahe siddha<br />“chaitanyākhya”-śabde haya baḍa-i viruddha [50]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhā</span>–That <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">siddha nahe</span>–is never <span class=\\"e2\\">ābhāse</span>–the intention <span class=\\"e2\\">ślokera</span>–of the verse. <span class=\\"e2\\">“chaitanyākhya”-śabde</span>–The word <span class=\\"e33\\">Chaitanyākhya</span> (‘known as “Chaitanya”’) <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–is <span class=\\"e2\\">baḍa-i</span>–completely <span class=\\"e2\\">viruddha</span>–contradictory [to this]."},{"class":"b50","text":" That can never be the intended meaning of the verse, however, because the word <span class=\\"e3\\">Chaitanyākhya</span> (‘known as ‘Chaitanya’’) is completely contradictory to this."},{"class":"b97","text":" মূলতত্ত্ব শ্রীচৈতন্যস্বরূপ জানিবা ।<br />তাঁহার অংশ পরমাত্মা সর্ব্বদা বুঝিবা ॥৫১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" mūla-tattva śrī-chaitanya-svarūpa jānibā<br />tā̐hāra aṁśa paramātmā sarvadā bujhibā [51]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">jānibā</span>–Understand [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-chaitanya-svarūpa</span>–Śrī Chaitanya Himself [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">mūla-tattva</span>–the original truth, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">bujhibā</span>–understand [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">paramātmā</span>–the Supersoul [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">tā̐hāra</span>–His <span class=\\"e2\\">sarvadā</span>–eternal <span class=\\"e2\\">aṁśa</span>–expansion."},{"class":"b50","text":" Understand that Śrī Chaitanya is the original truth, and that the Supersoul is His eternal expansion."},{"class":"b97","text":" রাধাকৃষ্ণ-ঐক্য সেই ‘একাত্ম’-স্বরূপ ।<br />শ্রীচৈতন্য মোর প্রাণ-নাথ অপরূপ ॥৫২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" rādhā-kṛṣṇa-aikya sei ‘ekātma’-svarūpa<br />śrī-chaitanya mora prāṇa-nātha aparūpa [52]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">rādhā-kṛṣṇa-aikya</span>–The combination of Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa, <span class=\\"e2\\">sei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">‘ekātma’-svarūpa</span>–the form of that <span class=\\"e33\\">ekātmā</span> (‘one being’), [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-chaitanya</span>–Śrī Chaitanya, [the] <span class=\\"e2\\">aparūpa</span>–sublime <span class=\\"e2\\">mora</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">prāṇa-nātha</span>–Lord of my heart."},{"class":"b50","text":" The combination of Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa, the form of that <span class=\\"e3\\">ekātmā</span> (‘one being’), is Śrī Chaitanya, the sublime Lord of my heart."},{"class":"b97","text":" রাধাপদ-দাসী আমি রাধাপদ-দাসী ।<br />রাধা দ্যুতি সুবলিত রূপ ভালবাসি ॥৫৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" rādhā-pada-dāsī āmi rādhā-pada-dāsī<br />rādhā-dyuti-suvalita rūpa bhālavāsi [53]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">āmi</span>–I [am] <span class=\\"e2\\">rādhā-pada-dāsī</span>–a maidservant of Rādhā’s feet. [I am] <span class=\\"e2\\">rādhā-pada-dāsī</span>–a maidservant of Rādhā’s feet, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhālavāsi</span>–I love <span class=\\"e2\\">rūpa</span>–the form [that is] <span class=\\"e2\\">rādhā-dyuti-suvalita</span>–adorned with Her halo."},{"class":"b50","text":" I am a maidservant of Rādhā’s feet. I am a maidservant of Rādhā’s feet, and I love the form of the Lord that is adorned with Her halo."},{"class":"b97","text":" পরাৎপর শচীসুত তাঁহার চরণে ।<br />দণ্ড-পরণাম মোর অনন্যশরণে ॥৫৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" parātpara śachī-suta tā̐hara charaṇe<br />daṇḍa-paraṇāma mora ananya-śaraṇe [54]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">śachī-suta</span>–The son of Śachī (Śrī Chaitanya) [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">parātpara</span>–the Supreme Being, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">daṇḍa-paraṇāma</span>–I bow <span class=\\"e2\\">tā̐hara</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">charaṇe</span>–at His feet. [He is] <span class=\\"e2\\">mora</span>–my <span class=\\"e2\\">ananya-śaraṇe</span>–sole shelter."},{"class":"b55","text":" The son of Śachī is the Supreme Being, and I bow at His feet. He is my sole shelter."}]},{"title":"The Composition of this Book","paragraphs":[{"class":"b46","text":"\\r"},{"class":"b58","text":" Chapter Two"},{"class":"b120","text":" গ্রন্থরচনা"},{"class":"b121","text":" Grantha-rachanā"},{"class":"b175","text":" The Composition of this Book"},{"class":"b97","text":" চৈতন্যের রূপ গুণ সদা পড়ে মনে ।<br />পরাণ কাঁদায় দেহ ফাঁপায় সঘনে ॥১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" chaitanyera rūpa guṇa sadā paḍe mane<br />parāṇa kā̐dāya, deha phā̐pāya saghane [1]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">chaitanyera</span>–Śrī Chaitanya’s <span class=\\"e2\\">rūpa</span>–form [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">guṇa</span>–qualities <span class=\\"e2\\">sadā</span>–always <span class=\\"e2\\">paḍe</span>–come <span class=\\"e2\\">mane</span>–to [my] mind, [and thus my] <span class=\\"e2\\">parāṇa</span>–heart <span class=\\"e2\\">kā̐dāya</span>–cries, [and my] <span class=\\"e2\\">deha</span>–body <span class=\\"e2\\">saghane</span>–constantly <span class=\\"e2\\">phā̐pāya</span>–swells."},{"class":"b50","text":" Śrī Chaitanya’s form and qualities always come to my mind, and thus my heart cries, and my body constantly swells."},{"class":"b97","text":" কাঁদিতে কাঁদিতে মনে হইল উদয় ।<br />লেখনী ধরিয়া লিখি ছাড়ি’ লাজ ভয় ॥২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kā̐dite kā̐dite mane ha-ila udaya<br />lekhanī dhariyā likhi chhāḍi’ lāja bhaya [2]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kā̐dite</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kā̐dite</span>–As I cry, <span class=\\"e2\\">dhariyā</span>–I hold <span class=\\"e2\\">lekhanī</span>–a pen [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">likhi</span>–write [what] <span class=\\"e2\\">udaya ha-ila</span>–arises <span class=\\"e2\\">mane</span>–in [my] mind, <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍi’</span>–leaving aside [my] <span class=\\"e2\\">lāja</span>–shame [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaya</span>–fear."},{"class":"b50","text":" As I cry, I hold a pen and write what comes to mind, leaving aside my shame and fear."},{"class":"b97","text":" নামেতে ‘পণ্ডিত’ মাত্র, ঘটে কিছু নাই ।<br />চৈতন্যের লীলা তবু লিখিবারে চাই ॥৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" nāmete ‘paṇḍita’ mātra, ghaṭe kichhu nāi<br />chaitanyera līlā tabu likhibāre chāi [3]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [I am] <span class=\\"e2\\">‘paṇḍita’</span>–a ‘paṇḍit’ (scholar) <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmete</span>–in name <span class=\\"e2\\">mātra</span>–only. <span class=\\"e2\\">kichhu</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāi</span>–There is nothing <span class=\\"e2\\">ghaṭe</span>–in [my] pot (head). <span class=\\"e2\\">tabu</span>–Still, <span class=\\"e2\\">chāi</span>–I want <span class=\\"e2\\">likhibāre</span>–to write <span class=\\"e2\\">chaitanyera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">līlā</span>–about Śrī Chaitanya’s Pastimes."},{"class":"b71","text":" I am a paṇḍit in name only. There is nothing in my pot. Still, I want to write about Śrī Chaitanya’s Pastimes."},{"class":"b176","text":" স্বরূপ গোসাঞি ও পণ্ডিত জগদানন্দ"},{"class":"b177","text":" svarūpa gosāñi o paṇḍita jagadānanda"},{"class":"b70","text":" Svarūp Gosāñi and Paṇḍit Jagadānanda"},{"class":"b97","text":" গোসাঞি স্বরূপ বলে, “কি লিখ পণ্ডিত” ।<br />আমি বলি, “লিখি তাই যাহাতে পীরিত ॥৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" gosāñi svarūpa bale, “ki likha paṇḍita”<br />āmi bali, “likhi tāi yāhāte pīrita [4]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">svarūpa gosāñi</span>–Svarūp Dāmodar <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–said [to me,] <span class=\\"e2\\">“paṇḍita</span>–“O Paṇḍit, <span class=\\"e2\\">ki</span>–what <span class=\\"e2\\">likha”</span>–are you writing?” <span class=\\"e2\\">āmi</span>–I <span class=\\"e2\\">bali</span>–said, <span class=\\"e2\\">“likhi</span>–“I write <span class=\\"e2\\">tāi</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">yāhāte</span>–about whom <span class=\\"e2\\">pīrita</span>–I love."},{"class":"b50","text":" Svarūp Dāmodar asked me, “O Paṇḍit, what are you writing?” I replied, “I am writing about whom I love."},{"class":"b97","text":" চৈতন্যের লীলাকথা যাহা পড়ে মনে ।<br />লিখিয়া রাখিব আমি অতি সঙ্গোপনে” ॥৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" chaitanyera līlā-kathā yāhā paḍe mane<br />likhiyā rākhiba āmi ati saṅgopane” [5]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">āmi</span>–I <span class=\\"e2\\">likhiyā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">rākhiba</span>–will write down <span class=\\"e2\\">yāhā</span>–what <span class=\\"e2\\">paḍe</span>–comes <span class=\\"e2\\">mane</span>–to mind <span class=\\"e2\\">chaitanyera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">līlā-kathā</span>–about Śrī Chaitanya’s Pastimes <span class=\\"e2\\">ati</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">saṅgopane”</span>–very confiden­tially.”"},{"class":"b50","text":" “I am very confidentially writing down whatever comes to my mind about Śrī Chaitanya’s Pastimes.”"},{"class":"b97","text":" স্বরূপ বলেন, “তবে লিখ প্রভুর চরিত ।<br />যাহা পড়ি’ জগতের হবে বড় হিত” ॥৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" svarūpa balena, “tabe likha prabhura charita<br />yāhā paḍi’ jagatera habe baḍa hita” [6]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">svarūpa</span>–Svarūp Dāmodar <span class=\\"e2\\">balena</span>–said, <span class=\\"e2\\">“tabe</span>–“Then <span class=\\"e2\\">likha</span>–write <span class=\\"e2\\">prabhura</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">charita</span>–about the Pastimes of the Lord <span class=\\"e2\\">yāhā</span>–that <span class=\\"e2\\">jagatera baḍa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">hita</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">habe</span>–the world will be greatly benefitted <span class=\\"e2\\">paḍi’”</span>–by reading [about].”"},{"class":"b50","text":" Svarūp Dāmodar said, “Then write about the Pastimes of the Lord that the world will be greatly benefitted by reading about.”"},{"class":"b97","text":" আমি বলি, “জগতের হিত নাহি জানি ।<br />যাহা যাহা ভাল লাগে তাই লিখে আনি” ॥৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" āmi bali, “jagatera hita nāhi jāni<br />yāhā yāhā bhāla lāge tāi likhe āni” [7]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">āmi</span>–I <span class=\\"e2\\">bali</span>–replied, <span class=\\"e2\\">“jāni nāhi</span>–“I do not know [what is] <span class=\\"e2\\">hita</span>–beneficial <span class=\\"e2\\">jagatera</span>–for the world. <span class=\\"e2\\">likhe</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">āni</span>–I write <span class=\\"e2\\">tāi</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">yāhā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">yāhā</span>–whatever <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāla</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">lāge”</span>–appeals [to me.]”"},{"class":"b50","text":" I replied, “I don’t know what is beneficial for the world. I just write whatever I like.”"},{"class":"b97","text":" স্বরূপ ছাড়িল মোরে বাতুল বলিয়া ।<br />একা বসি’ লিখি আমি প্রভু ধেয়াইয়া ॥৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" svarūpa chhāḍila more bātula baliyā<br />ekā basi’ likhi āmi prabhu dheyāiya [8]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">svarūpa</span>–Svarūp <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍila</span>–left, <span class=\\"e2\\">baliyā</span>–considering <span class=\\"e2\\">more</span>–me <span class=\\"e2\\">bātula</span>–mad. <span class=\\"e2\\">basi’</span>–Sitting <span class=\\"e2\\">ekā</span>–alone, <span class=\\"e2\\">āmi</span>–I <span class=\\"e2\\">likhi</span>–write, <span class=\\"e2\\">dheyāiya</span>–meditating <span class=\\"e2\\">prabhu</span>–on the Lord."},{"class":"b50","text":" Svarūp left, considering me mad. Sitting alone, I write, meditating on the Lord."},{"class":"b97","text":" দেখিছি অনেক লীলা থাকি’ প্রভু সঙ্গে ।<br />কিছু কিছু লিখি তাই নিজ মনোরঙ্গে ॥৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" dekhichhi aneka līlā thāki’ prabhu-saṅge<br />kichhu kichhu likhi tāi nija mano-raṅge [9]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">dekhichhi</span>–I saw <span class=\\"e2\\">aneka</span>–many <span class=\\"e2\\">līlā</span>–Pastimes [while] <span class=\\"e2\\">thāki’</span>–living <span class=\\"e2\\">prabhu-saṅge</span>–with the Lord, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">likhi</span>–I write <span class=\\"e2\\">kichhu</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kichhu tāi</span>–some of them, <span class=\\"e2\\">nija</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">mano-raṅge</span>–as is pleasing to my mind."},{"class":"b50","text":" I saw many Pastimes while living with the Lord, and I write about some of them, as is pleasing to my mind."},{"class":"b97","text":" মন কাঁদে, প্রাণ কাঁদে, কাঁদে দুটী আঁখি ।<br />যখন যাহা মনে পড়ে তখন তাহা লিখি ॥১০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" mana kā̐de, prāṇa kā̐de, kā̐de duṭī ā̐khi<br />yakhana yāhā mane paḍe takhana tāhā likhi [10]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [My] <span class=\\"e2\\">mana</span>–mind <span class=\\"e2\\">kā̐de</span>–cries, [my] <span class=\\"e2\\">prāṇa</span>–heart <span class=\\"e2\\">kā̐de</span>–cries, [my] <span class=\\"e2\\">duṭī</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ā̐khi</span>–two eyes <span class=\\"e2\\">kā̐de</span>–cry, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">yakhana</span>–when <span class=\\"e2\\">yāhā</span>–something <span class=\\"e2\\">paḍe</span>–comes <span class=\\"e2\\">mane</span>–to mind, <span class=\\"e2\\">takhana</span>–then <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">likhi</span>–I write it down."},{"class":"b71","text":" My mind cries, my heart cries, my eyes cry, and whenever something comes to mind, I write it down."},{"class":"b176","text":" মহাপ্রভু ও গ্রন্থকার"},{"class":"b177","text":" mahāprabhu o granthakāra"},{"class":"b70","text":" Śrīman Mahāprabhu and the author"},{"class":"b97","text":" প্রভু মোরে হাস্য করি’ কৈল এক দিন ।<br />“দ্বারকার পাটেশ্বরী তুমি ত’ প্রবীন ॥১১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" prabhu more hāsya kari’ kaila eka-dina<br />“dvārakāra pāṭeśvarī tumi ta’ pravīṇa [11]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">eka-dina</span>–One day, <span class=\\"e2\\">prabhu</span>–the Lord <span class=\\"e2\\">hāsya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kari’</span>–smiled <span class=\\"e2\\">more</span>–at me [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">kaila</span>–said, <span class=\\"e2\\">“tumi</span>–You [are the] <span class=\\"e2\\">ta’</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">pravīṇa</span>–renowned <span class=\\"e2\\">pāṭeśvarī</span>–queen <span class=\\"e2\\">dvārakāra</span>–of Dvārakā."},{"class":"b50","text":" One day, the Lord smiled at me and said, “You are the renowned queen of Dvārakā."},{"class":"b97","text":" আমি ত’ ভিখারী অতি, মোরে সেব কেন ।<br />কত শত সন্ন্যাসী পাইবে আমা হেন” ॥১২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" āmi ta’ bhikhārī ati, more seva kena<br />kata śata sannyāsī pāibe āmā hena” [12]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">āmi</span>–I [am] <span class=\\"e2\\">ta’ ati</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bhikhārī</span>–a poor beggar. <span class=\\"e2\\">kena</span>–Why <span class=\\"e2\\">more</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">seva</span>–do you serve Me? <span class=\\"e2\\">pāibe</span>–You will find <span class=\\"e2\\">kata</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">śata</span>–hundreds <span class=\\"e2\\">sannyāsī</span>–of sannyāsīs <span class=\\"e2\\">āmā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">hena”</span>–like Me.”"},{"class":"b50","text":" “I am a poor beggar. Why do you serve Me? You will find hundreds of sannyāsīs like Me.”"},{"class":"b97","text":" মুঞি বলি, “রেখে দাও তোমার ছলনা ।<br />রাধাপদ-দাসী আমি, ও কথা বলো না ।১৩॥।"},{"class":"b60","text":" muñi bali, “rekhe dāo tomāra chhalanā<br />rādhā-pada-dāsī āmi, o kathā balo nā [13]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">muñi</span>–I <span class=\\"e2\\">bali</span>–said, <span class=\\"e2\\">“rekhe</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">dāo</span>–“Stop <span class=\\"e2\\">tomāra</span>–Your <span class=\\"e2\\">chhalanā</span>–tricks. <span class=\\"e2\\">āmi</span>–I [am] <span class=\\"e2\\">rādhā-pada-dāsī</span>–a maidservant of Rādhā’s feet. <span class=\\"e2\\">o kathā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">balo</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nā</span>–Do not say that."},{"class":"b50","text":" I said, “Stop Your tricks. I am a maidservant of Rādhā’s feet. Do not speak that way."},{"class":"b97","text":" আমার রাধার বর্ণ করিয়াছ চুরি ।<br />ব্রজে লয়ে যাব আমি তোমায় চোর ধরি’ ॥১৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" āmāra rādhāra varṇa kariyāchha churi<br />vraje laye yāba āmi tomāya chora dhari’ [14]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">churi kariyāchha</span>–You stole <span class=\\"e2\\">varṇa</span>–the complexion <span class=\\"e2\\">āmāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">rādhāra</span>–of my Rādhā, [You] <span class=\\"e2\\">chora</span>–thief! <span class=\\"e2\\">āmi</span>–I <span class=\\"e2\\">dhari’</span>–am going to catch <span class=\\"e2\\">tomāya</span>–You [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">laye</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">yāba</span>–bring [You back] <span class=\\"e2\\">vraje</span>–to Vraja."},{"class":"b50","text":" “You stole the complexion of my Rādhā, You thief! I am going to catch You and bring You back to Vraja."},{"class":"b97","text":" আমি চাই রাধাপদ, তুমি ফেল ঠেলি’ ।<br />দ্বারকা পাঠাও মোরে, এই তোমার কেলি ॥১৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" āmi chāi rādhā-pada, tumi phela ṭheli’<br />dvārakā pāṭhāo more, ei tomāra keli [15]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">āmi</span>–I <span class=\\"e2\\">chāi</span>–want <span class=\\"e2\\">rādhā-pada</span>–Rādhā’s feet, [but] <span class=\\"e2\\">tumi</span>–You <span class=\\"e2\\">ṭheli’ phela</span>–push [me] aside [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">pāṭhāo</span>–send <span class=\\"e2\\">more</span>–me <span class=\\"e2\\">dvārakā</span>–to Dvārakā. <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span>–This [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">tomāra</span>–Your <span class=\\"e2\\">keli</span>–play."},{"class":"b50","text":" “I want Rādhā’s feet, but You want to push me aside and send me to Dvārakā. This is Your play."},{"class":"b97","text":" তোমার সন্ন্যাসি-গিরি আমি ভাল জানি ।<br />মোদের বঞ্চিয়া রাধা সেবিবে আপনি” ॥১৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" tomāra sannyāsi-giri āmi bhāla jāni<br />modera vañchiyā rādhā sevibe āpani” [16]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">āmi</span>–I <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāla</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">jāni</span>–understand well <span class=\\"e2\\">tomāra</span>–Your <span class=\\"e2\\">sannyāsi-giri</span>–act as a sannyāsī. <span class=\\"e2\\">modera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">vañchiyā</span>–You will trick us [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">sevibe</span>–serve <span class=\\"e2\\">rādhā</span>–Rādhā <span class=\\"e2\\">āpani”</span>–Yourself.”"},{"class":"b71","text":" “I understand perfectly Your act as a sannyāsī. You want to trick us and serve Rādhā Yourself.”"},{"class":"b176","text":" বাল্য-ঘটনা-স্মরণে গ্রন্থকারের আক্ষেপোক্তি"},{"class":"b177","text":" bālya-ghaṭanā-smaraṇe granthakārera ākṣepokti"},{"class":"b70","text":" The author’s lament in remembrance of the Lord’s childhood Pastimes"},{"class":"b123","text":" আহা সে চৈতন্য পদ\\tভজনের সম্পদ<br />\\tকোথা এবে গেল আমা ছাড়ি’<br />আমাকে ফেলিয়া গেল\\tমৃত্যু মোর না হৈল<br />\\tশোকে আমি যাই গড়াগড়ি ॥১৭॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" āhā se chaitanya-pada\\tbhajanera sampada<br />\\tkothā ebe gela āmā chhāḍi’<br />āmāke pheliyā gela\\tmṛtyu mora nā ha-ila<br />\\tśoke āmi yāi gaḍāgaḍi [17]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">āhā</span>–Oh! <span class=\\"e2\\">se</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">chaitanya-pada</span>–Śrī Chaitanya’s feet [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">sampada</span>–the wealth <span class=\\"e2\\">bhajanera</span>–of devotion. <span class=\\"e2\\">kothā</span>–Where <span class=\\"e2\\">gela</span>–have they gone <span class=\\"e2\\">ebe</span>–now, <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍi’</span>–leaving <span class=\\"e2\\">āmā</span>–me? <span class=\\"e2\\">āmāke</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">pheliyā</span>–They have thrown me away [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">gela</span>–left, [but] <span class=\\"e2\\">mora mṛtyu</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-ila nā</span>–I have not died. <span class=\\"e2\\">āmi</span>–I <span class=\\"e2\\">gaḍāgaḍi yāi</span>–wallow <span class=\\"e2\\">śoke</span>–in lamentation."},{"class":"b50","text":" Oh! Śrī Chaitanya’s feet are the wealth of devotion. Where have they gone, leaving me alone? They have thrown me away and left, but I have not died. I simply wallow in lamentation."},{"class":"b123","text":" একদিন শিশুকালে\\tদুজনেতে পাঠশালে<br />\\tকোন্দলে করিনু হাতাহাতি ।<br />মায়াপুরে গঙ্গাতীরে\\tপড়িয়া দুঃখের ভারে<br />\\tকাঁঁদিলাম এক দিন রাতি ॥১৮॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" eka-dina śiśu-kāle\\tdu-janete pāṭhaśāle<br />\\tkondale karinu hātāhāti<br />māyāpure gaṅgā-tīre\\tpaḍiyā duḥkhera bhāre<br />\\tkā̐dilāma eka-dina rāti [18]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">eka-dina</span>–One day, <span class=\\"e2\\">śiśu-kāle</span>–in [our] childhood, <span class=\\"e2\\">du-janete</span>–we <span class=\\"e2\\">hātāhāti karinu</span>–fought hand to hand <span class=\\"e2\\">kondale</span>–in a quarrel <span class=\\"e2\\">pāṭhaśāle</span>–at school. <span class=\\"e2\\">duḥkhera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāre paḍiyā</span>–I became filled with sadness [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">kā̐dilāma</span>–cried <span class=\\"e2\\">eka-dina</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">rāti</span>–that day and night <span class=\\"e2\\">gaṅgā-tīre</span>–on the bank of the Gaṅgā <span class=\\"e2\\">māyāpure</span>–in Māyāpur."},{"class":"b50","text":" One day, in our childhood, we fought hand to hand in a quarrel at school. I became filled with sadness and cried all day and night on the bank of the Gaṅgā in Māyāpur."},{"class":"b123","text":" সদয় হইয়া নাথ\\tনা হইতে পরভাত <br />\\tগদাধরের সঙ্গেতে আসিয়া ।<br />ডাকেন, “জগদানন্দ!\\tঅভিমান বড় মন্দ<br />\\tকথা বলো বক্রতা ছাড়িয়া” ॥১৯॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" sadaya ha-iyā nātha\\tnā ha-ite parabhāta<br />\\tgadādharera saṅgete āsiyā<br />ḍākena, “jagadānanda!\\tabhimāna baḍa manda<br />\\tkathā balo vakratā chhāḍiyā” [19]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sadaya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-iyā</span>–Compassionately, <span class=\\"e2\\">nātha</span>–the Lord <span class=\\"e2\\">āsiyā</span>–came [to me] <span class=\\"e2\\">parabhāta</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-ite nā</span>–before dawn <span class=\\"e2\\">gadādharera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">saṅgete</span>–with Gadādhar [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">ḍākena</span>–called out, <span class=\\"e2\\">“jagadānanda!</span>–Jagadānanda! <span class=\\"e2\\">abhimāna</span>–Pride [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">baḍa</span>–very <span class=\\"e2\\">manda</span>–bad. <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍiyā</span>–Give up [your] <span class=\\"e2\\">vakratā</span>–crookedness [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">kathā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">balo”</span>–speak [to Me].”"},{"class":"b50","text":" Compassionately, the Lord came to me before dawn with Gadādhar and called out, “Jagadānanda! Pride is very bad. Be straightforward and speak to Me.”"},{"class":"b123","text":" প্রভুর বদন হেরি’\\tঅভিমান দূর করি’<br />\\tজিজ্ঞাসিলাম, “এত রাত্রে কেন<br />নদীয়ার কড়া ভূমি\\tচলি’ কষ্ট পাইলে তুমি<br />\\tমো লাগি’ তোমার কষ্ট হেন” ॥২০॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" prabhura vadana heri’\\tabhimāna dūra kari’<br />\\tjijñāsilāma, “eta rātre kena<br />nadīyāra kaḍā bhūmi\\tchali’ kaṣṭa pāile tumi<br />\\tmo lāgi’ tomāra kaṣṭa hena” [20]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">heri’</span>–Seeing <span class=\\"e2\\">prabhura</span>–the Lord’s <span class=\\"e2\\">vadana</span>–face, <span class=\\"e2\\">dūra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kari’</span>–I did away with [my] <span class=\\"e2\\">abhimāna</span>–pride [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">jijñāsilāma</span>–asked, <span class=\\"e2\\">“kena</span>–“Why <span class=\\"e2\\">kaṣṭa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">tumi pāile</span>–have You taken [such] trouble [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">chali’</span>–walked [here,] <span class=\\"e2\\">kaḍā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bhūmi</span>–across the hard ground <span class=\\"e2\\">nadīyāra</span>–of Nadia, <span class=\\"e2\\">eta</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">rātre</span>–so late at night? <span class=\\"e2\\">tomāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">hena kaṣṭa</span>–Have You taken such trouble <span class=\\"e2\\">mo</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">lāgi’”</span>–for me?”"},{"class":"b50","text":" Seeing the Lord’s face, I gave up my pride and asked, “Why have You taken such trouble and walked here, across the hard ground of Nadia, so late at night? Have You taken such trouble for me?”"},{"class":"b123","text":" প্রভু বলে, “চল চল\\tনিশি অবসান ভেল<br />\\tগৃহে গিয়া করহ ভোজন ।<br />তব দুঃখ জানি’ মনে\\tছিলাম আমি অনশনে<br />\\tশয্যা ছাড়ি’ ভূমিতে শয়ান ॥২১॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" prabhu bale, “chala chala\\tniśi avasāna bhela<br />\\tgṛhe giyā karaha bhojana<br />tava duḥkha jāni’ mane\\tchhilāma āmi anaśane<br />\\tśayyā chhāḍi’ bhūmite śayāna [21]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">prabhu</span>–The Lord <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–said, <span class=\\"e2\\">“chala</span>–“Let’s go! <span class=\\"e2\\">chala</span>–Let’s go! <span class=\\"e2\\">niśi</span>–The night <span class=\\"e2\\">avasāna</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bhela</span>–has ended. <span class=\\"e2\\">giyā</span>–Come <span class=\\"e2\\">gṛhe</span>–to [My] house [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhojana karaha</span>–eat. <span class=\\"e2\\">jāni’</span>–Knowing [of] <span class=\\"e2\\">tava</span>–your <span class=\\"e2\\">duḥkha</span>–sadness <span class=\\"e2\\">mane</span>–at heart, <span class=\\"e2\\">āmi</span>–I <span class=\\"e2\\">anaśane chhilāma</span>–fasted. <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍi’</span>–I left [My] <span class=\\"e2\\">śayyā</span>–bed [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">śayāna</span>–laid <span class=\\"e2\\">bhūmite</span>–on the ground."},{"class":"b50","text":" The Lord replied, “Let’s go! Let’s go! The night has ended. Come to My house and eat. Knowing you were sad, I also fasted. I left My bed and laid on the ground."},{"class":"b123","text":" হেনকালে গদাধর\\tআইল আমার ঘর<br />\\tদুঁহে আইনু তোমার তল্লাসে ।<br />ভাল হৈল মান গেল\\tএবে নিজ গৃহে চল <br />\\tকালি খেলা করিব উল্লাসে” ॥২২॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" hena-kāle gadādhara\\tāila āmāra ghara<br />\\tdu̐he āinu tomāra tallāse<br />bhāla haila māna gela\\tebe nija gṛhe chala<br />\\tkāli khelā kariba ullāse” [22]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">hena-kāle</span>–At that time, <span class=\\"e2\\">gadādhara</span>–Gadādhar <span class=\\"e2\\">āila</span>–came <span class=\\"e2\\">āmāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ghara</span>–to my room, [and then] <span class=\\"e2\\">du̐he</span>–we <span class=\\"e2\\">āinu</span>–came <span class=\\"e2\\">tallāse</span>–to search <span class=\\"e2\\">tomāra</span>–for you. <span class=\\"e2\\">haila</span>–It is <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāla</span>–good [that your] <span class=\\"e2\\">māna</span>–pride <span class=\\"e2\\">gela</span>–has gone. <span class=\\"e2\\">ebe</span>–Now <span class=\\"e2\\">chala</span>–let’s go <span class=\\"e2\\">nija</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">gṛhe</span>–to My house, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">kāli</span>–tomorrow <span class=\\"e2\\">khelā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kariba</span>–we will play [together] <span class=\\"e2\\">ullāse”</span>–happily.”"},{"class":"b50","text":" “Gadādhar came to My room, and then we came here to search for you. It is good that your pride is gone. Now let’s go to My house, and tomorrow we will play together happily.”"},{"class":"b123","text":" গদাই-চরণ ধরি’\\tউঠিলাম ধীরি ধীরি<br />\\tপ্রভু-আজ্ঞা ঠেলিতে না পারি ।<br />প্রভুর গৃহেতে গিয়া\\tকিছু খাই জল পিয়া<br />\\tশুইলাম দণ্ড দুই চারি ॥২৩॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" gadāi-charaṇa dhari’\\tuṭhilāma dhīri dhīri<br />\\tprabhu-ājñā ṭhelite nā pāri<br />prabhura gṛhete giyā\\tkichhu khāi jala piyā<br />\\tśuilāma daṇḍa dui chāri [23]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">dhari’</span>–I grasped <span class=\\"e2\\">gadāi-charaṇa</span>–Gadāi’s (Gadādhar’s) feet [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">dhīri</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">dhīri</span>–slowly <span class=\\"e2\\">uṭhilāma</span>–got up. <span class=\\"e2\\">ṭhelite</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">pāri nā</span>–I could not disobey <span class=\\"e2\\">prabhu-ājñā</span>–the Lord’s order. <span class=\\"e2\\">giyā</span>–I went <span class=\\"e2\\">prabhura</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">gṛhete</span>–to the Lord’s home, <span class=\\"e2\\">khāi</span>–ate<span class=\\"e2\\"> kichhu</span>–something, <span class=\\"e2\\">piyā</span>–drank [some] <span class=\\"e2\\">jala</span>–water, [and then] <span class=\\"e2\\">śuilāma</span>–rested <span class=\\"e2\\">dui</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">chāri daṇḍa</span>–for forty-eight to ninety-six minutes."},{"class":"b50","text":" I grasped Gadāi’s feet and slowly got up. I could not disobey the Lord’s order. I went to His home, ate something, drank some water, and then rested for an hour or so."},{"class":"b123","text":" প্রাতে শচী-জগন্নাথ\\tমোরে দিলা দুধ-ভাত<br />\\tপ্রভু সঙ্গে পড়িতে পাঠায় ।<br />পড়িয়া শুনিয়া তবে\\tআইলাম গৃহে যবে<br />\\tপ্রভু মোরে গৃহে আসি’ খায় ॥২৪॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" prāte śachī-jagannātha\\tmore dilā dudha-bhāta<br />\\tprabhu saṅge paḍite pāṭhāya<br />paḍiyā śuniyā tabe\\tāilāma gṛhe yabe<br />\\tprabhu mora gṛhe āsi’ khāya [24]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">prāte</span>–In the morning, <span class=\\"e2\\">śachī-jagannātha</span>–Śachī and Jagannāth <span class=\\"e2\\">dilā</span>–gave <span class=\\"e2\\">more</span>–me <span class=\\"e2\\">dudha-bhāta</span>–some milk and rice [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">pāṭhāya</span>–sent [me] <span class=\\"e2\\">paḍite</span>–to study <span class=\\"e2\\">saṅge</span>–with <span class=\\"e2\\">prabhu</span>–the Lord. <span class=\\"e2\\">tabe</span>–Then, <span class=\\"e2\\">yabe</span>–when <span class=\\"e2\\">āilāma</span>–I came <span class=\\"e2\\">gṛhe</span>–home <span class=\\"e2\\">paḍiyā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">śuniyā</span>–after reading and listening, <span class=\\"e2\\">prabhu</span>–the Lord <span class=\\"e2\\">āsi’</span>–came <span class=\\"e2\\">mora</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">gṛhe</span>–to my house [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">khāya</span>–ate [with me]."},{"class":"b50","text":" In the morning, Śachī and Jagannāth gave me some milk and rice and sent me to school with the Lord. When I came home after studying, the Lord came over and ate with me."},{"class":"b123","text":" কোন্দলের পরে প্রেম\\tহয় যেন শুদ্ধ হেম<br />\\tকত সুখ মনেতে হইল ।<br />প্রভু বলে, “এই লাগি’\\tতুমি রাগো, আমি রাগি<br />\\tপরস্পর প্রেম বৃদ্ধি ভেল” ॥২৫॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" kondalera pare prema\\thaya yena śuddha hema<br />\\tkata sukha manete ha-ila<br />prabhu bale, “ei lāgi’\\ttumi rāgo, āmi rāgi<br />\\tparaspara prema-vṛddhi bhela” [25]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">prema</span>–Love <span class=\\"e2\\">kondalera pare</span>–after a quarrel <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–is <span class=\\"e2\\">yena</span>–like <span class=\\"e2\\">śuddha</span>–pure <span class=\\"e2\\">hema</span>–gold. <span class=\\"e2\\">kata</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sukha ha-ila</span>–I was so happy <span class=\\"e2\\">manete</span>–within [my] heart, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">prabhu</span>–the Lord <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–said, <span class=\\"e2\\">“tumi</span>–“You <span class=\\"e2\\">rāgo</span>–got angry [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">āmi</span>–I <span class=\\"e2\\">rāgi</span>–got angry <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">lāgi’</span>–for this reason, [and now our] <span class=\\"e2\\">prema</span>–love <span class=\\"e2\\">paraspara</span>–for one another <span class=\\"e2\\">vṛddhi</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bhela”</span>–has increased.”"},{"class":"b71","text":" Love after a quarrel is like pure gold. I was so happy within my heart, and the Lord said, “Both you and I became angry out of love, and now our love for one another has increased.”"},{"class":"b176","text":" গ্রন্থকারের শ্রীচৈতন্য প্রীতি"},{"class":"b177","text":" granthakārera śrī-chaitanya prīti"},{"class":"b70","text":" The author’s love for Śrī Chaitanya"},{"class":"b123","text":" এ হেন গৌরাঙ্গচাঁদ\\tনা ভজিলে পরমাদ<br />\\tভজিলে পরম সুখ হয় ।<br />দয়ার ঠাকুর তেঁহো\\tতাঁকে কি ভুলিবে কেহ <br />\\tএত দয়া দাসে বিতরয় ॥২৬॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" e hena gaurāṅgachā̐da\\tnā bhajile paramāda<br />\\tbhajile parama sukha haya<br />dayāra ṭhākura te̐ha\\ttā̐ke ki bhulibe keha<br />\\teta dayā dāse vitaraya [26]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bhajile nā</span>–If you do not serve <span class=\\"e2\\">e</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">hena</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">gaurāṅgachā̐da</span>–Gaurāṅgachā̐d, [then you are] <span class=\\"e2\\">paramāda</span>–crazy. <span class=\\"e2\\">bhajile</span>–If you serve [Him,] <span class=\\"e2\\">parama</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sukha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–you feel the greatest joy. <span class=\\"e2\\">te̐ha</span>–He [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">ṭhākura</span>–the Deity <span class=\\"e2\\">dayāra</span>–of mercy. <span class=\\"e2\\">ki</span>–How could <span class=\\"e2\\">keha</span>–anyone <span class=\\"e2\\">bhulibe</span>–forget <span class=\\"e2\\">tā̐ke</span>–Him? <span class=\\"e2\\">vitaraya</span>–He bestows <span class=\\"e2\\">eta</span>–such <span class=\\"e2\\">dayā</span>–mercy <span class=\\"e2\\">dāse</span>–upon [His] servants."},{"class":"b50","text":" If you do not serve Gaurāṅgachā̐d, then you are crazy. If you serve Him, you will feel the greatest joy. He is the Deity of mercy. How could anyone forget Him? He bestows such mercy upon His servants."},{"class":"b123","text":" চৈতন্য আমার প্রভু\\tচৈতন্যে না ছাড়ি কভু<br />\\tসেই মোর প্রাণের ঈশ্বর ।<br />যে “চৈতন্য” বলি’ ডাকে\\tউঠে কোল দিই তাকে <br />\\tসেই মোর প্রাণের সোদর ॥২৭॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" chaitanya āmāra prabhu\\tchaitanye nā chhāḍi kabhu<br />\\tsei mora prāṇera īśvara<br />ye “chaitanya” bali’ ḍāke\\tuṭhe kola dii tāke<br />\\tsei mora prāṇera sodara [27]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">chaitanya</span>–Chaitanya [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">āmāra</span>–my <span class=\\"e2\\">prabhu</span>–master. <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu nā chhāḍi</span>–I shall never leave <span class=\\"e2\\">chaitanye</span>–Śrī Chaitanya. <span class=\\"e2\\">sei</span>–He [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">īśvara</span>–the Lord <span class=\\"e2\\">mora</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">prāṇera</span>–of my heart. <span class=\\"e2\\">uṭhe</span>–I arise [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">kola</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">dii</span>–embrace <span class=\\"e2\\">tāke</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ye</span>–anyone who <span class=\\"e2\\">bali’</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ḍāke</span>–calls out, <span class=\\"e2\\">“chaitanya”</span>–“Chaitanya!” <span class=\\"e2\\">sei</span>–They [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">sodara</span>–a dear brother <span class=\\"e2\\">mora</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">prāṇera</span>–of my heart."},{"class":"b50","text":" Chaitanya is my master. I shall never leave Him—He is the Lord of my heart. I arise and embrace anyone who calls out, “Chaitanya!” They are a brother dear to my heart."},{"class":"b123","text":" “হা চৈতন্য প্রাণধন”\\tনা বলিল যেই জন<br />\\tমুখ তার না দেখি নয়নে ।<br />চৈতন্যে ভুলিল যেবা \\tযদিও সে দেবী দেবা<br />\\tকুপ্রভাত তার দরশনে ॥২৮॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" “hā chaitanya prāṇa-dhana”\\tnā balila yei jana<br />\\tmukha tāra nā dekhi nayane<br />chaitanye bhulila yebā\\tyadio se devī devā<br />\\tkuprabhāta tāra daraśane [28]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">dekhi nā</span>–I do not look <span class=\\"e2\\">nayane</span>–with [my] eyes [at] <span class=\\"e2\\">mukha</span>–the face <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra yei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">jana</span>–of anyone who <span class=\\"e2\\">balila nā</span>–does not call out, <span class=\\"e2\\">“hā</span>–O <span class=\\"e2\\">chaitanya</span>–Chaitanya, [my] <span class=\\"e2\\">prāṇa-dhana”</span>–life and wealth!” <span class=\\"e2\\">daraśane</span>–By seeing <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra yebā</span>–anyone who <span class=\\"e2\\">bhulila</span>–has forgotten <span class=\\"e2\\">chaitanye</span>–Chaitanya, <span class=\\"e2\\">yadio</span>–even if <span class=\\"e2\\">se</span>–they [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">devī</span>–a goddess [or] <span class=\\"e2\\">devā</span>–god, [I have] <span class=\\"e2\\">kuprabhāta</span>–an inauspicious morning."},{"class":"b50","text":" I do not look at the face of anyone who does not call out, “O Chaitanya, my wealth and life!” Seeing anyone who has forgotten Chaitanya, even if they are a god or goddess, spoils my morning."},{"class":"b123","text":" চৈতন্যে ছাড়িয়া অন্য\\tসন্ন্যাসীরে করে মান্য<br />\\tতারে যষ্টি করিব প্রহার ।<br />ছাড়িয়া চৈতন্যকথা\\tঅন্য ইতিহাস বৃথা<br />\\tবলে যেই মুখে আগুন তার ॥২৯॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" chaitanye chhāḍiyā anya\\tsannyāsīre kare mānya<br />\\ttāre yaṣṭi kariba prahāra<br />chhāḍiyā chaitanya-kathā\\tanya itihāsa vṛthā<br />\\tbale yei mukhe āguna tāra [29]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">prahāra kariba</span>–I will beat <span class=\\"e2\\">yaṣṭi</span>–with a stick <span class=\\"e2\\">tāre</span>–anyone who <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍiyā</span>–leaves <span class=\\"e2\\">chaitanye</span>–Chaitanya [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">mānya kare</span>–honours <span class=\\"e2\\">anya</span>–another <span class=\\"e2\\">sannyāsīre</span>–sannyāsī. [I will throw] <span class=\\"e2\\">āguna</span>–fire <span class=\\"e2\\">mukhe</span>–in the mouth <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra yei</span>–of anyone who <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍiyā</span>–leaves aside <span class=\\"e2\\">chaitanya-kathā</span>–discussion of Chaitanya [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–speaks [about] <span class=\\"e2\\">anya</span>–irrelevant, <span class=\\"e2\\">vṛthā</span>–meaningless <span class=\\"e2\\">itihāsa</span>–subjects."},{"class":"b50","text":" I will beat with a stick anyone who leaves Chaitanya and honours another sannyāsī. I will throw fire into the mouth of anyone who leaves aside discussion of Chaitanya and speaks about irrelevant, meaningless subjects."},{"class":"b123","text":" চৈতন্যের যাহে সুখ\\tতাহে যদি ঘটে দুঃখ<br />\\tচির দুঃখ ভোগ হউ মোর ।<br />সে যদি স্বসুখ ত্যজে\\tযতি-ধর্ম্ম কভু ভজে<br />\\tআমি তাহে দুঃখেতে বিভোর ॥৩০॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" chaitanyera yāhe sukha\\ttāhe yadi ghaṭe duḥkha<br />\\tchira duḥkha bhoga ha-u mora<br />se yadi svasukha tyaje\\tyati-dharma kabhu bhaje<br />\\tāmi tāhe duḥkhete vibhora [30]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">yadi</span>–If <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhe</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">yāhe</span>–that by which <span class=\\"e2\\">chaitanyera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sukha</span>–Chaitanya is pleased <span class=\\"e2\\">ghaṭe</span>–results [in my] <span class=\\"e2\\">duḥkha</span>–sadness, [then] <span class=\\"e2\\">mora bhoga</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-u</span>–let me endure <span class=\\"e2\\">duḥkha</span>–such sadness <span class=\\"e2\\">chira</span>–forever. <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu yadi</span>–Whenever <span class=\\"e2\\">se</span>–He <span class=\\"e2\\">tyaje</span>–gives up <span class=\\"e2\\">svasukha</span>–His own happiness [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaje</span>–follows <span class=\\"e2\\">yati-dharma</span>–the duties of a renunciant, <span class=\\"e2\\">āmi</span>–I [am] <span class=\\"e2\\">vibhora</span>–overwhelmed <span class=\\"e2\\">duḥkhete</span>–with sadness <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhe</span>–by that."},{"class":"b71","text":" If what pleases Chaitanya makes me sad, then let me endure such sadness forever. But, when He gives up His own happiness and follows the duties of a renunciant, I am overwhelmed with sadness."},{"class":"b176","text":" শ্রীগৌর-গদাধর তত্ত্ব"},{"class":"b177","text":" śrī-gaura-gadādhara tattva"},{"class":"b70","text":" The nature of Śrī Gaura and Śrī Gadādhar"},{"class":"b97","text":" একদিন প্রভু মোর খেলিতে খেলিতে ।<br />চলিল অলকাতীরে নিবিড় বনেতে ॥৩১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" eka-dina prabhu mora khelite khelite<br />chalila alakā-tīre nibiḍa vanete [31]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">eka-dina</span>–One day, <span class=\\"e2\\">khelite</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">khelite</span>–while playing <span class=\\"e2\\">mora</span>–with me, <span class=\\"e2\\">prabhu</span>–the Lord <span class=\\"e2\\">chalila</span>–went <span class=\\"e2\\">nibiḍa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">vanete</span>–into the dense forest <span class=\\"e2\\">alakā-tīre</span>–on the bank of the Alakā River."},{"class":"b50","text":" One day, while playing with Me, the Lord went into the dense forest on the bank of the Alakā."},{"class":"b97","text":" আমি আর গদাধর আছিলাম সঙ্গে ।<br />বকুলের গাছে শুক পক্ষী ধরে রঙ্গে ॥৩২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" āmi āra gadādhara āchhilāma saṅge<br />bakulera gāchhe śuka pakṣī dhare raṅge [32]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">gadādhara</span>–Gadādhar <span class=\\"e2\\">āra</span>–and <span class=\\"e2\\">āmi</span>–I <span class=\\"e2\\">āchhilāma</span>–were <span class=\\"e2\\">saṅge</span>–with [Him]. <span class=\\"e2\\">raṅge dhare</span>–The Lord playfully caught <span class=\\"e2\\">śuka</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">pakṣī</span>–a parrot<span class=\\"e2\\"> bakulera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">gāchhe</span>–in a bakul tree."},{"class":"b50","text":" Gadādhar and I were with Him. The Lord playfully caught a parrot in a bakul tree."},{"class":"b97","text":" শুকে ধরি’ বলে, “তুই ব্যাসের নন্দন ।<br />রাধাকৃষ্ণ বলি’ কর আনন্দ বর্ধন” ॥৩৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" śuke dhari’ bale, “tui vyāsera nandana<br />rādhā-kṛṣṇa bali’ kara ānanda vardhana” [33]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">dhari’</span>–Holding <span class=\\"e2\\">śuke</span>–the parrot, <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–He said, <span class=\\"e2\\">“tui</span>–“You [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">nandana</span>–the son <span class=\\"e2\\">vyāsera</span>–of Vyāsa. <span class=\\"e2\\">bali’</span>–Tell [us about] <span class=\\"e2\\">rādhā-kṛṣṇa</span>–Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">vardhana kara</span>–increase [our] <span class=\\"e2\\">ānanda”</span>–joy.”"},{"class":"b50","text":" Holding the parrot, He said, “You are the son of Vyāsa. Please delight us by speaking about Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa.”"},{"class":"b97","text":" শুক তাহা নাহি বলে, বলে, “গৌরহরি” ।<br />প্রভু তারে দূরে ফেলে কোপ ছল করি’ ॥৩৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" śuka tāhā nāhi bale, bale, “gaurahari”<br />prabhu tāre dūre phele kopa chhala kari’ [34]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">śuka</span>–The parrot <span class=\\"e2\\">bale nāhi</span>–did not speak <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhā</span>–about Them. [Instead,] <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–he called out, <span class=\\"e2\\">“gaurahari”</span>–“Gaurahari!” <span class=\\"e2\\">kopa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">chhala</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kari’</span>–Feigning anger, <span class=\\"e2\\">prabhu</span>–the Lord <span class=\\"e2\\">phele</span>–threw <span class=\\"e2\\">tāre</span>–him <span class=\\"e2\\">dūre</span>–away."},{"class":"b50","text":" The parrot did not do this, and instead called out, “Gaurahari!” Feigning anger, the Lord threw the parrot away."},{"class":"b97","text":" তবু শুক “গৌর গৌর” বলিয়া নাচয় ।<br />শুকের কীর্ত্তনে হয় প্রেমের উদয় ॥৩৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" tabu śuka “gaura gaura” baliyā nāchaya<br />śukera kīrtane haya premera udaya [35]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">tabu</span>–Still, <span class=\\"e2\\">śuka</span>–the parrot <span class=\\"e2\\">baliyā</span>–chanted, <span class=\\"e2\\">“gaura</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">gaura”</span>–“Gaura! Gaura!” [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāchaya</span>–danced, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">premera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">udaya haya</span>–divine love arose <span class=\\"e2\\">śukera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kīrtane</span>–through the parrot’s kīrtan."},{"class":"b50","text":" Still, the parrot continued chanting, “Gaura! Gaura!” and danced, and his kīrtan gave rise to feelings of divine love."},{"class":"b97","text":" প্রভু বলে, “ওরে শুক এ যে বৃন্দাবন ।<br />রাধাকৃষ্ণ বল হেথা শুনুক সর্ব্বজন” ॥৩৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" prabhu bale, “ore śuka e ye vṛndāvana<br />rādhā-kṛṣṇa bala hethā śunuka sarva-jana” [36]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">prabhu</span>–The Lord <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–said, <span class=\\"e2\\">“ore</span>–O <span class=\\"e2\\">śuka</span>–parrot! <span class=\\"e2\\">e</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ye</span>–This [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">vṛndāvana</span>–Vṛndāvan. <span class=\\"e2\\">bala</span>–Speak <span class=\\"e2\\">rādhā-kṛṣṇa</span>–about Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">hethā</span>–here <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-jana śunuka”</span>–so that everyone may hear.”"},{"class":"b50","text":" The Lord said, “O parrot! This is Vṛndāvan. Speak about Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa so that everyone may hear.”"},{"class":"b97","text":" শুক বলে, “বৃন্দাবন নবদ্বীপ হইল ।<br />রাধাকৃষ্ণ গৌরহরি-রূপে দেখা দিল ॥৩৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" śuka bale, “vṛndāvana navadvīpa ha-ila<br />rādhā-kṛṣṇa gaurahari-rūpe dekhā dila [37]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">śuka</span>–The parrot <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–said, <span class=\\"e2\\">“vṛndāvana</span>–Vṛndāvan <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-ila</span>–has become <span class=\\"e2\\">navadvīpa</span>–Nabadwīp, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">rādhā-kṛṣṇa</span>–Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">dekhā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">dila</span>–have revealed [Themselves] <span class=\\"e2\\">gaurahari-rūpe</span>–as Gaurahari."},{"class":"b50","text":" The parrot said, “Vṛndāvan has become Nabadwīp, and Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa have revealed Themselves as Gaurahari."},{"class":"b97","text":" আমি শুক এই বনে গৌর-নাম গাই ।<br />তুমি মোর কৃষ্ণ, রাধা এই যে গদাই ॥৩৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" āmi śuka ei vane gaura-nāma gāi<br />tumi mora kṛṣṇa, rādhā ei ye gadāi [38]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">āmi</span>–I [am] <span class=\\"e2\\">śuka</span>–a parrot, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">gāi</span>–I chant <span class=\\"e2\\">gaura-nāma</span>–the Name of Gaura <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">vane</span>–in this forest. <span class=\\"e2\\">tumi</span>–You [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">mora</span>–my <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span>–Kṛṣṇa, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ye</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">gadāi</span>–Gadāi [is] my <span class=\\"e2\\">rādhā</span>–Rādhā."},{"class":"b50","text":" “I am a parrot, and I chant the Name of Gaura in this forest. You are my Kṛṣṇa, and Gadāi is my Rādhā."},{"class":"b97","text":" গদাই-গৌরাঙ্গ মোর প্রাণের ঈশ্বর ।<br />আন কিছু মুখে না আইসে অতঃপর” ॥৩৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" gadāi-gaurāṅga mora prāṇera īśvara<br />āna kichhu mukhe nā āise ataḥpara” [39]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">gadāi-gaurāṅga</span>–Gadāi and Gaurāṅga [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">īśvara</span>–the Lords<span class=\\"e2\\"> mora</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">prāṇera</span>–of my heart. <span class=\\"e2\\">ataḥpara</span>–Thus, <span class=\\"e2\\">āna</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kichhu nā</span>–nothing else <span class=\\"e2\\">āise</span>–comes <span class=\\"e2\\">mukhe”</span>–from [my] mouth.”"},{"class":"b50","text":" “Gadāi and Gaurāṅga are the Lords of my heart. Thus, nothing else comes from my mouth.”"},{"class":"b97","text":" প্রভু বলে, “আমি রাধাকৃষ্ণ-উপাসক ।<br />অন্য নাম শুনিলে আমার হয় শোক” ॥৪০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" prabhu bale, “āmi rādhā-kṛṣṇa-upāsaka<br />anya nāma śunile āmāra haya śoka” [40]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">prabhu</span>–The Lord <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–said, <span class=\\"e2\\">“āmi</span>–“I [am] <span class=\\"e2\\">rādhā-kṛṣṇa-upāsaka</span>–a worshipper of Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">śunile</span>–if I hear <span class=\\"e2\\">anya</span>–other <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–names, <span class=\\"e2\\">āmāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">śoka haya”</span>–I become upset.”"},{"class":"b50","text":" The Lord said, “I am a worshipper of Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa, and if I hear anyone else’s name, I become upset.”"},{"class":"b97","text":" এত বলি’ গদাইয়ের হাতটী ধরিয়া ।<br />মায়াপুরে ফিরে আইল শুকেরে ছাড়িয়া ॥৪১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" eta bali’ gadāiyera hātaṭī dhariyā<br />māyāpure phire āila śukere chhāḍiyā [41]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bali’</span>–Saying <span class=\\"e2\\">eta</span>–this, <span class=\\"e2\\">dhariyā</span>–the Lord grasped <span class=\\"e2\\">gadāiyera</span>–Gadāi’s <span class=\\"e2\\">hātaṭī</span>–hand [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">phire</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">āila</span>–went back <span class=\\"e2\\">māyāpure</span>–to Māyāpur, <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍiyā</span>–leaving <span class=\\"e2\\">śukere</span>–the parrot."},{"class":"b50","text":" Saying this, the Lord took Gadāi’s hand and went back to Māyāpur, leaving the parrot behind."},{"class":"b97","text":" শুকে বলে, “গাও তুমি যাহা লাগে ভাল ।<br />আমার ভজন আমি করি চিরকাল” ॥৪২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" śuke bale, “gāo tumi yāhā lāge bhāla<br />āmāra bhajana āmi kari chira-kāla” [42]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">śuke</span>–The parrot <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–said, [“You may] <span class=\\"e2\\">“gāo</span>–sing <span class=\\"e2\\">yāhā</span>–whatever <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāla lāge</span>–appeals <span class=\\"e2\\">tumi</span>–to You, [but] <span class=\\"e2\\">āmi</span>–I <span class=\\"e2\\">kari</span>–will do <span class=\\"e2\\">āmāra</span>–my <span class=\\"e2\\">bhajana</span>–worship <span class=\\"e2\\">chira-kāla”</span>–forever.”"},{"class":"b50","text":" The parrot said, “You may sing whatever You like, but I will continue my worship forever.”"},{"class":"b97","text":" মধুর চৈতন্যলীলা জাগে যার মনে ।<br />মোর দণ্ডবৎ ভাই তাঁহার চরণে ॥৪৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" madhura chaitanya-līlā jāge yāra mane<br />mora daṇḍavat bhāi tā̐hāra charaṇe [43]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāi</span>–Brother, <span class=\\"e2\\">mora</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">daṇḍavat</span>–I bow <span class=\\"e2\\">charaṇe</span>–at the feet <span class=\\"e2\\">tā̐hāra yāra</span>–of anyone in whose <span class=\\"e2\\">mane</span>–heart <span class=\\"e2\\">madhura</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">chaitanya-līlā</span>–the sweet Pastimes of Śrī Chaitanya <span class=\\"e2\\">jāge</span>–arise."},{"class":"b71","text":" Brother, I bow at the feet of anyone in whose heart the sweet Pastimes of Śrī Chaitanya arise."},{"class":"b176","text":" শ্রীনবদ্বীপ ও বৃন্দাবন"},{"class":"b177","text":" śrī-navadvīpa o vṛndāvana"},{"class":"b70","text":" Śrī Nabadwīp and Vṛndāvan"},{"class":"b97","text":" গদাই গৌরাঙ্গ মুঞি “রাধাশ্যাম” জানি ।<br />ষোলক্রোশ “নবদ্বীপে” “বৃন্দাবন” মানি ॥৪৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" gadāi gaurāṅge muñi “rādhā-śyāma” jāni<br />ṣola-krośa “navadvīpe” “vṛndāvana” māni [44]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">muñi</span>–I <span class=\\"e2\\">jāni</span>–know [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">gadāi</span>–Gadāi [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">gaurāṅge</span>–Gaurāṅga [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">“rādhā-śyāma”</span>–Rādhā and Śyām. <span class=\\"e2\\">māni</span>–I know [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">ṣola-krośa</span>–the thirty-two miles <span class=\\"e2\\">“navadvīpe”</span>–of Nabadwīp [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">“vṛndāvana”</span>–Vṛndāvan."},{"class":"b50","text":" I know that Gadāi and Gaurāṅga are Rādhā and Śyām, and that the thirty-two miles of Nabadwīp are Vṛndāvan."},{"class":"b97","text":" যশোদানন্দনে আর শচীর নন্দনে ।<br />যে জন পৃথক্ দেখে সে না মরে কেনে ॥৪৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" yaśodā-nandane āra śachīra nandane<br />ye jana pṛthak dekhe se nā mare kene [45]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kene</span>–Why [do] <span class=\\"e2\\">se ye</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">jana</span>–those who <span class=\\"e2\\">dekhe</span>–see <span class=\\"e2\\">pṛthak</span>–a distinction <span class=\\"e2\\">yaśodā-nandane</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">āra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">śachīra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nandane</span>–between the son of Yaśodā and the son of Śachī <span class=\\"e2\\">mare nā</span>–not die?"},{"class":"b50","text":" Why do those who see a distinction between the son of Yaśodā and the son of Śachī not die?"},{"class":"b97","text":" নবদ্বীপে না পাইল যেই বৃন্দাবন ।<br />বৃথা সে তার্কিক কেন ধরয় জীবন ॥৪৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" navadvīpe nā pāile yei vṛndāvana<br />vṛthā se tārkika kena dharaya jīvana [46]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kena</span>–Why [do] <span class=\\"e2\\">se</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">yei tārkika</span>–speculators who <span class=\\"e2\\">pāile nā</span>–do not find <span class=\\"e2\\">vṛndāvana</span>–Vṛndāvan <span class=\\"e2\\">navadvīpe</span>–within Nabadwīp <span class=\\"e2\\">dharaya</span>–continue [their] <span class=\\"e2\\">vṛthā</span>–meaningless <span class=\\"e2\\">jīvana</span>–lives?"},{"class":"b71","text":" Why do speculators who do not find Vṛndāvan within Nabadwīp continue their meaningless lives?"},{"class":"b176","text":" গৌর-ভজন বিনা ‘রাধাকৃষ্ণ’-ভজন বৃথা"},{"class":"b177","text":" gaura-bhajana vinā ‘rādhā-kṛṣṇa’-bhajana vṛthā"},{"class":"b70","text":" Without service to Gaura, service to Rādhā-Kṛṣṇa is useless"},{"class":"b97","text":" গৌর-নাম গৌর-ধাম গৌরাঙ্গ-চরিত ।<br />যে ভজে তাতে মোর অকৈতব প্রীত ॥৪৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" gaura-nāma gaura-dhāma gaurāṅga-charita<br />ye bhaje tāte mora akaitava prīta [47]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">mora</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">akaitava</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">prīta</span>–I sincerely love <span class=\\"e2\\">tāte ye</span>–those who <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaje</span>–worship <span class=\\"e2\\">gaura-nāma</span>–Gaura’s Name, <span class=\\"e2\\">gaura-dhāma</span>–Gaura’s abode, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">gaurāṅga-charita</span>–Gaurāṅga’s Pastimes."},{"class":"b50","text":" I sincerely love those who worship Gaura’s Name, Gaura’s abode, and Gaura’s Pastimes."},{"class":"b123","text":" গৌর-রূপ গৌর-নাম\\tগৌর-লীলা গৌর-ধাম<br />\\tযে না ভজে গৌড়েতে জন্মিয়া ।<br />রাধাকৃষ্ণ-নাম-রূপ-\\tধাম-লীলা অপরূপ<br />\\tকভু নাহি স্পর্শে তার হিয়া ॥৪৮॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" gaura-rūpa gaura-nāma\\tgaura-līlā gaura-dhāma<br />\\tye nā bhaje gauḍete janmiyā<br />rādhā-kṛṣṇa-nāma-rūpa-\\tdhāma-līlā aparūpa<br />\\tkabhu nāhi sparśe tāra hiyā [48]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">rādhā-kṛṣṇa</span>–Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa’s <span class=\\"e2\\">aparūpa</span>–extraordinary <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-rūpa-dhāma-līlā</span>–Names, Forms, Abode, and Pastimes <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāhi</span>–never <span class=\\"e2\\">sparśe</span>–touch <span class=\\"e2\\">hiyā</span>–the hearts <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra ye</span>–of those who <span class=\\"e2\\">janmiyā</span>–take birth <span class=\\"e2\\">gauḍete</span>–in Gauḍa [but] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaje nā</span>–do not worship <span class=\\"e2\\">gaura-rūpa</span>–Gaura’s Form, <span class=\\"e2\\">gaura-nāma</span>–Gaura’s Name, <span class=\\"e2\\">gaura-līlā</span>–Gaura’s Pastimes, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">gaura-dhāma</span>–Gaura’s Abode."},{"class":"b55","text":" Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa’s extraordinary Names, Forms, Abode, and Pastimes never touch the hearts of those who take birth in Gauḍa but do not worship Gaura’s Form, Gaura’s Name, Gaura’s Pastimes, and Gaura’s Abode."}]},{"title":"First Obeisances","paragraphs":[{"class":"b46","text":"\\r"},{"class":"b58","text":" Chapter Three"},{"class":"b120","text":" প্রথম প্রণাম"},{"class":"b121","text":" Prathama Praṇāma"},{"class":"b175","text":" First Obeisances"},{"class":"b97","text":" যাঁর অংশে সত্যভামা দ্বারকায় ধাম ।<br />সে রাধা-চরণে মোর অসংখ্য প্রণাম ॥১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" yā̐ra aṁśe satyabhāmā dvārakāya dhāma<br />se rādhā-charaṇe mora asaṅkhya praṇāma [1]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">mora</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">asaṅkhya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">praṇāma</span>–I bow innumerable times <span class=\\"e2\\">se</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">rādhā-charaṇe</span>–at the feet of Rādhā, <span class=\\"e2\\">yā̐ra</span>–whose <span class=\\"e2\\">aṁśe</span>–expansion <span class=\\"e2\\">dvārakāya dhāma</span>–in the abode of Dvārakā [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">satyabhāmā</span>–Satyabhāmā."},{"class":"b50","text":" I bow innumerable times at the feet of Rādhā, whose expansion in Dvārakā is Satyabhāmā."},{"class":"b97","text":" শ্রীনন্দনন্দন এবে শ্রীকৃষ্ণচৈতন্য ।<br />গদাধরে সঙ্গে আনি’ নদীয়া কৈল ধন্য ॥২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" śrī-nanda-nandana ebe śrī-kṛṣṇa-chaitanya<br />gadādhare saṅge āni’ nadīyā kaila dhanya [2]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-nanda-nandana</span>–The son of Śrī Nanda [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">ebe</span>–now <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-kṛṣṇa-chaitanya</span>–Śrī Kṛṣṇa Chaitanya. <span class=\\"e2\\">āni’</span>–Bringing <span class=\\"e2\\">gadādhare</span>–Gadādhar <span class=\\"e2\\">saṅge</span>–with [Him,] <span class=\\"e2\\">dhanya kaila</span>–He has blessed <span class=\\"e2\\">nadīyā</span>–Nadia."},{"class":"b50","text":" The son of Nanda is now Śrī Kṛṣṇa Chaitanya. Bringing Gadādhar with Him, He has blessed Nadia."},{"class":"b97","text":" গদাধর লঞা শ্রীপুরুষোত্তম আইল ।<br />গদাই-গৌরাঙ্গ-রূপে গূঢ়-লীলা কৈল ।<br />টোটা-গোপীনাথ-সেবা গদাধরে দিল ॥৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" gadādhare lañā śrī-puruṣottama āila<br />gadāi-gaurāṅga-rūpe gūḍha-līlā kaila<br />ṭoṭā-gopīnātha-sevā gadādhare dila [3]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">lañā</span>–He took <span class=\\"e2\\">gadādhare</span>–Gadādhar [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">āila</span>–came <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-puruṣottama</span>–to Jagannāth Purī. <span class=\\"e2\\">gadāi-gaurāṅga-rūpe</span>–As Gaurāṅga with Gadāi, <span class=\\"e2\\">kaila</span>–He performed <span class=\\"e2\\">gūḍha-līlā</span>–confidential Pastimes, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">dila</span>–He gave <span class=\\"e2\\">gadādhare</span>–Gadādhar <span class=\\"e2\\">ṭoṭā-gopīnātha-sevā</span>–the service of Ṭoṭā Gopīnāth."},{"class":"b50","text":" He took Gadādhar and came to Śrī Puruṣottam Kṣetra. As Gaurāṅga with Gadāi, He performed confidential Pastimes, and He gave Gadādhar the service of Ṭoṭā Gopīnāth."},{"class":"b97","text":" মোরে দিল গিরিধারী-সেবা সিন্ধুতটে ।<br />গৌড়ীয়-ভকত সব আমার নিকটে ॥৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" more dila giridhārī-sevā sindhu-taṭe<br />gauḍīya-bhakata saba āmāra nikaṭe [4]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">dila</span>–The Lord gave <span class=\\"e2\\">more</span>–me <span class=\\"e2\\">giridhārī-sevā</span>–the service of Giridhārī <span class=\\"e2\\">sindhu-taṭe</span>–on the shore of the ocean, [and kept] <span class=\\"e2\\">saba</span>–all the <span class=\\"e2\\">gauḍīya-bhakata</span>–devotees from Gauḍa <span class=\\"e2\\">āmāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nikaṭe</span>–with me."},{"class":"b50","text":" The Lord gave me the service of Giridhārī on the shore of the ocean, and kept all the devotees from Gauḍa with me."},{"class":"b97","text":" দামোদর স্বরূপ আমার প্রাণের সমান ।<br />শ্রীকৃষ্ণচৈতন্য যার দেহ-মন-প্রাণ ॥৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" dāmodara svarūpa āmāra prāṇera samāna<br />śrī-kṛṣṇa-chaitanya yāra deha-mana-prāṇa [5]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">svarūpa dāmodara</span>–Svarūp Dāmodar [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">āmāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">prāṇera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">samāna</span>–like my heart, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-kṛṣṇa-chaitanya</span>–Śrī Kṛṣṇa Chaitanya [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">yāra</span>–his <span class=\\"e2\\">deha-mana-prāṇa</span>–body, heart, and mind."},{"class":"b50","text":" Svarūp Dāmodar is my heart, and Śrī Kṛṣṇa Chaitanya is his body, heart, and mind."},{"class":"b97","text":" নমি প্রাণ-গৌর-পদে সাষ্টাঙ্গ পড়িয়া ।<br />এ ‘প্রেমবিবর্ত্ত’ লিখি ভক্ত-আজ্ঞা পায়া ॥৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" nami prāṇa-gaura-pade sāṣṭāṅge paḍiyā<br />e ‘prema-vivarta’ likhi bhakta-ājñā pāyā [6]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">nami</span>–I bow, <span class=\\"e2\\">sāṣṭāṅge</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">paḍiyā</span>–prostrating myself, <span class=\\"e2\\">prāṇa-gaura-pade</span>–at the feet of [my] beloved Gaura, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">likhi</span>–write <span class=\\"e2\\">e</span>–this <span class=\\"e2\\">‘prema-vivarta’</span>–<span class=\\"e33\\">Prema-vivarta</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">pāyā</span>–having received <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakta-ājñā</span>–the order of the devotees."},{"class":"b55","text":" I prostrate myself at the feet of my beloved Gaura and write this <span class=\\"e3\\">Prema-vivarta</span>, having received the order of the devotees."}]},{"title":"Gaura’s Greatness","paragraphs":[{"class":"b46","text":"\\r"},{"class":"b58","text":" Chapter Four"},{"class":"b120","text":" গৌরস্য গুরুতা"},{"class":"b121","text":" Gaurasya Gurutā"},{"class":"b175","text":" Gaura’s Greatness"},{"class":"b176","text":" গৌরের নৃত্য, নিত্য"},{"class":"b177","text":" gaurera nṛtya, nitya"},{"class":"b70","text":" Gaura’s dancing is eternal"},{"class":"b97","text":" ভাইরে ভজ মোর প্রাণের গৌরাঙ্গ ।<br />গৌর বিনা বৃথা সব জীবনের রঙ্গ ॥১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" bhāi-re bhaja mora prāṇera gaurāṅga<br />gaura vinā vṛthā saba jīvanera raṅga [1]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāi-re</span>–O brother! <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaja</span>–Serve <span class=\\"e2\\">gaurāṅga</span>–the Gaurāṅga <span class=\\"e2\\">mora</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">prāṇera</span>–of my heart. <span class=\\"e2\\">vinā</span>–Without <span class=\\"e2\\">gaura</span>–Gaura, <span class=\\"e2\\">saba</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">jīvanera</span>–all of life’s <span class=\\"e2\\">raṅga</span>–pleasures [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">vṛthā</span>–meaningless."},{"class":"b50","text":" O brother! Serve the Gaurāṅga of my heart. Without Gaura, all of life’s pleasures are meaningless."},{"class":"b97","text":" নবদ্বীপ-মায়াপুরে শচীর অঙ্গনে ।<br />গৌর নাচে নিত্য নিতাই-অদ্বৈতের সনে ॥২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" navadvīpa-māyāpure śachīra aṅgane<br />gaura nāche nitya nitāi-advaitera sane [2]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">gaura</span>–Gaura <span class=\\"e2\\">nāche</span>–dances <span class=\\"e2\\">nitāi-advaitera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sane</span>–with Nitāi and Advaita <span class=\\"e2\\">nitya</span>–eternally <span class=\\"e2\\">śachīra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">aṅgane</span>–in Śachī’s courtyard <span class=\\"e2\\">navadvīpa-māyāpure</span>–in Māyāpur within Nabadwīp."},{"class":"b50","text":" Gaura dances with Nitāi and Advaita eternally in Śachī’s courtyard in Māyāpur within Nabadwīp."},{"class":"b97","text":" শ্রীবাস-অঙ্গনে নাচে গায় রসভরে ।<br />যে দেখিল একবার আর না পাশরে ॥৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" śrīvāsa-aṅgane nāche gāya rasa-bhare<br />ye dekhila eka-bāra āra nā pāśare [3]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">rasa-bhare</span>–Filled with ecstasy, <span class=\\"e2\\">nāche</span>–He dances [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">gāya</span>–sings <span class=\\"e2\\">śrīvāsa-aṅgane</span>–in Śrīvās’s courtyard. <span class=\\"e2\\">ye</span>–Anyone who <span class=\\"e2\\">dekhila</span>–sees [this] <span class=\\"e2\\">eka-bāra</span>–once <span class=\\"e2\\">āra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">pāśare nā</span>–never forgets [it]."},{"class":"b50","text":" Filled with ecstasy, He dances and sings in Śrīvās’s courtyard. Anyone who sees this once never forgets it."},{"class":"b97","text":" আমার হৃদয়ে নাট অঙ্কিত হইয়া ।<br />নিরন্তর আছে মোর প্রাণ কাঁদাইয়া ॥৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" āmāra hṛdaye nāṭa aṅkita ha-iyā<br />nirantara āchhe mora prāṇa kā̐dāiyā [4]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [His] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāṭa</span>–dancing <span class=\\"e2\\">aṅkita</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-iyā</span>–is imprinted <span class=\\"e2\\">āmāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">hṛdaye</span>–in my heart, <span class=\\"e2\\">āchhe</span>–remains [there] <span class=\\"e2\\">nirantara</span>–forever, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">mora</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">prāṇa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kā̐dāiyā</span>–makes my heart cry."},{"class":"b50","text":" His dancing is imprinted in my heart. It remains there forever and makes my heart cry."},{"class":"b97","text":" জগন্নাথ-মন্দিরেতে নৃত্য দেখি যবে ।<br />অনন্ত ভাবের ঢেউ মনে উঠে তবে ॥৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" jagannātha-mandirete nṛtya dekhi yabe<br />ananta bhāvera ḍheu mane uṭhe tabe [5]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">yabe</span>–When <span class=\\"e2\\">dekhi</span>–I see [His] <span class=\\"e2\\">nṛtya</span>–dancing <span class=\\"e2\\">jagannātha-mandirete</span>–in the Temple of Jagannāth, <span class=\\"e2\\">tabe</span>–then <span class=\\"e2\\">ḍheu</span>–waves <span class=\\"e2\\">ananta</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāvera</span>–of innumerable emotions <span class=\\"e2\\">uṭhe</span>–swell <span class=\\"e2\\">mane</span>–within [my] heart."},{"class":"b50","text":" When I see His dancing in the Temple of Jagannāth, waves of innumerable emotions swell within my heart."},{"class":"b97","text":" আর কি দেখিব প্রভুর জাহ্নবীপুলিনে ।<br />সুনৃত্য-কীর্ত্তনলীলা এ ছার জীবনে ॥৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" āra ki dekhiba prabhura jāhnavī-puline<br />sunṛtya-kīrtana-līlā e chhāra jīvane [6]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">ki</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">dekhiba</span>–Will I see <span class=\\"e2\\">prabhura</span>–the Lord’s <span class=\\"e2\\">sunṛtya-kīrtana-līlā</span>–Pastimes of kīrtan and wondrous dancing <span class=\\"e2\\">jāhnavī-puline</span>–on the banks of the Gaṅgā <span class=\\"e2\\">āra</span>–again <span class=\\"e2\\">e</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">jīvane</span>–in this wretched life?"},{"class":"b71","text":" Will I ever see the Lord’s Pastimes of kīrtan and wondrous dancing on the banks of the Gaṅgā again in this wretched life?"},{"class":"b176","text":" সর্ব্বদেবদেবী শ্রীগৌরাঙ্গের দাস"},{"class":"b177","text":" sarva-deva-devī śrī-gaurāṅgera dāsa"},{"class":"b70","text":" All gods and goddesses are servants of Śrī Gaurāṅga"},{"class":"b97","text":" নিষ্ঠা করি’ ভজ ভাই গৌরাঙ্গচরণ ।<br />অন্য দেব-দেবী কভু না কর ভজন ॥৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" niṣṭhā kari’ bhaja bhāi gaurāṅga-charaṇa<br />anya deva-devī kabhu nā kara bhajana [7]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāi</span>–Brother, <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaja</span>–worship <span class=\\"e2\\">gaurāṅga-charaṇa</span>–Gaurāṅga’s feet <span class=\\"e2\\">niṣṭhā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kari’</span>–sincerely: <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nā</span>–never <span class=\\"e2\\">bhajana kara</span>–serve <span class=\\"e2\\">anya</span>–other <span class=\\"e2\\">deva-devī</span>–gods and goddesses."},{"class":"b50","text":" Brother, worship Gaura’s feet sincerely: never worship other gods or goddesses."},{"class":"b97","text":" গৌরাঙ্গের দাস বলি’ সর্ব্বদেবে জান ।<br />কৃষ্ণ হৈতে গৌরকে কভু না জানিবে আন ॥৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" gaurāṅgera dāsa bali’ sarva-deve jāna<br />kṛṣṇa haite gaurake kabhu nā jānibe āna [8]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bali’ jāna</span>–Consider [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-deve</span>–all gods [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">dāsa</span>–servants <span class=\\"e2\\">gaurāṅgera</span>–of Gaurāṅga, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">jānibe</span>–never consider <span class=\\"e2\\">gaurake</span>–Gaura <span class=\\"e2\\">āna</span>–different <span class=\\"e2\\">haite</span>–from <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span>–Kṛṣṇa."},{"class":"b50","text":" Know that all gods are servants of Gaurāṅga, and never consider Gaura different from Kṛṣṇa."},{"class":"b97","text":" নিজ গুরুদেবে জান গৌরকৃষ্ণপাত্র ।<br />গৌরাঙ্গ-পার্ষদে জান গৌরদেহগাত্র ॥৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" nija gurudeve jāna gaura-kṛpā-pātra<br />gaurāṅga-pārṣade jāna gaura-deha-gātra [9]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">jāna</span>–Know <span class=\\"e2\\">nija</span>–your <span class=\\"e2\\">gurudeve</span>–Gurudev [to be] <span class=\\"e2\\">gaura-kṛpā-pātra</span>–a recipient of Gaura’s mercy, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">jāna</span>–know <span class=\\"e2\\">gaurāṅga-pārṣade</span>–Gaurāṅga’s associates [to be] <span class=\\"e2\\">gaura-deha-gātra</span>–limbs of Gaura’s body."},{"class":"b50","text":" Know your Gurudev to be a recipient of Gaura’s mercy, and know Gaura’s associates to be limbs of Gaura’s body."},{"class":"b97","text":" গৌর-বৈরী রসপোষ্টা এই মাত্র জান ।<br />সকলে গৌরাঙ্গ-দাস এ কথাটী মান ॥১০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" gaura-vairī rasa-poṣṭā ei mātra jāna<br />sakale gaurāṅga-dāsa e kathāṭī māna [10]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">jāna</span>–Know [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">gaura-vairī</span>–the enemies of Gaura [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">mātra</span>–simply <span class=\\"e2\\">rasa-poṣṭā</span>–nourishers of rasa— <span class=\\"e2\\">sakale</span>–everyone [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">gaurāṅga-dāsa</span>–a servant of Gaurāṅga. <span class=\\"e2\\">māna</span>–Accept <span class=\\"e2\\">e</span>–this <span class=\\"e2\\">kathāṭī</span>–truth."},{"class":"b71","text":" Know that the enemies of Gaura are simply nourishers of rasa—everyone is a servant of Gaurāṅga. Accept this truth."},{"class":"b176","text":" গৌরভজননিষ্ঠা"},{"class":"b177","text":" gaura-bhajana-niṣṭhā"},{"class":"b70","text":" Attachment to Gaura’s service"},{"class":"b97","text":" পরনিন্দা পরচর্চ্চা না কর কখন ।<br />দৃঢ়ভাবে একান্তে ভজ শ্রীগৌরচরণ ॥১১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" para-nindā para-charchchā nā kara kakhana<br />dṛḍha-bhāve ekānte bhaja śrī-gaura-charaṇa [11]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kakhana kara nā</span>–Never <span class=\\"e2\\">para-nindā</span>–criticise others [or] <span class=\\"e2\\">para-charchchā</span>–gossip about others; <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaja</span>–serve <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-gaura-charaṇa</span>–Śrī Gaura’s feet <span class=\\"e2\\">dṛḍha-bhāve</span>–resolutely [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">ekānte</span>–exclusively."},{"class":"b50","text":" Never criticise or gossip about others; serve Śrī Gaura’s feet resolutely and exclusively."},{"class":"b97","text":" গৌর যে শিখাল নাম সেই নাম গাও ।<br />অন্য সব নামমাহাত্ম্য সেই নামে পাও ॥১২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" gaura ye śikhāla nāma sei nāma gāo<br />anya saba nāma-māhātmya sei nāme pāo [12]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">gāo</span>–Chant <span class=\\"e2\\">sei ye</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma nāma</span>–the Name [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">gaura</span>–Gaura <span class=\\"e2\\">śikhāla</span>–taught [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">sei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāme</span>–through that Name, <span class=\\"e2\\">pāo</span>–get <span class=\\"e2\\">anya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">saba</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-māhātmya</span>–the benefits of all other Names."},{"class":"b50","text":" Chant the Name that Gaura taught and by doing so get the benefit of chanting all other Names."},{"class":"b97","text":" গৌর বিনা গুরু নাই এ ভব-সংসারে ।<br />সরল গৌরাঙ্গভক্তি শিখাও সবারে ॥১৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" gaura vinā guru nāi e bhava-saṁsāre<br />sarala gaurāṅga-bhakti śikhāo sabāre [13]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">nāi</span>–There is no <span class=\\"e2\\">guru</span>–Guru <span class=\\"e2\\">e</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bhava-saṁsāre</span>–in this world <span class=\\"e2\\">vinā</span>–other than <span class=\\"e2\\">gaura</span>–Gaura. <span class=\\"e2\\">śikhāo</span>–Teach <span class=\\"e2\\">sabāre</span>–everyone <span class=\\"e2\\">sarala</span>–sincere <span class=\\"e2\\">gaurāṅga-bhakti</span>–devotion to Gaurāṅga."},{"class":"b50","text":" There is no Guru in this world other than Gaura. Teach everyone sincere devotion to Gaurāṅga."},{"class":"b97","text":" কুটীনাটী ছাড়, মন করহ সরল ।<br />গৌর-ভজা লোকরক্ষা একত্রে নিষ্ফল ॥১৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kuṭīnāṭī chhāḍa, mana karaha sarala<br />gaura-bhajā loka-rakṣā ekatre niṣphala [14]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍa</span>–Give up <span class=\\"e2\\">kuṭīnāṭī</span>–deceit [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">karaha</span>–make [your] <span class=\\"e2\\">mana</span>–mind <span class=\\"e2\\">sarala</span>–sincere. <span class=\\"e2\\">gaura-bhajā</span>–Serving Gaura [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">loka-rakṣā</span>–serving society <span class=\\"e2\\">ekatre</span>–at the same time [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">niṣphala</span>–useless."},{"class":"b50","text":" Give up deceit and make your mind sincere. Serving Gaura and serving society at the same time is useless."},{"class":"b97","text":" হয় গোরা ভজ, নয় লোক ভজ ভাই ।<br />একপাত্রে দুই কভু না রহে এক ঠাঞি ॥১৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" haya gorā bhaja, naya loka bhaja bhāi<br />eka-pātre dui kabhu nā rahe eka ṭhāñi [15]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāi</span>–Brother, <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–either <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaja</span>–serve <span class=\\"e2\\">gorā</span>–Gorā <span class=\\"e2\\">naya</span>–or<span class=\\"e2\\"> bhaja</span>–serve <span class=\\"e2\\">loka</span>–society. <span class=\\"e2\\">dui</span>–The two <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nā</span>–never <span class=\\"e2\\">rahe</span>–remain <span class=\\"e2\\">eka</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ṭhāñi</span>–in one place <span class=\\"e2\\">eka-pātre</span>–together."},{"class":"b50","text":" Brother, either serve Gorā or serve society. The two never remain in one place together."},{"class":"b97","text":" জগাই বলে, “যদি একনিষ্ঠ না হইবে ।<br />দুই নায়ে নদী-পারের দুর্দ্দশা লভিবে” ॥১৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" jagāi bale, “yadi eka-niṣṭha nā ha-ibe<br />dui nāye nadī-pārera durdaśā labhibe” [16]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">jagāi</span>–Jagāi <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–says, <span class=\\"e2\\">“yadi</span>–“If <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-ibe nā</span>–you do not become <span class=\\"e2\\">eka-niṣṭha</span>–single-minded, <span class=\\"e2\\">durdaśā</span>–the plight <span class=\\"e2\\">nadī-pārera</span>–of crossing a river <span class=\\"e2\\">dui</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāye</span>–in two boats <span class=\\"e2\\">labhibe”</span>–will befall you.”"},{"class":"b55","text":" Jagāi says, “If you do not become single-minded, the plight of crossing a river in two boats will befall you.”"}]},{"title":"Transformations of Ecstasy in Service","paragraphs":[{"class":"b46","text":"\\r"},{"class":"b58","text":" Chapter Five"},{"class":"b120","text":" বিবর্ত্তবিলাসসেবা"},{"class":"b121","text":" Vivarta-vilāsa-sevā"},{"class":"b175","text":" Transformations of Ecstasy in Service"},{"class":"b123","text":" প্রেমের বৈচিত্ত্যগত\\tপ্রেমের বিবর্ত্ত যত<br />\\tমোর মনে নাচে নিরন্তর ।<br />কলহ গৌরের সনে\\tকরি আমি দিনে দিনে<br />\\t“কুন্দলে জগাই” নাম মোর ॥১॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" premera vaichitya-gata\\tpremera vivarta yata<br />\\tmora mane nāche nirantara<br />kalaha gaurera sane\\tkari āmi dine dine<br />\\t“kundale jagāi” nāma mora [1]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">yata</span>–The <span class=\\"e2\\">vaichitya-gata</span>–pangs <span class=\\"e2\\">premera</span>–of love [and the] <span class=\\"e2\\">yata vivarta</span>–transformations <span class=\\"e2\\">premera</span>–of love <span class=\\"e2\\">nirantara</span>–constantly <span class=\\"e2\\">nāche</span>–dance <span class=\\"e2\\">mora</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">mane</span>–within my heart. <span class=\\"e2\\">āmi</span>–I <span class=\\"e2\\">kalaha kari</span>–quarrel <span class=\\"e2\\">gaurera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sane</span>–with Gaura <span class=\\"e2\\">dine</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">dine</span>–every day. <span class=\\"e2\\">mora</span>–My <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–name [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">“kundale</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">jagāi”</span>–“Angry Jagāi”."},{"class":"b50","text":" The pangs and transformations of love constantly dance within my heart. I quarrel with Gaura every day, and thus I am known as “Angry Jagāi”."},{"class":"b123","text":" গেলাম ব্রজে দেখিবারে\\tরহি সনাতনের ঘরে<br />\\tকলহ করিনু তার সনে ।<br />রক্তবস্ত্র সন্ন্যাসীর\\tশিরে বাঁধি’ আইলা ধীর<br />\\tভাতের হাঁড়ি মারিতে কৈনু মনে ॥২॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" gelāma vraja dekhibāre\\trahi sanātanera ghare<br />\\tkalaha karinu tāra sane<br />rakta-vastra sannyāsīra\\tśire bā̐dhi’ āilā dhīra<br />\\tbhātera hā̐ḍi mārite kainu mane [2]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">gelāma</span>–I went <span class=\\"e2\\">dekhibāre</span>–to see <span class=\\"e2\\">vraja</span>–Vraja. <span class=\\"e2\\">rahi</span>–I stayed <span class=\\"e2\\">sanātanera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ghare</span>–at Sanātan’s place. <span class=\\"e2\\">kalaha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">karinu</span>–I quarrelled <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sane</span>–with him. [When] <span class=\\"e2\\">bā̐dhi’</span>–he tied <span class=\\"e2\\">sannyāsīra</span>–a sannyāsī’s <span class=\\"e2\\">rakta-vastra</span>–red cloth <span class=\\"e2\\">śire</span>–on [his] head [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">dhīra</span>–calmly <span class=\\"e2\\">āilā</span>–came [before me,] <span class=\\"e2\\">mane kainu</span>–I decided <span class=\\"e2\\">mārite</span>–to beat [him] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhātera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">hā̐ḍi</span>–with a rice pot."},{"class":"b50","text":" I went to see Vraja, and while staying at Sanātan’s place, I quarrelled with him. When he tied a sannyāsī’s red cloth on his head and calmly came before me, I decided to beat him with a rice pot."},{"class":"b123","text":" সনাতনের বিনয় দেখে\\tছাড়ি’ তারে এক পাকে<br />\\tলজ্জায় বসিনু এক ধারে ।<br />গৌর মোর যত জানে\\tআমায় পাঠায় বৃন্দাবনে<br />\\tমজা দেখে থাকি’ নিজে দূরে ॥৩॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" sanātanera vinaya dekhe\\tchhāḍi’ tāre eka pāke<br />\\tlajjāya basinu eka dhāre<br />gaura mora yata jāne\\tāmāya pāṭhāya vṛndāvane<br />\\tmajā dekhe thāki’ nije dūre [3]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">dekhe</span>–I saw <span class=\\"e2\\">sanātanera</span>–Sanātan’s <span class=\\"e2\\">vinaya</span>–humility, <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍi’</span>–left <span class=\\"e2\\">tāre</span>–him <span class=\\"e2\\">eka</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">pāke</span>–alone, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">lajjāya</span>–shamefully <span class=\\"e2\\">basinu</span>–sat <span class=\\"e2\\">eka</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">dhāre</span>–to one side. <span class=\\"e2\\">mora</span>–My <span class=\\"e2\\">gaura</span>–Gaura <span class=\\"e2\\">jāne</span>–knows <span class=\\"e2\\">yata</span>–everything. <span class=\\"e2\\">pāṭhāya</span>–He sent <span class=\\"e2\\">āmāya</span>–me <span class=\\"e2\\">vṛndāvane</span>–to Vṛndāvan [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">dekhe</span>–observed <span class=\\"e2\\">majā</span>–the result <span class=\\"e2\\">nije thāki’</span>–while Himself remaining <span class=\\"e2\\">dūre</span>–at a distance."},{"class":"b50","text":" When I saw Sanātan’s humility, I left him alone and shamefully sat to one side. My Gaura knows everything: He sent me to Vṛndāvan and observed the result from afar."},{"class":"b123","text":" ভাল তার হউক সুখ\\tমোর হউক চির দুঃখ<br />\\tতার সুখে হবে মোর সুখ ।<br />আমি কাঁদি রাত্রদিনে\\tগৌর বিচ্ছেদ ভাবি’ মনে<br />\\tগৌর হাসে দেখি কাঁদা মুখ ॥৪॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" bhāla tāra ha-uka sukha\\tmora ha-uka chira duḥkha<br />\\ttāra sukhe habe mora sukha<br />āmi kā̐di rātra-dine\\tgaura-vichchheda bhāvi’ mane<br />\\tgaura hāse dekhi’ kā̐dā mukha [4]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāla</span>–Good! <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sukha ha-uka</span>–Let Him be happy, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">mora</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">chira</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">duḥkha ha-uka</span>–let me be sad forever. <span class=\\"e2\\">mora</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sukha habe</span>–I will be happy <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sukhe</span>–with His happiness. <span class=\\"e2\\">rātra-dine</span>–Night and day <span class=\\"e2\\">āmi</span>–I <span class=\\"e2\\">kā̐di</span>–cry, <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāvi’</span>–feeling <span class=\\"e2\\">gaura-vichchheda</span>–separation from Gaura <span class=\\"e2\\">mane</span>–at heart, [but] <span class=\\"e2\\">gaura</span>–Gaura <span class=\\"e2\\">hāse</span>–laughs <span class=\\"e2\\">dekhi’</span>–seeing [my] <span class=\\"e2\\">kā̐dā</span>–crying <span class=\\"e2\\">mukha</span>–face."},{"class":"b50","text":" Good! He can be happy, and I can be sad forever. His happiness will be my happiness. Night and day I cry, feeling separation from Gaura, but Gaura laughs seeing my crying face."},{"class":"b123","text":" সেই ত’ কপটন্যাসী\\tতার লীলা ভালবাসি<br />\\tমধুমাখা কথাগুলি তার ।<br />যে ভাব ব্রজেতে ভেবে\\tপুনঃ সেই ভাব এবে<br />\\tবুঝেও না বুঝি আর বার ॥৫॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" sei ta’ kapaṭa-nyāsī\\ttāra līlā bhālavāsi<br />\\tmadhu-mākhā kathāguli tāra<br />ye bhāva vrajete bheve\\tpunaḥ sei bhāva ebe<br />\\tbujheo nā bujhi āra bāra [5]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ta’</span>–He [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">kapaṭa-nyāsī</span>–a deceitful sannyāsī, [but] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhālavāsi</span>–I love <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra</span>–His <span class=\\"e2\\">līlā</span>–Pastimes. <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra</span>–His <span class=\\"e2\\">kathāguli</span>–words [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">madhu-mākhā</span>–full of nectar. <span class=\\"e2\\">ebe</span>–Now <span class=\\"e2\\">bheve</span>–The Lord is feeling <span class=\\"e2\\">punaḥ</span>–again <span class=\\"e2\\">ye</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāva sei bhāva</span>–the same mood [He felt] <span class=\\"e2\\">vrajete</span>–in Vraja. <span class=\\"e2\\">bujheo</span>–Although I understand [this,] <span class=\\"e2\\">āra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bāra</span>–sometimes <span class=\\"e2\\">bujhi nā</span>–I do not understand [it]."},{"class":"b50","text":" He is a deceitful sannyāsī, but I love His Pastimes. His words are full of nectar. The Lord is now feeling the same mood that He felt in Vraja. Although I understand this, sometimes I do not."},{"class":"b123","text":" চন্দনাদি তৈল আনি’\\tবাঁকা বাঁকা কথা শুনি’<br />\\tতৈল-ভাণ্ড ভাঙ্গিলাম বলে ।<br />মান করি’ নিজাসনে\\tশুঞা রৈনু অনশনে<br />\\tসে মান ভাঙ্গিল নানা ছলে ॥৬॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" chandanādi taila āni’\\tbā̐kā bā̐kā kathā śuni’<br />\\ttaila-bhāṇḍa bhāṅgilāma bale<br />māna kari’ nijāsane\\tśuñā rainu anaśane<br />\\tse māna bhāṅgila nānā chhale [6]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">āni’</span>–I brought <span class=\\"e2\\">chandanādi</span>–sandalwood <span class=\\"e2\\">taila</span>–oil [for Him, but] <span class=\\"e2\\">śuni’</span>–after hearing [His] <span class=\\"e2\\">bā̐kā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bā̐kā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kathā</span>–stubborn remarks, <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāṅgilāma</span>–I broke <span class=\\"e2\\">taila-bhāṇḍa</span>–the pot of oil <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–forcibly. <span class=\\"e2\\">māna</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kari’</span>–Angrily, <span class=\\"e2\\">śuñā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">rainu</span>–I layed <span class=\\"e2\\">nijāsane</span>–on my bed <span class=\\"e2\\">anaśane</span>–fasting. <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāṅgila</span>–He pacified [my] <span class=\\"e2\\">se</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">māna</span>–anger <span class=\\"e2\\">nānā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">chhale</span>–with various pleas."},{"class":"b50","text":" I brought some sandalwood oil for Him, but after hearing His stubborn remarks, I smashed the pot of oil. Angrily, I layed on my bed fasting, but He pacified my anger with various pleas."},{"class":"b123","text":" আমারে করায় পাক\\tঅন্নব্যঞ্জন আবোনা শাক<br />\\tবলে, “ক্রোধের পাক বড় মিষ্ট” ।<br />বাড়ায় আমার রোষ\\tতাতে তার সন্তোষ<br />\\tতার প্রসন্নতা মোর ইষ্ট ॥৭॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" āmāre karāya pāka\\tanna-vyañjana ābonā śāka<br />\\tbale, “krodhera pāka baḍa miṣṭa”<br />bāḍāya āmāra roṣa\\ttāte tāra santoṣa<br />\\ttāra prasannatā mora iṣṭa [7]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">karāya</span>–He had <span class=\\"e2\\">āmāre</span>–me <span class=\\"e2\\">pāka</span>–cook <span class=\\"e2\\">anna-vyañjana</span>–rice, vegetables, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">ābonā</span>–wild <span class=\\"e2\\">śāka</span>–spinach. <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–He said, “[Your] <span class=\\"e2\\">“krodhera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">pāka</span>–angry cooking [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">baḍa</span>–very <span class=\\"e2\\">miṣṭa”</span>–sweet.” <span class=\\"e2\\">bāḍāya</span>–He increased <span class=\\"e2\\">āmāra</span>–my <span class=\\"e2\\">roṣa</span>–anger [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">tāte</span>–so <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">santoṣa</span>–He [was] pleased. <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra</span>–His <span class=\\"e2\\">prasannatā</span>–satisfaction [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">mora</span>–my <span class=\\"e2\\">iṣṭa</span>–desire."},{"class":"b50","text":" He had me cook rice, vegetables, and wild spinach. He said, “Your angry cooking is very sweet.” He increased my anger and so was pleased. His satisfaction is my desire."},{"class":"b123","text":" জিজ্ঞাসিল সনাতন\\tযাইতে কৈনু বৃন্দাবন<br />\\tতাতে মোরে রাখে বোকা করি’ ।<br />বাল্য বুদ্ধি দেখি’ তার\\tচিত্তে হয় চমৎকার<br />\\tআমি তার পাদপদ্ম ধরি’ ॥৮॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" jijñāsila sanātana\\tyāite kainu vṛndāvana<br />\\ttāte more rākhe bokā kari’<br />bālya buddhi dekhi’ tāra\\tchitte haya chamatkāra<br />\\tāmi tāra pāda-padma dhari’ [8]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sanātana</span>–Sanātan <span class=\\"e2\\">jijñāsila</span>–asked [me for advice, and] <span class=\\"e2\\">kainu</span>–I told [him] <span class=\\"e2\\">yāite</span>–to go <span class=\\"e2\\">vṛndāvana</span>–to Vṛndāvan. <span class=\\"e2\\">more</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bokā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kari’ rākhe</span>–The Lord deemed me a fool <span class=\\"e2\\">tāte</span>–for this. <span class=\\"e2\\">dekhi’</span>–Seeing <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra</span>–His <span class=\\"e2\\">bālya</span>–childish <span class=\\"e2\\">buddhi</span>–mentality, <span class=\\"e2\\">chitte</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">chamatkāra haya</span>–I was amazed at heart, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">āmi</span>–I <span class=\\"e2\\">dhari’</span>–grasped <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra</span>–His <span class=\\"e2\\">pāda-padma</span>–lotus feet."},{"class":"b50","text":" Once, Sanātan asked me for advice, and I told him to go to Vṛndāvan. The Lord deemed me a fool for this. Seeing His childish mentality, I was amazed at heart, and I grasped His lotus feet."},{"class":"b123","text":" বৃন্দাবন যাইতে চাই\\tতাতে আজ্ঞা নাহি পাই<br />\\tনানা ছল করে মোর সনে ।<br />যখন কোন্দল হয়\\tনবদ্বীপে যেতে কয়<br />\\tসেই তার কৃপা জানি মনে ॥৯॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" vṛndāvana yāite chāi\\ttāte ājñā nāhi pāi<br />\\tnānā chhala kare mora sane<br />yakhana kondala haya\\tnavadvīpe yete kaya<br />\\tsei tāra kṛpā jāni mane [9]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">chāi</span>–I wanted <span class=\\"e2\\">yāite</span>–to go <span class=\\"e2\\">vṛndāvana</span>–to Vṛndāvan, [but] <span class=\\"e2\\">pāi nāhi</span>–I did not receive <span class=\\"e2\\">ājñā</span>–permission <span class=\\"e2\\">tāte</span>–to do so. <span class=\\"e2\\">kare</span>–He gave <span class=\\"e2\\">mora</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sane</span>–me <span class=\\"e2\\">nānā</span>–various <span class=\\"e2\\">chhala</span>–excuses. <span class=\\"e2\\">yakhana</span>–When <span class=\\"e2\\">kondala</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–we quarrelled, [however] <span class=\\"e2\\">kaya</span>–He told [me] <span class=\\"e2\\">yete</span>–to go <span class=\\"e2\\">navadvīpe</span>–to Nabadwīp, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">mane jāni</span>–I accepted <span class=\\"e2\\">sei</span>–that [as] <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra</span>–His <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛpā</span>–mercy."},{"class":"b50","text":" I wanted to go to Vṛndāvan, but I did not receive His permission: He gave me various excuses. When we quarrelled, however, He told me to go to Nabadwīp, and I accepted that as His mercy."},{"class":"b123","text":" মাতৃ-আজ্ঞা ছল করি’\\tআছেন বৈকুণ্ঠপুরী<br />\\tনিজ ধাম ছাড়িয়া এখন ।<br />তাতে পাঠায় নিজপুরে\\tযাহাকে সে কৃপা করে<br />\\tযেন গোপের গোলোক-দর্শন ॥১০॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" mātṛ-ājñā chhala kari’\\tāchhena vaikuṇṭhapurī<br />\\tnija-dhāma chhāḍiyā ekhana<br />tāte pāṭhāya nija-pure\\tyāhāke se kṛpā kare<br />\\tyena gopera goloka-darśana [10]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍiyā</span>–He left <span class=\\"e2\\">nija-dhāma</span>–His home, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">mātṛ-ājñā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">chhala</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kari’</span>–using the pretext of His mother’s order, <span class=\\"e2\\">āchhena</span>–He is <span class=\\"e2\\">ekhana</span>–now <span class=\\"e2\\">vaikuṇṭhapurī</span>–in Jagannāth Purī. <span class=\\"e2\\">pāṭhāya</span>–He sends <span class=\\"e2\\">tāte yāhāke</span>–those whom <span class=\\"e2\\">se</span>–He <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛpā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kare</span>–blesses <span class=\\"e2\\">nija-pure</span>–to His abode, [where they] <span class=\\"e2\\">yena</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">gopera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">goloka-darśana</span>–can see Goloka as the cowherd men did."},{"class":"b50","text":" He left His home, and on the pretext of His mother’s order, He is now in Jagannāth Purī. He sends those whom He blesses to His abode, where they can behold Goloka as the cowherd men did.*"},{"class":"b123","text":" এই ভাবে গৌর-সেবা\\tকরি আমি রাত্রদিবা<br />\\tগৌরগণের এই ত’ স্বভাব ।<br />গৌর-গদাধর-পদ\\tআমার ত’ সম্পদ<br />\\tদামোদর জ্ঞানে এই ভাব ॥১১॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" ei bhāve gaura-sevā\\tkari āmi rātra-divā<br />\\tgaura-gaṇera ei ta’ svabhāva<br />gaura-gadādhara-pada\\tāmāra ta’ sampada<br />\\tdāmodara jñāne ei bhāva [11]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāve</span>–In this way, <span class=\\"e2\\">āmi</span>–I <span class=\\"e2\\">gaura-sevā kari</span>–serve Gaura <span class=\\"e2\\">rātra-divā</span>–night and day. <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ta’</span>–This [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">svabhāva</span>–the nature <span class=\\"e2\\">gaura-gaṇera</span>–of Gaura’s associates. <span class=\\"e2\\">gaura-gadādhara-pada</span>–The feet of Gaura and Gadādhar [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">āmāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ta’</span>–my <span class=\\"e2\\">sampada</span>–wealth. <span class=\\"e2\\">dāmodara</span>–Svarūp Dāmodar <span class=\\"e2\\">jñāne</span>–understands <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span>–this <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāva</span>–mood."},{"class":"b55","text":" In this way, I serve Gaura night and day. This is the nature of Gaura’s associates. The feet of Gaura and Gadādhar are my wealth. Svarūp Dāmodar understands this mood."},{"class":"b55","text":" *<span class=\\"e3\\">Śrīmad Bhāgavatam</span> (10.28) describes that Nanda Mahārāj was once captured by the attendants of Varuṇa while bathing in the River Yamunā. After Kṛṣṇa rescued Nanda Mahārāj from Varuṇa’s abode, Nanda Mahārāj described both Varuṇa’s majesty and Varuṇa’s reverence for Kṛṣṇa to the cowherd men, who under the cover of yogamāyā were amazed that Kṛṣṇa was the Supreme Lord. They then wondered whether Kṛṣṇa would ever show them His abode in the spiritual world. Knowing that the cowherd men were unaware of their own supreme fortune of already being in the expansion of His personal abode on earth, Gokula, Kṛṣṇa fulfilled their desire. He briefly removed them from Gokula, showed them that Goloka, His abode in the spiritual world, is above both Brahmaloka and Vaikuṇṭha, and then revealed Himself in Goloka being worshipped by the personified Vedas. As the cowherd men rejoiced in astonishment, Kṛṣṇa effortlessly returned them to Gokula."}]},{"title":"The Journey of the Soul","paragraphs":[{"class":"b46","text":"\\r"},{"class":"b58","text":" Chapter Six"},{"class":"b120","text":" জীব-গতি"},{"class":"b121","text":" Jīva-gati"},{"class":"b175","text":" The Journey of the Soul"},{"class":"b176","text":" জীব ও কৃষ্ণ"},{"class":"b177","text":" jīva o kṛṣṇa"},{"class":"b70","text":" The soul and Kṛṣṇa"},{"class":"b97","text":" চিৎকণ জীব, কৃষ্ণ চিন্ময় ভাস্কর ।<br />নিত্যকৃষ্ণ দেখি’ কৃষ্ণে করেন আদর ॥১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" chit-kaṇa jīva, kṛṣṇa chinmaya bhāskara<br />nitya-kṛṣṇa dekhi’ kṛṣṇe karena ādara [1]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">jīva</span>–The soul [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">chit-kaṇa</span>–a spiritual spark, [and]<span class=\\"e2\\"> kṛṣṇa</span>–Kṛṣṇa [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">chinmaya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāskara</span>–the spiritual sun. <span class=\\"e2\\">dekhi’</span>–Seeing<span class=\\"e2\\"> nitya-kṛṣṇa</span>–eternal Kṛṣṇa, <span class=\\"e2\\">ādara karena</span>–the soul adores <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇe</span>–Kṛṣṇa."},{"class":"b71","text":" The soul is a spiritual spark, and Kṛṣṇa is the spiritual sun. Seeing eternal Kṛṣṇa, the soul adores Him."},{"class":"b176","text":" মায়াগ্রস্ত জীব"},{"class":"b177","text":" māyā-grasta jīva"},{"class":"b70","text":" The soul bound by Māyā"},{"class":"b97","text":" কৃষ্ণ-বহির্ম্মুখ হঞা ভোগ বাঞ্ছা করে ।<br />নিকটস্থ মায়া তারে জাপটিয়া ধরে ॥২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kṛṣṇa-bahirmukha hañā bhoga vāñchhā kare<br />nikaṭastha māyā tāre jāpaṭiyā dhare [2]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [When] <span class=\\"e2\\">hañā</span>–souls become<span class=\\"e2\\"> kṛṣṇa-bahirmukha</span>–averse to Kṛṣṇa [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">vāñchhā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kare</span>–desire <span class=\\"e2\\">bhoga</span>–enjoyment, <span class=\\"e2\\">nikaṭastha</span>–nearby <span class=\\"e2\\">māyā</span>–Māyā <span class=\\"e2\\">jāpaṭiyā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">dhare</span>–seizes <span class=\\"e2\\">tāre</span>–them."},{"class":"b50","text":" When souls become averse to Kṛṣṇa and desire enjoyment, nearby Māyā seizes them."},{"class":"b97","text":" পিশাচী পাইলে যেন মতিচ্ছন্ন হয় ।<br />মায়াগ্রস্ত জীবের হয় সে ভাব উদয় ॥৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" piśachī pāile yena mati-chchhanna haya<br />māyā-grasta jīvera haya se bhāva udaya [3]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">piśachī</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">pāile</span>–When someone is possessed by a ghost, <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–they become <span class=\\"e2\\">mati-chchhanna</span>–bewildered. <span class=\\"e2\\">se</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāva</span>–This condition <span class=\\"e2\\">yena</span>–similarly <span class=\\"e2\\">jīvera udaya haya</span>–overtakes souls <span class=\\"e2\\">māyā-grasta</span>–bound by Māyā."},{"class":"b50","text":" When someone is possessed by a ghost, they become bewildered. This condition overtakes souls bound by Māyā."},{"class":"b97","text":" “আমি নিত্য কৃষ্ণদাস” এই কথা ভুলে<br />মায়ার নফর হঞা চিরদিন বুলে ॥৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" “āmi nitya kṛṣṇa-dāsa” ei kathā bhule<br />māyāra naphara hañā chira-dina bule [4]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">“āmi</span>–I [am] <span class=\\"e2\\">nitya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-dāsa”</span>–an eternal servant of Kṛṣṇa.” <span class=\\"e2\\">bhule</span>–Forgetting <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span>–this <span class=\\"e2\\">kathā</span>–principle, <span class=\\"e2\\">hañā</span>–souls become <span class=\\"e2\\">naphara</span>–slaves <span class=\\"e2\\">māyāra</span>–of Māyā [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">bule</span>–wander<span class=\\"e2\\"> chira-dina</span>–indefinitely."},{"class":"b50","text":" Forgetting, “I am an eternal servant of Kṛṣṇa”, souls become slaves of Māyā and wander indefinitely."},{"class":"b97","text":" কভু রাজা কভু প্রজা কভু বিপ্র শূদ্র ।<br />কভু দুঃখী কভু সুখী কভু কীট ক্ষুদ্র ॥৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kabhu rājā kabhu prajā kabhu vipra śūdra<br />kabhu duḥkhī kabhu sukhī kabhu kīṭa kṣudra [5]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [They are] <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu</span>–sometimes <span class=\\"e2\\">rājā</span>–kings, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu</span>–sometimes <span class=\\"e2\\">prajā</span>–subjects; <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu</span>–sometimes <span class=\\"e2\\">vipra</span>–brāhmaṇs, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu</span>–sometimes <span class=\\"e2\\">śūdra</span>–śūdras; <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu</span>–sometimes <span class=\\"e2\\">duḥkhī</span>–sad, <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu</span>–sometimes <span class=\\"e2\\">sukhī</span>–happy, [and sometimes] <span class=\\"e2\\">kīṭa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kṣudra</span>–insignificant ants."},{"class":"b50","text":" They are sometimes kings, and sometimes subjects; sometimes brāhmaṇs, and sometimes śūdras; sometimes sad, sometimes happy, and sometimes insignificant ants."},{"class":"b97","text":" কভু স্বর্গে, কভু মর্ত্ত্যে, নরকে বা কভু ।<br />কভু দেব, কভু দৈত্য, কভু দাস প্রভু ॥৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kabhu svarge, kabhu martye, narake vā kabhu<br />kabhu deva, kabhu daitya, kabhu dāsa prabhu [6]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [They are] <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu</span>–sometimes <span class=\\"e2\\">svarge</span>–in heaven, <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu</span>–sometimes <span class=\\"e2\\">martye</span>–on earth, <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu vā</span>–and sometimes <span class=\\"e2\\">narake</span>–in hell; <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu</span>–sometimes <span class=\\"e2\\">deva</span>–gods, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu</span>–sometimes <span class=\\"e2\\">daitya</span>–demons; <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu</span>–sometimes <span class=\\"e2\\">dāsa</span>–servants, [and sometimes] <span class=\\"e2\\">prabhu</span>–masters."},{"class":"b71","text":" They are sometimes in heaven, sometimes on earth, and sometimes in hell; sometimes gods, and sometimes demons; sometimes servants, and sometimes masters."},{"class":"b176","text":" সাধুসঙ্গে নিস্তার"},{"class":"b177","text":" sādhu-saṅge nistāra"},{"class":"b70","text":" Liberation through the association of the sādhus"},{"class":"b97","text":" এইরূপে সংসার ভ্রমিতে কোন জন ।<br />সাধুসঙ্গে নিজতত্ত্ব অবগত হন ॥৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ei-rūpe saṁsāra bhramite kona jana<br />sādhu-saṅge nija-tattva avagata hana [7]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bhramite</span>–While wandering <span class=\\"e2\\">saṁsāra</span>–throughout the world <span class=\\"e2\\">ei-rūpe</span>–in this way, <span class=\\"e2\\">kona</span>–some <span class=\\"e2\\">jana</span>–souls <span class=\\"e2\\">hana</span>–become <span class=\\"e2\\">avagata</span>–aware <span class=\\"e2\\">nija-tattva</span>–of their true nature <span class=\\"e2\\">sādhu-saṅge</span>–through association with the sādhus."},{"class":"b50","text":" While wandering throughout saṁsāra in this way, some souls become aware of their true nature by associating with the sādhus."},{"class":"b97","text":" নিজতত্ত্ব জানি’ আর সংসার না চায় ।<br />“কেন বা ভজিনু মায়া” করে হায় হায় ॥৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" nija-tattva jāni’ āra saṁsāra nā chāya<br />“kena vā bhajinu māyā” kare hāya hāya [8]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">jāni’</span>–Understanding <span class=\\"e2\\">nija-tattva</span>–their true nature, <span class=\\"e2\\">āra chāya nā</span>–they no longer desire <span class=\\"e2\\">saṁsāra</span>–the world, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">hāya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">hāya kare</span>–lament,<span class=\\"e2\\">“kena</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">vā</span>–“Why <span class=\\"e2\\">bhajinu</span>–have I been serving <span class=\\"e2\\">māyā”</span>–Māyā?”"},{"class":"b50","text":" Understanding their true nature, they no longer desire saṁsāra, and lament, “Why have I been serving Māyā?”"},{"class":"b97","text":" কেঁদে বলে, “ওহে কৃষ্ণ আমি তব দাস ।<br />তোমার চরণ ছাড়ি’ হৈল সর্ব্ব নাশ” ॥৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ke̐de bale, “ohe kṛṣṇa āmi tava dāsa<br />tomāra charaṇa chhāḍi’ haila sarva-nāśa” [9]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">ke̐de</span>–Crying, <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–they say, <span class=\\"e2\\">“ohe</span>–O <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span>–Kṛṣṇa! <span class=\\"e2\\">āmi</span>–I [am] <span class=\\"e2\\">tava</span>–Your <span class=\\"e2\\">dāsa</span>–servant, [but] <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍi’</span>–I have left <span class=\\"e2\\">tomāra</span>–Your <span class=\\"e2\\">charaṇa</span>–feet [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-nāśa haila”</span>–became utterly ruined."},{"class":"b50","text":" Crying, they say, “O Kṛṣṇa! I am Your servant, but I have left Your feet and become utterly ruined.”"},{"class":"b97","text":" কৃপা করি’ কৃষ্ণ তারে ছাড়ান সংসার ।<br />কাকুতি করিয়া কৃষ্ণে যদি ডাকে একবার ॥১০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kṛpā kari’ kṛṣṇa tāre chhāḍāna saṁsāra<br />kākuti kariyā kṛṣṇe yadi ḍāke eka-bāra [10]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span>–Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛpā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kari’</span>–mercifully <span class=\\"e2\\">tāre</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍāna</span>–causes them to leave <span class=\\"e2\\">saṁsāra</span>–the world <span class=\\"e2\\">yadi</span>–if <span class=\\"e2\\">kākuti</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kariyā</span>–they earnestly [even] <span class=\\"e2\\">eka-bāra</span>–once <span class=\\"e2\\">ḍāke</span>–call out <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇe</span>–to Kṛṣṇa."},{"class":"b50","text":" Kṛṣṇa mercifully frees souls from saṁsāra if they even once earnestly call out to Him."},{"class":"b97","text":" মায়াকে পিছনে রাখি’ কৃষ্ণপানে চায় ।<br />ভজিতে ভজিতে কৃষ্ণপাদপদ্ম পায় ॥১১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" māyāke pichhane rākhi’ kṛṣṇa-pāne chāya<br />bhajite bhajite kṛṣṇa-pāda-padma pāya [11]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">māyāke</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">pichhane</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">rākhi’</span>–Leaving Māyā behind, <span class=\\"e2\\">chāya</span>–souls hanker <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-pāne</span>–for Kṛṣṇa, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhajite</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bhajite</span>–by continuously serving [Kṛṣṇa,] <span class=\\"e2\\">pāya</span>–they reach <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-pāda-padma</span>–Kṛṣṇa’s lotus feet."},{"class":"b50","text":" Leaving Māyā behind, souls hanker for Kṛṣṇa, and by continuously serving Kṛṣṇa, they reach His lotus feet."},{"class":"b97","text":" কৃষ্ণ তারে দেন নিজ চিচ্ছক্তির বল ।<br />মায়া আকর্ষণ ছাড়ে হইয়া দুর্ব্বল ॥১২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kṛṣṇa tāre dena nija chich-chhaktira bala<br />māyā ākarṣaṇa chhāḍe ha-iyā durbala [12]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span>–Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">dena</span>–gives <span class=\\"e2\\">tāre</span>–them <span class=\\"e2\\">nija</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">chich-chhaktira</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bala</span>–the power of His spiritual energy, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">māyā</span>–Māyā, <span class=\\"e2\\">durbala ha-iyā</span>–becoming powerless, <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍe</span>–stops <span class=\\"e2\\">ākarṣaṇa</span>–attracting [them]."},{"class":"b50","text":" Kṛṣṇa gives them His spiritual power, and Māyā, becoming powerless, stops attracting them."},{"class":"b97","text":" সাধুসঙ্গে কৃষ্ণনামে—এই মাত্র চাই ।<br />সংসার জিনিতে আর কোন বস্তু নাই ॥১৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sādhu-saṅge kṛṣṇa-nāma—ei mātra chāi<br />saṁsāra jinite āra kona vastu nāi [13]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">chāi</span>–I want <span class=\\"e2\\">mātra</span>–only <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span>–this: [to chant] <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-nāma</span>–the Name of Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">sādhu-saṅge</span>–in the association of the sādhus. <span class=\\"e2\\">āra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kona</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">vastu</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāi</span>–There is no other way <span class=\\"e2\\">jinite</span>–to conquer <span class=\\"e2\\">saṁsāra</span>–the world."},{"class":"b50","text":" I want only to chant the Name of Kṛṣṇa in the association of the sādhus—there is no other way to conquer saṁsāra."},{"class":"b97","text":" সকল ভরসা ছাড়ি’ গোরাপদে আশ ।<br />করিয়া বসিয়া আছে জগাই গোরার দাস ॥১৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sakala bharasā chhāḍi’ gorā-pade āśa<br />kariyā basiyā āchhe jagāi gorāra dāsa [14]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍi’</span>–Giving up<span class=\\"e2\\"> sakala</span>–all [other] <span class=\\"e2\\">bharasā</span>–prospects, <span class=\\"e2\\">gorāra</span>–Gorā’s <span class=\\"e2\\">dāsa</span>–servant <span class=\\"e2\\">jagāi</span>–Jagāi <span class=\\"e2\\">basiyā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">āchhe</span>–sits <span class=\\"e2\\">āśa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kariyā</span>–hopefully <span class=\\"e2\\">gorā-pade</span>–at Gorā’s feet."},{"class":"b55","text":" Giving up all other prospects, Gorā’s servant Jagāi sits hopefully at Gorā’s feet."}]},{"title":"The Name is for Everyone","paragraphs":[{"class":"b46","text":"\\r"},{"class":"b58","text":" Chapter Seven"},{"class":"b120","text":" সকলের পক্ষে নাম"},{"class":"b121","text":" Sakalera Pakṣe Nāma"},{"class":"b175","text":" The Name is for Everyone"},{"class":"b176","text":" অসাধুসঙ্গে নাম হয় না"},{"class":"b177","text":" asādhu-saṅge nāma haya nā"},{"class":"b70","text":" The Name does not appear in bad association"},{"class":"b97","text":" অসাধুসঙ্গে ভাই কৃষ্ণনাম নাহি হয় ।<br />নামাক্ষর বাহিরায় বটে তবু নাম কভু নয় ॥১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" asādhu-saṅge bhāi kṛṣṇa-nāma nāhi haya<br />nāmākṣara bāhirāya baṭe tabu nāma kabhu naya [1]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāi</span>–Brother, <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-nāma</span>–the Name of Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">haya nāhi</span>–does not appear <span class=\\"e2\\">asādhu-saṅge</span>–in bad association: <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmākṣara</span>–the letters of the Name <span class=\\"e2\\">bāhirāya</span>–appear, <span class=\\"e2\\">baṭe</span>–true, <span class=\\"e2\\">tabu</span>–but <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">naya</span>–never <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–the Name."},{"class":"b50","text":" Brother, the Name of Kṛṣṇa never appears in bad association: the letters of the Name may appear, but the Name never does."},{"class":"b97","text":" কভু নামাভাস হয়, সদা নাম-অপরাধ ।<br />এ সব জানিবে ভাই কৃষ্ণভক্তির বাধ ॥২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kabhu nāmābhāsa haya, sadā nāma-aparādha<br />e saba jānibe bhāi kṛṣṇa-bhaktira bādha [2]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu</span>–Sometimes <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmābhāsa</span>–a semblance of the Name <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–appears, [but] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-aparādha</span>–offences to the Name <span class=\\"e2\\">sadā</span>–always [do]. <span class=\\"e2\\">jānibe</span>–Know <span class=\\"e2\\">e</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">saba</span>–all of these, <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāi</span>–brother, [to be] <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-bhaktira</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bādha</span>–obstacles to devotion to Kṛṣṇa."},{"class":"b71","text":" Sometimes a semblance of the Name appears, but offences to the Name always do. Know both of these, brother, to be obstacles to devotion to Kṛṣṇa."},{"class":"b176","text":" নামভজন-প্রণালী"},{"class":"b177","text":" nāma-bhajana-praṇālī"},{"class":"b70","text":" The process to serve the Name"},{"class":"b97","text":" যদি করিবে কৃষ্ণনাম সাধুসঙ্গ কর ।<br />ভুক্তি-মুক্তি-সিদ্ধি-বাঞ্ছা দূরে পরিহর ॥৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" yadi karibe kṛṣṇa-nāma sādhu-saṅga kara<br />bhukti-mukti-siddhi-vāñchhā dūre parihara [3]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">yadi</span>–If <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-nāma karibe</span>–you want to chant the Name of Kṛṣṇa, [then] <span class=\\"e2\\">sādhu-saṅga</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kara</span>–associate with sādhus [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">dūre</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">parihara</span>–leave behind <span class=\\"e2\\">bhukti-mukti-siddhi-vāñchhā</span>–the desires for enjoyment, liberation, and supernatural power."},{"class":"b50","text":" If you want to chant the Name of Kṛṣṇa, then associate with sādhus and leave behind the desires for enjoyment, liberation, and supernatural power."},{"class":"b97","text":" “দশ-অপরাধ” ত্যজ মান অপমান ।<br />অনাসক্ত্যে বিষয় ভুঞ্জ আর লহ কৃষ্ণনাম ॥৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" “daśa-aparādha” tyaja māna apamāna<br />anāsaktye viṣaya bhuñja āra laha kṛṣṇa-nāma [4]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">tyaja</span>–Give up <span class=\\"e2\\">“daśa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">aparādha”</span>–the ten offences, <span class=\\"e2\\">māna</span>–honour, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">apamāna</span>–dishonour, <span class=\\"e2\\">bhuñja</span>–interact <span class=\\"e2\\">viṣaya</span>–with the world <span class=\\"e2\\">anāsaktye</span>–with detachment, <span class=\\"e2\\">āra</span>–and <span class=\\"e2\\">laha</span>–chant <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-nāma</span>–the Name of Kṛṣṇa."},{"class":"b50","text":" Give up the ten offences, honour, and dishonour, interact with the world with detachment, and chant the Name of Kṛṣṇa."},{"class":"b97","text":" কৃষ্ণভক্তির অনুকূল সব করহ স্বীকার ।<br />কৃষ্ণভক্তির প্রতিকূল সব কর পরিহার ॥৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kṛṣṇa-bhaktira anukūla saba karaha svīkāra<br />kṛṣṇa-bhaktira pratikūla saba kara parihāra [5]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">svīkāra karaha</span>–Accept <span class=\\"e2\\">saba</span>–everything <span class=\\"e2\\">anukūla</span>–favourable <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-bhaktira</span>–to devotion to Kṛṣṇa, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">parihāra kara</span>–reject <span class=\\"e2\\">saba</span>–everything <span class=\\"e2\\">pratikūla</span>–unfavourable <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-bhaktira</span>–to devotion to Kṛṣṇa."},{"class":"b50","text":" Accept everything favourable to devotion to Kṛṣṇa, and reject everything unfavourable to devotion to Kṛṣṇa."},{"class":"b97","text":" জ্ঞানযোগচেষ্টা ছাড় আর কর্ম্মসঙ্গ ।<br />মর্কটবৈরাগ্য ত্যজ যাতে দেহরঙ্গ ॥৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" jñāna-yoga-cheṣṭā chhāḍa āra karma-saṅga<br />markaṭa-vairāgya tyaja yāte deha-raṅga [6]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍa</span>–Give up <span class=\\"e2\\">karma-saṅga</span>–attachment to material activity <span class=\\"e2\\">āra</span>–and <span class=\\"e2\\">jñāna-yoga-cheṣṭā</span>–endeavours based on knowledge and yoga. <span class=\\"e2\\">tyaja</span>–Avoid <span class=\\"e2\\">markaṭa-vairāgya</span>–‘monkey renunciation’, <span class=\\"e2\\">yāte</span>–in which [there is only] <span class=\\"e2\\">deha-raṅga</span>–bodily enjoyment."},{"class":"b50","text":" Give up attachment to material activity and endeavours based on knowledge and yoga. Avoid ‘monkey renunciation’, in which there is only bodily enjoyment."},{"class":"b97","text":" কৃষ্ণ আমায় পালে রাখে জান সর্ব্বকাল ।<br />আত্মনিবেদনদৈন্যে ঘুচাও জঞ্জাল ॥৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kṛṣṇa āmāya pāle rākhe jāna sarva-kāla<br />ātma-nivedana-dainye ghuchāo jañjāla [7]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-kāla</span>–At all times, <span class=\\"e2\\">jāna</span>–know, <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span>–“Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">rākhe</span>–protects [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">pāle</span>–maintains <span class=\\"e2\\">āmāya</span>–me.” <span class=\\"e2\\">ghuchāo</span>–Put an end <span class=\\"e2\\">jañjāla</span>–to [your] troubles <span class=\\"e2\\">ātma-nivedana-dainye</span>–through self-surrender and humility."},{"class":"b50","text":" Always know, “Kṛṣṇa protects and maintains me.” Put an end to your troubles through self-surrender and humility."},{"class":"b97","text":" সাধু পাওয়া কষ্ট বড় জীবের জানিয়া ।<br />সাধুগুরুরূপে কৃষ্ণ আইল নদীয়া ॥৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sādhu pāoyā kaṣṭa baḍa jīvera jāniyā<br />sādhu-bhakta-rūpe kṛṣṇa āilā nadīyā [8]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">jāniyā</span>–Understanding [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">pāoyā</span>–finding <span class=\\"e2\\">sādhu</span>–a pure devotee [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">baḍa kaṣṭa</span>–very difficult <span class=\\"e2\\">jīvera</span>–for a soul, <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span>–Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">āilā</span>–came <span class=\\"e2\\">nadīyā</span>–to Nadia <span class=\\"e2\\">sādhu-bhakta-rūpe</span>–in the form of a pure devotee."},{"class":"b50","text":" Understanding that it is very difficult for a soul to find a sādhu, Kṛṣṇa came to Nadia in the form of a pure devotee."},{"class":"b97","text":" গোরাপদ আশ্রয় করহ বুদ্ধিমান্ ।<br />গোরা বৈ সাধু গুরু আছে কে বা আন ॥৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" gorā-pada āśraya karaha buddhimān<br />gorā vai sādhu guru āchhe ke vā āna [9]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">buddhimān</span>–O intelligent soul,<span class=\\"e2\\"> āśraya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">karaha</span>–take shelter <span class=\\"e2\\">gorā-pada</span>–at Gorā’s feet. <span class=\\"e2\\">ke</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">vā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">āna</span>–What other <span class=\\"e2\\">sādhu</span>–sādhu [or] <span class=\\"e2\\">guru</span>–Guru <span class=\\"e2\\">āchhe</span>–is there <span class=\\"e2\\">vai</span>–besides <span class=\\"e2\\">gorā</span>–Gorā?"},{"class":"b71","text":" O intelligent soul, take shelter at Gorā’s feet. What other sādhu or Guru is there besides Gorā?"},{"class":"b176","text":" বৈরাগীর কর্ত্তব্য"},{"class":"b177","text":" vairāgīra kartavya"},{"class":"b70","text":" The duty of a renunciant"},{"class":"b97","text":" বৈরাগী ভাই গ্রাম্যকথা না শুনিবে কানে ।<br />গ্রাম্যবার্তা না কহিবে যবে মিলিবে আনে ॥১০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" vairāgī bhāi grāmya-kathā nā śunibe kāne<br />grāmya-vārtā nā kahibe yabe milibe āne [10]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāi</span>–Brother, <span class=\\"e2\\">vairāgī</span>–renunciants <span class=\\"e2\\">śunibe nā</span>–should not listen <span class=\\"e2\\">grāmya-kathā</span>–to village talk <span class=\\"e2\\">kāne</span>–with [their] ears [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">kahibe nā</span>–should not speak <span class=\\"e2\\">grāmya-vārtā</span>–about village news <span class=\\"e2\\">yabe</span>–when <span class=\\"e2\\">milibe</span>–they meet <span class=\\"e2\\">āne</span>–with others."},{"class":"b50","text":" Brother, renunciants should neither listen to village talk nor discuss village news when they meet with others."},{"class":"b97","text":" স্বপনেও না কর ভাই স্ত্রী-সম্ভাষণ ।<br />গৃহে স্ত্রী ছাড়িয়া ভাই আসিয়াছ বন ॥১১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" svapaneo nā kara bhāi strī-sambhāṣaṇa<br />gṛhe strī chhāḍiyā bhāi āsiyāchha vana [11]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāi</span>–Brother, <span class=\\"e2\\">strī-sambhāṣaṇa kara nā</span>–do not converse with women, <span class=\\"e2\\">svapaneo</span>–even in dreams. <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāi</span>–Brother, <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍiyā</span>–you have left <span class=\\"e2\\">strī</span>–women <span class=\\"e2\\">gṛhe</span>–at home [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">āsiyāchha</span>–come <span class=\\"e2\\">vana</span>–to the forest."},{"class":"b50","text":" Brother, do not converse with women, even in dreams. Brother, you have left women at home and come to the forest."},{"class":"b97","text":" যদি চাহ প্রণয় রাখিতে গৌরাঙ্গের সনে ।<br />ছোট হরিদাসের কথা থাকে যেন মনে ॥১২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" yadi chāha praṇaya rākhite gaurāṅgera sane<br />chhoṭa haridāsera kathā thāke yena mane [12]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">yadi</span>–If <span class=\\"e2\\">chāha</span>–you want <span class=\\"e2\\">rākhite</span>–to maintain [your] <span class=\\"e2\\">praṇaya</span>–love <span class=\\"e2\\">gaurāṅgera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sane</span>–for Gaurāṅga, <span class=\\"e2\\">yena</span>–then <span class=\\"e2\\">mane thāke</span>–remember <span class=\\"e2\\">kathā</span>–the story <span class=\\"e2\\">chhoṭa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haridāsera</span>–of Chhoṭa Haridās."},{"class":"b50","text":" If you want to maintain your love for Gaurāṅga, then remember the story of Chhoṭa Haridās."},{"class":"b97","text":" ভাল না খাইবে আর ভাল না পরিবে ।<br />হৃদয়েতে রাধাকৃষ্ণ সর্ব্বদা সেবিবে ॥১৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" bhāla nā khāibe āra bhāla nā paribe<br />hṛdayete rādhā-kṛṣṇa sarvadā sevibe [13]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">khāibe nā</span>–Do not eat <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāla</span>–fancy, <span class=\\"e2\\">āra</span>–and <span class=\\"e2\\">paribe nā</span>–do not dress <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāla</span>–fancy. <span class=\\"e2\\">sarvadā</span>–Always <span class=\\"e2\\">sevibe</span>–serve <span class=\\"e2\\">rādhā-kṛṣṇa</span>–Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">hṛdayete</span>–within [your] heart."},{"class":"b50","text":" Do not eat fancy food, and do not wear fancy clothes. Always serve Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa within your heart."},{"class":"b97","text":" বড় হরিদাসের ন্যায় কৃষ্ণনাম বলিবে বদনে ।<br />অষ্টকাল রাধাকৃষ্ণ সেবিবে কুঞ্জবনে ॥১৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" baḍa haridāsera nyāya kṛṣṇa-nāma balibe vadane<br />aṣṭa-kāla rādhā-kṛṣṇa sevibe kuñja-vane [14]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">vadane balibe</span>–Loudly chant <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-nāma</span>–the Name of Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">nyāya</span>–like <span class=\\"e2\\">baḍa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haridāsera</span>–Haridās Ṭhākur, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">sevibe</span>–serve <span class=\\"e2\\">rādhā-kṛṣṇa</span>–Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">kuñja-vane</span>–in the groves <span class=\\"e2\\">aṣṭa-kāla</span>–twenty-four hours [a day]."},{"class":"b71","text":" Loudly chant the Name of Kṛṣṇa like Haridās Ṭhākur, and serve Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa in the groves of Vraja twenty-four hours a day."},{"class":"b176","text":" গৃহস্থ ও বৈরাগীর প্রতি আদেশ"},{"class":"b177","text":" gṛhastha o vairāgīra prati ādeśa"},{"class":"b70","text":" Instructions for householders and renunciants"},{"class":"b97","text":" গৃহস্থ বৈরাগী দুঁহে বলে গোরারায় ।<br />“দেখ ভাই নাম বিনা যেন দিন নাহি যায়” ॥১৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" gṛhastha vairāgī du̐he bale gorā-rāya<br />“dekha bhāi nāma vinā yena dina nāhi yāya” [15]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">gorā-rāya</span>–Gorā Rāy <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–says <span class=\\"e2\\">du̐he</span>–to both <span class=\\"e2\\">gṛhastha</span>–householders [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">vairāgī</span>–renunciants, <span class=\\"e2\\">“bhāi</span>–Brothers, <span class=\\"e2\\">dekha yena</span>–see to it that <span class=\\"e2\\">dina</span>–a day <span class=\\"e2\\">yāya nāhi</span>–does not pass <span class=\\"e2\\">vinā</span>–without [chanting] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma”</span>–the Name.”"},{"class":"b50","text":" Gorā Rāy says to both householders and renunciants, “Brothers, see to it that a day does not pass without chanting the Name.”"},{"class":"b97","text":" বহু-অঙ্গ সাধনে ভাই নাহি প্রয়োজন ।<br />কৃষ্ণনামাশ্রয়ে শুদ্ধ করহ জীবন ॥১৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" bahu-aṅga sādhane bhāi nāhi prayojana<br />kṛṣṇa-nāmāśraye śuddha karaha jīvana [16]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāi</span>–Brother, <span class=\\"e2\\">prayojana nāhi</span>–there is no need <span class=\\"e2\\">sādhane</span>–to perform <span class=\\"e2\\">bahu-aṅga</span>–many practices: <span class=\\"e2\\">śuddha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">karaha</span>–purify [your] <span class=\\"e2\\">jīvana</span>–life <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-nāmāśraye</span>–in the shelter of Kṛṣṇa’s Name."},{"class":"b50","text":" Brother, there is no need to perform many practices: purify your life in the shelter of Kṛṣṇa’s Name."},{"class":"b97","text":" বদ্ধ জীবে কৃপা করি’ কৃষ্ণ হইল নাম ।<br />কলিজীবে দয়া করি’ কৃষ্ণ হইল গৌরধাম ॥১৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" baddha jīve kṛpā kari’ kṛṣṇa ha-ila nāma<br />kali-jīve dayā kari’ kṛṣṇa ha-ila gaura-dhāma [17]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛpā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kari’</span>–Being merciful <span class=\\"e2\\">baddha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">jīve</span>–to the conditioned souls, <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span>–Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-ila</span>–appeared <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–as [His] Name, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">dayā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kari’</span>–being compassionate <span class=\\"e2\\">kali-jīve</span>–to the souls of Kali-yuga, <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span>–Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-ila</span>–appeared <span class=\\"e2\\">gaura-dhāma</span>–as Gaura."},{"class":"b50","text":" Being merciful to the conditioned souls, Kṛṣṇa appeared as His Name, and being compassionate to the souls of Kali-yuga, He appeared as Gaura."},{"class":"b97","text":" একান্ত-সরল-ভাবে ভজ গৌরজন ।<br />তবে ত’ পাইবে ভাই শ্রীকৃষ্ণচরণ ॥১৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ekānta-sarala-bhāve bhaja gaura-jana<br />tabe ta’ pāibe bhāi śrī-kṛṣṇa-charaṇa [18]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaja</span>–Serve <span class=\\"e2\\">gaura-jana</span>–Gaura’s devotees <span class=\\"e2\\">ekānta-sarala-bhāve</span>–with perfect sincerity, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">tabe</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ta’</span>–then, <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāi</span>–brother, <span class=\\"e2\\">pāibe</span>–you will attain <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-kṛṣṇa-charaṇa</span>–Śrī Kṛṣṇa’s feet."},{"class":"b50","text":" Serve Gaura’s devotees with perfect sincerity, and then, brother, you will reach Śrī Kṛṣṇa’s feet."},{"class":"b97","text":" গৌরজন সঙ্গ কর গৌরাঙ্গ বলিয়া ।<br />‘হরে কৃষ্ণ’ নাম বল নাচিয়া নাচিয়া ॥১৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" gaura-jana saṅga kara gaurāṅga baliyā<br />‘hare kṛṣṇa’ nāma bala nāchiyā nāchiyā [19]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">baliyā</span>–Chant <span class=\\"e2\\">gaurāṅga</span>–‘Gaurāṅga’ [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">saṅga</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kara</span>–associate [with] <span class=\\"e2\\">gaura-jana</span>–Gaura’s devotees. <span class=\\"e2\\">bala</span>–Chant <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–the Names <span class=\\"e2\\">‘hare</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa’</span>–‘Hare Kṛṣṇa’ [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāchiyā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāchiyā</span>–dance and dance."},{"class":"b50","text":" Chant ‘Gaurāṅga’ and associate with Gaura’s devotees. Chant ‘Hare Kṛṣṇa’ and dance."},{"class":"b97","text":" অচিরে পাইবে ভাই নামপ্রেমধন ।<br />যাহা বিলাইতে প্রভুর নদে আগমন ॥২০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" achire pāibe bhāi nāma-prema-dhana<br />yāhā bilāite prabhura nade āgamana [20]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāi</span>–Brother,<span class=\\"e2\\"> achire</span>–soon <span class=\\"e2\\">pāibe</span>–you will attain <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-prema-dhana</span>–the Name and the wealth of divine love, <span class=\\"e2\\">yāhā</span>–which <span class=\\"e2\\">prabhura</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nade</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">āgamana</span>–the Lord came to Nadia <span class=\\"e2\\">bilāite</span>–to distribute."},{"class":"b50","text":" Brother, soon you will attain the Name and the wealth of divine love, which the Lord came to Nadia to distribute."},{"class":"b97","text":" প্রভুর কুন্দলে জগা কেঁদে কেঁদে বলে ।<br />নাম ভজ নাম গাও ভকত সকল ॥২১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" prabhura kundale jagā ke̐de ke̐de bale<br />nāma bhaja nāma gāo bhakata sakale [21]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">ke̐de</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ke̐de</span>–Crying, <span class=\\"e2\\">prabhura</span>–the Lord’s <span class=\\"e2\\">kundale</span>–angry <span class=\\"e2\\">jagā</span>–Jagā <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–says, <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakata</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sakale</span>–“O devotees! <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaja</span>–Serve <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–the Name! <span class=\\"e2\\">gāo</span>–Chant <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–the Name!”"},{"class":"b55","text":" Crying, the Lord’s angry Jagā says, “O devotees! Serve the Name and chant the Name!”"}]},{"title":"Give up Deceit","paragraphs":[{"class":"b46","text":"\\r"},{"class":"b58","text":" Chapter Eight"},{"class":"b120","text":" কুটীনাটী ছাড়"},{"class":"b121","text":" Kuṭīnāṭī Chhāḍa"},{"class":"b175","text":" Give up Deceit"},{"class":"b176","text":" সরল মনে গোরাভজন"},{"class":"b177","text":" sarala mane gorā-bhajana"},{"class":"b70","text":" Serving Gorā with a sincere heart"},{"class":"b97","text":" গোরা ভজ, গোরা ভজ, গোরা ভজ ভাই ।<br />গোরা বিনা এ জগতে গুরু আর নাই ॥১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" gorā bhaja, gorā bhaja, gorā bhaja bhāi<br />gorā vinā e jagate guru āra nāi [1]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaja</span>–Serve <span class=\\"e2\\">gorā</span>–Gorā! <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaja</span>–Serve <span class=\\"e2\\">gorā</span>–Gorā! <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaja</span>–Serve <span class=\\"e2\\">gorā</span>–Gorā! <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāi</span>–Brother, <span class=\\"e2\\">nāi</span>–there is no <span class=\\"e2\\">guru</span>–Guru <span class=\\"e2\\">e</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">jagate</span>–in this world <span class=\\"e2\\">vinā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">āra</span>–other than <span class=\\"e2\\">gorā</span>–Gorā."},{"class":"b50","text":" Serve Gorā! Serve Gorā! Serve Gorā! Brother, there is no Guru in this world other than Gorā."},{"class":"b97","text":" যদি ভজিবে গোরা সরল কর নিজ মন ।<br />কুটীনাটিই ছাড়ি’ ভজ গোরার চরণ ॥২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" yadi bhajibe gorā sarala kara nija mana<br />kuṭīnāṭi chhāḍi’ bhaja gorāra charaṇa [2]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">yadi</span>–If <span class=\\"e2\\">bhajibe</span>–you want to serve <span class=\\"e2\\">gorā</span>–Gorā, <span class=\\"e2\\">kara</span>–make <span class=\\"e2\\">nija</span>–your <span class=\\"e2\\">mana</span>–heart <span class=\\"e2\\">sarala</span>–sincere. <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍi’</span>–Give up <span class=\\"e2\\">kuṭīnāṭi</span>–deceit [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaja</span>–serve <span class=\\"e2\\">gorāra</span>–Gorā’s <span class=\\"e2\\">charaṇa</span>–feet."},{"class":"b50","text":" If you want to serve Gorā, make your heart sincere. Give up deceit and serve Gorā’s feet."},{"class":"b97","text":" মনের কথা গোরা জানে ফাঁকি কেমনে দিবে ।<br />সরল হলে গোরার শিক্ষা বুঝিয়া লইবে ॥৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" manera kathā gorā jāne phā̐ki kemane dibe<br />sarala hale gorāra śikṣā bujhiyā la-ibe [3]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">gorā</span>–Gorā <span class=\\"e2\\">jāne</span>–knows [your] <span class=\\"e2\\">manera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kathā</span>–thoughts. <span class=\\"e2\\">kemane</span>–How <span class=\\"e2\\">phā̐ki dibe</span>–will you cheat [Him]? <span class=\\"e2\\">sarala</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">hale</span>–When you are sincere, <span class=\\"e2\\">bujhiyā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">la-ibe</span>–you will understand <span class=\\"e2\\">gorāra</span>–Gorā’s <span class=\\"e2\\">śikṣā</span>–teachings."},{"class":"b50","text":" Gorā knows your thoughts, so how will you cheat Him? When you are sincere, you will understand Gorā’s teachings."},{"class":"b97","text":" আনের মন রাখিতে গিয়া আপনাকে দিবে ফাঁকি ।<br />মনের কথা জানে গোরা কেমনে হৃদয় ঢাকি ॥৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ānera mana rākhite giyā āpanāke dibe phā̐ki<br />manera kathā jāne gorā kemane hṛdaya ḍhāki [4]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">giyā</span>–Going <span class=\\"e2\\">rākhite</span>–to satisfy <span class=\\"e2\\">mana</span>–the minds <span class=\\"e2\\">ānera</span>–of others, <span class=\\"e2\\">phā̐ki dibe</span>–you will cheat <span class=\\"e2\\">āpanāke</span>–yourself. <span class=\\"e2\\">gorā</span>–Gorā <span class=\\"e2\\">jāne</span>–knows [your] <span class=\\"e2\\">manera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kathā</span>–thoughts, [so] <span class=\\"e2\\">kemane</span>–how <span class=\\"e2\\">ḍhāki</span>–will you hide [your] <span class=\\"e2\\">hṛdaya</span>–heart [from Him]?"},{"class":"b50","text":" If you go to satisfy the minds of others, you will only cheat yourself. Gorā knows your thoughts, so how will you hide your heart from Him?"},{"class":"b97","text":" গোরা বলে, “আমার মত করহ চরিত ।<br />আমার আজ্ঞা পালন কর চাহ যদি হিত” ॥৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" gorā bale, “āmāra mata karaha charita<br />āmāra ājñā pālana kara chāha yadi hita” [5]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">gorā</span>–Gorā <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–says, <span class=\\"e2\\">“charita karaha</span>–“Behave <span class=\\"e2\\">āmāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">mata</span>–like Me [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">pālana</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kara</span>–follow <span class=\\"e2\\">āmāra</span>–My <span class=\\"e2\\">ājñā</span>–instructions <span class=\\"e2\\">yadi</span>–if <span class=\\"e2\\">chāha</span>–you want <span class=\\"e2\\">hita”</span>–good fortune.”"},{"class":"b71","text":" Gorā says, “Behave like Me and follow My instructions if you want good fortune.”"},{"class":"b176","text":" কপট ভজন"},{"class":"b177","text":" kapaṭa bhajana"},{"class":"b70","text":" Deceitful service"},{"class":"b97","text":" “গোরার আমি, গোরার আমি” মুখে বলিলে না চলে ।<br />গোরার আচার, গোরার বিচার লইলে ফল ফলে ॥৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" “gorāra āmi, gorāra āmi” mukhe balile nāhi chale<br />gorāra āchāra, gorāra vichāra la-ile phala phale [6]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">mukhe</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">balile</span>–You may say aloud, <span class=\\"e2\\">“āmi</span>–I [am] <span class=\\"e2\\">gorāra</span>–Gorā’s. <span class=\\"e2\\">āmi</span>–I [am] <span class=\\"e2\\">gorāra”</span>–Gorā’s”, [but this] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāhi</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">chale</span>–does not do. <span class=\\"e2\\">la-ile</span>–When you follow <span class=\\"e2\\">gorāra</span>–Gorā’s <span class=\\"e2\\">āchāra</span>–practices [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">gorāra</span>–Gorā’s <span class=\\"e2\\">vichāra</span>–conception, [then] <span class=\\"e2\\">phala</span>–the result <span class=\\"e2\\">phale</span>–manifests."},{"class":"b50","text":" Just saying, “I am Gorā’s! I am Gorā’s!” does not do. Only when you follow Gorā’s practices and Gorā’s conception will you get the proper result."},{"class":"b97","text":" লোক দেখান গোরা ভজা তিলক মাত্র ধরি ।<br />গোপনেতে অত্যাচার গোরা ধরে চুরি ॥৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" loka dekhāna gorā bhajā tilaka mātra dhari’<br />gopanete atyāchāra gorā dhare churi [7]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">loka-dekhāna</span>–You show the world [you] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhajā</span>–serve <span class=\\"e2\\">gorā</span>–Gorā <span class=\\"e2\\">mātra</span>–simply <span class=\\"e2\\">dhari’</span>–by wearing <span class=\\"e2\\">tilaka</span>–tilak [but] <span class=\\"e2\\">gopanete</span>–secretly you <span class=\\"e2\\">atyāchāra</span>–misbehave. <span class=\\"e2\\">gorā</span>–Gorā <span class=\\"e2\\">dhare</span>–will catch [you, you] <span class=\\"e2\\">churi</span>–thief!"},{"class":"b50","text":" You show the world you serve Gorā simply by wearing tilak but secretly you misbehave. Gorā will catch you, you thief!"},{"class":"b97","text":" অধঃপতন হবে ভাই কৈলে কুটীনাটি ।<br />নাম-অপরাধে তোমার ভজন হবে মাটি ॥৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" adhaḥ-patana habe bhāi kaile kuṭīnāṭi<br />nāma-aparādhe tomāra bhajana habe māṭi [8]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāi</span>–Brother, <span class=\\"e2\\">kuṭīnāṭi</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kaile</span>–if you act deceitfully <span class=\\"e2\\">adhaḥ-patana</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">habe</span>–you will fall down. <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-aparādhe</span>–Because of offences to the Name <span class=\\"e2\\">tomāra</span>–your <span class=\\"e2\\">bhajana</span>–service <span class=\\"e2\\">māṭi habe</span>–will be ruined."},{"class":"b50","text":" Brother, if you act deceitfully, you will fall down. Because of offences to the Name, your service will be ruined."},{"class":"b97","text":" নাম লঞা যে করে পাপ হয় অপরাধ ।<br />এর মত ভক্তি আর আছে কিবা বাধ ?॥৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" nāma lañā ye kare pāpa haya aparādha<br />era mata bhakti āra āchhe kibā bādha? [9]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">ye</span>–Those who <span class=\\"e2\\">lañā</span>–chant <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–the Name [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">pāpa kare</span>–sin <span class=\\"e2\\">aparādha haya</span>–commit offence. <span class=\\"e2\\">kibā āra</span>–What greater <span class=\\"e2\\">bādha</span>–obstacle <span class=\\"e2\\">āchhe</span>–is there <span class=\\"e2\\">era</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">mata</span>–than such <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakti</span>–‘devotion’?"},{"class":"b50","text":" Those who chant the Name and sin commit offence. What greater obstacle is there than such ‘devotion’?"},{"class":"b97","text":" নাম করিতে কষ্ট নাই নাম সহজ ধন ।<br />ওষ্ঠ-স্পন্দ-মাত্রে হয় নামের কীর্ত্তন ।<br />তাহাও না হয় যদি হয় নামের স্মরণ ॥১০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" nāma karite kaṣṭa nāi nāma sahaja dhana<br />oṣṭha-spanda-mātre haya nāmera kīrtana<br />tāhāo nā haya yadi haya nāmera smaraṇa [10]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">nāi</span>–There is no <span class=\\"e2\\">kaṣṭa</span>–difficulty <span class=\\"e2\\">karite</span>–in chanting <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–the Name. <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–The Name [is everyone’s] <span class=\\"e2\\">sahaja</span>–natural <span class=\\"e2\\">dhana</span>–wealth. <span class=\\"e2\\">oṣṭha-spanda-mātre</span>–Simply by moving your lips, <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kīrtana haya</span>–you chant the Name. <span class=\\"e2\\">yadi</span>–If <span class=\\"e2\\">haya nā</span>–you cannot do <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhāo</span>–even that, [then] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">smaraṇa haya</span>–you can remember the Name."},{"class":"b50","text":" The Name is everyone’s natural wealth, and chanting the Name is not difficult: simply by moving your lips you can chant the Name. If you cannot do even that, then you can remember the Name."},{"class":"b97","text":" তুণ্ডবন্ধে চিত্তভ্রংশে শ্রবণ তবু হয় ।<br />সর্ব্বপাপ ক্ষয়ে জীবের মুখ্য ফলোদয় ॥১১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" tuṇḍa-bandhe chita-bhraṁśe śravaṇa tabu haya<br />sarva-pāpa kṣaye jīvera mukhya phalodaya [11]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">tuṇḍa-bandhe</span>–The mute [and]<span class=\\"e2\\"> chita-bhraṁśe</span>–the deranged <span class=\\"e2\\">tabu</span>–still <span class=\\"e2\\">śravaṇa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–hear [the Name, and this alone] <span class=\\"e2\\">kṣaye</span>–destroys <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-pāpa</span>–all sins [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">jīvera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">mukhya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">phalodaya</span>–gives rise to the true fortune of the soul."},{"class":"b50","text":" Even the mute and the deranged can still hear the Name, and this alone destroys all sins and gives rise to the true fortune of the soul."},{"class":"b97","text":" বহুজন্ম অর্চ্চনেতে এই ফল ধরে ।<br />কৃষ্ণনাম নিরন্তর তুণ্ডে নৃত্য করে ॥১২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" bahu-janma archchanete ei phala dhare<br />krṣṇa-nāma nirantara tuṇḍe nṛtya kare [12]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bahu-janma</span>–Many lifetimes <span class=\\"e2\\">archanete</span>–of Deity worship <span class=\\"e2\\">dhare</span>–bear <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">phala</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">dhare</span>–this result: <span class=\\"e2\\">krṣṇa-nāma</span>–the Name of Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">nirantara</span>–constantly <span class=\\"e2\\">nṛtya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kare</span>–dances <span class=\\"e2\\">tuṇḍe</span>–in [your] mouth."},{"class":"b50","text":" Many lifetimes of Deity worship bear this result: the Name of Kṛṣṇa constantly dances in your mouth."},{"class":"b97","text":" কর্ম্মজ্ঞানযোগাদির সেই শক্তি নহে ।<br />বিধিভঙ্গদোষে ফলহীন শাস্ত্রে কহে ॥১৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" karma-jñāna-yogādira sei śakti nahe<br />vidhi-bhaṅga-doṣe phala-hīna śāstre kahe [13]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">śāstre</span>–The scriptures <span class=\\"e2\\">kahe</span>–say [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">karma-jñāna-yogādira nahe</span>–worldly action, knowledge, yoga, and so on, do not have <span class=\\"e2\\">sei</span>–such <span class=\\"e2\\">śakti</span>–power, [and that] <span class=\\"e2\\">vidhi-bhaṅga-doṣe</span>–by the fault of breaking [their] rules, [they become] <span class=\\"e2\\">phala-hīna</span>–fruitless."},{"class":"b50","text":" The scriptures say that worldly action, knowledge, yoga, and so on, do not have such power, and that when the rules for practising them are broken, they bear no fruit at all."},{"class":"b97","text":" সে সব ছাড় ভাই নাম কর সার ।<br />অতি অল্পদিনে তবে জিনিবে সংসার ॥১৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" se saba chhāḍa bhāi nāma kara sāra<br />ati alpa-dine tabe jinibe saṁsāra [14]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāi</span>–Brother, <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍa</span>–leave behind <span class=\\"e2\\">se</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">saba</span>–all of them [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma sāra kara</span>–accept the Name as all-in-all. <span class=\\"e2\\">tabe</span>–Then <span class=\\"e2\\">jinibe</span>–you will conquer <span class=\\"e2\\">saṁsāra</span>–the world <span class=\\"e2\\">ati</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">alpa-dine</span>–very soon."},{"class":"b71","text":" Brother, leave them all behind and accept the Name as all-in-all. Then you will conquer saṁsāra very soon."},{"class":"b176","text":" কবি কর্ণপূর"},{"class":"b177","text":" kavi karṇapūra"},{"class":"b70","text":" Kavi Karṇapūr"},{"class":"b97","text":" ধন্য কবি কর্ণপূর স্বগ্রামনিবাসী ।<br />নামের মহিমা কিছু রাখিল প্রকাশি’ ॥১৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" dhanya kavi karṇapūra sva-grāma-nivāsī<br />nāmera mahimā kichhu rākhila prakāśi’ [15]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">dhanya</span>–The glorious <span class=\\"e2\\">kavi</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">karṇapūra</span>–Kavi Karṇapūr [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">sva-grāma-nivāsī</span>–a resident of my village. <span class=\\"e2\\">prakāśi’ rākhila</span>–He revealed and recorded <span class=\\"e2\\">kichhu</span>–some <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmera</span>–of the Name’s <span class=\\"e2\\">mahimā</span>–glories."},{"class":"b50","text":" The glorious Kavi Karṇapūr is a resident of my village. He revealed and recorded some of the Name’s glories."},{"class":"b97","text":" গৌর যারে কৃপা করে, বিশ্বে সেই ধন্য ।<br />সপ্তবর্ষে বয়সে হৈল মহাকবি মান্য ॥১৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" gaura yāre kṛpā kare, viśve sei dhanya<br />sapta-varṣe vayase haila mahākavi mānya [16]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sei yāre</span>–Those whom <span class=\\"e2\\">gaura</span>–Gaura <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛpā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kare</span>–blesses [become] <span class=\\"e2\\">dhanya</span>–glorious <span class=\\"e2\\">viśve</span>–throughout the world, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">mānya haila</span>–Kavi Karṇapūr was honoured <span class=\\"e2\\">mahākavi</span>–as a great poet <span class=\\"e2\\">sapta-varṣe</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">vayase</span>–at the age of seven."},{"class":"b50","text":" Those whom Gaura blesses become glorious throughout the world, and Kavi Karṇapūr was honoured as a great poet when he was only seven years old."},{"class":"b97","text":" ধন্য শিবানন্দ কবি-কর্ণপূর-পিতা ।<br />মোরে বাল্যে শিখাইল ভাগবত-গীতা ॥১৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" dhanya śivānanda kavi-karṇapūra-pitā<br />more bālye śikhāila bhāgavata-gītā [17]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">dhanya</span>–The glorious <span class=\\"e2\\">śivānanda</span>–Śivānanda Sen, <span class=\\"e2\\">kavi-karṇapūra-pitā</span>–Kavi Karṇapūr’s father, <span class=\\"e2\\">śikhāila</span>–taught <span class=\\"e2\\">more</span>–me <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāgavata-gītā</span>–<span class=\\"e33\\">Śrīmad Bhāgavatam</span> and <span class=\\"e33\\">Bhagavad-gītā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bālye</span>–in my youth."},{"class":"b50","text":" The glorious Śivānanda Sen, Kavi Karṇapūr’s father, taught me <span class=\\"e3\\">Śrīmad Bhāgavatam</span> and <span class=\\"e3\\">Bhagavad-gītā</span> in my youth."},{"class":"b97","text":" নদীয়া লইয়া মোরে রাখে প্রভুপদে ।<br />শিবানন্দ ত্রাতা মোর সম্পদে বিপদে ॥১৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" nadīyā la-iyā more rākhe prabhu-pade<br />śivānanda trātā mora sampade vipade [18]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">la-iyā</span>–Śivānanda brought <span class=\\"e2\\">more</span>–me <span class=\\"e2\\">nadīyā</span>–to Nadia [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">rākhe</span>–kept [me] <span class=\\"e2\\">prabhu-pade</span>–at the feet of the Lord. <span class=\\"e2\\">śivānanda</span>–Śivānanda [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">mora</span>–my <span class=\\"e2\\">trātā</span>–saviour, <span class=\\"e2\\">sampade</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">vipade</span>–in good fortune and in bad."},{"class":"b50","text":" Śivānanda brought me to Nadia and kept me at the feet of the Lord. He is my saviour, in good fortune and in bad."},{"class":"b97","text":" তার ঘরে ভোগ রান্ধি’ পাক-শিক্ষা হইল ।<br />ভাল পাক করি’ শ্রীগৌরাঙ্গ-সেবা কৈল ॥১৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" tāra ghare bhoga rāndhi’ pāka-śikṣā haila<br />bhāla pāka kari’ śrī-gaurāṅga-sevā kaila [19]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">pāka</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">śikṣā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haila</span>–I learned to cook [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhoga</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">rāndhi’</span>–prepared offerings <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ghare</span>–in his home, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">pāka</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kari’</span>–by cooking <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāla</span>–well, <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-gaurāṅga-sevā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kaila</span>–I served Śrī Gaurāṅga."},{"class":"b50","text":" I learned to cook and prepare offerings in his home, and by cooking well, I served Śrī Gaurāṅga."},{"class":"b97","text":" জগাই বলে, “সাধুসঙ্গে দিন যায় যার ।<br />সেই মাত্র নামাশ্রয় করে নিরন্তর” ॥২০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" jagāi bale, “sādhu-saṅge dina yāya yāra<br />sei mātra nāmāśraya kare nirantara” [20]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">jagāi</span>–Jagāi <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–says, <span class=\\"e2\\">“mātra</span>–“Only <span class=\\"e2\\">sei yāra</span>–those whose <span class=\\"e2\\">dina</span>–days <span class=\\"e2\\">yāya</span>–pass <span class=\\"e2\\">sādhu-saṅge</span>–in the association of sādhus <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmāśraya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kare</span>–take shelter of the Name <span class=\\"e2\\">nirantara”</span>–constantly.”"},{"class":"b55","text":" Jagāi says, “Only those whose days pass in the association of sādhus take shelter of the Name constantly.”"}]},{"title":"Proper Renunciation","paragraphs":[{"class":"b46","text":"\\r"},{"class":"b58","text":" Chapter Nine"},{"class":"b120","text":" যুক্তবৈরাগ্য"},{"class":"b121","text":" Yukta-vairāgya"},{"class":"b175","text":" Proper Renunciation"},{"class":"b176","text":" বৈরাগ্য দুই প্রকার—ফল্গু ও যুক্ত"},{"class":"b177","text":" vairāgya dui prakāra—phalgu o yukta"},{"class":"b70","text":" There are two types of renunciation: false and proper"},{"class":"b97","text":" একদিন জিজ্ঞাসিলেন গোসাঞি সনাতন ।<br />“‘যুক্ত বৈরাগ্য’ কারে বলে প্রভু করুন বর্ণন ॥১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" eka-dina jijñāsilena gosāñi sanātana<br />“‘yukta vairāgya’ kāre bale prabhu karuna varṇana [1]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">eka-dina</span>–One day, <span class=\\"e2\\">sanātana gosāñi</span>–Sanātan Goswāmī <span class=\\"e2\\">jijñāsilena</span>–asked, <span class=\\"e2\\">“kare</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–“What is <span class=\\"e2\\">‘yukta</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">vairāgya’</span>–proper renunciation? <span class=\\"e2\\">prabhu</span>–O Lord, <span class=\\"e2\\">varṇana karuna</span>–please explain [it]."},{"class":"b50","text":" One day, Sanātan Goswāmī asked, “What is proper renunciation? O Lord, please explain it."},{"class":"b97","text":" মায়াবাদী বলে, ‘সব কাকবিষ্ঠাসম ।<br />বিষয় জানিলে ন্যাসী হয় সর্ব্বোত্তম’ ॥২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" māyāvādī bale, ‘saba kāka-viṣṭhā-sama<br />viṣaya jānile nyāsī haya sarvottama’ [2]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">māyāvādī</span>–Illusionists <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–say, <span class=\\"e2\\">‘nyāsī jānile</span>–‘If a sannyāsī considers <span class=\\"e2\\">saba viṣaya</span>–everything material <span class=\\"e2\\">kāka-viṣṭhā-sama</span>–to be equal to crow’s stool, [then] <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–they are <span class=\\"e2\\">sarvottama’</span>–the best of all.’"},{"class":"b50","text":" “Māyāvādīs say, ‘If a sannyāsī considers everything material to be crow’s stool, then they are the best of men.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" বৈষ্ণবের কি কর্ত্তব্য জানিতে ইচ্ছা করি ।<br />কৃপা করি’ আজ্ঞা কর আজ্ঞা শিরে ধরি” ॥৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" vaiṣṇavera ki kartavya jānite ichchhā kari<br />kṛpā kari’ ājñā kara ājñā śire dhari” [3]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">ichchhā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kari</span>–I want <span class=\\"e2\\">jānite</span>–to know <span class=\\"e2\\">ki</span>–what [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">kartavya</span>–the duties <span class=\\"e2\\">vaiṣṇavera</span>–of a Vaiṣṇava. <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛpā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kari’</span>–Mercifully <span class=\\"e2\\">ājñā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kara</span>–instruct [me]. <span class=\\"e2\\">dhari</span>–I hold [your] <span class=\\"e2\\">ājñā”</span>–instructions <span class=\\"e2\\">śire</span>–on [my] head.”"},{"class":"b50","text":" “I want to know the duties of a Vaiṣṇava. Please instruct me, so I can hold Your instructions on my head.”"},{"class":"b97","text":" প্রভু বলে, “বৈরাগ্য হয় দুই ত প্রকার ।<br />‘ফল্গু’-‘যুক্ত’ ভেদ আমি শিখাইনু বার বার ॥৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" prabhu bale, “vairāgya haya dui ta prakāra<br />‘phalgu’-‘yukta’ bhede āmi śikhāinu bāra bāra [4]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">prabhu</span>–The Lord <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–said, <span class=\\"e2\\">“haya</span>–“There are <span class=\\"e2\\">dui</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ta</span>–two <span class=\\"e2\\">prakāra</span>–types <span class=\\"e2\\">vairāgya</span>–of renunciation: <span class=\\"e2\\">‘phalgu’-‘yukta’</span>–false and proper. <span class=\\"e2\\">āmi</span>–I <span class=\\"e2\\">śikhāinu</span>–have taught <span class=\\"e2\\">bhede</span>–the difference <span class=\\"e2\\">bāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bāra</span>–many times."},{"class":"b71","text":" The Lord said, “There are two types of renunciation: false and proper. I have taught the difference between them many times."},{"class":"b176","text":" ফল্গুবৈরাগ্য"},{"class":"b177","text":" phalgu-vairāgya"},{"class":"b70","text":" False renunciation"},{"class":"b97","text":" কর্ম্মী জ্ঞানী যবে করে নির্ব্বেদ আশ্রয় ।<br />তার চিত্তে ফল্গুবৈরাগ্য পায় দুষ্টাশয় ॥৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" karmī jñānī yabe kare nirveda āśraya<br />tāra chitte phalgu-vairāgya pāya duṣṭāśaya [5]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">yabe</span>–When <span class=\\"e2\\">karmī</span>–materialists [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">jñānī</span>–speculators <span class=\\"e2\\">nirveda</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">āśraya kare</span>–resort to apathy, <span class=\\"e2\\">pāya</span>–they develop <span class=\\"e2\\">duṣṭāśaya</span>–the wickedness <span class=\\"e2\\">phalgu-vairāgya</span>–of false renunciation <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">chitte</span>–within their minds."},{"class":"b50","text":" “When materialists and speculators resort to apathy (towards the world), the wickedness of false renunciation arises in their minds."},{"class":"b97","text":" সংসারেতে তুচ্ছবুদ্ধি আসিয়া তখন ।<br />জড়-বিপরীত ধর্ম্মে করে প্রবর্ত্তন ॥৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" saṁsārete tuchchha-buddhi āsiyā takhana<br />jaḍa-viparīta dharme kare pravartana [6]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">takhana</span>–Then, <span class=\\"e2\\">saṁsārete</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">tuchchha-buddhi</span>–the mentality that the world is trifling <span class=\\"e2\\">āsiyā</span>–comes [to them, and] <span class=\\"e2\\">pravartana kare</span>–they start <span class=\\"e2\\">jaḍa-viparīta</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">dharme</span>–to oppose material nature."},{"class":"b50","text":" “They develop the mentality that saṁsāra is trifling and begin to oppose material nature."},{"class":"b97","text":" কৃষ্ণসেবা সাধুসেবা আত্মরসাস্বাদ ।<br />জড়-বিপরীত ধর্ম্মে পায় নিতান্ত অবসাদ ॥৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kṛṣṇa-sevā sādhu-sevā ātma-rasāsvāda<br />jaḍa-viparīta dharme pāya nitānta avasāda [7]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-sevā</span>–Service to Kṛṣṇa [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">sādhu-sevā</span>–service to the sādhus [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">ātma-rasāsvāda</span>–relishable to the soul. <span class=\\"e2\\">jaḍa-viparīta</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">dharme</span>–By opposing material nature, <span class=\\"e2\\">pāya</span>–you become <span class=\\"e2\\">nitānta</span>–completely <span class=\\"e2\\">avasāda</span>–disheartened."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Service to Kṛṣṇa and the sādhus is relishable to the soul. By simply opposing material nature, you end up completely disheartened."},{"class":"b97","text":" ফল্গুবৈরাগীর মন সদা শুষ্ক রসহীন ।<br />নামরূপগুণলীলা না হয় সমীচীন ॥৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" phalgu-vairāgīra mana sadā śuṣka rasa-hīna<br />nāma-rūpa-guṇa-līlā nā haya samīchīna [8]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">mana</span>–The mind <span class=\\"e2\\">phalgu-vairāgīra</span>–of a false renunciant [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">sadā</span>–always <span class=\\"e2\\">śuṣka</span>–dry [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">rasa-hīna</span>–dissatisfied. <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–It is <span class=\\"e2\\">nā</span>–not <span class=\\"e2\\">samīchīna</span>–fit <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-rūpa-guṇa-līlā</span>–for [the Lord’s] Name, Form, Qualities, and Pastimes."},{"class":"b71","text":" “The mind of a false renunciant is always dry and dissatisfied. It is unfit for the Lord’s Name, Form, Qualities, and Pastimes."},{"class":"b176","text":" যুক্তবৈরাগ্য"},{"class":"b177","text":" yukta-vairāgya"},{"class":"b70","text":" Proper renunciation"},{"class":"b97","text":" যুক্তবৈরাগীর ভক্তি হয় ত’ সুলভ ।<br />কৃষ্ণভক্তি-পূত বিষয় তার ঘটে সব ॥৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" yukta-vairāgīra bhakti haya ta’ sulabha<br />kṛṣṇa-bhakti-pūta viṣaya tāra ghaṭe saba [9]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">yukta-vairāgīra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ta’</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sulabha haya</span>–A proper renunciant easily attains <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakti</span>–devotion: <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">saba viṣaya ghaṭe</span>–everything they do [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-bhakti-pūta</span>–purified by devotion to Kṛṣṇa."},{"class":"b50","text":" “A proper renunciant easily attains devotion: everything they do is purified by devotion to Kṛṣṇa."},{"class":"b97","text":" প্রকৃতির জড়ধর্ম্ম তার চিত্ত ছাড়ে অনায়াসে ।<br />চিৎ-আশ্রয়ে মজে শীঘ্র অপ্রাকৃত ভক্তিরসে ॥১০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" prakṛtira jaḍa-dharma tāra chitta chhāḍe anāyāse<br />chit-āśraye maje śīghra āprākṛta bhakti-rase [10]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra</span>–Their <span class=\\"e2\\">chitta</span>–heart <span class=\\"e2\\">anāyāse</span>–easily <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍe</span>–gives up <span class=\\"e2\\">jaḍa-dharma</span>–the dull nature <span class=\\"e2\\">prakṛtira</span>–of matter, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">chit-āśraye</span>–in shelter of spirit, <span class=\\"e2\\">śīghra</span>–quickly <span class=\\"e2\\">maje</span>–revels <span class=\\"e2\\">āprākṛta</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakti-rase</span>–in the joy of supramundane devotion."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Their heart easily gives up the dull nature of matter and, sheltered in spirit, quickly begins to relish the joy of supramundane devotion."},{"class":"b97","text":" ভক্তিযোগে শ্রীকৃষ্ণের প্রসন্নতা পায় ।<br />‘ন মে ভক্তঃ প্রণশ্যতি’, প্রতিজ্ঞা জানায় ॥১১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" bhakti-yoge śrī-kṛṣṇera prasannatā pāya<br />‘na me bhaktaḥ praṇaśyati’, pratijñā jānāya [11]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">pāya</span>–They attain <span class=\\"e2\\">prasannatā</span>–the favour <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-kṛṣṇera</span>–of Śrī Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakti-yoge</span>–through the practice of devotion, [and then] <span class=\\"e2\\">jānāya</span>–proclaim [Kṛṣṇa’s] <span class=\\"e2\\">pratijñā</span>–promise (Bg: 9.31): <span class=\\"e2\\">‘me</span>–‘My <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaktaḥ</span>–devotee <span class=\\"e2\\">praṇaśyati na’</span>–is never vanquished.’"},{"class":"b50","text":" “They attain the favour of Śrī Kṛṣṇa through the practice of devotion and then proclaim Kṛṣṇa’s promise: ‘<span class=\\"e3\\">Na Me bhaktaḥ praṇaśyati</span>: My devotee is never vanquished.’*"},{"class":"b97","text":" প্রসন্ন হইয়া কৃষ্ণ যারে কৃপা করে ।<br />সেই জন ধন্য এই সংসার-ভিতরে ॥১২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" prasanna ha-iyā kṛṣṇa yāre kṛpā kare<br />sei jana dhanya ei saṁsāra-bhitare [12]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">jana yāre</span>–Those whom <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span>–Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">prasanna</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-iyā</span>–is pleased [with and] <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛpā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kare</span>–blesses [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">dhanya</span>–fortunate <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">saṁsāra-bhitare</span>–within this world."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Those whom Kṛṣṇa is pleased with and blesses are truly fortunate within this world."},{"class":"b97","text":" গোলোকের পরম ভাব তার চিত্তে স্ফুরে ।<br />গোকুলে গোলোক পায় মায়া পড়ে দূরে ॥১৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" golokera parama bhāva tāra chitte sphure<br />gokule goloka pāya māyā paḍe dūre [13]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">parama</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāva</span>–The supreme mood <span class=\\"e2\\">golokera</span>–of Goloka <span class=\\"e2\\">sphure</span>–appears <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">chitte</span>–in their hearts, <span class=\\"e2\\">pāya</span>–they attain <span class=\\"e2\\">goloka</span>–Goloka <span class=\\"e2\\">gokule</span>–in Gokula (on earth), [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">māyā</span>–Māyā <span class=\\"e2\\">dūre paḍe</span>–falls away [from them]."},{"class":"b71","text":" “The supreme mood of Goloka appears in their hearts, they attain Goloka in Gokula, and Māyā falls away from them."},{"class":"b176","text":" শুষ্কবৈরাগ্য দূর করা কর্ত্তব্য"},{"class":"b177","text":" śuṣka-vairāgya dūra karā kartavya"},{"class":"b70","text":" Avoiding dry renunciation is our duty"},{"class":"b97","text":" ওরে ভাই শুষ্কবৈরাগ্য এবে দূর কর ।<br />যুক্তবৈরাগ্য আনি’ সদা হৃদয়েতে ধর ॥১৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ore bhāi śuṣka-vairāgya ebe dūra kara<br />yukta-vairāgya āni’ sadā hṛdayete dhara [14]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">ore</span>–O <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāi</span>–brother, <span class=\\"e2\\">ebe</span>–now <span class=\\"e2\\">dūra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kara</span>–avoid <span class=\\"e2\\">śuṣka</span>–dry <span class=\\"e2\\">vairāgya</span>–renunciation. <span class=\\"e2\\">āni’</span>–Bring <span class=\\"e2\\">yukta</span>–proper <span class=\\"e2\\">vairāgya</span>–renunciation <span class=\\"e2\\">hṛdayete</span>–into [your] heart [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">dhara</span>–hold [it there] <span class=\\"e2\\">sadā</span>–forever."},{"class":"b50","text":" “O brother, from now on, avoid dry renunciation. Bring proper renunciation into your heart and keep it there forever."},{"class":"b97","text":" বিষয় ছাড়িয়া ভাই কোথা যাবে বল ।<br />বনে যাবে, সেখানে বিষয়-জঞ্জাল ॥১৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" viṣaya chhāḍiyā bhāi kothā yābe bala<br />vane yābe, sekhāne viṣaya-jañjāla [15]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāi</span>–Brother, <span class=\\"e2\\">bala</span>–tell Me, <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍiyā</span>–after abandoning <span class=\\"e2\\">viṣaya</span>–worldly affairs, <span class=\\"e2\\">kothā</span>–where <span class=\\"e2\\">yābe</span>–will you go? <span class=\\"e2\\">yābe</span>–You will go <span class=\\"e2\\">vane</span>–to the forest, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">sekhāne</span>–there [you will find] <span class=\\"e2\\">viṣaya-jañjāla</span>–worldly troubles."},{"class":"b43","text":" “Brother, tell Me, after abandoning worldly affairs, where will you go? You will go to the forest, and there also you will find worldly troubles."},{"class":"b69","text":" * See 19.42."},{"class":"b97","text":" পেট তোমার সঙ্গে যাবে, দেহের রক্ষণে ।<br />কত লেঠা হবে তাহা ভেবে দেখ মনে ॥১৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" peṭa tomāra saṅge yābe, dehera rakṣaṇe<br />kata leṭhā habe tāhā bhebe dekha mane [16]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">tomāra</span>–Your <span class=\\"e2\\">peṭa</span>–belly <span class=\\"e2\\">yābe</span>–will go <span class=\\"e2\\">saṅge</span>–with [you;] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhebe</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">mane dekha</span>–think [about] <span class=\\"e2\\">kata</span>–how much <span class=\\"e2\\">leṭhā</span>–difficulty <span class=\\"e2\\">habe</span>–there will be <span class=\\"e2\\">dehera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">rakṣaṇe</span>–to maintain [your] body <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhā</span>–there."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Your belly will go with you; think about how difficult it will be to maintain your body there."},{"class":"b97","text":" অকারণে জীবনের শীঘ্র হবে ক্ষয় ।<br />মরিলে কেমনে আর মায়া কর্বে জয় ॥১৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" akāraṇe jīvanera śighra habe kṣaya<br />marile kemane āra māyā karbe jaya [17]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">akāraṇe</span>–Unnecessarily, [your] <span class=\\"e2\\">jīvanera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kṣaya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">habe</span>–life will end <span class=\\"e2\\">śighra</span>–quickly, <span class=\\"e2\\">āra</span>–and <span class=\\"e2\\">marile</span>–if you die, <span class=\\"e2\\">kemane</span>–how <span class=\\"e2\\">jaya karbe</span>–will you conquer <span class=\\"e2\\">māyā</span>–māyā?"},{"class":"b50","text":" “Unnecessarily, your life will end quickly, and if you die, how will you conquer māyā?"},{"class":"b97","text":" যদিও না মর তবু হইবে দুর্ব্বল ।<br />জ্ঞাননাশ হৈলে কোথা জ্ঞানের সম্বল ॥১৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" yadio nā mara tabu ha-ibe durbala<br />jñāna-nāśa ha-ile kothā jñānera sambala [18]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">yadio</span>–Even if <span class=\\"e2\\">mara nā</span>–you do not die, <span class=\\"e2\\">tabu</span>–still <span class=\\"e2\\">durbala ha-ibe</span>–you will become weak, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">jñāna-nāśa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-ile</span>–if your knowledge is lost [as a result, then] <span class=\\"e2\\">kothā</span>–where [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">sambala</span>–the benefit <span class=\\"e2\\">jñānera</span>–of that knowledge?"},{"class":"b71","text":" “Even if you do not die, you will still become weak, and if you lose your knowledge as a result, what benefit will you get from it?"},{"class":"b176","text":" সুতরাং যুক্তবৈরাগ্য কর্ত্তব্য"},{"class":"b177","text":" sutarāṁ yukta-vairāgya kartavya"},{"class":"b70","text":" So, proper renunciation is our duty"},{"class":"b97","text":" ঘরে বসি’ সদা কাল কৃষ্ণনাম লঞা ।<br />যথাযোগ্য-বিষয় ভুঞ্জ, অনাসক্ত হঞা ॥১৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ghare basi’ sadā kāla kṛṣṇa-nāma lañā<br />yathā-yogya-viṣaya bhuñja, anāsakta hañā [19]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">basi’</span>–Stay <span class=\\"e2\\">ghare</span>–at home, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">sadā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kāla</span>–at all times <span class=\\"e2\\">lañā</span>–chant <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-nāma</span>–the Name of Kṛṣṇa. <span class=\\"e2\\">yathā-yogya</span>–As appropriate, <span class=\\"e2\\">viṣaya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bhuñja</span>–interact with the world, <span class=\\"e2\\">hañā</span>–remaining <span class=\\"e2\\">anāsakta</span>–detached."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Stay at home and always chant the Name of Kṛṣṇa. As appropriate, interact with the world, remaining detached."},{"class":"b97","text":" “যথাযোগ্য” এই শব্দ দুটীর মর্ম্মার্থ বুঝে লহ ।<br />কপটার্থ লঞা যেন দেহারামী না হ ॥২০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" “yathā-yogya” ei śabda duṭīra marmārtha bujhe laha<br />kapaṭārtha lañā yena dehārāmī nā ha [20]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bujhe</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">laha</span>–Understand <span class=\\"e2\\">duṭīra</span>–the two <span class=\\"e2\\">marmārtha</span>–purports <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">śabda</span>–of the phrase <span class=\\"e2\\">“yathā-yogya”</span>–‘as appropriate’. <span class=\\"e2\\">yena nā</span>–Do not <span class=\\"e2\\">lañā</span>–accept <span class=\\"e2\\">kapaṭārtha</span>–the false meaning [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">ha</span>–become <span class=\\"e2\\">dehārāmī</span>–a sensualist."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Understand the two purports of the phrase ‘as appropriate’ so that you do not accept the false meaning and become a sensualist."},{"class":"b97","text":" শুদ্ধভক্তির অনুকূল কর অঙ্গীকার ।<br />শুদ্ধভক্তির প্রতিকূল কর অস্বীকার ॥২১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" śuddha-bhaktira anukūla kara aṅgīkāra<br />śuddha-bhaktira pratikūla kara asvīkāra [21]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">aṅgīkāra kara</span>–Accept [everything] <span class=\\"e2\\">anukūla</span>–favourable <span class=\\"e2\\">śuddha-bhaktira</span>–to pure devotion, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">asvīkāra kara</span>–reject [everything] <span class=\\"e2\\">pratikūla</span>–unfavourable <span class=\\"e2\\">śuddha-bhaktira</span>–to pure devotion."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Accept everything favourable to pure devotion, and reject everything unfavourable to pure devotion."},{"class":"b97","text":" মর্ম্মার্থ ছাড়িয়া যেবা শব্দ অর্থ করে ।<br />রসের বশে দেহারামী কপট মার্গ ধরে ॥২২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" marmārtha chhāḍiyā yebā śabda artha kare<br />rasera vaśe dehārāmī kapaṭa mārga dhare [22]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">yebā</span>–Those who <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍiyā</span>–reject <span class=\\"e2\\">marmārtha</span>–this purport [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">artha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kare</span>–interpret <span class=\\"e2\\">śabda</span>–the phrase [otherwise are] <span class=\\"e2\\">dehārāmī</span>–sensualists <span class=\\"e2\\">rasera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">vaśe</span>–controlled by pleas­ures; [they] <span class=\\"e2\\">dhare</span>–follow <span class=\\"e2\\">mārga</span>–the path <span class=\\"e2\\">kapaṭa</span>–of deceit."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Those who reject this purport and misinterpret the phrase are sensualists controlled by pleasures; they follow the path of deceit."},{"class":"b97","text":" ভাল খায়, ভাল পরে, করে বহু ধনার্জ্জন ।<br />যোষিৎসঙ্গে রত হঞা ফিরে রাত্রদিন ।<br />ভাল শয্যা অট্টালিকা খোঁজে অর্ব্বাচীন ॥২৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" bhāla khāya, bhāla pare, kare bahu dhanārjana<br />yoṣit-saṅge rata hañā phire rātra-dina<br />bhāla śayyā aṭṭālikā kho̐je arvāchīna [23]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">khāya</span>–They eat <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāla</span>–fancy [food], <span class=\\"e2\\">pare</span>–wear <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāla</span>–fancy [clothes, and] <span class=\\"e2\\">bahu</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">dhanārjana kare</span>–accumulate immense wealth. <span class=\\"e2\\">hañā</span>–Being <span class=\\"e2\\">rata</span>–attached <span class=\\"e2\\">yoṣit-saṅge</span>–to the company of women, <span class=\\"e2\\">arvāchīna</span>–such fools <span class=\\"e2\\">phire</span>–roam about <span class=\\"e2\\">rātra-dina</span>–night and day [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">kho̐je</span>–search <span class=\\"e2\\">aṭṭālikā</span>–for a mansion [with] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāla</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">śayyā</span>–a fancy bed."},{"class":"b50","text":" “They eat fancy food, wear fancy clothes, and accumulate immense wealth. Attached to the company of women, such fools roam about night and day searching for a mansion with a fancy bed."},{"class":"b97","text":" দেহযাত্রার উপযোগী নিতান্ত প্রয়োজন ।<br />বিষয় স্বীকার করি’ কর দেহের রক্ষণ ॥২৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" deha-yātrāra upayogī nitānta prayojana<br />viṣaya svīkāra kari’ kara dehera rakṣaṇa [24]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [Instead of all this,] <span class=\\"e2\\">dehera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">rakṣaṇa kara</span>–maintain the body <span class=\\"e2\\">svīkāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kari’</span>–by accepting <span class=\\"e2\\">viṣaya</span>–things [that are] <span class=\\"e2\\">upayogī</span>–suitable [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">nitānta</span>–actually <span class=\\"e2\\">prayojana</span>–necessary <span class=\\"e2\\">deha-yātrāra</span>–for the body’s preservation."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Instead of all this, maintain the body by accepting things that are suitable and actually necessary for its preservation."},{"class":"b97","text":" সাত্ত্বিক সেবন কর আসব বর্জ্জন ।<br />সর্ব্বভূতে দয়া করি’ কর উচ্চ সঙ্কীর্ত্তন ॥২৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sāttvika sevana kara āsaba varjana<br />sarva-bhūte dayā kari’ kara uchcha saṅkīrtana [25]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sevana</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kara</span>–Eat <span class=\\"e2\\">sāttvika</span>–things in the mode of goodness [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">varjana</span>–reject <span class=\\"e2\\">āsaba</span>–intoxicants. <span class=\\"e2\\">dayā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kari’</span>–Be kind <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-bhūta</span>–to all beings [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">uchcha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">saṅkīrtana kara</span>–chant loudly."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Eat food in the mode of goodness and reject intoxicants. Be kind to all beings and loudly chant the Name."},{"class":"b97","text":" দেবসেবা ছল করি’ বিষয় নাহি কর ।<br />বিষয়েতে রাগ-দ্বেষ সদা পরিহর ॥২৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" deva-sevā chhala kari’ viṣaya nāhi kara<br />viṣayete rāga-dveṣa sadā parihara [26]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">viṣaya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kara nāhi</span>–Do not engage in worldly affairs <span class=\\"e2\\">chhala</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kari’</span>–by making a pretence <span class=\\"e2\\">deva-sevā</span>–of Deity worship, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">sadā</span>–always <span class=\\"e2\\">parihara</span>–avoid <span class=\\"e2\\">rāga-dveṣa</span>–attachment and aversion <span class=\\"e2\\">viṣayete</span>–to worldly matters."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Do not engage in worldly affairs on the pretence of Deity worship, and always avoid attachment and aversion to worldly matters."},{"class":"b97","text":" পরহিংসা কপটতা অন্য সনে বৈর ।<br />কভু নাহি কর ভাই যদি মোর বাক্য ধর ॥২৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" para-hiṁsā kapaṭatā anya sane vaira<br />kabhu nāhi kara bhāi yadi mora vākya dhara [27]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāhi</span>–Never <span class=\\"e2\\">kara</span>–engage in <span class=\\"e2\\">para-hiṁsā</span>–envy, <span class=\\"e2\\">kapaṭatā</span>–deceit, [or] <span class=\\"e2\\">vaira</span>–enmity <span class=\\"e2\\">anya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sane</span>–with others, <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāi</span>–brother, <span class=\\"e2\\">yadi</span>–if [you want to] <span class=\\"e2\\">dhara</span>–follow <span class=\\"e2\\">mora</span>–My <span class=\\"e2\\">vākya</span>–advice."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Never behave enviously, deceitfully, or inimically with others, brother, if you want to follow My advice."},{"class":"b97","text":" নির্জ্জন সুদৃঢ় ভক্তি কর আলোচন ।<br />কৃষ্ণসেবার সম্বন্ধে দিন করহ যাপন ॥২৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" nirjana sudṛḍha bhakti kara ālochana<br />kṛṣṇa-sevāra sambandhe dina karaha yāpana [28]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">ālochana kara</span>–Discuss <span class=\\"e2\\">sudṛḍha</span>–resolute <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakti</span>–devotion <span class=\\"e2\\">nirjana</span>–in seclusion, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">yāpana karaha</span>–spend [your] <span class=\\"e2\\">dina</span>–days <span class=\\"e2\\">sambandhe</span>–engaged in <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-sevāra</span>–the service of Kṛṣṇa."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Discuss resolute devotion in seclusion, and spend your days engaged in the service of Kṛṣṇa."},{"class":"b97","text":" মঠ মন্দির দালান বাড়ীর না কর প্রয়াস ।<br />অর্থ থাকে কর ভাই যেমন অভিলাষ ॥২৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" maṭha mandira dālāna bāḍīra nā kara prayāsa<br />artha thāke kara bhāi yemana abhilāṣa [29]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">prayāsa kara nā</span>–Do not endeavour <span class=\\"e2\\">maṭha mandira</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">dālāna</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bāḍīra</span>–for monasteries, temples, or big houses, [but] <span class=\\"e2\\">artha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">thāke</span>–if you have wealth, <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāi</span>–brother, [then you can] <span class=\\"e2\\">kara</span>–make [them,] <span class=\\"e2\\">yemana</span>–as [you] <span class=\\"e2\\">abhilāṣa</span>–desire."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Do not endeavour to make monasteries, temples, or big houses, but if you have wealth, brother, then you can make them, as you desire."},{"class":"b97","text":" অর্থ নাই তবে মাত্র সাত্ত্বিক সেবা কর ।<br />জল-তুলসী দিয়া গিরিধারীকে বক্ষে ধর ॥৩০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" artha nāi tabe mātra sāttvika sevā kara<br />jala-tulasī diyā giridhārīke vakṣe dhara [30]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">artha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāi</span>–If you do not have wealth, <span class=\\"e2\\">tabe</span>–then <span class=\\"e2\\">mātra</span>–simply <span class=\\"e2\\">sāttvika</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sevā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kara</span>–perform pure worship. <span class=\\"e2\\">diyā</span>–Offer <span class=\\"e2\\">jala-tulasī</span>–water and Tulasī <span class=\\"e2\\">giridhārīke</span>–to Giridhārī [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">dhara</span>–hold [Him] <span class=\\"e2\\">vakṣe</span>–to [your] chest."},{"class":"b50","text":" “If you do not have wealth, then simply perform pure worship. Offer water and Tulasī to Giridhārī and hold Him to your chest."},{"class":"b97","text":" ভাবেতে কাঁদিয়া বল, “আমি ত’ তোমার ।<br />তব পাদপদ্ম চিত্তে রহুক আমার” ॥৩১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" bhāvete kā̐diyā bala, “āmi ta’ tomāra<br />tava pāda-padma chitte rahuka āmāra” [31]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kā̐diyā</span>–Crying <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāvete</span>–with love, <span class=\\"e2\\">bala</span>–say, <span class=\\"e2\\">‘āmi</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ta’</span>–‘I [am] <span class=\\"e2\\">tomāra</span>–Yours. [Let] <span class=\\"e2\\">tava</span>–Your <span class=\\"e2\\">pāda-padma</span>–lotus feet <span class=\\"e2\\">rahuka</span>–remain <span class=\\"e2\\">āmāra chitte’</span>–in my heart.’"},{"class":"b50","text":" “Crying with love, pray, ‘I am Yours. Let Your lotus feet remain in my heart.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" বৈষ্ণবে আদর কর প্রসাদাদি দিয়া ।<br />অর্থ নাই দৈন্যবাক্যে তোষ মিনতি করিয়া ॥৩২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" vaiṣṇave ādara kara prasādādi diyā<br />artha nāi dainya-vākye toṣa minati kariyā [32]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">ādara</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kara</span>–Honour <span class=\\"e2\\">vaiṣṇave</span>–the Vaiṣṇavas <span class=\\"e2\\">diyā</span>–with <span class=\\"e2\\">prasādādi</span>–prasād and other remnants. <span class=\\"e2\\">artha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāi</span>–If you have no wealth, [then] <span class=\\"e2\\">minati</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kariyā</span>–submissively <span class=\\"e2\\">toṣa</span>–satisfy [them] <span class=\\"e2\\">dainya-vākye</span>–with humble words."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Honour the Vaiṣṇavas with prasād and other remnants. If you have no wealth, then submissively satisfy them with humble words."},{"class":"b97","text":" পরিজন পরিকর কৃষ্ণদাস-দাসী ।<br />আত্মসম পালনে হইবে মিষ্টভাষী ॥৩৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" parijana parikara kṛṣṇa-dāsa-dāsī<br />ātma-sama pālane ha-ibe miṣṭa-bhāṣī [33]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [Consider your] <span class=\\"e2\\">parijana</span>–friends [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">parikara</span>–relatives <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-dāsa-dāsī</span>–Kṛṣṇa’s servants and maidservants, <span class=\\"e2\\">pālane</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-ibe</span>–care [for them] <span class=\\"e2\\">ātma-sama</span>–as you do for yourself, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">miṣṭa-bhāṣī</span>–speak [to them] sweetly."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Consider your friends and relatives servants of Kṛṣṇa, care for them as well as you care for yourself, and speak to them sweetly."},{"class":"b97","text":" স্মরণ-কীর্ত্তন-সেবা সর্ব্বভূতে দয়া ।<br />এই ত’ করিবে যুক্ত বৈরাগী হইয়া ॥৩৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" smaraṇa-kīrtana-sevā sarva-bhūte dayā<br />ei ta’ karibe yukta vairāgī ha-iyā [34]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">smaraṇa-kīrtana-sevā</span>–Remember, glorify, and serve [the Lord, and] <span class=\\"e2\\">dayā</span>–be kind <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-bhūte</span>–to all beings. <span class=\\"e2\\">karibe</span>–Do <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ta’</span>–this, <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-iyā</span>–being <span class=\\"e2\\">yukta</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">vairāgī</span>–a proper renunciant."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Remember, glorify, and serve the Lord, and be kind to all beings. Do all this as a proper renunciant."},{"class":"b97","text":" কৃষ্ণ যদি নাহি দেয় পরিজন-পরিকর ।<br />অথবা দিয়া ত লয় সর্ব্ব সুখের আকর ॥৩৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kṛṣṇa yadi nāhi deya parijana-parikara<br />athavā diyā ta laya sarva sukhera ākara [35]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">yadi</span>–If <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span>–Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">deya nāhi</span>–does not give [you] <span class=\\"e2\\">parijana-parikara</span>–friends and relatives, <span class=\\"e2\\">athavā</span>–or if <span class=\\"e2\\">diyā</span>–He gives [them and then] <span class=\\"e2\\">ta</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">laya</span>–takes [them] away, [accept] <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva</span>–all [such conditions as] <span class=\\"e2\\">ākara</span>–a source <span class=\\"e2\\">sukhera</span>–of joy."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Kṛṣṇa may not give you friends and relatives, or He may give them and then take them away. Accept all such conditions as a source of joy."},{"class":"b97","text":" শোক-মোহ ছাড় ভাই নাম কর নিরন্তর” ।<br />জগাই বলে, “এভাব গৌরের সনে মোর কোঁদল বিস্তর” ॥৩৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" śoka-moha chhāḍa bhāi nāma kara nirantara”<br />jagāi bale, “e-bhāva gaurera sane mora ko̐dala vistara” [36]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāi</span>–Brother, <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍa</span>–leave behind <span class=\\"e2\\">śoka-moha</span>–lamentation and bewilderment, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">nirantara</span>–always <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kara”</span>–chant the Name.” <span class=\\"e2\\">jagāi</span>–Jagāi <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–says, <span class=\\"e2\\">“mora</span>–“I have <span class=\\"e2\\">vistara</span>–many <span class=\\"e2\\">ko̐dala</span>–quarrels <span class=\\"e2\\">e-bhāva”</span>–about this subject <span class=\\"e2\\">gaurera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sane</span>–with Gaura.”"},{"class":"b55","text":" “Brother, leave behind all lamentation and bewilderment, and always chant the Name.” Jagāi says, “I have many quarrels with Gaura about this.”"}]},{"title":"Caste and Class","paragraphs":[{"class":"b46","text":"\\r"},{"class":"b58","text":" Chapter Ten"},{"class":"b120","text":" জাতিকুল"},{"class":"b121","text":" Jāti-kula"},{"class":"b175","text":" Caste and Class"},{"class":"b176","text":" কুল ও ভজন যোগ্যতা"},{"class":"b177","text":" kula o bhajana yogyatā"},{"class":"b70","text":" Class and qualification for devotion"},{"class":"b97","text":" শ্রদ্ধা হইলে নরমাত্র নামের অধিকারী ।<br />জাতিকুলের তর্ক তর্কীর না চলে ভারিভুরি ॥১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" śraddhā ha-ile nara-mātra nāmera adhikārī<br />jāti-kulera tarka tarkīra nā chale bhāri-bhuri [1]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">nara-mātra</span>–Every human being— <span class=\\"e2\\">śraddhā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-ile</span>–if they have faith— [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">adhikārī</span>–qualified [to chant] the Name. <span class=\\"e2\\">tarka</span>–The arguments [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāri-bhuri</span>–brashness <span class=\\"e2\\">tarkīra</span>–of speculators <span class=\\"e2\\">jāti-kulera</span>–about caste and class <span class=\\"e2\\">chale nā</span>–do not go [anywhere]."},{"class":"b50","text":" Every human being—if they have faith—is qualified to chant the Name. The arguments and brashness of speculators about caste and class do not count for anything."},{"class":"b97","text":" ব্রাহ্মণের সৎকুল না হয় ভজনের যোগ্য ।<br />শ্রদ্ধাবান্ নীচজাতি নহে ভজনে অযোগ্য ॥২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" brāhmaṇera sat-kula nā haya bhajanera yogya<br />śraddhāvan nīcha-jāti nahe bhajane ayogya [2]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">brāhmaṇera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sat-kula</span>–Birth in a family of brāhmaṇs <span class=\\"e2\\">haya nā</span>–does not make one <span class=\\"e2\\">yogya</span>–fit <span class=\\"e2\\">bhajanera</span>–for devotion, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">nīcha-jāti</span>–a lowborn person [who] <span class=\\"e2\\">śraddhāvan</span>–has faith <span class=\\"e2\\">nahe</span>–is not <span class=\\"e2\\">ayogya</span>–unfit <span class=\\"e2\\">bhajane</span>–for devotion."},{"class":"b71","text":" Birth in a family of brāhmaṇs does not make one fit for devotion, and a lowborn person who has faith is not unfit for devotion."},{"class":"b176","text":" কুলাভিমানী অভক্ত"},{"class":"b177","text":" kulābhimānī abhakta"},{"class":"b70","text":" Non-devotees are proud of their class"},{"class":"b97","text":" সংসারের দশকর্ম্মে জাতিকুলের আধিপত্য ।<br />কৃষ্ণজনে জাতিকুলের না আছে মাহাত্ম্য ॥৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" saṁsārera daśa-karme jāti-kulera ādhipatya<br />kṛṣṇa-jane jāti-kulera nā āchhe māhātmya [3]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">jāti-kulera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ādhipatya</span>–The importance of caste and class [lies in] <span class=\\"e2\\">saṁsārera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">daśa-karme</span>–the ten worldly rites, [but] <span class=\\"e2\\">jāti-kulera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">āchhe nā</span>–caste and creed have no <span class=\\"e2\\">māhātmya</span>–importance <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-jane</span>–for devotees of Kṛṣṇa."},{"class":"b50","text":" Caste and class are important in worldly religious ceremonies, but are of no importance to devotees of Kṛṣṇa."},{"class":"b97","text":" জাতিকুলের অভিমানে অহঙ্কারী জন ।<br />ভক্তিকে বিদ্বেষ করি’ যায় নরক-ভবন ॥৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" jāti-kulera abhimāne ahaṅkārī jana<br />bhaktike vidveṣa kari’ yāya naraka-bhavana [4]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">ahaṅkārī jana</span>–Egotists [who are] <span class=\\"e2\\">abhimāne</span>–proud <span class=\\"e2\\">jāti-kulera</span>–of [their] caste and class <span class=\\"e2\\">vidveṣa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kari’</span>–oppose <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaktike</span>–devotion [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">yāya</span>–go <span class=\\"e2\\">naraka-bhavana</span>–to hell."},{"class":"b50","text":" Egotists who are proud of their caste and class oppose devotion and go to hell."},{"class":"b97","text":" না মানে বৈষ্ণবভক্ত, না মানে ধর্ম্মাধর্ম্ম ।<br />অহঙ্কারে করে সদা অকর্ম্ম-বিকর্ম্ম ॥৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" nā māne vaiṣṇava-bhakta, nā māne dharmādharma<br />ahaṅkāre kare sadā akarma-vikarma [5]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">māne nā</span>–They do not respect <span class=\\"e2\\">vaiṣṇava-bhakta</span>–Vaiṣṇava devotees, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">māne nā</span>–do not honour <span class=\\"e2\\">dharmādharma</span>–religion [as opposed to] irreligion. <span class=\\"e2\\">ahaṅkāre</span>–Out of pride, <span class=\\"e2\\">sadā kare</span>–they always engage in <span class=\\"e2\\">akarma-vikarma</span>–idleness and sin."},{"class":"b71","text":" They neither respect Vaiṣṇava devotees nor do they have any regard for religion or irreligion. Out of pride, they always remain idle or commit sins."},{"class":"b176","text":" অভক্ত বিপ্র হইতে ভক্তি মুচি শ্রেষ্ঠ"},{"class":"b177","text":" abhakta vipra ha-ite bhakti muchi śreṣṭha"},{"class":"b70","text":" A devotee cobbler is superior to a non-devotee brāhmaṇ"},{"class":"b97","text":" মুচি হঞা কৃষ্ণ ভজে কৃষ্ণকৃপা পায় ।<br />শুচি হঞা ভক্তিহীন কৃষ্ণকৃপা নাহি তায় ॥৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" muchi hañā kṛṣṇa bhaje kṛṣṇa-kṛpā pāya<br />śuchi hañā bhakti-hīna kṛṣṇa-kṛpā nāhi tāya [6]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">muchi</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">hañā</span>–Remaining a cobbler, <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaje</span>–a soul who serves <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span>–Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">pāya</span>–gets <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-kṛpā</span>–Kṛṣṇa’s mercy, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">śuchi</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">hañā</span>–a soul who is virtuous [but] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakti-hīna</span>–devoid of devotion <span class=\\"e2\\">tāya nāhi</span>–does not get <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-kṛpā</span>–Kṛṣṇa’s mercy."},{"class":"b50","text":" Remaining a cobbler, a soul who serves Kṛṣṇa gets Kṛṣṇa’s mercy, and a soul who is virtuous but devoid of devotion does not get Kṛṣṇa’s mercy."},{"class":"b97","text":" দ্বাদশ গুণেতে বিপ্র অলঙ্কৃত হঞা ।<br />কৃষ্ণভক্তি বিনা যায় নরকে চলিয়া ॥৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" dvādaśa guṇete vipra alaṅkṛta hañā<br />kṛṣṇa-bhakti vinā yāya narake chaliyā [7]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">vipra</span>–A brāhmaṇ <span class=\\"e2\\">alaṅkṛta</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">hañā</span>–ornamented <span class=\\"e2\\">dvādaśa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">guṇete</span>–with the twelve qualities (given in <span class=\\"e33\\">Mahābhārata</span> as piety, truthfulness, self-control, austerity, non-enviousness, humility, tolerance, non-maliciousness, expertise in sacrifice, charitableness, steadiness, and learning) [but] <span class=\\"e2\\">vinā</span>–devoid <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-bhakti</span>–of devotion to Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">chaliyā yāya</span>–goes <span class=\\"e2\\">narake</span>–to hell."},{"class":"b50","text":" A brāhmaṇ ornamented with the twelve qualities but devoid of devotion to Kṛṣṇa goes to hell."},{"class":"b97","text":" কৃষ্ণভক্তি যথা, তথা সর্ব্বগুণগণ ।<br />আপন ইচ্ছায় দেহে বৈসে অনুক্ষণ ॥৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kṛṣṇa-bhakti yathā, tathā sarva-guṇa-gaṇa<br />āpana ichchhāya dehe vaise anukṣaṇa [8]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-guṇa-gaṇa</span>–All qualities [are present] <span class=\\"e2\\">yathā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">tathā</span>–wherever <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-bhakti</span>–devotion to Kṛṣṇa [is present]; <span class=\\"e2\\">āpana</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ichchhāya</span>–by their own desire, <span class=\\"e2\\">anukṣaṇa vaise</span>–they always reside <span class=\\"e2\\">dehe</span>–in the body [of a devotee]."},{"class":"b50","text":" All qualities are present wherever devotion to Kṛṣṇa is present; by their own desire, they always reside in the body of a devotee."},{"class":"b97","text":" মৃতদেহে অলঙ্কার হয় ঘৃণাস্পদ ।<br />অভক্তের জপ তপ বাহ্য সে সম্পদ ॥৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" mṛta-dehe alaṅkāra haya ghṛṇāspada<br />abhaktera japa tapa bāhya se sampada [9]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">alaṅkāra</span>–Ornaments <span class=\\"e2\\">mṛta-dehe</span>–on a dead body <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–are <span class=\\"e2\\">ghṛṇāspada</span>–revolting; <span class=\\"e2\\">abhaktera</span>–a non-devotee’s <span class=\\"e2\\">japa</span>–chanting [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">tapa</span>–austerity [are comparable to] <span class=\\"e2\\">se</span>–such <span class=\\"e2\\">bāhya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sampada</span>–external ‘wealth’."},{"class":"b71","text":" Ornaments on a dead body are revolting; a non-devotee’s chanting and austerity are comparable to such external ‘wealth’."},{"class":"b176","text":" বিষয়ে রাগেদ্বেষ বর্জ্জনীয়"},{"class":"b177","text":" viṣaye rāga-dveṣa varjanīya"},{"class":"b70","text":" Attachment and aversion to the mundane must be given up"},{"class":"b97","text":" ভজ ভাই একমনে শচীর নন্দন ।<br />জাতিকুলের অভিমান হবে বিসর্জ্জন ॥১০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" bhaja bhāi eka-mane śachīra nandana<br />jāti-kulera abhimāna habe visarjana [10]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāi</span>–Brother, <span class=\\"e2\\">eka-mane</span>–single-mindedly <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaja</span>–serve <span class=\\"e2\\">nandana</span>–the son <span class=\\"e2\\">śachīra</span>–<br />of Śachī. [Then] <span class=\\"e2\\">visarjana habe</span>–you will give up [your] <span class=\\"e2\\">abhimāna</span>–pride <span class=\\"e2\\">jāti-kulera</span>–in [your] caste and class."},{"class":"b50","text":" Brother, single-mindedly serve the son of Śachī. Then you will give up your pride in your caste and class."},{"class":"b97","text":" অভিমান ছাড়িলে ভাই ছাড়িবে বিষয় ।<br />বিষয় ছাড়িলে শুদ্ধ হবে তোমার আশয় ॥১১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" abhimāna chhāḍile bhāi chhāḍibe viṣaya<br />viṣaya chhāḍile śuddha habe tomāra āśaya [11]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāi</span>–Brother, <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍile</span>–when you give up [your] <span class=\\"e2\\">abhimāna</span>–pride, <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍibe</span>–you will give up <span class=\\"e2\\">viṣaya</span>–the world, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍile</span>–when you give up <span class=\\"e2\\">viṣaya</span>–the world, <span class=\\"e2\\">tomāra</span>–your <span class=\\"e2\\">āśaya</span>–heart <span class=\\"e2\\">śuddha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">habe</span>–will become pure."},{"class":"b50","text":" Brother, when you give up your pride, you will give up the world, and when you give up the world, your heart will become pure."},{"class":"b97","text":" বিষয় হইতে অনুরাগ লও উঠাইয়া ।<br />কৃষ্ণপদাম্বুজে রাগে দেহ লাগাইয়া ॥১২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" viṣaya ha-ite anurāga lao uṭhāiyā<br />kṛṣṇa-padāmbuje rāge deha lāgāiyā [12]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">uṭhāiyā lao</span>–Withdraw [your] <span class=\\"e2\\">anurāga</span>–affection <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-ite</span>–from <span class=\\"e2\\">viṣaya</span>–the world [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">lāgāiyā deha</span>–dedicate [your] <span class=\\"e2\\">rāge</span>–affection <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-padāmbuje</span>–to the lotus feet of Kṛṣṇa."},{"class":"b50","text":" Withdraw your affection from the world and dedicate it to the lotus feet of Kṛṣṇa."},{"class":"b97","text":" হও তুমি সৎকুলীন তাহে কিবা ক্ষতি ।<br />কুলের অভিমান ছাড়ি’ হও দীনমতি ॥১৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" hao tumi sat-kulīna tāhe kibā kṣati<br />kulera abhimāna chhāḍi’ hao dīna-mati [13]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">tumi</span>–You <span class=\\"e2\\">hao</span>–may be <span class=\\"e2\\">sat-kulīna</span>–high-class; <span class=\\"e2\\">kibā</span>–what [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">kṣati</span>–the harm <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhe</span>–in that? <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍi’</span>–Give up [your] <span class=\\"e2\\">abhimāna</span>–pride <span class=\\"e2\\">kulera</span>–in [your] class [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">hao</span>–be <span class=\\"e2\\">dīna-mati</span>–humble."},{"class":"b71","text":" You may be high-class; what is the harm in that? Just give up your pride in your class and be humble."},{"class":"b176","text":" অভিমানহীন দীনের প্রতি ভগবানের দয়া"},{"class":"b177","text":" abhimāna-hīna dīnera prati bhagavāner dayā"},{"class":"b70","text":" The Lord’s mercy upon the prideless, humble souls"},{"class":"b97","text":" দীনেরে অধিক দয়া করে ভগবান্ ।<br />অভিমান দৈন্য নাহি রহে একস্থান ॥১৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" dīnere adhika dayā kare bhagavān<br />abhimāna dainya nāhi rahe eka-sthāna [14]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bhagavān</span>–The Lord <span class=\\"e2\\">adhika</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">dayā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kare</span>–bestows greater mercy <span class=\\"e2\\">dīnere</span>–upon the humble, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">abhimāna</span>–pride [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">dainya</span>–humility <span class=\\"e2\\">rahe nāhi</span>–do not exist <span class=\\"e2\\">eka-sthāna</span>–in one place."},{"class":"b50","text":" The Lord bestows greater mercy upon the humble, and pride and humility do not co-exist."},{"class":"b97","text":" অভিমান নরকের পথ, তাহা যত্নে ত্যজ ।<br />দৈন্যে রাধাগোবিন্দের পাদপদ্মে মজ ॥১৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" abhimāna narakera patha, tāhā yatne tyaja<br />dainye rādhā-govindera pāda-padme maja [15]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">abhimāna</span>–Pride [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">patha</span>–the path <span class=\\"e2\\">narakera</span>–to hell. <span class=\\"e2\\">yatne</span>–Carefully <span class=\\"e2\\">tyaja</span>–avoid <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhā</span>–it. <span class=\\"e2\\">dainye</span>–Humbly <span class=\\"e2\\">maja</span>–immerse yourself <span class=\\"e2\\">rādhā-govindera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">pāda-padme</span>–in the lotus feet of Rādhā and Govinda."},{"class":"b71","text":" Pride is the path to hell. Carefully avoid it, and humbly immerse yourself in the lotus feet of Rādhā and Govinda."},{"class":"b176","text":" অভিমান-ত্যাগ নিত্যানন্দের দয়া সাপেক্ষ"},{"class":"b177","text":" abhimāna-tyāga nityānandera dayā sāpekṣa"},{"class":"b70","text":" Giving up pride is dependent on Nityānanda’s mercy"},{"class":"b97","text":" আহা! প্রভু নিত্যানন্দ কবে করিবে দয়া ।<br />অভিমান ছাড়াঞা মোরে দিবে পদ-ছায়া ॥১৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" āhā! prabhu nityānanda kabe karibe dayā<br />abhimāna chhāḍāñā more dibe pada-chhāyā [16]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">āhā!</span>–Ah! <span class=\\"e2\\">kabe</span>–When [will] <span class=\\"e2\\">nityānanda prabhu</span>–Nityānanda Prabhu <span class=\\"e2\\">dayā karibe</span>–be merciful [to me]? [When] <span class=\\"e2\\">more chhāḍāñā</span>–will He force me to leave [my] <span class=\\"e2\\">abhimāna</span>–pride [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">dibe</span>–give [me] <span class=\\"e2\\">pada-chhāyā</span>–the shade of His feet?"},{"class":"b55","text":" Ah! When will Nityānanda Prabhu be merciful to me? When will He force me to leave my pride and give me the shade of His feet?"}]},{"title":"The Light of Nabadwīp","paragraphs":[{"class":"b46","text":"\\r"},{"class":"b58","text":" Chapter Eleven"},{"class":"b120","text":" নবদ্বীপ-দীপক"},{"class":"b121","text":" Navadvīpa-dīpaka"},{"class":"b175","text":" The Light of Nabadwīp"},{"class":"b176","text":" শ্রীনবদ্বীপ বৃন্দাবন অভিন্ন"},{"class":"b177","text":" śrī-navadvīpa vṛndāvana abhinna"},{"class":"b70","text":" Śrī Nabadwīp and Vṛndāvan are nondifferent"},{"class":"b97","text":" ব্রহ্মাণ্ডে ধরণী ধন্য, ধরায় গৌড়-ক্ষৌণী ধন্য ।<br />গৌড়ে নবদ্বীপ ধন্য দ্ব্যষ্টক্রোশ জগৎ মান্য ॥১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" brahmāṇḍe dharaṇī dhanya, dharāya gauḍa-kṣauṇī dhanya<br />gauḍe navadvīpa dhanya dvyaṣṭa-krośa jagat mānya [1]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">brahmāṇḍe</span>–Within the universe, <span class=\\"e2\\">dharaṇī</span>–the earth [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">dhanya</span>–glorious; <span class=\\"e2\\">dharāya</span>–on the earth, <span class=\\"e2\\">gauḍa-kṣauṇī</span>–the land of Gauḍa [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">dhanya</span>–glorious; [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">gauḍe</span>–within Gauḍa, <span class=\\"e2\\">navadvīpa</span>–Nabadwīp [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">dhanya</span>–glorious. [Its] <span class=\\"e2\\">dvyaṣṭa-krośa</span>–thirty-two miles [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">mānya</span>–revered <span class=\\"e2\\">jagat</span>–by the [entire] world."},{"class":"b50","text":" Within the universe, the earth is glorious; on the earth, the land of Gauḍa is glorious; and within Gauḍa, Śrī Nabadwīp is glorious. Its thirty-two miles are revered by the entire world."},{"class":"b97","text":" মধ্যে স্রোতস্বতী ধন্য ভাগীরথী বেগবতী ।<br />তাহাতে মিলেছে আসি’ শ্রীযমুনা সরস্বতী ॥২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" madhye srotasvatī dhanya bhāgīrathī vegavatī<br />tāhāte milechhe āsi’ śrī-yamunā sarasvatī [2]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">madhye</span>–Within it, <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāgīrathī vegavatī srotasvatī</span>–the swift River Ganges [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">dhanya</span>–glorious; [there] <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-yamunā</span>–the Yamunā [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">sarasvatī</span>–Saraswatī <span class=\\"e2\\">āsi’ milechhe</span>–have come and united <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhāte</span>–with her."},{"class":"b50","text":" Within Nabadwīp, the swift River Ganges is glorious; there the Yamunā and Saraswatī have come and united with her."},{"class":"b97","text":" তার পূর্ব্বতীরে সাক্ষাৎ গোলোক মায়াপুর ।<br />তথায় শ্রীশচীগৃহে শোভে গৌরাঙ্গঠাকুর ॥৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" tāra pūrva-tīre sākṣāt goloka māyāpura<br />tathāya śrī-śachī-gṛhe śobhe gaurāṅga-ṭhākura [3]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">pūrva-tīre</span>–On the east bank of the Ganges [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">goloka</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">māyāpura</span>–Goloka Māyāpur <span class=\\"e2\\">sākṣāt</span>–itself, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">tathāya</span>–there, <span class=\\"e2\\">gaurāṅga-ṭhākura</span>–Lord Gaurāṅga <span class=\\"e2\\">śobhe</span>–shines <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-śachī-gṛhe</span>–in the home of Śrī Śachī."},{"class":"b50","text":" On the east bank of the Ganges is Goloka Māyāpur itself, and there, Lord Gaurāṅga shines in the home of Śrī Śachī."},{"class":"b97","text":" যে ঠাকুর দ্বাপরের শেষ বৃন্দাবনে বনে ।<br />মহারাসক্রীড়া কৈল রাধিকাদি গোপী সনে ॥৪॥<br />পরকীয় মহারাস গোলোকের নিত্যধন ।<br />আনিল ব্রজের সহ নন্দযশোদানন্দন ॥৫॥<br />সেই ঠাকুর আবার নিজের যোগ-মায়াপুর ।<br />প্রপঞ্চে আনিল গৌড়ে রসাস্বাদ সুচতুর ॥৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ye ṭhākura dvāparera śeṣa vṛndāvane vane<br />mahārāsa-krīḍā kaila rādhikādi gopī sane [4]<br />parakīya mahārāsa golokera nitya-dhana<br />ānila vrajera saha nanda-yaśodā-nandana [5]<br />sei ṭhākura ābāra nijera yoga-māyāpura<br />prapañche ānila gauḍe rasāsvāda suchatura [6]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">ye</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ṭhākura</span>–The Lord who <span class=\\"e2\\">kaila</span>–performed <span class=\\"e2\\">mahārāsa-krīḍā</span>–the Mahārāsa-līlā <span class=\\"e2\\">sane</span>–with <span class=\\"e2\\">rādhikādi</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">gopī</span>–Rādhikā and the gopīs <span class=\\"e2\\">vṛndāvane</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">vane</span>–in the forest of Vṛndāvan <span class=\\"e2\\">dvāparera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">śeṣa</span>–at the end of the Dvāpar-yuga, <span class=\\"e2\\">nanda-yaśodā-nandana</span>–the son of Nanda and Yaśodā [who] <span class=\\"e2\\">ānila</span>–brought <span class=\\"e2\\">golokera</span>–Goloka’s <span class=\\"e2\\">nitya-dhana</span>–eternal wealth— <span class=\\"e2\\">mahārāsa</span>–the Mahārāsa-līlā <span class=\\"e2\\">parakīya</span>–in paramour love— <span class=\\"e2\\">vrajera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">saha</span>–with Vraja [to this earth—] <span class=\\"e2\\">sei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ṭhākura</span>–this Lord, <span class=\\"e2\\">rasāsvāda</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">suchatura</span>–the connoisseur of rasa, <span class=\\"e2\\">ābāra</span>–again <span class=\\"e2\\">ānila</span>–has brought <span class=\\"e2\\">nijera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">yoga-māyāpura</span>–His abode of Yogamāyāpur <span class=\\"e2\\">prapañche</span>–to the earth <span class=\\"e2\\">gauḍe</span>–in Gauḍa."},{"class":"b71","text":" As the son of Nanda and Yaśodā, the Lord performed the Rāsa-līlā with Rādhikā and the gopīs in the forest of Vṛndāvan at the end of the Dvāpar-yuga. He brought Goloka’s eternal wealth—the Rāsa-līlā in paramour love—with Vraja to this earth, and now this Lord, the connoisseur of rasa, has again brought His abode of Yogamāyāpur to the earth in Gauḍa."},{"class":"b176","text":" গৌরাবতারের হেতু"},{"class":"b177","text":" gaurāvatārera hetu"},{"class":"b70","text":" The reason for Gaura’s appearance"},{"class":"b97","text":" শ্রীকৃষ্ণলীলায় বাঞ্ছাত্রয় না হৈল পূরণ ।<br />শ্রীগৌরলীলায় পূর্ণ কৈল সে সুখ সাধন ॥৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" śrī-kṛṣṇa-līlāya vāñchhā-traya nā haila pūraṇa<br />śrī-gaura-līlāya pūrṇa kaila se sukha sādhana [7]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-kṛṣṇa-līlāya</span>–During [His] Pastimes as Śrī Kṛṣṇa, <span class=\\"e2\\">vāñchhā-traya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">pūraṇa haila nā</span>–the Lord had three unfulfilled desires. <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-gaura-līlāya</span>–During [His] Pastimes as Śrī Gaura, <span class=\\"e2\\">pūrṇa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kaila</span>–the Lord completed [His] <span class=\\"e2\\">sādhana</span>–endeavour <span class=\\"e2\\">se</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sukha</span>–for that satisfaction."},{"class":"b50","text":" During His Pastimes as Śrī Kṛṣṇa, the Lord had three unfulfilled desires, and during His Pastimes as Śrī Gaura, He fulfilled them."},{"class":"b97","text":" “মোরে প্রণয় করি’ রাধা পায় কিবা সুখ ।<br />মোর মাধুর্য-আস্বাদনে রাধার কত যে কৌতুক ॥৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" “more praṇaya kari’ rādhā pāya kibā sukha<br />mora mādhurya-āsvādane rādhāra kata ye kautuka [8]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">“kibā</span>–“What sort <span class=\\"e2\\">sukha</span>–of happiness <span class=\\"e2\\">rādhā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">pāya</span>–does Rādhā feel <span class=\\"e2\\">praṇaya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kari’</span>–by loving <span class=\\"e2\\">more</span>–Me? <span class=\\"e2\\">kata</span>–How great [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">rādhāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ye</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kautuka</span>–Rādhā’s delight <span class=\\"e2\\">mora mādhurya-āsvādane</span>–in tasting My sweetness?"},{"class":"b50","text":" “What sort of happiness does Rādhā feel by loving Me? How great is Rādhā’s delight in tasting My sweetness?"},{"class":"b97","text":" আমার অনুভবে রাধায় সৌখ্য কি প্রকার ।<br />নায়ক হঞা নাহি বুঝি এ সুখের সার ॥৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" āmāra anubhave rādhāya saukhya ki prakāra<br />nāyaka hañā nāhi bujhi e sukhera sāra [9]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">ki</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">prakāra</span>–What sort <span class=\\"e2\\">saukhya</span>–of joy [arises] <span class=\\"e2\\">rādhāya</span>–in Rādhā [in Her] <span class=\\"e2\\">anubhave</span>–experience <span class=\\"e2\\">āmāra</span>–of Me? <span class=\\"e2\\">hañā</span>–Being <span class=\\"e2\\">nāyaka</span>–the beloved, <span class=\\"e2\\">bujhi nāhi</span>–I do not understand <span class=\\"e2\\">sāra</span>–the essence <span class=\\"e2\\">e</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sukhera</span>–of this happiness."},{"class":"b50","text":" “What sort of joy does Rādhā feel in Her experience of Me? Being Her beloved, I do not understand the essence of this happiness."},{"class":"b97","text":" অতএব রাধার ভাবকান্তি লঞা গৌর হব ।<br />কৃষ্ণমাধুর্য্যাদি ভক্তভাবে আস্বাদ পাইব” ॥১০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ataeva rādhāra bhāva-kānti lañā gaura haba<br />kṛṣṇa-mādhuryādi bhakta-bhāve āsvāda pāiba” [10]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">ataeva</span>–So, <span class=\\"e2\\">lañā</span>–I will take <span class=\\"e2\\">rādhāra</span>–Rādhā’s <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāva-kānti</span>–heart and halo [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">haba</span>–become <span class=\\"e2\\">gaura</span>–Gaura. <span class=\\"e2\\">āsvāda pāiba</span>–I will relish <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-mādhuryādi</span>–Kṛṣṇa’s sweetness and other qualities <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakta-bhāve”</span>–in the mood of a devotee.”"},{"class":"b50","text":" “So, I will take Rādhā’s heart and halo and become Gaura. I will relish Kṛṣṇa’s sweetness in the mood of a devotee.”"},{"class":"b97","text":" এত ভাবি’ কৃষ্ণ নিজধাম লঞা গৌড়-দেশে ।<br />নবদ্বীপে প্রকটিল স্বয়ং আনন্দ-আবেশে ॥১১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" eta bhāvi’ kṛṣṇa nija-dhāma lañā gauḍa-deśe<br />navadvīpe prakaṭila svayaṁ ānanda-āveśe [11]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāvi’</span>–Thinking <span class=\\"e2\\">eta</span>–this, <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span>–Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">lañā</span>–took <span class=\\"e2\\">nija-dhāma</span>–His abode <span class=\\"e2\\">gauḍa-deśe</span>–to the land of Gauḍa [and,] <span class=\\"e2\\">ānanda-āveśe</span>–overwhelmed with joy, <span class=\\"e2\\">prakaṭila</span>–manifested <span class=\\"e2\\">svayaṁ</span>–Himself <span class=\\"e2\\">navadvīpe</span>–in Nabadwīp."},{"class":"b71","text":" Thinking in this way, Kṛṣṇa took His abode to the land of Gauḍa and, overwhelmed with joy, manifested Himself in Nabadwīp."},{"class":"b176","text":" গৌরের ভজন-প্রণালীতে কৃষ্ণভজন"},{"class":"b177","text":" gaurera bhajana-praṇālīte kṛṣṇa-bhajana"},{"class":"b70","text":" Serving Gaura is the way to serve Kṛṣṇa"},{"class":"b97","text":" ওরে ভাই সব ছাড়ি’ বৈস নবদ্বীপপুরে ।<br />গৌরাঙ্গের অষ্টকাল ভজ, দুঃখ যাবে দূরে ॥১২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ore bhāi saba chhāḍi’ vaisa navadvīpapure<br />gaurāṅgera aṣṭa-kāla bhaja, duḥkha yābe dūre [12]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">ore</span>–O <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāi</span>–brother, <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍi’</span>–give up <span class=\\"e2\\">saba</span>–everything [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">vaisa</span>–stay <span class=\\"e2\\">navadvīpapure</span>–in the town of Nabadwīp. <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaja</span>–Serve <span class=\\"e2\\">gaurāṅgera</span>–Gaurāṅga <span class=\\"e2\\">aṣṭa-kāla</span>–throughout the eight periods of the day, [and your] <span class=\\"e2\\">duḥkha</span>–sadness <span class=\\"e2\\">yābe</span>–will go <span class=\\"e2\\">dūre</span>–away."},{"class":"b50","text":" O brother, give up everything and stay in Nabadwīp. Serve Gaurāṅga throughout the eight periods of the day and your sadness will go away."},{"class":"b97","text":" অষ্টকালে অষ্টপরকার কৃষ্ণলীলা-সার ।<br />গৌরোদিত ভাবে ভজ, পাবে প্রেম চমৎকার ॥১৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" aṣṭa-kāle aṣṭa-parakāra kṛṣṇa-līlā-sāra<br />gaurodita bhāve bhaja, pābe prema chamatkāra [13]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāve</span>–In the mood <span class=\\"e2\\">gaurodita</span>–revealed by Gaura, <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaja</span>–worship <span class=\\"e2\\">aṣṭa-parakāra</span>–the eight modes <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-līlā-sāra</span>–of Kṛṣṇa’s super-excellent Pastimes <span class=\\"e2\\">aṣṭa-kāle</span>–during the eight periods of the day, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">pābe</span>–you will attain <span class=\\"e2\\">chamatkāra</span>–astonishing <span class=\\"e2\\">prema</span>–divine love."},{"class":"b50","text":" In the mood revealed by Gaura, worship the eight modes of Kṛṣṇa’s super-excellent Pastimes during the eight periods of the day and you will attain astonishing divine love."},{"class":"b97","text":" কৃষ্ণ ভজিবারে যার একান্ত আছে মন ।<br />গৌড়ের অষ্টকালে ভজ কৃষ্ণরসধন ॥১৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kṛṣṇa bhajibāre yāra ekānta āchhe mana<br />gauḍera aṣṭa-kāle bhaja kṛṣṇa-rasa-dhana [14]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">yāra mana āchhe</span>–Those who want <span class=\\"e2\\">ekānta</span>–sincerely <span class=\\"e2\\">bhajibāre</span>–to serve <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span>–Kṛṣṇa, <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaja</span>–should serve <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-rasa-dhana</span>–Gaura, whose wealth is devotion to Krṣṇa, <span class=\\"e2\\">aṣṭa-kāle</span>–during the eight periods of the day <span class=\\"e2\\">gauḍera</span>–in Gauḍa."},{"class":"b50","text":" Those who sincerely want to serve Kṛṣṇa should serve Gaura, whose wealth is devotion to Kṛṣṇa, during the eight periods of the day in Gauḍa."},{"class":"b97","text":" গৌরভাব নাহি জানে যে কৃষ্ণ ভজিতে চায় ।<br />অপ্রাকৃত কৃষ্ণতত্ত্ব তার কভু নাহি ভায় ॥১৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" gaura-bhāva nāhi jāne ye kṛṣṇa bhajite chāya<br />aprākṛta kṛṣṇa-tattva tāra kabhu nāhi bhāya [15]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra ye</span>–Those who <span class=\\"e2\\">chāya</span>–want <span class=\\"e2\\">bhajite</span>–to serve <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span>–Kṛṣṇa [but] <span class=\\"e2\\">jāne nāhi</span>–do not understand <span class=\\"e2\\">gaura-bhāva</span>–Gaura’s mood [will] <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāhi</span>–never <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāya</span>–perceive <span class=\\"e2\\">aprākṛta</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-tattva</span>–Kṛṣṇa’s divine nature."},{"class":"b71","text":" Those who want to serve Kṛṣṇa but do not understand Gaura’s mood will never perceive Kṛṣṇa’s divine nature."},{"class":"b176","text":" আচার্য বর্ণাশ্রমে আবদ্ধ নহেন"},{"class":"b177","text":" āchārya varṇāśrame ābaddha nahena"},{"class":"b70","text":" An Āchārya is not restricted by socio-religious principles"},{"class":"b97","text":" কিবা বর্ণী, কিবাশ্রমী, কিবা বর্ণাশ্রমহীন ।<br />কৃষ্ণতত্ত্ব বেত্তা যেই, সেই আচার্য প্রবীণ ॥১৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kibā varṇī, kibāśramī, kibā varṇāśrama-hīna<br />kṛṣṇa-tattva vettā yei, sei āchārya pravīṇa [16]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sei yei</span>–Anyone [who] <span class=\\"e2\\">vettā</span>–knows <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-tattva</span>–Kṛṣṇa’s nature [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">pravīṇa āchārya</span>–an expert Āchārya, <span class=\\"e2\\">kibā</span>–whether [they] <span class=\\"e2\\">varṇī</span>–belong to a social order, <span class=\\"e2\\">kibāśramī</span>–whether they belong to a religious order, [or] <span class=\\"e2\\">kibā</span>–whether <span class=\\"e2\\">varṇāśrama-hīna</span>–they have no religious or social order."},{"class":"b71","text":" Anyone who knows Kṛṣṇa’s nature is an expert Āchārya, whether they belong to a religious and social order or not."},{"class":"b176","text":" অসদ্গুরুগ্রহণে সর্ব্বনাশ"},{"class":"b177","text":" asad-guru-grahaṇe sarva-nāśa"},{"class":"b70","text":" By accepting a false guru, everything is lost"},{"class":"b97","text":" আসল কথা ছেড়ে ভাই বর্ণে যে করে আদর ।<br />অসদ্গুরু করি’ তার বিনষ্ট পূর্ব্বাপর ॥১৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" āsala kathā chheḍe bhāi varṇe ye kare ādara<br />asad-guru kari’ tāra vinaṣṭa pūrvāpara [17]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāi</span>–Brother, <span class=\\"e2\\">pūrvāpara</span>–the past and future <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra ye</span>–of those who <span class=\\"e2\\">chheḍe</span>–reject <span class=\\"e2\\">āsala</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kathā</span>–truth, <span class=\\"e2\\">ādara kare</span>–revere <span class=\\"e2\\">varṇe</span>–social status, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">kari’</span>–accept <span class=\\"e2\\">asad-guru</span>–a false guru [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">vinaṣṭa</span>–ruined."},{"class":"b55","text":" Brother, the past and future of those who reject truth, revere social status, and accept a false guru are ruined."}]},{"title":"Glories of the Vaiṣṇavas","paragraphs":[{"class":"b46","text":"\\r"},{"class":"b58","text":" Chapter Twelve"},{"class":"b120","text":" বৈষ্ণব-মহিমা"},{"class":"b121","text":" Vaiṣṇava-mahimā"},{"class":"b175","text":" Glories of the Vaiṣṇavas"},{"class":"b176","text":" কৃষ্ণভক্তি ও তীর্থ"},{"class":"b177","text":" kṛṣṇa-bhakti o tīrtha"},{"class":"b70","text":" Devotion to Kṛṣṇa and holy places"},{"class":"b97","text":" জলময় তীর্থ মৃৎশিলাময় মূর্ত্তি ।<br />বহুকালে দেয় জীবহৃদে ধর্ম্ম স্ফূর্ত্তি ॥১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" jalamaya tīrtha mṛtśilāmaya mūrti<br />bahu-kāle deya jīva-hṛde dharma sphūrti [1]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">jalamaya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">tīrtha</span>–Holy waters [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">mṛtśilāmaya mūrti</span>–earthen Deities <span class=\\"e2\\">sphūrti deya</span>–reveal <span class=\\"e2\\">dharma</span>–religion <span class=\\"e2\\">jīva-hṛde</span>–in the hearts of souls <span class=\\"e2\\">bahu-kāle</span>–over the course of a long time."},{"class":"b50","text":" Holy waters and earthen Deities gradually reveal dharma in the hearts of souls."},{"class":"b97","text":" কৃষ্ণভক্ত দেখি’ দূরে যায় সর্ব্বানর্থ ।<br />কৃষ্ণভক্তি সমুদিত হয় পরমার্থ ॥২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kṛṣṇa-bhakta dekhi’ dūre yāya sarvānartha<br />kṛṣṇa-bhakti samudita haya paramārtha [2]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [But simply] <span class=\\"e2\\">dekhi’</span>–by seeing <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-bhakta</span>–a devotee of Kṛṣṇa, <span class=\\"e2\\">sarvānartha</span>–all obstacles <span class=\\"e2\\">yāya</span>–go <span class=\\"e2\\">dūre</span>–away [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">paramārtha</span>–the supreme wealth— <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-bhakti</span>–devotion to Kṛṣṇa— <span class=\\"e2\\">samudita</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–arises in full."},{"class":"b71","text":" But simply by seeing a devotee of Kṛṣṇa, all obstacles go away and the supreme wealth—devotion to Kṛṣṇa—arises in full."},{"class":"b176","text":" সাধুসঙ্গের ফল"},{"class":"b177","text":" sādhu-saṅgera phala"},{"class":"b70","text":" The result of association with sādhus"},{"class":"b97","text":" সংসার ভ্রমিতে ভব-ক্ষয়োন্মুখ যবে ।<br />সাধুসঙ্গ-সংঘটন ভাগ্যক্রমে হবে ॥৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" saṁsāra bhramite bhava-kṣayonmukha yabe<br />sādhu-saṅga-saṁghaṭana bhāgya-krame habe [3]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">yabe</span>–When <span class=\\"e2\\">bhramite</span>–the souls’ wandering <span class=\\"e2\\">saṁsāra</span>–throughout the world <span class=\\"e2\\">bhava-kṣayonmukha</span>–comes to an end, [then] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāgya-krame</span>–according to their fortune, <span class=\\"e2\\">sādhu-saṅga-saṁghaṭana habe</span>–they attain the association of the sādhus."},{"class":"b50","text":" When the souls’ wandering throughout saṁsāra comes to an end, then, according to their fortune, they attain the association of the sādhus."},{"class":"b97","text":" সাধুসঙ্গফলে কৃষ্ণে সর্ব্বেশ্বরেশ্বরে ।<br />ভাবোদয় হয় ভাই জীবের অন্তরে ॥৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sādhu-saṅga-phale kṛṣṇe sarveśvareśvare<br />bhāvodaya haya bhāi jīvera antare [4]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāi</span>–Brother, <span class=\\"e2\\">sādhu-saṅga-phale</span>–as a result of this association with the sādhus, <span class=\\"e2\\">sarveśvareśvare kṛṣṇe bhāvodaya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–devotion to Kṛṣṇa, the Lord of all Lords, appears <span class=\\"e2\\">jīvera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">antare</span>–within the hearts of the souls."},{"class":"b71","text":" Brother, as a result of this association with the sādhus, devotion to Kṛṣṇa, the Lord of all Lords, appears within their hearts."},{"class":"b176","text":" প্রাকৃত বা কনিষ্ঠ ভক্ত"},{"class":"b177","text":" prākṛta vā kaniṣṭha bhakta"},{"class":"b70","text":" The beginner or neophyte devotee"},{"class":"b97","text":" সেই ত’ প্রাকৃত ভক্ত দীক্ষিত হইয়া ।<br />কৃষ্ণার্চ্চন করে বিধিমার্গেতে বসিয়া ॥৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sei ta’ prākṛta bhakta dīkṣita ha-iyā<br />kṛṣṇārchana kare vidhi-mārgete vasiyā [5]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ta’</span>–These <span class=\\"e2\\">prākṛta</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakta</span>–beginner devotees <span class=\\"e2\\">dīkṣita</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-iyā</span>–become initiated [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇārchana</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kare</span>–worship Kṛṣṇa, <span class=\\"e2\\">vasiyā</span>–following <span class=\\"e2\\">vidhi-mārgete</span>–the regulated path."},{"class":"b50","text":" These beginner devotees become initiated and worship Kṛṣṇa according to the regulated path."},{"class":"b97","text":" উত্তম মধ্যম ভক্ত না করে বিচার ।<br />শুদ্ধভক্তে সমাদর না হয় তাহার ॥৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" uttama madhyama bhakta nā kare vichāra<br />śuddha-bhakte samādara nā haya tāhāra [6]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">vichāra kare nā</span>–They cannot judge [who is] <span class=\\"e2\\">uttama</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">madhyama</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakta</span>–an advanced or intermediate devotee, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhāra samādara</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haya nā</span>–they do not appreciate <span class=\\"e2\\">śuddha-bhakta</span>–pure devotees."},{"class":"b71","text":" They cannot judge who is an advanced or intermediate devotee and do not appreciate pure devotees."},{"class":"b176","text":" মধ্যম ভক্ত"},{"class":"b177","text":" madhyama bhakta"},{"class":"b70","text":" The intermediate devotee"},{"class":"b97","text":" কৃষ্ণে প্রেম, ভক্তে মৈত্রী, মূঢ়ে কৃপা আর ।<br />শুদ্ধভক্তদ্বেষী উপেক্ষা যাঁহার ॥৭॥<br />তিহোঁ ত’ প্রকৃত ভক্তিসাধক মধ্যম ।<br />অতি শীঘ্র কৃষ্ণ-বলে হইবে উত্তম ॥৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kṛṣṇe prema, bhakte maitrī, mūḍhe kṛpā āra<br />śuddha-bhakta-dveṣī upekṣā yā̐hāra [7]<br />tiho̐ ta’ prakṛta bhakti-sādhaka madhyama<br />ati śīghra kṛṣṇa-bale ha-ibe uttama [8]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">tiho̐</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ta’ yā̐hāra</span>–Those who have <span class=\\"e2\\">prema</span>–love <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇe</span>–for Kṛṣṇa, <span class=\\"e2\\">maitrī</span>–friendship <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakte</span>–with devotees, <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛpā</span>–compassion <span class=\\"e2\\">mūḍhe</span>–for the ignorant, <span class=\\"e2\\">āra</span>–and <span class=\\"e2\\">upekṣā</span>–disregard <span class=\\"e2\\">śuddha-bhakta-dveṣī</span>–for those who are inimical to pure devotees [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">prakṛta</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">madhyama bhakti-sādhaka</span>–genuine intermediate practitioners of devotion. <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-bale</span>–By Kṛṣṇa’s grace, <span class=\\"e2\\">uttama ha-ibe</span>–they become advanced <span class=\\"e2\\">ati</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">śīghra</span>–very quickly."},{"class":"b71","text":" Those who have love for Kṛṣṇa, friendship with devotees, compassion for the ignorant, and disregard for those who are inimical to pure devotees are intermediate practitioners of devotion. By Kṛṣṇa’s grace, they very quickly become advanced devotees."},{"class":"b176","text":" উত্তম ভক্ত"},{"class":"b177","text":" uttama bhakta"},{"class":"b70","text":" The advanced devotee"},{"class":"b97","text":" সর্ব্বভূতে শ্রীকৃষ্ণের ভাব সন্দর্শন ।<br />ভগবানে সর্ব্বভূতে করেন দর্শন ॥৯॥<br />শত্রু-মিত্র-বিষয়েতে নাহি রাগদ্বেষ ।<br />তিহোঁ ভাগবতোত্তম এই গৌর-উপদেশ ॥১০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sarva-bhūte śrī-kṛṣṇera bhāva sandarśana<br />bhagavāne sarva-bhūte karena darśana [9]<br />śatru-mitra-viṣayete nāhi rāga-dveṣa<br />tiho̐ bhāgavatottama ei gaura-upadeśa [10]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">tiho̐</span>–Those [who] <span class=\\"e2\\">sandarśana</span>–see <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-kṛṣṇera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāva</span>–the presence of Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-bhūte</span>–in all beings [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">darśana karena</span>–see <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-bhūte</span>–all beings <span class=\\"e2\\">bhagavāne</span>–within the Lord, [and who] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāhi</span>–have no <span class=\\"e2\\">rāga-dveṣa</span>–attachment or aversion <span class=\\"e2\\">śatru-mitra-viṣayete</span>–to enemies, friends, or the world [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāgavatottama</span>–advanced devotees. <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span>–These [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">gaura-upadeśa</span>–Gaura’s teachings."},{"class":"b71","text":" Those who see the presence of Kṛṣṇa in all beings, see all beings within Kṛṣṇa, and have no attachment or aversion to enemies, friends, or the world are advanced devotees. These are Gaura’s teachings."},{"class":"b176","text":" উত্তম ভক্তের বিষয়-স্বীকার"},{"class":"b177","text":" uttama bhaktera viṣaya-svīkāra"},{"class":"b70","text":" How the advanced devotee accepts material things"},{"class":"b97","text":" বিষয় ইন্দ্রিয়দ্বারে করিয়া স্বীকার ।<br />রাগদ্বেষহীন ভক্তি জীবনে যাঁহার ॥১১॥<br />সমস্ত জগৎ দেখি’ বিষ্ণুমায়াময় ।<br />ভাগবতগণোত্তম সেই মহাশয় ॥১২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" viṣaya indriya-dvāre kariyā svīkāra<br />rāga-dveṣa-hīna bhakti jīvane yā̐hāra [11]<br />samasta jagat dekhi’ viṣṇu-māyā-maya<br />bhāgavata-gaṇottama sei mahāśaya [12]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">mahāśaya yā̐hāra</span>–Those great souls who <span class=\\"e2\\">svīkāra kariyā</span>–accept <span class=\\"e2\\">viṣaya</span>–material things <span class=\\"e2\\">indriya-dvāre</span>–through [their] senses <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakti</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">jīvane</span>–in [their] life of devotion [but] <span class=\\"e2\\">rāga-dveṣa-hīna</span>–have no attachment or aversion, [and who] <span class=\\"e2\\">dekhi’</span>–see <span class=\\"e2\\">samasta</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">jagat</span>–the entire world [to be] <span class=\\"e2\\">viṣṇu-māyā-maya</span>–made of Viṣṇu’s energy, [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāgavata-gaṇottama</span>–advanced amongst the devotees of the Lord."},{"class":"b71","text":" Those great souls who accept material things through their senses but live a life of devotion free from attachment and aversion, and who see the entire world as a manifestation of Viṣṇu’s energy, are advanced amongst the devotees of the Lord."},{"class":"b176","text":" তাঁহার ইন্দ্রিয় বৃত্তি পরিচালন"},{"class":"b177","text":" tā̐hāra indriya-vṛtti parichālana"},{"class":"b70","text":" How they control the work of their senses"},{"class":"b97","text":" দেহেন্দ্রিয়-প্রাণ-মন-বুদ্ধি-যুক্ত-সবে ।<br />জন্ম নাশ ক্ষুধা তৃষ্ণা ভয় উপদ্রবে ॥১৩॥<br />অনিত্য সংসার-ধর্ম্মে হঞা মোহহীন ।<br />কৃষ্ণ স্মরি’ কাল কাটে ভক্ত সমীচীন ॥১৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" dehendriya-prāṇa-mana-buddhi-yukta-sabe<br />janma nāśa kṣudhā tṛṣṇā bhaya upadrave [13]<span class=\\"e2\\"><br /></span>anitya saṁsāra-dharme hañā moha-hīna<br />kṛṣṇa smari’ kāla kāṭe bhakta samīchīna [14]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [Although] <span class=\\"e2\\">dehendriya-prāṇa-mana-buddhi-yukta-sabe</span>–they have a body, senses, a life-force, a mind, and intelligence, <span class=\\"e2\\">samīchīna bhakta</span>–wise devotees <span class=\\"e2\\">moha-hīna hañā</span>–remaining unaffected <span class=\\"e2\\">janma</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāśa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kṣudhā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">tṛṣṇā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">upadrave</span>–by birth, death, hunger, thirst, fear, and disturbances, [as well as] <span class=\\"e2\\">anitya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">saṁsāra-dharme</span>–the temporary nature of this world. <span class=\\"e2\\">kāla</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kāṭe</span>–They spend [their] time <span class=\\"e2\\">smari’</span>–remembering <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span>–Kṛṣṇa."},{"class":"b71","text":" Although they have a body, senses, a life-force, a mind, and intelligence, wise devotees remain unaffected by birth, death, hunger, thirst, fear, and disturbances, as well as the temporary nature of this world. They spend their time remembering Kṛṣṇa."},{"class":"b176","text":" তাঁহার কর্ম্ম দেহযাত্রার্থে মাত্র—কামের জন্য নহে"},{"class":"b177","text":" tā̐hāra karma deha-yātrārthe mātra—kāmera janya nahe"},{"class":"b70","text":" Their worldly activities are only for the maintenance of their body—not for selfish enjoyment"},{"class":"b97","text":" যাঁর চিত্তে নিরন্তর যশোদানন্দন ।<br />দেহযাত্রামাত্র কামকর্ম্মের গ্রহণ ॥১৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" yā̐ra chitte nirantara yaśodā-nandana<br />deha-yātrā-mātra kāma-karmera grahaṇa [15]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">yā̐ra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">chitte</span>–Devotees in whose heart <span class=\\"e2\\">yaśodā-nandana</span>–Kṛṣṇa [is present] <span class=\\"e2\\">nirantara</span>–always <span class=\\"e2\\">grahaṇa</span>–accept [engagement in] <span class=\\"e2\\">kāma-karmera</span>–worldly actions <span class=\\"e2\\">deha-yātrā-mātra</span>–only to maintain their bodies."},{"class":"b50","text":" Devotees in whose heart Kṛṣṇa is always present accept engagement in worldly actions only to maintain their bodies."},{"class":"b97","text":" কামকর্ম্মবীজরূপ বাসনা তাঁহার ।<br />চিত্তে নাহি জন্মে এই ভক্তিতত্ত্বসার ॥১৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kāma-karma-bīja-rūpa vāsanā tā̐hāra<br />chitte nāhi janme ei bhakti-tattva-sāra [16]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">vāsanā</span>–Material desire,<span class=\\"e2\\"> kāma-karma-bīja-rūpa</span>–the seed of worldly actions, <span class=\\"e2\\">janme nāhi</span>–does not arise <span class=\\"e2\\">tā̐hāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">chitte</span>–in their heart. <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span>–This [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakti-tattva-sāra</span>–the essence of the nature of devotion."},{"class":"b71","text":" Material desire—the seed of worldly actions—does not arise in their heart. This is the essence of devotion."},{"class":"b176","text":" হরিজন দেহাত্মবুদ্ধিহীন"},{"class":"b177","text":" hari-jana dehātma-buddhi-hīna"},{"class":"b70","text":" The surrendered soul has no conception of the body being the self"},{"class":"b97","text":" জ্ঞান-কর্ম্ম-বর্ণাশ্রম দেহের স্বভাব ।<br />তাহে সঙ্গদ্বারা হয় ‘অহং-মম’-ভাব ॥১৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" jñāna-karma-varṇāśrama dehera svabhāva<br />tāhe saṅga-dvārā haya ‘ahaṁ-mama’-bhāva [17]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">jñāna-karma-varṇāśrama</span>–Knowledge, action, and social duties [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">svabhāva</span>–attributes <span class=\\"e2\\">dehera</span>–of the body, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">‘ahaṁ-mama’-bhāva</span>–the conception of ‘I’ and ‘mine’ <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–arise <span class=\\"e2\\">saṅga-dvārā</span>–through attachment <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhe</span>–to them."},{"class":"b50","text":" Knowledge, action, and social duties are attributes of the body, and the conceptions of ‘I’ and ‘mine’ arise through attachment to them."},{"class":"b97","text":" দেহসত্ত্বে ‘অহং-মম’-ভাব নাহি যাঁর ।<br />হরিপ্রিয়জন তিহোঁ, করহ বিচার ॥১৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" deha-sattve ‘ahaṁ-mama’-bhāva nāhi yā̐ra<br />hari-priya-jana tiho̐, karaha vichāra [18]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">vichāra karaha</span>–Consider <span class=\\"e2\\">tiho̐ yā̐ra nāhi</span>–those who have no <span class=\\"e2\\">‘ahaṁ-mama’-bhāva</span>–conception of ‘I’ or ‘mine’ <span class=\\"e2\\">deha-sattve</span>–in relation to [their] body [to be] <span class=\\"e2\\">hari-priya-jana</span>–dear to the Lord."},{"class":"b71","text":" Consider those who have no conception of ‘I’ or ‘mine’ in relation to their body to be dear to the Lord."},{"class":"b176","text":" সর্ব্বভূতে সমবুদ্ধিসম্পন্ন"},{"class":"b177","text":" sarva-bhūte sama-buddhi-sampanna"},{"class":"b70","text":" Equality towards all beings"},{"class":"b97","text":" বিত্তসত্ত্বে তাহে ছাড়ি’ স্ব-পরভাবনা ।<br />‘তুমি’ ‘আমি’-সত্ত্বভেদে মিত্রারি-কল্পনা ॥১৯॥<br />সর্ব্বভূতে সমবুদ্ধি শান্ত যেই জন ।<br />ভাগবতোত্তম বলি’ তাঁহার গণন ॥২০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" vitta-sattve tāhe chhāḍi’ sva-para-bhāvanā<br />‘tumi’ ‘āmi’-sattva-bhede mitrāri-kalpanā [19]<br />sarva-bhūte sama-buddhi śānta yei jana<br />bhāgavatottama bali’ tā̐hāra gaṇana [20]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">tā̐hāra yei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">śānta jana</span>–Peaceful souls who <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍi’</span>–reject <span class=\\"e2\\">sva-para-bhāvanā</span>–the conceptions of ‘mine’ and ‘other’s’ <span class=\\"e2\\">vitta-sattve tāhe</span>–with regard to property, <span class=\\"e2\\">sattva-bhede</span>–the distinction between <span class=\\"e2\\">‘tumi’</span>–‘You’ [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">‘āmi’</span>–‘I’, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">mitrāri-kalpanā</span>–the conceptions of friends and enemies, [and who are] <span class=\\"e2\\">sama-buddhi</span>–equal <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-bhūte</span>–towards all beings, [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">gaṇana</span>–considered <span class=\\"e2\\">bali’</span>–to be <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāgavatottama</span>–advanced devotees."},{"class":"b50","text":" Peaceful souls who reject the conceptions of ‘mine’ and ‘other’s’ regarding property, reject distinctions between themself and others, reject the conceptions of friends and enemies, and are equal towards all beings, are advanced devotees."},{"class":"b97","text":" কৃষ্ণপাদপদ্মে সেই সুরমৃগ্য ধন ।<br />ভুবনবৈভব লাগি’ না ছাড়ে যে জন ॥২১॥<br />কৃষ্ণপদস্মৃতি নিমেষার্ধ নাহি ত্যজে ।<br />বৈষ্ণব-অগ্রণী তিহোঁ পরানন্দে মজে ॥২২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kṛṣṇa-pāda-padme sei sura-mṛgya dhana<br />bhuvana-vaibhava lāgi’ nā chhāḍe ye jana [21]<br />kṛṣṇa-pada-smṛti nimeṣārdha nāhi tyaje<br />vaiṣṇava-agraṇī tiho̐ parānande maje [22]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">tiho̐ ye</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">jana</span>–Those who <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍe nā</span>–do not leave <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-pāda-padme</span>–Kṛṣṇa’s lotus feet— <span class=\\"e2\\">sei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sura-mṛgya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">dhana</span>–the wealth sought by the wise— <span class=\\"e2\\">lāgi’</span>–for the sake of <span class=\\"e2\\">bhuvana-vaibhava</span>–worldly opulence, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">tyaje nāhi</span>–do not neglect <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-pada-smṛti</span>–remem­bering Kṛṣṇa’s feet <span class=\\"e2\\">nimeṣārdha</span>–for half a second, [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">vaiṣṇava-agraṇī</span>–advanced devotees [and are] <span class=\\"e2\\">maje</span>–immersed <span class=\\"e2\\">parānande</span>–in divine ecstasy."},{"class":"b71","text":" Those who do not leave Kṛṣṇa’s lotus feet—the wealth sought by the wise—for the sake of worldly opulence, and do not forget Kṛṣṇa’s feet for even half a second, are advanced devotees and are immersed in divine ecstasy."},{"class":"b176","text":" ভক্ত ত্রিতাপমুক্ত"},{"class":"b177","text":" bhakta tritāpa-mukta"},{"class":"b70","text":" The devotee is free from the three miseries"},{"class":"b97","text":" কৃষ্ণপদশাখানখমণিচন্দ্রিকায় ।<br />নিরস্ত সকল তাপ যাঁহার হিয়ায় ॥২৩॥<br />সে কেন বিষয়সূর্য্যতাপ অন্বেষিবে ।<br />হৃদয় শীতল তার সর্ব্বদা রহিবে ॥২৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kṛṣṇa-pada-śākhā-nakha-maṇi-chandrikāya<br />nirasta sakala tāpa yā̐hāra hiyāya [23]<br />se kena viṣaya-sūrya-tāpa anveṣibe<br />hṛdaya śītala tāra sarvadā rahibe [24]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kena</span>–Why [would] <span class=\\"e2\\">se</span>–the soul <span class=\\"e2\\">yā̐hāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">hiyāya</span>–from whose heart <span class=\\"e2\\">sakala</span>–all <span class=\\"e2\\">tāpa</span>–miseries [have been] <span class=\\"e2\\">nirasta</span>–driven away <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-pada-śākhā-nakha-maṇi-chandrikāya</span>–by the moonlight from the jewel-like toenails of Kṛṣṇa’s feet <span class=\\"e2\\">anveṣibe</span>–seek <span class=\\"e2\\">viṣaya-sūrya-tāpa</span>–the misery produced by the sun of mundanity? <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra</span>–Their <span class=\\"e2\\">hṛdaya</span>–heart <span class=\\"e2\\">rahibe</span>–will remain <span class=\\"e2\\">śītala</span>–cool <span class=\\"e2\\">sarvadā</span>–always."},{"class":"b71","text":" Why would the soul from whose heart all miseries have been driven away by the moonlight from the jewel-like toenails of Kṛṣṇa’s feet seek the misery produced by the sun of mundanity? Such a soul’s heart always remains tranquil."},{"class":"b176","text":" উত্তম ভক্তের অন্যান্য লক্ষণ"},{"class":"b177","text":" uttama bhaktera anyānya lakṣaṇa"},{"class":"b70","text":" Other qualities of the advanced devotee"},{"class":"b97","text":" যে বেঁধেছে প্রেমছাঁদে কৃষ্ণাঙ্ঘ্রিকমল ।<br />নাহি ছাড়ে হরি তার হৃদয় সরল ॥২৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ye be̐dhechhe prema-chhā̐de kṛṣṇāṅghri-kamala<br />nāhi chhāḍe hari tāra hṛdaya sarala [25]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">hari</span>–The Lord <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍe nāhi</span>–never leaves <span class=\\"e2\\">sarala hṛdaya</span>–the sincere hearts <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra ye</span>–of those who <span class=\\"e2\\">be̐dhechhe</span>–have bound <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇāṅghri-kamala</span>–Kṛṣṇa’s lotus feet <span class=\\"e2\\">prema-chhā̐de</span>–with the rope of divine love."},{"class":"b50","text":" The Lord never leaves the sincere hearts of those who have bound His lotus feet with the rope of divine love."},{"class":"b97","text":" অবশেও যদি মুখে স্ফুরে কৃষ্ণনাম ।<br />ভাগবতোত্তম সেই, পূর্ণ সর্ব্ব কাম ॥২৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" avaśeo yadi mukhe sphure kṛṣṇa-nāma<br />bhāgavatottama sei, pūrṇa sarva kāma [26]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">yadi</span>–If <span class=\\"e2\\">avaśeo</span>–even involuntarily <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-nāma</span>–the Name of Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">sphure</span>–appears <span class=\\"e2\\">mukhe</span>–in [their] mouth, [then] <span class=\\"e2\\">sei</span>–they [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāgavatottama</span>–an advanced devotee, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kāma</span>–all [their] desires [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">pūrṇa</span>–fulfilled."},{"class":"b50","text":" If even involuntarily the Name of Kṛṣṇa appears in their mouth, then they are an advanced devotee, and all their desires are fulfilled."},{"class":"b97","text":" স্বধর্ম্মের গুণদোষ বুঝিয়া যে জন ।<br />সর্ব্ব ধর্ম্ম ছাড়ি’ ভজে কৃষ্ণের চরণ ॥২৭॥<br />সেই ত’ উত্তম ভক্ত, কেহ তার সম ।<br />না আছে জগতে আর ভাগবতোত্তম ॥২৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" svadharmera guṇa-doṣa bujhiyā ye jana<br />sarva dharma chhāḍi’ bhaje kṛṣṇera charaṇa [27]<br />sei ta’ uttama bhakta, keha tāra sama<br />nā āchhe jagate āra bhāgavatottama [28]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ta’ ye</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">jana</span>–Those who <span class=\\"e2\\">bujhiyā</span>–understand <span class=\\"e2\\">guṇa-doṣa</span>–the qualities and faults <span class=\\"e2\\">svadharmera</span>–of social duties (the duties of their varṇa and āśram), [subsequently] <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍi’</span>–leave aside <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">dharma</span>–all [such] duties, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaje</span>–serve <span class=\\"e2\\">charaṇa</span>–the feet <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇera</span>–of Kṛṣṇa [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">uttama</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakta</span>–advanced devotees. <span class=\\"e2\\">jagate</span>–Throughout the world, <span class=\\"e2\\">keha āchhe nā</span>–there are no <span class=\\"e2\\">āra</span>–other <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāgavatottama</span>–advanced devotees <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sama</span>–equal to them."},{"class":"b50","text":" Those who understand the qualities and faults of social duties, subsequently leave aside all such duties, and serve the feet of Kṛṣṇa are advanced devotees. Throughout the world, there are no advanced devotees equal to them."},{"class":"b97","text":" কৃষ্ণের স্বরূপ আর নামের স্বরূপ ।<br />ভক্তের স্বরূপ আর ভক্তির স্বরূপ ॥২৯॥<br />জানিয়া ভজন করে যেই মহাজন ।<br />তার তুল্য নাহি কেহ বৈষ্ণব সুজন ॥৩০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kṛṣṇera svarūpa āra nāmera svarūpa<br />bhaktera svarūpa āra bhaktira svarūpa [29]<br />jāniyā bhajana kare yei mahājana<br />tāra tulya nāhi keha vaiṣṇava sujana [30]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">keha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">vaiṣṇava</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sujana</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāhi</span>–There are no sincere devotees <span class=\\"e2\\">tulya</span>–comparable <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra yei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">mahājana</span>–to the great souls who <span class=\\"e2\\">bhajana</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kare</span>–engage in service <span class=\\"e2\\">jāniyā</span>–understanding <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">svarūpa</span>–the true nature of Kṛṣṇa, <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">svarūpa</span>–the true nature of the Name, <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaktera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">svarūpa</span>–the true nature of devotees, <span class=\\"e2\\">āra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">āra</span>–and <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaktira</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">svarūpa</span>–the true nature of devotion."},{"class":"b50","text":" There are no sincere devotees comparable to the great souls who engage in service understanding the true nature of Kṛṣṇa, the true nature of the Name, the true nature of devotees, and the true nature of devotion."},{"class":"b97","text":" স্বরূপ না জানে তবু অনন্যভাবেতে ।<br />শ্রীকৃষ্ণে সাক্ষাৎ ভজে নামস্বরূপেতে ॥৩১॥<br />তিহোঁ ভক্তোত্তম বলি’ জানিবেরে ভাই ।<br />এই আজ্ঞা দিয়াছেন চৈতন্য গোসাঞি ॥৩২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" svarūpa nā jāne tabu ananya-bhāvete<br />śrī-kṛṣṇe sākṣāt bhaje nāma-svarūpete [31]<br />tiho̐ bhaktottama bali’ jānibere bhāi<br />ei ājñā diyāchhena chaitanya gosāñi [32]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāi</span>–Brother, <span class=\\"e2\\">jānibere</span>–know <span class=\\"e2\\">tiho̐</span>–those who <span class=\\"e2\\">jāne nā</span>–do not understand <span class=\\"e2\\">svarūpa</span>–these truths, <span class=\\"e2\\">tabu</span>–but <span class=\\"e2\\">ananya-bhāvete</span>–exclusively [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">sākṣāt</span>–directly <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaje</span>–serve <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-kṛṣṇe</span>–Śrī Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-svarūpete</span>–in the form of [His] Name <span class=\\"e2\\">bali’</span>–to be <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaktottama</span>–advanced devotees. <span class=\\"e2\\">chaitanya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">gosāñi</span>–Lord Chaitanya <span class=\\"e2\\">diyāchhena</span>–has given <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span>–this <span class=\\"e2\\">ājñā</span>–instruction."},{"class":"b55","text":" Brother, know even those who do not understand these truths but exclusively and directly serve Kṛṣṇa in the form of His Name to be advanced devotees. Lord Chaitanya has given this instruction."}]},{"title":"Eagerness to see Śrī Gaura","paragraphs":[{"class":"b46","text":"\\r"},{"class":"b58","text":" Chapter Thirteen"},{"class":"b120","text":" শ্রীগৌরদর্শনের ব্যাকুলতা"},{"class":"b121","text":" Śrī-Gaura-darśanera Vyākulatā"},{"class":"b175","text":" Eagerness to see Śrī Gaura"},{"class":"b129","text":" গৌরাঙ্গ তোমার\\tচরণ ছাড়িয়া<br />\\tচলিনু শ্রীবৃন্দাবনে ।<br />পূর্ব্ব-লীলা তব\\tদেখিব বলিয়া<br />\\tহইল আমার মনে ॥১॥"},{"class":"b93","text":" gaurāṅga tomāra\\tcharaṇa chhāḍiyā<br />\\tchalinu śrī-vṛndāvane<br />pūrva-līlā tava\\tdekhiba baliyā<br />\\tha-ila āmāra mane [1]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">gaurāṅga</span>–O Gaurāṅga! <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍiyā</span>–I left <span class=\\"e2\\">tomāra</span>–Your <span class=\\"e2\\">charaṇa</span>–feet [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">chalinu</span>–went <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-vṛndāvane</span>–to Śrī Vṛndāvan. <span class=\\"e2\\">baliyā</span>–Thinking <span class=\\"e2\\">dekhiba</span>–I would see<span class=\\"e2\\"> tava</span>–Your <span class=\\"e2\\">pūrva-līlā</span>–previous Pastimes, <span class=\\"e2\\">āmāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">mane ha-ila</span>–I decided [to go there]."},{"class":"b50","text":" O Gaurāṅga! I left Your feet and went to Vṛndāvan. Thinking I would see Your previous Pastimes, I decided to go there."},{"class":"b129","text":" কেন সেই ভাব\\tহইল আমার<br />\\tএখন কাঁদিয়া মরি ।<br />তোমারে না দেখি’\\tপ্রাণ ছাড়ি’ যায় <br />\\tনা জানি এবে কি করি ॥২॥"},{"class":"b93","text":" kena sei bhāva\\tha-ila āmāra<br />\\tekhana kā̐diyā mari<br />tomāre nā dekhi’\\tprāṇa chhāḍi’ yāya<br />\\tnā jāni ebe ki kari [2]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kena</span>–Why <span class=\\"e2\\">āmāra sei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāva</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-ila</span>–did I think that? <span class=\\"e2\\">ekhana</span>–Now <span class=\\"e2\\">kā̐diyā</span>–I am crying [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">mari</span>–dying. <span class=\\"e2\\">dekhi’ nā</span>–Not seeing <span class=\\"e2\\">tomāre</span>–You, [my] <span class=\\"e2\\">prāṇa</span>–heart <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍi’</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">yāya</span>–is leaving [me]. <span class=\\"e2\\">jāni nā</span>–I do not know <span class=\\"e2\\">ki</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kari</span>–what to do <span class=\\"e2\\">ebe</span>–now."},{"class":"b50","text":" Why did I think that? Now I am crying and dying. Not seeing You, my heart is leaving me. I do not know what to do now."},{"class":"b129","text":" ও রাঙ্গা চরণ\\tমম প্রাণ ধন<br />\\tসমুদ্রবালিতে রাখি’ ।<br />কি দেখিতে আইনু\\tনিজ মাথা খাইনু <br />\\tউড়ু উড়ু প্রাণপাখী ॥৩॥"},{"class":"b93","text":" o rāṅgā charaṇa\\tmama prāṇa dhana<br />\\tsamudra-bālite rākhi’<br />ki dekhite āinu\\tnija māthā khāinu<br />\\tuḍu uḍu prāṇa-pākhī [3]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">o</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">rāṅgā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">charaṇa</span>–Your reddish feet [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">mama</span>–my <span class=\\"e2\\">prāṇa</span>–life [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">dhana</span>–wealth, [but] <span class=\\"e2\\">rākhi’</span>–I left [them] <span class=\\"e2\\">samudra-bālite</span>–on the sand beside the ocean; <span class=\\"e2\\">ki</span>–what <span class=\\"e2\\">āinu</span>–have I come [here] <span class=\\"e2\\">dekhite</span>–to see? <span class=\\"e2\\">nija</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">māthā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">khāinu</span>–I indulged my mind, [and now] <span class=\\"e2\\">prāṇa-pākhī</span>–the bird of my heart [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">uḍu</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">uḍu</span>–anxious to fly [away]."},{"class":"b50","text":" Your reddish feet are my life and wealth, but I left them on the sand beside the ocean; what have I come here to see? I indulged my mind, and now the bird of my heart is anxious to fly away."},{"class":"b129","text":" যত চলি’ যাই\\tমন নাহি চলে<br />\\tতবু যাই জেদ করি’ ।<br />প্রেমের বিবর্ত্ত\\tআমারে নাচায়<br />\\tনা বুঝিয়া আমি মরি ॥৪॥"},{"class":"b93","text":" yata chali’ yāi\\tmana nāhi chale<br />\\ttabu yāi jeda kari’<br />premera vivarta\\tāmāre nāchāya<br />\\tnā bujhiyā āmi mari [4]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">yata</span>–As far as <span class=\\"e2\\">chali’</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">yāi</span>–I go on, [my] <span class=\\"e2\\">mana</span>–heart <span class=\\"e2\\">chale nāhi</span>–does not proceed. <span class=\\"e2\\">tabu</span>–Still, <span class=\\"e2\\">yāi</span>–I go on <span class=\\"e2\\">jeda</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kari’</span>–stubbornly. <span class=\\"e2\\">vivarta</span>–Transformations <span class=\\"e2\\">premera</span>–of love <span class=\\"e2\\">āmāre</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāchāya</span>–make me dance, [but] <span class=\\"e2\\">bujhiyā nā</span>–not understanding [them,] <span class=\\"e2\\">āmi</span>–I <span class=\\"e2\\">mari</span>–am dying."},{"class":"b50","text":" Although I go on, my heart does not. Still, I go on stubbornly …Transformations of love make me dance, but, not understanding them, I am dying."},{"class":"b129","text":" গৌরাঙ্গের রঙ্গ\\tবুঝিতে নারিনু<br />\\tপড়িনু দুঃখ-সাগরে ।<br />আমি চাই যাহা\\tনাহি পাই তাহা<br />\\tমন যে কেমন করে ॥৫॥"},{"class":"b93","text":" gaurāṅgera raṅga\\tbujhite nārinu<br />\\tpaḍinu duḥkha-sāgare<br />āmi chāi yāhā\\tnāhi pāi tāhā<br />\\tmana ye kemana kare [5]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">nārinu</span>–I could not <span class=\\"e2\\">bujhite</span>–understand <span class=\\"e2\\">gaurāṅgera</span>–Gaurāṅga’s <span class=\\"e2\\">raṅga</span>–Pastimes, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">paḍinu</span>–I have fallen <span class=\\"e2\\">duḥkha-sāgare</span>–into an ocean of sorrow. <span class=\\"e2\\">pāi nāhi</span>–I do not get <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhā yāhā</span>–that which <span class=\\"e2\\">āmi</span>–I <span class=\\"e2\\">chāi</span>–want. <span class=\\"e2\\">ye</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kemana</span>–How might <span class=\\"e2\\">mana</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kare</span>–[my] heart act?"},{"class":"b50","text":" Failing to understand Gaurāṅga’s Pastimes, I have fallen into an ocean of sorrow. I do not get what I want; what is my heart going to do now?"},{"class":"b129","text":" গৌরাঙ্গের তরে\\tপ্রাণ দিতে যাই<br />\\tনা হয় মরণ তবু ।<br />মরিব বলিয়া\\tপড়িয়া সমুদ্রে<br />\\tখাই মাত্র হাবুডুবু ॥৬॥"},{"class":"b93","text":" gaurāṅgera tare\\tprāṇa dite yāi<br />\\tnā haya maraṇa tabu<br />mariba baliyā\\tpaḍiyā samudre<br />\\tkhāi mātra hābuḍubu [6]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">yāi</span>–I go <span class=\\"e2\\">dite</span>–to give [my] <span class=\\"e2\\">prāṇa</span>–life <span class=\\"e2\\">gaurāṅgera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">tare</span>–to Gaurāṅga <span class=\\"e2\\">tabu</span>–but <span class=\\"e2\\">maraṇa haya nā</span>–I do not die. <span class=\\"e2\\">baliyā</span>–I decide <span class=\\"e2\\">mariba</span>–I will die [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">paḍiyā</span>–I jump <span class=\\"e2\\">samudre</span>–into the ocean [but] <span class=\\"e2\\">mātra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">hābuḍubu khāi</span>–I only flounder in the water."},{"class":"b50","text":" I go to give my life to Gaurāṅga, but I do not die. I decide to die and jump into the ocean, but I only flounder in the water."},{"class":"b129","text":" সে চন্দ্রবদন\\tদেখিবার লোভে<br />\\tশীঘ্র উঠি সিন্ধুতটে ।<br />পুনঃ নাহি দেখি’\\tপ্রাণ উড়ি’ যায়<br />\\tচলি পুনঃ টোটাবাটে ॥৭॥"},{"class":"b93","text":" se chandra-vadana\\tdekhibāra lobhe<br />\\tśīghra uṭhi sindhu-taṭe<br />punaḥ nāhi dekhi’\\tprāṇa uḍi’ yāya <br />\\tchali punaḥ ṭoṭā-vāṭe [7]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">lobhe</span>–Anxious <span class=\\"e2\\">dekhibāra</span>–to see <span class=\\"e2\\">se</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">chandra-vadana</span>–His moon-like face, <span class=\\"e2\\">śīghra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">uṭhi</span>–I quickly get up <span class=\\"e2\\">sindhu-taṭe</span>–on the shore of the ocean. <span class=\\"e2\\">punaḥ</span>–Again, <span class=\\"e2\\">dekhi’ nāhi</span>–not seeing [Him, my] <span class=\\"e2\\">prāṇa</span>–heart <span class=\\"e2\\">uḍi’</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">yāya</span>–flies [up, and] <span class=\\"e2\\">chali</span>–I run <span class=\\"e2\\">punaḥ ṭoṭā-vāṭe</span>–back down the path to the garden."},{"class":"b50","text":" Anxious to see His moon-like face, I quickly return to the shore. Again, not seeing Him, my heart flies up, and I run back down the path to the garden."},{"class":"b129","text":" গোপীনাথাঙ্গনে\\tদেখি’ গোরামুখ<br />\\tপড়ি অচেতন হঞা ।<br />পণ্ডিত গোঁসাঞি\\tমোরে লঞা রাখে<br />\\tদেখি পুনঃ সংজ্ঞা পাঞা ॥৮॥"},{"class":"b93","text":" gopīnāthāṅgane\\tdekhi’ gorā-mukha<br />\\tpaḍi achetana hañā<br />paṇḍita go̐sāñi\\tmore lañā rākhe<br />\\tdekhi punaḥ saṁjñā pāñā [8]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">dekhi’</span>–Seeing <span class=\\"e2\\">gorā-mukha</span>–Gorā’s face <span class=\\"e2\\">gopīnāthāṅgane</span>–in the courtyard of Gopīnāth, <span class=\\"e2\\">achetana</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">hañā paḍi</span>–I fell unconscious. <span class=\\"e2\\">paṇḍita</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">go̐sāñi</span>–Gadādhar Paṇḍit <span class=\\"e2\\">lañā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">rākhe</span>–took care <span class=\\"e2\\">more</span>–of me, [and then] <span class=\\"e2\\">dekhi</span>–I saw [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">saṁjñā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">pāñā</span>–I was conscious <span class=\\"e2\\">punaḥ</span>–again."},{"class":"b50","text":" Seeing Gorā’s face in the courtyard of Gopīnāth, I fell unconscious. Gadādhar Paṇḍit took care of me, and then I saw that I was conscious again."},{"class":"b129","text":" গৌর গদাধর\\tবসিয়া দুজনে<br />\\tবলেন আমার কথা ।<br />অমনি কাঁদিয়া\\tযাই গড়াগড়ি<br />\\tনা বিচারি যথা তথা ॥৯॥"},{"class":"b93","text":" gaura gadādhara\\tbasiyā dujane<br />\\tbalena āmāra kathā<br />amani kā̐diyā\\tyāi gaḍāgaḍi<br />\\tnā vichāri yathā tathā [9]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">gaura</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">gadādhara</span>–Gaura and Gadādhar <span class=\\"e2\\">basiyā</span>–were sitting [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">dujane</span>–the two of Them <span class=\\"e2\\">balena</span>–where speaking <span class=\\"e2\\">āmāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kathā</span>–about me, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">amani</span>–all of a sudden <span class=\\"e2\\">kā̐diyā</span>–I [began to] cry [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">gaḍāgaḍi yāi</span>–rolled on the ground, <span class=\\"e2\\">vichāri nā</span>–not considering <span class=\\"e2\\">yathā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">tathā</span>–here from there."},{"class":"b50","text":" Gaura and Gadādhar were sitting and speaking about me, and all of a sudden, I began to cry and roll on the ground, unaware of where I was."},{"class":"b129","text":" ক্ষণেক বিরহ\\tসহিতে না পারি<br />\\tগৌর মোর হৃদে নাচে ।<br />মরিতে না দেয়\\tবাঁচিলে কোন্দল<br />\\tকিসে মোর প্রাণ বাঁচে ॥১০॥"},{"class":"b93","text":" kṣaṇeka viraha\\tsahite nā pāri<br />\\tgaura mora hṛde nāche<br />marite nā deya\\tvā̐chile kondala<br />\\tkise mora prāṇa vā̐che [10]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">pāri nā</span>–I cannot <span class=\\"e2\\">sahite</span>–tolerate <span class=\\"e2\\">kṣaṇeka</span>–a moment <span class=\\"e2\\">viraha</span>–of separation [as] <span class=\\"e2\\">gaura</span>–Gaura <span class=\\"e2\\">nāche</span>–dances <span class=\\"e2\\">mora</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">hṛde</span>–in my heart. <span class=\\"e2\\">deya nā</span>–He does not allow [me] <span class=\\"e2\\">marite</span>–to die, [but] <span class=\\"e2\\">vā̐chile</span>–when I live, <span class=\\"e2\\">kondala</span>–we quarrel. <span class=\\"e2\\">kise</span>–How [can] <span class=\\"e2\\">mora</span>–my <span class=\\"e2\\">prāṇa</span>–heart <span class=\\"e2\\">vā̐che</span>–live?"},{"class":"b50","text":" I cannot tolerate a moment of separation as Gaura dances in my heart. He does not let me die, but when I live, we quarrel. How does my life go on?"},{"class":"b129","text":" হেন অবস্থায়\\tগৌরপদ ছাড়ি’<br />\\tমোর বৃন্দাবনে আসা ।<br />এ বুদ্ধি হইল\\tকেন নাহি জানি<br />\\tইহ-পরলোক-নাশা ॥১১॥"},{"class":"b93","text":" hena avasthāya\\tgaura-pada chhāḍi’<br />\\tmora vṛndāvane āsā<br />e buddhi ha-ila\\tkena nāhi jāni<br />\\tiha-para-loka-nāśā [11]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">hena</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">avasthāya</span>–In this condition, <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍi’</span>–I left <span class=\\"e2\\">gaura-pada</span>–Gaura’s feet [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">mora āsā</span>–came <span class=\\"e2\\">vṛndāvane</span>–to Vṛndāvan. <span class=\\"e2\\">jāni nāhi</span>–I do not know <span class=\\"e2\\">kena</span>–why <span class=\\"e2\\">e</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">buddhi</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-ila</span>–this decision was made, [but now my] <span class=\\"e2\\">iha-para-loka-nāśā</span>–present and future [are] ruined."},{"class":"b50","text":" In this condition, I left Gaura’s feet and came to Vṛndāvan. I do not know what made me do this, but now my present and future are ruined."},{"class":"b129","text":" আজ্ঞা লইনু যাইতে\\tআজ্ঞা না পালিলে<br />\\tতাতে হয় অপরাধ ।<br />গোরাচাঁদমুখ\\tনা দেখিয়া মরি <br />\\tসব দিকে মোর বাধ ॥১২॥"},{"class":"b93","text":" ājñā la-inu yāite\\tājñā nā pālile<br />\\ttāte haya aparādha<br />gorāchā̐da-mukha\\tnā dekhiyā mari<br />\\tsaba dike mora bādha [12]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">la-inu</span>–I took <span class=\\"e2\\">ājñā</span>–permission <span class=\\"e2\\">yāite</span>–to go, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">pālile nā</span>–if I don’t act according [to this] <span class=\\"e2\\">ājñā</span>–permission, <span class=\\"e2\\">tāte</span>–then <span class=\\"e2\\">aparādha haya</span>–I will commit an offence. [But] <span class=\\"e2\\">dekhiyā nā</span>–not seeing<span class=\\"e2\\"> gorāchā̐da-mukha</span>–Gorāchā̐d’s face, <span class=\\"e2\\">mari</span>–I am dying. <span class=\\"e2\\">mora</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bādha</span>–I have obstacles <span class=\\"e2\\">saba</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">dike</span>–in all directions!"},{"class":"b50","text":" I took permission to go, and if I don’t do so accordingly, I will commit an offence. But not seeing Gorāchā̐d’s face, I am dying; there are obstacles all around me!"},{"class":"b129","text":" গোরাপ্রেম যার\\tসঙ্কট তাহার<br />\\tপ্রাণ লঞা টানাটানি ।<br />গদাধরগণে\\tএই ত’ দুর্দ্দশা<br />\\tসবে করে কাণাকাণি ॥১৩॥"},{"class":"b93","text":" gorā-prema yāra\\tsaṅkaṭa tāhāra<br />\\tprāṇa lañā ṭānāṭāni<br />gadādhara-gaṇe\\tei ta’ durdaśā<br />\\tsabe kare kāṇākāṇi [13]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhāra yāra</span>–Those who have <span class=\\"e2\\">gorā-prema</span>–love for Gorā [undergo] <span class=\\"e2\\">saṅkaṭa</span>–distress. [That love] <span class=\\"e2\\">prāṇa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">lañā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ṭānāṭāni</span>–pulls [their] hearts in opposite directions [simultaneously]. <span class=\\"e2\\">sabe</span>–Everyone <span class=\\"e2\\">kāṇākāṇi kare</span>–whispers [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ta’</span>–this [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">durdaśā</span>–the miserable state <span class=\\"e2\\">gadādhara-gaṇe</span>–of Gadādhar’s associates."},{"class":"b55","text":" Those who have love for Gorā undergo distress: that love pulls their hearts in opposite directions simultaneously. Everyone whispers that this is the miserable state of Gadādhar’s associates."}]},{"title":"Contradictory Transformations","paragraphs":[{"class":"b46","text":"\\r"},{"class":"b58","text":" Chapter Fourteen"},{"class":"b120","text":" বিপরীত বিবর্ত্ত"},{"class":"b121","text":" Viparīta Vivarta"},{"class":"b175","text":" Contradictory Transformations"},{"class":"b176","text":" নবদ্বীপ-দর্শনে বৃন্দাবন-দর্শন"},{"class":"b177","text":" navadvīpa-darśane vṛndāvana-darśana"},{"class":"b70","text":" Seeing Vṛndāvan by seeing Nabadwīp"},{"class":"b97","text":" ভাইরে<br />বৃন্দাবনে যাওয়া আর হলো না ॥১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" bhāi-re<br />vṛndāvane yāoyā āra halo nā [1]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāi-re</span>–O brother, <span class=\\"e2\\">āra yāoyā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">halo</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nā</span>–I could not continue <span class=\\"e2\\">vṛndāvane</span>–to Vṛndāvan."},{"class":"b50","text":" O brother, I could not continue to Vṛndāvan."},{"class":"b123","text":" গোরামুখ না দেখিয়া\\tগোরারূপ ধেয়াইয়া<br />\\tপথ ভুলি’ যাই অন্য দেশ ।<br />সেখান হইতে ফিরি’\\tপুনঃ যাই ধীরি ধীরি<br />\\tপুনঃ আসি’ দেখি সে প্রদেশ ॥২॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" gorā-mukha nā dekhiyā\\tgorā-rūpa dheyāiyā<br />\\tpatha bhuli’ yāi anya deśa<br />sekhāna ha-ite phiri’\\tpunaḥ yāi dhīri dhīri<br />\\tpunaḥ āsi’ dekhi se pradeśa [2]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">dekhiyā nā</span>–I had not seen <span class=\\"e2\\">gorā-mukha</span>–Gorā’s face, [and so] <span class=\\"e2\\">dheyāiyā</span>–was meditating <span class=\\"e2\\">gorā-rūpa</span>–on Gorā’s form; <span class=\\"e2\\">bhuli’</span>–I lost <span class=\\"e2\\">patha</span>–the way [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">yāi</span>–went <span class=\\"e2\\">anya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">deśa</span>–elsewhere. <span class=\\"e2\\">phiri’</span>–Turning around <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-ite</span>–from <span class=\\"e2\\">sekhāna</span>–there, <span class=\\"e2\\">yāi punaḥ</span>–I went on <span class=\\"e2\\">dhīri</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">dhīri</span>–slowly. [When] <span class=\\"e2\\">punaḥ āsi’</span>–I came back, <span class=\\"e2\\">dekhi</span>–I saw <span class=\\"e2\\">se</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">pradeśa</span>–the same place."},{"class":"b50","text":" I had not seen Gorā’s face and so was meditating on His form; I lost the way and went in the wrong direction. I turned back and slowly went on. When I came back, I saw I was in the same place!"},{"class":"b123","text":" এইরূপে কত দিনে\\tযাব আমি বৃন্দাবনে<br />\\tনা জানি কি হবে দশা মোর ।<br />বৃক্ষতলে বসি’ বসি’\\tকাটি আমি অহর্নিশি<br />\\tকভু মোর নিদ্রা আসে ঘোর ॥৩॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" ei-rūpe kata dine\\tyāba āmi vṛndāvane<br />\\tnā jāni ki habe daśā mora<br />vṛkṣa-tale basi’ basi‘\\tkāṭi āmi ahar-niśi<br />\\tkabhu mora nidrā āse ghora [3]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">ei-rūpe</span>–In this way, <span class=\\"e2\\">kata</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">dine</span>–for many days, [I thought,] <span class=\\"e2\\">āmi</span>–I <span class=\\"e2\\">yāba</span>–would go <span class=\\"e2\\">vṛndāvane</span>–to Vṛndāvan, [but] <span class=\\"e2\\">jāni nā</span>–I did not know <span class=\\"e2\\">ki</span>–what <span class=\\"e2\\">mora daśā habe</span>–condition would befall me. <span class=\\"e2\\">āmi</span>–I <span class=\\"e2\\">kāṭi</span>–passed <span class=\\"e2\\">ahar-niśi</span>–days and nights <span class=\\"e2\\">basi’</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">basi‘</span>–sitting <span class=\\"e2\\">vṛkṣa-tale</span>–under trees, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu</span>–sometimes <span class=\\"e2\\">mora</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ghora</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nidrā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">āse</span>–I slept heavily."},{"class":"b50","text":" In this way, for many days I thought I would go to Vṛndāvan, but I did not know what would become of me. I passed days and nights sitting under trees, and sometimes I slept heavily."},{"class":"b123","text":" স্বপ্নে বহু দূরে গিয়া\\tসিন্ধুতটে প্রবেশিয়া<br />\\tদেখি গোরার অপূর্ব্ব নর্ত্তন ।<br />গদাধর নাচে সঙ্গে\\tভক্তগণ নাচে রঙ্গে<br />\\tগায় গীত অমৃত বর্ষণ ॥৪॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" svapne bahu dūre giyā\\tsindhu-taṭe praveśiyā<br />\\tdekhi gorāra apūrva nartana<br />gadādhara nāche saṅge\\tbhakta-gaṇa nāche raṅge<br />\\tgāya gīta amṛta varṣaṇa [4]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">svapne</span>–In a dream, <span class=\\"e2\\">giyā</span>–I went <span class=\\"e2\\">bahu</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">dūre</span>–a long way, <span class=\\"e2\\">praveśiyā</span>–arrived <span class=\\"e2\\">sindhu-taṭe</span>–at the shore of the ocean, [where] <span class=\\"e2\\">dekhi</span>–I saw <span class=\\"e2\\">gorāra</span>–Gorā’s <span class=\\"e2\\">apūrva</span>–wonderful <span class=\\"e2\\">nartana</span>–dancing. <span class=\\"e2\\">gadādhara</span>–Gadādhar <span class=\\"e2\\">nāche</span>–danced <span class=\\"e2\\">saṅge</span>–with [Him]. <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakta-gaṇa</span>–The devotees <span class=\\"e2\\">nāche</span>–danced <span class=\\"e2\\">raṅge</span>–joyfully, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">gāya</span>–they sang <span class=\\"e2\\">gīta</span>–songs [that were like] <span class=\\"e2\\">amṛta</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">varṣaṇa</span>–showers of nectar."},{"class":"b50","text":" In a dream, I walked a long way and arrived at the shore of the ocean, where I saw Gorā’s wonderful dancing. Gadādhar and the devotees joyfully danced with Him, and they sang songs that were like showers of nectar."},{"class":"b123","text":" নৃত্যগীত-অবসানে\\tগোরা মোর হাত টানে<br />\\tবলে, “তুমি ক্রোধে ছাড়ি’ গেলে ।<br />আমার কি দোষ বল\\tতব চিত্ত সুচঞ্চল<br />\\tব্রজে গেলে আমা হেথা ফেলে ॥৫॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" nṛtya-gīta-avasāne\\tgorā mora hāta ṭāne<br />\\tbale, “tumi krodhe chhāḍi’ gele<br />āmāra ki doṣa bala\\ttava chitta suchañchala<br />\\tvraje gele āmā hethā phele [5]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">nṛtya-gīta-avasāne</span>–When they finished dancing and singing, <span class=\\"e2\\">gorā</span>–Gorā <span class=\\"e2\\">ṭāne</span>–pulled <span class=\\"e2\\">mora</span>–my <span class=\\"e2\\">hāta</span>–hand [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–said, <span class=\\"e2\\">“tumi</span>–“You <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍi’</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">gele</span>–left <span class=\\"e2\\">krodhe</span>–in anger. <span class=\\"e2\\">bala</span>–Tell [Me,] <span class=\\"e2\\">ki</span>–what [was] <span class=\\"e2\\">āmāra</span>–My <span class=\\"e2\\">doṣa</span>–fault? <span class=\\"e2\\">tava</span>–Your <span class=\\"e2\\">chitta</span>–heart [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">suchañchala</span>–so fickle: <span class=\\"e2\\">phele</span>–you left <span class=\\"e2\\">āmā</span>–Me <span class=\\"e2\\">hethā</span>–here [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">gele</span>–went <span class=\\"e2\\">vraje</span>–to Vraja!"},{"class":"b50","text":" When they finished dancing and singing, Gorā took my hand and said, “You left in anger. Tell Me, what was My fault? Your heart is so fickle: you left Me here and went to Vraja!"},{"class":"b123","text":" আইস আলিঙ্গন করি\\tতব বক্ষে বক্ষ ধরি’<br />\\tছাঁড়ো মুঞি চিত্তের বিকার ।<br />মধ্যাহ্নে করিয়া পাক\\tদেহ মোরে অন্ন শাক<br />\\tক্ষুন্নিবৃত্তি হউক্ আমার ॥৬॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" āisa āliṅgana kari\\ttava vakṣe vakṣa dhari’<br />\\tchhā̐ḍo muñi chittera vikāra<br />madhyāhne kariyā pāka\\tdeha more anna śāka<br />\\tkṣun-nivṛtti ha-uk āmāra [6]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">āisa</span>–Come! <span class=\\"e2\\">āliṅgana</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kari</span>–I will embrace [you]. <span class=\\"e2\\">dhari’</span>–Holding [My] <span class=\\"e2\\">vakṣa</span>–chest <span class=\\"e2\\">tava</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">vakṣe</span>–to your chest, <span class=\\"e2\\">muñi</span>–I <span class=\\"e2\\">chhā̐ḍo</span>–will give up [My] <span class=\\"e2\\">chittera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">vikāra</span>–anxiety. <span class=\\"e2\\">pāka kariyā</span>–Cook <span class=\\"e2\\">madhyāhne</span>–at midday [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">deha</span>–give <span class=\\"e2\\">more</span>–Me <span class=\\"e2\\">anna</span>–some rice [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">śāka</span>–spinach [so that] <span class=\\"e2\\">āmāra</span>–My <span class=\\"e2\\">kṣun-nivṛtti</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-uk</span>–hunger will [also] be relieved."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Come! Let Me embrace you, let Me hold your chest to Mine, then My anxiety will go away. Cook at midday and give Me some rice and spinach so that My hunger will also be relieved."},{"class":"b123","text":" ছাড়িয়া জগদানন্দে\\tমোর মন নিরানন্দে<br />\\tভোজনাদি লইল কত দিন ।<br />কি বুঝিয়া গেলে তুমি\\tদুঃখেতে পড়িনু আমি<br />\\tজগা মোরে সদা দয়াহীন ॥৭॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" chhāḍiyā jagadānande\\tmora mana nirānande<br />\\tbhojanādi la-ila kata dina<br />ki bujhiyā gele tumi\\tduḥkhete paḍinu āmi<br />\\tjagā more sadā dayā-hīna [7]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">jagadānande</span>–O Jagadānanda! <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍiyā</span>–after [your] leaving, <span class=\\"e2\\">bhojanādi</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">la-ila</span>–I ate, slept, and so on, <span class=\\"e2\\">kata</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">dina</span>–for many days [while] <span class=\\"e2\\">mora</span>–My <span class=\\"e2\\">mana</span>–heart [was] <span class=\\"e2\\">nirānande</span>–unhappy. <span class=\\"e2\\">ki</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bujhiyā</span>–With what understanding <span class=\\"e2\\">tumi gele</span>–did you leave [Me]? <span class=\\"e2\\">āmi</span>–I <span class=\\"e2\\">paḍinu</span>–slumped <span class=\\"e2\\">duḥkhete</span>–in sadness: <span class=\\"e2\\">jagā</span>–Jagā [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">sadā</span>–always <span class=\\"e2\\">dayā-hīna</span>–merciless <span class=\\"e2\\">more</span>–to Me."},{"class":"b50","text":" “O Jagadānanda, after you left, I ate and slept for many days with an unhappy heart. Why did you leave Me? I slumped into sadness: Jagā is always merciless to Me."},{"class":"b123","text":" শীঘ্র ব্রজ নিরখিয়া\\tআইস তুমি সুখী হঞা<br />\\tমোরে দেহ শাকান্ন ব্যঞ্জন ।<br />তবে ত’ বাঁচিব আমি\\tতাতে সুখী হবে তুমি<br />\\tক্রোধে মোরে না ছাড কখন” ॥৮॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" śīghra vraja nirakhiyā\\tāisa tumi sukhī hañā<br />\\tmore deha śākānna vyañjana<br />tabe ta’ vā̐chiba āmi\\ttāte sukhī habe tumi<br />\\tkrodhe more nā chhāḍa kakhana” [8]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">śīghra</span>–Quickly <span class=\\"e2\\">nirakhiyā</span>–see <span class=\\"e2\\">vraja</span>–Vraja, <span class=\\"e2\\">tumi</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">āisa</span>–come back <span class=\\"e2\\">sukhī</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">hañā</span>–feeling happy, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">deha</span>–offer <span class=\\"e2\\">more</span>–Me <span class=\\"e2\\">śākānna</span>–some rice, spinach, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">vyañjana</span>–vegetables. <span class=\\"e2\\">tabe</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ta’</span>–Then <span class=\\"e2\\">āmi</span>–I <span class=\\"e2\\">vā̐chiba</span>–will live, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">tāte</span>–thereby <span class=\\"e2\\">sukhī</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">habe</span>–you will [also] be happy. <span class=\\"e2\\">tumi</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kakhana chhāḍa nā</span>–Never leave <span class=\\"e2\\">more</span>–Me <span class=\\"e2\\">krodhe”</span>–out of anger.”"},{"class":"b50","text":" “Quickly see Vraja, come back happy, and offer Me some rice, spinach, and vegetables. Then I will be able to live, and you will also be happy. Never leave Me out of anger again.”"},{"class":"b123","text":" নিদ্রা ভাঙ্গি’ দেখি আমি\\tবহুদূর ব্রজভূমি<br />\\tনিকটেতে জাহ্নবীপুলিনে ।<br />আহা! নবদ্বীপধাম\\tনিত্যগৌরলীলাগ্রাম<br />\\tব্রজসার অতি সমীচীন ॥৯॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" nidrā bhāṅgi’ dekhi āmi\\tbahu-dūra vraja-bhūmi<br />\\tnikaṭete jāhnavī-puline<br />āhā! navadvīpa-dhāma\\tnitya-gaura-līlā-grāma<br />\\tvraja-sāra ati samīchīna [9]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">āmi</span>–I <span class=\\"e2\\">nidrā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāṅgi’</span>–suddenly awoke [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">dekhi</span>–saw [that I was] <span class=\\"e2\\">nikaṭete</span>–near <span class=\\"e2\\">jāhnavī-puline</span>–the bank of the Ganges, <span class=\\"e2\\">bahu-dūra</span>–far away <span class=\\"e2\\">vraja-bhūmi</span>–from the land of Vraja. <span class=\\"e2\\">āhā!</span>–Oh! <span class=\\"e2\\">navadvīpa-dhāma</span>–Nabadwīp Dhām! <span class=\\"e2\\">nitya-gaura-līlā-grāma</span>–The eternal abode of Gaura’s Pastimes! <span class=\\"e2\\">ati</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">samīchīna</span>–The perfect <span class=\\"e2\\">vraja-sāra</span>–essence of Vraja!"},{"class":"b50","text":" I suddenly awoke and saw that I was on the bank of the Ganges, far away from the land of Vraja. Oh! Nabadwīp Dhām! The eternal abode of Gaura’s Pastimes! The perfect essence of Vraja!"},{"class":"b123","text":" আনন্দেতে মায়াপুরে\\tপ্রবেশিনু অন্তঃপুরে<br />\\tনমি আমি আইমাতা-পদ ।<br />গৌরাঙ্গের কথা বলি’\\tশীঘ্র আইলাম চলি’<br />\\tদেখি নবদ্বীপ-সুসম্পদ ॥১০॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" ānandete māyāpure\\tpraveśinu antaḥpure<br />\\tnami āmi āi-mātā-pada<br />gaurāṅgera kathā bali’\\tśīghra āilāma chali’<br />\\tdekhi navadvīpa-susampada [10]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">ānandete</span>–Overjoyed [to be] <span class=\\"e2\\">māyāpure</span>–in Māyāpur, <span class=\\"e2\\">praveśinu</span>–I entered <span class=\\"e2\\">antaḥpure</span>–the inner apartment [of the Lord’s house and] <span class=\\"e2\\">nami</span>–bowed <span class=\\"e2\\">āi-mātā-pada</span>–at the feet of Mother Śachī. <span class=\\"e2\\">bali’</span>–I spoke <span class=\\"e2\\">gaurāṅgera kathā</span>–Gaurāṅga’s message, <span class=\\"e2\\">śīghra</span>–quickly <span class=\\"e2\\">chali’ āilāma</span>–came out, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">dekhi</span>–saw <span class=\\"e2\\">navadvīpa-susampada</span>–the divine opulence of Nabadwīp."},{"class":"b50","text":" Overjoyed to be in Māyāpur, I entered the inner apartment of the Lord’s house and bowed at the feet of Mother Āi. I explained what Gaurāṅga had told me, quickly came out, and saw the divine opulence of Nabadwīp."},{"class":"b123","text":" ভাবিলাম বৃন্দাবন\\tকরিলাম দরশন<br />\\tআর কেন যাউ দূর দেশ ।<br />গৌর দরশন করি’\\tসব দুঃখ পরিহরি’<br />\\tছাড়ি’ দিব বিরহজ-ক্লেশ ॥১১॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" bhāvilāma vṛndāvana\\tkarilāma daraśana<br />\\tāra kena yāu dūra deśa<br />gaura daraśana kari’\\tsaba duḥkha parihari’<br />\\tchhāḍi’ diba virahaja-kleśa [11]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāvilāma</span>–I felt [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">daraśana karilāma</span>–I had seen <span class=\\"e2\\">vṛndāvana</span>–Vṛndāvan, [so] <span class=\\"e2\\">āra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kena</span>–why again <span class=\\"e2\\">yāu</span>–should I go <span class=\\"e2\\">dūra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">deśa</span>–to that faraway land? <span class=\\"e2\\">daraśana</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kari’</span>–I will meet <span class=\\"e2\\">gaura</span>–Gaura, <span class=\\"e2\\">parihari’</span>–give up <span class=\\"e2\\">saba</span>–all [my] <span class=\\"e2\\">duḥkha</span>–sadness, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍi’</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">diba</span>–leave behind <span class=\\"e2\\">virahaja-kleśa</span>–the sorrow produced by separation."},{"class":"b55","text":" I felt that I had already seen Vṛndāvan, so why should I now go to that faraway land? Instead, I will go to meet Gaura, give up all my sadness, and leave behind the sorrow of separation."}]},{"title":"Morning Pastimes in Nabadwīp","paragraphs":[{"class":"b46","text":"\\r"},{"class":"b58","text":" Chapter Fifteen"},{"class":"b120","text":" শ্রীনবদ্বীপে পূর্বাহ্ন-লীলা"},{"class":"b121","text":" Śrī-Navadvīpe Pūrvāhna-līlā"},{"class":"b175","text":" Morning Pastimes in Nabadwīp"},{"class":"b97","text":" যখন যাহা মনে পড়ে গৌরাঙ্গ-চরিত ।<br />তাহা লিখি, হইলেও ক্রম-বিপরীত ॥১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" yakhana yāhā mane paḍe gaurāṅga-charita<br />tāhā likhi, ha-ileo krama-viparīta [1]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">yakhana</span>–Whenever <span class=\\"e2\\">yāhā tāhā</span>–anything <span class=\\"e2\\">gaurāṅga-charita</span>–about Gaurāṅga’s Pastimes <span class=\\"e2\\">paḍe</span>–comes <span class=\\"e2\\">mane</span>–to mind, <span class=\\"e2\\">likhi</span>–I write [it] down, <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-ileo</span>–even if it is <span class=\\"e2\\">krama-viparīta</span>–out of sequence."},{"class":"b71","text":" I write whatever comes to my mind about Gaurāṅga’s Pastimes, whenever it does, even if it is out of sequence."},{"class":"b176","text":" গৌরাঙ্গ-প্রসাদ"},{"class":"b177","text":" gaurāṅga-prasāda"},{"class":"b70","text":" Gaurāṅga’s prasād"},{"class":"b97","text":" শচী আই একদিন বড় যত্ন করি’ ।<br />গোরা-অবশিষ্ট-পাত্র মোরে দিল ধরি’ ॥২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" śachī āi eka-dina baḍa yatna kari’<br />gorā-avaśiṣṭa-pātra more dila dhari’ [2]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">eka-dina</span>–One day, <span class=\\"e2\\">śachī</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">āi</span>–Mother Śachī <span class=\\"e2\\">baḍa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">yatna</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kari’</span>–very affectionately <span class=\\"e2\\">dhari’ dila</span>–gave <span class=\\"e2\\">more</span>–me <span class=\\"e2\\">gorā-avaśiṣṭa-pātra</span>–the plate with the remnants of Gorā’s meal."},{"class":"b50","text":" One day, Mother Śachī very affectionately gave me the plate of Gorā’s remnants."},{"class":"b97","text":" আমি খাইলাম যেন অমৃতাস্বাদন ।<br />গৌরাঙ্গ-প্রসাদ পাঞা আহ্লাদিত মন ॥৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" āmi khāilāma yena amṛtāsvādana<br />gaurāṅga-prasāda pāñā āhlādita mana [3]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [My] <span class=\\"e2\\">āhlādita</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">mana</span>–heart was delighted <span class=\\"e2\\">pāñā</span>–by receiving <span class=\\"e2\\">gaurāṅga-prasāda</span>–Gaurāṅga’s remnants, [and when] <span class=\\"e2\\">āmi</span>–I <span class=\\"e2\\">khāilāma</span>–ate [it, it was] <span class=\\"e2\\">yena</span>–like <span class=\\"e2\\">amṛtāsvādana</span>–the taste of nectar."},{"class":"b50","text":" I was delighted to receive Gaurāṅga’s prasād, and as I ate it, I felt as though I was tasting nectar."},{"class":"b97","text":" কভু কি করিব আমি সে ভূরি ভোজন ।<br />আবোনা অচ্যুত শাক, আইয়ের রন্ধন ॥৪॥"},{"class":"b97","text":" মোচাঘণ্ট, কচুশাক তাহে ফুলবড়ি ।<br />মানচাকি, নিম্বপটোল, আর দধিবড়ি ॥৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kabhu ki kariba āmi se bhūri bhojana<br />ābonā achyuta śāka, āiyera randhana [4]"},{"class":"b60","text":" mochā ghaṇṭa, kachu-śāka tāhe phula-baḍi<br />mānachāki, nimba-paṭola, āra dadhi-baḍi [5]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ki</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">āmi kariba</span>–Will I ever eat <span class=\\"e2\\">se</span>–such <span class=\\"e2\\">bhūri</span>–delicious <span class=\\"e2\\">bhojana</span>–food [again]? <span class=\\"e2\\">āiyera</span>–Śachī’s <span class=\\"e2\\">randhana</span>–cooking [consisted of] <span class=\\"e2\\">ābonā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">achyuta</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">śāka</span>–wild spinach, <span class=\\"e2\\">mochā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ghaṇṭa</span>–banana flower, <span class=\\"e2\\">kachu-śāka</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhe</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">phula-baḍi</span>–taro with balls of fried dal, <span class=\\"e2\\">mānachāki</span>–ground taro, <span class=\\"e2\\">nimba-paṭola</span>–paṭol with neem, <span class=\\"e2\\">āra</span>–and <span class=\\"e2\\">dadhi-baḍi</span>–balls of fried dal in yoghurt."},{"class":"b71","text":" Will I ever eat such delicious food again? Mother Śachī made wild spinach, banana flower, taro with balls of fried dal, ground taro, paṭol with neem leaves, and patties of fried dal in yoghurt."},{"class":"b176","text":" গাদিগাছা গ্রামে গমন"},{"class":"b177","text":" gādigāchhā grāme gamana"},{"class":"b70","text":" Visiting the village of Gādigāchhā"},{"class":"b123","text":" ভোজনে আনন্দমতি\\tচলিলাম হংসগতি<br />\\tনিতাই-গৌরাঙ্গগণ-সঙ্গে ।<br />গঙ্গাতীরে তীরে যাই \\tগাদিগাছা গ্রাম পাই<br />\\tহরিনাম-গানের প্রসঙ্গে ॥৬॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" bhojane ānanda-mati\\tchalilāma haṁsa-gati<br />\\tnitāi-gaurāṅga-gaṇa-saṅge<br />gaṅgā-tīre tīre yāi\\tgādigāchhā grāma pāi<br />\\thari-nāma-gānera prasaṅge [6]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">ānanda-mati</span>–Joyful <span class=\\"e2\\">bhojane</span>–after eating, <span class=\\"e2\\">chalilāma</span>–I walked, <span class=\\"e2\\">haṁsa-gati</span>–moving like a swan, <span class=\\"e2\\">nitāi-gaurāṅga-gaṇa-saṅge</span>–in the company of Nitāi, Gaurāṅga, and Their associates. <span class=\\"e2\\">yāi</span>–We walked <span class=\\"e2\\">gaṅgā-tīre</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">tīre</span>–along the banks of the Ganges <span class=\\"e2\\">hari-nāma-gānera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">prasaṅge</span>–engaged in chanting the Lord’s Name [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">pāi</span>–arrived <span class=\\"e2\\">gādigāchhā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">grāma</span>–in the village of Gādigāchhā."},{"class":"b50","text":" Joyful after eating, I walked like a swan in the company of Nitāi, Gaurāṅga, and Their associates. Walking along the banks of the Ganges and chanting the Lord’s Name, we arrived in the village of Gādigāchhā."},{"class":"b123","text":" গোবিন্দ মৃদঙ্গ বায়\\tবাসুঘোষ নাম গায়<br />\\tনাচে গদাধর বক্রেশ্বর ।<br />হরিবোল রব শুনি’\\tচারিদিকে হুলুধ্বনি<br />\\tগোরাপ্রেমে সবে মাতোয়ার ॥৭॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" govinda mṛdaṅga vāya\\tvāsu-ghoṣa nāma gāya<br />\\tnāche gadādhara vakreśvara<br />haribola rava śuni’\\tchāri-dike hulu-dhvani<br />\\tgorā-preme sabe mātoyāra [7]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">govinda</span>–Govinda <span class=\\"e2\\">vāya</span>–played <span class=\\"e2\\">mṛdaṅga</span>–the drum, <span class=\\"e2\\">vāsu-ghoṣa</span>–Vāsudev Ghoṣ <span class=\\"e2\\">gāya</span>–chanted <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–the Name, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">gadādhara</span>–Gadādhar [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">vakreśvara</span>–Vakreśvar <span class=\\"e2\\">nāche</span>–danced. <span class=\\"e2\\">śuni’</span>–Hearing <span class=\\"e2\\">rava</span>–the sound <span class=\\"e2\\">haribola</span>–of ‘Haribol!’ [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">hulu-dhvani</span>–cheering <span class=\\"e2\\">chāri-dike</span>–in the four directions, <span class=\\"e2\\">sabe</span>–everyone <span class=\\"e2\\">mātoyāra</span>–become mad <span class=\\"e2\\">gorā-preme</span>–with love for Gorā."},{"class":"b50","text":" Govinda Ghoṣ played mṛdaṅga, Vāsudev Ghoṣ chanted the Name, and Gadādhar and Vakreśvar danced. Hearing the sound of ‘Haribol!’ and cheering in all directions, everyone became mad with love for Gorā."},{"class":"b123","text":" নাচ গান নাহি জানি\\tতবু নাচি ঊর্ধ্বপাণি<br />\\tগৌরাঙ্গ নাচায় অঙ্গে পশি’ ।<br />সুরতালবোধ নাই\\tতবু নাচি, তবু গাই<br />\\tকি জানি কি জানে গৌরশশী ॥৮॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" nācha gāna nāhi jāni\\ttabu nāchi ūrdhva-pāṇi<br />\\tgaurāṅga nāchāya aṅge paśi’<br />sura-tāla-bodha nāi\\ttabu nāchi, tabu gāi<br />\\tki jāni ki jāne gaura-śaśī [8]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">jāni nāhi</span>–I do not know [how to] <span class=\\"e2\\">nācha</span>–dance [or] <span class=\\"e2\\">gāna</span>–sing. <span class=\\"e2\\">tabu</span>–Still, <span class=\\"e2\\">nāchi</span>–I dance— <span class=\\"e2\\">ūrdhva-pāṇi</span>–with upraised arms! <span class=\\"e2\\">gaurāṅga</span>–Gaurāṅga <span class=\\"e2\\">paśi’</span>–enters [my] <span class=\\"e2\\">aṅge</span>–body [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāchāya</span>–makes me dance. <span class=\\"e2\\">sura-tāla-bodha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāi</span>–I do not have a sense of rhythm or tune. <span class=\\"e2\\">tabu</span>–Still, <span class=\\"e2\\">nāchi</span>–I dance! <span class=\\"e2\\">tabu</span>–Still, <span class=\\"e2\\">gāi</span>–I sing! <span class=\\"e2\\">ki</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">jāni</span>–I do not know <span class=\\"e2\\">ki</span>–what [my] <span class=\\"e2\\">gaura-śaśī</span>–moon-like Gaura <span class=\\"e2\\">jāne</span>–thinks."},{"class":"b71","text":" I do not know how to dance or sing. Still, I dance—with my arms upraised! Gaurāṅga enters my body and makes me do so. I do not have any sense of rhythm or tune. Still, I dance! Still, I sing! I do not know what my moon-like Gaura thinks."},{"class":"b176","text":" তথায় গোপগণের সেবা"},{"class":"b177","text":" tathāya gopa-gaṇera sevā"},{"class":"b70","text":" The cowherd boys’ service there"},{"class":"b123","text":" গাদিগাছা গ্রামে আসি’\\tগোপপল্লী মাঝে পশি’<br />\\tগোরা বলে “শুন ভক্তগণ <br />দহকূলে বিচরণ\\tআজি মোদের বিচরণ<br />\\tবৃক্ষমূলে করিব শয়ন ॥৯॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" gādigāchhā grāme āsi’\\tgopa-pallī mājhe paśi’<br />\\tgorā bale, “śuna bhakta-gaṇa<br />daha-kūle vicharaṇa\\tāji modera vicharaṇa<br />\\tvṛkṣa-mūle kariba śayana [9]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">āsi’</span>–We came <span class=\\"e2\\">gādigāchhā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">grāme</span>–to the village of Gādigāchhā [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">paśi’</span>–entered <span class=\\"e2\\">gopa-pallī</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">mājhe</span>–a neighbourhood of cowherds. <span class=\\"e2\\">gorā</span>–Gorā <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–said, <span class=\\"e2\\">“bhakta-gaṇa</span>–“Devotees, <span class=\\"e2\\">śuna</span>–listen! <span class=\\"e2\\">āji</span>–Today <span class=\\"e2\\">modera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">vicharaṇa</span>–our walk [will be] <span class=\\"e2\\">vicharaṇa</span>–a walk <span class=\\"e2\\">daha-kūle</span>–around the bank of this lake. <span class=\\"e2\\">śayana kariba</span>–We will rest <span class=\\"e2\\">vṛkṣa-mūle</span>–at the base of this tree."},{"class":"b50","text":" We came to the village of Gādigāchhā and entered a neighbourhood of cowherds. Gorā said, “Devotees, listen! Today we will walk around the bank of this lake, and then we will rest under this tree."},{"class":"b123","text":" এই বটবৃক্ষতলে\\tগাভী আছে কুতূহলে<br />\\tগোপ-সহ করিব বিহার” ।<br />বহু গোপগণ আইল\\tদধি, ছানা, ননী দিল<br />\\tপথশ্রম না রহিল আর ॥১০॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" ei vaṭa-vṛkṣa-tale\\tgābhī āchhe kutūhale<br />\\tgopa-saha kariba vihāra”<br />bahu gopa-gaṇa āila\\tdadhi, chhānā, nanī dila<br />\\tpatha-śrama nā rahila āra [10]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">āchhe</span>–There are <span class=\\"e2\\">kutūhale</span>–happy <span class=\\"e2\\">gābhī</span>–cows <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">vaṭa-vṛkṣa-tale</span>–under this banyan tree. <span class=\\"e2\\">vihāra kariba</span>–Let us play <span class=\\"e2\\">gopa-saha”</span>–with the cowherd boys!” <span class=\\"e2\\">bahu</span>–Many <span class=\\"e2\\">gopa-gaṇa</span>–cowherds <span class=\\"e2\\">āila</span>–came [over and] <span class=\\"e2\\">dila</span>–offered <span class=\\"e2\\">dadhi</span>–yoghurt, <span class=\\"e2\\">chhānā</span>–curd, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">nanī</span>–butter. [Our] <span class=\\"e2\\">patha-śrama</span>–tiredness from the path <span class=\\"e2\\">āra rahila nā</span>–remained no longer."},{"class":"b50","text":" “There are happy cows under this banyan tree. Let us go and play with the cowherd boys!” Many cowherd boys then came over and offered us yoghurt, curd, and butter, and our tiredness from walking was gone."},{"class":"b123","text":" নৃসিংহানন্দের সঙ্গে\\tপ্রদ্যুম্ন আইল রঙ্গে<br />\\tপুরুষোত্তমাচার্য মিলিল ।<br />মৃদঙ্গের বাদ্যরবে\\tগৃহ ছাড়ি’ আইল সবে<br />\\tহরিধ্বনি গগনে উঠিল ॥১১॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" nṛsiṁhānandera saṅge\\tpradyumna āila raṅge<br />\\tpuruṣottamāchārya milila<br />mṛdaṅgera vādya-rave\\tgṛha chhāḍi’ āila sabe<br />\\thari-dhvani gagane uṭhila [11]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">pradyumna</span>–Pradyumna <span class=\\"e2\\">raṅge</span>–joyfully <span class=\\"e2\\">āila</span>–came over <span class=\\"e2\\">saṅge</span>–with <span class=\\"e2\\">nṛsiṁhānandera</span>–Nṛsiṁhānanda, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">puruṣottamāchārya</span>–Puruṣottam Āchārya (Svarūp Dāmodar) <span class=\\"e2\\">milila</span>–joined [us]. <span class=\\"e2\\">vādya-rave</span>–At the sound <span class=\\"e2\\">mṛdaṅgera</span>–of the mṛdaṅga, <span class=\\"e2\\">sabe</span>–everyone <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍi’</span>–left [their] <span class=\\"e2\\">gṛha</span>–homes [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">āila</span>–came over. <span class=\\"e2\\">hari-dhvani</span>–The sound of ‘Hari’ <span class=\\"e2\\">uṭhila</span>–arose <span class=\\"e2\\">gagane</span>–in the sky."},{"class":"b71","text":" Pradyumna joyfully came over with Nṛsiṁhānanda, and Puruṣottam Āchārya joined us there. Hearing the sound of the mṛdaṅga, everyone left their homes and came over, and the sound of ‘Hari’ resounded in the sky."},{"class":"b176","text":" ভীম গোপ"},{"class":"b177","text":" bhīma gopa"},{"class":"b70","text":" The cowherd boy Bhīma"},{"class":"b97","text":" ভীম-নামে গোপ এক পরম উদার ।<br />অগ্রসর হঞা বলে, “শুনহ গোহার ॥১২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" bhīma-nāme gopa eka parama udāra<br />agrasara hañā bale, “śunaha gohāra [12]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">eka</span>–A <span class=\\"e2\\">parama</span>–very <span class=\\"e2\\">udāra</span>–cordial <span class=\\"e2\\">gopa</span>–cowherd <span class=\\"e2\\">bhīma-nāme</span>–with the name Bhīma <span class=\\"e2\\">agrasara</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">hañā</span>–came forward [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–said, <span class=\\"e2\\">“gohāra</span>–“Dear sir, <span class=\\"e2\\">śunaha</span>–please listen."},{"class":"b50","text":" A very cordial cowherd boy named Bhīma came forward and said, “Dear sir, please listen."},{"class":"b97","text":" আমার জননী শ্যামা গোয়ালিনী ধন্যা ।<br />গঙ্গানগরের সাধু গোয়ালার কন্যা ॥১৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" āmāra jananī śyāmā goyālinī dhanyā<br />gaṅgā-nagarera sādhu goyālāra kanyā [13]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">āmāra</span>–My <span class=\\"e2\\">jananī</span>–mother <span class=\\"e2\\">śyāmā</span>–Śyāmā [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">dhanyā goyālinī</span>–a pious milkmaid [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">kanyā</span>–a daughter <span class=\\"e2\\">sādhu</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">goyālāra</span>–of a virtuous milkman <span class=\\"e2\\">gaṅgā-nagarera</span>–from Gaṅgā Nagar. "},{"class":"b50","text":" “My mother Śyāmā is a pious milkmaid and a daughter of a virtuous milkman from Gaṅgā Nagar."},{"class":"b97","text":" শচী আইকে মা বলিয়া সদা করে সেবা ।<br />সে সম্পর্কে তুমি আমার মাতুল হইবা ॥১৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" śachī āike mā baliyā sadā kare sevā<br />se samparke tumi āmāra mātula ha-ibā [14]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">baliyā</span>–She calls <span class=\\"e2\\">śachī</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">āike</span>–Śachī Āi <span class=\\"e2\\">mā</span>–‘Mother’ [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">sadā</span>–always <span class=\\"e2\\">sevā kare</span>–serves [her.] <span class=\\"e2\\">se</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">samparke</span>–According to this relationship, <span class=\\"e2\\">tumi</span>–You <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-ibā</span>–would be <span class=\\"e2\\">āmāra</span>–my <span class=\\"e2\\">mātula</span>–maternal uncle."},{"class":"b50","text":" “She calls Śachī Āi ‘Mother’ and always serves her. So, You are my uncle."},{"class":"b97","text":" চল মামা মোর ঘরে চল দল লঞা ।<br />শ্রীকৃষ্ণকীর্ত্তন কর আনন্দিত হঞা ॥১৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" chala māmā mora ghare chala dala lañā<br />śrī-kṛṣṇa-kīrtana kara ānandita hañā [15]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">māmā</span>–Dear Uncle, <span class=\\"e2\\">chala</span>–let’s go <span class=\\"e2\\">mora</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ghare</span>–to my house! <span class=\\"e2\\">chala</span>–Let’s go <span class=\\"e2\\">lañā</span>–with [Your] <span class=\\"e2\\">dala</span>–party [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">ānandita</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">hañā</span>–happily <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-kṛṣṇa-kīrtana</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kara</span>–chant the Name of Śrī Kṛṣṇa."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Dear Uncle, let’s go to my house! Come with Your party and happily chant the Name of Śrī Kṛṣṇa."},{"class":"b97","text":" দধি-দুগ্ধ যাহা কিছু রাখিয়াছে মা ।<br />সব খাওয়াইব আর টীপে দিব পা” ॥১৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" dadhi-dugdha yāhā kichhu rākhiyāchhe mā<br />saba khāoyāiba āra ṭīpe diba pā” [16]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">khāoyāiba</span>–I will feed [You] <span class=\\"e2\\">yāhā kichhu saba</span>–all <span class=\\"e2\\">dadhi-dugdha</span>–the yoghurt and milk [my] <span class=\\"e2\\">mā</span>–mother <span class=\\"e2\\">rākhiyāchhe</span>–has stored <span class=\\"e2\\">āra</span>–and <span class=\\"e2\\">ṭīpe</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">diba</span>–massage [Your] <span class=\\"e2\\">pā”</span>–feet.”"},{"class":"b71","text":" “I will feed You all the yoghurt and milk my mother has in store and massage Your feet.”"},{"class":"b176","text":" গৌরাঙ্গের ভীমের গৃহে গমন ও ক্ষীর-ভোজন"},{"class":"b177","text":" gaurāṅgera bhīmera gṛhe gamana o kṣīra bhojana"},{"class":"b70","text":" Gaurāṅga’s visiting Bhīma’s house and eating condensed milk"},{"class":"b97","text":" নাছোড় হইয়া যবে সকলে ধরিল ।<br />গোপপ্রেমে গোরা গোপগৃহেতে চলিল ॥১৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" nāchhoḍa ha-iyā yabe sakale dharila<br />gopa-preme gorā gopa-gṛhete chalila [17]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">yabe</span>–When <span class=\\"e2\\">nāchhoḍa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-iyā</span>–Bhīma became insistent [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">dharila</span>–requested [this] <span class=\\"e2\\">sakale</span>–of everyone, <span class=\\"e2\\">gorā</span>–Gorā <span class=\\"e2\\">chalila</span>–went <span class=\\"e2\\">gopa-gṛhete</span>–to the cowherd’s house <span class=\\"e2\\">gopa-preme</span>–out of love for the cowherd boys."},{"class":"b50","text":" When Bhīma became insistent and requested this of everyone, Gorā went to his home out of love for the cowherd boys."},{"class":"b97","text":" শ্যামা গোয়ালিনী তবে উলুধ্বনি দিয়া ।<br />সকলকে গোয়াল-ঘরে দিলে বসাইয়া ॥১৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" śyāmā goyālinī tabe ulu-dhvani diyā<br />sakalake goyāla-ghare dile basāiyā [18]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">śyāmā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">goyālinī</span>–The milkmaid Śyāmā <span class=\\"e2\\">tabe</span>–then <span class=\\"e2\\">ulu-dhvani</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">diyā</span>–cheered [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">sakalake basāiyā dile</span>–seated everyone down <span class=\\"e2\\">goyāla-ghare</span>–in [her] cowshed."},{"class":"b50","text":" The milkmaid Śyāmā cheered and seated everyone in her cowshed."},{"class":"b97","text":" শ্যামা বলে, “পণ্ডিত দাদা, কেমন আছেন মা?”<br />“ভাল ভাল” বলি’ গোরা নাচাইল গা ॥১৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" śyāmā bale, “paṇḍita dādā, kemana āchhena mā?”<br />“bhāla bhāla” bali’ gorā nāchāila gā [19]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">śyāmā</span>–Śyāmā <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–said, <span class=\\"e2\\">“paṇḍita</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">dādā</span>–“Learned elder brother, <span class=\\"e2\\">kemana</span>–how <span class=\\"e2\\">āchhena</span>–is <span class=\\"e2\\">mā?”</span>–Mother?” <span class=\\"e2\\">gorā</span>–Gorā <span class=\\"e2\\">bali’</span>–said, <span class=\\"e2\\">“bhāla</span>–[She is] well,<span class=\\"e2\\"> bhāla</span>–[She is] well,” [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">gā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāchāila</span>–caused [His] body to dance."},{"class":"b50","text":" Śyāmā said, “Learned elder brother, how is Mother?” Gorā replied, “She is well, she is well”, and began to dance."},{"class":"b97","text":" কলাপাতা পাতি’ শ্যামা দেয় দধি-ক্ষীর ।<br />ভক্তগণ লঞা নিমাই ভোজনে বসে ধীর ॥২০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kalā-pātā pāti’ śyāmā deya dadhi-kṣīra<br />bhakta-gaṇa lañā nimāi bhojane base dhīra [20]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">śyāmā</span>–Śyāmā <span class=\\"e2\\">pāti’</span>–laid out <span class=\\"e2\\">kalā-pātā</span>–banana leaves [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">dadhi-kṣīra deya</span>–served yoghurt and condensed milk. <span class=\\"e2\\">nimāi</span>–Nimāi, <span class=\\"e2\\">lañā</span>–with <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakta-gaṇa</span>–the devotees, <span class=\\"e2\\">dhīra</span>–respectfully <span class=\\"e2\\">base</span>–sat down <span class=\\"e2\\">bhojane</span>–to eat."},{"class":"b71","text":" Śyāmā laid out banana leaves and served yoghurt and condensed milk. Nimāi and the devotees respectfully sat down to eat."},{"class":"b176","text":" গোরাদহ"},{"class":"b177","text":" gorā-daha"},{"class":"b70","text":" Gorā’s lake"},{"class":"b97","text":" ভোজন সমাপি’ চলে সেই দহের তীরে ।<br />হরিগুণগান সবে করে ধীরে ধীরে ॥২১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" bhojana samāpi’ chale sei dahera tīre<br />hari-guṇa-gāna sabe kare dhīre dhīre [21]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [After] <span class=\\"e2\\">sabe</span>–everyone<span class=\\"e2\\"> samāpi’</span>–finished <span class=\\"e2\\">bhojana</span>–eating, [they] <span class=\\"e2\\">dhīre</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">dhīre</span>–slowly <span class=\\"e2\\">chale</span>–went <span class=\\"e2\\">sei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">dahera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">tīre</span>–to the edge of the lake, <span class=\\"e2\\">hari-guṇa-gāna</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kare</span>–chanting the glories of the Lord."},{"class":"b50","text":" After everyone finished eating, they strolled over to the edge of the lake, chanting the glories of the Lord."},{"class":"b97","text":" রামদাস গোপ আসি’ করে নিবেদন ।<br />“দহের জল পান নাহি করে গাভীগণ ॥২২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" rāmadāsa gopa āsi’ kare nivedana<br />“dahera jala pāna nāhi kare gābhī-gaṇa [22]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">gopa</span>–The cowherd boy <span class=\\"e2\\">rāmadāsa</span>–Rāmadās <span class=\\"e2\\">āsi’</span>–came over [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">nivedana kare</span>–said, <span class=\\"e2\\">“gābhī-gaṇa</span>–“[Our] cows <span class=\\"e2\\">pāna</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kare nāhi</span>–do not drink <span class=\\"e2\\">jala</span>–water <span class=\\"e2\\">dahera</span>–from this lake."},{"class":"b71","text":" A cowherd boy named Rāmadās came over and said, “Our cows do not drink water from this lake."},{"class":"b176","text":" দহে নক্র"},{"class":"b177","text":" dahe nakra"},{"class":"b70","text":" The crocodile in the lake"},{"class":"b97","text":" নক্র এক ভয়ঙ্কর বেড়ায় দহের জলে ।<br />জল না খাইয়া গাভী ডাকে হাম্বা বোল” ॥২৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" nakra eka bhayaṅkara beḍāya dahera jale<br />jala nā khāiyā gābhī ḍāke hāmbā bola” [23]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">eka</span>–A <span class=\\"e2\\">bhayaṅkara</span>–fearsome <span class=\\"e2\\">nakra</span>–crocodile <span class=\\"e2\\">beḍāya</span>–comes out <span class=\\"e2\\">dahera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">jale</span>–of this lake’s waters, [and our] <span class=\\"e2\\">gābhī</span>–cows, <span class=\\"e2\\">khāiyā nā</span>–not drinking <span class=\\"e2\\">jala</span>–the water, <span class=\\"e2\\">hāmbā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bola ḍāke”</span>–moo.”"},{"class":"b50","text":" “A fearsome crocodile comes out of this lake, and our cows moo because they cannot drink the water.”"},{"class":"b97","text":" তাহা শুনি’ গোরা করে শ্রীনামকীর্ত্তন ।<br />কীর্ত্তনে আকৃষ্ট হইল নক্র তত ক্ষণ ॥২৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" tāhā śuni’ gorā kare śrī-nāma-kīrtana<br />kīrtane ākṛṣṭa ha-ila nakra tata kṣaṇa [24]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [When] <span class=\\"e2\\">śuni’</span>–He heard <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhā</span>–this, <span class=\\"e2\\">gorā</span>–Gorā <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-nāma-kīrtana kare</span>–chanted the Name, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">nakra</span>–the crocodile <span class=\\"e2\\">tata</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kṣaṇa</span>–immediately <span class=\\"e2\\">ākṛṣṭa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-ila</span>–became attracted <span class=\\"e2\\">kīrtane</span>–to the chanting."},{"class":"b71","text":" When Gorā heard this, He chanted the Name, and the crocodile immediately became attracted to the chanting."},{"class":"b176","text":" নক্র নহে, দেব শিশু"},{"class":"b177","text":" nakra nahe, deva śiśu"},{"class":"b70","text":" Not a crocodile but a child god"},{"class":"b97","text":" শীঘ্র করি’ উঠিয়া আইল গোরা-পায় ।<br />পদস্পর্শে দেবশিশু পরিদৃশ্য হয় ॥২৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" śīghra kari’ uṭhiyā āila gorā-pāya<br />pada-sparśe deva-śiśu paridṛśya haya [25]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">śīghra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kari’</span>–The crocodile quickly <span class=\\"e2\\">uṭhiyā</span>–got out [of the water and] <span class=\\"e2\\">āila</span>–came [over] <span class=\\"e2\\">gorā-pāya</span>–to Gorā’s feet. <span class=\\"e2\\">pada-sparśe</span>–Upon touching [His] feet, <span class=\\"e2\\">paridṛśya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–the crocodile turned [into] <span class=\\"e2\\">deva-śiśu</span>–a child god."},{"class":"b50","text":" The crocodile quickly got out of the water and came over to Gorā’s feet. Upon touching them, the crocodile turned into a child god."},{"class":"b97","text":" কাঁদি’ সেই দেবশিশু করেন স্তবন ।<br />নিজ দুঃখকথা বলে আর করয় রোদন ॥২৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kā̐di’ sei deva-śiśu karena stavana<br />nija duḥkha-kathā bale āra karaya rodana [26]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kā̐di’</span>–Crying, <span class=\\"e2\\">sei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">deva-śiśu</span>–the child god <span class=\\"e2\\">stavana karena</span>–prayed [to the Lord]. <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–He told [the Lord] <span class=\\"e2\\">nija</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">duḥkha-kathā</span>–the tale of his sorrow <span class=\\"e2\\">āra</span>–and <span class=\\"e2\\">rodana karaya</span>–wept."},{"class":"b71","text":" Crying, the child god prayed to the Lord. He recounted the tale of his sorrow and wept."},{"class":"b176","text":" নক্ররূপী দেব শিশুর পূর্ব্ব-বিবরণ"},{"class":"b177","text":" nakra-rūpī deva-śiśura pūrva-vivaraṇa"},{"class":"b70","text":" The child god describes his past in the body of a crocodile"},{"class":"b97","text":" দেবশিশু বলে, “প্রভু দুর্ব্বাসার শাপে ।<br />নক্ররূপে ভ্রমি আমি, সর্ব্বলোক কাঁপে ॥২৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" deva-śiśu bale, “prabhu durvāsāra śāpe<br />nakra-rūpe bhrami āmi, sarva-loka kā̐pe [27]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">deva-śiśu</span>–The child god <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–said, <span class=\\"e2\\">“prabhu</span>–“O Lord! <span class=\\"e2\\">durvāsāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">śāpe</span>–As a result of a curse by Durvāsā Muni, <span class=\\"e2\\">āmi</span>–I <span class=\\"e2\\">bhrami</span>–have been wandering <span class=\\"e2\\">nakra-rūpe</span>–in the form of a crocodile, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-loka</span>–everyone <span class=\\"e2\\">kā̐pe</span>–trembles."},{"class":"b50","text":" The child god said, “O Lord! Cursed by Durvāsā Muni, I have been wandering in the form of a crocodile, making everyone tremble."},{"class":"b97","text":" কাম্যবনে মুনিবর শুতিয়া আছিল ।<br />চঞ্চলতা করি’ তার জটা কাটি নিল ॥২৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kāmyavane muni-vara śutiyā āchhila<br />chañchalatā kari’ tāra jaṭā kāṭi nila [28]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [Once, when] <span class=\\"e2\\">muni-vara</span>–the great sage <span class=\\"e2\\">śutiyā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">āchhila</span>–was resting <span class=\\"e2\\">kāmyavane</span>–in Kāmyavan, <span class=\\"e2\\">chañchalatā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kari’</span>–I mischievously <span class=\\"e2\\">kāṭi</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nila</span>–cut off <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra</span>–his <span class=\\"e2\\">jaṭā</span>–dreadlocks."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Once, when the great sage was resting in Kāmyavan, I mischievously cut off his dreadlocks."},{"class":"b97","text":" ক্রোধে মুনি কহে, ‘তুমি পাঞা নক্ররূপ ।<br />চারি যুগ থাক কর্ম্মফল-অনুরূপ’ ॥২৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" krodhe muni kahe, ‘tumi pāñā nakra-rūpa<br />chāri yuga thāka karma-phala-anurūpa’ [29]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">muni</span>–The sage <span class=\\"e2\\">kahe</span>–said <span class=\\"e2\\">krodhe</span>–angrily, <span class=\\"e2\\">‘tumi</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">pāñā</span>–‘Take <span class=\\"e2\\">nakra-rūpa</span>–the form of a crocodile [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">karma-phala-anurūpa thāka</span>–undergo the befitting results of [your] actions <span class=\\"e2\\">chāri</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">yuga’</span>–for four ages.’"},{"class":"b50","text":" “The sage angrily said, ‘Take the form of a crocodile and suffer the results of your actions for four ages.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" তবে কাঁদিলাম আমি মিনতি করিয়া ।<br />দয়া করি’ মুনি মোরে কহিল ডাকিয়া ॥৩০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" tabe kā̐dilāma āmi minati kariyā<br />dayā kari’ muni more kahila ḍākiyā [30]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">tabe</span>–Then <span class=\\"e2\\">āmi</span>–I <span class=\\"e2\\">kā̐dilāma</span>–cried [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">minati</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kariyā</span>–prayed [to the sage, and] <span class=\\"e2\\">muni</span>–the sage <span class=\\"e2\\">dayā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kari’</span>–graciously <span class=\\"e2\\">ḍākiyā</span>–called <span class=\\"e2\\">more</span>–for me [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">kahila</span>–spoke [to me]."},{"class":"b50","text":" “I cried and prayed to the sage, and he graciously called me over and spoke to me."},{"class":"b97","text":" ‘ওরে দেবশিশু যবে শ্রীনন্দনন্দন ।<br />নবদ্বীপে হইবেন শচীপ্রাণধন ॥৩১॥"},{"class":"b97","text":" তাঁহার কীর্ত্তনে তোমার শাপ-ক্ষয় হবে ।<br />দিব্য দেহ পেয়ে তবে ত্রিপিষ্টপ যাবে’ ॥৩২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ‘ore deva-śiśu yabe śrī-nanda-nandana<br />navadvīpe ha-ibena śachī-prāṇa-dhana [31]"},{"class":"b60","text":" tā̐hāra kīrtane tomāra śāpa-kṣaya habe<br />divya deha peye tabe tripiṣṭapa yābe’ [32]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">‘ore</span>–‘O <span class=\\"e2\\">deva-śiśu</span>–child god! <span class=\\"e2\\">yabe</span>–When <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-nanda-nandana</span>–the son of Śrī Nanda <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-ibena</span>–becomes <span class=\\"e2\\">śachī-prāṇa-dhana</span>–the life and wealth of Śachī <span class=\\"e2\\">navadvīpe</span>–in Nabadwīp, <span class=\\"e2\\">tomāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">śāpa-kṣaya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">habe</span>–you will be freed from [my] curse <span class=\\"e2\\">tā̐hāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kīrtane</span>–by His chanting; <span class=\\"e2\\">peye</span>–you will get <span class=\\"e2\\">divya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">deha</span>–a heavenly body [again and] <span class=\\"e2\\">tabe</span>–then <span class=\\"e2\\">yābe</span>–return <span class=\\"e2\\">tripiṣṭapa’</span>–to the abode of the gods.’"},{"class":"b71","text":" “‘O child god! When the son of Śrī Nanda becomes the life and wealth of Śachī in Nabadwīp, you will be freed from my curse by His chanting; you will get a heavenly body again and return to the abode of the gods.’"},{"class":"b176","text":" দেবশিশুর স্তব"},{"class":"b177","text":" deva-śiśura stava"},{"class":"b70","text":" The child god’s prayers"},{"class":"b97","text":" জয় জয় শচীসুত পতিতপাবন ।<br />দীনহীন অগতির গতি মহাজন ॥৩৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" jaya jaya śachī-suta patita-pāvana<br />dīna-hīna agatira gati mahājana [33]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">jaya</span>–Glory! <span class=\\"e2\\">jaya</span>–Glory <span class=\\"e2\\">śachī-suta</span>–to the son of Śachī, <span class=\\"e2\\">patita-pāvana</span>–the saviour of the fallen, <span class=\\"e2\\">mahājana</span>–the Supreme Soul, <span class=\\"e2\\">gati</span>–the shelter <span class=\\"e2\\">dīna-hīna</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">agatira</span>–of the humble, lowly, and shelterless!"},{"class":"b50","text":" “Glory to the son of Śachī, the saviour of the fallen, the Supreme Soul, the shelter of the humble, lowly, and shelterless!"},{"class":"b97","text":" চৌদ্দ ভুবনে ঘোষে সুকীর্ত্তি তোমার ।<br />আমা হেন অধমেরে করিলে উদ্ধার ॥৩৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" chaudda bhuvane ghoṣe sukīrti tomāra<br />āmā hena adhamere karile uddhāra [34]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">tomāra</span>–Your <span class=\\"e2\\">sukīrti</span>–glories <span class=\\"e2\\">ghoṣe</span>–resound <span class=\\"e2\\">chaudda</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bhuvane</span>–throughout the fourteen worlds! <span class=\\"e2\\">uddhāra karile</span>–You have saved <span class=\\"e2\\">āmā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">hena</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">adhamere</span>–a soul as fallen as myself!"},{"class":"b50","text":" “Your glories resound throughout the fourteen worlds! You have saved a soul as fallen as myself!"},{"class":"b97","text":" এই নবদ্বীপধাম সর্ব্বধামসার ।<br />এখানে হইলে কলি-পাবনাবতার ॥৩৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ei navadvīpa-dhāma sarva-dhāma-sāra<br />ekhāne ha-ile kali-pāvanāvatāra [35]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">āvatāra ha-ile</span>–You have descended <span class=\\"e2\\">ekhāne</span>–here, <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">navadvīpa-dhāma</span>–in Nabadwīp Dhām, <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-dhāma-sāra</span>–the best of all abodes, <span class=\\"e2\\">kali-pāvana</span>–as the saviour for the Age of Kali."},{"class":"b50","text":" “You have descended here, in Nabadwīp Dhām, the best of all abodes, as the saviour for the Age of Kali."},{"class":"b97","text":" কলিজীব উদ্ধারিবে দিয়া হরিনাম ।<br />আসিয়াছ, মহাপ্রভু তোমাকে প্রণাম ॥৩৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kali-jīva uddhāribe diyā hari-nāma<br />āsiyāchha, mahāprabhu tomāke praṇāma [36]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">uddhāribe</span>–You will deliver <span class=\\"e2\\">kali-jīva</span>–the souls of Kali-yuga <span class=\\"e2\\">diyā</span>–by giving <span class=\\"e2\\">hari-nāma</span>–the Name of the Lord. <span class=\\"e2\\">āsiyāchha</span>–You have come, <span class=\\"e2\\">mahāprabhu</span>–O Mahāprabhu! <span class=\\"e2\\">praṇāma</span>–I bow <span class=\\"e2\\">tomāke</span>–to You."},{"class":"b50","text":" “You will deliver the souls of Kali-yuga by giving the Name of the Lord. You have come, O Mahāprabhu! I bow to You."},{"class":"b97","text":" চারি যুগ আছি আমি নক্ররূপ ধরি’ ।<br />এবে উদ্ধারিলে তুমি পতিতপাবন হরি ॥৩৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" chāri yuga āchhi āmi nakra-rūpa dhari’<br />ebe uddhārile tumi patita-pāvana hari [37]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">āmi</span>–I <span class=\\"e2\\">āchhi</span>–have been [here] <span class=\\"e2\\">chāri</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">yuga</span>–for four ages, <span class=\\"e2\\">dhari’</span>–bearing <span class=\\"e2\\">nakra-rūpa</span>–the form of a crocodile. <span class=\\"e2\\">hari</span>–O Lord! <span class=\\"e2\\">patita-pāvana</span>–O saviour of the fallen! <span class=\\"e2\\">ebe</span>–Now <span class=\\"e2\\">tumi</span>–You <span class=\\"e2\\">uddhārile</span>–have delivered [me]."},{"class":"b50","text":" “I have spent four ages in the form of a crocodile. O Lord! O saviour of the fallen! Now You have delivered me."},{"class":"b97","text":" তব মুখে হরিনাম পরম মধুর ।<br />স্থাবরাস্থাবর জীব তারিলে প্রচুর ॥৩৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" tava mukhe hari-nāma parama madhura<br />sthāvarāsthāvara jīva tārile prachura [38]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">tava</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">mukhe</span>–From Your mouth, <span class=\\"e2\\">hari-nāma</span>–the Name of the Lord [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">parama</span>–extremely <span class=\\"e2\\">madhura</span>–sweet. <span class=\\"e2\\">tārile</span>–You have delivered <span class=\\"e2\\">prachura</span>–innumerable <span class=\\"e2\\">jīva</span>–souls, [both] <span class=\\"e2\\">sthāvarāsthāvara</span>–moving and inert."},{"class":"b50","text":" “From Your mouth, the Name of the Lord is extremely sweet, and You have delivered innumerable souls, both moving and inert."},{"class":"b97","text":" আজ্ঞা দেও যাই আমি ত্রিপিষ্টপ যথা ।<br />মাতা পিতা দেখি’ সুখ পাইব সর্ব্বথা” ॥৩৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ājñā deo yāi āmi tripiṣṭapa yathā<br />mātā pitā dekhi’ sukha pāiba sarvathā” [39]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">ājñā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">deo</span>–Give [me] permission, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">āmi</span>–I <span class=\\"e2\\">yāi</span>–will return <span class=\\"e2\\">tripiṣṭapa</span>–to the abode of the gods. <span class=\\"e2\\">dekhi’</span>–Seeing [my] <span class=\\"e2\\">mātā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">pitā</span>–mother and father <span class=\\"e2\\">yathā</span>–there, <span class=\\"e2\\">pāiba</span>–I will feel <span class=\\"e2\\">sarvathā</span>–completely <span class=\\"e2\\">sukha”</span>–happy.”"},{"class":"b71","text":" “Give me permission, and I will return to the abode of the gods. Seeing my mother and father there, I will be completely happy.”"},{"class":"b176","text":" দেবশিশুর স্বরূপপ্রাপ্তি ও স্বস্থানে গমন"},{"class":"b177","text":" deva-śiśura svarūpa-prāpti o svasthāne gamana"},{"class":"b70","text":" The child god obtains his original form and returns home"},{"class":"b97","text":" এত বলি’ প্রণমিয়া দেবশিশু যায় ।<br />কীর্ত্তনের রোল তবে উঠে পুনরায় ॥৪০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" eta bali’ praṇamiyā deva-śiśu yāya<br />kīrtanera rola tabe uṭhe punarāya [40]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bali’</span>–Having said <span class=\\"e2\\">eta</span>–this, <span class=\\"e2\\">deva-śiśu</span>–the child god <span class=\\"e2\\">praṇamiyā</span>–bowed [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">yāya</span>–left, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">rola</span>–the sound <span class=\\"e2\\">kīrtanera</span>–of the chanting <span class=\\"e2\\">tabe</span>–then <span class=\\"e2\\">uṭhe</span>–arose <span class=\\"e2\\">punarāya</span>–again."},{"class":"b50","text":" Having said this, the child god bowed and left, and the sound of the kīrtan arose again."},{"class":"b97","text":" মধ্যাহ্ন হইল দেখি’ সর্ব্ব ভক্তগণ ।<br />প্রভুসঙ্গে মায়াপুর করিল গমন ॥৪১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" madhyāhna ha-ila dekhi’ sarva bhakta-gaṇa<br />prabhu-saṅge māyāpura karila gamana [41]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">dekhi’</span>–Seeing [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">madhyāhna</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-ila</span>–it was midday, <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakta-gaṇa</span>–all the devotees <span class=\\"e2\\">gamana karila</span>–went <span class=\\"e2\\">māyāpura</span>–to Māyāpur <span class=\\"e2\\">prabhu-saṅge</span>–with the Lord."},{"class":"b50","text":" Seeing that it was midday, all the devotees went back to Māyāpur with the Lord."},{"class":"b97","text":" মহাপ্রভুর এই লীলা যে করে শ্রবণ ।<br />ব্রহ্মশাপমুক্ত হয় সেই মহাজন ॥৪২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" mahāprabhura ei līlā ye kare śravaṇa<br />brahma-śāpa-mukta haya sei mahājana [42]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sei ye</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">mahājana</span>–The great souls who <span class=\\"e2\\">śravaṇa kare</span>–hear <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span>–this <span class=\\"e2\\">līlā</span>–Pastime <span class=\\"e2\\">mahāprabhura</span>–of Mahāprabhu <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–become <span class=\\"e2\\">brahma-śāpa-mukta</span>–free from brāhmaṇs’ curses."},{"class":"b71","text":" The great souls who hear this Pastime of Mahāprabhu become free from brāhmaṇs’ curses."},{"class":"b176","text":" গোরাদহ দর্শনের ফল"},{"class":"b177","text":" gorā-daha darśanera phala"},{"class":"b70","text":" The result of seeing Gorā’s lake"},{"class":"b97","text":" সেই হইতে ‘গোরাদহ’ নাম পরচার ।<br />কালীয়দহের ন্যায় হইল তাহার ॥৪৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sei ha-ite ‘gorā-daha’ nāma parachāra<br />kālīya-dahera nyāya ha-ila tāhāra [43]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-ite</span>–Since then, <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–its name <span class=\\"e2\\">‘gorā-daha’</span>–‘Gorā’s lake’ <span class=\\"e2\\">parachāra ha-ila</span>–has spread <span class=\\"e2\\">nyāya</span>–like [the name] <span class=\\"e2\\">kālīya-dahera</span>–of Kālīya’s lake."},{"class":"b50","text":" Since then, the lake has become widely known as ‘Gorā Daha’, like Kālīya Daha in Vraja."},{"class":"b97","text":" সেই ‘দহ’ দর্শনে স্পর্শনে পাপক্ষয় ।<br />কৃষ্ণভক্তি লাভ হয় সর্ব্ববেদে কয় ॥৪৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sei ‘daha’ darśane sparśane pāpa-kṣaya<br />kṛṣṇa-bhakti lābha haya sarva-vede kaya [44]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-vede</span>–All the Vedas <span class=\\"e2\\">kaya</span>–say [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">pāpa-kṣaya haya</span>–sins are removed [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-bhakti</span>–devotion to Kṛṣṇa [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">lābha</span>–attained <span class=\\"e2\\">darśane</span>–by seeing [or] <span class=\\"e2\\">sparśane</span>–by touching <span class=\\"e2\\">sei</span>–this <span class=\\"e2\\">‘daha’</span>–lake."},{"class":"b50","text":" All the Vedas say that sins are removed and devotion to Kṛṣṇa is attained by seeing or touching this lake."},{"class":"b97","text":" সেই গোপগণ দেখ মহাপ্রেমানন্দে ।<br />গৌরাঙ্গে করিল হেথা মামা বলি’ স্কন্ধে ॥৪৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sei gopa-gaṇa dekha mahāpremānande<br />gaurāṅge karila hethā māmā bali’ skandhe [45]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">gopa-gaṇa</span>–The cowherd boys <span class=\\"e2\\">dekha</span>–saw [this Pastime] <span class=\\"e2\\">hethā</span>–here, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">mahā­premānande</span>–with the joy of intense divine love, <span class=\\"e2\\">bali’</span>–they called <span class=\\"e2\\">gaurāṅge</span>–Gaurāṅga <span class=\\"e2\\">māmā</span>–uncle [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">skandhe karila</span>–held [Him] on [their] shoulders."},{"class":"b50","text":" The cowherd boys saw this Pastime here, and with the joy of intense divine love, they called Gaurāṅga ‘uncle’ and held Him on their shoulders."},{"class":"b97","text":" সকলে দেখিল প্রভুর পূর্ব্বাহ্ন-বিহার ।<br />তঁহি মধ্যে দেখে রামকৃষ্ণ-লীলাসার ॥৪৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sakale dekhila prabhura pūrvāhna-vihāra<br />ta̐hi madhye dekhe rāma-kṛṣṇa-līlā-sāra [46]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sakale</span>–Everyone <span class=\\"e2\\">dekhila</span>–saw <span class=\\"e2\\">prabhura</span>–the Lord’s <span class=\\"e2\\">pūrvāhna-vihāra</span>–morning Pastimes, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">ta̐hi</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">madhye</span>–within them, <span class=\\"e2\\">dekhe</span>–they saw <span class=\\"e2\\">rāma-kṛṣṇa-līlā-sāra</span>–the essence of Balarām and Kṛṣṇa’s Pastimes."},{"class":"b50","text":" Everyone saw the Lord’s morning Pastimes, and within them, they saw the essence of Balarām and Kṛṣṇa’s Pastimes."},{"class":"b97","text":" দেখে গোবর্ধন তথা মানস-জাহ্নবীপুলিনে ।<br />কৃষ্ণগোচারণলীলা অতি সমীচীন ॥৪৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" dekhe govardhana tathā mānasa-jāhnavī-puline<br />kṛṣṇa-go-chāraṇa-līlā ati samīchīna [47]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [Everyone] <span class=\\"e2\\">ati</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">samīchīna</span>–actually <span class=\\"e2\\">dekhe</span>–saw <span class=\\"e2\\">govardhana</span>–Govardhan [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-go-chāraṇa-līlā</span>–Kṛṣṇa’s cowherding Pastimes <span class=\\"e2\\">tathā</span>–there <span class=\\"e2\\">mānasa-jāhnavī-puline</span>–on the bank of the Mānasa Gaṅgā."},{"class":"b50","text":" They actually saw Govardhan and Kṛṣṇa’s cowherding Pastimes there on the bank of the Mānasa Gaṅgā."},{"class":"b97","text":" গোপগণ জানিল যে নিমাঞি-চরিত ।<br />শ্রীনন্দনন্দনলীলা নিজ সমীহিত ॥৪৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" gopa-gaṇa jānila ye nimāñi-charita<br />śrī-nanda-nandana-līlā nija samīhita [48]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">gopa-gaṇa</span>–The cowherd boys <span class=\\"e2\\">jānila</span>–understood <span class=\\"e2\\">ye</span>–that <span class=\\"e2\\">nimāñi-charita</span>–the Pastimes of Nimāi [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">līlā</span>–the Pastimes [of] <span class=\\"e2\\">nija</span>–their <span class=\\"e2\\">samīhita</span>–dear <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-nanda-nandana</span>–son of Śrī Nanda."},{"class":"b55","text":" The cowherd boys understood that the Pastimes of Nimāi are the Pastimes of their dear Kṛṣṇa, the son of Śrī Nanda."}]},{"title":"What is Love?","paragraphs":[{"class":"b46","text":"\\r"},{"class":"b58","text":" Chapter Sixteen"},{"class":"b120","text":" পীরিতি কিরূপ?"},{"class":"b121","text":" Pīriti Ki-rūpa?"},{"class":"b175","text":" What is Love?"},{"class":"b176","text":" শ্রীরঘুনাথ গোস্বামীর প্রশ্ন"},{"class":"b177","text":" śrī-raghunātha gosvāmīra praśna"},{"class":"b70","text":" Śrī Raghunāth Goswāmī’s question"},{"class":"b97","text":" একদিন রঘুনাথ স্বরূপে জিজ্ঞাসে ।<br />“কি বস্তু পীরিতি, মোরে শিখাও আভাসে ॥১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" eka-dina raghunātha svarūpe jijñāse<br />“ki vastu pīriti, more śikhāo ābhāse [1]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">eka-dina</span>–One day, <span class=\\"e2\\">raghunātha</span>–Raghunāth <span class=\\"e2\\">jijñāse</span>–asked <span class=\\"e2\\">svarūpe</span>–Svarūp, <span class=\\"e2\\">“ki</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">vastu</span>–“What [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">pīriti</span>–love? <span class=\\"e2\\">śikhāo</span>–Teach <span class=\\"e2\\">more</span>–me <span class=\\"e2\\">ābhāse</span>–in essence."},{"class":"b50","text":" One day, Raghunāth Dās asked Svarūp Dāmodar, “What is love? Please teach me in essence."},{"class":"b97","text":" বিদ্যাপতি চণ্ডীদাস যে প্রীতি বর্ণিল ।<br />সে প্রীতি বুঝিতে মোর শক্তি না হইল ॥২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" vidyāpati chaṇḍī-dāsa ye prīti varṇila<br />se prīti bujhite mora śakti nā ha-ila [2]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">mora</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">śakti</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-ila nā</span>–I do not have the ability <span class=\\"e2\\">bujhite</span>–to understand <span class=\\"e2\\">se</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">prīti ye</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">prīti</span>–the love that <span class=\\"e2\\">vidyāpati</span>–Vidyāpati [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">chaṇḍī-dāsa</span>–Chaṇḍī Dās <span class=\\"e2\\">varṇila</span>–described."},{"class":"b50","text":" “I cannot understand the love that Vidyāpati and Chaṇḍī Dās described."},{"class":"b97","text":" তাঁহাদের বাক্যে বাহ্যে বুঝে যে পীরিতি ।<br />সে কেবল স্ত্রীপুরুষের প্রণয়ের রীতি ॥৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" tā̐hādera vākye bāhye bujhe ye pīriti<br />se kevala strī-puruṣera praṇayera rīti [3]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">se ye</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">pīriti</span>–The love that <span class=\\"e2\\">bujhe</span>–I understand <span class=\\"e2\\">tā̐hādera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">vākye</span>–from their words <span class=\\"e2\\">bāhye</span>–externally [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">kevala</span>–nothing [more than] <span class=\\"e2\\">praṇayera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">rīti</span>–the type of love <span class=\\"e2\\">strī-puruṣera</span>–between a man and a woman."},{"class":"b50","text":" “The love that I understand from their words externally is nothing more than the love between a man and a woman."},{"class":"b97","text":" সে কেমনে পরমার্থ-মধ্যে গণ্য হয় ।<br />প্রাকৃত কামকে কেন অপ্রাকৃত কয় ॥৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" se kemane paramārtha-madhye gaṇya haya<br />prākṛta kāmake kena aprākṛta kaya [4]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kemane</span>–How <span class=\\"e2\\">se</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">gaṇya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–has that been accepted <span class=\\"e2\\">paramārtha-madhye</span>–as spiritual? <span class=\\"e2\\">kena</span>–Why <span class=\\"e2\\">kaya</span>–do they call <span class=\\"e2\\">prākṛta</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kāmake</span>–mundane lust <span class=\\"e2\\">aprākṛta</span>–divine?"},{"class":"b50","text":" “How has that love been accepted as spiritual? And why do they call mundane lust divine?"},{"class":"b97","text":" মহাপ্রভু তোমার সঙ্গে সেই সব গান ।<br />করেন সর্ব্বদা, তার না পাই সন্ধান ॥৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" mahāprabhu tomāra saṅge sei saba gāna<br />karena sarvadā, tāra nā pāi sandhāna [5]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">mahāprabhu</span>–Mahāprabhu <span class=\\"e2\\">sarvadā</span>–always <span class=\\"e2\\">sei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">saba</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">gāna</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">karena</span>–sings all their songs <span class=\\"e2\\">tomāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">saṅge</span>–with you, [but] <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sandhāna</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">pāi nā</span>–I do not understand them."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Mahāprabhu always sings their songs with you, but I do not understand them."},{"class":"b97","text":" প্রভু তব হস্তে মোরে করিল সমর্পণ ।<br />আজ্ঞা কৈল, ‘শিখাও এবে নিগূঢ তত্ত্বধন’ ॥৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" prabhu tava haste more karila samarpaṇa<br />ājñā kaila, ‘śikhāo ebe nigūḍha tattva-dhana’ [6]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">prabhu</span>–The Lord <span class=\\"e2\\">samarpaṇa karila</span>–put <span class=\\"e2\\">more</span>–me <span class=\\"e2\\">tava</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haste</span>–in your hands [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">ājñā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kaila</span>–instructed [you,] <span class=\\"e2\\">‘ebe</span>–‘Now <span class=\\"e2\\">śikhāo</span>–teach [him] <span class=\\"e2\\">nigūḍha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">tattva-dhana’</span>–these precious hidden truths.’"},{"class":"b71","text":" “The Lord put me in your hands and instructed you, ‘Now teach him these precious hidden truths.’"},{"class":"b176","text":" প্রীতি-তত্ত্ব কি ?"},{"class":"b177","text":" prīti-tattva ki ?"},{"class":"b70","text":" What is the nature of love?"},{"class":"b97","text":" কৃপা করি’ প্রীতিতত্ত্ব মোরে দেহ বুঝাইয়া ।<br />কৃতার্থ হইব মুঞি সংশয় ত্যজিয়া” ॥৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kṛpā kari’ prīti-tattva more deha bujhāiyā<br />kṛtārtha ha-iba muñi saṁśaya tyajiyā” [7]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛpā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kari’</span>–Mercifully <span class=\\"e2\\">more bujhāiyā deha</span>–help me understand <span class=\\"e2\\">prīti-tattva</span>–the nature of love. [Then] <span class=\\"e2\\">muñi</span>–I <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛtārtha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-iba</span>–will be fulfilled [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">tyajiyā</span>–leave behind [my] <span class=\\"e2\\">saṁśaya”</span>–doubts.”"},{"class":"b71","text":" “Please help me understand the nature of love. Then I will be fulfilled and leave behind my doubts.”"},{"class":"b176","text":" উত্তর"},{"class":"b177","text":" uttara"},{"class":"b70","text":" The answer"},{"class":"b97","text":" স্বরূপ বলিল, “ভাই রঘুনাথদাস ।<br />নিভৃতে তোমারে তত্ত্ব করিব প্রকাশ ॥৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" svarūpa balila, “bhāi raghunātha-dāsa<br />nibhṛte tomāre tattva kariba prakāśa [8]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">svarūpa</span>–Svarūp <span class=\\"e2\\">balila</span>–said, <span class=\\"e2\\">“bhāi</span>–“Dear brother, <span class=\\"e2\\">raghunātha-dāsa</span>–Raghunāth Dās! <span class=\\"e2\\">nibhṛte</span>–Confidentially, <span class=\\"e2\\">prakāśa kariba</span>–I will reveal <span class=\\"e2\\">tattva</span>–this truth <span class=\\"e2\\">tomāre</span>–to you."},{"class":"b50","text":" Svarūp said, “Dear brother, Raghunāth Dās! Confidentially, I will reveal this truth to you."},{"class":"b97","text":" আমি কিবা রামানন্দ অথবা পণ্ডিত ।<br />কেহ না বুঝিবে তত্ত্ব প্রভুর উদিত ॥৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" āmi kibā rāmānanda athavā paṇḍita<br />keha nā bujhibe tattva prabhura udita [9]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kibā</span>–Neither <span class=\\"e2\\">āmi</span>–I, <span class=\\"e2\\">athavā</span>–nor <span class=\\"e2\\">rāmānanda</span>–Rāmānanda, <span class=\\"e2\\">paṇḍita</span>–Gadādhar Paṇḍit, <span class=\\"e2\\">keha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nā</span>–or anyone [else], <span class=\\"e2\\">bujhibe</span>–will [ever] understand <span class=\\"e2\\">tattva</span>–the truth <span class=\\"e2\\">prabhura</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">udita</span>–revealed by the Lord."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Neither I, nor Rāmānanda, Gadādhar Paṇḍit, or anyone else, will ever understand the love that the Lord revealed."},{"class":"b97","text":" তবে যদি গৌরচন্দ্র জিহ্বায় বসিয়া ।<br />বলাইবে নিজতত্ত্ব সকৃপ হইয়া ॥১০॥<br />তখনি জানিবে হৈল সুসত্য প্রকাশ ।<br />শুনিয়া আনন্দ পাবে রঘুনাথদাস ॥১১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" tabe yadi gaurachandra jihvāya basiyā<br />balāibe nija-tattva sakṛpa ha-iyā [10]<br />takhani jānibe haila susatya prakāśa<br />śuniyā ānanda pābe raghunātha-dāsa [11]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">tabe</span>–Still, <span class=\\"e2\\">yadi</span>–if <span class=\\"e2\\">gaurachandra</span>–Gaurachandra <span class=\\"e2\\">sakṛpa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-iyā</span>–mercifully <span class=\\"e2\\">basiyā</span>–sits <span class=\\"e2\\">jihvāya</span>–on [my] tongue [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">balāibe</span>–causes me to speak <span class=\\"e2\\">nija-tattva</span>–about His love, <span class=\\"e2\\">takhani</span>–then <span class=\\"e2\\">jānibe</span>–you will know [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">susatya</span>–the highest truth <span class=\\"e2\\">prakāśa haila</span>–has been revealed, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">śuniyā</span>–hearing [it,] <span class=\\"e2\\">raghunātha-dāsa</span>–Raghunāth Dās, <span class=\\"e2\\">ānanda</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">pābe</span>–you will be overjoyed!"},{"class":"b50","text":" “Still, if Gaurachandra mercifully takes control of my tongue and causes me to speak about His love, then you will know that the highest truth has been revealed to you, and when you hear it, Raghunāth Dās, you will be overjoyed!"},{"class":"b123","text":" চণ্ডীদাস বিদ্যাপতি\\tকর্ণামৃত রায়ের গীতি<br />\\tএসব অমূল্য শাস্ত্র জান ।<br />এসবে নাহিক কাম\\tএসব প্রেমের ধাম<br />\\tঅপ্রাকৃত তাহাতে বিধান ॥১২॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" chaṇḍī-dāsa vidyāpati\\tkarṇāmṛta rāyera gīti<br />\\te-saba amūlya śāstra jāna<br />e-sabe nāhika kāma\\te-saba premera dhāma<br />\\taprākṛta tāhāte vidhāna [12]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">jāna</span>–Know [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">karṇāmṛta</span>–<span class=\\"e33\\">Śrī Kṛṣṇa-karṇāmṛta</span> [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">gīti</span>–the songs <span class=\\"e2\\">chaṇḍī-dāsa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">vidyāpati</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">rāyera</span>–of Chaṇḍī Dās, Vidyāpati, and Rāmānanda Rāy [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">e-saba</span>–all <span class=\\"e2\\">amūlya</span>–invaluable <span class=\\"e2\\">śāstra</span>–scriptures. <span class=\\"e2\\">nāhika</span>–There is no <span class=\\"e2\\">kāma</span>–lust <span class=\\"e2\\">e-sabe</span>–within them. <span class=\\"e2\\">e-saba</span>–They [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">dhāma</span>–repositories <span class=\\"e2\\">premera</span>–of divine love. <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhāte</span>–Within them, <span class=\\"e2\\">aprākṛta</span>–the divine [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">vidhāna</span>–the law."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Know that <span class=\\"e3\\">Śrī Kṛṣṇa-karṇāmṛta</span> and the songs of Chaṇḍī Dās, Vidyāpati, and Rāmānanda Rāy are invaluable scriptures that contain no lust. They are repositories of love, and by nature divine."},{"class":"b123","text":" স্ত্রী-পুরুষ-বিবরণ\\tযে কিছু তঁহি বর্ণন<br />\\tসে সব উপমা মাত্র সার ।<br />প্রাকৃত-কাম-বর্ণন\\tতাহে কৃষ্ণ-অদর্শন<br />\\tঅপ্রাকৃত করহ বিচার ॥১৩॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" strī-puruṣa-vivaraṇa\\tye kichhu ta̐hi varṇana<br />\\tse saba upamā mātra sāra<br />prākṛta-kāma-varṇana\\ttāhe kṛṣṇa-adarśana<br />\\taprākṛta karaha vichāra [13]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">strī-puruṣa-vivaraṇa</span>–The descriptions of men and women— <span class=\\"e2\\">se</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">saba ye</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kichhu</span>–all the <span class=\\"e2\\">varṇana</span>–descriptions— <span class=\\"e2\\">ta̐hi</span>–within them [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">upamā</span>–analogies, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">mātra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sāra</span>–nothing more. <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-adarśana</span>–Kṛṣṇa is absent <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhe</span>–within <span class=\\"e2\\">prākṛta-kāma-varṇana</span>–descriptions of mundane lust; [so,] <span class=\\"e2\\">vichāra karaha</span>–consider [these descriptions] <span class=\\"e2\\">aprākṛta</span>–divine."},{"class":"b50","text":" “All the descriptions of men and women within them are analogies, and nothing more. Kṛṣṇa is never present within descriptions of mundane lust; so, consider the descriptions within them to be divine."},{"class":"b123","text":" কি পুরুষ, কিবা নারী,\\tএ-তত্ত্ব বুঝিতে নারি<br />\\tজড়দেহে করে রসরঙ্গ ।<br />সে গুরু কৃষ্ণের ভাণে\\tশুদ্ধ-রতি নাহি জানে<br />\\tতাহার ভজন মায়ারঙ্গ ॥১৪॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" ki puruṣa, kibā nārī,\\te-tattva bujhite nāri<br />\\tjaḍa-dehe kare rasa-raṅga<br />se guru kṛṣṇera bhāṇe\\tśuddha-rati nāhi jāne<br />\\ttāhāra bhajana māyā-raṅga [14]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">ki</span>–Whether <span class=\\"e2\\">puruṣa</span>–a man <span class=\\"e2\\">kibā</span>–or <span class=\\"e2\\">nārī</span>–a women, [one who] <span class=\\"e2\\">rasa-raṅga kare</span>–takes pleasure <span class=\\"e2\\">jaḍa-dehe</span>–in [their] material body <span class=\\"e2\\">bujhite nāri</span>–cannot understand <span class=\\"e2\\">e-tattva</span>–this love. <span class=\\"e2\\">se</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">guru</span>–A ‘guru’ who <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāṇe</span>–pretends to be Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">jāne nāhi</span>–does not understand <span class=\\"e2\\">śuddha-rati</span>–pure love, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhāra</span>–his <span class=\\"e2\\">bhajana</span>–‘worship’ [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">māyā-raṅga</span>–a trick of Māyā."},{"class":"b71","text":" “If anyone—be they a man or a woman—takes pleasure in their material body, they can never understand this love. A ‘guru’ who pretends to be Kṛṣṇa does not understand pure love, and his ‘worship’ is a trick of Māyā."},{"class":"b176","text":" কৃষ্ণপ্রেম"},{"class":"b177","text":" kṛṣṇa-prema"},{"class":"b70","text":" Love for Kṛṣṇa"},{"class":"b123","text":" কৃষ্ণপ্রেম সুনির্ম্মল\\tযেন শুদ্ধ গঙ্গাজল<br />\\tসেই প্রেমা অমৃতের সিন্ধু ।<br />নির্ম্মল সে অনুরাগ\\tনাহি তাহে জড়দাগ<br />\\tশুক্লবস্ত্র শূন্যমসীবিন্দু ॥১৫॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" kṛṣṇa-prema sunirmala\\tyena śuddha gaṅgā-jala<br />\\tsei premā amṛtera sindhu<br />nirmala se anurāga\\tnāhi tāhe jaḍa-dāga<br />\\tśukla-vastra śūnya-masī-bindu [15]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-prema</span>–Love for Kṛṣṇa [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">sunirmala</span>–perfectly pure, <span class=\\"e2\\">yena</span>–like [the] <span class=\\"e2\\">śuddha</span>–pure <span class=\\"e2\\">gaṅgā-jala</span>–water of the Ganges. <span class=\\"e2\\">sei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">premā</span>–Such love [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">amṛtera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sindhu</span>–an ocean of nectar. <span class=\\"e2\\">nāhi</span>–There is not <span class=\\"e2\\">jaḍa-dāga</span>–a trace of mundanity <span class=\\"e2\\">se nirmala</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">anurāga tāhe</span>–within such pure love. [It is like] <span class=\\"e2\\">śukla-vastra</span>–a white cloth [that is] <span class=\\"e2\\">śūnya-masī-bindu</span>–free from a drop of ink."},{"class":"b50","text":" [Svarūp Dāmodar continued:] “Love for Kṛṣṇa is perfectly pure, like the pure water of the Ganges; it is an ocean of nectar. Within such pure love, there is not even a trace of mundanity. It is like a white cloth that is free from even a single drop of ink."},{"class":"b123","text":" শুদ্ধপ্রেম সুখসিন্ধু\\tপাই তার এক বিন্দু<br />\\tসেই বিন্দু জগৎ ডুবায় ।<br />জড়দেহে করি’ প্রীতি\\tকেবল কামের রীতি<br />\\tশুদ্ধ দেহ না হয় উদয় ॥১৬॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" śuddha-prema sukha-sindhu\\tpāi tāra eka bindu<br />\\tsei bindu jagat ḍubāya<br />jaḍa-dehe kari’ prīti\\tkevala kāmera rīti<br />\\tśuddha deha nā haya udaya [16]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">śuddha-prema</span>–Pure love [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">sukha-sindhu</span>–an ocean of joy. <span class=\\"e2\\">pāi</span>–I have received <span class=\\"e2\\">eka</span>–one <span class=\\"e2\\">bindu</span>–drop <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra</span>–of it, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">sei</span>–this <span class=\\"e2\\">bindu</span>–drop <span class=\\"e2\\">ḍubāya</span>–floods <span class=\\"e2\\">jagat</span>–the world. <span class=\\"e2\\">prīti kari’</span>–Loving <span class=\\"e2\\">jaḍa-dehe</span>–the material body [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">kevala</span>–merely <span class=\\"e2\\">kāmera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">rīti</span>–a form of lust, [and one’s] <span class=\\"e2\\">śuddha</span>–pure <span class=\\"e2\\">deha</span>–body <span class=\\"e2\\">udaya haya nā</span>–is not revealed [by doing so]."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Pure love is an ocean of joy. I have received one drop of it, and this drop floods the world. Loving the material body is merely a form of lust, and one’s divine body will never be revealed by doing so."},{"class":"b123","text":" দূরে শুদ্ধ প্রেমবন্ধ\\tকপট প্রেমেতে অন্ধ<br />\\tসেই প্রেমে কৃষ্ণ নাহি পায় ।<br />তবে যে করে ক্রন্দন\\tস্বসৌভাগ্য প্রখ্যাপন<br />\\tকরে ইহা, জানিহ নিশ্চয় ॥১৭॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" dūre śuddha prema-bandha\\tkapaṭa premete andha<br />\\tsei preme kṛṣṇa nāhi pāya<br />tabe ye kare krandana\\tsvasaubhāgya prakhyāpana<br />\\tkare ihā, jāniha niśchaya [17]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">andha</span>–Those who are blinded <span class=\\"e2\\">kapaṭa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">premete</span>–by insincere love [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">dūre</span>–far <span class=\\"e2\\">śuddha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">prema-bandha</span>–from a connection with pure love: <span class=\\"e2\\">pāya nāhi</span>–one does not attain <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span>–Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">sei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">preme</span>–with such ‘love’. <span class=\\"e2\\">jāniha</span>–Know <span class=\\"e2\\">niśchaya</span>–for certain <span class=\\"e2\\">ihā</span>–that <span class=\\"e2\\">ye</span>–those who <span class=\\"e2\\">tabe</span>–still <span class=\\"e2\\">krandana kare</span>–shed tears [only] <span class=\\"e2\\">prakhyāpana</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kare</span>–make a show <span class=\\"e2\\">svasaubhāgya</span>–of their ‘fortune’."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Those who are blinded by insincere love are far from having pure love: no one can get Kṛṣṇa with such ‘love’. Know for certain that those who still shed tears are only making a show of their ‘fortune’."},{"class":"b123","text":" কৃষ্ণপ্রেম যার হয়\\tতার বিভাব চিন্ময়<br />\\tঅনুভাব দেহেতে প্রকাশ ।<br />সাত্ত্বিকাদি ব্যভিচারী\\tচিন্ময় স্বরূপ ধরি’<br />\\tচিৎস্বরূপে করয়ে বিলাস ॥১৮॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" kṛṣṇa-prema yāra haya\\ttāra vibhāva chinmaya<br />\\tanubhāva dehete prakāśa<br />sāttvikādi vyabhichārī\\tchinmaya svarūpa dhari’<br />\\tchit-svarūpe karaye vilāsa [18]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">vibhāva</span>–The stimuli (causes of rati) <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra yāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–of those who have <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-prema</span>–love for Kṛṣṇa [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">chinmaya</span>–spiritual. [Their] <span class=\\"e2\\">anubhāva</span>–gestures, <span class=\\"e2\\">sāttvikādi</span>–ecstasies, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">vyabhichārī</span>–emotions, <span class=\\"e2\\">dhari’</span>–having <span class=\\"e2\\">chinmaya</span>–spiritual <span class=\\"e2\\">svarūpa</span>–forms, <span class=\\"e2\\">prakāśa</span>–manifest [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">vilāsa karaye</span>–play <span class=\\"e2\\">chit-svarūpe dehete</span>–within [their] spiritual bodies."},{"class":"b50","text":" “The stimuli of those who have love for Kṛṣṇa are spiritual. Their gestures, ecstasies, and emotions, having spiritual forms, manifest and play within their spiritual bodies."},{"class":"b123","text":" ধন্য সেই লীলাশুক\\tকৃষ্ণ তারে হয়ে সম্মুখ<br />\\tদিল ব্রজের অপ্রাকৃত রস ।<br />ছাড়িল এদেহ-রঙ্গ\\tপ্রাকৃতালম্বন-ভঙ্গ<br />\\tতাহে কৃষ্ণ পরম সন্তোষ ॥১৯॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" dhanya sei līlāśuka\\tkṛṣṇa tāre haye sammukha<br />\\tdila vrajera aprākṛta rasa<br />chhāḍila e-deha-raṅga\\tprākṛtālambana-bhaṅga<br />\\ttāhe kṛṣṇa parama santoṣa [19]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sei līlāśuka</span>–Līlāśuka (Śrīla Bilvamaṅgal Ṭhākur) [is most] <span class=\\"e2\\">dhanya</span>–fortunate: <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span>–Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">tāre sammukha haye</span>–came before him [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">dila</span>–revealed <span class=\\"e2\\">aprākṛta</span>–the divine <span class=\\"e2\\">rasa</span>–rasas <span class=\\"e2\\">vrajera</span>–of Vraja [to him when] <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍila</span>–he gave up <span class=\\"e2\\">e-deha-raṅga</span>–the pleasures of the body, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">prākṛtālambana-bhaṅga</span>–broke away from material para­phernalia. <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhe</span>–Thereby, <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span>–Kṛṣṇa [was] <span class=\\"e2\\">parama</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">santoṣa</span>–greatly pleased."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Līlāśuka is most fortunate: Kṛṣṇa came before him and revealed the divine rasas of Vraja to him when he gave up bodily pleasures and broke away from material paraphernalia. Kṛṣṇa was greatly pleased by this."},{"class":"b123","text":" বিদ্যাপতি, চণ্ডীদাস\\tছাড়ি’ পূর্ব্ব রসাভাস<br />\\tঅপ্রাকৃত-রসলাভ কৈল ।<br />পূর্ব্বে ছিল তুচ্ছ রস\\tতাহা ছাড়ি’ প্রেমবশ<br />\\tহঞা, কৃষ্ণভজন লভিল ॥২০॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" vidyāpati chaṇḍī-dāsa\\tchhāḍi’ pūrva rasābhāsa<br />\\taprākṛta-rasa-lābha kaila<br />pūrve chhila tuchchha rasa\\ttāhā chhāḍi’ prema-vaśa<br />\\thañā, kṛṣṇa-bhajana labhila [20]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">vidyāpati</span>–Vidyāpati [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">chaṇḍī-dāsa</span>–Chaṇḍī Dās <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍi’</span>–rejected <span class=\\"e2\\">rasābhāsa</span>–the tainted rasas <span class=\\"e2\\">pūrva</span>–of the past [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">aprākṛta-rasa-lābha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kaila</span>–attained divine rasa. <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍi’</span>–They left behind <span class=\\"e2\\">tuchchha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">rasa</span>–the crude pleasures <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhā</span>–that <span class=\\"e2\\">chhila</span>–existed <span class=\\"e2\\">pūrve</span>–previously, <span class=\\"e2\\">hañā</span>–became <span class=\\"e2\\">prema-vaśa</span>–captivated by divine love, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">labhila</span>–attained <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-bhajana</span>–service to Kṛṣṇa."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Vidyāpati and Chaṇḍī Dās rejected the tainted rasas of the past and attained divine rasa. They left behind the crude pleasures that existed previously, became captivated by divine love, and attained service to Kṛṣṇa."},{"class":"b123","text":" তুচ্ছ রসে মাতোয়ার\\tনা পায় কৃষ্ণরস-সার<br />\\tনহে বংশীবদনালম্বন ।<br />জড় দেহে সাজ সাজ\\tমাথায় তার পড়ে বাজ<br />\\tপ্রাণকীটের করয়ে ধারণ ॥২১॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" tuchchha rase mātoyāra\\tnā pāya kṛṣṇa-rasa-sāra<br />\\tnahe vaṁśī-vadanālambana<br />jaḍa dehe sāja sāja\\tmāthāya tāra paḍe vāja<br />\\tprāṇa-kīṭera karaye dhāraṇa [21]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">mātoyāra</span>–Those who are intoxicated <span class=\\"e2\\">tuchchha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">rase</span>–by crude pleasures <span class=\\"e2\\">pāya nā</span>–do not attain <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-rasa-sāra</span>–the essence of devotion to Kṛṣṇa, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">vaṁśī-vadanālambana nahe</span>–the Flute Player does not become the object [of their love]. [Let] <span class=\\"e2\\">vāja</span>–lightning <span class=\\"e2\\">paḍe</span>–strike <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">māthāya</span>–the head of those [who] <span class=\\"e2\\">sāja</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sāja</span>–pamper [their] <span class=\\"e2\\">jaḍa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">dehe</span>–material bodies! <span class=\\"e2\\">prāṇa-kītera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">dhāraṇa karaye</span>–They live the life of an insect!"},{"class":"b50","text":" “Those who are intoxicated by crude pleasures do not attain the essence of devotion to Kṛṣṇa, and Kṛṣṇa the flute player does not become the object of their love. Let lightning strike the heads of those who pamper their bodies! They live the life of an insect!"},{"class":"b123","text":" সেই তুচ্ছ রস ত্যজি’\\tশ্রীনন্দনন্দন ভজি’<br />\\tদেখে কৃষ্ণ শ্রীবংশীবদন ।<br />নিজে গোপীদেহ পায়\\tব্রজবনে বেগে যায়<br />\\tপূর্ব্ব সঙ্গ করয় ত্যজন ॥২২॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" sei tuchchha rasa tyaji’\\tśrī-nanda-nandana bhaji’<br />\\tdekhe kṛṣṇa śrī-vaṁśī-vadana<br />nije gopī-deha pāya\\tvraja-vane vege yāya<br />\\tpūrva saṅga karaya tyajana [22]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [When] <span class=\\"e2\\">tyaji’</span>–souls leave behind <span class=\\"e2\\">sei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">tuchchha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">rasa</span>–crude pleasures, <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaji’</span>–serve <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-nanda-nandana</span>–the son of Nanda, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">dekhe</span>–see <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span>–Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-vaṁśī-vadana</span>–the flute player, [they then] <span class=\\"e2\\">pāya</span>–attain <span class=\\"e2\\">nije</span>–personally <span class=\\"e2\\">gopī-deha</span>–the bodies of gopīs, <span class=\\"e2\\">vege</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">yāya</span>–run <span class=\\"e2\\">vraja-vane</span>–to the forest of Vraja, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">tyajana karaya</span>–leave behind <span class=\\"e2\\">pūrva</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">saṅga</span>–all [their] previous attachments."},{"class":"b71","text":" “When souls leave behind crude pleasures, serve Kṛṣṇa, and see Him playing the flute, they then attain the bodies of gopīs and run to Vṛndāvan, leaving behind all their previous attachments."},{"class":"b176","text":" তথাহি মহাপ্রভুর শ্লোক"},{"class":"b177","text":" tathāhi mahāprabhura śloka"},{"class":"b70","text":" Mahāprabhu’s verse in confirmation"},{"class":"b123","text":" ‘ন প্রেমগন্ধোঽস্তি দরাপি মে হরৌ<br />ক্রন্দামি সৌভাগ্যভরং প্রকাশিতুম্ ।<br />বংশীবিলাস্যাননলোকনং বিনা<br />বিভর্ম্মি যৎ প্রাণপতঙ্গকান্ বৃথা’ ॥২৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ‘na prema-gandho ’sti darāpi me harau<br />krandāmi saubhāgya-bharaṁ prakāśitum<br />vaṁśī-vilāsy-ānana-lokanaṁ vinā<br />bibharmi yat prāṇa-pataṅgakān vṛthā’ [23]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">me asti na</span>–I do not have <span class=\\"e2\\">darā api</span>–even a trace <span class=\\"e2\\">prema-gandhaḥ</span>–of the fragrance of divine love <span class=\\"e2\\">harau</span>–for Kṛṣṇa. [Still,] <span class=\\"e2\\">krandāmi</span>–I cry <span class=\\"e2\\">prakāśitum</span>–to show [others that I have]<span class=\\"e2\\"> saubhāgya-bharaṁ</span>–a great fortune. <span class=\\"e2\\">vinā</span>–Without <span class=\\"e2\\">vaṁśī-vilāsy-ānana-lokanaṁ</span>–a glimpse of the face of that Flute Player, <span class=\\"e2\\">bibharmi</span>–I carry on [my] <span class=\\"e2\\">vṛthā</span>–meaningless, <span class=\\"e2\\">yat prāṇa-pataṅgakān</span>–insect-like life."},{"class":"b71","text":" “‘I do not have even a trace of love for Kṛṣṇa. Still, I cry to show that I have a great fortune. Without a glimpse of the face of that Flute Player, I carry on My meaningless, insect-like life.’"},{"class":"b176","text":" ব্রজগোপী ব্যতীত পীরিতি বুঝে না"},{"class":"b177","text":" vraja-gopī vyatīta pīriti bujhe nā"},{"class":"b70","text":" No one understands love except the gopīs of Vraja"},{"class":"b129","text":" পীরিতি পীরিতি\\tপীরিতি বলে<br />\\tপীরিতি বুঝিল কে ?<br />যে জন পীরিতি\\tবুঝিতে পারে<br />\\tব্রজগোপী হয় সে ॥২৪॥"},{"class":"b93","text":" pīriti pīriti\\tpīriti bale<br />\\tpīriti bujhila ke?<br />ye jana pīriti\\tbujhite pāre<br />\\tvraja-gopī haya se [24]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–People say, <span class=\\"e2\\">pīriti</span>–“Love, <span class=\\"e2\\">pīriti</span>–love, <span class=\\"e2\\">pīriti</span>–love”, [but] <span class=\\"e2\\">ke</span>–who <span class=\\"e2\\">bujhila</span>–has understood <span class=\\"e2\\">pīriti</span>–love? <span class=\\"e2\\">se ye</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">jana</span>–Souls who <span class=\\"e2\\">pāre</span>–can [actually] <span class=\\"e2\\">bujhite</span>–understand <span class=\\"e2\\">pīriti</span>–love <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–become <span class=\\"e2\\">vraja-gopī</span>–gopīs in Vraja."},{"class":"b50","text":" [Svarūp Dāmodar continued:] “People say, ‘Love, love, love’, but who has understood love? Souls who can actually understand love become gopīs in Vraja."},{"class":"b129","text":" পীরিতি বলিয়া\\tতিনটি আঁখর<br />\\tবিদিত ভুবন-মাঝে ।<br />যাহাতে পশিল\\tসেই সে মজিল<br />\\tকি তার কলঙ্কলাজে ॥২৫॥"},{"class":"b93","text":" pīriti baliyā\\ttinaṭi ā̐khara<br />\\tvidita bhuvana-mājhe<br />yāhāte paśila\\tsei se majila<br />\\tki tāra kalaṅka-lāje [25]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">tinaṭi</span>–The three <span class=\\"e2\\">baliyā</span>–spoken <span class=\\"e2\\">ā̐khara</span>–syllables <span class=\\"e2\\">pīriti</span>–<span class=\\"e33\\">pī</span>, <span class=\\"e33\\">ri</span>, and <span class=\\"e33\\">ti</span> [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">vidita</span>–known <span class=\\"e2\\">bhuvana-mājhe</span>–throughout the world. <span class=\\"e2\\">se yāhāte</span>–Souls in whom <span class=\\"e2\\">sei</span>–they <span class=\\"e2\\">paśila</span>–have entered <span class=\\"e2\\">majila</span>–become overwhelmed. <span class=\\"e2\\">ki</span>–What <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kalaṅka-lāje</span>–is shame or disgrace to them?"},{"class":"b50","text":" “These three syllables <span class=\\"e3\\">pī</span>, <span class=\\"e3\\">ri</span>, and <span class=\\"e3\\">ti</span> (in the word <span class=\\"e3\\">pīriti</span>) are known throughout the world. Souls in whom they have entered become overwhelmed. What is shame or disgrace to them?"},{"class":"b129","text":" ব্রজগোপী হঞা\\tচিদ্দেহ স্মরিয়া<br />\\tজড়ের সম্বন্ধ ছাড়ে ।<br />বিষয়ে আশ্রয়ে\\tশুদ্ধ-আলম্বন<br />\\tপরকীয়-রস বাড়ে ॥২৬॥"},{"class":"b93","text":" vraja-gopī hañā\\tchid-deha smariyā<br />\\tjaḍera sambandha chhāḍe<br />viṣaye āśraye\\tśuddha-ālambana<br />\\tparakīya-rasa bāḍe [26]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">hañā</span>–Becoming <span class=\\"e2\\">vraja-gopī</span>–gopīs in Vraja [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">smariyā</span>–meditating <span class=\\"e2\\">chid-deha</span>–with [their] spiritual bodies, <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍe</span>–they give up<span class=\\"e2\\"> jaḍera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sambandha</span>–all connection with matter. <span class=\\"e2\\">parakīya-rasa</span>–Paramour love <span class=\\"e2\\">bāḍe</span>–develops [when its] <span class=\\"e2\\">ālambana</span>–basis, <span class=\\"e2\\">viṣaye</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">āśraye</span>–the lover and the beloved, [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">śuddha</span>–pure."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Becoming gopīs in Vraja and meditating with their spiritual bodies, they give up all connection with matter. Paramour love develops when its basis, the lover and the beloved, are pure."},{"class":"b97","text":" ব্রজ বিনা কোথাও নাহি পরকীয়-ভাব ।<br />বৈকুণ্ঠ-লক্ষ্মীতে তার সদা অসদ্ভাব ॥২৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" vraja vinā kothāo nāhi parakīya-bhāva<br />vaikuṇṭha-lakṣmīte tāra sadā asadbhāva [27]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">parakīya-bhāva</span>–Paramour love <span class=\\"e2\\">kothāo</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāhi</span>–does not exist anywhere <span class=\\"e2\\">vinā</span>–except <span class=\\"e2\\">vraja</span>–Vraja. <span class=\\"e2\\">sadā</span>–Forever, <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">asadbhāva</span>–it is incompatible <span class=\\"e2\\">vaikuṇṭha-lakṣmīte</span>–with Lakṣmī in Vaikuṇṭha."},{"class":"b71","text":" “Paramour love does not exist anywhere except Vraja. It is forever incompatible with Lakṣmī Devī in Vaikuṇṭha."},{"class":"b176","text":" সহজিয়ার প্রীতি"},{"class":"b177","text":" sahajiyāra prīti"},{"class":"b70","text":" The love of the imitationists"},{"class":"b129","text":" সংসারে যতেক\\tপুরুষ, রমণী<br />\\tআলম্বন-দোষে সদা ।<br />রক্তমাংসদেহে\\tআরোপ করিতে<br />\\tনারকী হয় সর্ব্বদা ॥২৮॥"},{"class":"b93","text":" saṁsāre yateka\\tpuruṣa, ramaṇī<br />\\tālambana-doṣe sadā<br />rakta-māṁsa-dehe\\tāropa karite<br />\\tnārakī haya sarvadā [28]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">yateka</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">puruṣa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ramaṇī</span>–The men and woman <span class=\\"e2\\">saṁsāre</span>–in this world [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">sadā</span>–always <span class=\\"e2\\">ālambana-doṣe</span>–the wrong basis [for that love]. <span class=\\"e2\\">āropa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">karite</span>–By attributing [that love] <span class=\\"e2\\">rakta-māṁsa-dehe</span>–to bodies of flesh and blood, <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–souls become <span class=\\"e2\\">nārakī</span>–sinners <span class=\\"e2\\">sarvadā</span>–perpetually."},{"class":"b50","text":" “The men and women of this world are always the wrong basis for that love. By attributing that love to bodies of flesh and blood, souls become perpetual sinners."},{"class":"b129","text":" অতএব তারা\\tসহজ-সাধনে<br />\\tকৃষ্ণকৃপা যবে পায় ।<br />জড়দেহগন্ধ\\tছাড়িয়া সে সব<br />\\tচিদানন্দরসে ধায় ॥২৯॥"},{"class":"b93","text":" ataeva tārā\\tsahaja sādhane<br />\\tkṛṣṇa-kṛpā yabe pāya<br />jaḍa-deha-gandha\\tchhāḍiyā se saba<br />\\tchid-ānanda-rase dhāya [29]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">ataeva</span>–So, <span class=\\"e2\\">yabe</span>–when <span class=\\"e2\\">tārā</span>–they <span class=\\"e2\\">pāya</span>–attain <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-kṛpā</span>–Kṛṣṇa’s mercy [through] <span class=\\"e2\\">sahaja</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sādhane</span>–natural practice, <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍiyā</span>–they avoid <span class=\\"e2\\">se</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">saba</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">jaḍa-deha-gandha</span>–even the scent of the material body [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">dhāya</span>–run <span class=\\"e2\\">chid-ānanda-rase</span>–towards joyful, spiritual rasa."},{"class":"b71","text":" “So, when souls attain Kṛṣṇa’s mercy through natural practice, they avoid even subtle connection with the material body and run towards joyful, spiritual rasa."},{"class":"b176","text":" রায় রামানন্দের প্রীতি"},{"class":"b177","text":" rāya rāmānandera prīti"},{"class":"b70","text":" Rāy Rāmānanda’s love"},{"class":"b129","text":" প্রকৃত সহজ\\tশ্রীকৃষ্ণভজন<br />\\tকরে রামানন্দ রায় ।<br />সুবৈধ সাধনে\\tএ জড দেহেতে<br />\\tসুযুক্ত বৈরাগ্য ভায় ॥৩০॥"},{"class":"b93","text":" prakṛta sahaja\\tśrī-kṛṣṇa-bhajana<br />\\tkare rāmānanda rāya<br />suvaidha sādhane\\te jaḍa dehete<br />\\tsuyukta vairāgya bhāya [30]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">rāmānanda</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">rāya</span>–Rāmānanda Rāy <span class=\\"e2\\">kare</span>–renders <span class=\\"e2\\">prakṛta</span>–genuine, <span class=\\"e2\\">sahaja</span>–natural <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-kṛṣṇa-bhajana</span>–service to Śrī Kṛṣṇa. [He is] <span class=\\"e2\\">suvaidha</span>–perfectly regulated <span class=\\"e2\\">sādhane</span>–in [his] practice, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">suyukta</span>–perfect <span class=\\"e2\\">vairāgya</span>–renunciation <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāya</span>–shines <span class=\\"e2\\">e</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">jaḍa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">dehete</span>–in his physical body."},{"class":"b50","text":" [Svarūp Dāmodar continued:] “Rāmānanda Rāy’s service to Kṛṣṇa is genuine and natural. He is perfectly regulated in his practice, and perfect renunciation shines in his physical body."},{"class":"b129","text":" বিশুদ্ধ দেহেতে\\tব্রজে কৃষ্ণ ভজে<br />\\tমহাপ্রভু-কৃপা পাঞা ।<br />নাটকাভিনয়ে\\tদেবদাসীশিক্ষা<br />\\tসঙ্গদোষশূন্য হঞা ॥৩১॥"},{"class":"b93","text":" viśuddha dehete\\tvraje kṛṣṇa bhaje<br />\\tmahāprabhu-kṛpā pāñā<br />nāṭakābhinaye\\tdeva-dāsī-śikṣā<br />\\tsaṅga-doṣa-śūnya hañā [31]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">pāñā</span>–Having received <span class=\\"e2\\">mahāprabhu-kṛpā</span>–Mahāprabhu’s mercy, <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaje</span>–he serves <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span>–Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">vraje</span>–in Vraja <span class=\\"e2\\">viśuddha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">dehete</span>–in [his] pure body. <span class=\\"e2\\">deva-dāsī-śikṣā</span>–He teaches maidservants of the Lord <span class=\\"e2\\">nāṭakābhinaye</span>–to perform plays, [but he] <span class=\\"e2\\">saṅga-doṣa-śūnya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">hañā</span>–is free from any inappropriate association [with them]."},{"class":"b71","text":" “Having received Mahāprabhu’s mercy, he serves Kṛṣṇa in Vraja in his pure body. He teaches maidservants of Jagannāth to perform plays, but he is free from any inappropriate association with them."},{"class":"b176","text":" প্রীতি-শিক্ষায় অধিকার কাহার ?"},{"class":"b177","text":" prīti-śikṣāya adhikāra kāhāra?"},{"class":"b70","text":" Who is qualified to learn about love?"},{"class":"b129","text":" রামানন্দ বিনা\\tতাহে অধিকার<br />\\tকেহ নাহি পায় আর ।<br />পরস্ত্রী-দর্শন\\tস্পর্শন, সেবন<br />\\tবুদ্ধি হৃদে আছে যার ।<br />পীরিতি শিক্ষায়\\tজানিবে নিশ্চয়<br />\\tনাহি তার অধিকার ॥৩২॥"},{"class":"b93","text":" rāmānanda vinā\\ttāhe adhikāra<br />\\tkeha nāhi pāya āra<br />para-strī-darśana\\tsparśana, sevana<br />\\tbuddhi hṛde āchhe yāra<br />pīriti śikṣāya\\tjānibe niśchaya<br />\\tnāhi tāra adhikāra [32]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">vinā</span>–Except for <span class=\\"e2\\">rāmānanda</span>–Rāmānanda, <span class=\\"e2\\">keha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāhi āra</span>–no one else <span class=\\"e2\\">pāya</span>–has <span class=\\"e2\\">adhikāra</span>–the qualification <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhe</span>–for this. <span class=\\"e2\\">jānibe</span>–Know <span class=\\"e2\\">niśchaya</span>–for certain [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra yāra āchhe</span>–anyone who has <span class=\\"e2\\">buddhi</span>–the inclination <span class=\\"e2\\">hṛde</span>–in their heart <span class=\\"e2\\">darśana</span>–to see, <span class=\\"e2\\">sparśana</span>–touch, [or] <span class=\\"e2\\">sevana</span>–serve <span class=\\"e2\\">para-strī</span>–another’s wife <span class=\\"e2\\">nāhi</span>–does not have <span class=\\"e2\\">adhikāra</span>–the qualification <span class=\\"e2\\">pīriti</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">śikṣāya</span>–to learn about love."},{"class":"b71","text":" “No one has this qualification except Rāmānanda. Know for certain that anyone who desires at heart to see, touch, or serve another’s wife is never qualified to learn about love."},{"class":"b176","text":" স্ত্রীপুরুষবুদ্ধি থাকিতে প্রীতিসাধন অসম্ভব"},{"class":"b177","text":" strī-puruṣa-buddhi thākite prīti-sādhana asambhava"},{"class":"b70","text":" Developing love is impossible in the presence of man-woman consciousness"},{"class":"b129","text":" কভু এ সংসারে\\tস্ত্রী-পুং-ব্যবহারে<br />\\tনা হয় পীরিতি-ধন ।<br />চর্ম্মসুখ যত\\tঅনিত্য নিয়ত<br />\\tনহে নিত্য সংঘটন ॥৩৩॥"},{"class":"b93","text":" kabhu e saṁsāre\\tstrī-puṁ-vyavahāre<br />\\tnā haya pīriti-dhana<br />charma-sukha yata\\tanitya niyata<br />\\tnahe nitya saṁghaṭana [33]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">pīriti-dhana</span>–The wealth of that love <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu nā</span>–never <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–exists <span class=\\"e2\\">strī-puṁ-vyavahāre</span>–in the affairs of men and women <span class=\\"e2\\">e</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">saṁsāre</span>–in this world. <span class=\\"e2\\">yata</span>–All <span class=\\"e2\\">charma-sukha</span>–carnal pleasures [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">niyata</span>–always <span class=\\"e2\\">anitya</span>–temporary. <span class=\\"e2\\">nahe</span>–They have no <span class=\\"e2\\">saṁghaṭana</span>–connection <span class=\\"e2\\">nitya</span>–with eternity."},{"class":"b50","text":" “The wealth of love never exists in the affairs of men and women in this world. Carnal pleasures are always temporary. They have no connection with eternity."},{"class":"b129","text":" গোপীভাব ধরি’\\tচিদ্ধর্ম্ম আচরি’<br />\\tপীরিতি সাধিবে যেই ।<br />স্ত্রী-পুং-ব্যবহার\\tনাহিক তাহার<br />\\tভিতরে গোপিনী সেই ॥৩৪॥"},{"class":"b93","text":" gopī-bhāva dhari’\\tchid-dharma āchari’<br />\\tpīriti sādhibe yei<br />strī-puṁ-vyavahāra\\tnāhika tāhāra<br />\\tbhitare gopinī sei [34]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sei yei</span>–Those who <span class=\\"e2\\">dhari’</span>–embrace <span class=\\"e2\\">gopī-bhāva</span>–the mood of the gopīs, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">sādhibe</span>–cultivate <span class=\\"e2\\">pīriti</span>–love <span class=\\"e2\\">āchari’</span>–by acting <span class=\\"e2\\">chid-dharma</span>–according [to their] spiritual nature <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhāra nāhika</span>–have no [involvement in] <span class=\\"e2\\">strī-puṁ-vyavahāra</span>–man-woman affairs; [they are] <span class=\\"e2\\">gopinī</span>–gopīs <span class=\\"e2\\">bhitare</span>–internally."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Those who embrace the mood of the gopīs and cultivate love by acting according to their spiritual nature are never involved in the affairs of men and women; they are gopīs internally."},{"class":"b129","text":" বাহিরে সজ্জন\\tধর্ম্ম-আচরণ<br />\\tআমরণ বৈধাচার ।<br />অন্তরেতে গোপী\\tচিত্তে কৃষ্ণ সেবে<br />\\tকেবল পীরিতি তার ॥৩৫॥"},{"class":"b93","text":" bāhire sajjana\\tdharma-ācharaṇa<br />\\tāmaraṇa vaidhāchāra<br />antarete gopī\\tchitte kṛṣṇa seve<br />\\tkevala pīriti tāra [35]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bāhire</span>–Externally, <span class=\\"e2\\">sajjana</span>–as sādhus, <span class=\\"e2\\">dharma-ācharaṇa</span>–they behave virtuously [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">vaidhāchāra</span>–adhere to regulations <span class=\\"e2\\">āmaraṇa</span>–until death. <span class=\\"e2\\">antarete</span>–Internally, <span class=\\"e2\\">gopī</span>–as gopīs, <span class=\\"e2\\">seve</span>–they serve <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span>–Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">chitte</span>–within the heart: [their] <span class=\\"e2\\">pīriti</span>–love [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">kevala</span>–only <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra</span>–for Him."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Externally, as sādhus, they behave virtuously and adhere to regulations until death. Internally, as gopīs, they serve Kṛṣṇa within the heart: their love is only for Him."},{"class":"b129","text":" ‘যঃ কৌমারহরঃ’\\tইত্যাদি কবিতা<br />\\tকেবল উপমাস্থল ।<br />নায়ক-নায়িকা\\tচিৎস্বরূপ হঞা<br />\\tকৃষ্ণ ভজে সুনির্ম্মল ॥৩৬॥"},{"class":"b93","text":" ‘yaḥ kaumāra-haraḥ’\\tityādi kavitā<br />\\tkevala upamā-sthala<br />nāyaka-nāyikā\\tchit-svarūpa hañā<br />\\tkṛṣṇa bhaje sunirmala [36]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kavitā</span>–Verses <span class=\\"e2\\">ityādi</span>–such as <span class=\\"e2\\">‘yaḥ</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kaumāra-haraḥ’</span>–‘He who has stolen my youth’ [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">kevala</span>–simply <span class=\\"e2\\">upamā-sthala</span>–analogies. [Understanding that] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāyaka-nāyikā</span>–the lover and the beloved <span class=\\"e2\\">hañā</span>–are <span class=\\"e2\\">chit-svarūpa</span>–spiritual, <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaje</span>–souls serve <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span>–Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">sunirmala</span>–purely."},{"class":"b71","text":" “Verses such as <span class=\\"e3\\">Yaḥ Kaumāra-haraḥ</span>* are simply analogies. Under­standing that the lover and the beloved in these verses are spiritual, souls should serve Kṛṣṇa purely."},{"class":"b176","text":" জডেতে এই ভাব আরোপ, নরক—কলির ছলনা"},{"class":"b177","text":" jaḍete ei bhāva āropa, naraka—kalira chhalanā"},{"class":"b70","text":" Attributing this love to the mundane is hellish; it is a deception produced by Kali"},{"class":"b97","text":" কেহ যদি বলে ইহা আরোপ চিন্তায় ।<br />পরপুরুষেতে কৃষ্ণভজন উপায় ॥৩৭॥<br />চৈতন্য আজ্ঞায় আমি একথা না মানি ।<br />জড়েতে এরূপ বুদ্ধি নরক বলি’ মানি ॥৩৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" keha yadi bale ihā āropa chintāya<br />para-puruṣete kṛṣṇa-bhajana upāya [37]<br />chaitanya ājñāya āmi e-kathā nā māni<br />jaḍete e-rūpa buddhi naraka bali’ māni [38]"},{"class":"b84","text":" *yaḥ kaumāra-haraḥ sa eva hi varas tā eva chaitra-kṣapās<br />te chonmīlita-mālatī-surabhayaḥ prauḍhāḥ kadambānilāḥ<br />sā chaivāsmi tathāpi tatra surata-vyāpāra-līlā-vidhau<br />revā-rodhasi vetasī-taru-tale chetaḥ samutkaṇṭhat"},{"class":"b85","text":" (Śrī Chaitanya-charitāmṛta: Madhya-līlā, 1.58)"},{"class":"b96","text":" “He is the paramour who has stolen my youth, these are the same moonlit spring nights filled with the fragrance of blooming jasmine and sweet breezes blowing from the kadamba forest, and I am the same lover. Still, my heart is yearning for our trysts on the bank of the Revā beneath that vetasī tree.”"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">yadi</span>–If <span class=\\"e2\\">keha</span>–someone <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–says [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">āropa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">chintāya</span>–attributing <span class=\\"e2\\">ihā</span>–that love <span class=\\"e2\\">para-puruṣete</span>–to another person [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">upāya</span>–a way <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-bhajana</span>–to serve Kṛṣṇa, [then,] <span class=\\"e2\\">chaitanya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ājñāya</span>–on Śrī Chaitanya’s order, <span class=\\"e2\\">āmi</span>–I <span class=\\"e2\\">māni nā</span>–do not accept <span class=\\"e2\\">e-kathā</span>–their statement. <span class=\\"e2\\">māni</span>–I consider <span class=\\"e2\\">e-rūpa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">buddhi</span>–such a conception <span class=\\"e2\\">jaḍete</span>–of the mundane <span class=\\"e2\\">bali’</span>–to be <span class=\\"e2\\">naraka</span>–hellish."},{"class":"b50","text":" [Svarūp Dāmodar continued:] “If someone says that ascribing love to another man is a way to serve Kṛṣṇa, then, on Śrī Chaitanya’s order, I do not accept their statement. I consider such a mundane conception to be hellish."},{"class":"b97","text":" জড়দেহে চিদারোপ, সঙ্গ তুচ্ছ অতি ।<br />তাহে কৃষ্ণভাব আনা, সমূহ দুর্ম্মতি ॥৩৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" jaḍa-dehe chid-āropa, saṅga tuchchha ati<br />tāhe kṛṣṇa-bhāva ānā, samūha durmati [39]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">chid-āropa</span>–Attributing spirit <span class=\\"e2\\">jaḍa-dehe</span>–to the material body [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">ati tuchchha</span>–a very crude <span class=\\"e2\\">saṅga</span>–attachment, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">ānā</span>–bringing <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-bhāva</span>–love for Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhe</span>–into it [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">samūha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">durmati</span>–completely wicked."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Attributing spirit to the material body is a very crude attachment, and associating love for Kṛṣṇa with the material body is completely wicked."},{"class":"b97","text":" কলির ছলনা এই জানিহ নিশ্চয় ।<br />ইহাতে বৈষ্ণব-ধর্ম্ম অধঃপথে যায় ॥৪০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kalira chhalanā ei jāniha niśchaya<br />ihāte vaiṣṇava-dharma adhaḥ-pathe yāya [40]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">jāniha</span>–Know <span class=\\"e2\\">niśchaya</span>–for certain [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span>–this [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">chhalanā</span>–a deception <span class=\\"e2\\">kalira</span>–produced by Kali, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">vaiṣṇava-dharma</span>–the Vaiṣṇava religion <span class=\\"e2\\">adhaḥ-pathe</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">yāya</span>–becomes degraded <span class=\\"e2\\">ihāte</span>–because of it."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Know for certain that such thinking is a deception produced by Kali, and the Vaiṣṇava dharma becomes degraded because of it."},{"class":"b97","text":" সুকৃতি পুরুষ মাত্র উপমা বুঝিয়া ।<br />স্বীয় অপ্রাকৃতদেহে কৃষ্ণ ভজে গিয়া ॥৪১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sukṛti puruṣa mātra upamā bujhiyā<br />svīya aprākṛta-dehe kṛṣṇa bhaje giyā [41]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">mātra</span>–Only <span class=\\"e2\\">sukṛti</span>–fortunate <span class=\\"e2\\">puruṣa</span>–souls <span class=\\"e2\\">bujhiyā</span>–understand <span class=\\"e2\\">upamā</span>–the analogies [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">giyā bhaje</span>–serve <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span>–Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">svīya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">aprākṛta-dehe</span>–in their divine bodies."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Only fortunate souls understand the analogies in the scriptures and serve Kṛṣṇa in their divine bodies."},{"class":"b97","text":" চণ্ডীদাস বিদ্যাপতি আদি মহাজন ।<br />পূর্ব্ববুদ্ধি দূরে রাখি’ করিল ভজন ॥৪২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" chaṇḍī-dāsa vidyāpati ādi mahājana<br />pūrva-buddhi dūre rākhi’ karila bhajana [42]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">chaṇḍī-dāsa</span>–Chaṇḍī Dās, <span class=\\"e2\\">vidyāpati</span>–Vidyāpati, <span class=\\"e2\\">ādi</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">mahājana</span>–and other great souls <span class=\\"e2\\">dūre</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">rākhi’</span>–left behind [their] <span class=\\"e2\\">pūrva-buddhi</span>–previous conceptions [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhajana karila</span>–practised devotion."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Chaṇḍī Dās, Vidyāpati, and the other great souls left their previous conceptions behind and practised devotion."},{"class":"b97","text":" সে সবার শেষ বাক্য চিন্ময়ী পীরিতি ।<br />আছে তবু নাহি বুঝে দুষ্কৃতির রীতি ॥৪৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" se sabāra śeṣa vākya chinmayī pīriti<br />āchhe tabu nāhi bujhe duṣkṛtira rīti [43]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">śeṣa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">vākya</span>–The final statement <span class=\\"e2\\">se</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sabāra</span>–of them all [is that] <span class=\\"e2\\">chinmayī</span>–spiritual <span class=\\"e2\\">pīriti</span>–love <span class=\\"e2\\">āchhe</span>–exists, <span class=\\"e2\\">tabu</span>–but [those whose] <span class=\\"e2\\">duṣkṛtira</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">rīti</span>–habits are sinful <span class=\\"e2\\">bujhe nāhi</span>–do not understand [it]."},{"class":"b50","text":" “The final statement of all these great souls is that spiritual love does exist, but sinners never understand it."},{"class":"b97","text":" রঘুনাথ এ বিষয়ে করহ বিচার ।<br />তোমা হেন ভক্ত প্রচারিবে সদাচার ॥৪৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" raghunātha e viṣaye karaha vichāra<br />tomā hena bhakta prachāribe sad-āchāra [44]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">raghunātha</span>–O Raghunāth, <span class=\\"e2\\">vichāra karaha</span>–consider <span class=\\"e2\\">e</span>–this <span class=\\"e2\\">viṣaye</span>–matter. <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakta</span>–Devotees <span class=\\"e2\\">tomā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">hena</span>–such as yourself <span class=\\"e2\\">prachāribe</span>–should preach [about] <span class=\\"e2\\">sad-āchāra</span>–proper practice."},{"class":"b50","text":" “O Raghunāth, consider this matter. Devotees such as yourself should preach the proper way to practise."},{"class":"b97","text":" এ বিষয় একবার প্রভুকে জানাঞা ।<br />চিত্ত দৃঢ করি’ লও, দৃঢ় কর হিয়া” ॥৪৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" e viṣaya eka-bāra prabhuke jānāñā<br />chitta dṛḍha kari’ lao, dṛḍha kara hiyā” [45]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">eka-bāra</span>–Once <span class=\\"e2\\">jānāñā</span>–ask <span class=\\"e2\\">prabhuke</span>–the Lord <span class=\\"e2\\">e</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">viṣaya</span>–about this matter. <span class=\\"e2\\">kari’</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">lao</span>–Make [your] <span class=\\"e2\\">chitta</span>–mind <span class=\\"e2\\">dṛḍha</span>–resolute, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">kara</span>–make [your] <span class=\\"e2\\">hiyā</span>–heart <span class=\\"e2\\">dṛḍha”</span>–resolute.”"},{"class":"b50","text":" [Svarūp Dāmodar concluded:] “You should once ask the Lord about this matter, and make your mind and heart resolute.”"},{"class":"b97","text":" তবে রঘুনাথ শ্রীমৎ প্রভুপদে গিয়া ।<br />ঠারে ঠোরে জিজ্ঞাসিল বিনীত হইয়া ॥৪৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" tabe raghunātha śrīmat prabhu-pade giyā<br />ṭhāre ṭhore jijñāsila vinīta ha-iyā [46]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">raghunātha</span>–Raghunāth <span class=\\"e2\\">tabe</span>–then <span class=\\"e2\\">giyā</span>–went <span class=\\"e2\\">śrīmat</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">prabhu-pade</span>–to the holy feet of the Lord [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">vinīta</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-iyā</span>–humbly <span class=\\"e2\\">jijñāsila</span>–asked [Him about the matter] <span class=\\"e2\\">ṭhāre</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ṭhore</span>–indirectly."},{"class":"b50","text":" Raghunāth then went to the holy feet of the Lord and humbly asked Him about the matter indirectly."},{"class":"b97","text":" প্রভু তারে আজ্ঞা দিল আমার সম্মুখে ।<br />রঘুনাথ আজ্ঞা পেয়ে ভজে মনসুখে ॥৪৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" prabhu tāre ājñā dila āmāra sammukhe<br />raghunātha ājñā peye bhaje mana-sukhe [47]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">prabhu</span>–The Lord <span class=\\"e2\\">ājñā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">dila</span>–instructed <span class=\\"e2\\">tāre</span>–him <span class=\\"e2\\">āmāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sammukhe</span>–in front of me. <span class=\\"e2\\">raghunātha</span>–Raghunāth <span class=\\"e2\\">peye</span>–received [the Lord’s] <span class=\\"e2\\">ājñā</span>–instructions [and then] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaje</span>–served <span class=\\"e2\\">mana-sukhe</span>–with joy in [his] heart."},{"class":"b71","text":" The Lord instructed Raghunāth in front of me. He received the Lord’s instructions and then engaged in service with joy in his heart."},{"class":"b176","text":" শ্রীরঘুনাথ-প্রতি শ্রীমন্মহাপ্রভুর আজ্ঞা"},{"class":"b177","text":" śrī-raghunātha-prati śrīman mahāprabhura ājñā"},{"class":"b70","text":" Śrīman Mahāprabhu’s instructions to Śrī Raghunāth"},{"class":"b97","text":" “গ্রাম্য কথা না শুনিবে, গ্রাম্য বার্তা না কহিবে ।<br />ভাল না খাইবে, আর ভাল না পরিবে ॥৪৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" “grāmya kathā nā śunibe, grāmya vārtā nā kahibe<br />bhāla nā khāibe, āra bhāla nā paribe [48]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">“śunibe nā</span>–“Do not listen <span class=\\"e2\\">grāmya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kathā</span>–to village talk, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">kahibe nā</span>–do not discuss <span class=\\"e2\\">grāmya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">vārtā</span>–village matters. <span class=\\"e2\\">khāibe nā</span>–Do not eat <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāla</span>–fancy [food] <span class=\\"e2\\">āra</span>–and <span class=\\"e2\\">paribe nā</span>–do not wear <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāla</span>–fancy [clothes]."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Do not listen to village talk or discuss village matters. Do not eat fancy food or wear fancy clothes."},{"class":"b97","text":" অমানী, মানদ হঞা কৃষ্ণনাম সদা লবে ।<br />ব্রজে রাধাকৃষ্ণ-সেবা মানসে করিবে” ॥৪৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" amānī, mānada hañā kṛṣṇa-nāma sadā labe<br />vraje rādhā-kṛṣṇa-sevā mānase karibe” [49]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">hañā</span>–Be <span class=\\"e2\\">amānī</span>–prideless [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">mānada</span>–respectful, <span class=\\"e2\\">sadā</span>–always <span class=\\"e2\\">labe</span>–chant <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-nāma</span>–Kṛṣṇa’s Name, [and,] <span class=\\"e2\\">mānase</span>–within [your] heart, <span class=\\"e2\\">rādhā-kṛṣṇa-sevā karibe</span>–serve Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">vraje”</span>–in Vraja.”"},{"class":"b50","text":" “Be prideless and respectful, always chant Kṛṣṇa’s Name, and, within your heart, serve Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa in Vraja.”"},{"class":"b97","text":" এই আজ্ঞা পাঞা রঘু বুঝিল তখন ।<br />পীরিতি না হয় কভু জড়েতে সাধন ॥৫০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ei ājñā pāñā raghu bujhila takhana<br />pīriti nā haya kabhu jaḍete sādhana [50]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">pāñā</span>–Upon receiving <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span>–these <span class=\\"e2\\">ājñā</span>–instructions, <span class=\\"e2\\">raghu</span>–Raghunāth <span class=\\"e2\\">takhana</span>–then <span class=\\"e2\\">bujhila</span>–understood [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">pīriti</span>–divine love <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu nā</span>–never <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–develops <span class=\\"e2\\">sādhana</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">jaḍete</span>–through material practices."},{"class":"b50","text":" When Raghunāth received these instructions, he then understood that divine love never develops through material practices."},{"class":"b97","text":" মানসেতে সিদ্ধদেহ করিয়া ভাবন ।<br />সেই দেহে রাধানাথের করিবে সেবন ॥৫১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" mānasete siddha-deha kariyā bhāvana<br />sei dehe rādhānāthera karibe sevana [51]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">mānasete</span>–Within your heart, <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāvana kariyā</span>–meditate <span class=\\"e2\\">siddha-deha</span>–with [your] spiritual body [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">sei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">dehe</span>–in that body, <span class=\\"e2\\">sevana karibe</span>–serve <span class=\\"e2\\">rādhānāthera</span>–the Lord of Rādhā."},{"class":"b50","text":" Within your heart, meditate with your spiritual body, and in that body, serve the Lord of Rādhā."},{"class":"b97","text":" অমানী মানদ ভাবে অকিঞ্চন হঞা ।<br />বৃক্ষ হেন সহিষ্ণুতা আপনে করিয়া ॥৫২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" amānī mānada bhāve akiñchana hañā<br />vṛkṣa hena sahiṣṇutā āpane kariyā [52]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">amānī</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">mānada</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāve</span>–In a prideless and respectful manner, <span class=\\"e2\\">akiñchana hañā</span>–be humble [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">āpane</span>–personally <span class=\\"e2\\">kariyā</span>–be <span class=\\"e2\\">sahiṣṇutā</span>–tolerant <span class=\\"e2\\">hena</span>–like <span class=\\"e2\\">vṛkṣa</span>–a tree."},{"class":"b50","text":" Be prideless, respectful, humble, and tolerant like a tree."},{"class":"b97","text":" বাহ্যদেহে কৃষ্ণনাম সর্ব্বকাল গায় ।<br />অন্তর্দেহে থাকে রাধাকৃষ্ণের সেবায় ॥৫৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" bāhya-dehe kṛṣṇa-nāma sarva-kāla gāya<br />antar-dehe thāke rādhā-kṛṣṇera sevāya [53]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bāhya-dehe</span>–In [your] external body, <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-kāla</span>–always <span class=\\"e2\\">gāya</span>–chant <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-nāma</span>–the Name of Kṛṣṇa, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">antar-dehe</span>–in your internal body, <span class=\\"e2\\">sevāya thāke</span>–engage in service <span class=\\"e2\\">rādhā-kṛṣṇera</span>–to Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa."},{"class":"b50","text":" In your external body, always chant the Name of Kṛṣṇa, and in your internal body, serve Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa."},{"class":"b97","text":" ভাল খাওয়া, ভাল পরা পরিত্যাগ করি’ ।<br />প্রাণবৃত্তি দ্বারা জড়দেহযাত্রা ধরি’ ॥৫৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" bhāla khāoyā, bhāla parā parityāga kari’<br />prāṇa-vṛtti dvārā jaḍa-deha-yātrā dhari’ [54]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">parityāga</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kari’</span>–Give up <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāla</span>–fancy <span class=\\"e2\\">khāoyā</span>–eating [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāla</span>–fancy <span class=\\"e2\\">parā</span>–dressing, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">jaḍa-deha-yātrā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">dhari’</span>–maintain [your] material body <span class=\\"e2\\">dvārā</span>–with <span class=\\"e2\\">prāṇa-vṛtti</span>–the necessities for life."},{"class":"b71","text":" Give up fancy food and fancy clothes, and maintain your material body with the necessities for life."},{"class":"b176","text":" মর্কট-বৈরাগ্য"},{"class":"b177","text":" markaṭa-vairāgī"},{"class":"b70","text":" The monkey renunciant"},{"class":"b97","text":" এই জড়দেহে রাধাকৃষ্ণ বুদ্ধ্যারোপ ।<br />মর্কট বৈরাগী করে সর্ব্বধর্ম্ম লোপ ॥৫৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ei jaḍa-dehe rādhā-kṛṣṇa buddhyāropa<br />markaṭa vairāgī kare sarva-dharma lopa [55]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">markaṭa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">vairāgī</span>–The monkey renunciant <span class=\\"e2\\">buddhyāropa</span>–attributes a conception <span class=\\"e2\\">rādhā-kṛṣṇa</span>–of Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">jaḍa-dehe</span>–to the material body [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">lopa kare</span>–disregards <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-dharma</span>–all principles."},{"class":"b50","text":" The monkey renunciant attributes a conception of Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa to the material body and disregards all principles."},{"class":"b97","text":" প্রভু বলিয়াছেন, “মর্কট বৈরাগী সে জন ।<br />বৈরাগীর প্রায় থাকি’ করে প্রকৃতি-সম্ভাষণ” ॥৫৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" prabhu baliyāchhena, “markaṭa vairāgī se jana<br />vairāgīra prāya thāki’ kare prakṛti-sambhāṣaṇa” [56]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">prabhu</span>–The Lord <span class=\\"e2\\">baliyāchhena</span>–has said, <span class=\\"e2\\">“se</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">jana</span>–Those who <span class=\\"e2\\">thāki’</span>–act <span class=\\"e2\\">vairāgīra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">prāya</span>–like renunciants [but] <span class=\\"e2\\">prakṛti-sambhāṣaṇa kare</span>–converse with women [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">markaṭa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">vairāgī”</span>–monkey renunciants.”"},{"class":"b71","text":" The Lord has said, “Those who act like renunciants but converse with women are monkey renunciants.”"},{"class":"b176","text":" বিশুদ্ধ বৈরাগী"},{"class":"b177","text":" viśuddha vairāgī"},{"class":"b70","text":" The pure renunciant"},{"class":"b97","text":" বিশুদ্ধ বৈরাগী করে নাম সঙ্কীর্ত্তন ।<br />মাগিয়া খাইয়া করে জীবন-যাপন ॥৫৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" viśuddha vairāgī kare nāma saṅkīrtana<br />māgiyā khāiyā kare jīvana-yāpana [57]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">viśuddha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">vairāgī</span>–Pure renunciants <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">saṅkīrtana kare</span>–chant the Name [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">jīvana-yāpana kare</span>–maintain [their] life <span class=\\"e2\\">māgiyā</span>–by begging [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">khāiyā</span>–eating."},{"class":"b50","text":" Pure renunciants chant the Name and live by begging and eating."},{"class":"b97","text":" বৈরাগী হইয়া যেবা করে পরাপেক্ষা ।<br />কার্যসিদ্ধি নহে, কৃষ্ণ করে উপেক্ষা ॥৫৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" vairāgī ha-iyā yebā kare parāpekṣā<br />kārya-siddhi nahe, kṛṣṇa kare upekṣā [58]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">yebā</span>–Those who <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-iyā</span>–become <span class=\\"e2\\">vairāgī</span>–renunciants [but] <span class=\\"e2\\">parāpekṣā kare</span>–depend on others <span class=\\"e2\\">nahe</span>–do not become <span class=\\"e2\\">kārya-siddhi</span>–successful, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span>–Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">upekṣā kare</span>–ignores [them]."},{"class":"b50","text":" Those who become renunciants but depend on others do not become successful, and Kṛṣṇa ignores them."},{"class":"b97","text":" বৈরাগী হইয়া করে জিহ্বার লালস ।<br />পরমার্থ যায়, আর হয় রসের বশ ॥৫৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" vairāgī ha-iyā kare jihvāra lālasa<br />paramārtha yāya, āra haya rasera vaśa [59]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-iyā</span>–Those who become <span class=\\"e2\\">vairāgī</span>–renunciants [but] <span class=\\"e2\\">jihvāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">lālasa kare</span>–follow the cravings of the tongue <span class=\\"e2\\">paramārtha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">yāya</span>–go away from spiritual life <span class=\\"e2\\">āra</span>–and <span class=\\"e2\\">rasera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">vaśa haya</span>–become controlled by tastes."},{"class":"b50","text":" Those who become renunciants but indulge the cravings of the tongue stray from spiritual life and become controlled by material tastes."},{"class":"b97","text":" বৈরাগী করিবে সদা নাম-সঙ্কীর্ত্তন ।<br />শাক-পত্র-ফল-মূলে উদর ভরণ ॥৬০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" vairāgī karibe sadā nāma-saṅkīrtana<br />śāka-patra-phala-mūle udara bharaṇa [60]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">vairāgī</span>–A renunciant <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-saṅkīrtana karibe</span>–should chant the Name <span class=\\"e2\\">sadā</span>–always [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">bharaṇa</span>–fill [their] <span class=\\"e2\\">udara</span>–belly <span class=\\"e2\\">śāka-patra-phala-mūle</span>–with leaves, vegetables, fruits, and roots."},{"class":"b50","text":" A renunciant should always chant the Name and fill their belly with leaves, vegetables, fruits, and roots."},{"class":"b97","text":" জিহ্বার লালসে যেই সমাজে বেড়ায় ।<br />শিশ্নোদরপরায়ণ কৃষ্ণ নাহি পায় ॥৬১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" jihvāra lālase yei samāje beḍāya<br />śiśnodara-parāyaṇa kṛṣṇa nāhi pāya [61]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">yei</span>–Those who <span class=\\"e2\\">beḍāya</span>–go out <span class=\\"e2\\">samāje</span>–amidst society [under the control of] <span class=\\"e2\\">jihvāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">lālase</span>–the cravings of their tongue [become] <span class=\\"e2\\">śiśnodara-parāyaṇa</span>–engrossed in the genitals and stomach, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">pāya nāhi</span>–do not attain <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span>–Kṛṣṇa."},{"class":"b55","text":" Those who go out amidst society to indulge the cravings of their tongue become engrossed in their genitals and stomach, and do not attain Kṛṣṇa."}]},{"title":"Different Practices for Different Devotees","paragraphs":[{"class":"b46","text":"\\r"},{"class":"b58","text":" Chapter Seventeen"},{"class":"b120","text":" ভক্তভেদে আচারভেদ"},{"class":"b121","text":" Bhakta-bhede Āchāra-bheda"},{"class":"b175","text":" Different Practices <br />for Different Devotees"},{"class":"b97","text":" আর দিনে শ্রীস্বরূপ রঘুনাথে কয় ।<br />“তোমারে নিগূঢ় কিছু কহিব নিশ্চয়” ॥১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" āra dine śrī-svarūpa raghunāthe kaya<br />“tomāre nigūḍha kichhu kahiba niśchaya” [1]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">āra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">dine</span>–Another day, <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-svarūpa</span>–Śrī Svarūp <span class=\\"e2\\">kaya</span>–said, <span class=\\"e2\\">raghunāthe</span>–to Raghunāth, <span class=\\"e2\\">“kahiba niśchaya</span>–“I will explain <span class=\\"e2\\">kichhu</span>–something <span class=\\"e2\\">nigūḍha</span>–confidential <span class=\\"e2\\">tomāre</span>–to you."},{"class":"b71","text":" Another day, Svarūp said to Raghunāth, “I will explain something confidential to you."},{"class":"b176","text":" ভজনবিহীন-ধর্ম্ম কেবল কৈতব"},{"class":"b177","text":" bhajana-vihīna-dharma kevala kaitava"},{"class":"b70","text":" Dharma without devotion is simply deception"},{"class":"b97","text":" যে বর্ণেতে জন্ম যার যে আশ্রমে স্থিতি ।<br />তত্তদ্ধর্ম্মে দেহযাত্রা এই শুদ্ধ নীতি ॥২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ye varṇete janma yāra ye āśrame sthiti<br />tat-tad-dharme deha-yātrā ei śuddha nīti [2]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">deha-yātrā</span>–Maintaining the body <span class=\\"e2\\">tat-tad-dharme</span>–according to the duties <span class=\\"e2\\">ye</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">varṇete</span>–of the class <span class=\\"e2\\">yāra janma</span>–of one’s birth [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">ye</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">āśrame</span>–the order [in which one is] <span class=\\"e2\\">sthiti</span>–situated [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">śuddha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nīti</span>–the proper conduct."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Maintaining the body according to the duties of the class in which one is born and the order in which one is situated is the proper conduct."},{"class":"b97","text":" এইমতে দেহযাত্রা নির্বাহ করিয়া ।<br />নিরন্তর কৃষ্ণ ভজে একান্ত হইয়া ॥৩॥<br />সেই সে সুবোধ, সুধার্ম্মিক, সুবৈষ্ণব ।<br />ভজনবিহীন-ধর্ম্ম কেবল কৈতব ॥৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ei-mate deha-yātrā nirvāha kariyā<br />nirantara kṛṣṇa bhaje ekānta ha-iyā [3]<br />sei se subodha, sudhārmika, suvaiṣṇava<br />bhajana-vihīna-dharma kevala kaitava [4]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">se</span>–Those who <span class=\\"e2\\">deha-yātrā nirvāha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kariyā</span>–maintain the body <span class=\\"e2\\">ei-mate</span>–in this way [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">nirantara</span>–always <span class=\\"e2\\">ekānta</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-iyā</span>–sincerely <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaje</span>–serve <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span>–Kṛṣṇa [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">subodha</span>–truly wise [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">sudhārmika</span>–truly religious; [they are] <span class=\\"e2\\">suvaiṣṇava</span>–true devotees. <span class=\\"e2\\">bhajana-vihīna-dharma</span>–Religion (varṇāśram-dharma) without devotion, [however, is] <span class=\\"e2\\">kevala</span>–simply <span class=\\"e2\\">kaitava</span>–deception."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Those who maintain the body in this way and always sincerely serve Kṛṣṇa, are truly wise, religious, and devoted. Dharma without devotion, however, is simply deception."},{"class":"b97","text":" কৃষ্ণ নাহি ভজে, করে ধর্ম্ম-আচরণ ।<br />অধঃপথে যায় তার মানব-জীবন ॥৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kṛṣṇa nāhi bhaje, kare dharma-ācharaṇa<br />adhaḥ-pathe yāya tāra mānava-jīvana [5]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">mānava-jīvana</span>–The human life <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra</span>–of those who <span class=\\"e2\\">dharma-ācharaṇa kare</span>–practise dharma [but] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaje nāhi</span>–do not serve <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span>–Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">adhaḥ-pathe</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">yāya</span>–is ruined."},{"class":"b50","text":" “The human life of those who practise dharma but do not serve Kṛṣṇa is ruined."},{"class":"b97","text":" গৃহী, ব্রহ্মচারী, বানপ্রস্থ বা সন্ন্যাসী ।<br />কৃষ্ণভক্তিশূন্য অসম্ভাষ্য দিবানিশি ॥৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" gṛhī, brahmachārī, vānaprastha vā sannyāsī<br />kṛṣṇa-bhakti-śūnya asambhāṣya divā-niśi [6]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">gṛhī</span>–Householders, <span class=\\"e2\\">brahmachārī</span>–students, <span class=\\"e2\\">vānaprastha</span>–retired householders, <span class=\\"e2\\">vā</span>–or <span class=\\"e2\\">sannyāsī</span>–renunciants [who are] <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-bhakti-śūnya</span>–devoid of devotion to Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">asambhāṣya</span>–should not be mixed with, <span class=\\"e2\\">divā-niśi</span>–day [or] night."},{"class":"b71","text":" “Do not mix, day or night, with householders, students, retired householders, or renunciants who are devoid of devotion to Kṛṣṇa."},{"class":"b176","text":" সম্বন্ধজ্ঞানলাভ ও যুক্ত-বৈরাগ্য-আশ্রয়"},{"class":"b177","text":" sambandha-jñāna-lābha o yukta-vairāgya-āśraya"},{"class":"b70","text":" Acquiring knowledge of the soul’s relationship with the Lord and practising proper renunciation"},{"class":"b97","text":" সকলেই করিবেন যুক্ত-বৈরাগ্য-আশ্রয় ।<br />কৃষ্ণ ভজিবেন বুঝি’ সম্বন্ধ নিশ্চয় ॥৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sakalei karibena yukta-vairāgya-āśraya<br />kṛṣṇa bhajibena bujhi’ sambandha niśchaya [7]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sakalei</span>–Everyone <span class=\\"e2\\">yukta-vairāgya-āśraya karibena</span>–should practise proper renunciation [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhajibena</span>–serve <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span>–Kṛṣṇa, <span class=\\"e2\\">bujhi’</span>–understanding <span class=\\"e2\\">niśchaya</span>–clearly [their] <span class=\\"e2\\">sambandha</span>–relationship with [Him]."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Everyone should practise proper renunciation and serve Kṛṣṇa with a clear understanding of their relationship with Him."},{"class":"b97","text":" সম্বন্ধনির্ণয়ে হয় আলম্বন বোধ ।<br />শুদ্ধ-আলম্বন হৈলে হয় প্রেমের প্রবোধ ॥৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sambandha-nirṇaye haya ālambana bodha<br />śuddha-ālambana haile haya premera prabodha [8]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sambandha-nirṇaye</span>–By understanding that relationship, [its] <span class=\\"e2\\">ālambana</span>–object (the Lord) <span class=\\"e2\\">bodha haya</span>–is realised, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">śuddha-ālambana</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haile</span>–when this proper object is realised, <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–there is <span class=\\"e2\\">prabodha</span>–an awakening <span class=\\"e2\\">premera</span>–of divine love."},{"class":"b50","text":" “By understanding that relationship, its object (the Lord) is realised, and when this proper object is realised, divine love awakens."},{"class":"b97","text":" প্রেমে কৃষ্ণ ভজে সেই বাপের ঠাকুর ।<br />প্রেমশূন্য জীব কেবল ছাঁচের কুকুর ॥৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" preme kṛṣṇa bhaje sei bāpera ṭhākura<br />prema-śūnya jīva kevala chhā̐chera kukura [9]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sei bhaje</span>–Souls who serve <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span>–Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">preme</span>–with love [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">bāpera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ṭhākura</span>–worshippable to their own fathers, [but] <span class=\\"e2\\">jīva</span>–souls <span class=\\"e2\\">prema-śūnya</span>–devoid of divine love [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">kevala</span>–merely <span class=\\"e2\\">chhā̐chera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kukura</span>–toy dogs."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Souls who serve Kṛṣṇa with love are worshippable, even to their own fathers, but souls devoid of divine love are no better than toy dogs."},{"class":"b97","text":" কৃষ্ণভক্তি আছে যার বৈষ্ণব সে জন ।<br />গৃহ ছাড়ি’ ভিক্ষা করে, না করে ভজন ।<br />বৈষ্ণব বলিয়া তারে না কর গণন ॥১০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kṛṣṇa-bhakti āchhe yāra vaiṣṇava se jana<br />gṛha chhāḍi’ bhikṣā kare, nā kare bhajana<br />vaiṣṇava baliyā tāre nā kara gaṇana [10]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">se</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">jana yāra āchhe</span>–Those who have <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-bhakti</span>–devotion to Kṛṣṇa [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">vaiṣṇava</span>–devotees. <span class=\\"e2\\">gaṇana kara nā</span>–Do not consider <span class=\\"e2\\">tāre</span>–someone who <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍi’</span>–gives up [their] <span class=\\"e2\\">gṛha</span>–home [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhikṣā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kare</span>–begs [but] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhajana kare nā</span>–does not serve, <span class=\\"e2\\">baliyā</span>–to be <span class=\\"e2\\">vaiṣṇava</span>–a devotee."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Those who have devotion to Kṛṣṇa are Vaiṣṇavas. Do not consider someone who gives up their home and begs but does not serve Kṛṣṇa to be a Vaiṣṇava."},{"class":"b97","text":" অন্য দেব-নির্ম্মাল্যাদি না কর গ্রহণ ।<br />কর্ম্মকাণ্ডে কভু না মানিবে নিমন্ত্রণ ॥১১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" anya deva-nirmālyādi nā kara grahaṇa<br />karma-kāṇḍe kabhu nā mānibe nimantraṇa [11]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">grahaṇa kara nā</span>–Do not accept <span class=\\"e2\\">anya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">deva-nirmālyādi</span>–the remnants of other gods, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nā</span>–never <span class=\\"e2\\">mānibe</span>–accept <span class=\\"e2\\">nimantraṇa</span>–invitations <span class=\\"e2\\">karma-kāṇḍe</span>–to sacrifices performed for worldly gain."},{"class":"b71","text":" “Do not accept the remnants of other gods, and never accept invitations to sacrifices performed for worldly gain."},{"class":"b176","text":" গৃহী ও গৃহত্যাগী-বৈষ্ণবের আচার"},{"class":"b177","text":" gṛhī o gṛha-tyāgī-vaiṣṇavera āchāra"},{"class":"b70","text":" The practices of householder Vaiṣṇavas and Vaiṣṇavas who have renounced household life"},{"class":"b97","text":" গৃহী গৃহত্যাগী ভেদে বৈষ্ণব-বিচার ।<br />দুঁহে ভক্তি-অধিকারী পৃথক্ আচার ॥১২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" gṛhī gṛha-tyāgī bhede vaiṣṇava-vichāra<br />du̐he bhakti-adhikārī pṛthak āchāra [12]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [There are] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhede vaiṣṇava-vichāra</span>–different types of devotees: <span class=\\"e2\\">gṛhī</span>–householders [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">gṛha-tyāgī</span>–those who have renounced household life. <span class=\\"e2\\">du̐he</span>–Both [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakti-adhikārī</span>–qualified for devotion, [but their] <span class=\\"e2\\">āchāra</span>–practices [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">pṛthak</span>–different."},{"class":"b50","text":" “There are two types of Vaiṣṇavas: householders and renunciants. Both are qualified for devotion, but their practices are different."},{"class":"b97","text":" দুঁহার চাহিয়ে যুক্ত-বৈরাগ্য বিধান ।<br />সুজ্ঞান, সুভক্তি দুঁহার সমপরিমাণ ॥১৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" du̐hāra chāhiye yukta-vairāgya vidhāna<br />sujñāna, subhakti du̐hāra sama-parimāṇa [13]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">chāhiye</span>–The requirement <span class=\\"e2\\">du̐hāra</span>–of both [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">vidhāna</span>–the practice <span class=\\"e2\\">yukta-vairāgya</span>–of proper renunciation. <span class=\\"e2\\">du̐hāra</span>–Their <span class=\\"e2\\">sujñāna</span>–pure knowledge [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">subhakti</span>–pure devotion [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">sama-parimāṇa</span>–of equal measure."},{"class":"b71","text":" “Both are required to practise proper renunciation, and in terms of pure knowledge and pure devotion, they are equal."},{"class":"b176","text":" গৃহস্থ-বৈষ্ণব কৃত্য"},{"class":"b177","text":" gṛhastha-vaiṣṇava kṛtya"},{"class":"b70","text":" The duties of householder devotees"},{"class":"b97","text":" গৃহস্থ-বৈষ্ণব সদা স্বধর্ম্মে অর্জ্জিবে ।<br />আতিথ্যাদি সেবা যথাসাধ্য আচরিবে ॥১৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" gṛhastha-vaiṣṇava sadā sva-dharme arjibe<br />ātithyādi sevā yathā-sādhya ācharibe [14]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">gṛhastha-vaiṣṇava</span>–Householder devotees [should] <span class=\\"e2\\">sadā</span>–always <span class=\\"e2\\">arjibe</span>–earn [their living] <span class=\\"e2\\">sva-dharme</span>–according to their social duty (their varṇa and āśram), [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">ācharibe</span>–practise <span class=\\"e2\\">sevā</span>–serving <span class=\\"e2\\">ātithyādi</span>–guests and others <span class=\\"e2\\">yathā-sādhya</span>–to the best of [their] ability."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Householder devotees should always earn their living according to their social duty, and they should serve guests and others to the best of their ability."},{"class":"b97","text":" বৈধপত্নী সহবাসে নহে ভক্তি হানি ।<br />সার্ষপ সুতৈল ব্যবহারে নাহি দোষ মানি ॥১৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" vaidha-patnī sahavāse nahe bhakti hāni<br />sārṣapa sutaila vyavahāre nāhi doṣa māni [15]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sahavāse</span>–Living with <span class=\\"e2\\">vaidha-patnī</span>–a lawful wife <span class=\\"e2\\">nahe</span>–is not <span class=\\"e2\\">hāni</span>–a harm <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakti</span>–to devotion, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">māni nāhi</span>–I do not consider <span class=\\"e2\\">vyavahāre</span>–using <span class=\\"e2\\">sārṣapa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sutaila</span>–refined mustard oil <span class=\\"e2\\">doṣa</span>–a fault."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Living with a lawful wife is not harmful to devotion, and I do not consider using mustard oil to be a fault."},{"class":"b97","text":" দধি দুগ্ধ স্মার্ত্ত-উপচরিত আমিষ ।<br />যুক্ত-বৈরাগীর হয় গ্রহণে নিরামিষ ॥১৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" dadhi dugdha smārta-upacharita āmiṣa<br />yukta-vairāgīra haya grahaṇe nirāmiṣa [16]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">dadhi</span>–Yoghurt [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">dugdha</span>–milk <span class=\\"e2\\">smārta-upacharita</span>–prepared according to the smṛti scriptures [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">āmiṣa</span>–non-vegetarian, [but] <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–they become <span class=\\"e2\\">nirāmiṣa</span>–vegetarian <span class=\\"e2\\">yukta-vairāgīra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">grahaṇe</span>–through acceptance by a proper renunciant."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Milk and yoghurt prepared according to smārta regulations are non-vegetarian, but they become vegetarian when they are accepted by proper renunciants."},{"class":"b97","text":" গৃহস্থ-বৈষ্ণব সদা নামাপরাধ রাখি’ দূরে ।<br />আনুকূল্য লয়, প্রাতিকূল্য ত্যাগ করে ॥১৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" gṛhastha-vaiṣṇava sadā nāmāparādha rākhi’ dūre<br />ānukūlya laya, prātikūlya tyāga kare [17]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">gṛhastha-vaiṣṇava</span>–Householder devotees <span class=\\"e2\\">sadā</span>–always <span class=\\"e2\\">dūre rākhi’</span>–avoid <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmāparādha</span>–offences to the Name, <span class=\\"e2\\">laya</span>–accept <span class=\\"e2\\">ānukūlya</span>–the favourable, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">tyāga</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kare</span>–reject <span class=\\"e2\\">prātikūlya</span>–the unfavourable."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Householder devotees always avoid offences to the Name, accept the favourable, and reject the unfavourable."},{"class":"b97","text":" ঐকান্তিক নামাশ্রয় তাহার মহিমা ।<br />গৃহস্থ বৈষ্ণবের নাহি মাহাত্ম্যের সীমা ॥১৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" aikāntika nāmāśraya tāhāra mahimā<br />gṛhastha vaiṣṇavera nāhi māhātmyera sīmā [18]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">aikāntika</span>–Sincerely <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmāśraya</span>–taking shelter of the Name [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhāra</span>–their <span class=\\"e2\\">mahimā</span>–glory. <span class=\\"e2\\">nāhi</span>–There is no <span class=\\"e2\\">sīmā</span>–limit <span class=\\"e2\\">māhātmyera</span>–to the glories <span class=\\"e2\\">gṛhastha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">vaiṣṇavera</span>–of householder devotees."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Sincerely taking shelter of the Name is a householder’s glory. The glories of householder devotees have no end."},{"class":"b97","text":" পরহিংসা ত্যাগ, পর-উপকারে রত ।<br />সর্ব্বভূতে দয়া গৃহীর এইমাত্র ব্রত ॥১৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" para-hiṁsā tyāga, para-upakāre rata<br />sarva-bhūte dayā gṛhīra ei-mātra vrata [19]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">gṛhīra</span>–The householder’s <span class=\\"e2\\">ei-mātra</span>–only <span class=\\"e2\\">vrata</span>–duty [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">tyāga</span>–to avoid <span class=\\"e2\\">para-hiṁsā</span>–envy, <span class=\\"e2\\">para-upakāre</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">rata</span>–engage in helping others, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-bhūte</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">dayā</span>–be compassionate to all beings."},{"class":"b71","text":" “The householder’s only duty is to avoid envy, help others, and be compassionate to all beings."},{"class":"b176","text":" গৃহত্যাগী বা বৈরাগী বৈষ্ণবের কৃত্য"},{"class":"b177","text":" gṛha-tyāgī vā vairāgī vaiṣṇavera kṛtya"},{"class":"b70","text":" The duties of renounced devotees who have given up household life"},{"class":"b97","text":" বৈরাগী বৈষ্ণব প্রাণবৃত্তি অঙ্গীকরি’ ।<br />অসঞ্চয় স্ত্রীসম্ভাষণশূন্য, ভজে হরি ॥২০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" vairāgī vaiṣṇava prāṇa-vṛtti aṅgīkari’<br />asañchaya strī-sambhāṣaṇa-śūnya, bhaje hari [20]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">vairāgī</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">vaiṣṇava</span>–Renounced devotees <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaje</span>–serve <span class=\\"e2\\">hari</span>–the Lord, <span class=\\"e2\\">aṅgīkari’</span>–accept <span class=\\"e2\\">prāṇa-vṛtti</span>–the necessities for life, <span class=\\"e2\\">asañchaya</span>–do not accumulate [wealth, and] <span class=\\"e2\\">strī-sambhāṣaṇa-śūnya</span>–do not converse with women."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Renounced devotees serve the Lord, accept the necessities for life, do not accumulate wealth, and do not converse with women."},{"class":"b97","text":" এইরূপ আচারভেদে সকল বৈষ্ণব ।<br />কৃষ্ণ ভজি’ পায় কৃষ্ণের অপ্রাকৃত বৈভব ॥২১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ei-rūpa āchāra-bhede sakala vaiṣṇava<br />kṛṣṇa bhaji’ pāya kṛṣṇera aprākṛta vaibhava [21]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">ei-rūpa</span>–In this way, <span class=\\"e2\\">āchāra-bhede</span>–according to different practices, <span class=\\"e2\\">sakala</span>–all <span class=\\"e2\\">vaiṣṇava</span>–devotees <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaji’</span>–serve <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span>–Kṛṣṇa [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">pāya</span>–realise <span class=\\"e2\\">aprākṛta</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">vaibhava</span>–the divine glory <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇera</span>–of Kṛṣṇa."},{"class":"b71","text":" “In this way, according to different practices, all devotees serve Kṛṣṇa and realise His divine glory."},{"class":"b176","text":" বৈষ্ণবের কুটীনাটী নাই"},{"class":"b177","text":" vaiṣṇavera kuṭīnāṭī nāi"},{"class":"b70","text":" Vaiṣṇavas are not deceitful"},{"class":"b97","text":" গৃহী হউক ত্যাগী হউক ভক্তে ভেদ নাই ।<br />ভেদ কৈলে কুম্ভীপাক নরকেতে যাই ॥২২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" gṛhī ha-uka tyāgī ha-uka bhakte bheda nāi<br />bheda kaile kumbhīpāka narakete yāi [22]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">nāi</span>–There is no <span class=\\"e2\\">bheda</span>–difference <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakte</span>–between devotees— <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-uka</span>–be they <span class=\\"e2\\">gṛhī</span>–householders [or] <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-uka</span>–be they <span class=\\"e2\\">tyāgī</span>–renunciants. <span class=\\"e2\\">bheda</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kaile</span>–If someone makes distinctions [between them,] <span class=\\"e2\\">yāi</span>–they go <span class=\\"e2\\">kumbhīpāka</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">narakete</span>–to the hell of boiling oil."},{"class":"b50","text":" “There is no difference between devotees—be they householders or renunciants. If someone makes distinctions between them, they go to the hell of boiling oil."},{"class":"b97","text":" মূল কথা, কুটীনাটী ব্যবহার যার ।<br />বৈষ্ণবকুলেতে সেই মহাকুলাঙ্গার ॥২৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" mūla kathā, kuṭīnāṭī vyavahāra yāra<br />vaiṣṇava-kulete sei mahākulāṅgāra [23]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">mūla</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kathā</span>–The main point [is that] <span class=\\"e2\\">sei yāra</span>–those who <span class=\\"e2\\">vyavahāra</span>–behave <span class=\\"e2\\">kuṭīnāṭī</span>–deceitfully [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">mahākulāṅgāra</span>–a great disgrace <span class=\\"e2\\">vaiṣṇava-kulete</span>–to the society of devotees."},{"class":"b50","text":" “The main point is that those who behave deceitfully are a great disgrace to the society of Vaiṣṇavas."},{"class":"b97","text":" সরল ভাবেতে গঠি’ নিজ ব্যবহার ।<br />জীবনে মরণে কৃষ্ণভক্তি জানি সার ॥২৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sarala bhāvete gaṭhi’ nija vyavahāra<br />jīvane maraṇe kṛṣṇa-bhakti jāni sāra [24]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">nija</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">vyavahāra gaṭhi’</span>–Everyone should behave <span class=\\"e2\\">sarala</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāvete</span>–in a sincere manner [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">jāni</span>–know <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-bhakti</span>–devotion to Kṛṣṇa [to be] <span class=\\"e2\\">sāra</span>–all-in-all, <span class=\\"e2\\">jīvane</span>–in life [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">maraṇe</span>–death."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Everyone should behave in a sincere manner and know devotion to Kṛṣṇa to be all-in-all, in life and death."},{"class":"b97","text":" কুটীনাটী কপটতা শাঠ্য কুটীলতা ।<br />না ছাড়িয়া হরি ভজে, তার দিন গেল বৃথা ॥২৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kuṭīnāṭī kapaṭatā śāṭhya kuṭīlatā<br />nā chhāḍiyā hari bhaje, tāra dina gela vṛthā [25]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">dina</span>–The days <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra</span>–of those who <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaje</span>–serve <span class=\\"e2\\">hari</span>–the Lord [but] <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍiyā nā</span>–do not give up <span class=\\"e2\\">kuṭīnāṭī</span>–deceit, <span class=\\"e2\\">kapaṭatā</span>–duplicity, <span class=\\"e2\\">śāṭhya</span>–dishonesty, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">kuṭīlatā</span>–insincerity <span class=\\"e2\\">gela</span>–pass <span class=\\"e2\\">vṛthā</span>–in vain."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Those who serve the Lord but do not give up deceit, duplicity, dishonesty, and insincerity pass their days in vain."},{"class":"b97","text":" সেই সব ভাগবত কদর্থ করিয়া ।<br />ইন্দ্রিয় চরাঞা বুলে প্রকৃতি ভুলাইয়া ॥২৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sei saba bhāgavata kadartha kariyā<br />indriya charāñā bule prakṛti bhulāiyā [26]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">saba</span>–They <span class=\\"e2\\">kadartha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kariyā</span>–distort the meaning <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāgavata</span>–of <span class=\\"e33\\">Śrīmad Bhāgavatam</span>, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">bule</span>–roam about <span class=\\"e2\\">charāñā</span>–enjoying <span class=\\"e2\\">indriya</span>–the senses [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhulāiyā</span>–seducing <span class=\\"e2\\">prakṛti</span>–women."},{"class":"b71","text":" “They distort the meaning of <span class=\\"e3\\">Śrīmad Bhāgavatam</span> and roam about enjoying the senses and seducing women."},{"class":"b176","text":" ভাগবত-শ্লোক যথা"},{"class":"b177","text":" bhāgavata-śloka yathā"},{"class":"b70","text":" A verse from Śrīmad Bhāgavatam (10.33.36)"},{"class":"b97","text":" অনুগ্রহায় ভক্তানাং মানুষং দেহমাশ্রিতঃ ।<br />ভজতে তাদৃশীঃ ক্রীড়া যাঃ শ্রুত্বা তৎপরো ভবেৎ ॥২৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" anugrahāya bhaktānāṁ mānuṣaṁ deham āśritaḥ<br />bhajate tādṛśīḥ krīḍā yāḥ śrutvā tat-paro bhavet [27]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">anugrahāya</span>–To bestow mercy <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaktānāṁ</span>–upon [His] devotees, <span class=\\"e2\\">āśritaḥ</span>–Kṛṣṇa assumes <span class=\\"e2\\">mānuṣaṁ</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">deham</span>–a human-like form [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhajate</span>–manifests <span class=\\"e2\\">krīḍā</span>–Pastimes. <span class=\\"e2\\">śrutvā</span>–Hearing <span class=\\"e2\\">tādṛśīḥ</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">yāḥ</span>–about them, <span class=\\"e2\\">bhavet</span>–souls become <span class=\\"e2\\">tat-paro</span>–devoted to Him."},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘To bestow mercy upon His devotees, Kṛṣṇa assumes a human-like form and manifests His Pastimes. Those who hear about these Pastimes become devoted to Kṛṣṇa.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" লম্পট পাপিষ্ঠ আপনাকে কৃষ্ণ মানি’ ।<br />কৃষ্ণলীলা অনুকৃতি করে ধর্ম্মহানি ॥২৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" lampaṭa pāpiṣṭha āpanāke kṛṣṇa māni’<br />kṛṣṇa-līlā anukṛti kare dharma-hāni [28]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">lampaṭa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">pāpiṣṭha</span>–Lewd sinners <span class=\\"e2\\">māni’</span>–consider <span class=\\"e2\\">āpanāke</span>–themselves <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span>–Kṛṣṇa, <span class=\\"e2\\">anukṛti</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kare</span>–imitate <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-līlā</span>–Kṛṣṇa’s Pastimes, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">dharma-hāni</span>–desecrate religious principles."},{"class":"b71","text":" “Lewd sinners consider themselves Kṛṣṇa, imitate Kṛṣṇa’s Pastimes, and desecrate dharma."},{"class":"b176","text":" শুদ্ধভক্তের রাধাকৃষ্ণের সেবা"},{"class":"b177","text":" śuddha-bhaktera rādhā-kṛṣṇera sevā"},{"class":"b70","text":" A pure devotee’s service to Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa"},{"class":"b97","text":" শুদ্ধভক্ত ভক্তভাবে চিৎস্বরূপ হঞা ।<br />ব্রজে রাধাকৃষ্ণ সেবে সখীভাব লঞা ॥২৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" śuddha-bhakta bhakta-bhāve chit-svarūpa hañā<br />vraje rādhā-kṛṣṇa seve sakhī-bhāva lañā [29]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">śuddha-bhakta</span>–Pure devotees <span class=\\"e2\\">hañā</span>–attain [their] <span class=\\"e2\\">chit-svarūpa</span>–spiritual form <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakta-bhāve</span>–as a devotee [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">seve</span>–serve <span class=\\"e2\\">rādhā-kṛṣṇa</span>–Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">vraje</span>–in Vraja <span class=\\"e2\\">lañā</span>–with <span class=\\"e2\\">sakhī-bhāva</span>–the mood of a sakhī."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Pure devotees attain their spiritual devotee form and serve Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa in Vraja in the mood of a sakhī."},{"class":"b97","text":" কৃষ্ণভাবে তৎপর হয় যে পামর ।<br />কুম্ভীপাক প্রাপ্ত হয় মরণের পর ॥৩০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kṛṣṇa-bhāve tat-para haya ye pāmara<br />kumbhīpāka prāpta haya maraṇera para [30]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">ye</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">pāmara</span>–Fools who <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-bhāve</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">tat-para</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–impersonate Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">prāpta</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–go <span class=\\"e2\\">kumbhīpāka</span>–to the hell of boiling oil <span class=\\"e2\\">maraṇera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">para</span>–after death."},{"class":"b71","text":" “Fools who impersonate Kṛṣṇa go to the hell of boiling oil after death."},{"class":"b176","text":" অন্তরঙ্গ ভক্তি দেহে নহে, আত্মায়"},{"class":"b177","text":" antaraṅga bhakti dehe nahe, ātmāya"},{"class":"b70","text":" Confidential devotion exists within the heart—not the body"},{"class":"b97","text":" অন্তরঙ্গ ভক্তি মনে, দেহে কিছু নয় ।<br />কুটীনাটী বলে মূঢ় আচরণ হয় ॥৩১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" antaraṅga bhakti mane, dehe kichhu naya<br />kuṭīnāṭī bale mūḍha ācharaṇa haya [31]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">antaraṅga</span>–Confidential <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakti</span>–devotion [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">mane</span>–in the heart. <span class=\\"e2\\">kichhu</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">naya</span>–There is nothing <span class=\\"e2\\">dehe</span>–within the body, [but] <span class=\\"e2\\">mūḍha</span>–fools <span class=\\"e2\\">kuṭīnāṭī</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–deceitfully <span class=\\"e2\\">ācharaṇa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–imitate [it]."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Confidential devotion is in the heart, not the body, but fools deceitfully imitate it."},{"class":"b97","text":" সেই সব অসৎসঙ্গ দূরে পরিহরি’ ।<br />কৃষ্ণ ভজে শুদ্ধভক্ত সিদ্ধদেহ ধরি ॥৩২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sei saba asat-saṅga dūre parihari’<br />kṛṣṇa bhaje śuddha-bhakta siddha-deha dhari’ [32]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">dūre</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">parihari’</span>–Avoiding <span class=\\"e2\\">sei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">saba</span>–all such <span class=\\"e2\\">asat-saṅga</span>–bad association, <span class=\\"e2\\">śuddha-bhakta</span>–pure devotees <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaje</span>–serve <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span>–Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">siddha-deha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">dhari’</span>–with [their] spiritual bodies."},{"class":"b71","text":" “Avoiding all such forms of bad association, pure devotees serve Kṛṣṇa with their spiritual bodies."},{"class":"b176","text":" কৃষ্ণই পুরুষ, আর সব প্রকৃতি"},{"class":"b177","text":" kṛṣṇa-i puruṣa, āra saba prakṛti"},{"class":"b70","text":" Kṛṣṇa is the only male; everyone else is female"},{"class":"b97","text":" ভক্তসব প্রকৃতি হইয়া মজে কৃষ্ণপায় ।<br />পুরুষ একলে কৃষ্ণ, দাস মহাশয়” ॥৩৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" bhakta-saba prakṛti ha-iyā maje kṛṣṇa-pāya<br />puruṣa ekale kṛṣṇa, dāsa mahāśaya” [33]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakta-saba</span>–All devotees <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-iyā</span>–are <span class=\\"e2\\">prakṛti</span>–female [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">maje</span>–revel <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-pāya</span>–in Kṛṣṇa’s feet. <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span>–Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">ekale</span>–alone [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">puruṣa</span>–male, <span class=\\"e2\\">dāsa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">mahāśaya”</span>–O honour­able servant, Dās.”"},{"class":"b50","text":" “All devotees are female and revel in Kṛṣṇa’s feet. Kṛṣṇa is the only male, O Dās Mahāśay.”"},{"class":"b97","text":" রঘুনাথ দাস তবে বিনীত হইয়া ।<br />স্বরূপেরে নিবেদন করে দু’হাত জুড়িয়া ॥৩৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" raghunātha dāsa tabe vinīta ha-iyā<br />svarūpere nivedana kare du’hāta juḍiyā [34]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">raghunātha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">dāsa</span>–Raghunāth Dās <span class=\\"e2\\">tabe</span>–then <span class=\\"e2\\">juḍiyā</span>–joined [his] <span class=\\"e2\\">du’hāta</span>–two hands [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">vinīta</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-iyā</span>–humbly <span class=\\"e2\\">nivedana</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kare</span>–spoke <span class=\\"e2\\">svarūpere</span>–to Svarūp."},{"class":"b50","text":" Raghunāth Dās joined his palms and humbly spoke to Svarūp."},{"class":"b97","text":" “বল প্রভু, আছে এক জিজ্ঞাস্য আমার ।<br />স্বধর্ম্মবিহীনভক্তি সর্ব্বভক্তিসার ॥৩৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" “bala prabhu, āchhe eka jijñāsya āmāra<br />sva-dharma-vihīna-bhakti sarva-bhakti-sāra [35]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">“prabhu</span>–“Master, <span class=\\"e2\\">bala</span>–please speak [to me]. <span class=\\"e2\\">āmāra āchhe</span>–I have <span class=\\"e2\\">eka</span>–a <span class=\\"e2\\">jijñāsya</span>–question. <span class=\\"e2\\">sva-dharma-vihīna-bhakti</span>–Devotion that is free from social duty (the duties of varṇa and āśram) [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-bhakti-sāra</span>–the best of all forms of devotion."},{"class":"b71","text":" “Master, I have a question. Please answer me. Devotion that is free from social duty is the best of all forms of devotion."},{"class":"b176","text":" গৃহস্থ ও স্বধর্ম্ম"},{"class":"b177","text":" gṛhastha o svadharma"},{"class":"b70","text":" Householders and social duty"},{"class":"b97","text":" তবে কেন গৃহস্থ থাকিবে স্বধর্ম্মেতে ।<br />স্বধর্ম্ম ছাড়িয়া ভক্তি পারে ত’ করিতে” ॥৩৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" tabe kena gṛhastha thākibe svadharmete<br />svadharma chhāḍiyā bhakti pāre ta’ karite” [36]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">tabe</span>–So <span class=\\"e2\\">kena</span>–why [should] <span class=\\"e2\\">gṛhastha</span>–householders <span class=\\"e2\\">thākibe</span>–remain [engaged] <span class=\\"e2\\">svadharmete</span>–in their social duty? <span class=\\"e2\\">pāre</span>–They can <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍiyā</span>–leave [their] <span class=\\"e2\\">svadharma</span>–social duty [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">ta’</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">karite</span>–practise <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakti”</span>–devotion.”"},{"class":"b50","text":" “So why should householders remain engaged in their social duty when they can give it up and practise devotion?”"},{"class":"b97","text":" স্বরূপ বলে, “শুন, ভাই, ইহাতে যে মর্ম্ম ।<br />বলিব তোমাকে আমি শুদ্ধভক্তি ধর্ম্ম ॥৩৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" svarūpa bale, “śuna, bhāi, ihāte ye marma<br />baliba tomāke āmi śuddha-bhakti dharma [37]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">svarūpa</span>–Svarūp <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–said, <span class=\\"e2\\">“bhāi</span>–“Brother, <span class=\\"e2\\">śuna</span>–listen! <span class=\\"e2\\">āmi</span>–I <span class=\\"e2\\">baliba</span>–will explain <span class=\\"e2\\">tomāke</span>–to you<span class=\\"e2\\"> dharma</span>–the nature <span class=\\"e2\\">śuddha-bhakti</span>–of pure devotion, <span class=\\"e2\\">ye</span>–which [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">marma</span>–the essence <span class=\\"e2\\">ihāte</span>–of this."},{"class":"b50","text":" Svarūp replied, “Brother, listen! I will explain to you the nature of pure devotion, which is the essence of this matter."},{"class":"b97","text":" স্বধর্ম্মে জীবনযাত্রা সহজে ঘটয় ।<br />পরধর্ম্মে কষ্ট আছে, স্বাভাবিক নয় ॥৩৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" svadharme jīvana-yātrā sahaje ghaṭaya<br />para-dharme kaṣṭa āchhe, svābhāvika naya [38]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [Your] <span class=\\"e2\\">jīvana-yātrā</span>–livelihood <span class=\\"e2\\">ghaṭaya</span>–is maintained <span class=\\"e2\\">sahaje</span>–easily <span class=\\"e2\\">svadharme</span>–by fol­lowing [your] own social duty; <span class=\\"e2\\">āchhe</span>–there is <span class=\\"e2\\">kaṣṭa</span>–difficulty <span class=\\"e2\\">para-dharme</span>–in following someone else’s duty, [because] <span class=\\"e2\\">naya</span>–it is not <span class=\\"e2\\">svābhāvika</span>–natural."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Your livelihood is easily maintained by following your own social duty; it is difficult to follow someone else’s duty because it is unnatural."},{"class":"b97","text":" স্বধর্ম্মে ভক্তির অনুকূল যাহা হয় ।<br />তাই ভক্তিমান্ জন গ্রহণ করয় ॥৩৯॥<br />যাহা যখন ভক্তি-প্রতিকূল হঞা যায় ।<br />তাহা ত্যাগ করিলে ত’ শুদ্ধভক্তি পায় ॥৪০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" svadharme bhaktira anukūla yāhā haya<br />tāi bhaktimān jana grahaṇa karaya [39]"},{"class":"b60","text":" yāhā yakhana bhakti-pratikūla hañā yāya<br />tāhā tyāga karile ta’ śuddha-bhakti pāya [40]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [When] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaktimān</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">jana</span>–devotees, <span class=\\"e2\\">svadharme</span>–in the midst of [their] social duty, <span class=\\"e2\\">grahaṇa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">karaya</span>–accept <span class=\\"e2\\">tāi yāhā</span>–that which <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–is <span class=\\"e2\\">anukūla</span>–favourable <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaktira</span>–to devotion [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">tyāga</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">karile</span>–avoid <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhā</span>–things <span class=\\"e2\\">yakhana</span>–when <span class=\\"e2\\">yāhā</span>–they <span class=\\"e2\\">hañā yāya</span>–become <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakti-pratikūla</span>–unfavourable to devotion, [then] <span class=\\"e2\\">pāya ta’</span>–they attain <span class=\\"e2\\">śuddha-bhakti</span>–pure devotion."},{"class":"b50","text":" “When devotees, in the midst their social duty, accept everything that is favourable to devotion and avoid everything that is unfavourable to devotion, then they attain pure devotion."},{"class":"b97","text":" অতএব স্বধর্ম্মনিষ্ঠা চিত্ত হইতে ত্যজি’ ।<br />ভক্তিনিষ্ঠা করিলেই সাধুধর্ম্ম ভজি’ ॥৪১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ataeva svadharma-niṣṭhā chitta ha-ite tyaji’<br />bhakti-niṣṭhā karilei sādhu-dharma bhaji’ [41]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">ataeva</span>–So, [only if] <span class=\\"e2\\">tyaji’</span>–they remove <span class=\\"e2\\">svadharma-niṣṭhā</span>–attachment to [their] social duty <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-ite</span>–from [their] <span class=\\"e2\\">chitta</span>–heart [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakti-niṣṭhā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">karilei</span>–develop attachment to devotion [do they] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaji’</span>–follow <span class=\\"e2\\">sādhu-dharma</span>–the duty of a sādhu."},{"class":"b50","text":" “So, only if they remove attachment to their social duty from their heart and develop attachment to devotion do they follow the duty of a sādhu."},{"class":"b97","text":" স্বধর্ম্মত্যাগের নাম নিষ্ঠাপরিহার ।<br />নিয়মাগ্রহ দূর হইলে হয় বৈষ্ণব আচার ॥৪২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" svadharma-tyāgera nāma niṣṭhā-parihāra<br />niyamāgraha dūra ha-ile haya vaiṣṇava āchāra [42]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">svadharma-tyāgera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–The phrase, ‘renouncing social duty’ [means] <span class=\\"e2\\">niṣṭhā-parihāra</span>–giving up attachment [to it. When] <span class=\\"e2\\">niyamāgraha</span>–excessive attachment to rules <span class=\\"e2\\">dūra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-ile</span>–withdraws, <span class=\\"e2\\">vaiṣṇava</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">āchāra</span>–Vaiṣṇava practice <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–takes place."},{"class":"b71","text":" “‘Renouncing social duty’ means giving up attachment to it. When excessive attachment to the rules for social duty withdraws, Vaiṣṇava practice begins."},{"class":"b176","text":" কৃষ্ণস্মৃতি বিধি; কৃষ্ণবিস্মৃতি নিষেধ"},{"class":"b177","text":" kṛṣṇa-smṛti vidhi; kṛṣṇa-vismṛti niṣedha"},{"class":"b70","text":" The rule is: remember Kṛṣṇa, <br />and the prohibition is: do not forget Kṛṣṇa"},{"class":"b97","text":" নিরন্তর কৃষ্ণস্মৃতি মূলবিধি ভাই ।<br />শ্রীকৃষ্ণবিস্মৃতি যাহে নিষেধ মূল তাই” ॥৪৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" nirantara kṛṣṇa-smṛti mūla-vidhi bhāi<br />śrī-kṛṣṇa-vismṛti yāhe niṣedha mūla tāi” [43]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāi</span>–Brother, <span class=\\"e2\\">nirantara</span>–constant <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-smṛti</span>–remembrance of Kṛṣṇa [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">mūla-vidhi</span>–the fundamental rule, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">tāi yāhe</span>–that by which <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-kṛṣṇa-vismṛti</span>–forgetfulness of Śrī Kṛṣṇa [occurs is] <span class=\\"e2\\">mūla niṣedha”</span>–the fundamental prohibition.”"},{"class":"b50","text":" “Brother, constant remembrance of Kṛṣṇa is the fundamental rule, and forgetfulness of Kṛṣṇa is the fundamental prohibition.”"},{"class":"b97","text":" তবে রঘুনাথ বলে, “কথা এক আর ।<br />আজ্ঞা হয় শুনি যাহে বৈষ্ণব-বিচার ॥৪৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" tabe raghunātha bale, “kathā eka āra<br />ājñā haya śuni yāhe vaiṣṇava-vichāra [44]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">raghunātha</span>–Raghunāth <span class=\\"e2\\">tabe</span>–then <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–said, [“There is] <span class=\\"e2\\">“āra eka kathā</span>–another subject. <span class=\\"e2\\">ājñā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–If you allow [me,] <span class=\\"e2\\">śuni</span>–I would like to hear [further] <span class=\\"e2\\">yāhe</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">vaiṣṇava-vichāra</span>–explanation about Vaiṣṇavas."},{"class":"b71","text":" Raghunāth said, “I have another subject to discuss. If you allow me, I would like to hear further explanation about Vaiṣṇavas."},{"class":"b176","text":" শ্রীঅচ্যুতগোত্র ও স্বধর্ম্ম"},{"class":"b177","text":" śrī-achyuta-gotra o svadharma"},{"class":"b70","text":" The family of the Lord and social duty"},{"class":"b97","text":" শ্রীঅচ্যুতগোত্র বলি’ বৈষ্ণব-নির্দ্দেশ ।<br />ইহার তাৎপর্য কিবা, ইথে কি বিশেষ” ॥৪৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" śrī-achyuta-gotra bali’ vaiṣṇava-nirdeśa<br />ihāra tātparya kibā, ithe ki viśeṣa” [45]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">vaiṣṇava-nirdeśa bali’</span>–Devotees are identified as <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-achyuta-gotra</span>–the family of the Lord. <span class=\\"e2\\">kibā</span>–What [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">tātparya</span>–the meaning <span class=\\"e2\\">ihāra</span>–of this? <span class=\\"e2\\">ki</span>–What [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">viśeṣa</span>–significant <span class=\\"e2\\">ithe”</span>–in this regard?”"},{"class":"b50","text":" “Vaiṣṇavas are described as the family of the Lord. What is the meaning and significance of this?”"},{"class":"b97","text":" স্বরূপ বলে, “গৃহী, ত্যাগী উভয়ে সর্ব্বথা ।<br />এই গোত্রে অধিকারী নাহিক অন্যথা ॥৪৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" svarūpa bale, “gṛhī, tyāgī ubhaye sarvathā<br />ei gotre adhikārī nāhika anyathā [46]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">svarūpa</span>–Svarūp <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–said, <span class=\\"e2\\">“ubhaye</span>–Both <span class=\\"e2\\">gṛhī</span>–householders [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">tyāgī</span>–renunciants [are,] <span class=\\"e2\\">sarvathā</span>–in all respects, <span class=\\"e2\\">adhikārī</span>–members <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">gotre</span>–of this family [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāhika</span>–no <span class=\\"e2\\">anyathā</span>–other."},{"class":"b50","text":" Svarūp said, “Both householders and renunciants are, in all respects, members of this family and no other."},{"class":"b97","text":" শ্রীঅচ্যুতগোত্রে থাকে শুদ্ধভক্ত যত ।<br />স্বধর্ম্মনিষ্ঠায় কভু নাহি হয় রত ॥৪৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" śrī-achyuta-gotre thāke śuddha-bhakta yata<br />svadharma-niṣṭhāya kabhu nāhi haya rata [47]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">yata</span>–All <span class=\\"e2\\">śuddha-bhakta</span>–pure devotees <span class=\\"e2\\">thāke</span>–live <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-achyuta-gotre</span>–in the family of the Lord [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāhi</span>–never <span class=\\"e2\\">svadharma-niṣṭhāya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">rata haya</span>–become attached to social duty."},{"class":"b50","text":" “All pure devotees belong to the family of the Lord and never become attached to social duty."},{"class":"b97","text":" সংসারের গোত্র ত্যজি’ কৃষ্ণগোত্র ভজে ।<br />সেই নিত্যগোত্র তার যেই বৈসে ব্রজে ॥৪৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" saṁsārera gotra tyaji’ kṛṣṇa-gotra bhaje<br />sei nitya-gotra tāra yei vaise vraje [48]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">tyaji’</span>–They leave behind [their]<span class=\\"e2\\"> saṁsārera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">gotra</span>–worldly family [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaje</span>–serve <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-gotra</span>–Kṛṣṇa’s family. <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">yei</span>–Those who <span class=\\"e2\\">vaise</span>–reside <span class=\\"e2\\">vraje</span>–in Vraja [are part of] <span class=\\"e2\\">sei</span>–that <span class=\\"e2\\">nitya-gotra</span>–eternal family."},{"class":"b50","text":" “They give up their worldly families and serve Kṛṣṇa’s family. Those who reside in Vraja are part of that eternal family."},{"class":"b97","text":" কেহ বা স্বদেহে বৈসে ব্রজগোপী হঞা ।<br />কেহ বা আরোপসিদ্ধ-মানসে লইয়া ॥৪৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" keha vā svadehe vaise vraja-gopī hañā<br />keha vā āropa-siddha-mānase la-iyā [49]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">keha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">vā</span>–Some <span class=\\"e2\\">vaise</span>–reside <span class=\\"e2\\">svadehe</span>–in [their] own body <span class=\\"e2\\">hañā</span>–as <span class=\\"e2\\">vraja-gopī</span>–a gopī of Vraja, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">keha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">vā</span>–some <span class=\\"e2\\">la-iyā</span>–practise <span class=\\"e2\\">āropa-siddha-mānase</span>–ascription within their minds."},{"class":"b71","text":" “Some reside in their spiritual body as Vraja-gopīs, and others practise ārop-siddhā* within their minds."},{"class":"b176","text":" প্রবর্ত্ত, সাধক, সিদ্ধ"},{"class":"b177","text":" pravarta, sādhaka, siddha"},{"class":"b70","text":" Beginners, practitioners, and experts"},{"class":"b97","text":" প্রবর্ত্ত, সাধক, সিদ্ধ—তিন যে প্রকার ।<br />বুঝিতে পারিলে বুঝি ভক্তিধর্ম্মসার ॥৫০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" pravarta, sādhaka, siddha—tina ye prakāra<br />bujhite pārile bujhi bhakti-dharma-sāra [50]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">pārile</span>–If you can <span class=\\"e2\\">bujhite</span>–understand <span class=\\"e2\\">ye</span>–the <span class=\\"e2\\">tina</span>–three <span class=\\"e2\\">prakāra</span>–classes [of devotees]— <span class=\\"e2\\">pravarta</span>–beginners, <span class=\\"e2\\">sādhaka</span>–practitioners, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">siddha</span>–experts— [then] <span class=\\"e2\\">bujhi</span>–you can understand <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakti-dharma-sāra</span>–the essence of devotional practice."},{"class":"b50","text":" “If you can understand the three classes of devotees—beginners, practitioners, and experts—then you can understand the essence of devotional practice."},{"class":"b97","text":" ‘কনিষ্ঠাধিকারী’ হয় ‘প্রবর্ত্তে’ গণন ।<br />মধ্যমাধিকারী সাধক ভক্ত মহাজন ॥৫১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ‘kaniṣṭhādhikārī’ haya ‘pravarte’ gaṇana<br />‘madhyamādhikārī’ ‘sādhaka’ bhakta mahājana [51]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">‘kaniṣṭhādhikārī’</span>–A kaniṣṭha adhikārī <span class=\\"e2\\">gaṇana haya</span>–is counted <span class=\\"e2\\">‘pravarte’</span>–as a beginner. <span class=\\"e2\\">‘madhyamādhikārī’</span>–A madhyam adhikārī [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">‘sādhaka’</span>–a practitioner, <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakta</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">mahājana</span>–a devotee, and a great soul."},{"class":"b50","text":" “A kaniṣṭha adhikārī is considered a beginner. A madhyam adhikārī is a practitioner, a devotee, and a great soul."},{"class":"b97","text":" ‘উত্তমাধিকারী’ হয় ‘সিদ্ধ’ মহাশয় ।<br />হৃদয়ে স্বধর্ম্মনিষ্ঠা কভু না করয় ॥৫২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ‘uttamādhikārī’ haya ‘siddha’ mahāśaya<br />hṛdaye svadharma-niṣṭhā kabhu nā karaya [52]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">‘uttamādhikārī’</span>–An uttam adhikārī <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–is <span class=\\"e2\\">mahāśaya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">‘siddha’</span>–a worshippable expert, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nā</span>–never <span class=\\"e2\\">svadharma-niṣṭhā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">karaya</span>–becomes attached to social duty <span class=\\"e2\\">hṛdaye</span>–at heart."},{"class":"b43","text":" “An uttam adhikārī is a worshippable expert and never becomes attached to social duty at heart."},{"class":"b69","text":" * See 17.57."},{"class":"b97","text":" মধ্যমাধিকারী আর উত্তমাধিকারী ।<br />সকলে অচ্যুতগোত্র দেখহ বিচারি’” ॥৫৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" madhyamādhikārī āra uttamādhikārī<br />sakale achyuta-gotra dekhaha vichāri’” [53]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">vichāri’ dekhaha</span>–Consider <span class=\\"e2\\">sakale</span>–both <span class=\\"e2\\">madhyamādhikārī</span>–practitioners <span class=\\"e2\\">āra</span>–and <span class=\\"e2\\">uttamādhikārī</span>–experts [to be part] <span class=\\"e2\\">achyuta-gotra”</span>–of the family of the Lord.”"},{"class":"b71","text":" “Consider both practitioners and experts to be part of the family of the Lord.”"},{"class":"b176","text":" আরোপ"},{"class":"b177","text":" āropa"},{"class":"b70","text":" Ascription"},{"class":"b97","text":" রঘুনাথ বলে, “এবে আরোপ বুঝিব ।<br />তাৎপর্য বুঝিয়া সব সন্দেহ ত্যজিব” ॥৫৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" raghunātha bale, “ebe āropa bujhiba<br />tātparya bujhiyā saba sandeha tyajiba” [54]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">raghunātha</span>–Raghunāth <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–said, <span class=\\"e2\\">“bujhiba</span>–“I wish to understand <span class=\\"e2\\">āropa</span>–ascription <span class=\\"e2\\">ebe</span>–now. <span class=\\"e2\\">bujhiyā</span>–By understanding [its] <span class=\\"e2\\">tātparya</span>–significance, <span class=\\"e2\\">tyajiba</span>–I will give up <span class=\\"e2\\">saba</span>–all [my] <span class=\\"e2\\">sandeha</span>–doubts."},{"class":"b50","text":" Raghunāth said, “I now wish to understand ascription. By understanding its significance, I will give up all my doubts."},{"class":"b97","text":" দামোদর বলে, “শুন আরোপ-সন্ধান ।<br />ইহাতে চাহিয়ে ভক্তিস্বরূপের জ্ঞান ॥৫৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" dāmodara bale, “śuna āropa-sandhāna<br />ihāte chāhiye bhakti-svarūpera jñāna [55]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">dāmodara</span>–Dāmodar <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–said, <span class=\\"e2\\">“śuna</span>–“Hear <span class=\\"e2\\">āropa-sandhāna</span>–a description of ascription. <span class=\\"e2\\">ihāte</span>–In this regard, <span class=\\"e2\\">chāhiye</span>–you need <span class=\\"e2\\">jñāna</span>–knowledge <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakti-svarūpera</span>–of the nature of devotion [itself]."},{"class":"b71","text":" Dāmodar said, “Hear now about ascription. To understand it, you need to understand the nature of devotion itself."},{"class":"b176","text":" ত্রিবিধা বৈষ্ণবী ভক্তি"},{"class":"b177","text":" trividhā vaiṣṇavī bhakti"},{"class":"b70","text":" The three types of Vaiṣṇava devotion"},{"class":"b97","text":" ত্রিবিধা বৈষ্ণবী ভক্তি করহ বিচার ।<br />(১) ‘আরোপ-সিদ্ধা’, (২) ‘সঙ্গসিদ্ধা’, (৩) ‘স্বরূপ-সিদ্ধা’ আর ॥৫৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" trividhā vaiṣṇavī bhakti karaha vichāra<br />(1) ‘āropa-siddhā’, (2) ‘saṅga-siddhā’, (3) ‘svarūpa-siddhā’ āra [56]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">vichāra karaha</span>–Consider <span class=\\"e2\\">trividhā</span>–the three types <span class=\\"e2\\">vaiṣṇavī</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakti</span>–of Vaiṣṇava devotion: <span class=\\"e2\\">‘āropa-siddhā’</span>–‘ārop-siddhā’, <span class=\\"e2\\">‘saṅga-siddhā’</span>–‘saṅga-siddhā’, <span class=\\"e2\\">āra</span>–and <span class=\\"e2\\">‘svarūpa-siddhā’</span>–‘svarūp-siddhā’."},{"class":"b71","text":" “You should know that there are three types of Vaiṣṇava devotion: ārop-siddhā, saṅga-siddhā, and svarūp-siddhā."},{"class":"b176","text":" (১) আরোপ-সিদ্ধা ভক্তি—কনিষ্ঠাধিকারীর"},{"class":"b177","text":" (1) āropa-siddhā bhakti—kaniṣṭhādhikārīra"},{"class":"b70","text":" (1) Devotion expressed through ascription is for the beginner"},{"class":"b97","text":" আরোপ-সিদ্ধার কথা বলিব প্রথমে ।<br />সুস্থির হইয়া বুঝ চিত্তের সংযমে ॥৫৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" āropa-siddhāra kathā baliba prathame<br />susthira ha-iyā bujha chittera saṁyame [57]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">prathame</span>–First, <span class=\\"e2\\">āropa-siddhāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kathā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">baliba</span>–I will explain ārop-siddhā. <span class=\\"e2\\">susthira ha-iyā</span>–Focus [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">bujha</span>–understand [it] <span class=\\"e2\\">chittera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">saṁyame</span>–with a controlled mind."},{"class":"b50","text":" “First, I will explain ārop-siddhā. Focus and understand it with a controlled mind."},{"class":"b97","text":" বদ্ধ বহির্ম্মুখ জীব বিষয়ী প্রধান ।<br />জড়সঙ্গমাত্র করি’ করে অবস্থান ॥৫৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" baddha bahirmukha jīva viṣayī pradhāna<br />jaḍa-saṅga-mātra kari’ kare avasthāna [58]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">baddha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">jīva</span>–Conditioned souls [who are] <span class=\\"e2\\">bahirmukha</span>–averse [to the Lord are] <span class=\\"e2\\">viṣayī</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">pradhāna</span>–mostly materialists. <span class=\\"e2\\">avasthāna kare</span>–They live [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">saṅga-mātra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kari’</span>–associate only <span class=\\"e2\\">jaḍa</span>–with matter."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Conditioned souls who are averse to the Lord are mostly materialists and associate only with material things."},{"class":"b97","text":" জড়সুখ জড়দুঃখ নিয়ত তাহার ।<br />প্রাকৃত সংসর্গ বিনা কিছু নাহি আর ॥৫৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" jaḍa-sukha jaḍa-duḥkha niyata tāhāra<br />prākṛta saṁsarga vinā kichhu nāhi āra [59]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">niyata</span>–Constantly, <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhāra</span>–their [experience] <span class=\\"e2\\">jaḍa-sukha</span>–of material happiness [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">jaḍa-duḥkha</span>–material sadness [takes places]. <span class=\\"e2\\">kichhu</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāhi</span>–They have no <span class=\\"e2\\">saṁsarga</span>–connection <span class=\\"e2\\">āra</span>–with anything <span class=\\"e2\\">vinā</span>–other than <span class=\\"e2\\">prākṛta</span>–matter."},{"class":"b50","text":" “They are constantly engrossed in material happiness and sadness, and have no experience of anything other than matter."},{"class":"b97","text":" অপ্রাকৃত বলি’ কিছু নাহি পায় জ্ঞান ।<br />অপ্রাকৃত-তত্ত্ব মনে নাহি পায় স্থান ॥৬০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" aprākṛta bali’ kichhu nāhi pāya jñāna<br />aprākṛta-tattva mane nāhi pāya sthāna [60]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kichhu</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāhi</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">pāya</span>–They have no <span class=\\"e2\\">jñāna</span>–knowledge <span class=\\"e2\\">bali’</span>–regarding <span class=\\"e2\\">aprākṛta</span>–spirit, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">aprākṛta-tattva</span>–spiritual truth <span class=\\"e2\\">pāya nāhi</span>–finds no <span class=\\"e2\\">sthāna</span>–place <span class=\\"e2\\">mane</span>–in [their] hearts."},{"class":"b50","text":" “They know nothing about spirit, and there is no place for spiritual truth in their hearts."},{"class":"b97","text":" নিজে অপ্রাকৃত বস্তু তাহাও না জানে ।<br />অরক্ষিত শিশু যেন সদাই অজ্ঞানে ॥৬১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" nije aprākṛta vastu tāhāo nā jāne<br />arakṣita śiśu yena sadāi ajñāne [61]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">jāne nā</span>–They do not know <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhāo</span>–even that <span class=\\"e2\\">nije</span>–they [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">aprākṛta</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">vastu</span>–spiritual beings. <span class=\\"e2\\">yena</span>–Like <span class=\\"e2\\">arakṣita</span>–uneducated <span class=\\"e2\\">śiśu</span>–children, [they] <span class=\\"e2\\">sadāi</span>–always [remain] <span class=\\"e2\\">ajñāne</span>–ignorance."},{"class":"b50","text":" “They do not even know that they are spiritual beings. Like uneducated children, they always remain in ignorance."},{"class":"b97","text":" কোন ভাগ্যে কোন জন্মে সুকৃতির ফলে ।<br />শ্রদ্ধার উদয় হয় হৃদয়কমলে ॥৬২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kona bhāgye kona janme sukṛtira phale<br />śraddhāra udaya haya hṛdaya-kamale [62]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kona</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāgye</span>–By some good fortune, <span class=\\"e2\\">kona</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">janme</span>–in some birth, <span class=\\"e2\\">sukṛtira</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">phale</span>–as a result of sukṛti (rendering of service knowingly or unknowingly to the Lord or His paraphernalia), <span class=\\"e2\\">śraddhāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">udaya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–faith arises <span class=\\"e2\\">hṛdaya-kamale</span>–in the lotus of their hearts."},{"class":"b50","text":" “By some good fortune, in some birth, as a result of sukṛti, faith arises in the lotus of their hearts."},{"class":"b97","text":" প্রথম সন্ধানে শুনে, ‘আমি কৃষ্ণদাস’ ।<br />এ সংসার হইতে উদ্ধারে করে আশ ॥৬৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" prathama sandhāne śune, ‘āmi kṛṣṇa-dāsa’<br />e saṁsāra haite uddhāre kare āśa [63]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">prathama</span>–At first, <span class=\\"e2\\">sandhāne</span>–in the course of their search, <span class=\\"e2\\">śune</span>–they hear, <span class=\\"e2\\">‘āmi</span>–‘I [am] <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-dāsa’</span>–a servant of Kṛṣṇa’, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">āśa kare</span>–aspire <span class=\\"e2\\">uddhāre</span>–to be delivered <span class=\\"e2\\">haite</span>–from <span class=\\"e2\\">e</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">saṁsāra</span>–this world."},{"class":"b71","text":" “At first, in the course of their search, they hear, ‘I am a servant of Kṛṣṇa’, and then they aspire to be delivered from saṁsāra."},{"class":"b176","text":" কৃষ্ণার্চ্চন"},{"class":"b177","text":" kṛṣṇārchana"},{"class":"b70","text":" Worshipping Kṛṣṇa"},{"class":"b97","text":" গুরু বলে, ‘শুন, বাছা, কর কৃষ্ণার্চ্চন’ ।<br />কৃষ্ণার্চ্চনে তবে তার ইচ্ছা-সঙ্গঠন ॥৬৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" guru bale, ‘śuna, vāchhā, kara kṛṣṇārchana’<br />kṛṣṇārchane tabe tāra ichchhā-saṅgaṭhana [64]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [Their] <span class=\\"e2\\">guru</span>–Guru <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–says [to them,] <span class=\\"e2\\">‘śuna</span>–‘Listen! [My] <span class=\\"e2\\">vāchhā</span>–child, <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇārchana kara’</span>–you should worship Kṛṣṇa.’ <span class=\\"e2\\">tabe</span>–Then <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ichchhā-saṅgaṭhana</span>–they become eager <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇārchane</span>–to worship Kṛṣṇa."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Their Guru says to them, ‘Listen! My child, you should worship Kṛṣṇa’, and they then become eager to worship Kṛṣṇa."},{"class":"b97","text":" কৃষ্ণ যে অপ্রাকৃত প্রভু, এই মাত্র শুনে ।<br />কৃষ্ণস্বরূপ অপ্রাকৃত তাহা নাহি জানে ॥৬৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kṛṣṇa ye aprākṛta prabhu, ei mātra śune<br />kṛṣṇa-svarūpa aprākṛta tāhā nāhi jāne [65]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">śune</span>–They hear <span class=\\"e2\\">mātra</span>–simply <span class=\\"e2\\">ei ye</span>–that <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span>–Kṛṣṇa [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">aprākṛta</span>–spiritual [and that He is] <span class=\\"e2\\">prabhu</span>–the Lord, [but] <span class=\\"e2\\">jāne nāhi</span>–they do not understand <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhā aprākṛta kṛṣṇa-svarūpa</span>–Kṛṣṇa’s spiritual nature."},{"class":"b50","text":" “They simply hear that Kṛṣṇa is spiritual and that He is the Lord, but they do not understand Kṛṣṇa’s spiritual nature."},{"class":"b97","text":" নিজ চতুর্দিকে যাহা করে দরশনে ।<br />তঁহি মধ্যে ইষ্ট যাহা বুঝি দেখ মনে ॥৬৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" nija chatur-dike yāhā kare daraśane<br />ta̐hi madhye iṣṭa yāhā bujhi dekha mane [66]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bujhi</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">dekha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">mane</span>–They understand and regard <span class=\\"e2\\">yāhā</span>–everything <span class=\\"e2\\">ta̐hi</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">madhye</span>–within <span class=\\"e2\\">yāhā</span>–what <span class=\\"e2\\">daraśane kare</span>–they see <span class=\\"e2\\">nija</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">chatur-dike</span>–in the four directions around them [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">iṣṭa</span>–the Lord’s."},{"class":"b50","text":" “They understand that everything they see around them belongs to the Lord."},{"class":"b97","text":" ইষ্টদ্রব্যে ইষ্টমূর্ত্তির করয় পূজন ।<br />এই স্থলে হয় তার আরোপ-চিন্তন ॥৬৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" iṣṭa-dravye iṣṭa-mūrtira karaya pūjana<br />ei sthale haya tāra āropa-chintana [67]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">iṣṭa-mūrtira</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">pūjana karaya</span>–They [then] worship the Lord’s form <span class=\\"e2\\">iṣṭa-dravye</span>–with the Lord’s paraphernalia. <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sthale</span>–At this stage, <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">āropa-chintana haya</span>–they practise ascription."},{"class":"b50","text":" “They then worship the Lord’s form with the Lord’s paraphernalia. At this stage, they practise ascription."},{"class":"b97","text":" মনুষ্যমূরতি এক করিয়া গঠন ।<br />গন্ধ-পুষ্প-ধূপ-দীপে করয়ে অর্চ্চন ॥৬৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" manuṣya-mūrati eka kariyā gaṭhana<br />gandha-puṣpa-dhūpa-dīpe karaye archana [68]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">gaṭhana kariyā</span>–They make <span class=\\"e2\\">eka</span>–a <span class=\\"e2\\">manuṣya-mūrati</span>–human form [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">archana karaye</span>–worship [Him] <span class=\\"e2\\">gandha-puṣpa-dhūpa-dīpe</span>–with fragrances, flowers, incense, and lamps."},{"class":"b50","text":" “They make a human-like form of the Lord and worship Him with fragrances, flowers, incense, and lamps."},{"class":"b97","text":" আরোপ-বুদ্ধ্যে ভাবে সব অপ্রাকৃত ধন ।<br />আরোপ চিন্তিয়া কভু অপ্রাকৃতাপন ॥৬৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" āropa-buddhye bhāve saba aprākṛta dhana<br />āropa chintiyā kabhu aprākṛtāpana [69]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">āropa-buddhye</span>–By understanding ascription, <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāve</span>–they consider [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">saba</span>–everything [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">aprākṛta</span>–spiritual <span class=\\"e2\\">dhana</span>–property, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">āropa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">chintiyā</span>–by practising ascription, [they] <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu</span>–sometimes <span class=\\"e2\\">aprākṛtāpana</span>–perceive spiritual reality."},{"class":"b50","text":" “By understanding ascription, they consider that everything is spiritual property, and by practising ascription, they sometimes perceive spiritual reality."},{"class":"b97","text":" ইহাতে যে কর্ম্মার্পণ আরোপের স্থল ।<br />আরোপে ক্রমশঃ ভক্তিতত্ত্বে পায় বল ॥৭০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ihāte ye karmārpaṇa āropera sthala<br />ārope kramaśaḥ bhakti-tattve pāya bala [70]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">ye</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">karmārpaṇa</span>–The offering of actions [to the Lord] <span class=\\"e2\\">ihāte</span>–in this way [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">āropera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sthala</span>–the stage of ascription, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">ārope</span>–through ascription, [souls] <span class=\\"e2\\">kramaśaḥ</span>–gradually <span class=\\"e2\\">pāya</span>–develop <span class=\\"e2\\">bala</span>–strength <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakti-tattve</span>–in devotion."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Offering actions to the Lord in this way is the practice of ascription, and through it, souls gradually develop devotional strength."},{"class":"b97","text":" এই ত’ আরোপ-সিদ্ধা ভক্তির লক্ষণ ।<br />কনিষ্ঠাধিকারীর হয় এই সমর্চ্চন ॥৭১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ei ta’ āropa-siddhā bhaktira lakṣaṇa<br />kaniṣṭhādhikārīra haya ei samarchana [71]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ta’</span>–These [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">lakṣaṇa</span>–the characteristics <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaktira</span>–of devotion <span class=\\"e2\\">āropa-siddhā</span>–expressed through ascription. <span class=\\"e2\\">kaniṣṭhādhikārīra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ei samarchana</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–Beginners perform such worship."},{"class":"b71","text":" “These are the characteristics of ārop-siddhā devotion. Beginners perform worship in this way."},{"class":"b176","text":" তত্ত্ববোধে শ্রীমূর্ত্তি পূজা"},{"class":"b177","text":" tattva-bodhe śrī-mūrti-pūjā"},{"class":"b70","text":" Worshipping the Deity with realisation"},{"class":"b97","text":" তত্ত্বটী বুঝিয়া যবে শ্রীমূর্ত্তি পূজয় ।<br />তবে মধ্যম অধিকার হয় ত’ উদয় ॥৭২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" tattvaṭī bujhiyā yabe śrī-mūrti pūjaya<br />tabe madhyama adhikāra haya ta’ udaya [72]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">yabe</span>–When <span class=\\"e2\\">pūjaya</span>–they worship <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-mūrti</span>–the Deity <span class=\\"e2\\">bujhiyā</span>–understanding <span class=\\"e2\\">tattvaṭī</span>–the Lord’s nature, <span class=\\"e2\\">tabe</span>–then <span class=\\"e2\\">madhyama</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">adhikāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">udaya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ta’ haya</span>–they rise to the inter­mediate stage."},{"class":"b50","text":" “When beginners worship the Deity and come to understand the Lord’s nature, they rise to the intermediate stage."},{"class":"b97","text":" উত্তমাধিকারীর আরোপের নাহি স্থান ।<br />মানসে অপ্রাকৃত তত্ত্বের পায় ত’ সন্ধান ॥৭৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" uttamādhikārīra āropera nāhi sthāna<br />mānase aprākṛta tattvera pāya ta’ sandhāna [73]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">āropera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sthāna nāhi</span>–Ascription has no position <span class=\\"e2\\">uttamādhikārīra</span>–for experts: <span class=\\"e2\\">sandhāna ta’ pāya</span>–they perceive <span class=\\"e2\\">aprākṛta</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">tattvera</span>–spiritual reality [directly] <span class=\\"e2\\">mānase</span>–within [their] hearts."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Experts do not practise ascription: they directly perceive spiritual reality within their hearts."},{"class":"b97","text":" প্রেমের উদয় হয় প্রেমচক্ষে হেরি’ ।<br />প্রাণেশ্বর ভজে পূর্ব্ব-আরোপ দূর করি’ ॥৭৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" premera udaya haya prema-chakṣe heri’<br />prāṇeśvara bhaje pūrva-āropa dūra kari’ [74]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">premera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">udaya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–Divine love arises [within them, and] <span class=\\"e2\\">heri’</span>–they [begin to] see <span class=\\"e2\\">prema-chakṣe</span>–with the eyes of that love. <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaje</span>–They serve <span class=\\"e2\\">prāṇeśvara</span>–the Lord of their heart, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">dūra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kari’</span>–give up [their] <span class=\\"e2\\">pūrva-āropa</span>–previous [practice of] ascription."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Divine love arises in them, and they begin to see with the eyes of that love. They serve the Lord of their heart and give up their previous practice of ascription."},{"class":"b97","text":" ভক্তি স্বভাবতঃ নহে হেন কর্ম্মার্পণে ।<br />আরোপ-সিদ্ধা ভক্তিমধ্যে হয় ত’ গণনে ॥৭৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" bhakti svabhāvataḥ nahe hena karmārpaṇe<br />āropa-siddhā bhakti-madhye haya ta’ gaṇane [75]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">svabhāvataḥ</span>–By nature, <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakti</span>–devotion <span class=\\"e2\\">nahe</span>–is not <span class=\\"e2\\">hena</span>–like <span class=\\"e2\\">karmārpaṇe</span>–offering actions. [Still,] <span class=\\"e2\\">āropa-siddhā</span>–ascription <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–is <span class=\\"e2\\">ta’</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">gaṇane</span>–counted <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakti-madhye</span>–within devotion."},{"class":"b71","text":" “By nature, devotion is not the same as offering actions. Still, ascription is considered a type of devotion."},{"class":"b176","text":" (১) আরোপ-সিদ্ধার মূল তত্ত্ব"},{"class":"b177","text":" (1) āropa-siddhāra mūla tattva"},{"class":"b70","text":" (1) The key principle of ascription"},{"class":"b97","text":" আরোপ-সিদ্ধার এক মূলতত্ত্ব এই ।<br />জড়বস্তু, জড়কর্ম্ম ভক্তিভাবে লই ॥৭৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" āropa-siddhāra eka mūla-tattva ei<br />jaḍa-vastu jaḍa-karma bhakti-bhāve la-i [76]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">ei eka</span>–The <span class=\\"e2\\">mūla-tattva</span>–key principle <span class=\\"e2\\">āropa-siddhāra</span>–within ascription [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">la-i</span>–using <span class=\\"e2\\">jaḍa-vastu</span>–material objects [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">jaḍa-karma</span>–material actions <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakti-bhāve</span>–in a devo­tional way."},{"class":"b50","text":" “The key principle within ascription is to use material objects and actions in a devotional way."},{"class":"b97","text":" জড়বস্তু, জড়কর্ম্মমধ্যে ঘৃণ্য যাহা ।<br />অর্পণেও ভক্তি নাহি হয় কভু তাহা ॥৭৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" jaḍa-vastu, jaḍa-karma-madhye ghṛṇya yāhā<br />arpaṇeo bhakti nāhi haya kabhu tāhā [77]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">arpaṇeo</span>–By offering [the Lord], however, <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhā yāhā</span>–that which [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">ghṛṇya</span>–objectionable <span class=\\"e2\\">jaḍa-karma-madhye</span>–amongst material actions [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">jaḍa-vastu</span>–material objects, <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakti</span>–devotion <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu nāhi</span>–never <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–comes about."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Offering the Lord objectionable material objects and actions, however, is never devotion."},{"class":"b97","text":" উপাদেয় ইষ্ট বলি’ কর্ম্মার্পণ করে ।<br />‘আরোপ-সিদ্ধা ভক্তি’ বলি’ বলিব তাহারে ॥৭৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" upādeya iṣṭa bali’ karmārpaṇa kare<br />‘āropa-siddhā bhakti’ bali’ baliba tāhāre [78]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">karmārpaṇa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kare</span>–Offering actions [to the Lord] <span class=\\"e2\\">upādeya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">iṣṭa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bali’</span>–considering [them] pleasing to the Lord— <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhāre</span>–that <span class=\\"e2\\">bali’ baliba</span>–I will consider to be <span class=\\"e2\\">‘āropa-siddhā bhakti’</span>–devotion expressed through ascription."},{"class":"b50","text":" “I consider offering the Lord actions that are pleasing to Him to be ārop-siddhā devotion."},{"class":"b97","text":" মায়াবাদে অর্চ্চনাঙ্গ আরোপ-লক্ষণ ।<br />ভক্তিবাদে স্বরূপসিদ্ধা ভক্তির দর্শন ॥৭৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" māyāvāde archanāṅga āropa-lakṣaṇa<br />bhaktivāde svarūpa-siddhā bhaktira darśana [79]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">māyāvāde</span>–According to illusionist principles, <span class=\\"e2\\">archanāṅga</span>–the practice of worship [has] <span class=\\"e2\\">āropa-lakṣaṇa</span>–the characteristics of ascription, [but] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaktivāde</span>–according to devotional principles, [worship is also] <span class=\\"e2\\">darśana</span>–seen <span class=\\"e2\\">svarūpa-siddhā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaktira</span>–[as a type] of self-manifest devotion."},{"class":"b43","text":" “According to illusionist principles, worshipping the Lord is a form of ascription, but according to devotional principles, it is also seen as a type of self-manifest* devotion."},{"class":"b69","text":" * See 17.83."},{"class":"b176","text":" (২) সঙ্গ-সিদ্ধা ভক্তি"},{"class":"b177","text":" (2) saṅga-siddhā bhakti"},{"class":"b70","text":" (2) Devotion expressed as associated qualities"},{"class":"b97","text":" এবে শুন, ‘সঙ্গ-সিদ্ধা ভক্তি’ যেই রূপ ।<br />শুদ্ধজ্ঞান সুবৈরাগ্য সঙ্গসিদ্ধার স্বরূপ ॥৮০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ebe śuna, ‘saṅga-siddhā bhakti’ yei rūpa<br />śuddha-jñāna suvairāgya saṅga-siddhāra svarūpa [80]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">ebe</span>–Now <span class=\\"e2\\">śuna</span>–hear <span class=\\"e2\\">yei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">rūpa</span>–about <span class=\\"e2\\">‘saṅga-siddhā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakti’</span>–devotion expressed as associated qualities. <span class=\\"e2\\">śuddha-jñāna</span>–Pure knowledge [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">suvairāgya</span>–proper renunciation [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">svarūpa</span>–the forms <span class=\\"e2\\">saṅga-siddhāra</span>–of saṅga-siddhā [devotion]."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Now hear about saṅga-siddhā devotion. Pure knowledge and proper renunciation are themselves saṅga-siddhā devotion."},{"class":"b97","text":" যথা ভক্তি তথা যুক্তবৈরাগ্য শুদ্ধজ্ঞান ।<br />সাহচর্য্যে সঙ্গসিদ্ধ বুঝহ সন্ধান ॥৮১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" yathā bhakti tathā yukta-vairāgya śuddha-jñāna<br />sāhacharye saṅga-siddha bujhaha sandhāna [81]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">yathā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">tathā</span>–Wherever [there is] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakti</span>–devotion, [there is] <span class=\\"e2\\">śuddha-jñāna</span>–pure knowledge [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">yukta-vairāgya</span>–proper renunciation. <span class=\\"e2\\">sāhacharye</span>–With the help [of this principle], <span class=\\"e2\\">bujhaha</span>–understand <span class=\\"e2\\">sandhāna</span>–the nature <span class=\\"e2\\">saṅga-siddha</span>–of saṅga-siddhā [devotion]."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Wherever there is devotion, there is pure knowledge and proper renunciation. With this principle, understand the nature of saṅga-siddhā devotion."},{"class":"b97","text":" দৈন্য দয়া সহিষ্ণুতা ভক্তি-সহচর ।<br />সঙ্গসিদ্ধ-ভক্তি-অঙ্গ জান অতঃপর ॥৮২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" dainya dayā sahiṣṇutā bhakti-sahachara<br />saṅga-siddha-bhakti-aṅga jāna ataḥpara [82]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">dainya</span>–Humility, <span class=\\"e2\\">dayā</span>–compassion, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">sahiṣṇutā</span>–tolerance, <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakti-sahachara</span>–accompany devotion. <span class=\\"e2\\">ataḥpara</span>–From now on, <span class=\\"e2\\">jāna</span>–you know <span class=\\"e2\\">saṅga-siddha-bhakti-aṅga</span>–the limbs of saṅga-siddhā devotion."},{"class":"b71","text":" “Humility, compassion, and tolerance also accompany devotion. You now know the limbs of saṅga-siddhā devotion."},{"class":"b176","text":" (৩) স্বরূপ-সিদ্ধা ভক্তি"},{"class":"b177","text":" (3) svarūpa-siddhā bhakti"},{"class":"b70","text":" (3) Self-manifest devotion"},{"class":"b97","text":" সাক্ষাৎ ভক্তির কার্য্য যাহাতে নিশ্চয় ।<br />‘স্বরূপসিদ্ধা ভক্তি’র ক্রিয়া তাহাই হয় ॥৮৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sākṣāt bhaktira kārya yāhāte niśchaya<br />‘svarūpa-siddhā bhakti’ra kriyā tāhāi haya [83]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhāi yāhāte</span>–That by which <span class=\\"e2\\">kārya</span>–an act <span class=\\"e2\\">sākṣāt</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaktira</span>–of devotion itself <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–takes place [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">niśchaya</span>–certainly <span class=\\"e2\\">kriyā</span>–an act <span class=\\"e2\\">‘svarūpa-siddhā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakti’ra</span>–of self-manifest devotion."},{"class":"b50","text":" “An act of svarūp-siddhā devotion is an act of devotion itself."},{"class":"b97","text":" শ্রবণ-কীর্ত্তন-আদি নববিধ ভজন ।<br />স্বরূপসিদ্ধা ভক্তি বলি’ তন্নামকীর্ত্তন ॥৮৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" śravaṇa-kīrtana-ādi nava-vidha bhajana<br />svarūpa-siddhā bhakti bali’ tan-nāma-kīrtana [84]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">nava-vidha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bhajana</span>–The nine types of service— <span class=\\"e2\\">śravaṇa-kīrtana-ādi</span>–hearing, chanting, remembering, attending, worshipping, praying, serving, befriending, and surrendering— [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">bali’</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">tan-nāma-kīrtana</span>–renowned by the name <span class=\\"e2\\">svarūpa-siddhā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakti</span>–‘svarūp-siddhā devotion’."},{"class":"b50","text":" “The nine types of service—hearing, chanting, and so on—are known as svarūp-siddhā devotion."},{"class":"b97","text":" কৃষ্ণেতে সাক্ষাৎ তাহাদের মুখ্যগতি ।<br />আরোপসিদ্ধা, সঙ্গসিদ্ধার গৌণভাবে স্থিতি ॥৮৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kṛṣṇete sākṣāt tāhādera mukhya-gati<br />āropa-siddhā, saṅga-siddhāra gauṇa-bhāve sthiti [85]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhādera</span>–Their <span class=\\"e2\\">mukhya-gati</span>–main focus [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇete</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sākṣāt</span>–Kṛṣṇa Himself, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">āropa-siddhā</span>–ārop-siddhā [devotion and] <span class=\\"e2\\">saṅga-siddhāra</span>–saṅga-siddhā [devotion are] <span class=\\"e2\\">sthiti</span>–situated [within them] <span class=\\"e2\\">gauṇa-bhāve</span>–secondarily."},{"class":"b50","text":" “The main focus of these practices is Kṛṣṇa Himself, and ārop-siddhā and saṅga-siddhā devotion are present within them secondarily."},{"class":"b97","text":" স্বতঃসিদ্ধ আত্মবৃত্তি শুদ্ধভক্তিসার ।<br />বদ্ধজীবে মনোবৃত্তে উদয় তাহার ॥৮৬॥<br />কৃষ্ণোন্মুখ জড়দেহে তাহার বিস্তৃতি ।<br />এ জগতে ভক্তিদেবীর এইরূপ স্থিতি ॥৮৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" svataḥ-siddha ātma-vṛtti śuddha-bhakti sāra<br />baddha-jīve mano-vṛtte udaya tāhāra [86]"},{"class":"b60","text":" kṛṣṇonmukha jaḍa-dehe tāhāra vistṛti<br />e jagate bhakti-devīra ei-rūpa sthiti [87]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sāra</span>–The essence <span class=\\"e2\\">svataḥ-siddha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ātma-vṛtti</span>–of the natural propensity of the soul [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">śuddha-bhakti</span>–pure devotion. <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhāra udaya</span>–It arises <span class=\\"e2\\">mano-vṛtte</span>–in the mental functioning <span class=\\"e2\\">baddha-jīve</span>–of a conditioned soul [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhāra vistṛti</span>–expands [as] <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇonmukha</span>–inclination towards Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">jaḍa-dehe</span>–in [their] material body. <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakti-devīra sthiti</span>–The goddess of devotion exists <span class=\\"e2\\">e</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">jagate</span>–in this world <span class=\\"e2\\">ei-rūpa</span>–in this way."},{"class":"b71","text":" “The essence of the natural propensity of the soul is pure devotion. It arises in the mind of a conditioned soul and expands as inclination towards Kṛṣṇa within their material body. This is how the goddess of devotion exists in this world."},{"class":"b176","text":" ত্রিবিধা ভক্তির ত্রিবিধা ক্রিয়া"},{"class":"b177","text":" trividhā bhaktir trividhā kriyā"},{"class":"b70","text":" The three functions of the three types of devotion"},{"class":"b97","text":" সেই ভক্তি ‘স্বরূপসিদ্ধা’ সাক্ষাৎ ক্রিয়া যথা ।<br />‘সঙ্গসিদ্ধা’ সহচর সাহায্যে সর্ব্বথা ॥৮৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sei bhakti ‘svarūpa-siddhā’ sākṣāt kriyā yathā<br />‘saṅga-siddhā’ sahachara sāhāye sarvathā [88]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">yathā</span>–Where [there is] <span class=\\"e2\\">kriyā</span>–an act [of devotion] <span class=\\"e2\\">sākṣāt</span>–itself, <span class=\\"e2\\">sei</span>–such <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakti</span>–devotion [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">‘svarūpa-siddhā’</span>–svarūp-siddhā [devotion]. <span class=\\"e2\\">‘saṅga-siddhā’</span>–Saṅga-siddhā [devotion] <span class=\\"e2\\">sāhāye</span>–assists [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">sahachara</span>–accompanies [svarūp-siddhā devotion] <span class=\\"e2\\">sarvathā</span>–everywhere."},{"class":"b50","text":" “An act of devotion itself is svarūp-siddhā devotion. Saṅga-siddhā devotion assists and accompanies svarūp-siddhā devotion everywhere."},{"class":"b97","text":" ‘আরোপসিদ্ধা’ হয় যথা প্রাকৃত বস্তু ক্রিয়া ।<br />অপ্রাকৃত ভাবে সাধে প্রাকৃত নাশিয়া” ॥৮৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ‘āropa-siddhā’ haya yathā prākṛta vastu kriyā<br />aprākṛta bhāve sādhe prākṛta nāśiyā” [89]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">‘āropa-siddhā’</span>–Ārop-siddhā devotion <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–takes place <span class=\\"e2\\">yathā</span>–where [there are] <span class=\\"e2\\">prākṛta</span>–material <span class=\\"e2\\">vastu</span>–objects [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">kriyā</span>–actions. [When] <span class=\\"e2\\">sādhe</span>–practised <span class=\\"e2\\">aprākṛta</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāve</span>–in a spiritual manner, [it] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāśiyā</span>–conquers <span class=\\"e2\\">prākṛta”</span>–material nature.”"},{"class":"b50","text":" “Ārop-siddhā devotion is practised in connection with material objects and actions. When practised with realisation of spirit, it conquers material nature.”"},{"class":"b97","text":" স্বরূপের উপদেশে, বুঝে রঘুনাথ ।<br />পীরিতি-স্বরূপতত্ত্ব জগাইয়ের সাথ ॥৯০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" svarūpera upadeśe, bujhe raghunātha<br />pīriti-svarūpa-tattva jagāiyera sātha [90]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">upadeśe</span>–Through the advice <span class=\\"e2\\">svarūpera</span>–of Svarūp, <span class=\\"e2\\">raghunātha</span>–Raghunāth <span class=\\"e2\\">bujhe</span>–understood <span class=\\"e2\\">pīriti-svarūpa-tattva</span>–the nature of love <span class=\\"e2\\">jagāiyera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sātha</span>–in the company of Jagāi."},{"class":"b55","text":" Through Svarūp’s advice, Raghunāth understood the nature of love in the company of Jagāi."}]},{"title":"Śrī Ekādaśī","paragraphs":[{"class":"b46","text":"\\r"},{"class":"b58","text":" Chapter Eighteen"},{"class":"b120","text":" শ্রীএকাদশী"},{"class":"b121","text":" Śrī-Ekādaśī"},{"class":"b175","text":" Śrī Ekādaśī"},{"class":"b123","text":" একদিন গৌরহরি\\tশ্রীগুণ্ডিচা পরিহরি’<br />\\t‘জগন্নাথ বল্লভে’ বসিলা ।<br />শুদ্ধা একাদশী দিনে\\tকৃষ্ণনাম-সঙ্কীর্ত্তনে<br />\\tদিবস রজনী কাটাইলা ॥১॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" eka-dina gaurahari\\tśrī-guṇḍichā parihari’<br />\\t‘jagannātha-vallabhe’ vasilā<br />śuddhā ekādaśī dine\\tkṛṣṇa-nāma-saṅkīrtane<br />\\tdivasa rajanī kāṭāilā [1]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">eka-dina</span>–One day, <span class=\\"e2\\">gaurahari</span>–Gaurahari <span class=\\"e2\\">parihari’</span>–left <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-guṇḍichā</span>–Śrī Guṇḍichā [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">vasilā</span>–sat <span class=\\"e2\\">‘jagannātha-vallabhe’</span>–in the Jagannāth Vallabha garden. <span class=\\"e2\\">dine</span>–On the day <span class=\\"e2\\">śuddhā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ekādaśī</span>–of pure Ekādaśī (the day on which Ekādaśī begins before dawn), <span class=\\"e2\\">kāṭāilā</span>–the Lord spent <span class=\\"e2\\">divasa</span>–the day [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">rajanī</span>–night <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-nāma-saṅkīrtane</span>–chanting the Name of Kṛṣṇa."},{"class":"b50","text":" One day, Gaurahari left the Guṇḍichā Temple and sat in the Jagannāth Vallabha garden. It was pure Ekādaśī, and the Lord spent the whole day and night chanting the Name of Kṛṣṇa."},{"class":"b123","text":" সঙ্গে স্বরূপদামোদর\\tরামানন্দ, বক্রেশ্বর<br />\\tআর যত ক্ষেত্রবাসিগণ ।<br />প্রভু বলে, “একমনে\\tকৃষ্ণনাম-সঙ্কীর্ত্তনে<br />\\tনিদ্রাহার করিয়ে বর্জ্জন ॥২॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" saṅge svarūpa-dāmodara\\trāmānanda vakreśvara<br />\\tāra yata kṣetra-vāsi-gaṇa<br />prabhu bale, “ekamane\\tkṛṣṇa-nāma-saṅkīrtane<br />\\tnidrāhāra kariye varjana [2]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">svarūpa-dāmodara</span>–Svarūp Dāmodar, <span class=\\"e2\\">rāmānanda</span>–Rāmānanda, <span class=\\"e2\\">vakreśvara</span>–Vakreśvar, <span class=\\"e2\\">āra</span>–and <span class=\\"e2\\">yata</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kṣetra-vāsi-gaṇa</span>–other residents of Śrī Kṣetra (Jagannāth Purī) [were there] <span class=\\"e2\\">saṅge</span>–with [the Lord]. <span class=\\"e2\\">prabhu</span>–The Lord <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–said, <span class=\\"e2\\">“ekamane</span>–“Single-mindedly <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-nāma-saṅkīrtane</span>–chant the Name of Kṛṣṇa [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">varjana kariye</span>–avoid <span class=\\"e2\\">nidrāhāra</span>–sleeping and eating."},{"class":"b50","text":" Svarūp Dāmodar, Rāmānanda Rāy, Vakreśvar Paṇḍit, and the other devotees residing in Śrī Kṣetra were there with Him. The Lord said, “Single-mindedly chant the Name of Kṛṣṇa and avoid sleeping and eating."},{"class":"b123","text":" কেহ কর সঙ্খ্যানাম\\tকেহ দণ্ড-পরণাম<br />\\tকেল বল রামকৃষ্ণকথা” ।<br />যথা তথা পড়ি’ সবে\\t‘গোবিন্দ’ ‘গোবিন্দ’ রবে<br />\\tমহাপ্রেমে প্রমত্ত সর্ব্বথা ॥৩॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" keha kara saṅkhyā-nāma\\tkeha daṇḍa-paraṇāma<br />\\tkeha bala rāma-kṛṣṇa-kathā”<br />yathā tathā paḍi’ sabe\\t‘govinda’ ‘govinda’ rave<br />\\tmahāpreme pramatta sarvathā [3]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">keha</span>–Some of you <span class=\\"e2\\">kara</span>–should <span class=\\"e2\\">saṅkhyā-nāma</span>–chant japa, <span class=\\"e2\\">keha</span>–some of you [should] <span class=\\"e2\\">daṇḍa-paraṇāma</span>–offer obeisances, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">keha</span>–some of you <span class=\\"e2\\">kathā bala</span>–should speak <span class=\\"e2\\">rāma-kṛṣṇa”</span>–about Balarām and Kṛṣṇa. <span class=\\"e2\\">paḍi’</span>–Bowing <span class=\\"e2\\">yathā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">tathā</span>–wherever [they were,] <span class=\\"e2\\">sabe</span>–everyone <span class=\\"e2\\">rave</span>–chanted <span class=\\"e2\\">‘govinda’</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">‘govinda’</span>–“Govinda! Govinda!” [and became] <span class=\\"e2\\">sarvathā</span>–completely <span class=\\"e2\\">pramatta</span>–intoxicated <span class=\\"e2\\">mahāpreme</span>–with intense divine love."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Some of you should chant japa, some of you should offer obeisances, and some of you should speak about Balarām and Kṛṣṇa.” Bowing wherever they were, everyone chanted, “Govinda! Govinda!” and became completely intoxicated with intense divine love."},{"class":"b123","text":" হেন কালে গোপীনাথ\\tপড়িছা সার্ব্বভৌম সাথ<br />\\tগুণ্ডিচা-প্রসাদ লঞা আইল ।<br />অন্নব্যঞ্জন, পিঠা, পানা,\\tপরমান্ন, দধি, ছানা<br />\\tমহাপ্রভু-অগ্রেতে ধরিল ॥৪॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" hena kāle gopīnātha\\tpaḍichhā sārvabhauma sātha<br />\\tguṇḍichā-prasāda lañā āila<br />anna-vyañjana, pīṭhā, pānā,\\tparamānna, dadhi, chhānā,<br />\\tmahāprabhu-agrete dharila [4]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">hena</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kāle</span>–At that time, <span class=\\"e2\\">gopīnātha</span>–Gopīnāth, <span class=\\"e2\\">paḍichhā</span>–Tulasī Paḍichhā, <span class=\\"e2\\">sārvabhauma sātha</span>–and Sārvabhauma Bhaṭṭāchārya <span class=\\"e2\\">lañā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">āila</span>–brought <span class=\\"e2\\">guṇḍichā-prasāda</span>–prasād from the Guṇḍichā Temple. <span class=\\"e2\\">dharila</span>–They placed <span class=\\"e2\\">anna-vyañjana</span>–rice, vegetables, <span class=\\"e2\\">pīṭhā</span>–pancakes, <span class=\\"e2\\">pānā</span>–sherbert, <span class=\\"e2\\">paramānna</span>–sweet rice, <span class=\\"e2\\">dadhi</span>–yoghurt, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">chhānā</span>–curd <span class=\\"e2\\">mahāprabhu-agrete</span>–before Mahāprabhu."},{"class":"b50","text":" At that time, Gopīnāth Āchārya, Tulasī Paḍichhā, and Sārvabhauma Bhaṭṭāchārya brought prasād from the Guṇḍichā Temple. They placed rice, vegetables, pancakes, sherbert, sweet rice, yoghurt, and curd before Mahāprabhu."},{"class":"b123","text":" প্রভুর আজ্ঞায় সবে\\tদণ্ডবৎ পড়ি’ তবে<br />\\tমহাপ্রসাদ বন্দিয়া বন্দিয়া ।<br />ত্রিযামা রজনী সবে\\tমহাপ্রেমে মগ্নভাবে<br />\\tঅকৈতবে নামে কাটাইয়া ॥৫॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" prabhura ājñāya sabe\\tdaṇḍavat paḍi’ tabe<br />\\tmahāprasāda vandiyā vandiyā<br />triyāmā rajanī sabe\\tmahāpreme magna-bhāve<br />\\takaitave nāme kāṭāiyā [5]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">prabhura</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ājñāya</span>–On the Lord’s order, <span class=\\"e2\\">sabe</span>–everyone <span class=\\"e2\\">daṇḍavat</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">paḍi’</span>–bowed down [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">tabe</span>–then <span class=\\"e2\\">vandiyā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">vandiyā</span>–offered prayers <span class=\\"e2\\">mahāprasāda</span>–to the mahāprasād. <span class=\\"e2\\">sabe</span>–They <span class=\\"e2\\">kāṭāiyā</span>–spent <span class=\\"e2\\">triyāmā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">rajanī</span>–the entire night <span class=\\"e2\\">akaitave</span>–earnestly <span class=\\"e2\\">nāme</span>–chanting the Name, <span class=\\"e2\\">magna-bhāve</span>–immersed <span class=\\"e2\\">mahāpreme</span>–in intense divine love."},{"class":"b50","text":" On the Lord’s order, everyone bowed down and offered prayers to the mahāprasād. Then they spent the entire night earnestly chanting the Name, immersed in intense divine love."},{"class":"b123","text":" প্রভু-আজ্ঞা শিরে ধরি’\\tপ্রাতঃস্নান সবে করি’<br />\\tমহাপ্রসাদ সেবায় পারণ ।<br />করি’ হৃষ্ট চিত্ত সবে\\tপ্রভুর চরণে তবে<br />\\tকরযোড়ে করে নিবেদন ॥৬॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" prabhu-ājñā śire dhari’\\tprātaḥ-snāna sabe kari’<br />\\tmahāprasāda sevāya pāraṇa<br />kari’ hṛṣṭa chitta sabe\\tprabhura charaṇe tabe<br />\\tkara-yoḍe kare nivedana [6]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">dhari’</span>–Holding <span class=\\"e2\\">prabhu-ājñā</span>–the Lord’s order <span class=\\"e2\\">śire</span>–on [their] heads, <span class=\\"e2\\">sabe</span>–everyone <span class=\\"e2\\">prātaḥ-snāna</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kari’</span>–bathed in the morning, [and then] <span class=\\"e2\\">pāraṇa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kari’</span>–broke the fast <span class=\\"e2\\">sevāya</span>–by honouring <span class=\\"e2\\">mahāprasāda</span>–the mahāprasād. <span class=\\"e2\\">hṛṣṭa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">chitta</span>–With joyful hearts [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">kara-yoḍe</span>–joined palms, <span class=\\"e2\\">sabe</span>–they <span class=\\"e2\\">tabe</span>–then <span class=\\"e2\\">nivedana kare</span>–made an appeal <span class=\\"e2\\">prabhura</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">charaṇe</span>–at the feet of the Lord."},{"class":"b71","text":" Holding the Lord’s order on their heads, everyone bathed in the morning, and then broke their fast by honouring the mahāprasād. With joyful hearts and joined palms, the devotees then made an appeal at the feet of the Lord."},{"class":"b176","text":" শ্রীক্ষেত্রে শ্রীএকাদশী"},{"class":"b177","text":" śrī-kṣetre śrī-ekādaśī"},{"class":"b70","text":" Śrī Ekādaśī in Śrī Kṣetra"},{"class":"b123","text":" “সর্ব্বব্রত-শিরোমণি\\tশ্রীহরিবাসরে জানি<br />\\tনিরাহারে করি জাগরণ ।<br />জগন্নাথ-প্রসাদান্ন\\tক্ষেত্রে সর্ব্বকালে মান্য<br />\\tপাইলেই করিয়ে ভক্ষণ ॥৭॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" “sarva-vrata-śiromaṇi\\tśrī-hari-vāsare jāni<br />\\tnirāhāre kari jāgaraṇa<br />jagannātha-prasādānna\\tkṣetre sarva-kāle mānya<br />\\tpāilei kariye bhakṣaṇa [7]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">“jāni</span>–We know [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-vrata-śiromaṇi</span>–the crown jewel of all rites [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">jāgaraṇa kari</span>–staying awake [all night] <span class=\\"e2\\">nirāhāre</span>–without food or water <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-hari-vāsare</span>–on the day of the Lord (pure Ekādaśī or Mahādvādaśī) [and that] <span class=\\"e2\\">kṣetre</span>–in Śrī Kṣetra, <span class=\\"e2\\">jagannātha-prasādānna</span>–Jagannāth’s prasād <span class=\\"e2\\">mānya</span>–should be honoured <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-kāle</span>–at all times. <span class=\\"e2\\">pāilei</span>–Whenever one receives [it,] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakṣaṇa kariye</span>–one should eat [it]."},{"class":"b50","text":" “We know that the crown jewel of all rites is to stay awake all night without food or water on the day of the Lord. We also know that in Śrī Kṣetra, Jagannāth’s prasād should be honoured at all times and should be eaten whenever it is received."},{"class":"b123","text":" এ সঙ্কটে ক্ষেত্রবাসে\\tমনে হয় বড় ত্রাসে<br />\\tস্পষ্ট আজ্ঞা করিয়ে প্রার্থনা ।<br />সর্ব্ববেদ আজ্ঞা তব\\tযাহা মানে ব্রহ্মা শিব<br />\\tতাহা দিয়া ঘুচাও যাতনা” ॥৮॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" e saṅkaṭe kṣetra-vāse\\tmane haya baḍa trāse<br />\\tspaṣṭa ājñā kariye prārthanā<br />sarva-veda ājñā tava\\tyāhā māne brahmā śiva<br />\\ttāhā diyā ghuchāo yātanā” [8]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kṣetra-vāse</span>–Living in Śrī Kṣetra <span class=\\"e2\\">e</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">saṅkaṭe</span>–with this dilemma, <span class=\\"e2\\">baḍa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">trāse haya</span>–we feel great fear <span class=\\"e2\\">mane</span>–in [our] minds. [Our] <span class=\\"e2\\">prārthanā</span>–prayer [is that] <span class=\\"e2\\">spaṣṭa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ājñā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kariye</span>–You give [us] a clear instruction. <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-veda</span>–All the Vedas [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">tava</span>–Your <span class=\\"e2\\">ājñā</span>–instructions, <span class=\\"e2\\">yāhā</span>–which <span class=\\"e2\\">brahmā</span>–Brahmā [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">śiva</span>–Śiva <span class=\\"e2\\">māne</span>–follow. <span class=\\"e2\\">ghuchāo</span>–Please put an end [to our] <span class=\\"e2\\">yātanā</span>–confusion <span class=\\"e2\\">diyā</span>–by giving [us] <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhā”</span>–that [such an instruction].”"},{"class":"b71","text":" “We live in Śrī Kṣetra and are very afraid because of this dilemma, so we pray that You give us a clear instruction. All the Vedas are Your instructions, and Brahmā and Śiva follow them. Please put an end to our confusion by giving us an instruction.”"},{"class":"b176","text":" শ্রীমহাপ্রভুর বিচার"},{"class":"b177","text":" śrī-mahāprabhur vichāra"},{"class":"b70","text":" Śrīman Mahāprabhu’s conclusion"},{"class":"b123","text":" প্রভু বলে, “ভক্তি-অঙ্গে\\tএকাদশী-মান-ভঙ্গে<br />\\tসর্ব্বনাশ উপস্থিত হয় ।<br />প্রসাদ-পূজন করি’\\tপরদিনে পাইলে তরি<br />\\tতিথি পরদিনে নাহি রয় ॥৯॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" prabhu bale, “bhakti-aṅge\\tekādaśī-māna-bhaṅge<br />\\tsarva-nāśa upasthita haya<br />prasāda-pūjana kari’\\tpara-dine pāile tari<br />\\ttithi para-dine nāhi raya [9]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">prabhu</span>–The Lord <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–said, <span class=\\"e2\\">“bhakti-aṅge</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ekādaśī-māna-bhaṅge</span>–By failing to observe the devotional practice of Ekādaśī, <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-nāśa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">upasthita</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–total ruination occurs. <span class=\\"e2\\">prasāda-pūjana</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kari’</span>–If you worship the prasād [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">pāile</span>–take it <span class=\\"e2\\">para-dine</span>–the following day, <span class=\\"e2\\">tari</span>–you will cross over [this dilemma because] <span class=\\"e2\\">tithi</span>–the lunar day <span class=\\"e2\\">raya nāhi</span>–does not continue <span class=\\"e2\\">para-dine</span>–the next day."},{"class":"b50","text":" The Lord said, “Failing to observe the practice of Ekādaśī leads to total ruination. If you worship the prasād (on Ekādaśī) and take it the following day, you will cross over this dilemma because the period of Ekādaśī always ends the next day."},{"class":"b123","text":" শ্রীহরিবাসর-দিনে\\tকৃষ্ণনামরসপানে<br />\\tতৃপ্ত হয় বৈষ্ণব সুজন ।<br />অন্য রস নাহি লয়\\tঅন্য কথা নাহি কয়<br />\\tসর্ব্বভোগ করয়ে বর্জ্জন ॥১০॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" śrī-hari-vāsara-dine\\tkṛṣṇa-nāma-rasa-pāne<br />\\ttṛpta haya vaiṣṇava sujana<br />anya rasa nāhi laya\\tanya kathā nāhi kaya<br />\\tsarva-bhoga karaye varjana [10]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-hari-vāsara-dine</span>–On the day of the Lord, <span class=\\"e2\\">sujana vaiṣṇava</span>–pure devotees <span class=\\"e2\\">tṛpta</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–are satisfied <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-nāma-rasa-pāne</span>–by drinking the rasa of Kṛṣṇa’s Name. <span class=\\"e2\\">laya nāhi</span>–They do not partake <span class=\\"e2\\">anya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">rasa</span>–of any other rasa, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">kaya nāhi</span>–do not speak <span class=\\"e2\\">anya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kathā</span>–about any other subject. <span class=\\"e2\\">varjana karaye</span>–They avoid <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-bhoga</span>–all [forms of] enjoyment."},{"class":"b50","text":" “On the day of the Lord, pure devotees are satisfied by drinking the rasa of Kṛṣṇa’s Name. They do not partake of any other rasa or speak about anything else. They avoid all forms of enjoyment."},{"class":"b123","text":" প্রসাদ ভোজন নিত্য\\tশুদ্ধ বৈষ্ণবের কৃত্য<br />\\tঅপ্রসাদ না করে ভক্ষণ ।<br />শুদ্ধা একাদশী যবে\\tনিরাহার থাকে তবে<br />\\tপারণেতে প্রসাদ ভোজন ॥১১॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" prasāda bhojana nitya\\tśuddha vaiṣṇavera kṛtya<br />\\taprasāda nā kare bhakṣaṇa<br />śuddhā ekādaśī yabe \\tnirāhāra thāke tabe<br />\\tpāraṇete prasāda bhojana [11]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bhojana</span>–Taking <span class=\\"e2\\">prasāda</span>–prasād [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">nitya kṛtya</span>–the daily activity <span class=\\"e2\\">śuddha vaiṣṇavera</span>–of pure devotees; <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakṣaṇa kare nā</span>–they do not eat <span class=\\"e2\\">aprasāda</span>–non-prasād. <span class=\\"e2\\">yabe</span>–When [it is] <span class=\\"e2\\">śuddhā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ekādaśī</span>–pure Ekādaśī, <span class=\\"e2\\">nirāhāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">thāke</span>–they fast, [however, and] <span class=\\"e2\\">tabe</span>–then <span class=\\"e2\\">prasāda</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bhojana</span>–they take prasād <span class=\\"e2\\">pāraṇete</span>–to break the fast."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Taking prasād is a daily activity of pure devotees; they do not eat anything that is not prasād. On pure Ekādaśī, however, they fast and then take prasād to break their fast (the following day)."},{"class":"b123","text":" অনুকল্পস্থানমাত্র\\tনিরন্ন প্রসাদপাত্র<br />\\tবৈষ্ণবকে জানিহ নিশ্চিত ।<br />অবৈষ্ণব জন যারা\\tপ্রসাদ-ছলেতে তারা<br />\\tভোগে হয় দিবানিশি রত ।<br />পাপপুরুষের সঙ্গে\\tঅন্নাহার করে রঙ্গে<br />\\tনাহি মানে হরিবাসর-ব্রত ॥১২॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" anukalpa-sthāna-mātra\\tniranna prasāda-pātra<br />\\tvaiṣṇavake jāniha niśchita<br />avaiṣṇava jana yārā\\tprasāda-chhalete tārā<br />\\tbhoge haya divā-niśi rata<br />pāpa-puruṣera saṅge\\tannāhāra kare raṅge<br />\\tnāhi māne hari-vāsara-vrata [12]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">vaiṣṇavake jāniha</span>–Devotees should know <span class=\\"e2\\">niśchita</span>–for certain [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">mātra</span>–only <span class=\\"e2\\">niranna</span>–non-grain <span class=\\"e2\\">prasāda-pātra</span>–prasād [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">anukalpa-sthāna</span>–a supplement [acceptable on Ekādaśī]. <span class=\\"e2\\">tārā yārā</span>–Those who [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">avaiṣṇava</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">jana</span>–non-devotees <span class=\\"e2\\">bhoge rata</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–enjoy <span class=\\"e2\\">divā-niśi</span>–day and night <span class=\\"e2\\">prasāda-chhalete</span>–on the pretence of [honouring] prasād. <span class=\\"e2\\">raṅge</span>–Lightheartedly, <span class=\\"e2\\">annāhāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kare</span>–they eat grains <span class=\\"e2\\">pāpa-puruṣera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">saṅge</span>–with the association of the personification of sin [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">māne nāhi</span>–disregard <span class=\\"e2\\">hari-vāsara-vrata</span>–the rite for the day of the Lord."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Devotees should know for certain that non-grain prasād is the only supplement acceptable on Ekādaśī. Non-devotees enjoy day and night using prasād as an excuse. Lightheartedly, they eat grains in which the personification of sin is present and disregard the rite for the day of the Lord."},{"class":"b123","text":" ভক্তি-অঙ্গ সদাচার\\tভক্তির সম্মান কর<br />\\tভক্তি-দেবী-কৃপা-লাভ হবে ।<br />অবৈষ্ণবসঙ্গ ছাড়\\tএকাদশীব্রত ধর<br />\\tনামব্রতে একাদশী তবে ॥১৩॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" bhakti-aṅga sadāchāra\\tbhaktira sammāna kara<br />\\tbhakti-devī-kṛpā-lābha habe<br />avaiṣṇava-saṅga chhāḍa\\tekādaśī-vrata dhara<br />\\tnāma-vrate ekādaśī tabe [13]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaktira</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sammāna</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kara</span>–Everyone should devoutly honour [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakti-aṅga</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sadāchāra</span>–properly perform the practices of devotion. [Then] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakti-devī-kṛpā-lābha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">habe</span>–they will attain the grace of the goddess of devotion. [So,] <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍa</span>–reject <span class=\\"e2\\">avaiṣṇava-saṅga</span>–the association of non-devotees [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">dhara</span>–follow <span class=\\"e2\\">ekādaśī-vrata</span>–the Ekādaśī rite <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-vrate</span>–by following the rite of chanting the Name. <span class=\\"e2\\">tabe</span>–Then [your observance] <span class=\\"e2\\">ekādaśī</span>–of Ekādaśī [will be successful]."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Everyone should devoutly honour and properly perform the practices of devotion. Then they will attain the grace of Bhakti Devī. So, reject the association of non-devotees and follow the Ekādaśī rite by following the rite of chanting the Name. Then your observance of Ekādaśī will be successful."},{"class":"b97","text":" প্রসাদসেবন আর শ্রীহরিবাসরে ।<br />বিরোধ না করে কভু বুঝহ অন্তরে ॥১৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" prasāda-sevana āra śrī-hari-vāsare<br />virodha nā kare kabhu bujhaha antare [14]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bujhaha</span>–Understand <span class=\\"e2\\">antare</span>–within [your] heart [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">prasāda-sevana</span>–honouring prasād <span class=\\"e2\\">āra</span>–and [honouring] <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-hari-vāsare</span>–the day of the Lord <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu nā</span>–never <span class=\\"e2\\">virodha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kare</span>–conflict."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Understand within your heart that honouring prasād and honouring the day of the Lord never conflict."},{"class":"b97","text":" এক অঙ্গ মানে, আর অন্য অঙ্গে দ্বেষ ।<br />যে করে নির্ব্বোধ সেই, জানহ বিশেষ ॥১৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" eka aṅga māne, āra anya aṅge dveṣa<br />ye kare nirbodha sei, jānaha viśeṣa [15]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sei ye</span>–Those who <span class=\\"e2\\">māne</span>–follow <span class=\\"e2\\">eka</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">aṅga</span>–one practice <span class=\\"e2\\">āra</span>–and <span class=\\"e2\\">dveṣa kare</span>–disregard <span class=\\"e2\\">anya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">aṅge</span>–the other practices [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">nirbodha</span>–foolish. <span class=\\"e2\\">jānaha</span>–Know [this] <span class=\\"e2\\">viśeṣa</span>–for certain."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Those who follow one practice of devotion but disregard the others are foolish. Know this for certain."},{"class":"b97","text":" যে অঙ্গের যেই দেশকালবিধিব্রত ।<br />তাহাতে একান্তভাবে হও ভক্তিরত ॥১৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ye aṅgera yei deśa-kāla-vidhi-vrata<br />tāhāte ekānta-bhāve hao bhakti-rata [16]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">ekānta-bhāve</span>–Sincerely <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakti-rata hao</span>–devote yourself <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhāte ye</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">aṅgera</span>–to each practice <span class=\\"e2\\">yei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">deśa-kāla-vidhi-vrata</span>–according to its place, time, rules, and rites."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Sincerely devote yourself to each practice according to its place, time, rules, and rites."},{"class":"b97","text":" সর্ব্ব অঙ্গের অধিপতি ব্রজেন্দ্রনন্দন ।<br />যাহে তেঁহ তুষ্ট তাহা করহ পালন ॥১৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sarva aṅgera adhipati vrajendra-nandana<br />yāhe te̐ha tuṣṭa tāhā karaha pālana [17]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">vrajendra-nandana</span>–The prince of Vraja [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">adhipati</span>–the enjoyer <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">aṅgera</span>–of all the practices, [so] <span class=\\"e2\\">pālana karaha</span>–adhere <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhā yāhe</span>–to that by which <span class=\\"e2\\">te̐ha</span>–He [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">tuṣṭa</span>–pleased."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Kṛṣṇa is the enjoyer of all devotional practices, so adhere to what pleases Him."},{"class":"b97","text":" একাদশী-দিনে নিদ্রাহার বিসর্জ্জন ।<br />অন্য দিনে প্রসাদ নির্ম্মাল্য সুসেবন” ॥১৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ekādaśī-dine nidrāhāra visarjana<br />anya dine prasāda nirmālya susevana” [18]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">ekādaśī-dine</span>–On the day of Ekādaśī, <span class=\\"e2\\">visarjana</span>–give up <span class=\\"e2\\">nidrāhāra</span>–sleep and food, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">anya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">dine</span>–on the following day, <span class=\\"e2\\">susevana</span>–fully honour <span class=\\"e2\\">prasāda</span>–prasād [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">nirmālya”</span>–the other remnants of the Lord.”"},{"class":"b50","text":" “On the day of Ekādaśī, give up sleep and food, and on the following day, fully honour prasād and the other remnants of the Lord.”"},{"class":"b97","text":" শুনিয়া বৈষ্ণব সব\\tআনন্দে গোবিন্দরব<br />\\tদণ্ডবৎ পড়িলেন তবে ।<br />স্বরূপাদি রামানন্দ\\tপাইলেন মহানন্দ<br />\\t‘উড়িয়া’ ‘গৌড়িয়া’ ভক্ত সবে ॥১৯॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" śuniyā vaiṣṇava saba\\tānande govinda-rava<br />\\tdaṇḍavat paḍilena tabe<br />svarūpādi rāmānanda\\tpāilena mahānanda<br />\\t‘uḍiyā’ ‘gauḍiyā’ bhakta sabe [19]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">śuniyā</span>–Hearing [this,] <span class=\\"e2\\">vaiṣṇava</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">saba</span>–all the devotees <span class=\\"e2\\">ānande</span>–joyfully <span class=\\"e2\\">govinda-rava</span>–chanted, “Govinda!” [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">tabe</span>–then <span class=\\"e2\\">daṇḍavat</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">paḍilena</span>–bowed down. <span class=\\"e2\\">svarūpādi</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">rāmānanda</span>–Svarūp, Rāmānanda, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakta</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sabe</span>–all the devotees <span class=\\"e2\\">‘uḍiyā’</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">‘gauḍīyā’</span>–from Odisha and Gauḍa <span class=\\"e2\\">pāilena</span>–felt <span class=\\"e2\\">mahānanda</span>–great joy."},{"class":"b50","text":" Hearing this, all the devotees joyfully chanted, “Govinda!” and bowed down. Svarūp Dāmodar, Rāmānanda Rāy, and all the devotees from Odisha and Gauḍa were overjoyed."},{"class":"b97","text":" ওহে ভাই!<br />\\tগৌরাঙ্গ আমার প্রাণধন ।<br />অকৈতবে ভজ তাঁরে\\tযাবে তবে ভবপারে<br />\\tশীতল হইবে তনুমন ॥২০॥"},{"class":"b61","text":" ohe bhāi!<br />\\tgaurāṅga āmāra prāṇa-dhana<br />akaitave bhaja tā̐re\\tyābe tabe bhava-pāre<br />\\tśītala ha-ibe tanu-mana [20]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">ohe</span>–O <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāi!</span>–brother! <span class=\\"e2\\">gaurāṅga</span>–Gaurāṅga [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">āmāra</span>–my <span class=\\"e2\\">prāṇa-dhana</span>–life and wealth. <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaja</span>–Serve <span class=\\"e2\\">tā̐re</span>–Him <span class=\\"e2\\">akaitave</span>–sincerely. <span class=\\"e2\\">tabe</span>–Then, <span class=\\"e2\\">bhava-pāre yābe</span>–you will cross the ocean of material existence [and your] <span class=\\"e2\\">tanu-mana</span>–body and mind <span class=\\"e2\\">śītala</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-ibe</span>–will become tranquil."},{"class":"b71","text":" O brother! Gaurāṅga is my life and wealth. Serve Him sincerely. Then, you will cross the ocean of material existence and your body and mind will become tranquil."},{"class":"b176","text":" শ্রীনামভজন ও একাদশী এক"},{"class":"b177","text":" śrī-nāma-bhajana o ekādaśī eka"},{"class":"b70","text":" Serving the Name and following Ekādaśī are one"},{"class":"b97","text":" শ্রীনামভজন আর একাদশী ব্রত ।<br />এক-তত্ত্ব নিত্য জানি’ হও তাহে রত ॥২১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" śrī-nāma-bhajana āra ekādaśī-vrata<br />eka-tattva nitya jāni’ hao tāhe rata [21]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">jāni’</span>–Knowing <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-nāma-bhajana</span>–service to the Name <span class=\\"e2\\">āra</span>–and <span class=\\"e2\\">ekādaśī-vrata</span>–the Ekādaśī rite [to be] <span class=\\"e2\\">nitya</span>–eternally <span class=\\"e2\\">eka-tattva</span>–one, <span class=\\"e2\\">rata hao</span>–practise <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhe</span>–them both."},{"class":"b55","text":" Knowing service to the Name and the Ekādaśī rite to be eternally one, practise them both."}]},{"title":"A Collection of Hidden Truths about the Name","paragraphs":[{"class":"b46","text":"\\r"},{"class":"b58","text":" Chapter Nineteen"},{"class":"b120","text":" নামরহস্যপটল"},{"class":"b121","text":" Nāma-rahasya-paṭala"},{"class":"b175","text":" A Collection of <br />Hidden Truths about the Name"},{"class":"b97","text":" একদা গৌরাঙ্গচাঁদ চন্দ্রালোক পাইয়া ।<br />সমুদ্রের তীরে আইল ভক্তবৃন্দ লঞা ॥১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ekadā gaurāṅgachā̐da chandrāloka pāiyā<br />samudrera tīre āila bhakta-vṛnda lañā [1]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">ekadā</span>–Once, <span class=\\"e2\\">gaurāṅgachā̐da</span>–Gaurāṅgachā̐d, <span class=\\"e2\\">chandrāloka</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">pāiyā</span>–shining like the moon, <span class=\\"e2\\">āila</span>–came <span class=\\"e2\\">lañā</span>–with <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakta-vṛnda</span>–the devotees <span class=\\"e2\\">samudrera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">tīre</span>–to the bank of the ocean."},{"class":"b50","text":" Once, Gaurāṅgachā̐d, shining like the moon, brought the devotees to the bank of the ocean."},{"class":"b97","text":" হরিদাস-সমাজের উপকণ্ঠে বসি’ ।<br />সর্ব্ব বৈষ্ণবের প্রতি বলে গৌরশশী ॥২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" hari-dāsa-samājera upakaṇṭhe basi’<br />sarva vaiṣṇavera prati bale gaura-śaśī [2]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">basi’</span>–Sitting <span class=\\"e2\\">upakaṇṭhe</span>–in the midst <span class=\\"e2\\">hari-dāsa-samājera</span>–of the assembly of the Lord’s servants, <span class=\\"e2\\">gaura-śaśī</span>–moon-like Gaura <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–spoke <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">vaiṣṇavera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">prati</span>–to all the devotees."},{"class":"b71","text":" Sitting in the midst of the assembly of devotees, moon-like Gaura spoke to everyone."},{"class":"b176","text":" শ্রীনামই একমাত্র ও শ্রেষ্ঠ সাধন"},{"class":"b177","text":" śrī-nāma-i eka-mātra o śreṣṭha sādhana"},{"class":"b70","text":" The Holy Name is the best and only practice"},{"class":"b97","text":" “শুন হে ভকতবৃন্দ কলিকালে ধর্ম্ম ।<br />শ্রীকৃষ্ণকীর্ত্তন বিনা আর নাহি কর্ম্ম ॥৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" “śuna he bhakata-vṛnda kali-kāle dharma<br />śrī-kṛṣṇa-kīrtana vinā āra nāhi karma [3]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">“he</span>–“O <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakata-vṛnda</span>–devotees, <span class=\\"e2\\">śuna</span>–hear <span class=\\"e2\\">dharma</span>–about the religion <span class=\\"e2\\">kali-kāle</span>–in the Age of Kali: <span class=\\"e2\\">nāhi</span>–there is no <span class=\\"e2\\">karma</span>–duty <span class=\\"e2\\">vinā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">āra</span>–other than <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-kṛṣṇa-kīrtana</span>–chanting, ‘Śrī Kṛṣṇa’."},{"class":"b50","text":" “O devotees, hear about the dharma in the Age of Kali: there is no duty other than chanting the Name of Śrī Kṛṣṇa."},{"class":"b97","text":" কর্ম্ম-জ্ঞান-যোগ-ধ্যান দুর্ব্বল সাধন ।<br />অপ্রাকৃত সম্পত্তি লাভের নহে ক্রম ॥৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" karma-jñāna-yoga-dhyāna durbala sādhana<br />aprākṛta sampatti lābhera nahe krama [4]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sādhana</span>–The practices [of] <span class=\\"e2\\">karma-jñāna-yoga-dhyāna</span>–piety, knowledge, yoga, and meditation [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">durbala</span>–powerless; <span class=\\"e2\\">nahe</span>–they are not <span class=\\"e2\\">krama</span>–methods <span class=\\"e2\\">lābhera</span>–to attain <span class=\\"e2\\">aprākṛta</span>–spiritual <span class=\\"e2\\">sampatti</span>–wealth."},{"class":"b50","text":" “The practices of piety, knowledge, yoga, and meditation are powerless; they are not methods to attain spiritual wealth."},{"class":"b97","text":" ধর্ম্ম, ব্রত, ত্যাগ, হোম, সকলই প্রাকৃত ।<br />অপ্রাকৃততত্ত্ব লাভে নাহি করে হিত ॥৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" dharma, vrata, tyāga, homa sakala-i prākṛta<br />aprākṛta-tattva lābhe nāhi kare hita [5]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">dharma</span>–Virtue, <span class=\\"e2\\">vrata</span>–rites, <span class=\\"e2\\">tyāga</span>–renunciation, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">homa</span>–fire sacrifices [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">sakala-i</span>–all <span class=\\"e2\\">prākṛta</span>–mundane. <span class=\\"e2\\">hita kare nāhi</span>–They do not help [anyone] <span class=\\"e2\\">lābhe</span>–attain <span class=\\"e2\\">aprākṛta-tattva</span>–spiritual wealth."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Virtue, rites, renunciation, and fire sacrifices are all mundane. They do not help anyone attain spiritual wealth."},{"class":"b97","text":" কৃষ্ণনাম উচ্চারণে, স্মরণে, শ্রবণে ।<br />অপ্রাকৃতসিদ্ধি হয়, বলে শ্রুতিগণে ॥৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kṛṣṇa-nāma uchchāraṇe, smaraṇe, śravaṇe<br />aprākṛta-siddhi haya, bale śruti-gaṇe [6]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">śruti-gaṇe</span>–The scriptures <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–say [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">aprākṛta-siddhi</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–you will attain spiritual perfection <span class=\\"e2\\">uchchāraṇe</span>–by uttering, <span class=\\"e2\\">smaraṇe</span>–remembering, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">śravaṇe</span>–hearing <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-nāma</span>–the Name of Kṛṣṇa."},{"class":"b50","text":" “The scriptures say that you will attain spiritual perfection by uttering, remembering, and hearing the Name of Kṛṣṇa."},{"class":"b97","text":" শ্রীনামরহস্য সর্ব্বশাস্ত্রেতে দেখিবা ।<br />নাম-উচ্চারণমাত্র চিৎসুখ লভিবা ॥৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" śrī-nāma-rahasya sarva-śāstrete dekhibā<br />nāma-uchchāraṇa-mātra chit-sukha labhibā [7]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">dekhibā</span>–You will find <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-nāma-rahasya</span>–hidden truths about the Name <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-śāstrete</span>–in all the scriptures, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-uchchāraṇa-mātra</span>–simply by uttering the Name, <span class=\\"e2\\">labhibā</span>–you will feel <span class=\\"e2\\">chit-sukha</span>–spiritual joy."},{"class":"b71","text":" “You will find hidden truths about the Name in all the scriptures, and simply by uttering the Name, you will feel spiritual joy."},{"class":"b176","text":" পদ্মপুরাণে স্বর্গখণ্ড ৪৮ অধ্যায়, নামরহস্যপটলং, যথা—"},{"class":"b177","text":" padma-purāṇe svarga-khaṇḍa 48 adhyāya, nāma-rahasya-paṭalaṁ, yathā—"},{"class":"b70","text":" Hidden truths about the Name in chapter forty-eight of the Svarga-khaṇḍa in the Padma-purāṇa—"},{"class":"b97","text":" ‘শ্রীশৌনক উবাচ—<br />নামোচ্চারণমাহাত্ম্যং শ্রূয়তে মহদদ্ভুতম্ ।<br />যদুচ্চারণমাত্রেণ নরো যায়াৎ পরং পদম্ ।<br />তদ্বদস্বাধুনা সূত বিধানং নামকীর্ত্তনে ॥৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ‘śrī-śaunaka uvācha—<br />nāmochchāraṇa-māhātmyaṁ śrūyate mahad-adbhutam<br />yad uchchāraṇa-mātreṇa naro yāyāt paraṁ padam<br />tad vadasvādhunā sūta vidhānaṁ nāma-kīrtane [8]"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘Śrī Śaunaka said, “We have heard that the glories of uttering the Name are greatly astounding. Just by uttering the Name, the soul attains the supreme abode. So now, please describe the rules for chanting the Name.”"},{"class":"b97","text":" শ্রীসূত উবাচ—<br />শৃণু শৌনক বক্ষ্যামি সংবাদং মোক্ষসাধনম্ ।<br />নারদঃ পৃষ্টবান্ পূর্ব্বং কুমারং তদ্বদামি তে ॥৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" śrī-sūta uvācha—<br />śṛṇu śaunaka vakṣyāmi saṁvādaṁ mokṣa-sādhanam<br />nāradaḥ pṛṣṭavān pūrvaṁ kumāraṁ tad vadāmi te [9]"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘Śrī Sūta said, “Śaunaka, listen to me. I will recount for you a conversation about the path to liberation: I will relate to you what Nārad previously enquired about from Sanat Kumār."},{"class":"b97","text":" একদা যমুনাতীরে নিবিষ্টং শান্তমানসম্ ।<br />সনৎকুমারং পপ্রচ্ছ নারদো রচিতাঞ্জলিঃ ।<br />শ্রুত্বা নানাবিধান্ ধর্ম্মান্ ধর্ম্মব্যতিকরাংস্তথা ॥১০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ekadā yamunā-tīre niviṣṭaṁ śānta-mānasam<br />sanat-kumāraṁ paprachchha nārado rachitāñjaliḥ<br />śrutvā nānā-vidhān dharmān dharma-vyatikarāṁs tathā [10]"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘“Once, having heard about the various types of dharma and the violations against dharma, Nārad, with joined palms, enquired from the peaceful-hearted Sanat Kumār, who was seated on the bank of the Yamunā.”"},{"class":"b97","text":" শ্রীনারদ উবাচ—<br />যোঽসৌ ভগবতা প্রোক্তো ধর্ম্মব্যতিকরো নৃণাম্ ।<br />কথং তস্য বিনাশঃ স্যাদুচ্যতাং ভগবৎপ্রিয়’ ॥১১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" śrī-nārada uvācha—<br />yo ’sau bhagavatā prokto dharma-vyatikaro nṛṇām<br />kathaṁ tasya vināśaḥ syād uchyatāṁ bhagavat-priya’ [11]"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘Śrī Nārad said, “O favourite of the Lord, please tell me how the violations against dharma made by the soul that you have described may be counteracted?”’"},{"class":"b97","text":" এই পটলের অর্থ কিছু বিশেষ করিয়া ।<br />বলি স্বরূপ রামানন্দ শুন মন দিয়া ॥১২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ei paṭalera artha kichhu viśeṣa kariyā<br />bali svarūpa rāmānanda śuna mana diyā [12]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bali</span>–I will explain <span class=\\"e2\\">artha</span>–the meaning <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">paṭalera</span>–of this collection <span class=\\"e2\\">kichhu</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">viśeṣa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kariyā</span>–in detail. <span class=\\"e2\\">svarūpa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">rāmānanda</span>–O Svarūp and Rāmānanda, <span class=\\"e2\\">śuna</span>–listen <span class=\\"e2\\">mana</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">diyā</span>–attentively."},{"class":"b71","text":" [Śrīman Mahāprabhu continues:] “I will explain the meaning of this collection of verses in detail. O Svarūp and Rāmānanda, listen attentively."},{"class":"b176","text":" শ্রীনামকীর্ত্তন কি? ‘উচ্চারণ’"},{"class":"b177","text":" śrī-nāma-kīrtana ki? ‘Uchchāraṇa’"},{"class":"b70","text":" What is chanting the Name? ‘Utterance’"},{"class":"b97","text":" ‘উচ্চারণ’-শব্দে বুঝ শ্রীনামকীর্ত্তন ।<br />‘করে’ বা ‘মালায়’ সঙ্খ্যা করে ভক্তগণ ॥১৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ‘uchchāraṇa’-śabde bujha śrī-nāma-kīrtana<br />‘kare’ vā ‘mālāya’ saṅkhyā kare bhakta-gaṇa [13]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bujha</span>–Understand [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">‘uchchāraṇa’-śabde</span>–the word ‘utterance’ [means] <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-nāma-kīrtana</span>–chanting the Name. <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakta-gaṇa</span>–Devotees <span class=\\"e2\\">saṅkhyā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kare</span>–count [their chanting either] <span class=\\"e2\\">‘kare’</span>–on [their] hands <span class=\\"e2\\">vā</span>–or <span class=\\"e2\\">‘mālāya’</span>–on a rosary."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Understand that the word ‘utterance’ means chanting the Name. Devotees count their chanting either on their hands or on beads."},{"class":"b97","text":" সঙ্খ্যা ছাড়ি’ অসঙ্খ্য নাম কভু কভু হয় ।<br />‘উচ্চারণ’-শব্দে এসব জানহ নিশ্চয় ॥১৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" saṅkhyā chhāḍi’ asaṅkhya nāma kabhu kabhu haya<br />‘uchchāraṇa’-śabde e-saba jānaha niśchaya [14]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu</span>–Sometimes <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍi’</span>–they stop <span class=\\"e2\\">saṅkhyā</span>–counting [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">asaṅkhya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–chant without counting. <span class=\\"e2\\">jānaha</span>–Understand <span class=\\"e2\\">niśchaya</span>–clearly [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">‘uchchāraṇa’-śabde</span>–the word ‘utterance’ [refers to] <span class=\\"e2\\">e-saba</span>–both of these."},{"class":"b71","text":" “Sometimes they stop counting and chant the Name without counting. Understand clearly that the word ‘utterance’ refers to both of these types of chanting."},{"class":"b176","text":" জপ ও কীর্ত্তন"},{"class":"b177","text":" japa o kīrtana"},{"class":"b70","text":" Japa and kīrtan"},{"class":"b97","text":" লঘূচ্চারে ‘জপ’ হয়, উচ্চারে ‘কীর্ত্তন’ ।<br />স্মরণ-কীর্ত্তনে সব হয় ত’ গণন ॥১৫॥<br />কি প্রকারে নাম কৈলে সুকীর্ত্তন হয় ।<br />শ্রীনামকীর্ত্তনে তাহা বিধান নিশ্চয় ॥১৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" laghūchchāre ‘japa’ haya, uchchāre ‘kīrtana’<br />smaraṇa-kīrtane saba haya ta’ gaṇana [15]<br />ki prakāre nāma kaile sukīrtana haya<br />śrī-nāma-kīrtane tāhā vidhāna niśchaya [16]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">laghūchchāre</span>–Soft utterance <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–is <span class=\\"e2\\">‘japa’</span>–called <span class=\\"e33\\">japa</span>, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">uchchāre</span>–loud utterance [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">‘kīrtana’</span>–called <span class=\\"e33\\">kīrtan</span>. <span class=\\"e2\\">saba</span>–Both <span class=\\"e2\\">gaṇana ta’ haya</span>–are considered <span class=\\"e2\\">smaraṇa-kīrtane</span>–remembrance and chanting, [but] <span class=\\"e2\\">ki</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">prakāre</span>–in whatever way <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma kaile</span>–of serving the Name <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–there is <span class=\\"e2\\">sukīrtana</span>–true glorification [of the Lord,] <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhā</span>–that <span class=\\"e2\\">niśchaya</span>–certainly [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">vidhāna</span>–the proper method <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-nāma-kīrtane</span>–to glorify the Name."},{"class":"b71","text":" “Soft utterance is called <span class=\\"e3\\">japa</span>, and loud utterance is called <span class=\\"e3\\">kīrtan</span>. Both are considered ways to practise remembrance and chanting, but howsoever the Name is taken, the way of doing so in which there is true glorification of the Name is certainly the proper method to glorify the Name."},{"class":"b176","text":" কীর্ত্তন সর্ব্বথা ও সর্ব্বদা কর্ত্তব্য"},{"class":"b177","text":" kīrtana sarvathā o sarvadā kartavya"},{"class":"b70","text":" Chanting everywhere and always is our duty"},{"class":"b97","text":" শ্রীনামকীর্ত্তন হয় জীবের নিত্যধর্ম্ম ।<br />জগতে বৈকুণ্ঠে জীবের এই মুখ্য কর্ম্ম ॥১৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" śrī-nāma-kīrtana haya jīvera nitya-dharma<br />jagate vaikuṇṭhe jīvera ei mukhya karma [17]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-nāma-kīrtana</span>–Chanting the Name <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–is <span class=\\"e2\\">nitya-dharma</span>–the eternal duty <span class=\\"e2\\">jīvera</span>–of the soul: <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span>–it [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">mukhya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">karma</span>–the primary activity <span class=\\"e2\\">jīvera</span>–of the soul [both] <span class=\\"e2\\">jagate</span>–in [this] world [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">vaikuṇṭhe</span>–in the spiritual world."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Chanting the Name is the eternal duty of the soul: it is the primary activity of the soul both in this world and in the spiritual world."},{"class":"b97","text":" মায়াবদ্ধ জীবের এই মোক্ষ সাধন হয় ।<br />মুক্তজীবের পক্ষে তাহা সাধ্যাবধি রয় ॥১৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" māyā-baddha jīvera ei mokṣa sādhana haya<br />mukta-jīvera pakṣe tāhā sādhyāvadhi raya [18]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span>–It <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–is <span class=\\"e2\\">sādhana</span>–the means <span class=\\"e2\\">mokṣa</span>–to liberation <span class=\\"e2\\">māyā-baddha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">jīvera</span>–for souls conditioned by māyā, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhā</span>–it <span class=\\"e2\\">raya</span>–remains <span class=\\"e2\\">sādhyāvadhi</span>–the eternal engagement <span class=\\"e2\\">mukta-jīvera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">pakṣe</span>–of the liberated souls."},{"class":"b71","text":" “Chanting the Name is the means to liberation for the conditioned souls and is the eternal engagement of the liberated souls."},{"class":"b176","text":" ভক্তিহীন শুভকার্য ত্যাজ্য"},{"class":"b177","text":" bhakti-hīna śubha-kārya tyājya"},{"class":"b70","text":" Non-devotional pious activities should be given up"},{"class":"b97","text":" ধর্ম্মশাস্ত্র-উক্ত ভক্তিহীন ধর্ম্ম যত ।<br />ভক্ত্যুদ্দেশ বিনা আর যত প্রকার ব্রত ॥১৯॥<br />ভক্ত্যুত্থিত বিরাগ ব্যতীত যত ত্যাগ ।<br />ভক্তি-প্রতিকূল যজ্ঞ প্রাকৃত বিভাগ ॥২০॥<br />এই সব শুভকর্ম্ম সম্বন্ধ বিচারে ।<br />ভক্তি-অনুকূল বলি’ শাস্ত্রেতে প্রচারে ॥২১॥<br />কলিকালে সেই সব জড়ধর্ম্ম হইল ।<br />ভক্তি-আনুকূল্য ত্যজি’ ধর্ম্ম নষ্ট ভেল ॥২২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" dharma-śāstra-ukta bhakti-hīna dharma yata<br />bhakty-uddeśa vinā āra yata prakāra vrata [19]<br />bhakty-utthita virāga vyatīta yata tyāga<br />bhakti-pratikūla yajña prākṛta vibhāga [20]<br />ei saba śubha-karma sambandha vichāre<br />bhakti-anukūla bali’ śāstrete prachāre [21]<br />kali-kāle sei saba jaḍa-dharma ha-ila<br />bhakti-ānukūlya tyaji’ dharma naṣṭa bhela [22]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">yata</span>–All <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakti-hīna</span>–non-devotional <span class=\\"e2\\">dharma</span>–duties <span class=\\"e2\\">dharma-śāstra-ukta</span>–mentioned in the religious scriptures, <span class=\\"e2\\">yata</span>–all <span class=\\"e2\\">prakāra</span>–sorts <span class=\\"e2\\">vrata</span>–of rites <span class=\\"e2\\">vinā</span>–apart from [those with] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakty-uddeśa</span>–a devotional purpose, <span class=\\"e2\\">yata</span>–all [forms of] <span class=\\"e2\\">tyāga</span>–renunciation <span class=\\"e2\\">vyatīta</span>–devoid <span class=\\"e2\\">virāga</span>–of detachment <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakty-utthita</span>–produced by devotion, <span class=\\"e2\\">āra</span>–and <span class=\\"e2\\">vibhāga</span>–the section of <span class=\\"e2\\">yajña</span>–sacrifices [that are] <span class=\\"e2\\">prākṛta</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">vibhāga</span>–mundane [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakti-pratikūla</span>–unfavourable to devotion— <span class=\\"e2\\">śāstrete</span>–the scriptures <span class=\\"e2\\">bali’ prachāre</span>–state [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">saba</span>–all of these <span class=\\"e2\\">śubha-karma</span>–pious activities [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakti-anukūla</span>–favourable to devotion <span class=\\"e2\\">vichāre</span>–by assessment [of their] <span class=\\"e2\\">sambandha</span>–connection [with the Lord]. <span class=\\"e2\\">kali-kāle</span>–In the Age of Kali, [however,] <span class=\\"e2\\">sei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">saba</span>–they all <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-ila</span>–have become <span class=\\"e2\\">jaḍa-dharma</span>–material activities; <span class=\\"e2\\">tyaji’</span>–losing [their] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakti-ānukūlya</span>–favourableness to devotion, <span class=\\"e2\\">dharma</span>–such duties <span class=\\"e2\\">bhela</span>–have become <span class=\\"e2\\">naṣṭa</span>–corrupted."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Non-devotional duties mentioned in the religious scriptures, rites that do not have a devotional purpose, renunciation that is not an expression of detachment produced by devotion, and mundane, non-devotional sacrifices—the scriptures say that all of these pious activities are favourable to devotion because they have some connection with the Lord. In the Age of Kali, however, they have all become material activities; losing their favourableness to devotion, they have all become corrupted."},{"class":"b97","text":" অতএব কলিকালে নামসঙ্কীর্ত্তন ।<br />বিনা আর ধর্ম্ম নাই শুন ভক্তগণ ॥২৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ataeva kali-kāle nāma-saṅkīrtana<br />vinā āra dharma nāi śuna bhakta-gaṇa [23]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">ataeva</span>–So, <span class=\\"e2\\">kali-kāle</span>–in the Age of Kali, <span class=\\"e2\\">nāi</span>–there is no <span class=\\"e2\\">dharma</span>–duty <span class=\\"e2\\">vinā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">āra</span>–other than <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-saṅkīrtana</span>–chanting the Name. <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakta-gaṇa</span>–O devotees, <span class=\\"e2\\">śuna</span>–listen!"},{"class":"b50","text":" “So, in the Age of Kali, there is no duty other than chanting the Name. O devotees, listen!"},{"class":"b97","text":" সে ধর্ম্মের ব্যতিকর যাহাই দেখিবে ।<br />তাহাই বর্জ্জিবে যত্নে ভক্তির প্রভাবে ॥২৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" se dharmera vyatikara yāhāi dekhibe<br />tāhāi varjibe yatne bhaktira prabhāve [24]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaktira</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">prabhāve</span>–With the strength produced by devotion, <span class=\\"e2\\">yatne</span>–carefully <span class=\\"e2\\">varjibe</span>–avoid <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhāi</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">yāhāi</span>–all <span class=\\"e2\\">vyatikara</span>–violations <span class=\\"e2\\">se</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">dharmera</span>–against this duty [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">dekhibe</span>–you find."},{"class":"b50","text":" “With the strength produced by devotion, carefully avoid all violations against chanting the Name that you find."},{"class":"b97","text":" ‘শ্রীসনৎকুমার উবাচ—<br />শৃণু নারদ গোবিন্দপ্রিয় গোবিন্দধর্ম্মবিৎ ।<br />যৎ পৃষ্টং লোকনির্ম্মুক্তিকারণং তমসঃ পরম্’ ॥২৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ‘śrī-sanat-kumāra uvācha—<br />śṛṇu nārada govinda-priya govinda-dharma-vit<br />yat pṛṣṭaṁ loka-nirmukti-kāraṇaṁ tamasaḥ param’ [25]"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘Śrī Sanat Kumār said, “Listen, O Nārad, favourite of Govinda, expert in the service of Govinda! You have asked about the cause of being liberated from this world and overcoming ignorance.”’"},{"class":"b97","text":" তুমি ত’ নারদ শ্রীগোবিন্দধর্ম্মবেত্তা ।<br />গোবিন্দের প্রিয়, মায়াবন্ধনের ছেত্তা ॥২৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" tumi ta’ nārada śrī-govinda-dharma-vettā<br />govindera priya, māyā-bandhanera chhettā [26]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">nārada</span>–O Nārad, <span class=\\"e2\\">tumi</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ta’</span>–You [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-govinda-dharma-vettā</span>–an expert in the service of Śrī Govinda. [You are] <span class=\\"e2\\">govindera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">priya</span>–dear to Govinda, [and you are] <span class=\\"e2\\">chhettā</span>–the cutter <span class=\\"e2\\">māyā-bandhanera</span>–of [the soul’s] bondage within illusion."},{"class":"b50","text":" [Śrīman Mahāprabhu paraphrases:] “O Nārad, you are an expert in the service of Śrī Govinda. You are dear to Govinda, and you cut away the soul’s bondage within illusion."},{"class":"b97","text":" লোকনির্ম্মুক্তির হেতু জিজ্ঞাসা তোমার ।<br />তব প্রশ্নোত্তরে জীব হবে তমঃ পার ॥২৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" loka-nirmuktira hetu jijñāsā tomāra<br />tava praśnottare jīva habe tamaḥ pāra [27]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">tomāra</span>–Your <span class=\\"e2\\">jijñāsā</span>–question [is about] <span class=\\"e2\\">hetu</span>–the cause <span class=\\"e2\\">loka-nirmuktira</span>–of liberation from this world. <span class=\\"e2\\">jīva</span>–Souls <span class=\\"e2\\">pāra habe</span>–will overcome <span class=\\"e2\\">tamaḥ</span>–ignorance <span class=\\"e2\\">tava</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">praśnottare</span>–through the answer to your question."},{"class":"b50","text":" “You have asked about the cause of liberation from this world. Souls will overcome ignorance through the answer to your question."},{"class":"b97","text":" কলিতে সকল ধর্ম্মাধর্ম্ম তমোময় ।<br />নামধর্ম্ম বিনা জীবের সংসার নহে ক্ষয় ॥২৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kalite sakala dharmādharma tamomaya<br />nāma-dharma vinā jīvera saṁsāra nahe kṣaya [28]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kalite</span>–In the Age of Kali, <span class=\\"e2\\">sakala</span>–all <span class=\\"e2\\">dharmādharma</span>–religion and irreligion [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">tamomaya</span>–filled with ignorance. <span class=\\"e2\\">vinā</span>–Without <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-dharma</span>–the religion of [chanting] the Name, <span class=\\"e2\\">jīvera</span>–the soul’s <span class=\\"e2\\">saṁsāra</span>–entanglement in this world <span class=\\"e2\\">nahe</span>–is not <span class=\\"e2\\">kṣaya</span>–destroyed."},{"class":"b71","text":" “In the Age of Kali, all forms of religion and irreligion are filled with ignorance. Without chanting the Name, the soul’s entanglement in this world cannot be destroyed."},{"class":"b176","text":" অতএব নামে সর্ব্বপাপক্ষয়"},{"class":"b177","text":" ataeva nāme sarva-pāpa-kṣaya"},{"class":"b70","text":" So, the Name destroys all sins"},{"class":"b97","text":" ‘সর্ব্বাচারবিবর্জ্জিতাঃ শঠধিয়ো ব্রাত্যা জগদ্বঞ্চকাঃ<br />দম্ভাহঙ্কৃতিপানপৈশুন্যপরাঃ পাপাশ্চ যে নিষ্ঠুরাঃ ।<br />যে চান্যে ধনদারপুত্রনিরতাঃ সর্ব্বেঽধমাস্তেঽপি হি<br />শ্রীগোবিন্দপদারবিন্দশরণাঃ শুদ্ধা ভবন্তি দ্বিজ’ ॥২৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ‘sarvāchāra-vivarjitāḥ śaṭha-dhiyo vrātyā jagad-vañchakāḥ<br />dambhāhaṅkṛti-pāna-paiśunya-parāḥ pāpāś cha ye niṣṭhurāḥ<br />ye chānye dhana-dāra-putra-niratāḥ sarve ’dhamās te ’pi hi<br />śrī-govinda-padāravinda-śaraṇāḥ śuddhā bhavanti dvija’ [29]"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘[Śrī Sanat Kumār said:] “O brāhmaṇ, persons who are devoid of all virtues, deceitful, uncultured, fraudulent, arrogant, egotistical, addicted to intoxicants, sinful, malicious, cruel-natured, and grossly infatuated with son, wife, wealth, and so forth—even such extremely fallen persons are purified by surrendering to the lotus feet of Śrī Govinda.”’"},{"class":"b97","text":" শ্রীগোবিন্দপদারবিন্দ শরণ যে লয় ।<br />তার সর্ব্বপাপ নামে নিশ্চয় হয় ক্ষয় ॥৩০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" śrī-govinda-padāravinda śaraṇa ye laya<br />tāra sarva-pāpa nāme niśchaya haya kṣaya [30]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-pāpa</span>–All the sins <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra ye</span>–of those who <span class=\\"e2\\">laya</span>–take <span class=\\"e2\\">śaraṇa</span>–shelter <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-govinda-padāravinda</span>–at the lotus feet of Śrī Govinda <span class=\\"e2\\">niśchaya</span>–certainly <span class=\\"e2\\">kṣaya haya</span>–are destroyed <span class=\\"e2\\">nāme</span>–by the Name."},{"class":"b50","text":" [Śrīman Mahāprabhu paraphrases:] “The Name certainly destroys all the sins of those who take shelter at the lotus feet of Śrī Govinda."},{"class":"b97","text":" কৃষ্ণনাম লয়ে কাঁদে, নিজ দোষ বলে ।<br />অতি শীঘ্র তার পাপ যায় ভক্তিবলে ॥৩১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kṛṣṇa-nāma laye kā̐de, nija doṣa bale<br />ati śīghra tāra pāpa yāya bhakti-bale [31]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">pāpa</span>–The sins <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra</span>–of those who <span class=\\"e2\\">laye</span>–chant <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-nāma</span>–Kṛṣṇa’s Name, <span class=\\"e2\\">kā̐de</span>–cry, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–confess <span class=\\"e2\\">nija</span>–their <span class=\\"e2\\">doṣa</span>–sins <span class=\\"e2\\">yāya</span>–go away <span class=\\"e2\\">ati</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">śīghra</span>–very quickly <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakti-bale</span>–by the power of devotion."},{"class":"b71","text":" “The sins of those who chant Kṛṣṇa’s Name, crying and repenting for their faults, are very quickly driven away by the power of devotion."},{"class":"b176","text":" কর্ম্মপ্রায়শ্চিত্তে বাসনা নষ্ট হয় না"},{"class":"b177","text":" karma-prāyaśchitte vāsanā naṣṭa haya nā"},{"class":"b70","text":" Pious atonements do not destroy material desire"},{"class":"b97","text":" কর্ম্মজ্ঞান-প্রায়শ্চিত্তে তার কিবা ফল ।<br />সে ফল দুর্ব্বল অতি, তার নাহি বল ॥৩২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" karma-jñāna-prāyaśchitte tāra kibā phala<br />se phala durbala ati, tāra nāhi bala [32]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kibā</span>–What [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">phala</span>–the results <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra karma-jñāna-prāyaśchitte</span>–of atonements made through piety or knowledge? <span class=\\"e2\\">se</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">phala</span>–The results [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">ati durbala</span>–extremely weak. <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāhi</span>–They have no <span class=\\"e2\\">bala</span>–power."},{"class":"b50","text":" “What are the results of atonements made through piety or knowledge? The results are extremely weak; they have no power at all."},{"class":"b97","text":" এক কৃষ্ণনামে পাপীর যত পাপক্ষয় ।<br />বহু জন্মে সেই পাপী করিতে নারয় ॥৩৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" eka kṛṣṇa-nāme pāpīra yata pāpa-kṣaya<br />bahu janme sei pāpī karite nāraya [33]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [But] <span class=\\"e2\\">sei pāpī</span>–a sinner <span class=\\"e2\\">karite nāraya</span>–cannot commit <span class=\\"e2\\">bahu</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">janme</span>–over the course of many births <span class=\\"e2\\">yata</span>–as many <span class=\\"e2\\">pāpa</span>–sins [as are] <span class=\\"e2\\">kṣaya</span>–destroyed <span class=\\"e2\\">pāpīra</span>–for a sinner [by] <span class=\\"e2\\">eka</span>–one <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-nāme</span>–Name of Kṛṣṇa."},{"class":"b50","text":" “But a sinner cannot commit over the course of many births as many sins as one Name of Kṛṣṇa can destroy."},{"class":"b97","text":" হেন পাপ স্মার্ত্তশাস্ত্রে না আছে বর্ণন ।<br />এক কৃষ্ণনামে যাহা না হয় খণ্ডন ॥৩৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" hena pāpa smārta-śāstre nā āchhe varṇana<br />eka kṛṣṇa-nāme yāhā nā haya khaṇḍana [34]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">āchhe nā</span>–There is no <span class=\\"e2\\">hena</span>–such <span class=\\"e2\\">pāpa</span>–sin <span class=\\"e2\\">varṇana</span>–mentioned <span class=\\"e2\\">smārta-śāstre</span>–in the smārta scriptures (the scriptures that explain codes of piety and rites of atonement) <span class=\\"e2\\">yāhā</span>–that <span class=\\"e2\\">eka</span>–one <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-nāme</span>–Name of Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">khaṇḍana haya nā</span>–does not counteract."},{"class":"b50","text":" “There is no sin mentioned in the smārta scriptures that one Name of Kṛṣṇa does not counteract."},{"class":"b97","text":" তবে কেন স্মার্ত্তলোক প্রায়শ্চিত্ত করে ।<br />সুকৃতি-অভাবে তার কর্ম্মে মতি হরে ॥৩৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" tabe kena smārta-loka prāyaśchitta kare<br />sukṛti-abhāve tāra karme mati hare [35]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">tabe</span>–So <span class=\\"e2\\">kena</span>–why [do] <span class=\\"e2\\">smārta-loka</span>–the followers of the smārta scriptures <span class=\\"e2\\">prāyaśchitta</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kare</span>–perform atonements? [Because they have] <span class=\\"e2\\">sukṛti-abhāve</span>–a lack of spiritual fortune [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">karme</span>–the reactions to their actions <span class=\\"e2\\">hare</span>–take away [their] <span class=\\"e2\\">mati</span>–intelligence."},{"class":"b50","text":" “So why do the followers of the smārta scriptures perform rites of atonement for their sins (instead of chanting the Name)? Because they lack spiritual fortune and their karma deludes their intelligence."},{"class":"b97","text":" কর্ম্ম-প্রায়শ্চিত্তে কভু বাসনা না যায় ।<br />জ্ঞান-প্রায়শ্চিত্তে শোধে বাসনা হিয়ায় ॥৩৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" karma-prāyaśchitte kabhu vāsanā nā yāya<br />jñāna-prāyaśchitte śodhe vāsanā hiyāya [36]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">vāsanā</span>–Material desires <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu nā</span>–never <span class=\\"e2\\">yāya</span>–go away <span class=\\"e2\\">karma-prāyaśchitte</span>–through atonement made through pious activities. <span class=\\"e2\\">jñāna-prāyaśchitte</span>–Atonement made through knowledge <span class=\\"e2\\">śodhe</span>–counteracts <span class=\\"e2\\">vāsanā</span>–material desires <span class=\\"e2\\">hiyāya</span>–within the heart."},{"class":"b71","text":" “Atonement made by performing pious activities does not remove material desires. Atonement made through knowledge does counteract material desires within the heart."},{"class":"b176","text":" বাসনার মূল অবিদ্যা ভক্তিতে বিনষ্ট হয়"},{"class":"b177","text":" vāsanāra mūla avidyā bhaktite vinaṣṭa haya"},{"class":"b70","text":" Devotion destroys ignorance, the root of material desire"},{"class":"b97","text":" পুনঃ কিছুদিনে সে বাসনা হয় স্থূল ।<br />ভক্তিতে অবিদ্যা যায় বাসনার মূল ॥৩৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" punaḥ kichhu-dine se vāsanā haya sthūla<br />bhaktite avidyā yāya vāsanāra mūla [37]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kichhu-dine</span>–After some time, [however,] <span class=\\"e2\\">se</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">vāsanā</span>–those material desires <span class=\\"e2\\">sthūla haya</span>–swell <span class=\\"e2\\">punaḥ</span>–again. <span class=\\"e2\\">avidyā</span>–Ignorance, <span class=\\"e2\\">mūla</span>–the root <span class=\\"e2\\">vāsanāra</span>–of material desire, <span class=\\"e2\\">yāya</span>–goes away [only] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaktite</span>–through devotion."},{"class":"b50","text":" “After some time, however, those material desires swell in the heart again. Only devotion removes ignorance, the root cause of material desire."},{"class":"b97","text":" যে জন গোবিন্দপদে লইয়া শরণ ।<br />নাম লয় কাকুভরে করয় রোদন ॥৩৮॥<br />তার পক্ষে শ্রীমুখের বাক্য সুমধুর ।<br />জীবের মঙ্গল, গীতায় দেখহ প্রচুর ॥৩৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ye jana govinda-pade la-iyā śaraṇa<br />nāma laya kāku-bhare karaya rodana [38]<br />tāra pakṣe śrī-mukhera vākya sumadhura<br />jīvera maṅgala, gītāya dekhaha prachura [39]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">vākya</span>–The words <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-mukhera</span>–from the divine mouth [of Govinda are] <span class=\\"e2\\">sumadhura</span>–supremely sweet <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">pakṣe ye</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">jana</span>–to the souls who <span class=\\"e2\\">la-iyā</span>–take <span class=\\"e2\\">śaraṇa</span>–shelter <span class=\\"e2\\">govinda-pade</span>–at the feet of Govinda, <span class=\\"e2\\">laya</span>–chant [His] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–Name, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">kāku-bhare</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">rodana karaya</span>–cry out [to Him] in prayer. <span class=\\"e2\\">dekhaha</span>–See <span class=\\"e2\\">prachura</span>–many [of such words, spoken for] <span class=\\"e2\\">jīvera maṅgala</span>–the benefit of all souls, <span class=\\"e2\\">gītāya</span>–in <span class=\\"e33\\">Śrī Gītā</span>."},{"class":"b71","text":" “The words from the divine mouth of Śrī Govinda are supremely sweet to the souls who take shelter at His feet, chant His Name, and cry out to Him in prayer. You will find many of His words, spoken for the benefit of all souls, in <span class=\\"e3\\">Śrī Gītā</span>."},{"class":"b176","text":" শ্রীগীতা—"},{"class":"b177","text":" śrī gītā—"},{"class":"b70","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">Śrī Gītā—</span>"},{"class":"b97","text":" ‘সর্ব্বধর্ম্মান্ পরিত্যজ্য মামেকং শরণং ব্রজ ।<br />অহং ত্বাং সর্ব্বপাপেভ্যো মোক্ষয়িষ্যামি মা শুচঃ ॥৪০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ‘sarva-dharmān parityajya mām ekaṁ śaraṇaṁ vraja<br />ahaṁ tvāṁ sarva-pāpebhyo mokṣayiṣyāmi mā śuchaḥ [40]"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘Abandon all duties and surrender exclusively unto Me. I will liberate you from all sin. Do not despair."},{"class":"b97","text":" অপি চেৎ সুদুরাচারো ভজতে মামনন্যভাক্ ।<br />সাধুরেব স মন্তব্যঃ সম্যগ্ব্যবসিতো হি সঃ ॥৪১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" api chet sudurāchāro bhajate mām ananya-bhāk<br />sādhur eva sa mantavyaḥ samyag vyavasito hi saḥ [41]"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘If even a very sinful person serves Me exclusively with devotion, he should be regarded as saintly, for his resolve is perfect."},{"class":"b97","text":" ক্ষিপ্রং ভবতি ধর্ম্মাত্মা শাশ্বচ্ছান্তিং নিগচ্ছতি ।<br />কৌন্তেয় প্রতিজানীহি ন মে ভক্তঃ প্রণশ্যতি’ ॥৪২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kṣipraṁ bhavati dharmātmā śāśvach-chhāntiṁ nigachchhati<br />kaunteya pratijānīhi na me bhaktaḥ praṇaśyati’ [42]"},{"class":"b71","text":" “‘He swiftly becomes a person of virtuous practices and attains constant peace. O son of Kuntī, declare to the world that My devotee is never vanquished!”’"},{"class":"b97","text":" অতএব কর্ম্মাঙ্গ প্রায়শ্চিত্তাদি পরিহরি’ ।<br />বুদ্ধিমান্ জন ভজে প্রাণেশ্বর হরি ॥৪৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ataeva karmāṅga prāyaśchittādi parihari’<br />buddhimān jana bhaje prāṇeśvara hari [43]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">ataeva</span>–So, <span class=\\"e2\\">buddhimān</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">jana</span>–the intelligent souls <span class=\\"e2\\">parihari’</span>–give up [performing] <span class=\\"e2\\">karmāṅga</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">prāyaśchittādi</span>–atonement and other worldly rites, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaje</span>–serve <span class=\\"e2\\">hari</span>–Hari, <span class=\\"e2\\">prāṇeśvara</span>–the Lord of [their] heart."},{"class":"b71","text":" [Śrīman Mahāprabhu paraphrases:] “So, the intelligent souls give up atoning for their sins through worldly rites, and serve Hari, the Lord of their heart."},{"class":"b176","text":" অতএব নামের ফল"},{"class":"b177","text":" ataeva nāmera phala"},{"class":"b70","text":" So, the Name’s effect"},{"class":"b97","text":" ‘তমপি দেবকরং করুণাকরং<br />স্থাবর-জঙ্গম-মুক্তিকরং পরম্ ।<br />অতিচরন্ত্যপরাধপরা জনা <br />য ইহ তান্বপতি ধ্রুবনাম হি’ ॥৪৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ‘tam api devakaraṁ karuṇākaraṁ<br />sthāvara-jaṅgama-muktikaraṁ param<br />aticharanty aparādha-parā janā<br />ya iha tān vapati dhruva-nāma hi’ [44]"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘[Sanat Kumār said:] “The eternal Name—the source of divinity, the fountain of mercy, the supreme giver of liberation to both moving and inert beings—certainly removes the sins of the offenders who go against Him.”’"},{"class":"b97","text":" কৃষ্ণনাম দয়াময় কৃষ্ণতেজোময় ।<br />স্থাবর-জঙ্গম-মুক্তিদাতা সুনিশ্চয় ॥৪৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kṛṣṇa-nāma dayāmaya kṛṣṇa-tejo-maya<br />sthāvara-jaṅgama-mukti-dātā suniśchaya [45]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-nāma</span>–The Name of Kṛṣṇa [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">dayāmaya</span>–compassionate, <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-tejo-maya</span>–filled with Kṛṣṇa’s power, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">suniśchaya</span>–certainly <span class=\\"e2\\">sthāvara-jaṅgama-mukti-dātā</span>–the giver of liberation to all moving and inert beings."},{"class":"b50","text":" [Śrīman Mahāprabhu paraphrases:] “The Name of Kṛṣṇa is compassionate, filled with Kṛṣṇa’s power, and certainly the giver of liberation to all moving and inert beings."},{"class":"b97","text":" নাম-অপরাধী তাহে করে অপরাধ ।<br />অতিচার আসি’ নাম-ধর্ম্মে করে বাধ ॥৪৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" nāma-aparādhī tāhe kare aparādha<br />atichāra āsi’ nāma-dharme kare bādha [46]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-aparādhī</span>–Offenders of the Name <span class=\\"e2\\">aparādha kare</span>–commit offences <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhe</span>–against Him, [and such] <span class=\\"e2\\">atichāra</span>–violations <span class=\\"e2\\">āsi’</span>–come [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">bādha kare</span>–check <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-dharme</span>–[their] practice of [chanting] the Name."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Offenders of the Name commit offences against Him, and such violations check their chanting of the Name."},{"class":"b97","text":" সেই মহা-অপরাধীর দোষ, নামে হয় ক্ষয় ।<br />নাম বিনা জীববন্ধু জগতে না হয় ॥৪৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sei mahā-aparādhīra doṣa, nāme haya kṣaya<br />nāma vinā jīva-bandhu jagate nā haya [47]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sei</span>–The <span class=\\"e2\\">doṣa</span>–sins <span class=\\"e2\\">mahā-aparādhīra</span>–of such great offenders <span class=\\"e2\\">kṣaya haya</span>–are destroyed, [however,] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāme</span>–by the Name. <span class=\\"e2\\">vinā</span>–Other than <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–the Name, <span class=\\"e2\\">haya nā</span>–there is no <span class=\\"e2\\">jīva-bandhu</span>–friend of the soul <span class=\\"e2\\">jagate</span>–in this world."},{"class":"b50","text":" “The Name, however, destroys the sins of even such great offenders. Other than the Name, the soul has no friend in this world."},{"class":"b97","text":" ‘শ্রীনারদ উবাচ—<br />কে তেঽপরাধা বিপ্রেন্দ্র নাম্নো ভগবতঃ কৃতা ।<br />বিনিঘ্নন্তি নৃণাং কৃত্যং প্রাকৃতং হ্যানয়ন্তি চ’ ॥৪৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ‘śrī-nārada uvācha—<br />ke te ’parādhā viprendra nāmno bhagavataḥ kṛtā<br />vinighnanti nṛṇāṁ kṛtyaṁ prākṛtaṁ hy ānayanti cha’ [48]"},{"class":"b71","text":" “‘Nārad asked Sanat Kumār: “O best of the brāhmaṇs, what are the offences against the Lord’s Name that destroy and drag the mundane into the soul’s chanting of the Name?”’"},{"class":"b176","text":" নামাপরাধ"},{"class":"b177","text":" nāmāparādha"},{"class":"b70","text":" Offences to the Name"},{"class":"b97","text":" ওহে গুরু সনৎকুমার কৃপা করি’ বল ।<br />নামে অপরাধ যত প্রকার সকল ॥৪৯॥<br />নামরূপ মহাকৃত্য জীবের নিশ্চয় ।<br />সেই কৃত্য যাহে সাধকের নষ্ট হয় ॥৫০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ohe guru sanat-kumāra kṛpā kari’ bala<br />nāme aparādha yata prakāra sakala [49]<br />nāma-rūpa mahākṛtya jīvera niśchaya<br />sei kṛtya yāhe sādhakera naṣṭa haya [50]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">ohe</span>–O <span class=\\"e2\\">guru</span>–Guru, <span class=\\"e2\\">sanat-kumāra</span>–Sanat Kumār, [chanting] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-rūpa</span>–the form of the Name [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">niśchaya</span>–certainly <span class=\\"e2\\">mahākṛtya</span>–the foremost duty <span class=\\"e2\\">jīvera</span>–of the soul. <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛpā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kari’</span>–Mercifully <span class=\\"e2\\">bala</span>–tell [me] <span class=\\"e2\\">yata sakala</span>–all the <span class=\\"e2\\">prakāra</span>–types <span class=\\"e2\\">aparādha</span>–of offences <span class=\\"e2\\">nāme</span>–to the Name, <span class=\\"e2\\">yāhe</span>–by which <span class=\\"e2\\">sei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sādhakera kṛtya</span>–this duty of the practitioner <span class=\\"e2\\">naṣṭa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–is destroyed."},{"class":"b50","text":" [Śrīman Mahāprabhu paraphrases:] “O Gurudev, Sanat Kumār, chanting the Name is certainly the foremost duty of the soul. Mercifully tell me all the offences to the Name, which destroy the practitioner’s performance of that duty."},{"class":"b97","text":" নামকে প্রাকৃত করি’ সাধন করাঞা ।<br />সামান্য প্রাকৃত ফলে দেয় ফেলাইয়া ॥৫১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" nāmake prākṛta kari’ sādhana karāñā<br />sāmānya prākṛta phale deya phelāiyā [51]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [Offences] <span class=\\"e2\\">kari’</span>–make <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmake</span>–the Name <span class=\\"e2\\">prākṛta</span>–mundane [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">sādhana</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">karāñā</span>–make [a practitioner] practise [but] <span class=\\"e2\\">phelāiyā deya</span>–cause [them] to squander [their practice on] <span class=\\"e2\\">sāmānya</span>–trivial <span class=\\"e2\\">prākṛta</span>–mundane <span class=\\"e2\\">phale</span>–ends."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Offences make the Name assume a material form and make a practitioner squander their practice on trivial mundane ends."},{"class":"b97","text":" ‘শ্রীসনৎকুমার উবাচ—<br />সতাং নিন্দা নাম্নঃ পরমপরাধং বিতনুতে<br />যতঃ খ্যাতিং যাতং কথমুসহতে তদ্বিগর্হাম্ ।<br />শিবস্য শ্রীবিষ্ণোর্য ইহ গুণনামাদিসকলং<br />ধিয়াভিন্নং পশ্যেৎ স খলু হরিনামাহিতকরঃ’ ॥৫২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ‘śrī-sanat-kumāra uvācha—<br />satāṁ nindā nāmnaḥ param aparādhaṁ vitanute<br />yataḥ khyātiṁ yātaṁ katham u sahate tad-vigarhām<br />śivasya śrī-viṣṇor ya iha guṇa-nāmādi-sakalaṁ<br />dhiyā bhinnaṁ paśyet sa khalu hari-nāmāhita-karaḥ’ [52]"},{"class":"b71","text":" “‘Sanat Kumār replied to Nārad: “(1) Criticising sādhus is the worst offence to the Name. How can the Name tolerate condemnation of those who spread the Name’s glories? (2a) Those who see differences between Viṣṇu, the embodiment of auspiciousness, and any of His Names, Qualities, and so forth, are certainly offenders of the Name. (2b) Those who see any distinction between any of Śiva’s names and qualities and those of Viṣṇu are also offenders of the Name.”’"},{"class":"b176","text":" নামাপরাধ হইতে মুক্তি"},{"class":"b177","text":" nāmāparādha ha-ite mukti"},{"class":"b70","text":" Liberation from the offences to the Name"},{"class":"b97","text":" দশটী নামাপরাধ ভিন্ন ভিন্ন করি’ ।<br />বুঝিয়া লইলে নাম-অপরাধে তরি ॥৫৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" daśaṭī nāmāparādha bhinna bhinna kari’<br />bujhiyā la-ile nāma-aparādhe tari [53]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bujhiyā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">la-ile</span>–If you understand <span class=\\"e2\\">daśaṭī</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmāparādha</span>–the ten offences to the Name <span class=\\"e2\\">bhinna</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bhinna</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kari’</span>–separately, <span class=\\"e2\\">tari</span>–you will [be able to] overcome <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-aparādhe</span>–the offences to the Name."},{"class":"b50","text":" [Śrīman Mahāprabhu paraphrases:] “If one by one you understand the ten offences to the Name, you will be able to overcome them."},{"class":"b97","text":" এই শ্লোকে দুই অপরাধের বিচার ।<br />করিয়া করহ শুদ্ধ নামের আচার ॥৫৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ei śloke dui aparādhera vichāra<br />kariyā karaha śuddha nāmera āchāra [54]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [First] <span class=\\"e2\\">vichāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kariyā</span>–study <span class=\\"e2\\">dui</span>–the two <span class=\\"e2\\">aparādhera</span>–offences <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">śloke</span>–in this verse [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">śuddha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">āchāra karaha</span>–purely chant <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmera</span>–the Name."},{"class":"b71","text":" “First study the two offences mentioned in these verses and purely chant the Name."},{"class":"b176","text":" সাধুনিন্দা"},{"class":"b177","text":" sādhu-nindā"},{"class":"b70","text":" Criticising sādhus"},{"class":"b97","text":" একান্ত নামেতে আশ্রয় আছে যাঁর ।<br />সাধুপদবাচ্য তেঁহ তারেন সংসার ॥৫৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ekānta nāmete āśraya āchhe yā̐ra<br />sādhu-pada-vāchya te̐ha tārena saṁsāra [55]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">te̐ha yā̐ra</span>–Those whose <span class=\\"e2\\">ekānta</span>–sole <span class=\\"e2\\">āśraya</span>–shelter <span class=\\"e2\\">āchhe</span>–is <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmete</span>–in the Name <span class=\\"e2\\">sādhu-pada-vāchya</span>–should be known by the title ‘sādhu’. <span class=\\"e2\\">tārena</span>–They liberate <span class=\\"e2\\">saṁsāra</span>–the world."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Those whose sole shelter is the Name should be known as ‘sādhus’. They liberate the world."},{"class":"b97","text":" জড়কর্ম্মজ্ঞানচেষ্টা ছাড়ি’ সেই জন ।<br />শুদ্ধভক্তিভাবে নাম করেন উচ্চারণ ॥৫৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" jaḍa-karma-jñāna-cheṣṭā chhāḍi’ sei jana<br />śuddha-bhakti-bhāve nāma karena uchchāraṇa [56]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">jana</span>–They <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍi’</span>–reject <span class=\\"e2\\">jaḍa-karma-jñāna-cheṣṭā</span>–endeavours based on mundane action and knowledge, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">uchchāraṇa karena</span>–chant <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–the Name <span class=\\"e2\\">śuddha-bhakti-bhāve</span>–with pure devotion."},{"class":"b50","text":" “They reject endeavours based on mundane action and knowledge, and chant the Name with pure devotion."},{"class":"b97","text":" নামের প্রচার একা তাঁহা হৈতে হয় ।<br />তাঁর নিন্দা কৃষ্ণনাম কভু না সহয় ॥৫৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" nāmera prachāra ekā tā̐hā haite haya<br />tā̐ra nindā kṛṣṇa-nāma kabhu nā sahaya [57]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">prachāra haya</span>–The Name is preached <span class=\\"e2\\">tā̐hā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haite</span>–by them <span class=\\"e2\\">ekā</span>–alone, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-nāma</span>–the Name of Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nā</span>–never <span class=\\"e2\\">sahaya</span>–tolerates <span class=\\"e2\\">nindā</span>–criticism <span class=\\"e2\\">tā̐ra</span>–of them."},{"class":"b50","text":" “The Name of Kṛṣṇa is preached by them alone, and the Name never tolerates criticism of them."},{"class":"b97","text":" সে সাধুর নিন্দা, তাঁতে, লঘু-বুদ্ধি যার ।<br />বড় অপরাধ নামে নিশ্চয় তাহার ॥৫৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" se sādhura nindā, tā̐te, laghu-buddhi yāra<br />baḍa aparādha nāme niśchaya tāhāra [58]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhāra yāra</span>–Those who <span class=\\"e2\\">se</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sādhura nindā</span>–criticise such sādhus [or] <span class=\\"e2\\">tā̐te</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">laghu-buddhi</span>–consider them insignificant <span class=\\"e2\\">niśchaya</span>–certainly [make] <span class=\\"e2\\">baḍa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">aparādha</span>–a heavy offence <span class=\\"e2\\">nāme</span>–to the Name."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Those who criticise such sādhus or consider them insignificant certainly make a heavy offence to the Name."},{"class":"b97","text":" যত্নে এই অপরাধ করিয়া বর্জ্জন ।<br />সেই সাধু-সঙ্গ-বলে করহ ভজন ॥৫৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" yatne ei aparādha kariyā varjana<br />sei sādhu-saṅga-bale karaha bhajana [59]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">yatne</span>–Carefully <span class=\\"e2\\">varjana kariyā</span>–avoid <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span>–this <span class=\\"e2\\">aparādha</span>–offence [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhajana karaha</span>–engage in service <span class=\\"e2\\">sei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sādhu-saṅga-bale</span>–by the power of such sādhus’ association."},{"class":"b71","text":" “Carefully avoid this offence and engage in service by the power of such sādhus’ association."},{"class":"b176","text":" শ্রীনাম-নামী একতত্ত্ব"},{"class":"b177","text":" śrī-nāma-nāmī eka-tattva"},{"class":"b70","text":" The Name and the possessor of the Name are one"},{"class":"b97","text":" মঙ্গলস্বরূপ বিষ্ণু পরতত্ত্ব হরি ।<br />অপ্রাকৃত স্বরূপেতে শ্রীব্রজবিহারী ॥৬০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" maṅgala-svarūpa viṣṇu para-tattva hari<br />aprākṛta svarūpete śrī-vraja-vihārī [60]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">viṣṇu</span>–Viṣṇu— <span class=\\"e2\\">maṅgala-svarūpa</span>–the embodiment of auspiciousness, <span class=\\"e2\\">para-tattva</span>–the Absolute, <span class=\\"e2\\">hari</span>–the Supreme Lord— <span class=\\"e2\\">aprākṛta</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">svarūpete</span>–in [His] supramundane form, [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-vraja-vihārī</span>–the enjoyer of Vraja (Kṛṣṇa)."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Viṣṇu—the embodiment of auspiciousness, the Absolute, the Supreme Lord—in His supramundane form, is Kṛṣṇa, the enjoyer of Vraja."},{"class":"b97","text":" তাঁর নাম-রূপ-গুণ-লীলা অপ্রাকৃত ।<br />তাঁহার স্বরূপ হৈতে ভিন্ন নহে তত্ত্ব ॥৬১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" tā̐ra nāma-rūpa-guṇa-līlā aprākṛta<br />tā̐hāra svarūpa haite bhinna nahe tattva [61]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">tā̐ra</span>–His <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-rūpa-guṇa-līlā</span>–Name, Form, Qualities, and Pastimes [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">aprākṛta</span>–supramundane. <span class=\\"e2\\">nahe</span>–They are not <span class=\\"e2\\">tattva</span>–elements <span class=\\"e2\\">bhinna</span>–separate <span class=\\"e2\\">haite</span>–from <span class=\\"e2\\">tā̐hāra</span>–His <span class=\\"e2\\">svarūpa</span>–nature."},{"class":"b50","text":" “His Name, Form, Qualities, and Pastimes are supramundane. None of them are separate from Him."},{"class":"b97","text":" নাম নামী এক তত্ত্ব অপ্রাকৃত ধর্ম্ম ।<br />এ জড়জগতে তার নাহি আছে মর্ম্ম ॥৬২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" nāma nāmī eka tattva aprākṛta dharma<br />e jaḍa-jagate tāra nāhi āchhe marma [62]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–The Name [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmī</span>–the possessor of the Name [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">eka</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">tattva</span>–one being; [such is] <span class=\\"e2\\">dharma</span>–the nature <span class=\\"e2\\">aprākṛta</span>–of the supramundane. <span class=\\"e2\\">āchhe nāhi</span>–There is no <span class=\\"e2\\">marma</span>–understanding <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra</span>–of this, [however,] <span class=\\"e2\\">e</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">jaḍa-jagate</span>–in the material world."},{"class":"b50","text":" “The Name and the possessor of the Name are one; such is the nature of the supramundane. There is no understanding of this, however, in the material world."},{"class":"b97","text":" এই শুদ্ধজ্ঞানলাভ ভক্তিবলে হয় ।<br />তর্কে বহু দূর ইহা জানিহ নিশ্চয় ॥৬৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ei śuddha-jñāna-lābha bhakti-bale haya<br />tarke bahu dūra ihā jāniha niśchaya [63]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">śuddha-jñāna-lābha haya</span>–This pure conception is attained <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakti-bale</span>–through devotion. <span class=\\"e2\\">jāniha</span>–Know <span class=\\"e2\\">niśchaya</span>–for certain [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">ihā</span>–it [remains] <span class=\\"e2\\">bahu</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">dūra</span>–far away <span class=\\"e2\\">tarke</span>–from argument."},{"class":"b50","text":" “You can realise this pure conception only through devotion. Know for certain that it is far beyond argument."},{"class":"b97","text":" নিজ শুদ্ধসাধন, আর সাধুগুরবল ।<br />দুইয়ের সংয়োগে লভি’ এ তত্ত্বমঙ্গল ॥৬৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" nija śuddha-sādhana, āra sādhu-guru-bala<br />duiyera saṁyoge labhi’ e tattva-maṅgala [64]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">labhi’</span>–You will realise <span class=\\"e2\\">e</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">tattva-maṅgala</span>–this auspicious truth <span class=\\"e2\\">duiyera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">saṁyoge</span>–by the combination of two things: [your] <span class=\\"e2\\">nija</span>–own <span class=\\"e2\\">śuddha-sādhana</span>–pure practice, <span class=\\"e2\\">āra</span>–and <span class=\\"e2\\">sādhu-guru-bala</span>–the power of Śrī Guru and the sādhus."},{"class":"b50","text":" “You will realise this auspicious truth by the combination of two things: your pure practice, and the power of Śrī Guru and the sādhus."},{"class":"b97","text":" এই তত্ত্বসিদ্ধি যত দিন নাহি হয় ।<br />ততদিন প্রাকৃতবুদ্ধি কভু না ছাড়য় ॥৬৫॥<br />ততদিন নাম করি’ না পাই স্বরূপ ।<br />নামাভাসমাত্র হয় ভজনবিরূপ ॥৬৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ei tattva-siddhi yata dina nāhi haya<br />tata-dina prākṛta-buddhi kabhu nā chhāḍaya [65]<br />tata-dina nāma kari’ nā pāi svarūpa<br />nāmābhāsa-mātra haya bhajana-virūpa [66]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">tata-dina</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">tata-dina yata</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">dina</span>–As long as <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">tattva-siddhi</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haya nāhi</span>–you have not realised this truth, <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍaya</span>–you will never leave <span class=\\"e2\\">prākṛta-buddhi</span>–mundane consciousness: <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kari’</span>–you will chant the Name [but] <span class=\\"e2\\">pāi nā</span>–not get <span class=\\"e2\\">svarūpa</span>–the true form [of the Name;] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmābhāsa-mātra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–you will chant only a semblance of the Name, [and your] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhajana-virūpa</span>–service [will remain] imperfect."},{"class":"b50","text":" “As long as you have not realised this truth, you will never leave mundane consciousness: you will chant the Name but never get the pure Name; you will chant only Nāmābhās, and your service will remain imperfect."},{"class":"b97","text":" বহু যত্নে লাভ ভাই স্বরূপের সিদ্ধি ।<br />শুদ্ধনামোচ্চারে পাবে পরংপদ-বুদ্ধি ॥৬৭॥<br />যত্নসহ নিরন্তর নামাভাসে হরি ।<br />নামেতে স্বরূপসিদ্ধি দিবে কৃপা করি’ ॥৬৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" bahu yatne lābha bhāi svarūpera siddhi<br />śuddha-nāmochchāre pābe paraṁ-pada-buddhi [67]<br />yatnasaha nirantara nāmābhāse hari<br />nāmete svarūpa-siddhi dibe kṛpā kari’ [68]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāi</span>–Brother, <span class=\\"e2\\">bahu</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">yatne</span>–with great care, <span class=\\"e2\\">lābha</span>–[try to] attain <span class=\\"e2\\">svarūpera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">siddhi</span>–realisation of the true self. <span class=\\"e2\\">śuddha-nāmochchāre</span>–By chanting the Name purely (without offence), <span class=\\"e2\\">pābe</span>–you will attain <span class=\\"e2\\">paraṁ-pada-buddhi</span>–consciousness of the highest plane. [When you are engaged] <span class=\\"e2\\">yatnasaha</span>–carefully [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">nirantara</span>–constantly <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmābhāse</span>–in [chanting] a semblance of the Name, <span class=\\"e2\\">hari</span>–the Lord, <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛpā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kari’</span>–mercifully, <span class=\\"e2\\">dibe</span>–will grant [you] <span class=\\"e2\\">svarūpa-siddhi</span>–realisation of the true self <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmete</span>–through the Name."},{"class":"b71","text":" “Brother, with great care, try to realise the true self. By chanting the Name purely, you will attain consciousness of the highest plane. When you carefully and constantly chant Nāmābhās, the Lord will mercifully grant you realisation of the true self through the Name."},{"class":"b176","text":" কৃষ্ণ সর্ব্বেশ্বর, শিবাদি তাঁহার অংশ"},{"class":"b177","text":" kṛṣṇa sarveśvara, śivādi tā̐hāra aṁśa"},{"class":"b70","text":" Kṛṣṇa is the Lord of all; <br />Śiva and the other gods are partial forms of Him"},{"class":"b97","text":" সর্ব্বেশ্বর কৃষ্ণ, তাহে জানিবে নিশ্চয় ।<br />শিবাদি দেবতা তাঁর অংশরূপ হয় ॥৬৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sarveśvara kṛṣṇa, tāhe jānibe niśchaya<br />śivādi devatā tā̐ra aṁśa-rūpa haya [69]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span>–Kṛṣṇa [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">sarveśvara</span>–the Lord of all. <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhe</span>–Herein, <span class=\\"e2\\">jānibe</span>–you should know <span class=\\"e2\\">niśchaya</span>–for certain [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">śivādi</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">devatā</span>–Śiva and the other gods <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–are <span class=\\"e2\\">aṁśa-rūpa</span>–partial forms <span class=\\"e2\\">tā̐ra</span>–of Him."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Kṛṣṇa is the Lord of all; you should know for certain that Śiva and the other gods are partial forms of Him."},{"class":"b97","text":" সেই সেই দেবের নামাদি গুণরূপ ।<br />কৃষ্ণশক্তিদত্ত সিদ্ধ জানহ স্বরূপ ॥৭০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sei sei devera nāmādi guṇa-rūpa<br />kṛṣṇa-śakti-datta siddha jānaha svarūpa [70]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">jānaha</span>–Know <span class=\\"e2\\">svarūpa</span>–this truth: <span class=\\"e2\\">sei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">devera</span>–the gods’ <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmādi</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">guṇa-rūpa</span>–names, forms, qualities, and so on, [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-śakti-datta siddha</span>–given and produced by Kṛṣṇa’s energy."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Know this truth: the gods’ names, forms, qualities, and so on, are given and produced by Kṛṣṇa’s energy."},{"class":"b97","text":" এরূপ জানিলে শিববিষ্ণুতে অভেদে ।<br />জন্মিবে স্বরূপবুদ্ধি, গায় সর্ব্ববেদে ॥৭১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" e-rūpa jānile śiva-viṣṇute abhede<br />janmibe svarūpa-buddhi gāya sarva-vede [71]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-vede</span>–All the scriptures <span class=\\"e2\\">gāya</span>–sing [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">jānile</span>–if you understand [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">śiva-viṣṇute</span>–Śiva and Viṣṇu [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">abhede</span>–nondifferent <span class=\\"e2\\">e-rūpa</span>–in this sense, [then your] <span class=\\"e2\\">svarūpa-buddhi</span>–awareness of the truth <span class=\\"e2\\">janmibe</span>–will develop."},{"class":"b50","text":" “All the scriptures sing that if you understand that Śiva and Viṣṇu are nondifferent in this sense, then you will know the truth."},{"class":"b97","text":" ভেদবুদ্ধি অপরাধ যত্নেতে ত্যজিবে ।<br />গুরুকৃপাবলে তবে শ্রীনাম ভজিবে ॥৭২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" bheda-buddhi aparādha yatnete tyajibe<br />guru-kṛpā-bale tabe śrī-nāma bhajibe [72]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">yatnete</span>–Carefully <span class=\\"e2\\">tyajibe</span>–avoid <span class=\\"e2\\">aparādha</span>–the offence <span class=\\"e2\\">bheda-buddhi</span>–of considering [them] different, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">tabe</span>–then, <span class=\\"e2\\">guru-kṛpā-bale</span>–by the mercy of Śrī Guru, <span class=\\"e2\\">bhajibe</span>–you will [be able to] serve <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-nāma</span>–the Name."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Carefully avoid the offence of considering Viṣṇu and Śiva different, and then, by the mercy of Śrī Guru, you will be able to serve the Name."},{"class":"b97","text":" ‘গুরোরবজ্ঞা শ্রুতিশাস্ত্রনিন্দনম্<br />তথার্থবাদো হরিনাম্নি কল্পনম্ ।<br />নাম্নো বলাদ্যস্য হি পাপবুদ্ধির্<br />ন বিদ্যতে তস্য যমৈর্হি শুদ্ধিঃ’ ॥৭৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ‘guror avajñā śruti-śāstra-nindanam<br />tathārthavādo hari-nāmni kalpanam<br />nāmno balād yasya hi pāpa-buddhir<br />na vidyate tasya yamair hi śuddhiḥ’ [73]"},{"class":"b71","text":" “‘[Śrī Sanat Kumār said:] “Those who (3) disrespect Śrī Guru, (4) criticise the scriptures, (5) consider the Name’s glories exaggerated praise, (6) consider the Name imaginary, or (7) desire to sin on the power of the Name, cannot be purified by any type of regulation.”’*"},{"class":"b176","text":" গুরু-কর্ণধারের অনাদর"},{"class":"b177","text":" guru-karṇadhārera anādara"},{"class":"b70","text":" Disrespecting your captain, Śrī Guru"},{"class":"b97","text":" কৃপা করি’ যেই জন হরি দেখাইল ।<br />হরিনাম-পরিচয় করাইয়া দিল ॥৭৪॥<br />সেই মোর কর্ণধার গুরু মহাশয় ।<br />তাঁহারে অবজ্ঞা কৈলে নামাপরাধ হয় ॥৭৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kṛpā kari’ yei jana hari dekhāila<br />hari-nāma-parichaya karāiyā dila [74]<br />sei mora karṇadhāra guru mahāśaya<br />tā̐hāre avajñā kaile nāmāparādha haya [75]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sei yei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">jana</span>–He who <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛpā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kari’</span>–mercifully <span class=\\"e2\\">dekhāila</span>–has revealed <span class=\\"e2\\">hari</span>–the Lord [to me and] <span class=\\"e2\\">hari-nāma-parichaya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">karāiyā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">dila</span>–introduced me to the Lord’s Name [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">mora</span>–my <span class=\\"e2\\">karṇadhāra</span>–captain, [my] <span class=\\"e2\\">guru</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">mahāśaya</span>–worshippable Guru. <span class=\\"e2\\">avajñā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kaile</span>–If I disrespect <span class=\\"e2\\">tā̐hāre</span>–Him, <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmāparādha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–I offend the Name."},{"class":"b50","text":" [Śrīman Mahāprabhu paraphrases:] “He who has mercifully revealed the Lord to me and introduced me to His Name is my captain, my worshippable Guru. If I disrespect him, I offend the Name."},{"class":"b97","text":" ‘হীনজাতি পাণ্ডিত্য-রহিত মন্ত্রহীন’ ।<br />নামের গুরুতে হেন বুদ্ধি অর্ব্বাচীন ॥৭৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ‘hīna-jāti pāṇḍitya-rahita mantra-hīna’<br />nāmera gurute hena buddhi arvāchīna [76]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">‘hīna-jāti</span>–‘Low-class, <span class=\\"e2\\">pāṇḍitya-rahita</span>–uneducated, [or] <span class=\\"e2\\">mantra-hīna’</span>–uninitiated’—[those who have] <span class=\\"e2\\">hena</span>–such <span class=\\"e2\\">buddhi</span>–a mentality <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">gurute</span>–about the Guru of the Name [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">arvāchīna</span>–foolish."},{"class":"b43","text":" “Those who consider the Guru who reveals the Name to be low-class, uneducated, or uninitiated are foolish."},{"class":"b69","text":" *In his commentary on <span class=\\"e3\\">Śrī Hari-bhakti-vilāsa</span> (11.522), Śrīla Sanātan Goswāmī explains that ‘by any type of regulation’ (<span class=\\"e3\\">yamaiḥ</span>) means by aṣṭāṅga-yoga, pious activities, brahminical qualities, or prolonged punishment from Yamarāj."},{"class":"b176","text":" শ্রুতিশাস্ত্রে অনাদর"},{"class":"b177","text":" śruti-śāstre anādara"},{"class":"b70","text":" Disrespecting the scriptures"},{"class":"b97","text":" যেই শ্রুতিশাস্ত্র নামের ব্রহ্মত্ব দেখায় ।<br />অপার মাহাত্ম্য নামের জগতে জানায় ॥৭৭॥<br />তারে অনাদর করি’ কর্ম্মাদি প্রশংসে ।<br />শ্রুতিনিন্দা বলি’ তারে সর্ব্বশাস্ত্রে ভাষে ॥৭৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" yei śruti-śāstra nāmera brahmatva dekhāya<br />apāra māhātmya nāmera jagate jānāya [77]<br />tāre anādara kari’ karmādi praśaṁse<br />śruti-nindā bali’ tāre sarva-śāstre bhāṣe [78]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">yei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">śruti-śāstra</span>–The scriptures that <span class=\\"e2\\">dekhāya</span>–reveal <span class=\\"e2\\">brahmatva</span>–the transcendental nature <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmera</span>–of the Name [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">jānāya</span>–proclaim <span class=\\"e2\\">apāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">māhātmya</span>–the unlimited glories <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmera</span>–of the Name <span class=\\"e2\\">jagate</span>–throughout this world— <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-śāstre</span>–all the scriptures <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāṣe</span>–say [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">anādara</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kari’</span>–disrespecting <span class=\\"e2\\">tāre</span>–them [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">praśaṁse</span>–praising <span class=\\"e2\\">karmādi</span>–material activities and other non-devotional practices [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">bali’</span>–known as <span class=\\"e2\\">śruti-nindā</span>–criticism of the scriptures."},{"class":"b71","text":" “The scriptures reveal the transcendental nature of the Name and proclaim the unlimited glories of the Name throughout this world. Disrespecting them and praising non-devotional activities is criticism of the scriptures. All the scriptures say so."},{"class":"b176","text":" নামে কল্পনাবুদ্ধি"},{"class":"b177","text":" nāme kalpanā-buddhi"},{"class":"b70","text":" Considering the Name imaginary"},{"class":"b97","text":" নাম নিত্যধন সদা চিন্ময় অগাধ ।<br />তাহাতে কল্পনাবুদ্ধি গুরু অপরাধ ॥৭৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" nāma nitya-dhana sadā chinmaya agādha<br />tāhāte kalpanā-buddhi guru aparādha [79]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–The Name— <span class=\\"e2\\">sadā</span>–eternal, <span class=\\"e2\\">chinmaya</span>–spiritual, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">agādha</span>–unfathomable— [is your] <span class=\\"e2\\">nitya-dhana</span>–eternal wealth. [Having] <span class=\\"e2\\">buddhi</span>–the mentality [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhāte</span>–He [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">kalpanā</span>–an imagination [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">guru</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">aparādha</span>–a heavy offence."},{"class":"b71","text":" “The Name—eternal, spiritual, and unfathomable—is your eternal wealth. To consider the Name imaginary is a heavy offence."},{"class":"b176","text":" নামবলে পাপবুদ্ধি"},{"class":"b177","text":" nāma-bale pāpa-buddhi"},{"class":"b70","text":" Desiring to sin on the power of the Name"},{"class":"b97","text":" নামবলে পাপবুদ্ধি হৃদয়ে যাহার ।<br />সতত উদয় হয়, সেই ত’ অসার ॥৮০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" nāma-bale pāpa-buddhi hṛdaye yāhāra<br />satata udaya haya, sei ta’ asāra [80]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ta’ yāhāra hṛdaye</span>–Those within whose hearts <span class=\\"e2\\">pāpa-buddhi</span>–the desire to sin <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-bale</span>–on the power of the Name <span class=\\"e2\\">satata</span>–constantly <span class=\\"e2\\">udaya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–arises [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">asāra</span>–wretched."},{"class":"b71","text":" “Those who within their hearts desire to sin on the power of the Name are wretched."},{"class":"b176","text":" নামে অর্থবাদ"},{"class":"b177","text":" nāme arthavāda"},{"class":"b70","text":" Considering the glories of the Name exaggeration"},{"class":"b97","text":" রোচনার্থা ফলশ্রুতি কর্ম্মমার্গে সত্য ।<br />ভক্তিমার্গে নামফল সর্ব্বকালে নিত্য ॥৮১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" rochanārthā phala-śruti karma-mārge satya<br />bhakti-mārge nāma-phala sarva-kāle nitya [81]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">phala-śruti</span>–The (temporary, material) results, described in the Vedas, <span class=\\"e2\\">karma-mārge</span>–of the path of action, [which are] <span class=\\"e2\\">rochanārthā</span>–for the purpose of attraction, [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">satya</span>–real, [but] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-phala</span>–the results produced by the Name <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakti-mārge</span>–on the path of devotion [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-kāle</span>–always <span class=\\"e2\\">nitya</span>–eternal."},{"class":"b50","text":" “The benefits of the path of action, which the scriptures describe for the purpose of attraction, are real, but the benefits of chanting the Name on the path of devotion are always eternal."},{"class":"b97","text":" অপ্রাকৃত নামের মাহাত্ম্য সীমাহীন ।<br />তাতে যার ‘অর্থবাদ’ সেই অর্বাচীন ॥৮২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" aprākṛta nāmera māhātmya sīmā-hīna<br />tāte yāra ‘arthavāda’ sei arvāchīna [82]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">aprākṛta</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">māhātmya</span>–The supramundane glories of the Name [have] <span class=\\"e2\\">sīmā-hīna</span>–no end. <span class=\\"e2\\">sei yāra</span>–Those who [consider] <span class=\\"e2\\">tāte</span>–them <span class=\\"e2\\">‘arthavāda’</span>–exaggeration [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">arvāchīna</span>–foolish."},{"class":"b71","text":" “There is no end to the supramundane glories of the Name. Those who consider them exaggeration are foolish."},{"class":"b176","text":" এই সব অপরাধ বর্জ্জনে নামের কৃপা"},{"class":"b177","text":" ei saba aparādha varjane nāmera kṛpā"},{"class":"b70","text":" By avoiding these offences, <br />you will attain the grace of the Name"},{"class":"b97","text":" এই পঞ্চ অপরাধ বর্জ্জিবে যতনে ।<br />তবে ত’ নামের কৃপা লভিবে সাধনে ॥৮৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ei pañcha aparādha varjibe yatane<br />tabe ta’ nāmera kṛpā labhibe sādhane [83]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">yatane</span>–Carefully <span class=\\"e2\\">varjibe</span>–avoid <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">pañcha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">aparādha</span>–these five offences; <span class=\\"e2\\">tabe</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ta’</span>–then <span class=\\"e2\\">labhibe</span>–you will attain <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛpā</span>–the grace <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmera</span>–of the Name <span class=\\"e2\\">sādhane</span>–through [your] practice."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Carefully avoid these five offences; then you will attain the grace of the Name through your practice."},{"class":"b97","text":" ‘ধর্ম্মব্রতত্যাগহুতাদিসর্ব্বশুভক্রিয়াসাম্যমপি প্রমাদঃ ।<br />অশ্রদ্দধানে বিমুখেঽপ্যশৃণ্বতি যশ্চোপদেশঃ শিবনামাপরাধঃ’ ॥৮৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ‘dharma-vrata-tyāga-hutādi-sarva-<br />śubha-kriyā-sāmyam api pramādaḥ<br />aśraddadhāne vimukhe ’py aśṛṇvati<br />yaś chopadeśaḥ śiva-nāmāparādhaḥ’ [84]"},{"class":"b71","text":" “‘[Śrī Sanat Kumār said:] “(8) Disregarding the Name by considering pious activities, such as social duties, rites, austerities, and sacrifices, equal to chanting the Name, (9) and instructing the faithless, the averse, or those who do not want to hear about the Name, are offences to the all-auspicious Name.”’"},{"class":"b176","text":" সর্ব্ব শুভকর্ম্ম প্রাকৃত"},{"class":"b177","text":" sarva śubha-karma prākṛta"},{"class":"b70","text":" All pious activities are mundane"},{"class":"b97","text":" বর্ণাশ্রমময়-ধর্ম্ম ধর্ম্মশাস্ত্রে যত ।<br />দর্শপৌর্ণমাসী-আদি তমোময়-ব্রত ॥৮৫॥<br />দণ্ডী মুণ্ডী সন্ন্যাসাদি ত্যাগের প্রকার ।<br />নিত্য নৈমিত্তিক হোম-আদির ব্যাপার ॥৮৬॥<br />অষ্টাঙ্গ-ষড়ঙ্গ-যোগ-আদি শুভ-কর্ম্ম ।<br />সকলই প্রাকৃত-তত্ত্ব, এই সত্য মর্ম্ম ॥৮৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" varṇāśramamaya-dharma dharma-śāstre yata<br />darśa-paurṇamāsī-ādi tamomaya-vrata [85]<br />daṇḍī muṇḍī sannyāsādi tyāgera prakāra<br />nitya naimittika homa-ādira vyāpāra [86]<br />aṣṭāṅga-ṣaḍ-aṅga-yoga-ādi śubha-karma<br />sakala-i prākṛta-tattva, ei satya marma [87]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">śubha-karma</span>–The pious activities [prescribed] <span class=\\"e2\\">dharma-śāstre</span>–in religious scriptures— <span class=\\"e2\\">varṇāśramamaya-dharma</span>–the duties of your social role and class, <span class=\\"e2\\">yata</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">darśa-paurṇamāsī-ādi</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">tamomaya-vrata</span>–the dark rites on the new moon and the full moon,<span class=\\"e2\\"> nitya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">naimittika</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">homa-ādira</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">vyāpāra</span>–daily and periodic sacrifices,<span class=\\"e2\\"> aṣṭāṅga-ṣaḍ-aṅga-yoga</span>–the eightfold or sixfold paths of yoga, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">daṇḍī</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">muṇḍī</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sannyāsādi</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">tyāgera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">prakāra</span>–the austerities of carrying a staff, shaving your head, giving up all your possessions, <span class=\\"e2\\">ādi</span>–and so on— [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">sakala-i</span>–all <span class=\\"e2\\">prākṛta-tattva</span>–mundane. <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span>–This [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">satya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">marma</span>–the fundamental truth."},{"class":"b50","text":" [Śrīman Mahāprabhu paraphrases:] “The duties of your social role and class, the dark rites on the new moon and the full moon, daily and periodic sacrifices, the eightfold or sixfold paths of yoga, and the austerities of carrying a staff, shaving your head, and giving up all your possessions—all these and other pious activities prescribed in the religious scriptures are mundane. This is the fundamental truth."},{"class":"b97","text":" উপায়রূপেতে তারা উপেয় সাধয় ।<br />না সাধিলে জড় বই কিছু আর নয় ॥৮৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" upāya-rūpete tārā upeya sādhaya<br />nā sādhile jaḍa va-i kichhu āra naya [88]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">tārā</span>–They <span class=\\"e2\\">sādhaya</span>–may be performed <span class=\\"e2\\">upāya-rūpete</span>–as a means <span class=\\"e2\\">upeya</span>–to pursue the goal, [but] <span class=\\"e2\\">sādhile nā</span>–if they are not performed [for that purpose, then they are] <span class=\\"e2\\">va-i</span>–only <span class=\\"e2\\">jaḍa</span>–material <span class=\\"e2\\">āra kichhu</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">naya</span>–and nothing more."},{"class":"b71","text":" “These practices may be performed as a means to pursue the goal (of devotion), but if they are not performed for that purpose, then they are material and nothing more."},{"class":"b176","text":" শ্রীনাম উপায়, উপেয়"},{"class":"b177","text":" śrī-nāma upāya, upeya"},{"class":"b70","text":" The Name is the means and the goal"},{"class":"b97","text":" নাম কিন্তু অপ্রাকৃত চিন্ময় ব্যাপার ।<br />সাধনে উপায়তত্ত্ব সাধ্যে উপেয়-সার ॥৮৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" nāma kintu aprākṛta chinmaya vyāpāra<br />sādhane upāya-tattva sādhye upeya-sāra [89]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [Chanting] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–the Name, <span class=\\"e2\\">kintu</span>–however, [is a] <span class=\\"e2\\">aprākṛta</span>–supramundane, <span class=\\"e2\\">chinmaya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">vyāpāra</span>–spiritual engagement. <span class=\\"e2\\">sādhane</span>–In practice, [the Name is] <span class=\\"e2\\">upāya-tattva</span>–the means [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">sādhye</span>–in perfection, [the Name is] <span class=\\"e2\\">upeya-sāra</span>–the primary engagement."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Chanting the Name, however, is a supramundane, spiritual engagement. In the practising stage, the Name is the means, and in the perfectional stage, the Name is the primary engagement."},{"class":"b97","text":" অতএব নামতত্ত্ব বিশুদ্ধ চিন্ময় ।<br />জড়োপায় কর্ম্ম সহ সাম্য কভু নয় ॥৯০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ataeva nāma-tattva viśuddha chinmaya<br />jaḍopāya karma saha sāmya kabhu naya [90]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">ataeva</span>–So, <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-tattva</span>–the Name, by nature <span class=\\"e2\\">viśuddha</span>–pure [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">chinmaya</span>–spiritual, <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">naya</span>–is never <span class=\\"e2\\">sāmya</span>–equal <span class=\\"e2\\">jaḍopāya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">karma</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">saha</span>–to [any] mundane means or action."},{"class":"b71","text":" “So, the Name, which is pure and spiritual, is never equal to any mundane means or action."},{"class":"b176","text":" কর্ম্মজ্ঞান সহ নাম তুল্য নহে"},{"class":"b177","text":" karma-jñāna saha nāma tulya nahe"},{"class":"b70","text":" The Name is not equal to mundane action or knowledge"},{"class":"b97","text":" কর্ম্মজ্ঞান সহ নামে সাম্যবুদ্ধি যথা ।<br />নাম-অপরাধ গুরুতর ঘটে তথা ॥৯১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" karma-jñāna saha nāme sāmya-buddhi yathā<br />nāma-aparādha gurutara ghaṭe tathā [91]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">yathā</span>–When [you have] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāme</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sāmya-buddhi</span>–the mentality that the Name is equal <span class=\\"e2\\">karma-jñāna</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">saha</span>–to mundane activity or knowledge, <span class=\\"e2\\">tathā</span>–then <span class=\\"e2\\">gurutara nāma-aparādha</span>–a very heavy offence to the Name <span class=\\"e2\\">ghaṭe</span>–occurs."},{"class":"b71","text":" “If you think the Name is equal to mundane activity or knowledge, you commit a very heavy offence against the Name."},{"class":"b176","text":" অবিশ্বাসী জনে নাম উপদেশ"},{"class":"b177","text":" aviśvāsī jane nāma upadeśa"},{"class":"b70","text":" Instructing the faithless about the Name"},{"class":"b97","text":" নামে যার বিশ্বাস না জন্মিল ভাগ্যাভাবে ।<br />তাকে নাম উপদেশি’ অপরাধ পাবে ॥৯২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" nāme yāra viśvāsa nā janmila bhāgyābhāve<br />tāke nāma upadeśi’ aparādha pābe [92]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">upadeśi’</span>–By instructing <span class=\\"e2\\">tāke yāra</span>–those who, <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāgyābhāve</span>–lacking good fortune, <span class=\\"e2\\">viśvāsa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">janmila nā</span>–have not developed faith <span class=\\"e2\\">nāme</span>–in the Name [about] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–the Name, <span class=\\"e2\\">pābe</span>–you will make <span class=\\"e2\\">aparādha</span>–an offence."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Instructing those who, lacking good fortune, have no faith in the Name about the Name, is an offence."},{"class":"b97","text":" এই দুই অপরাধ সদ্গুরুকৃপায় ।<br />বহু যত্নে ছাড়ি’ ভাই নামধন পায় ॥৯৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ei dui aparādha sad-guru-kṛpāya<br />bahu yatne chhāḍi’ bhāi nāma-dhana pāya [93]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāi</span>–Brother, <span class=\\"e2\\">sad-guru-kṛpāya</span>–by the grace of Śrī Guru, <span class=\\"e2\\">bahu</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">yatne</span>–very carefully <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍi’</span>–avoid <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">dui</span>–these two <span class=\\"e2\\">aparādha</span>–offences [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">pāya</span>–attain <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-dhana</span>–the wealth of the Name."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Brother, by the grace of Śrī Guru, very carefully avoid these two offences and attain the wealth of the Name."},{"class":"b97","text":" ‘শ্রুত্বাপি নামমাহাত্ম্যং যঃ প্রীতিরহিতোঽধমঃ ।<br />অহং-মমাদি-পরমো নাম্নি সোঽপ্যপরাধকৃৎ’ ॥৯৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ‘śrutvāpi nāma-māhātmyaṁ yaḥ prīti-rahito ’dhamaḥ<br />ahaṁ-mamādi-paramo nāmni so ’py aparādha-kṛt’ [94]"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘[Śrī Sanat Kumār said:] “(10) Fallen souls who, even after hearing the glories of the Name, have no love for the Name and remain engrossed in the conceptions of ‘I’ and ‘mine’ are offenders to the Name.”’"},{"class":"b97","text":" নামের মাহাত্ম্য সব শুনি’ শাস্ত্র হৈতে ।<br />তবু তাহে রতি যার নৈল কোনমতে ॥৯৫॥<br />অহংতা-মমতা-বুদ্ধি দেহেতে করিয়া ।<br />লাভ-পূজা-প্রতিষ্ঠাতে রহিল মজিয়া ॥৯৬॥<br />পাপে রত হঞা পাপ ছাড়িতে না পারে ।<br />নামে যত্ন করি’ চেষ্টা করিবারে নারে ॥৯৭॥<br />সাধুসঙ্গে মতি নহে অসাধু বিষয়ে ।<br />সুখ পায় বিবেক বৈরাগ্য ছাড়াইয়ে ॥৯৮॥<br />এই ত’ নামাপরাধ ঘটনা তাহার ।<br />নামে রুচি নাহি পায় কৃষ্ণের সংসার ॥৯৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" nāmera māhātmya saba śuni’ śāstra haite<br />tabu tāhe rati yāra naila kona-mate [95]<br />ahaṁtā-mamatā-buddhi dehete kariyā<br />lābha-pūjā-pratiṣṭhāte rahila majiyā [96]<br />pāpe rata hañā pāpa chhāḍite nā pāre<br />nāme yatna kari’ cheṣṭā karibāre nāre [97]<br />sādhu-saṅge mati nahe asādhu viṣaye<br />sukha pāya viveka vairāgya chhāḍāiye [98]<br />ei ta’ nāmāparādha ghaṭanā tāhāra<br />nāme ruchi nāhi pāya kṛṣṇera saṁsāra [99]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhāra yāra</span>–Those who <span class=\\"e2\\">śuni’</span>–hear <span class=\\"e2\\">māhātmya</span>–the glories <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmera</span>–of the Name <span class=\\"e2\\">haite</span>–from <span class=\\"e2\\">saba</span>–all <span class=\\"e2\\">śāstra</span>–the scriptures [but] <span class=\\"e2\\">tabu</span>–still <span class=\\"e2\\">rati</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">naila</span>–have no attachment <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhe</span>–to the Name <span class=\\"e2\\">kona-mate</span>–whatsoever; [who] <span class=\\"e2\\">buddhi kariyā</span>–consider <span class=\\"e2\\">dehete</span>–the body [to be] <span class=\\"e2\\">ahaṁtā-mamatā</span>–‘I’ and ‘mine’; [who] <span class=\\"e2\\">majiyā rahila</span>–take interest <span class=\\"e2\\">lābha-pūjā-pratiṣṭhāte</span>–in gain, adoration, and position; [who] <span class=\\"e2\\">pāpe</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">rata</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">hañā</span>–sin [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">pāre nā</span>–cannot <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍite</span>–stop <span class=\\"e2\\">pāpa</span>–sinning; [who] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāre</span>–are unable <span class=\\"e2\\">cheṣṭā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">karibāre</span>–to try [to] <span class=\\"e2\\">yatna</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kari’</span>–carefully [chant] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāme</span>–the Name; [who] <span class=\\"e2\\">mati</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nahe</span>–have no attachment <span class=\\"e2\\">sādhu-saṅge</span>–to the association of sādhus; [who] <span class=\\"e2\\">sukha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">pāya</span>–find pleasure <span class=\\"e2\\">asādhu</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">viṣaye</span>–in sinful matters; [and who] <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍāiye</span>–shun <span class=\\"e2\\">vairāgya</span>–renunciation [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">viveka</span>–good judgement <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ta’</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmāparādha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ghaṭanā</span>–offend the Name [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">pāya nāhi</span>–do not get <span class=\\"e2\\">ruchi</span>–any taste <span class=\\"e2\\">nāme</span>–for the Name [or] <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇera</span>–Kṛṣṇa’s <span class=\\"e2\\">saṁsāra</span>–family."},{"class":"b50","text":" [Śrīman Mahāprabhu paraphrases:] “Those who hear the glories of the Name from all the scriptures but still do not have any love for the Name; who still consider the body to be ‘I’ and ‘mine’; still take interest in wealth, adoration, and position; still sin and fail to stop doing so; still cannot even try to carefully chant the Name; still have no attachment to the association of sādhus; still take pleasure in sinful matters; and still avoid renunciation and good judgement—they offend the Name and do not get any taste for the Name or Kṛṣṇa’s family."},{"class":"b97","text":" এই দশ অপরাধ নামাপরাধ হয় ।<br />নামধর্ম্মে বাধা দেয় সুমঙ্গলক্ষয় ॥১০০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ei daśa aparādha nāmāparādha haya<br />nāma-dharme bādhā deya sumaṅgala-kṣaya [100]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span>–These <span class=\\"e2\\">daśa</span>–ten <span class=\\"e2\\">aparādha</span>–offences <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–are <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmāparādha</span>–the offences to the Name. <span class=\\"e2\\">bādhā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">deya</span>–They obstruct <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-dharme</span>–the practice of [chanting] the Name [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">sumaṅgala-kṣaya</span>–destroy spiritual fortune."},{"class":"b50","text":" “These are the ten offences to the Name; they obstruct chanting of the Name and destroy spiritual fortune."},{"class":"b97","text":" ‘সর্ব্বাপরাধকৃদপি মুচ্যতে হরিসংশ্রয়ঃ ।<br />হরেরপ্যপরাধান্ যঃ কুর্য্যাদ্দ্বিপাদপাংসনঃ ॥১০১॥<br />নামাশ্রয়ঃ কদাচিৎ স্যাত্তরত্যেষ স নামতঃ ।<br />নাম্নো হি সর্ব্বসুহৃদো হ্যপরাধাৎ পতত্যধঃ’ ॥১০২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ‘sarvāparādha-kṛd api muchyate hari-saṁśrayaḥ<br />harer apy aparādhān yaḥ kuryād dvipāda-pāṁsanaḥ [101]<span class=\\"e2\\"><br /></span>nāmāśrayaḥ kadāchit syāt taraty eṣa sa nāmataḥ<br />nāmno hi sarva-suhṛdo hy aparādhāt pataty adhaḥ’ [102]"},{"class":"b50","text":" “[Śrī Sanat Kumār said:] “All kinds of offenders are delivered by taking shelter of the Lord, and two-legged animals who offend even the Lord are delivered by the Lord’s Name when they take shelter of the Name. The Name is certainly the true friend of every soul, but you will certainly fall down by offending the Name.”’"},{"class":"b97","text":" পাপ তাপ অপরাধ জীবের যত হয় ।<br />শ্রীহরিসংশ্রয়ে সব সদ্য হয় ক্ষয় ॥১০৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" pāpa tāpa aparādha jīvera yata haya<br />śrī-hari-saṁśraye saba sadya haya kṣaya [103]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-hari-saṁśraye</span>–By taking shelter of the Lord, <span class=\\"e2\\">saba yata</span>–all the <span class=\\"e2\\">pāpa</span>–sins, <span class=\\"e2\\">tāpa</span>–sorrows, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">aparādha</span>–offences <span class=\\"e2\\">jīvera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–the soul has incurred <span class=\\"e2\\">kṣaya haya</span>–are destroyed <span class=\\"e2\\">sadya</span>–immediately."},{"class":"b71","text":" [Śrīman Mahāprabhu paraphrases:] “Taking shelter of the Lord immediately destroys all the soul’s sins, sorrows, and offences."},{"class":"b176","text":" কলির সংসার ছাড়িয়া কৃষ্ণের সংসার কর"},{"class":"b177","text":" kalira saṁsāra chhāḍiyā kṛṣṇera saṁsāra kara"},{"class":"b70","text":" Leave Kali’s family and join Kṛṣṇa’s family"},{"class":"b97","text":" কলির সংসার ছাড়ি’ কৃষ্ণের সংসার ।<br />অকৈতবে করে যেই অপরাধ নাহি তার ॥১০৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kalira saṁsāra chhāḍi’ kṛṣṇera saṁsāra<br />akaitave kare yei aparādha nāhi tāra [104]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra yei</span>–Those who <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍi’</span>–leave <span class=\\"e2\\">kalira</span>–Kali’s <span class=\\"e2\\">saṁsāra</span>–family [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">akaitave</span>–sincerely <span class=\\"e2\\">kare</span>–act [as members of] <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇera</span>–Kṛṣṇa’s <span class=\\"e2\\">saṁsāra</span>–family <span class=\\"e2\\">nāhi</span>–make no <span class=\\"e2\\">aparādha</span>–offences."},{"class":"b71","text":" “Those who leave Kali’s family and sincerely live as members of Kṛṣṇa’s family commit no offences."},{"class":"b176","text":" দীক্ষাকালে অকৈতবে আত্মনিবেদনে সর্ব্বপাপক্ষয়"},{"class":"b177","text":" dīkṣā-kāle akaitave ātma-nivedane sarva-pāpa-kṣaya"},{"class":"b70","text":" Sincere self-surrender at the time of initiation destroys all sin"},{"class":"b97","text":" পূর্ব্ব যত পাপাদি বহু জন্মে করে ।<br />হরিদীক্ষামাত্রে সেই সব পাপে তরে ॥১০৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" pūrva yata pāpādi bahu janme kare<br />hari-dīkṣā-mātre sei saba pāpe tare [105]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">hari-dīkṣā-mātre</span>–Simply taking initiation [into the Lord’s service] <span class=\\"e2\\">tare</span>–destroys <span class=\\"e2\\">sei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">saba</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">pāpe yata</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">pāpādi</span>–all the sins and offences [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">kare</span>–you committed <span class=\\"e2\\">pūrva</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bahu</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">janme</span>–in [your] numerous previous births."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Simply taking initiation into the Lord’s service destroys all the sins and offences that you committed in all your previous births."},{"class":"b97","text":" অকৈতবে করে যবে আত্মনিবেদন ।<br />কৃষ্ণ তার পূর্ব্ব পাপ করেন খণ্ডন ॥১০৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" akaitave kare yabe ātma-nivedana<br />kṛṣṇa tāra pūrva pāpa karena khaṇḍana [106]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">yabe</span>–When [someone] <span class=\\"e2\\">akaitave</span>–sincerely <span class=\\"e2\\">ātma-nivedana kare</span>–surrenders themself, <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span>–Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">khaṇḍana karena</span>–cuts away [all] <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra</span>–their <span class=\\"e2\\">pūrva</span>–previous <span class=\\"e2\\">pāpa</span>–sins."},{"class":"b50","text":" “When you sincerely surrender yourself, Kṛṣṇa cuts away all your previous sins."},{"class":"b97","text":" প্রায়শ্চিত্ত করিবারে তার নাহি হয় ।<br />দীক্ষামাত্র পাপক্ষয় সর্ব্বশাস্ত্রে কয় ॥১০৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" prāyaśchitta karibāre tāra nāhi haya<br />dīkṣā-mātra pāpa-kṣaya sarva-śāstre kaya [107]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haya nāhi</span>–They do not need <span class=\\"e2\\">karibāre</span>–to make <span class=\\"e2\\">prāyaśchitta</span>–atonement: <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-śāstre</span>–all the scriptures <span class=\\"e2\\">kaya</span>–say [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">dīkṣā-mātra</span>–initiation alone <span class=\\"e2\\">pāpa-kṣaya</span>–destroys sins."},{"class":"b50","text":" “You do not need to make any atonement: all the scriptures say that initiation alone destroys all sins."},{"class":"b97","text":" নিষ্কপটে হর্য্যাশ্রয় করে যেই জন ।<br />সর্ব্ব অপরাধ তার বিনষ্ট তখন ॥১০৮॥<br />আর পাপতাপে কভু রুচি নাহি হয় ।<br />পুণ্য পাপ দূরে যায়, মায়া করে জয় ॥১০৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" niṣkapaṭe haryāśraya kare yei jana<br />sarva aparādha tāra vinaṣṭa takhana [108]<br />āra pāpa-tāpe kabhu ruchi nāhi haya<br />puṇya pāpa dūre yāya, māyā kare jaya [109]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [When] <span class=\\"e2\\">yei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">jana</span>–someone <span class=\\"e2\\">niṣkapaṭe</span>–sincerely <span class=\\"e2\\">haryāśraya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kare</span>–takes shelter of the Lord, <span class=\\"e2\\">takhana</span>–then <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra sarva</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">aparādha</span>–all their offences [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">vinaṣṭa</span>–destroyed, <span class=\\"e2\\">āra kabhu</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haya nāhi</span>–they never again have any more <span class=\\"e2\\">ruchi</span>–taste <span class=\\"e2\\">pāpa-tāpe</span>–for sin and suffering, [their] <span class=\\"e2\\">puṇya</span>–piety [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">pāpa</span>–sins <span class=\\"e2\\">dūre</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">yāya</span>–go away, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">jaya kare</span>–they conquer <span class=\\"e2\\">māyā</span>–the illusory environment."},{"class":"b71","text":" “When you sincerely take shelter of the Lord, all your offences are destroyed, you never again have any taste for sin and suffering, your piety and sins disappear, and you conquer the illusory environment."},{"class":"b176","text":" সেবা-অপরাধ"},{"class":"b177","text":" sevā-aparādha"},{"class":"b70","text":" Offences in worship*"},{"class":"b97","text":" তবে তার কভু হয় সেবা-অপরাধ ।<br />সেই অপরাধে হয় ভক্তিক্রিয়াবাধ ॥১১০॥<br />সাধুসঙ্গে করে কৃষ্ণনামের আশ্রয় ।<br />নামাশ্রয়ে সেবা-অপরাধ নষ্ট হয় ॥১১১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" tabe tāra kabhu haya sevā-aparādha<br />sei aparādhe haya bhakti-kriyā-bādha [110]<br />sādhu-saṅge kare kṛṣṇa-nāmera āśraya<br />nāmāśraye sevā-aparādha naṣṭa haya [111]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">tabe</span>–Thereafter, <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sevā-aparādha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu haya</span>–someone [may] sometimes commit offences in worship, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakti-kriyā-bādha haya</span>–the practice of devotion is obstructed <span class=\\"e2\\">sei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">aparādhe</span>–by such offences. [But if] <span class=\\"e2\\">āśraya kare</span>–someone takes shelter <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-nāmera</span>–of the Name of Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">sādhu-saṅge</span>–in the association of the sādhus, [all] <span class=\\"e2\\">sevā-aparādha</span>–offences in worship <span class=\\"e2\\">naṣṭa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–are destroyed <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmāśraye</span>–by the Name’s shelter."},{"class":"b43","text":" “After surrendering at initiation, you still may sometimes commit offences in worship, and such offences will obstruct your practice of devotion. But if you take shelter of the Name of Kṛṣṇa in the association of the sādhus, the Name’s shelter will destroy all such offences."},{"class":"b69","text":" *Thirty-two types of offences in worship are listed in <span class=\\"e3\\">Śrī Hari-bhakti-vilāsa</span> (8.441–8): (1) Entering the Lord’s Temple in a vehicle or while wearing shoes. (2) Not observing the Lord’s birthday and other Pastimes. (3) Not offering obeisance when coming before the Deity. (4) Visiting the Deity without appropriately washing oneself"},{"class":"b97","text":" নামকৃপা হৈলে জীব সর্ব্বশুদ্ধি পায় ।<br />কৃষ্ণের নিকট গিয়া করে শুদ্ধসেবার আশ্রয় ॥১১২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" nāma-kṛpā haile jīva sarva-śuddhi pāya<br />kṛṣṇera nikaṭa giyā kare śuddha-sevāra āśraya [112]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-kṛpā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haile</span>–When souls receive the mercy of the Name <span class=\\"e2\\">jīva</span>–souls <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-śuddhi</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">pāya</span>–become completely pure, <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nikaṭa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">giyā</span>–reach Kṛṣṇa, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">śuddha-sevāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">āśraya kare</span>–take shelter in pure service."},{"class":"b71","text":" “When souls receive the mercy of the Name, they become completely pure, reach Kṛṣṇa, and render pure service."},{"class":"b176","text":" সর্ব্বদা নামাপরাধ বর্জ্জনীয়"},{"class":"b177","text":" sarvadā nāmāparādha varjanīya"},{"class":"b70","text":" Offences to the Name must be avoided always"},{"class":"b97","text":" কিন্তু যদি নাম-অপরাধ তার হয় ।<br />তবে পুনঃ অধঃপাত হইবে নিশ্চয় ॥১১৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kintu yadi nāma-aparādha tāra haya<br />tabe punaḥ adhaḥpāta ha-ibe niśchaya [113]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">yadi</span>–If, <span class=\\"e2\\">kintu</span>–however, <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra nāma-aparādha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–someone offends the Name, <span class=\\"e2\\">tabe</span>–then <span class=\\"e2\\">niśchaya</span>–certainly <span class=\\"e2\\">adhaḥpāta</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-ibe</span>–they will fall down <span class=\\"e2\\">punaḥ</span>–again."},{"class":"b43","text":" “If, however, you offend the Name, you will certainly fall down again."},{"class":"b69","text":" after eating or evacuating. (5) Offering obeisance with one hand. (6) Circumambulating others before the Deity. (7) Spreading your legs before the Deity. (8) Sitting before the Deity while holding up your knees with your forearms. (9) Lying down before the Deity. (10) Eating before the Deity. (11) Telling lies before the Deity. (12) Speaking loudly before the Deity. (13) Conversing privately before the Deity. (14) Crying before the Deity (over a worldly matter). (15) Quarrelling before the Deity. (16) Punishing someone before the Deity. (17) Being charitable to someone before the Deity. (18) Behaving cruelly towards someone. (19) Serving the Deity while covered with a wool, fur, or down blanket. (20) Criticising others before the Deity. (21) Praising others before the Deity. (22) Using foul language before the Deity. (23) Passing air (or belching) before the Deity. (24) Offering low quality articles to the Deity when you are able to provide good quality ones. (25) Taking items for yourself that have not been offered to the Deity. (26) Not offering fruits and grains to the Deity when they come into season. (27) Offering the Deity articles that have partially used by others. (28) Sitting with your back to the Deity. (29) Offering obeisances to others before the Deity (one should offer obeisance to Śrī Gurudev before the Deity, but not to Vaiṣṇavas in general). (30) Remaining quiet and not offering praise, obeisance, and so on, before Śrī Gurudev. (31) Praising oneself before Śrī Gurudev. (32) Criticising the gods."},{"class":"b97","text":" সর্ব্বজীব-বন্ধু নাম, তাঁর অপরাধ ।<br />কোনক্রমে ক্ষয় নহে প্রাপ্ত্যে হয় বাধ ॥১১৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sarva-jīva-bandhu nāma, tā̐ra aparādha<br />kona-krame kṣaya nahe prāptye haya bādha [114]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–The Name [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-jīva-bandhu</span>–the friend of every soul, [but] <span class=\\"e2\\">tā̐ra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">aparādha</span>–offences against Him <span class=\\"e2\\">bādha haya</span>–obstruct [the soul] <span class=\\"e2\\">prāptye</span>–in [their] progress [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">nahe</span>–are not <span class=\\"e2\\">kṣaya</span>–destroyed <span class=\\"e2\\">kona-krame</span>–by any means (other than surrender to the Name)."},{"class":"b50","text":" “The Name is the friend of every soul, but offences against Him obstruct the soul’s progress and cannot be counteracted by any means."},{"class":"b97","text":" নাম অপরাধ ত্যাগ বহু যত্নে করি’ ।<br />লভে জীব সর্ব্বসিদ্ধি প্রাপ্ত হয় হরি ॥১১৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" nāma aparādha tyāga bahu yatne kari’<br />labhe jīva sarva-siddhi prāpta haya hari [115]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bahu</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">yatne</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kari’</span>–By very carefully <span class=\\"e2\\">tyāga</span>–avoiding <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">aparādha</span>–the offences to the Name, <span class=\\"e2\\">jīva</span>–the soul <span class=\\"e2\\">labhe</span>–attains <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-siddhi</span>–all perfection [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">prāpta</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–reaches <span class=\\"e2\\">hari</span>–the Lord."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Only by very carefully avoiding the offences to the Name does the soul attain all perfection and reach the Lord."},{"class":"b97","text":" ‘এবং নারদঃ শঙ্করেণ কৃপয়া মহ্যং মুনীনাং পরং<br />প্রোক্তং নাম সুখাবহং ভগবতো বর্জ্জ্যং সদা যত্নতঃ ।<br />যে জ্ঞাত্বাপি ন বর্জ্জয়ন্তি সহসা নামাপরাধান্দশ<br />ক্রুদ্ধা মাতরমপ্যভোজনপরাঃ খিদ্যন্তি তে বালবৎ’ ॥১১৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ‘evaṁ nāradaḥ śaṅkareṇa kṛpayā mahyaṁ munīnāṁ paraṁ<br />proktaṁ nāma sukhāvahaṁ bhagavato varjyaṁ sadā yatnataḥ<br />ye jñātvāpi na varjayanti sahasā nāmāparādhān daśa<br />kruddhā mātaram apy abhojana-parāḥ khidyanti te bālavat’ [116]"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘[Śrī Sanat Kumar said:] “O Nārad, in this way Śiva mercifully spoke to me and the great sages about the Name of the Lord, the source of all happiness. Those who understand these ten offences to the Name—which must always be carefully avoided—but still do not immediately avoid them are like children who become angry with their mothers, refuse to eat, and then suffer.”’"},{"class":"b97","text":" আমি পূর্ব্বে শিবলোকে শঙ্করসন্নিধানে ।<br />নাম-অপরাধ-কথা জিজ্ঞাসিলাম মুনে ॥১১৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" āmi pūrve śivaloke śaṅkara-sannidhāne<br />nāma-aparādha-kathā jijñāsilāma mune [117]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">mune</span>–O sage (O Nārad Muni), <span class=\\"e2\\">pūrve</span>–previously, <span class=\\"e2\\">śivaloke</span>–in the abode of Lord Śiva, <span class=\\"e2\\">śaṅkara-sannidhāne</span>–in the association of Lord Śiva, <span class=\\"e2\\">āmi</span>–I <span class=\\"e2\\">jijñāsilāma</span>–asked <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-aparādha-kathā</span>–about the offences to the Name."},{"class":"b50","text":" [Śrīman Mahāprabhu paraphrases:] “O sage, previously, in Śivaloka, I asked Śaṅkar about the offences to the Name."},{"class":"b97","text":" বহুমুনিগণ মধ্যে শম্ভু কৃপা করি’ ।<br />আমায় উপদেশ করে কৈলাস উপরি ॥১১৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" bahu-muni-gaṇa madhye śambhu kṛpā kari’<br />āmāya upadeśa kare kailāsa upari [118]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">upari</span>–Atop <span class=\\"e2\\">kailāsa</span>–Mount Kailash, <span class=\\"e2\\">bahu-muni-gaṇa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">madhye</span>–in the midst of many sages, <span class=\\"e2\\">śambhu</span>–Śiva <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛpā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kari’</span>–mercifully <span class=\\"e2\\">upadeśa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kare</span>–instructed <span class=\\"e2\\">āmāya</span>–me."},{"class":"b50","text":" “There, on Mount Kailash, in the midst of many sages, Śambhu mercifully instructed me."},{"class":"b97","text":" ভগবানের নাম সর্ব্বজীবসুখাবহ ।<br />তাতে অপরাধ সর্ব্ব-অমঙ্গল-বহ ॥১১৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" bhagavānera nāma sarva-jīva-sukhāvaha<br />tāte aparādha sarva-amaṅgala-vaha [119]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–The Name<span class=\\"e2\\"> bhagavānera</span>–of the Lord [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-jīva-sukhāvaha</span>–the source of all happiness for the souls, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">aparādha</span>–offences <span class=\\"e2\\">tāte</span>–to Him [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-amaṅgala-vaha</span>–the source of all inauspiciousness."},{"class":"b50","text":" “The Name of the Lord is the source of all happiness for the soul, and offences to the Name are the source of all inauspiciousness."},{"class":"b97","text":" মঙ্গল লভিতে যার ইচ্ছা আছে মনে ।<br />সদা নাম-অপরাধ বর্জ্জিবে যতনে ॥১২০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" maṅgala labhite yāra ichchhā āchhe mane<br />sadā nāma-aparādha varjibe yatane [120]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">yāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ichchhā mane</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">āchhe</span>–Those who desire <span class=\\"e2\\">labhite</span>–to attain <span class=\\"e2\\">maṅgala</span>–auspiciousness <span class=\\"e2\\">varjibe</span>–must avoid <span class=\\"e2\\">yatane</span>–carefully <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-aparādha</span>–the offences to the Name <span class=\\"e2\\">sadā</span>–always."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Those who desire auspiciousness must always carefully avoid the offences to the Name."},{"class":"b97","text":" সাধুগুরুসন্নিধানে বহু দৈন্য ধরি’ ।<br />দশ অপরাধ-তত্ত্ব লবে শিক্ষা করি’ ॥১২১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sādhu-guru-sannidhāne bahu dainya dhari’<br />daśa aparādha-tattva labe śikṣā kari’ [121]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bahu</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">dainya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">dhari’</span>–With great humility, <span class=\\"e2\\">śikṣā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kari’</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">labe</span>–you should learn <span class=\\"e2\\">daśa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">aparādha-tattva</span>–the ten offences <span class=\\"e2\\">sādhu-guru-sannidhāne</span>–from Śrī Guru and the sādhus."},{"class":"b50","text":" “With great humility, you should learn the ten offences from Śrī Guru and the sādhus."},{"class":"b97","text":" অপরাধগুলি যত্নে জানিয়া ত্যজিবে ।<br />সত্বরে শ্রীহরিনামে প্রেম উপজিবে ॥১২২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" aparādhaguli yatne jāniyā tyajibe<br />satvare śrī-hari-nāme prema upajibe [122]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">yatne</span>–Carefully <span class=\\"e2\\">jāniyā</span>–having understood <span class=\\"e2\\">aparādhaguli</span>–these offences, <span class=\\"e2\\">tyajibe</span>–you should avoid [them]. [Then] <span class=\\"e2\\">upajibe</span>–you will develop <span class=\\"e2\\">satvare</span>–quickly <span class=\\"e2\\">prema</span>–divine love <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-hari-nāme</span>–by [chanting] the Lord’s Name."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Having carefully understood the offences, you should avoid them. Then you will quickly develop divine love for the Lord’s Name."},{"class":"b97","text":" নাম পেয়ে অপরাধ বর্জ্জন না করে ।<br />সহসা তাহারে দশ অপরাধ ধরে ॥১২৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" nāma peye aparādha varjana nā kare<br />sahasā tāhāre daśa aparādha dhare [123]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">daśa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">aparādha</span>–The ten offences <span class=\\"e2\\">sahasā</span>–immediately <span class=\\"e2\\">dhare</span>–seize <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhāre</span>–those who <span class=\\"e2\\">peye</span>–receive <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–the Name [but] <span class=\\"e2\\">varjana</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kare nā</span>–do not avoid <span class=\\"e2\\">aparādha</span>–offences."},{"class":"b71","text":" “The ten offences immediately seize those who receive the Name but do not try to avoid them."},{"class":"b176","text":" অপরাধ বর্জ্জন না করিয়া নাম করা মূঢ়তা"},{"class":"b177","text":" aparādha varjana nā kariyā nāma karā mūḍhatā"},{"class":"b70","text":" Chanting the Name but not avoiding the offences is foolishness"},{"class":"b97","text":" অপরাধ বুঝিয়া যে বর্জ্জনে উদাসীন ।<br />তার দুঃখ নিরন্তর সেই অর্ব্বাচীন ॥১২৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" aparādha bujhiyā ye varjane udāsīna<br />tāra duḥkha nirantara sei arvāchīna [124]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sei ye</span>–Those who <span class=\\"e2\\">bujhiyā</span>–understand <span class=\\"e2\\">aparādha</span>–the offences [but are] <span class=\\"e2\\">udāsīna</span>–unconcerned <span class=\\"e2\\">varjane</span>–about avoiding [them are] <span class=\\"e2\\">arvāchīna</span>–foolish, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra</span>–their <span class=\\"e2\\">duḥkha</span>–suffering [goes on] <span class=\\"e2\\">nirantara</span>–forever."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Those who understand the offences but are unconcerned about avoiding them are foolish and suffer forever."},{"class":"b97","text":" মায়ে ক্রোধ করি’ বালক না করে ভোজন ।<br />সুপথ্য অভাবে সদা ক্লেশের ভাজন ॥১২৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" māye krodha kari’ bālaka nā kare bhojana<br />supathya abhāve sadā kleśera bhājana [125]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bālaka</span>–Children [who] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhojana kare nā</span>–do not eat, <span class=\\"e2\\">krodha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kari’</span>–being angry <span class=\\"e2\\">māye</span>–with [their] mothers, <span class=\\"e2\\">sadā</span>–always [become] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhājana</span>–a subject <span class=\\"e2\\">kleśera</span>–of suffering <span class=\\"e2\\">supathya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">abhāve</span>–because of a lack of nourishment."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Children who do not eat out of anger at their mothers always end up suffering without nourishment."},{"class":"b97","text":" সেইরূপ অপরাধ বর্জ্জন না করি’ ।<br />নাম করে মূঢ় নিজ শিব পরিহরি’ ॥১২৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sei-rūpa aparādha varjana nā kari’<br />nāma kare mūḍha nija śiva parihari’ [126]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sei-rūpa</span>–Similarly, <span class=\\"e2\\">mūḍha</span>–fools [who] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kare</span>–chant the Name [but] <span class=\\"e2\\">varjana</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kari’ nā</span>–do not avoid <span class=\\"e2\\">aparādha</span>–the offences <span class=\\"e2\\">parihari’</span>–throw away <span class=\\"e2\\">nija</span>–their own <span class=\\"e2\\">śiva</span>–good fortune."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Like such angry children, fools who chant the Name but do not avoid the offences throw away their own good fortune.”"},{"class":"b97","text":" ‘অপরাধবিমুক্তো হি নাম্নি জপ্তং সদাচর ।<br />নাম্নৈব তব দেবর্ষে সর্ব্বাং সেৎস্যতি নান্যথা’ ॥১২৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ‘aparādha-vimukto hi nāmni japtaṁ sadāchara<br />nāmnaiva tava devarṣe sarvāṁ setsyati nānyathā’ [127]"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘[Śrī Sanat Kumar said:] “Be free from the offences and always chant the Name. O sage amongst the gods, you will attain everything only through the Name, and not otherwise.”’"},{"class":"b97","text":" সনৎকুমার বলে, ‘ওহে দেবর্ষিপ্রবর ।<br />নিরপরাধে নাম জপ সদাই আচর ॥১২৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sanat kumāra bale, ‘ohe devarṣi-pravara<br />niraparādhe nāma japa sadāi āchara [128]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sanat</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kumāra</span>–Sanat Kumār <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–said, <span class=\\"e2\\">‘ohe</span>–‘O <span class=\\"e2\\">devarṣi-pravara</span>–best of the sages amongst the gods, <span class=\\"e2\\">sadāi</span>–always [engage in] <span class=\\"e2\\">āchara</span>–the practice <span class=\\"e2\\">japa</span>–of chanting <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–the Name <span class=\\"e2\\">niraparādhe</span>–without offence."},{"class":"b50","text":" [Śrīman Mahāprabhu paraphrases:] “Sanat Kumār said, ‘O best of the sages amongst the gods, always chant the Name without offence."},{"class":"b97","text":" নাম বিনা অন্য পন্থা নাহি প্রয়োজন ।<br />নামেতে সকল সিদ্ধি পাবে তপোধন’ ॥১২৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" nāma vinā anya panthā nāhi prayojana<br />nāmete sakala siddhi pābe tapo-dhana’ [129]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">nāhi</span>–There is no <span class=\\"e2\\">prayojana</span>–need <span class=\\"e2\\">anya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">panthā</span>–for any path <span class=\\"e2\\">vinā</span>–other [than] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–the Name. <span class=\\"e2\\">tapo-dhana</span>–O Nārad (‘he whose wealth is austerity’), <span class=\\"e2\\">pābe</span>–you will attain <span class=\\"e2\\">sakala</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">siddhi</span>–all perfection <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmete’</span>–through the Name.’"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘There is no need for any path other than the Name. O Nārad, You will attain all perfection through the Name.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" ‘শ্রীনারদ উবাচ—<br />সনৎকুমার প্রিয় সাহসানাং<br />বিবেক-বৈরাগ্যবিবর্জ্জিতানাম্ ।<br />দেহপ্রিয়ার্থাত্ম্য-পরায়ণানাম্<br />উক্তাপরাধাঃ প্রভবন্তি নো কথম্’ ॥১৩০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ‘śrī-nārada uvācha—<br />sanat-kumāra priya sāhasānāṁ<br />viveka-vairāgya-vivarjitānām<br />deha-priyārthātmya-parāyaṇānām<br />uktāparādhāḥ prabhavanti no katham’ [130]"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘Śrī Nārad said: “Dear Sanat Kumar, we are unruly, devoid of good judgement and renunciation, and engrossed in our bodies, companions, and wealth. How will we stop committing the offences you have described?”’"},{"class":"b97","text":" ওহে সনৎকুমার তুমি সিদ্ধ হরিদাস ।<br />অনায়াসে করিলে নামরহস্যপ্রকাশ ॥১৩১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ohe sanat-kumāra tumi siddha haridāsa<br />anāyāse karile nāma-rahasya-prakāśa [131]"},{"class":"b101","text":" “[Nārad said,] <span class=\\"e2\\">ohe</span>–O <span class=\\"e2\\">sanat-kumāra</span>–Sanat Kumār, <span class=\\"e2\\">tumi</span>–you [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">siddha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haridāsa</span>–a perfect servant of the Lord, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">anāyāse</span>–clearly <span class=\\"e2\\">prakāśa karile</span>–you have revealed <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-rahasya</span>–the hidden truths about the Name."},{"class":"b71","text":" [Śrīman Mahāprabhu paraphrases:] “Nārad said, ‘O Sanat Kumār, you are a perfect servant of the Lord, and you have clearly revealed the hidden truths about the Name."},{"class":"b176","text":" সাধকের নামাপরাধ বর্জ্জনোপায়"},{"class":"b177","text":" sādhakera nāmāparādha varjanopāya"},{"class":"b70","text":" The means for practitioners to avoid the offences to the Name"},{"class":"b97","text":" সাধক আমরা আমাদের বড় ভয় ।<br />অপরাধ-ত্যাগে যত্ন কিরূপেতে হয় ॥১৩২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sādhaka āmarā āmādera baḍa bhaya<br />aparādha tyāge yatna ki-rūpete haya [132]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">āmarā</span>–We [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">sādhaka</span>–practitioners, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">āmādera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">baḍa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaya</span>–we are very afraid. <span class=\\"e2\\">ki-rūpete</span>–How <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–are [we to] <span class=\\"e2\\">yatna</span>–try <span class=\\"e2\\">tyāge</span>–to avoid <span class=\\"e2\\">aparādha</span>–the offences?"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘We are practitioners, and we are very afraid. How should we try to avoid the offences?"},{"class":"b97","text":" বিষয় মোদের বন্ধু তাহার সাহসে ।<br />করিবে সকল কর্ম্ম বদ্ধ মায়াপাশে ॥১৩৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" viṣaya modera bandhu tāhāra sāhase<br />karibe sakala karma baddha māyā-pāśe [133]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">viṣaya</span>–Material things [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">modera</span>–our <span class=\\"e2\\">bandhu</span>–friends. <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sāhase</span>–With their audacity, <span class=\\"e2\\">baddha karibe</span>–they bind <span class=\\"e2\\">sakala</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">karma</span>–all [our] actions <span class=\\"e2\\">māyā-pāśe</span>–in māyā’s ropes."},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘Material things are our friends, and they audaciously bind all our actions in māyā’s ropes."},{"class":"b97","text":" বিবেকবৈরাগ্যশূন্য দেহ প্রিয়জন ।<br />অর্থস্বরূপে মোরা সদা পরায়ণ ॥১৩৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" viveka-vairāgya-śūnya deha priya-jana<br />artha-svarūpe morā sadā parāyaṇa [134]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [We are] <span class=\\"e2\\">viveka-vairāgya-śūnya</span>–devoid of good judgement or renunciation, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">morā</span>–we [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">sadā</span>–always <span class=\\"e2\\">parāyaṇa</span>–engrossed <span class=\\"e2\\">artha-svarūpe</span>–in [our] wealth, <span class=\\"e2\\">deha</span>–bodies, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">priya-jana</span>–companions."},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘We have no good judgement or renunciation, and we are always engrossed in our bodies, companions, and wealth."},{"class":"b97","text":" কিরূপে সাধক-মনে অপরাধ দশ ।<br />নাহি উপজিবে তাহা করহ প্রকাশ ॥১৩৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ki-rūpe sādhaka-mane aparādha daśa<br />nāhi upajibe tāhā karaha prakāśa [135]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">prakāśa karaha</span>–Please explain <span class=\\"e2\\">ki-rūpe</span>–how <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhā daśa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">aparādha</span>–the ten offences <span class=\\"e2\\">upajibe nāhi</span>–will not arise <span class=\\"e2\\">sādhaka-mane’</span>–in the minds of practitioners [like us]."},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘Please explain how the ten offences can be stopped from arising in the minds of practitioners like us.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" ‘শ্রীসনৎকুমার উবাচ—<br />জাতে নামাপরাধে তু প্রমাদে বৈ কথঞ্চন ।<br />সদা সঙ্কীর্ত্তয়েন্নাম তদেকশরণো ভবেৎ ॥১৩৬॥<br />নামাপরাধযুক্তানাং নামান্যেব হরন্ত্যঘম্ ।<br />অবিশ্রান্ত-প্রযুক্তানি তান্যেবার্থকরাণি হি’ ॥১৩৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ‘śrī-sanat-kumāra uvācha—<br />jāte nāmāparādhe tu pramāde vai kathañchana<br />sadā saṅkīrtayan nāma tad-eka-śaraṇo bhavet [136]<br />nāmāparādha-yuktānāṁ nāmāny eva haranty agham<br />aviśrānta-prayuktāni tāny evārthakarāṇi cha’ [137]"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘Śrī Sanat Kumār replied: “If someone offends the Name, out of negligence or otherwise, they must constantly chant the Name and take shelter of the Name exclusively. Only the Name destroys the sins of those who chant the Name with offences. When chanted constantly, the Name is certainly effective.”’"},{"class":"b97","text":" নামেতে শরণাপত্তি যেই ক্ষণে হয় ।<br />তখনই নামাপরাধের সদ্য হয় ক্ষয় ॥১৩৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" nāmete śaraṇāpatti yei kṣaṇe haya<br />takhana-i nāmāparādhera sadya haya kṣaya [138]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">takhana-i yei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kṣaṇe</span>–At the moment <span class=\\"e2\\">śaraṇāpatti haya</span>–someone surrenders <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmete</span>–to the Name, [their] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmāparādhera kṣaya haya</span>–offences to the Name are destroyed <span class=\\"e2\\">sadya</span>–immediately."},{"class":"b50","text":" [Śrīman Mahāprabhu paraphrases:] “Your offences to the Name are destroyed immediately the moment you surrender to the Name."},{"class":"b97","text":" তথাপি প্রমাদে যদি উঠে অপরাধ ।<br />তাহাতেও ভক্তিতে হইয়া পড়ে বাধ ॥১৩৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" tathāpi pramāde yadi uṭhe aparādha<br />tāhāteo bhaktite ha-iyā paḍe bādha [139]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">tathāpi</span>–Still, <span class=\\"e2\\">yadi</span>–if <span class=\\"e2\\">aparādha uṭhe</span>–offences arise <span class=\\"e2\\">pramāde</span>–out of negligence, [then] [your practice of] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaktite</span>–devotion <span class=\\"e2\\">bādha ha-iyā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">paḍe</span>–becomes obstructed <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhāteo</span>–by that also."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Still, if you happen to commit offences out of negligence, then those offences will obstruct your practice of devotion."},{"class":"b97","text":" অপরাধ প্রমাদেতে হইবে যখন ।<br />নামসঙ্কীর্ত্তন তবে করিবে অনুক্ষণ ॥১৪০॥<br />নামেতে শরণাগতি সুদৃঢ় করিবে ।<br />অনুক্ষণ নামবলে অপরাধ যাবে ॥১৪১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" aparādha pramādete ha-ibe yakhana<br />nāma-saṅkīrtana tabe karibe anukṣaṇa [140]<br />nāmete śaraṇāgati sudṛḍha karibe<br />anukṣaṇa nāma-bale aparādha yābe [141]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">yakhana</span>–When <span class=\\"e2\\">aparādha</span>–offences <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-ibe</span>–occur <span class=\\"e2\\">pramādete</span>–out of negligence, <span class=\\"e2\\">tabe</span>–then <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-saṅkīrtana</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">karibe</span>–you must chant the Name <span class=\\"e2\\">anukṣaṇa</span>–at every moment, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">sudṛḍha śaraṇāgati</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">karibe</span>–you must firmly surrender <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmete</span>–to the Name. <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-bale</span>–By chanting the Name <span class=\\"e2\\">anukṣaṇa</span>–at every moment, [your] <span class=\\"e2\\">aparādha</span>–offences <span class=\\"e2\\">yābe</span>–will go away."},{"class":"b71","text":" “When offences occur out of negligence, you must chant the Name at every moment and surrender to the Name with firm resolve. By chanting the Name at every moment, your offences will go away."},{"class":"b176","text":" নামই উপায়"},{"class":"b177","text":" nāma-i upāya"},{"class":"b70","text":" The Name is the only means"},{"class":"b97","text":" নামেই নামাপরাধ হইবেক ক্ষয় ।<br />অপরাধ নাশিতে আর কারও শক্তি নয় ॥১৪২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" nāmei nāmāparādha ha-ibeka kṣaya<br />aparādha nāśite āra kārao śakti naya [142]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmāparādha</span>–Offences to the Name <span class=\\"e2\\">kṣaya ha-ibeka</span>–will be destroyed <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmei</span>–only by the Name. <span class=\\"e2\\">āra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kārao</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">śakti</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">naya</span>–Nothing else has the power <span class=\\"e2\\">nāśite</span>–to destroy <span class=\\"e2\\">aparādha</span>–the offences."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Only the Name destroys offences against the Name; nothing else has the power to do so."},{"class":"b97","text":" এ বিষয়ে মূলতত্ত্ব বলি হে তোমায় ।<br />বুঝহ নারদ তুমি বেদে যাহা গায় ॥১৪৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" e viṣaye mūla-tattva bali he tomāya<br />bujhaha nārada tumi vede yāhā gāya [143]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bali</span>–I am telling <span class=\\"e2\\">tomāya</span>–you <span class=\\"e2\\">mūla-tattva</span>–the fundamental truth <span class=\\"e2\\">e</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">viṣaye</span>–in this regard, <span class=\\"e2\\">yāhā</span>–which <span class=\\"e2\\">vede</span>–the scriptures <span class=\\"e2\\">gāya</span>–proclaim. <span class=\\"e2\\">he</span>–O <span class=\\"e2\\">nārada</span>–Nārad, <span class=\\"e2\\">tumi bujhaha</span>–you should understand [this]."},{"class":"b50","text":" “I am telling you the fundamental truth about chanting the Name, which the scriptures proclaim. O Nārad, try to understand it."},{"class":"b97","text":" ‘নামৈকং যস্য বাচি স্মরণপথগতং শ্রোত্রমূলং গতং বা<br />শুদ্ধং বাশুদ্ধবর্ণং ব্যবহিতরহিতং তারয়ত্যেব সত্যম্ ।<br />তচ্চেদ্দেহ-দ্রবিণ-জনতা-লোভ-পাষণ্ড-মধ্যে<br />নিক্ষিপ্তং স্যান্নফলজনকং শীঘ্রমেবাত্র বিপ্র’ ॥১৪৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ‘nāmaikaṁ yasya vāchi smaraṇa-patha-gataṁ śrotra-mūlaṁ gataṁ vā<br />śuddhaṁ vāśuddha-varṇaṁ vyavahita-rahitaṁ tārayaty eva satyam<br />tach ched deha-draviṇa-janatā-lobha-pāṣaṇḍa-madhye<br />nikṣiptaṁ syān na phala-janakaṁ śīghram evātra vipra’ [144]"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘[Śrī Sanat Kumār said:] “The Name, when unconcealed, certainly delivers anyone who once calls, remembers, or hears Him, regardless of whether they utter the Name correctly or incorrectly. But, O brāhmaṇ, if the Name is used for the body, wealth, prestige, greed, or evil, the Name does not produce any quick results.”’"},{"class":"b97","text":" যার মুখে উচ্চারিত এক কৃষ্ণনাম ।<br />যাহার স্মরণপথে এক নাম গুণধাম ॥১৪৫॥<br />যার শ্রোত্রমূলে তাহা প্রবেশ করিবে ।<br />ব্যবহিত-রহিত হৈলে তখনই তারিবে ॥১৪৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" yāra mukhe uchchārita eka kṛṣṇa-nāma<br />yāhāra smaraṇa-pathe eka nāma guṇa-dhāma [145]<br />yāra śrotra-mūle tāhā praveśa karibe<br />vyavahita-rahita haile takhanai tāribe [146]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">vyavahita-rahita</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haile</span>–When unconcealed, <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-nāma</span>–Kṛṣṇa’s Name, <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">guṇa-dhāma</span>–the Name which is the abode of all qualities, <span class=\\"e2\\">takhanai</span>–immediately <span class=\\"e2\\">tāribe</span>–delivers <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhā</span>–anyone <span class=\\"e2\\">yāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">mukhe</span>–within whose mouth <span class=\\"e2\\">uchchārita</span>–He is uttered <span class=\\"e2\\">eka</span>–once, <span class=\\"e2\\">yāhāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">smaraṇa-pathe</span>–within whose path of remembrance [He appears] <span class=\\"e2\\">eka</span>–once, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">yāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">śrotra-mūle</span>–within whose ears <span class=\\"e2\\">praveśa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">karibe</span>–He enters."},{"class":"b50","text":" [Śrīman Mahāprabhu paraphrases:] “When unconcealed, Kṛṣṇa’s Name, the abode of all qualities, immediately delivers anyone within whose mouth He is once uttered, within whose remembrance He once arises, and within whose ears He once enters."},{"class":"b97","text":" ‘ব্যবহিত’ এই শব্দে দুই অর্থ হয় ।<br />অক্ষরের ব্যবধানে নাম আচ্ছাদয় ॥১৪৭॥<br />অবিদ্যার আচ্ছাদনে প্রাকৃত প্রকাশ ।<br />নাম নামী একভাবে অবিদ্যা-বিনাশ ॥১৪৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ‘vyavahita’ ei śabde dui artha haya<br />akṣarera vyavadhāne nāma āchchhādaya [147]<br />avidyāra āchchhādane prākṛta prakāśa<br />nāma nāmī eka-bhāve avidyā-vināśa [148]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">śabde</span>–The word <span class=\\"e2\\">‘vyavahita’</span>–‘concealed’ <span class=\\"e2\\">dui</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">artha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–has two meanings: <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–the Name <span class=\\"e2\\">āchchhādaya</span>–is hidden <span class=\\"e2\\">akṣarera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">vyavadhāne</span>–by separations between His syllables, [and the Name has a] <span class=\\"e2\\">prākṛta</span>–mundane <span class=\\"e2\\">prakāśa</span>–appearance [to the soul] <span class=\\"e2\\">avidyāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">āchchhādane</span>–under the covering of ignorance. [Considering] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–the Name [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmī</span>–the possessor of the Name <span class=\\"e2\\">eka-bhāve</span>–as one <span class=\\"e2\\">avidyā-vināśa</span>–destroys this ignorance."},{"class":"b50","text":" “The word ‘concealed’ has two meanings: (1) the Name is hidden by separations between the Name’s syllables, and (2) the Name appears in a mundane form to the soul covered over by ignorance. Considering the Name and the possessor of the Name to be one destroys this ignorance."},{"class":"b97","text":" ব্যবহিত-রহিত হৈলে শুদ্ধনামোদয় ।<br />বর্ণশুদ্ধাশুদ্ধিক্রমে দোষ নাহি হয় ॥১৪৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" vyavahita-rahita haile śuddha-nāmodaya<br />varṇa-śuddhāśuddhi-krame doṣa nāhi haya [149]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">śuddha-nāmodaya haile</span>–When the pure Name appears <span class=\\"e2\\">vyavahita-rahita</span>––unconcealed, <span class=\\"e2\\">doṣa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haya nāhi</span>–there are no faults <span class=\\"e2\\">varṇa-śuddhāśuddhi-krame</span>–pertaining to proper and improper pronunciation of [the Name’s] letters."},{"class":"b50","text":" “When the pure Name appears unconcealed, there is no consideration of faults pertaining to proper and improper pronunciation of the Name’s letters."},{"class":"b97","text":" অপ্রাকৃত নামে কৃষ্ণ সর্ব্বশক্তি দিল ।<br />কালাকাল শৌচাশৌচ নামে না রহিল ॥১৫০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" aprākṛta nāme kṛṣṇa sarva-śakti dila<br />kālākāla śauchāśaucha nāme nā rahila [150]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span>–Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">dila</span>–has put <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-śakti</span>–all [His] power <span class=\\"e2\\">aprākṛta</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāme</span>–in [His] supramundane Name, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">rahila nā</span>–there is no [consideration] <span class=\\"e2\\">kālākāla</span>–of the proper and improper time [or] <span class=\\"e2\\">śauchāśaucha</span>–cleanliness and uncleanliness <span class=\\"e2\\">nāme</span>–in [chanting] His Name."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Kṛṣṇa has put all His power in His supramundane Name, and there is no consideration of the proper time or cleanliness in chanting His Name."},{"class":"b97","text":" সর্ব্বকাল সর্ব্বাবস্থায় শুদ্ধ নাম কর ।<br />সর্ব্ব শুভোদয় হবে সর্ব্বাশুভ হর ॥১৫১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sarva-kāla sarvāvasthāya śuddha nāma kara<br />sarva śubhodaya habe sarvāśubha hara [151]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">śuddha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kara</span>–Chant the pure Name <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-kāla</span>–at all times [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">sarvāvasthāya</span>–under all circumstances: <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">śubhodaya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">habe</span>–all good fortune will arise, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">sarvāśubha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">hara</span>–all misfortune will be removed."},{"class":"b71","text":" “Chant the pure Name at all times and under all circumstances: you will attain all good fortune, and all your misfortune will be removed."},{"class":"b176","text":" অসৎসঙ্গ ত্যাগপূর্ব্বক নামগ্রহণ"},{"class":"b177","text":" asat-saṅga tyāga-pūrvaka nāma-grahaṇa"},{"class":"b70","text":" Give up mundane attachment and chant the Name"},{"class":"b97","text":" এমত অপূর্ব্ব-নাম সঙ্গযুক্ত যথা ।<br />শীঘ্র শুভফলদাতা না হয় সর্ব্বথা ॥১৫২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" emata apūrva-nāma saṅga-yukta yathā<br />śīghra śubha-phala-dātā nā haya sarvathā [152]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">yathā</span>–When [He is chanted] <span class=\\"e2\\">saṅga-yukta</span>–with [mundane] attachment, <span class=\\"e2\\">emata</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">apūrva-nāma</span>–this supramundane Name <span class=\\"e2\\">śīghra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haya nā</span>–never quickly becomes, <span class=\\"e2\\">sarvathā</span>–under any circumstances, <span class=\\"e2\\">śubha-phala-dātā</span>–a giver of auspicious results."},{"class":"b50","text":" “When chanted with mundane attachment, however, the supramundane Name never, under any circumstances, gives auspicious results quickly."},{"class":"b97","text":" দেহ, ধন, জন, লোভ, পাষণ্ডসঙ্গক্রমে ।<br />ব্যবহিত জন্মে, জীব পড়ে মহাভ্রমে ॥১৫৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" deha, dhana, jana, lobha, pāṣaṇḍa-saṅga-krame<br />vyavahita janme, jīva paḍe mahābhrame [153]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">krame</span>–As a result [of] <span class=\\"e2\\">lobha</span>–greed [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">pāṣaṇḍa-saṅga</span>–attachment to sinful persons, <span class=\\"e2\\">deha</span>–the body, <span class=\\"e2\\">dhana</span>–wealth, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">jana</span>–companions, <span class=\\"e2\\">vyavahita</span>–concealment [of the Name] <span class=\\"e2\\">janme</span>–arises, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">jīva</span>–the soul <span class=\\"e2\\">paḍe</span>–falls <span class=\\"e2\\">mahābhrame</span>–into a terrible predicament."},{"class":"b50","text":" “As a result of greed and attachment to the body, wealth, companions, and sinful persons, the Name becomes concealed, and the soul falls into a terrible predicament."},{"class":"b97","text":" অতএব সকলের অগ্রে সঙ্গ ত্যজি’ ।<br />অনন্যশরণ লঞা নামমাত্র ভজি ॥১৫৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ataeva sakalera agre saṅga tyaji’<br />ananya-śaraṇa lañā nāma-mātra bhaji [154]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">ataeva</span>–So, <span class=\\"e2\\">sakalera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">agre</span>–first of all, <span class=\\"e2\\">tyaji’</span>–give up [mundane] <span class=\\"e2\\">saṅga</span>–attachments, <span class=\\"e2\\">ananya-śaraṇa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">lañā</span>–sincerely surrender, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaji</span>–serve <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-mātra</span>–the Name exclusively."},{"class":"b50","text":" “So, first of all, give up mundane attachments, sincerely surrender, and serve the Name exclusively."},{"class":"b97","text":" নামকৃপাবলে হবে প্রমাদরহিত ।<br />অপরাধ দূরে যাবে, হইবেক হিত ॥১৫৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" nāma-kṛpā-bale habe pramāda-rahita<br />aparādha dūre yābe, ha-ibeka hita [155]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-kṛpā-bale</span>–By the Name’s grace, <span class=\\"e2\\">habe</span>–you will become <span class=\\"e2\\">pramāda-rahita</span>–free from negligence. [Then your] <span class=\\"e2\\">aparādha</span>–offences <span class=\\"e2\\">dūre</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">yābe</span>–will go away, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">hita ha-ibeka</span>–you will attain good fortune."},{"class":"b50","text":" “By the Name’s grace, you will become free from negligence. Then your offences will go away, and you will attain good fortune."},{"class":"b97","text":" অপরাধমুক্ত হঞা লয় কৃষ্ণনাম ।<br />প্রেম আসি’ নামসহ করিবে বিশ্রাম ॥১৫৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" aparādha-mukta hañā laya kṛṣṇa-nāma<br />prema āsi’ nāma-saha karibe viśrāma [156]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">aparādha-mukta</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">hañā</span>–Be free from offences [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-nāma laya</span>–chant the Name of Kṛṣṇa. [Then] <span class=\\"e2\\">prema</span>–divine love <span class=\\"e2\\">āsi’</span>–will come <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-saha</span>–with the Name [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">viśrāma karibe</span>–reside [within your heart]."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Be free from offences and chant the Name of Kṛṣṇa. Then divine love will come with the Name and reside within your heart."},{"class":"b97","text":" অপরাধীর নামলক্ষণ কৈতব নিশ্চয় ।<br />সে সঙ্গ যতনে ছাড়ি’ কর নামাশ্রয় ॥১৫৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" aparādhīra nāma-lakṣaṇa kaitava niśchaya<br />se saṅga yatane chhāḍi’ kara nāmāśraya [157]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">niśchaya</span>–Know for certain [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">aparādhīra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-lakṣaṇa</span>–the characteristic of an offender of the Name [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">kaitava</span>–insincerity. <span class=\\"e2\\">yatane</span>–Carefully <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāḍi’</span>–avoid <span class=\\"e2\\">se</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">saṅga</span>–their association [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmāśraya kara</span>–take shelter of the Name."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Know for certain that the characteristic of an offender of the Name is insincerity. Carefully avoid the association of such offenders and take shelter of the Name."},{"class":"b97","text":" ‘ইদং রহস্যং পরমং পুরা নারদ শঙ্করাৎ ।<br />শ্রুতং সর্ব্বাশুভহরমপরাধনিবারকম্ ॥১৫৮॥<br />বিদুর্বিষ্ণ্বাভিধানং যে হ্যপরাধপরা নরাঃ ।<br />তেষামপি ভবেন্মুক্তিঃ পঠনাদেব নারদ’ ॥১৫৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ‘idaṁ rahasyaṁ paramaṁ purā nārada śaṅkarāt<br />śrutaṁ sarvāśubha-haram aparādha-nivārakam [158]<br />vidur viṣṇv ābhidhānaṁ ye hy aparādha-parā narāḥ<br />teṣām api bhaven muktiḥ paṭhanād eva nārada’ [159]"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘[Śrī Sanat Kumār concluded:] “O Nārad, previously I heard from Lord Śaṅkar these supreme, hidden truths, which destroy all inauspiciousness and ward off the offences to the Name. O Nārad, even offensive souls who understand the Name of Viṣṇu will certainly attain liberation by chanting the Name.”’"},{"class":"b97","text":" সনৎকুমার বলে, ‘ওহে দেবর্ষিপ্রবর ।<br />পূর্ব্বে শ্রীশঙ্কর মোরে হঞা দয়াপর ॥১৬০॥<br />শ্রীনামরহস্য সর্ব্ব-অশুভ নাশন ।<br />অপরাধ-নিবারক কৈল বিজ্ঞাপন ॥১৬১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sanat-kumāra bale, ‘ohe devarṣi-pravara<br />pūrve śrī-śaṅkara more hañā dayāpara [160]<br />śrī-nāma-rahasya sarva-aśubha nāśana<br />aparādha-nivāraka kaila vijñāpana [161]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sanat-kumāra</span>–Sanat Kumār <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–said, <span class=\\"e2\\">‘ohe</span>–‘O <span class=\\"e2\\">devarṣi-pravara</span>–best of the sages amongst the gods, <span class=\\"e2\\">pūrve</span>–previously <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-śaṅkara</span>–Lord Śiva <span class=\\"e2\\">dayāpara hañā</span>–mercifully <span class=\\"e2\\">vijñāpana kaila</span>–taught <span class=\\"e2\\">more</span>–me <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-nāma-rahasya</span>–these hidden truths about the Name, [which] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāśana</span>–destroy <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-aśubha</span>–all inauspiciousness [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">aparādha-nivāraka</span>–ward off the offences."},{"class":"b50","text":" [Śrīman Mahāprabhu paraphrases:] “Sanat Kumār said, ‘O best of the sages amongst the gods, previously Lord Śaṅkar mercifully taught me these hidden truths about the Name, which destroy all inauspiciousness and ward off the offences."},{"class":"b97","text":" অপরাধপর জন বিষ্ণুনাম জানি’ ।<br />পাঠ করিলেই মুক্তি লভে ইহা মানি’ ॥১৬২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" aparādha-para jana viṣṇu-nāma jāni’<br />pāṭha karilei mukti labhe ihā māni’ [162]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [If] <span class=\\"e2\\">aparādha-para</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">jana</span>–offensive souls <span class=\\"e2\\">jāni’</span>–understand [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">pāṭha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">karilei</span>–chant <span class=\\"e2\\">viṣṇu-nāma</span>–the Name of the Lord, <span class=\\"e2\\">labhe</span>–they will attain <span class=\\"e2\\">mukti</span>–liberation. <span class=\\"e2\\">māni</span>–I affirm <span class=\\"e2\\">ihā’</span>–this.’"},{"class":"b71","text":" “If offensive souls understand and chant the Name of Viṣṇu, they will attain liberation. I affirm this.”"},{"class":"b176","text":" নামরহস্যপটল প্রচার"},{"class":"b177","text":" nāma-rahasya-paṭala prachāra"},{"class":"b70","text":" Preaching this collection of hidden truths about the Name"},{"class":"b97","text":" ওহে স্বরূপ রামরায় এ নামরহস্য- ।<br />পটল যতনে প্রচার করিবে অবশ্য ॥১৬৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ohe svarūpa rāma-rāya e nāma-rahasya-<br />paṭala yatane prachāra karibe avaśya [163]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">ohe</span>–O <span class=\\"e2\\">svarūpa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">rāma-rāya</span>–Svarūp and Rāma Rāy, <span class=\\"e2\\">yatane</span>–carefully, <span class=\\"e2\\">avaśya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">prachāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">karibe</span>–you must preach <span class=\\"e2\\">e</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-rahasya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">paṭala</span>–this collection of hidden truths about the Name."},{"class":"b50","text":" “O Svarūp and Rāma Rāy, you must carefully preach these hidden truths about the Name."},{"class":"b97","text":" কলিতে জীবের নাহি অন্য প্রতিকার ।<br />নামরহস্যেতে পার হইবে সংসার ॥১৬৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kalite jīvera nāhi anya pratikāra<br />nāma-rahasyete pāra ha-ibe saṁsāra [164]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">nāhi</span>–There is no <span class=\\"e2\\">anya</span>–other <span class=\\"e2\\">pratikāra</span>–remedy <span class=\\"e2\\">jīvera</span>–for the soul <span class=\\"e2\\">kalite</span>–in the Age of Kali. <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-rahasyete</span>–Through these hidden truths about the Name, <span class=\\"e2\\">saṁsāra pāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-ibe</span>–the soul can cross over the material world."},{"class":"b50","text":" “There is no other remedy for the soul in the Age of Kali. Through these hidden truths about the Name, the soul can cross over saṁsāra."},{"class":"b97","text":" পূর্ব্বে মুঞি ‘শিক্ষাষ্টকে’ যে তত্ত্ব কহিল ।<br />এবে ব্যাসবাক্যে তাহা পুনঃ দেখাইল ॥১৬৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" pūrve muñi ‘śikṣāṣṭake’ ye tattva kahila<br />ebe vyāsa-vākye tāhā punaḥ dekhāila [165]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">dekhāila</span>–I have shown [you] <span class=\\"e2\\">punaḥ</span>–again, <span class=\\"e2\\">ebe</span>–now <span class=\\"e2\\">vyāsa-vākye</span>–in the words of Vyāsa, <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhā ye</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">tattva</span>–the truths [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">muñi</span>–I <span class=\\"e2\\">kahila</span>–described <span class=\\"e2\\">pūrve</span>–previously <span class=\\"e2\\">‘śikṣāṣṭake’</span>–in [My] <span class=\\"e33\\">Śikṣāṣṭakam</span>."},{"class":"b50","text":" “I have shown you again, now in the words of Vyāsa, the truths that I previously described in My <span class=\\"e3\\">Śikṣāṣṭakam</span>."},{"class":"b97","text":" যতনে রহস্যপটল প্রচারিবে সবে ।<br />সর্ব্বক্ষণ আলোচিয়া নাম লবে তবে ॥১৬৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" yatane rahasya-paṭala prachāribe sabe<br />sarva-kṣaṇa ālochiyā nāma labe tabe [166]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sabe</span>–Both of you <span class=\\"e2\\">prachāribe</span>–must preach <span class=\\"e2\\">yatane</span>–carefully <span class=\\"e2\\">rahasya-paṭala</span>–this collection of hidden truths. <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-kṣaṇa</span>–Always <span class=\\"e2\\">ālochiyā</span>–discuss [it, and] <span class=\\"e2\\">tabe</span>–then <span class=\\"e2\\">labe</span>–chant <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–the Name."},{"class":"b71","text":" “You both must carefully preach this collection of hidden truths. Always discuss it and chant the Name."},{"class":"b176","text":" নামাচার্য্য ঠাকুর হরিদাসের আনুগত্যে শ্রীনামভজন"},{"class":"b177","text":" nāmāchārya ṭhākura haridāsera ānugatye śrī-nāma-bhajana"},{"class":"b70","text":" Serving the Name under the guidance <br />of the Nāmāchārya, Haridās Ṭhākur"},{"class":"b97","text":" পৃথিবীর শিরোমণি ছিল হরিদাস ।<br />এই নামরহস্য সব করিল প্রকাশ ॥১৬৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" pṛthivīra śiromaṇi chhila hari-dāsa<br />ei nāma-rahasya saba karila prakāśa [167]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">hari-dāsa</span>–Haridās <span class=\\"e2\\">chhila</span>–was <span class=\\"e2\\">śiromaṇi</span>–the crown jewel <span class=\\"e2\\">pṛthivīra</span>–of [this] world. <span class=\\"e2\\">prakāśa karila</span>–He revealed <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-rahasya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">saba</span>–all these hidden truths about the Name."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Haridās was the crown jewel of this world. He revealed all these hidden truths about the Name."},{"class":"b97","text":" প্রচারিল আচরিল এই নামধর্ম্ম ।<br />নামের আচার্য হরিদাস, জান মর্ম্ম ॥১৬৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" prachārila ācharila ei nāma-dharma<br />nāmera āchārya haridāsa, jāna marma [168]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">prachārila</span>–He preached [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">ācharila</span>–performed <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-dharma</span>–the practice of [chanting] the Name; <span class=\\"e2\\">haridāsa</span>–Haridās [was] <span class=\\"e2\\">āchārya</span>–the perfect teacher <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmera</span>–of the Name. <span class=\\"e2\\">jāna</span>–Understand <span class=\\"e2\\">marma</span>–the significance [of this]."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Haridās practised and preached the chanting of the Name; he was the Āchārya of the Name. Understand the significance of this."},{"class":"b97","text":" হরিদাসের অনুগত হইয়া শ্রীনাম ।<br />ভজিবে যে জন সেই নিত্যসিদ্ধকাম” ॥১৬৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" haridāsera anugata ha-iyā śrī-nāma<br />bhajibe ye jana sei nitya-siddha-kāma” [169]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sei ye</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">jana</span>–Those who <span class=\\"e2\\">anugata</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-iyā</span>–become followers <span class=\\"e2\\">haridāsera</span>–of Haridās [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhajibe</span>–serve <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-nāma</span>–the Name [attain] <span class=\\"e2\\">nitya-siddha-kāma”</span>–eternal perfection.”"},{"class":"b55","text":" “Those who follow Haridās and serve the Name attain eternal perfection.”"}]},{"title":"The Glories of the Name","paragraphs":[{"class":"b46","text":"\\r"},{"class":"b58","text":" Chapter Twenty"},{"class":"b120","text":" নাম-মহিমা"},{"class":"b121","text":" Nāma-mahimā"},{"class":"b175","text":" The Glories of the Name"},{"class":"b97","text":" একদিন কৃষ্ণদাস কাশীমিশ্রের ঘরে ।<br />আপন গৌছারি কিছু কহিল প্রভুরে ॥১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" eka-dina kṛṣṇa-dāsa kāśī-miśrera ghare<br />āpana gauchhāri kichhu kahila prabhure [1]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">eka-dina</span>–One day, <span class=\\"e2\\">ghare</span>–at the house <span class=\\"e2\\">kāśī-miśrera</span>–of Kāśī Miśra, <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-dāsa</span>–Kṛṣṇadās <span class=\\"e2\\">kahila</span>–expressed <span class=\\"e2\\">kichhu</span>–some <span class=\\"e2\\">āpana</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">gauchhāri</span>–of his personal feelings <span class=\\"e2\\">prabhure</span>–to the Lord."},{"class":"b50","text":" One day, at the house of Kāśī Miśra, Kṛṣṇadās expressed some of his personal feelings to the Lord."},{"class":"b97","text":" “আজ্ঞা হয় শুনি কৃষ্ণনামের মহিমা ।<br />যে মহিমার ব্রহ্মা শিব নাহি জানে সীমা” ॥২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" “ājñā haya śuni kṛṣṇa-nāmera mahimā<br />ye mahimāra brahmā śiva nāhi jāne sīmā” [2]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">“ājñā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–Please allow [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">śuni</span>–I hear <span class=\\"e2\\">mahimā</span>–the glories <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-nāmera</span>–of the Name of Kṛṣṇa, <span class=\\"e2\\">ye</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">mahimāra</span>–the glories that <span class=\\"e2\\">brahmā</span>–Brahmā [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">śiva</span>–Śiva <span class=\\"e2\\">jāne nāhi</span>–do not know <span class=\\"e2\\">sīmā”</span>–the end [of].”"},{"class":"b50","text":" [Kṛṣṇadās said:] “Please let me hear the glories of the Name of Kṛṣṇa, the glories that even Brahmā and Śiva do not know the end of.”"},{"class":"b97","text":" প্রভু বলে, “কৃষ্ণনামের মহিমা অপার ।<br />কৃষ্ণ নিজে নাহি জানে, কি জানিব জীব ছার ॥৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" prabhu bale, “kṛṣṇa-nāmera mahimā apāra<br />kṛṣṇa nije nāhi jāne, ki jāniba jīva chhāra [3]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">prabhu</span>–The Lord <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–said, <span class=\\"e2\\">“mahimā</span>–“The glories <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-nāmera</span>–of the Name of Kṛṣṇa [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">apāra</span>–unlimited. [Even] <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span>–Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">nije</span>–Himself <span class=\\"e2\\">jāne nāhi</span>–does not know [them]. [So,] <span class=\\"e2\\">ki</span>–what <span class=\\"e2\\">jāniba</span>–can I understand? [I am just] <span class=\\"e2\\">chhāra jīva</span>–a fallen soul."},{"class":"b50","text":" The Lord replied, “The glories of the Name of Kṛṣṇa are unlimited. Even Kṛṣṇa Himself does not know them. So, what can I understand? I am just a fallen soul."},{"class":"b97","text":" শাস্ত্রে যাহা শুনিয়াছি কহিব তোমারে ।<br />বিশ্বাস করিয়া শুন যাবে ভবপারে ॥৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" śāstre yāhā śuniyāchhi kahiba tomāre<br />viśvāsa kariyā śuna yābe bhava-pāre [4]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kahiba</span>–I can tell <span class=\\"e2\\">tomāre</span>–you <span class=\\"e2\\">yāhā</span>–what <span class=\\"e2\\">śuniyāchhi</span>–I have heard <span class=\\"e2\\">śāstre</span>–from the scriptures. <span class=\\"e2\\">śuna</span>–Listen <span class=\\"e2\\">viśvāsa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kariyā</span>–faithfully, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhava-pāre yābe</span>–you will cross over material existence."},{"class":"b50","text":" “I can tell you what I have heard from the scriptures. Listen with faith, and you will cross over material existence."},{"class":"b97","text":" সর্ব্বপাপপ্রশমক সর্ব্বব্যাধিনাশ ।<br />সর্ব্বদুঃখবিনাশন কলিবাধাহ্রাস ॥৫॥<br />নারকি-উদ্ধার আর প্রারব্ধখণ্ডন ।<br />সর্ব্ব-অপরাধ-ক্ষয় নামে সর্ব্বক্ষণ ॥৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sarva-pāpa-praśamaka sarva-vyādhi-nāśa<br />sarva-duḥkha-vināśana kali-bādhā-hrāsa [5]<br />nāraki-uddhāra āra prārabdha-khaṇḍana<br />sarva-aparādha-kṣaya nāme sarva-kṣaṇa [6]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-pāpa-praśamaka</span>–Destruction of all sin, <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-vyādhi-nāśa</span>–curing of all disease, <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-duḥkha-vināśana</span>–relief from all misery, <span class=\\"e2\\">kali-bādhā-hrāsa</span>–clearing of the obsta­cles made by Kali, <span class=\\"e2\\">nāraki-uddhāra</span>–deliverance of the residents of hell, <span class=\\"e2\\">prārabdha-khaṇḍana</span>–cutting away of the active consequences of previous actions, <span class=\\"e2\\">āra</span>–and <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-aparādha-kṣaya</span>–the removal of all offences <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-kṣaṇa</span>–always [occur] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāme</span>–through the Name."},{"class":"b50","text":" “The Name always destroys all sin, cures all disease, relieves all misery, clears away the obstacles made by Kali, delivers the residents of hell, cuts away active karma, and removes all offences."},{"class":"b97","text":" সর্ব্ব-সৎ-কর্ম্মের পূর্ত্তি নামের বিলাস ।<br />সর্ব্ববেদাধিক নামসূর্যের প্রকাশ ॥৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sarva-sat-karmera pūrti nāmera vilāsa<br />sarva-vedādhika nāma-sūryera prakāśa [7]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">pūrti</span>–Fulfilment <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-sat-karmera</span>–of all pious works [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">vilāsa</span>–a Pastime <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmera</span>–of the Name, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">prakāśa</span>–the appearance <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-sūryera</span>–of the sun-like Name [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-vedādhika</span>–superior to [studying] all the scriptures."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Making all pious works successful is a Pastime of the Name, and the appearance of the sun-like Name is superior to studying all the scriptures."},{"class":"b97","text":" সর্ব্বতীর্থের অধিক নাম সর্ব্বশাস্ত্র কয় ।<br />সকল সৎকর্ম্মাধিক্য নামেতে উদয় ॥৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sarva-tīrthera adhika nāma sarva-śāstra kaya<br />sakala sat-karmādhikya nāmete udaya [8]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-śāstra</span>–All the scriptures <span class=\\"e2\\">kaya</span>–say [that chanting] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–the Name [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">adhika</span>–superior <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-tīrthera</span>–to [visiting] all the holy places, [and that] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmete</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">udaya</span>–the revelation of the Name [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">sakala</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sat-karmādhikya</span>–superior to [performing] all pious works."},{"class":"b50","text":" “All the scriptures say that chanting the Name is superior to visiting all the holy places and superior to performing all pious work."},{"class":"b97","text":" সর্ব্বার্থপ্রদাতা নাম, সর্ব্বশক্তিময় ।<br />জগৎ-আনন্দকারী নামের ধর্ম্ম হয় ॥৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sarvārtha-pradātā nāma, sarva-śaktimaya<br />jagat-ānanda-kārī nāmera dharma haya [9]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–The Name [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-śaktimaya</span>–all-powerful [and is] <span class=\\"e2\\">sarvārtha-pradātā</span>–the giver of all desired ends. <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">dharma</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–The Name’s nature is [to be] <span class=\\"e2\\">jagat-ānanda-kārī</span>–the maker of joy for the world."},{"class":"b50","text":" “The Name is all-powerful, grants all desired ends, and naturally makes the world joyful."},{"class":"b97","text":" নাম লঞা জগদ্বন্দ্য হয় সর্ব্বজন ।<br />অগতির গতি নাম পতিতপাবন ॥১০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" nāma lañā jagad-vandya haya sarva-jana<br />agatira gati nāma patita-pāvana [10]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-jana</span>–Everyone [who] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">lañā</span>–chants the Name <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–becomes <span class=\\"e2\\">jagad-vandya</span>–worshippable throughout the world. <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–The Name [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">gati</span>–the shelter <span class=\\"e2\\">agatira</span>–of the shelterless, <span class=\\"e2\\">patita-pāvana</span>–the saviour of the fallen."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Everyone who chants the Name becomes worshippable throughout the world. The Name is the shelter of the shelterless, the saviour of the fallen."},{"class":"b97","text":" সর্ব্বত্র সর্ব্বদা সেব্য সর্ব্বমুক্তিদাতা ।<br />বৈকুণ্ঠপ্রাপক নাম হরিপ্রীতিদাতা ॥১১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sarvatra sarvadā sevya sarva-mukti-dātā<br />vaikuṇṭha-prāpaka nāma hari-prīti-dātā [11]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [The Name] <span class=\\"e2\\">sevya</span>–should be served <span class=\\"e2\\">sarvatra</span>–everywhere [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">sarvadā</span>–always. <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–The Name [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-mukti-dātā</span>–the giver of all types of liberation, <span class=\\"e2\\">vaikuṇṭha-prāpaka</span>–the giver of the spiritual world, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">hari-prīti-dātā</span>–the giver of love for the Lord."},{"class":"b50","text":" “The Name should be served everywhere and always. The Name gives all types of liberation, entrance into the spiritual world, and love for the Lord."},{"class":"b97","text":" নাম স্বয়ং পুরুষার্থ ভক্ত্যঙ্গপ্রধান ।<br />শ্রুতি-স্মৃতি-শাস্ত্রে আছে বহুত প্রমাণ ॥১২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" nāma svayaṁ puruṣārtha bhakty-aṅga-pradhāna<br />śruti-smṛti-śāstre āchhe bahuta pramāṇa [12]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–The Name <span class=\\"e2\\">svayaṁ</span>–Himself [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">puruṣārtha</span>–the goal of human life [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakty-aṅga-pradhāna</span>–the foremost practice of devotion. <span class=\\"e2\\">āchhe</span>–There is <span class=\\"e2\\">bahuta</span>–much <span class=\\"e2\\">pramāṇa</span>–evidence [of this] <span class=\\"e2\\">śruti-smṛti-śāstre</span>–in the śruti and smṛti scriptures."},{"class":"b71","text":" “The Name Himself is the goal of human life and the foremost practice of devotion. There is much evidence of this in the scriptures."},{"class":"b176","text":" নাম সর্ব্বপাপবিনাশক"},{"class":"b177","text":" nāma sarva-pāpa-vināśaka"},{"class":"b70","text":" The Name destroys all sin"},{"class":"b97","text":" সর্ব্বপাপ নাশ করা নামের একধর্ম্ম ।<br />প্রথমে তাহাই সপ্রমাণ শুন মর্ম্ম ॥১৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sarva-pāpa nāśa karā nāmera eka-dharma<br />prathame tāhāi sapramāṇa śuna marma [13]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">nāśa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">karā</span>–Destroying <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-pāpa</span>–all sin [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">eka-dharma</span>–one quality <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmera</span>–of the Name. <span class=\\"e2\\">śuna</span>–Hear <span class=\\"e2\\">prathame</span>–first <span class=\\"e2\\">marma</span>–the significance <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhāi</span>–of this <span class=\\"e2\\">sapramāṇa</span>–based on evidence [from the scriptures]."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Destroying all sin is one quality of the Name. Hear first the significance of this based on evidence from the scriptures."},{"class":"b97","text":" পাপী অজামিল দেখ বিবশ হইয়া ।<br />হরিনাম উচ্চারিল ‘নারায়ণ’ বলিয়া ॥১৪॥<br />কোটি কোটি জন্মে পাপ করিয়াছে যত ।<br />সে সকল হইতে মুক্ত হইল সাম্প্রত ॥১৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" pāpī ajāmila dekha vivaśa ha-iyā<br />hari-nāma uchchārila ‘nārāyaṇa’ baliyā [14]<br />koṭi koṭi janme pāpa kariyāchhe yata<br />se sakala ha-ite mukta ha-ila sāmprata [15]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">dekha</span>–Consider <span class=\\"e2\\">pāpī</span>–the sinner <span class=\\"e2\\">ajāmila</span>–Ajāmil. <span class=\\"e2\\">vivaśa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-iyā</span>–Desperately, <span class=\\"e2\\">uchchārila</span>–he uttered <span class=\\"e2\\">hari-nāma</span>–the Name of the Lord <span class=\\"e2\\">‘nārāyaṇa’</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">baliyā</span>–‘Nārāyaṇ’, [and he] <span class=\\"e2\\">sāmprata</span>–immediately <span class=\\"e2\\">mukta</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-ila</span>–became free <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-ite</span>–from <span class=\\"e2\\">yata</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">se</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sakala</span>–all <span class=\\"e2\\">pāpa</span>–the sins <span class=\\"e2\\">kariyāchhe</span>–he had committed <span class=\\"e2\\">koṭi</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">koṭi</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">janme</span>–over the course of millions of births."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Consider the sinner Ajāmil. Desperately, he uttered the Name of the Lord ‘Nārāyaṇ’, and he immediately became free from all the sins he had committed over the course of millions of births."},{"class":"b97","text":" অয়ং হি কৃতনির্ব্বেশো জন্মকোট্যংহসামপি ।<br />যদ্ব্যাজহার বিবশো নাম স্বস্ত্যয়নং হরেঃ ॥১৬॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" ayaṁ hi kṛta-nirveśo janma-koṭy-aṁhasām api<br />yad vyājahāra vivaśo nāma svasty-ayanaṁ hareḥ [16]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Śrīmad Bhāgavatam: 6.2.7)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “[The Viṣṇudūtas:] ‘Ajāmil has atoned for ten million births of sins because he has desperately called out the auspicious Name of the Lord.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" স্ত্রী-রাজ-গো-ব্রাহ্মণ-ঘাতী মদ্যরত ।<br />গুরুপত্নীগামী মিত্রদ্রোহী চৌর্য্যব্রত ॥১৭॥<br />এ সবের পাপ আর অন্য পাপচয় ।<br />হরিনাম উচ্চারণে সব পরিষ্কৃত হয় ॥১৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" strī-rāja-go-brāhmaṇa-ghātī madya-rata<br />guru-patnī-gāmī mitra-drohī chaurya-vrata [17]<br />e sabera pāpa āra anya pāpa-chaya<br />hari-nāma uchchāraṇe saba pariṣkṛta haya [18]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">uchchāraṇe</span>–By uttering <span class=\\"e2\\">hari-nāma</span>–the Name of the Lord, <span class=\\"e2\\">e sabera pāpa</span>–all the sins <span class=\\"e2\\">madya-rata</span>–of a drunkard, <span class=\\"e2\\">chaurya-vrata</span>–a thief, <span class=\\"e2\\">mitra-drohī</span>–a traitor, <span class=\\"e2\\">guru-patnī-gāmī</span>–one who commits adultery with an elder’s wife, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">strī-rāja-go-brāhmaṇa-ghātī</span>–a murderer of a woman, king, cow, or brāhmaṇ, <span class=\\"e2\\">āra</span>–as well as <span class=\\"e2\\">saba</span>–all <span class=\\"e2\\">anya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">pāpa-chaya</span>–other sins, <span class=\\"e2\\">pariṣkṛta</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–are counteracted."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Uttering the Name of the Lord counteracts the sins of a drunkard, a thief, a traitor, one who commits adultery with an elder’s wife, and a murderer of a woman, king, cow, or brāhmaṇ, as well as all other sins."},{"class":"b97","text":" পাপ সুনিষ্কৃত হৈলে কৃষ্ণে হয় মতি ।<br />এইরূপে নামে জীবের হয় ত’ সদ্গতি ॥১৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" pāpa suniṣkṛta haile kṛṣṇe haya mati<br />ei-rūpe nāme jīvera haya ta’ sad-gati [19]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">pāpa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">suniṣkṛta</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haile</span>–When [the soul’s] sins are counteracted, [the soul] <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–becomes <span class=\\"e2\\">mati</span>–devoted <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇe</span>–to Kṛṣṇa. <span class=\\"e2\\">ei-rūpe</span>–In this way, <span class=\\"e2\\">nāme</span>–through the Name, <span class=\\"e2\\">jīvera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–the soul attains <span class=\\"e2\\">ta’</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sad-gati</span>–good fortune."},{"class":"b50","text":" “When the soul’s sins are counteracted, the soul becomes devoted to Kṛṣṇa. In this way, through the Name, the soul attains good fortune."},{"class":"b97","text":" স্তেনঃ সুরাপো মিত্রধ্রুগ্ ব্রহ্মহা গুরুতল্পগঃ ।<br />স্ত্রীরাজপিতৃগোহন্তা যে চ পাতকিনোঽপরে ॥২০॥<br />সর্ব্বেষামপ্যঘবতামিদমেব সুনিষ্কৃতম্ ।<br />নামব্যাহরণং বিষ্ণোর্যতস্তদ্বিষয়া মতিঃ ॥২১॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" stenaḥ surā-po mitra-dhrug brahma-hā guru-talpa-gaḥ<br />strī-rāja-pitṛ-go-hantā ye cha pātakino ’pare [20]<br />sarveṣām apy aghavatām idam eva suniṣkṛtam<br />nāma-vyāharaṇaṁ viṣṇor yatas tad-viṣayā matiḥ [21]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Śrīmad Bhāgavatam: 6.2.9–10)"},{"class":"b71","text":" “[The Viṣṇudūtas:] ‘Chanting the Name of Viṣṇu is the best means of atonement for a thief, a drunkard, a traitor, one who commits adultery with an elder’s wife, a murderer of a brāhmaṇ, woman, king, father, or cow, and all other sorts of sinners because the Lord becomes attentive to (the protection of) those who chant His Name.’"},{"class":"b176","text":" ব্রতাদি নামের নিকট তুচ্ছ"},{"class":"b177","text":" vratādi nāmera nikaṭa tuchchha"},{"class":"b70","text":" Rites are useless in comparison to the Name"},{"class":"b97","text":" চান্দ্রায়ণব্রত-আদি শাস্ত্রোক্ত প্রকারে ।<br />পাপ হইতে পাপীকে নাহি সেরূপ নিস্তারে ॥২২॥<br />কৃষ্ণনাম একবার উচ্চারিত যবে ।<br />সর্ব্বপাপ হইতে পাপী মুক্ত হয় তবে ॥২৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" chāndrāyaṇa-vrata ādi śāstrokta prakāre<br />pāpa ha-ite pāpīke nāhi se-rūpa nistāre [22]<br />kṛṣṇa-nāma eka-bāra uchchārita yabe<br />sarva-pāpa ha-ite pāpī mukta haya tabe [23]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">yabe</span>–When <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-nāma</span>–the Name of Kṛṣṇa [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">uchchārita</span>–uttered <span class=\\"e2\\">eka-bāra</span>–once, <span class=\\"e2\\">tabe</span>–then <span class=\\"e2\\">pāpī</span>–a sinner <span class=\\"e2\\">mukta</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–becomes free <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-ite</span>–from <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-pāpa</span>–all sins. <span class=\\"e2\\">chāndrāyaṇa-vrata</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ādi</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">śāstrokta</span>–Rites mentioned in the scriptures, like the Chāndrāyaṇ-vrata, <span class=\\"e2\\">nistāre nāhi</span>–do not liberate <span class=\\"e2\\">pāpīke</span>–a sinner <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-ite</span>–from <span class=\\"e2\\">pāpa</span>–sin <span class=\\"e2\\">se-rūpa prakāre</span>–in this way."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Sinners who once chant the Name of Kṛṣṇa are freed from all sins. Rites mentioned in the scriptures, like the Chāndrāyaṇ-vrata, do not liberate sinners in this way."},{"class":"b97","text":" ন নিষ্কৃতৈরুদিতৈর্ব্রহ্মবাদিভিস্<br />তথা বিশুদ্ধ্যত্যঘবান্ ব্রতাদিভিঃ ।<br />যথা হরের্নামপদৈরুদাহৃতৈস্<br />তদুত্তমঃশ্লোকগুণোপলম্ভকম্ ॥২৪॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" na niṣkṛtair uditair brahma-vādibhis<br />tathā viśuddhyaty aghavān vratādibhiḥ<br />yathā harer nāma-padair udāhṛtais<br />tad uttamaḥśloka-guṇopalambhakam [24]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Śrīmad Bhāgavatam: 6.2.11)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “[The Viṣṇudūtas:] ‘Rites and other means of atonement prescribed by the sages do not purify a sinner to the extent that chanting the Name of the Lord does because chanting the Name produces remembrance of the Lord’s qualities.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" সঙ্কেত বা পরিহাস স্তোভ হেলা করি’ ।<br />নামাভাসে কভু যদি বলে ‘কৃষ্ণ’ ‘হরি’ ॥২৫॥<br />অশেষপাতক তার দূরে যায় তবে ।<br />শ্রীবৈকুণ্ঠে নীত হয় যমদূতের পরাভবে ॥২৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" saṅketa vā parihāsa stobha helā kari’<br />nāmābhāse kabhu yadi bale ‘kṛṣṇa’ ‘hari’ [25]<br />aśeṣa-pātaka tāra dūre yāya tabe<br />śrī-vaikuṇṭhe nīta haya yamadūtera parābhave [26]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">yadi</span>–If <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu</span>–at any time [souls] <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–chant <span class=\\"e2\\">‘kṛṣṇa’</span>–‘Kṛṣṇa’ [or] <span class=\\"e2\\">‘hari’</span>–‘Hari’ <span class=\\"e2\\">saṅketa kari’</span>–indirectly, <span class=\\"e2\\">parihāsa</span>–jokingly, <span class=\\"e2\\">stobha</span>–mnemonically, <span class=\\"e2\\">vā</span>–or <span class=\\"e2\\">helā</span>–neglectfully, <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmābhāse</span>–by this Nāmābhās, <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra</span>–their <span class=\\"e2\\">aśeṣa-pātaka</span>–innumerable sins <span class=\\"e2\\">dūre</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">yāya</span>–go away. <span class=\\"e2\\">tabe</span>–Then <span class=\\"e2\\">yamadūtera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">parābhave haya</span>–they overstep the attendants of Yamarāj [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">nīta</span>–are taken <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-vaikuṇṭhe</span>–to the spiritual world."},{"class":"b50","text":" “If ever souls chant ‘Kṛṣṇa’ or ‘Hari’ indirectly, jokingly, mnemonically, or neglectfully, by this semblance of the Name (Nāmābhās), their innumerable sins disappear, they overstep the attendants of Yamarāj, and they are taken to Vaikuṇṭha."},{"class":"b97","text":" সাঙ্কেত্যং পারিহাস্যং বা স্তোভং হেলনমেব বা ।<br />বৈকুণ্ঠনাম-গ্রহণমশেষাঘহরং বিদুঃ ॥২৭॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" sāṅketyaṁ pārihāsyaṁ vā stobhaṁ helanam eva vā<br />vaikuṇṭha-nāma-grahaṇam aśeṣāgha-haraṁ viduḥ [27]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Śrīmad Bhāgavatam: 6.2.14)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “[The Viṣṇudūtas:] ‘Be it indirectly, jokingly, mnemonically, or neglectfully, the wise know that chanting the Name of the Lord removes innumerable sins.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" পড়ি’ খসি’ ভগ্ন দষ্ট দগ্ধ বা আহত ।<br />হইয়া বিবশে বলে, ‘আমি হৈনু হত’ ॥২৮॥<br />‘কৃষ্ণ’ ‘হরি’ ‘নারায়ণ’ নাম মুখে ডাকে ।<br />যাতনা কখন আশ্রয় না করে তাহাকে ॥২৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" paḍi’ khasi’ bhagna daṣṭa dagdha vā āhata<br />ha-iyā vivaśe bale, ‘āmi hainu hata’ [28]<br />‘kṛṣṇa’ ‘hari’ ‘nārāyaṇa’ nāma mukhe ḍāke<br />yātanā kakhana āśraya nā kare tāhāke [29]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">yātanā</span>–The punishment of Yamarāj <span class=\\"e2\\">kakhana</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nā</span>–never <span class=\\"e2\\">āśraya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kare</span>–afflicts <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhāke</span>–those who <span class=\\"e2\\">vivaśe ha-iyā</span>–desperately <span class=\\"e2\\">mukhe</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ḍāke</span>–call aloud <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–the Names <span class=\\"e2\\">‘kṛṣṇa’</span>–‘Kṛṣṇa’, <span class=\\"e2\\">‘hari’</span>–‘Hari’, [or] <span class=\\"e2\\">‘nārāyaṇa’</span>–‘Nārāyaṇ’ [when] <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–they consider, <span class=\\"e2\\">‘āmi</span>–I <span class=\\"e2\\">hata hainu’</span>–am dying!’ <span class=\\"e2\\">paḍi’</span>–after having fallen [or] <span class=\\"e2\\">khasi’</span>–slipped, [or] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhagna</span>–been injured, <span class=\\"e2\\">daṣṭa</span>–bitten, <span class=\\"e2\\">dagdha</span>–burnt, <span class=\\"e2\\">vā</span>–or <span class=\\"e2\\">āhata</span>–beaten."},{"class":"b50","text":" “The punishment of Yamarāj never afflicts those who desperately call aloud ‘Kṛṣṇa’, ‘Hari’, or ‘Nārāyaṇ’ when they feel as though they are dying after having fallen or slipped, or been injured, bitten, beaten, or burnt."},{"class":"b97","text":" পতিতঃ স্খলিতো ভগ্নঃ সন্দষ্টস্তপ্ত আহতঃ ।<br />হরিরিত্যবশেনাহ পুমান্নার্হতি যাতনাঃ ॥৩০॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" patitaḥ skhalito bhagnaḥ sandaṣṭas tapta āhataḥ<br />harir ity avaśenāha pumān nārhati yātanāḥ [30]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Śrīmad Bhāgavatam: 6.2.15)"},{"class":"b71","text":" “[The Viṣṇudūtas:] ‘Having fallen, slipped, been injured, bitten, burnt, or beaten, souls who desperately call out ‘Hari’ never suffer the punishment of Yamarāj.’"},{"class":"b176","text":" জ্ঞানে বা অজ্ঞানে নাম"},{"class":"b177","text":" jñāne vā ajñāne nāma"},{"class":"b70","text":" Chanting the Name knowingly or unknowingly"},{"class":"b97","text":" অজ্ঞানে বা জ্ঞানে কৃষ্ণনাম-সঙ্কীর্ত্তনে ।<br />সর্ব্বপাপ ভস্ম হয়, যথা কাষ্ঠ অগ্ন্যর্পণে ॥৩১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ajñāne vā jñāne kṛṣṇa-nāma-saṅkīrtane<br />sarva-pāpa bhasma haya, yathā kāṣṭha agny-arpaṇe [31]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">yathā</span>–Like <span class=\\"e2\\">kāṣṭha</span>–wood <span class=\\"e2\\">agny-arpaṇe</span>–placed in a fire, <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-pāpa</span>–all sins <span class=\\"e2\\">bhasma</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–are reduced to ashes <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-nāma-saṅkīrtane</span>–by chanting the Name of Kṛṣṇa, <span class=\\"e2\\">ajñāne</span>–unknowingly <span class=\\"e2\\">vā</span>–or <span class=\\"e2\\">jñāne</span>–knowingly."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Like a piece of wood placed in a fire, all sins are reduced to ashes by chanting the Name of Kṛṣṇa, knowingly or unknowingly."},{"class":"b97","text":" অজ্ঞানাদথবা জ্ঞানাদুত্তমঃশ্লোকনাম যৎ ।<br />সঙ্কীর্ত্তিতমঘং পুংসো দহেদেধো যথানলঃ ॥৩২॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" ajñānād athavā jñānād uttamaḥśloka-nāma yat<br />saṅkīrtitam aghaṁ puṁso dahed edho yathānalaḥ [32]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Śrīmad Bhāgavatam: 6.2.18)"},{"class":"b71","text":" “[The Viṣṇudūtas:] ‘All sins are burnt up, like dry grass in fire, by chanting the Name of the Lord, knowingly or unknowingly.’"},{"class":"b176","text":" প্রারব্ধ অপ্রারব্ধ সমস্ত পাপনাশ"},{"class":"b177","text":" prārabdha aprārabdha samasta pāpa-nāśa"},{"class":"b70","text":" Destruction of all active and inactive sin"},{"class":"b97","text":" বর্ত্তমান পাপ আর পূর্ব্ব-জন্মার্জ্জিত ।<br />ভবিষ্যতে হবে যাহা সে সকল হত ॥৩৩॥<br />অনায়াসে হবে কৃষ্ণনাম-সঙ্কীর্ত্তনে ।<br />নাম বিনা বন্ধু নাহি জীবের জীবনে ॥৩৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" vartamāna pāpa āra pūrva-janmārjita<br />bhaviṣyate habe yāhā se sakala hata [33]<br />anāyāse habe kṛṣṇa-nāma-saṅkīrtane<br />nāma vinā bandhu nāhi jīvera jīvane [34]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-nāma-saṅkīrtane</span>–By chanting the Name of Kṛṣṇa, <span class=\\"e2\\">anāyāse</span>–easily <span class=\\"e2\\">sakala</span>–all <span class=\\"e2\\">pāpa</span>–sins <span class=\\"e2\\">hata</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">habe</span>–will be destroyed: <span class=\\"e2\\">se yāhā</span>–those that [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">vartamāna</span>–present, [were] <span class=\\"e2\\">pūrva-janmārjita</span>–incurred in previous births, <span class=\\"e2\\">āra</span>–and <span class=\\"e2\\">habe</span>–will take effect <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaviṣyate</span>–in the future. <span class=\\"e2\\">jīvera nāhi</span>–The soul has no <span class=\\"e2\\">bandhu</span>–friend <span class=\\"e2\\">jīvane</span>–in life <span class=\\"e2\\">vinā</span>–other than <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–the Name."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Chanting the Name of Kṛṣṇa easily destroys the reactions to present sins, sins from previous births, and sins that will take effect in the future. The soul has no friend in life other than the Name."},{"class":"b97","text":" বর্ত্তমানস্তু যৎ পাপং যদ্ভূতং যদ্ভবিষ্যতি ।<br />তৎসর্ব্বং নির্দ্দহত্যাশু গোবিন্দ-কীর্ত্তনানলঃ ॥৩৫॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" vartamānas tu yat pāpaṁ yad bhūtaṁ yad bhaviṣyati<br />tat sarvaṁ nirdahaty āśu govinda-kīrtanānalaḥ [35]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Laghu-bhāgavata)"},{"class":"b71","text":" “‘The fire of chanting Govinda’s Name quickly burns away all sins of the past, present, and future.’"},{"class":"b176","text":" দ্রোহকারীর মুক্তি"},{"class":"b177","text":" drohakārīra mukti"},{"class":"b70","text":" Liberation of the spiteful"},{"class":"b97","text":" মহীতলে সজ্জনের প্রতি পাপাচারে ।<br />নামকীর্ত্তনেতে মুক্তি লভে সর্ব্ব নরে ॥৩৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" mahī-tale sajjanera prati pāpāchāre<br />nāma-kīrtanete mukti labhe sarva nare [36]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nare</span>–All human beings [who] <span class=\\"e2\\">pāpāchāre</span>–behave sinfully <span class=\\"e2\\">sajjanera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">prati</span>–with the virtuous people <span class=\\"e2\\">mahī-tale</span>–of this world <span class=\\"e2\\">labhe</span>–attain <span class=\\"e2\\">mukti</span>–liberation<span class=\\"e2\\"> nāma-kīrtanete</span>–by chanting the Name."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Even those who abuse the virtuous people of this world attain liberation by chanting the Name."},{"class":"b97","text":" সদা দ্রোহপরো যস্তু সজ্জনানাং মহীতলে ।<br />জায়তে পবনো ধন্যো হরের্নামানুকীর্ত্তনাৎ ॥৩৭॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" sadā droha-paro yas tu sajjanānāṁ mahī-tale<br />jāyate pavano dhanyo harer nāmānukīrtanāt [37]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Laghu-bhāgavata)"},{"class":"b71","text":" “‘Even those who constantly abuse the virtuous people of this world become purified and fortunate by chanting the Name of the Lord.’"},{"class":"b176","text":" কোটি প্রায়শ্চিত্ত নামতুল্য নহে"},{"class":"b177","text":" koṭi prāyaśchitta nāma-tulya nahe"},{"class":"b70","text":" Millions of atonements do not compare to chanting the Name"},{"class":"b97","text":" শাস্ত্রে কোটি কোটি প্রায়শ্চিত্ত আছে কহে ।<br />কিন্তু কৃষ্ণকীর্ত্তনের তুল্য কেহ নহে ॥৩৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" śāstre koṭi koṭi prāyaśchitta āchhe kahe<br />kintu kṛṣṇa-kīrtanera tulya keha nahe [38]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">śāstre</span>–The scriptures <span class=\\"e2\\">kahe</span>–say [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">āchhe</span>–there are <span class=\\"e2\\">koṭi</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">koṭi</span>–millions <span class=\\"e2\\">prāyaśchitta</span>–of atonements [for sins], <span class=\\"e2\\">kintu</span>–but <span class=\\"e2\\">keha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nahe</span>–none of them <span class=\\"e2\\">tulya</span>–are comparable <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-kīrtanera</span>–to chanting the Name of Kṛṣṇa."},{"class":"b50","text":" “The scriptures say that there are millions of atonements, but none of them are comparable to chanting the Name of Kṛṣṇa."},{"class":"b97","text":" বসন্তি যানি কোটিস্তু পাবনানি মহীতলে ।<br />ন তানি তত্তুল্যং যান্তি কৃষ্ণনামানুকীর্ত্তনে ॥৩৯॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" vasanti yāni koṭis tu pāvanāni mahī-tale<br />na tāni tat-tulyaṁ yānti kṛṣṇa-nāmānukīrtane [39]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Kūrma-purāṇa)"},{"class":"b71","text":" “‘The millions of atonements that exist in this world never compare with chanting the Name of Kṛṣṇa.’"},{"class":"b176","text":" নামগ্রহণকারীর পাপ থাকে না"},{"class":"b177","text":" nāma-grahaṇakārīra pāpa thāke nā"},{"class":"b70","text":" Those who chant the Name have no sin"},{"class":"b97","text":" হরিনাম যত পাপ নির্হরণ করে ।<br />তত পাপ পাপী কভু করিতে না পারে ॥৪০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" hari-nāma yata pāpa nirharaṇa kare<br />tata pāpa pāpī kabhu karite nā pāre [40]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">pāpī</span>–A sinner <span class=\\"e2\\">pāre</span>–can <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu nā</span>–never <span class=\\"e2\\">karite</span>–commit <span class=\\"e2\\">tata</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">pāpa yata</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">pāpa</span>–as many sins as <span class=\\"e2\\">hari-nāma</span>–the Name of the Lord <span class=\\"e2\\">nirharaṇa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kare</span>–removes."},{"class":"b50","text":" “A sinner can never commit as many sins as the Lord’s Name can remove."},{"class":"b97","text":" নাম্নোঽস্য যাবতী শক্তিঃ পাপ-নির্হরণে হরেঃ ।<br />তাবৎ কর্ত্তুং ন শক্নোতি পাতকং পাতকী জনঃ ॥৪১॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" nāmno ’sya yāvatī śaktiḥ pāpa-nirharaṇe hareḥ<br />tāvat kartuṁ na śaknoti pātakaṁ pātakī janaḥ [41]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Bṛhad-viṣṇu-purāṇa)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘A sinner cannot commit as many sins as the Name of the Lord has the power to remove.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" মনোবাক্কায়জ পাপ তত নাহি হয় ।<br />কলিতে গোবিন্দ-নামে নাহি হয় ক্ষয় ॥৪২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" mano-vāk-kāya-ja pāpa tata nāhi haya<br />kalite govinda-nāme nāhi haya kṣaya [42]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">haya nāhi</span>–There are no <span class=\\"e2\\">pāpa</span>–sins <span class=\\"e2\\">mano-vāk-kāya-ja</span>–committed in thought, word, or deed <span class=\\"e2\\">kalite</span>–in the Age of Kali <span class=\\"e2\\">tata</span>–that <span class=\\"e2\\">kṣaya haya nāhi</span>–are not destroyed <span class=\\"e2\\">govinda-nāme</span>–by the Name of Govinda."},{"class":"b50","text":" “There are no sins committed in thought, word, or deed in the Age of Kali that chanting the Name of Govinda does not destroy."},{"class":"b97","text":" তন্নাস্তি কর্ম্মজং লোকে বাগ্জং মানসমেব বা ।<br />যন্ন ক্ষপয়তে পাপং কলৌ গোবিন্দকীর্ত্তনম্ ॥৪৩॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" tan nāsti karmajaṁ loke vāg-jaṁ mānasam eva vā<br />yan na kṣapayate pāpaṁ kalau govinda-kīrtanam [43]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Skanda-purāṇa)"},{"class":"b71","text":" “‘There are no sins committed in thought, word, or deed in the Age of Kali that chanting the Name of Govinda does not destroy.’"},{"class":"b176","text":" নামে সর্ব্বরোগ নাশ হয়"},{"class":"b177","text":" nāme sarva-roga nāśa haya"},{"class":"b70","text":" The Name cures all disease"},{"class":"b97","text":" নামে সর্ব্বব্যাধিধ্বংস সর্ব্বশাস্ত্রে গায় ।<br />ওগো স্থানেশ্বরী ভক্ত বলিহে তোমায় ॥৪৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" nāme sarva-vyādhi-dhvaṁsa sarva-śāstre gāya<br />ogo sthāneśvarī bhakta balihe tomāya [44]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-śāstre</span>–All the scriptures <span class=\\"e2\\">gāya</span>–sing [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-vyādhi-dhvaṁsa</span>–curing all diseases [occurs] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāme</span>–through the Name. <span class=\\"e2\\">ogo</span>–O <span class=\\"e2\\">sthāneśvarī</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakta</span>–devotee of Sthāneśvarī! <span class=\\"e2\\">balihe</span>–I am speaking <span class=\\"e2\\">tomāya</span>–to you."},{"class":"b50","text":" [Śrīman Mahāprabhu continues:] “All the scriptures sing that the Name cures all diseases. O devotee of Sthāneśvarī! I am speaking to you."},{"class":"b97","text":" সত্য সত্য বলি, ‘লহ বিশ্বাস করিয়া ।<br />‘অচ্যুতানন্দ’ ‘গোবিন্দ’ এই নাম উচ্চারিয়া ॥৪৫॥<br />কাঁদিয়া কাঁদিয়া ডক শ্রীমধুসূদন ।<br />সর্ব্বরোগ নাশ করে শ্রীনামকীর্ত্তনে ॥৪৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" satya satya bali, ‘laha viśvāsa kariyā<br />‘achyutānanda’ ‘govinda’ ei nāma uchchāriyā [45]<br />kā̐diyā kā̐diyā ḍāka śrī-madhusūdana<br />sarva-roga nāśa kare śrī-nāma-kīrtane’ [46]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">satya</span>–Truly, <span class=\\"e2\\">satya</span>–truly, <span class=\\"e2\\">bali</span>–I say, <span class=\\"e2\\">‘viśvāsa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kariyā</span>–‘Faithfully <span class=\\"e2\\">laha</span>–chant, <span class=\\"e2\\">uchchāriyā</span>–uttering <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span>–these <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–Names <span class=\\"e2\\">‘achyutānanda’</span>–‘Achyutānanda’ [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">‘govinda’</span>–‘Govinda’. <span class=\\"e2\\">kā̐diyā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kā̐diyā</span>–Cry [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">ḍāka</span>–call out <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-madhusūdana</span>–to Śrī Madhusūdan. <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-nāma-kīrtane</span>–Chanting the Name <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-roga</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāśa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kare’</span>–cures all diseases.’"},{"class":"b50","text":" “I speak the truth: ‘Chant the Names ‘Achyutānanda’ and ‘Govinda’ with faith. Cry and call out to Śrī Madhusūdan. Chanting the Name cures all diseases.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" অচ্যতানন্দ-গোবিন্দ-নামোচ্চরণভীষিতঃ ।<br />নশ্যন্তি সকলা রোগাঃ সত্যং সত্যং বদাম্যহম্ ॥৪৭॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" achyutānanda-govinda-nāmochcharaṇa-bhīṣitaḥ<br />naśyanti sakalā rogāḥ satyaṁ satyaṁ vadāmy aham [47]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Bṛhan-nāradīya-purāṇa)"},{"class":"b71","text":" “‘I tell you truthfully that all diseases die of fright when the Names ‘Achyutānanda’ and ‘Govinda’ are chanted.’"},{"class":"b176","text":" নামে মহাপাতকী পংক্তিপাবন হয়"},{"class":"b177","text":" nāme mahāpātakī paṁkti-pāvana haya"},{"class":"b70","text":" The Name turns the greatest sinners into purifiers of their class"},{"class":"b97","text":" মহাপাতকীও অহর্নিশ হরিগানে ।<br />শুদ্ধ হঞা গণ্য হয় সুপংক্তিপাবনে ॥৪৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" mahāpātakīo ahar-niśa hari-gāne<br />śuddha hañā gaṇya haya supaṁkti-pāvane [48]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">hari-gāne</span>–By chanting ‘Hari’ <span class=\\"e2\\">ahar-niśa</span>–day and night, <span class=\\"e2\\">mahāpātakīo</span>–even the greatest sinners <span class=\\"e2\\">śuddha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">hañā</span>–become pure [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">gaṇya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–recognised <span class=\\"e2\\">supaṁkti-pāvane</span>–as purifiers of [their] social class."},{"class":"b50","text":" “By chanting the Name of the Lord day and night, even the greatest sinners become pure and recognised as purifiers of their social class."},{"class":"b97","text":" মহাপাতকযুক্তোঽপি কীর্ত্তয়েন্ননিশং হরিম্ ।<br />শুদ্ধান্তঃকরণো ভূত্বা জায়তে পংক্তিপাবনঃ ॥৪৯॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" mahāpātaka-yukto ’pi kīrtayenn aniśaṁ harim<br />śuddhāntaḥkaraṇo bhūtvā jāyate paṁkti-pāvanaḥ [49]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Brahmāṇḍa-purāṇa)"},{"class":"b71","text":" “‘By chanting the Name of the Lord day and night, even the greatest sinners become pure in heart and then purify their social class.’"},{"class":"b176","text":" ভয় ও দণ্ড নিবারণ"},{"class":"b177","text":" bhaya o daṇḍa nivāraṇa"},{"class":"b70","text":" The Name dispels fear and punishment"},{"class":"b97","text":" মহাব্যাধি-ভয়ও বা রাজদণ্ড-ভয় ।<br />নারায়ণ-সঙ্কীর্ত্তনে নিরাতঙ্ক হয় ॥৫০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" mahāvyādhi-bhayao vā rāja-daṇḍa-bhaya<br />nārāyaṇa-saṅkīrtane nirātaṅka haya [50]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">nārāyaṇa-saṅkīrtane</span>–By chanting the Name of Nārāyaṇ, <span class=\\"e2\\">nirātaṅka</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–the soul becomes free from fear, <span class=\\"e2\\">mahāvyādhi-bhayao</span>–even fear of terrible diseases <span class=\\"e2\\">vā</span>–and <span class=\\"e2\\">rāja-daṇḍa-bhaya</span>–fear of punishment by kings."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Chanting the Name of Nārāyaṇ makes the soul fearless of even terrible diseases and punishment by kings."},{"class":"b97","text":" মহাব্যাধি-সমাচ্ছন্নো রাজবধোপপীড়িতঃ ।<br />নারায়ণেতি সঙ্কীর্ত্য নিরাতঙ্কো ভবেন্নরঃ ॥৫১॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" mahāvyādhi-samāchchhanno rāja-vadhopapīḍitaḥ<br />nārāyaṇeti saṅkīrtya nirāṭaṅko bhaven naraḥ [51]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Vahni-purāṇa)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘Souls who are afflicted with terrible diseases or oppressed by kings become fearless by chanting the Name of Nārāyaṇ.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" সর্ব্বরোগ-সর্ব্বক্লেশ-উপদ্রব-সনে ।<br />অরিষ্টাদি-বিনাশ হয় হরি-উচ্চারণে ॥৫২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sarva-roga-sarva-kleśa-upadrava-sane<br />ariṣṭādi-vināśa haya hari-uchchāraṇe [52]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">hari-uchchāraṇe</span>–By chanting the Name of the Lord, <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-roga</span>–all diseases, <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-kleśa </span>–all suffering, <span class=\\"e2\\">upadrava-sane</span>–along with [all] disturbances, <span class=\\"e2\\">ariṣṭādi</span>–calamities, and so on, <span class=\\"e2\\">vināśa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–are destroyed."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Chanting the Name of the Lord destroys all diseases, suffering, disturbances, calamities, and so on."},{"class":"b97","text":" সর্ব্বরোগোপশমনং সর্ব্বোপদ্রবনাশনম্ ।<br />শান্তিদং সর্ব্বারিষ্টানাং হরের্নামানুকীর্ত্তনম্ ॥৫৩॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" sarva-rogopaśamanaṁ sarvopadrava-nāśanam<br />śāntidaṁ sarvāriṣṭānāṁ harer nāmānukīrtanam [53]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Bṛhad-viṣṇu-purāṇa)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘Chanting the Name of the Lord cures all diseases, ends all disturbances, and pacifies all calamities.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" যথা অতিবায়ুবলে মেঘ দূরে যায় ।<br />সূর্য্যোদয়ে তমোনাশ অবশ্যই পায় ॥৫৪॥<br />তথা সঙ্কীর্ত্তিত নাম জীবের ব্যসন ।<br />দূর করে স্বপ্রভাবে, এ ব্যাসবচন ॥৫৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" yathā ativāyu-bale megha dūre yāya<br />sūryodaye tamo-nāśa avaśyai pāya [54]<br />tathā saṅkīrtita nāma jīvera vyasana<br />dūra kare svaprabhāve, e vyāsa-vachana [55]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">yathā</span>–As <span class=\\"e2\\">megha</span>–clouds <span class=\\"e2\\">dūre</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">yāya</span>–go away <span class=\\"e2\\">ativāyu-bale</span>–by the force of wind [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">tamo-nāśa pāya</span>–darkness is dispelled <span class=\\"e2\\">avaśyai</span>–invariably <span class=\\"e2\\">sūryodaye</span>–by the rising of the sun, <span class=\\"e2\\">tathā</span>–so <span class=\\"e2\\">saṅkīrtita</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–the chanted Name <span class=\\"e2\\">dūra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kare</span>–drives away <span class=\\"e2\\">jīvera</span>–the soul’s <span class=\\"e2\\">vyasana</span>–difficulties <span class=\\"e2\\">svaprabhāve</span>–by His own power. <span class=\\"e2\\">e</span>–These [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">vyāsa-vachana</span>–the words of Vyāsa."},{"class":"b50","text":" “As the wind drives away clouds and the rising sun invariably dispels darkness, so the chanted Name drives away the soul’s difficulties by His own power. These are the words of Vyāsa."},{"class":"b97","text":" সঙ্কীর্ত্ত্যমানো ভগবাননন্তঃ<br />শ্রুতানুভাবো ব্যসনং হি পুংসাম্ ।<br />প্রবিশ্য চিত্তং বিধুনোত্যশেষং<br />যথা তমোঽর্কোঽভ্রমিবাতিবাতঃ ॥৫৬॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" saṅkīrtyamāno bhagavān anantaḥ<br />śrutānubhāvo vyasanaṁ hi puṁsām<br />praviśya chittaṁ vidhunoty aśeṣaṁ<br />yathā tamo ’rko ’bhram ivāti-vātaḥ [56]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Śrīmad Bhāgavatam: 12.12.48)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘When souls hear and chant about the Infinite Lord, He enters their hearts and removes all their difficulties, just as the sun dispels darkness and the wind disperses clouds.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" আর্ত্ত বা বিষণ্ণ শিথিলমনা ভীত ।<br />ঘোরব্যাধিক্লেশে আর না দেখে হিত ॥৫৭॥<br />‘নারায়ণ’ ‘হরি’ বলি’ করে সঙ্কীর্ত্তন ।<br />নিশ্চয় বিমুক্তদুঃখ সুখী সেই জন ॥৫৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ārta vā viṣaṇṇa śithila-manā bhīta<br />ghora-vyādhi-kleśe āra nā dekhe hita [57]<br />‘nārāyaṇa’ ‘hari’ bali’ kare saṅkīrtana<br />niśchaya vimukta-duḥkha sukhī sei jana [58]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [When] <span class=\\"e2\\">sei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">jana</span>–those who [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">ārta</span>–distressed, <span class=\\"e2\\">viṣaṇṇa</span>–depressed, <span class=\\"e2\\">śithila-manā</span>–disheartened, <span class=\\"e2\\">bhīta</span>–fearful, <span class=\\"e2\\">vā</span>–or <span class=\\"e2\\">ghora-vyādhi-kleśe</span>–afflicted with a terrible disease <span class=\\"e2\\">dekhe</span>–see <span class=\\"e2\\">nā</span>–no <span class=\\"e2\\">āra</span>–other <span class=\\"e2\\">hita</span>–help [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">bali’</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">saṅkīrtana kare</span>–chant <span class=\\"e2\\">‘nārāyaṇa’</span>–‘Nārāyaṇ’ [or] <span class=\\"e2\\">‘hari’</span>–‘Hari’, [they] <span class=\\"e2\\">niśchaya</span>–certainly [become] <span class=\\"e2\\">sukhī</span>–happy [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">vimukta-duḥkha</span>–free from sorrow."},{"class":"b50","text":" “When those who are distressed, depressed, disheartened, fearful, or afflicted with a terrible disease see no help anywhere and chant ‘Nārāyaṇ’ or ‘Hari’, they certainly become happy and free from sorrow."},{"class":"b97","text":" আর্ত্তা বিষণ্ণাঃ শিথিলাশ্চ ভীতা<br />ঘোরেষু চ ব্যাধিষু বর্ত্তমানাঃ ।<br />সঙ্কীর্ত্ত্য নারায়ণ-শব্দমেকং<br />বিমুক্তদুঃখাঃ সুখিনো ভবন্তি ॥৫৯॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" ārtā viṣaṇṇāḥ śithilāś cha bhītā<br />ghoreṣu cha vyādhiṣu vartamānāḥ<br />saṅkīrtya nārāyaṇa-śabdam ekaṁ<br />vimukta-duḥkhāḥ sukhino bhavanti [59]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Viṣṇu-dharma-purāṇa)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘Those who are distressed, depressed, disheartened, fearful, or terribly diseased become free from sorrow and happy by once chanting the Name of Nārāyaṇ.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" অসীম শক্তিমান্ বিষ্ণু, তাঁহার কীর্ত্তনে ।<br />যক্ষ-রক্ষ-বেতালাদি ভূতপ্রেতগণে ॥৬০॥<br />বিনায়ক-ডাকিন্যাদি হিংস্রক সমস্ত ।<br />পলায়ন করে সব দুঃখ হয় অস্ত ॥৬১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" asīma śaktimān viṣṇu, tā̐hāra kīrtane<br />yakṣa-rakṣa-vetālādi bhūta-preta-gaṇe [60]<br />vināyaka-ḍākinyādi hiṁsraka samasta<br />palāyana kare saba duḥkha haya asta [61]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">viṣṇu</span>–Viṣṇu [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">asīma</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">śaktimān</span>–a possessor of unlimited power. <span class=\\"e2\\">yakṣa-rakṣa-vetālādi</span>–Fiends, demons, evil spirits, <span class=\\"e2\\">bhūta-preta-gaṇe</span>–ghosts, disembodied souls, <span class=\\"e2\\">vināyaka-ḍākinyādi</span>–monsters, witches, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">samasta</span>–all [other] <span class=\\"e2\\">hiṁsraka</span>–ferocious entities <span class=\\"e2\\">palāyana</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kare</span>–flee <span class=\\"e2\\">tā̐hāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kīrtane</span>–from the chanting [of] His [Name]. <span class=\\"e2\\">saba</span>–All <span class=\\"e2\\">duḥkha</span>–distress <span class=\\"e2\\">asta haya</span>–comes to an end [by chanting His Name]."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Viṣṇu is unlimitedly powerful. Fiends, demons, evil spirits, ghosts, disembodied souls, monsters, witches, and all other ferocious entities flee from the chanting of His Name. By chanting His Name, all distress comes to an end."},{"class":"b97","text":" সর্ব্বানর্থনাশী হরিনাম-সঙ্কীর্ত্তন ।<br />ক্ষুধা তৃষ্ণা স্খলিতাদি বিপদনাশন ॥৬২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sarvānartha-nāśī hari-nāma-saṅkīrtana<br />kṣudhā tṛṣṇā skhalitādi vipada-nāśana [62]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">hari-nāma-saṅkīrtana</span>–Chanting the Name of the Lord <span class=\\"e2\\">sarvānartha-nāśī</span>–destroys all obstacles [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">vipada-nāśana</span>–destroys dangers, <span class=\\"e2\\">kṣudhā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">tṛṣṇā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">skhalitādi</span>–such as hunger, thirst, and injury."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Chanting the Name of the Lord destroys all obstacles and dangers, such as hunger, thirst, and injury."},{"class":"b97","text":" ইহাতে সংশয় যথা, নিশ্চয় তথায় ।<br />নামের বিক্রম কভু না হয় উদয় ॥৬৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ihāte saṁśaya yathā, niśchaya tathāya<br />nāmera vikrama kabhu nā haya udaya [63]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">niśchaya</span>–Certainly, [however,] <span class=\\"e2\\">vikrama</span>–the power <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmera</span>–of the Name <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nā</span>–never <span class=\\"e2\\">udaya haya</span>–appears <span class=\\"e2\\">yathā tathāya</span>–where [there is] <span class=\\"e2\\">saṁśaya</span>–doubt <span class=\\"e2\\">ihāte</span>–about this."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Certainly, however, the power of the Name never appears where there is any doubt about this."},{"class":"b97","text":" বিশ্বাসে নামের কৃপা, অবিশ্বাসে নয় ।<br />এ এক রহস্য, ভক্ত জানহ নিশ্চয় ॥৬৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" viśvāse nāmera kṛpā, aviśvāse naya<br />e eka rahasya, bhakta jānaha niśchaya [64]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛpā</span>–The grace <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmera</span>–of the Name [is attained] <span class=\\"e2\\">viśvāse</span>–through faith, <span class=\\"e2\\">naya</span>–not <span class=\\"e2\\">aviśvāse</span>–through faithlessness. <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakta</span>–O devotees, <span class=\\"e2\\">jānaha</span>–know <span class=\\"e2\\">niśchaya</span>–for certain [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">e</span>–this [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">eka</span>–a <span class=\\"e2\\">rahasya</span>–hidden truth."},{"class":"b50","text":" “The grace of the Name is attained through faith, not faithlessness. O devotees, know for certain that this is one of the hidden truths of the Name."},{"class":"b97","text":" কীর্ত্তনদ্দেবদেবস্য বিষ্ণোর্মিততেজসঃ ।<br />যক্ষরাক্ষসবেতালভূতপ্রেতবিনয়কঃ ॥৬৫॥<br />ডাকিন্যো বিদ্রবন্তি স্ম যে তথান্যে চ হিংসকঃ ।<br />সর্ব্বানর্থহরং তস্য নামসঙ্কীর্ত্তনং স্মৃতম্ ॥৬৬॥<br />নামসঙ্কীর্ত্তনং কৃত্বা ক্ষুত্তৃট্ প্রস্খলিতাদিষু ।<br />বিয়োগং শীঘ্রমাপ্নোতি সর্ব্বানর্থৈর্ন সংশয়ঃ ॥৬৭॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" kīrtanad deva-devasya viṣṇor amita-tejasaḥ<br />yakṣa-rākṣasa-vetāla-bhūta-preta-vinayakaḥ [65]<br />ḍākinyo vidravanti sma ye tathānye cha hiṁsakaḥ<br />sarvānartha-haraṁ tasya nāma-saṅkīrtanaṁ smṛtam [66]<br />nāma-saṅkīrtanaṁ kṛtvā kṣut-tṛṭ praskhalitādiṣu<br />viyogaṁ śīghram āpnoti sarvānarthair na saṁśayaḥ [67]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Viṣṇu-dharma-purāṇa)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘Fiends, demons, evil spirits, ghosts, disembodied souls, monsters, witches, and other ferocious entities flee from the chanting of the Names of the God of gods, the immeasurably powerful Lord, Viṣṇu. Chanting and remembering the Lord’s Name removes all difficulties. Those who chant the Lord’s Name while hungry, thirsty, or injured immediately become free from all difficulties. There is no doubt about this.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" কলিকালকুসর্পের তীক্ষ্ণ দংষ্ট্রা হেরি’ ।<br />ভয় না করিও ভক্ত, শুন শ্রদ্ধা করি’ ॥৬৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kali-kāla-kusarpera tīkṣṇa daṁṣṭrā heri’<br />bhaya nā kario bhakta, śuna śraddhā kari’ [68]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kario nā</span>–Do not be afraid [when] <span class=\\"e2\\">heri’</span>–you see <span class=\\"e2\\">tīkṣṇa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">daṁṣṭrā</span>–the sharp teeth <span class=\\"e2\\">kali-kāla-kusarpera</span>–of the poisonous serpent of Kali-yuga. <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakta</span>–O devotees, <span class=\\"e2\\">śuna</span>–listen <span class=\\"e2\\">śraddhā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kari’</span>–faithfully!"},{"class":"b50","text":" “Do not be afraid when you see the sharp teeth of the poisonous serpent of Kali-yuga. O devotees, listen faithfully!"},{"class":"b97","text":" কৃষ্ণনাম-দাবানল প্রজ্জ্বলিত হঞা ।<br />সে সর্পের দংষ্ট্রা দগ্ধ করিবে ফেলিয়া ॥৬৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kṛṣṇa-nāma-dāvānala prajjvalita hañā<br />se sarpera daṁṣṭrā dagdha karibe pheliyā [69]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-nāma-dāvānala</span>–The raging fire of Kṛṣṇa’s Name <span class=\\"e2\\">prajjvalita</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">hañā</span>–will blaze up [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">pheliyā dagdha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">karibe</span>–burn away <span class=\\"e2\\">se</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sarpera</span>–the serpent’s <span class=\\"e2\\">daṁṣṭrā</span>–teeth."},{"class":"b50","text":" “The raging fire of Kṛṣṇa’s Name will blaze up and burn away the serpent’s teeth."},{"class":"b97","text":" কলিকলকুসর্পস্য তীক্ষ্ণদংষ্ট্রস্য মা ভয়ম্ ।<br />গোবিন্দনামদাবেন দগ্ধো যাস্যতি ভস্মতাম্ ॥৭০॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" kali-kala-kusarpasya tīkṣṇa-daṁṣṭrasya mā bhayam<br />govinda-nāma-dāvena dagdho yāsyati bhasmatām [70]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Skanda-purāṇa)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘Do not fear the sharp teeth of the poisonous serpent of Kali-yuga. The fire of Govinda’s Name will burn it to ashes.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" এই ঘোর কলিযুগে হরিনামাশ্রয়ে ।<br />কৃতকৃত্য ভক্তগণ ত্যক্ত-অন্যাশ্রয়ে ॥৭১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ei ghora kali-yuge hari-nāmāśraye<br />kṛta-kṛtya bhakta-gaṇa tyakta-anyāśraye [71]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakta-gaṇa</span>–Devotees [who] <span class=\\"e2\\">tyakta-anyāśraye</span>–have left all other shelters [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">hari-nāmāśraye</span>–taken shelter of the Lord’s Name <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ghora</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kali-yuge</span>–in this dark Age of Kali [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛta-kṛtya</span>–successful."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Devotees who have left all other shelters and taken shelter of the Lord’s Name in this dark Age of Kali are successful."},{"class":"b97","text":" হরে কেশব গোবিন্দ বাসুদেব জগন্ময় ।<br />এই নাম সঙ্কীর্ত্তনে বড় সুখোদয় ॥৭২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" hare keśava govinda vāsudeva jaganmaya<br />ei nāma saṅkīrtane baḍa sukhodaya [72]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [There is] <span class=\\"e2\\">baḍa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sukhodaya</span>–an arising of great joy <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">saṅkīrtane</span>–by chanting the Names <span class=\\"e2\\">hare</span>–Hari, <span class=\\"e2\\">keśava</span>–Keśava, <span class=\\"e2\\">govinda</span>–Govinda, <span class=\\"e2\\">vāsudeva</span>–Vāsudev, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">jaganmaya</span>–Jaganmay."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Great joy arises by chanting, ‘O Hari! O Keśava! O Govinda! O Vāsudev! O Jaganmay!’"},{"class":"b97","text":" সদা যেই গায় নাম বিশ্বাস করিয়া ।<br />কলিবাধা নাহি তার সদা শুদ্ধ হিয়া ॥৭৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sadā yei gāya nāma viśvāsa kariyā<br />kali-bādhā nāhi tāra sadā śuddha hiyā [73]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kali-bādhā</span>–The obstacles made by Kali <span class=\\"e2\\">nāhi</span>–do not exist <span class=\\"e2\\">sadā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">śuddha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">hiyā</span>–within the eternally pure hearts <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra yei</span>–of those who <span class=\\"e2\\">sadā</span>–constantly [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">viśvāsa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kariyā</span>–faithfully <span class=\\"e2\\">gāya</span>–chant <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–the Name."},{"class":"b50","text":" “The obstacles made by Kali do not exist within the eternally pure hearts of those who constantly and faithfully chant the Name."},{"class":"b97","text":" হরিনামপরা যে চ ঘোরে কলিযুগে নরাঃ ।<br />তে এব কৃতকৃত্যাশ্চ ন কলির্বাধতে হি তান্ ॥৭৪॥<br />হরে কেশব গোবিন্দ বাসুদেব জগন্ময় ।<br />ইতীরয়ন্তি তে নিত্যং ন হি তান্ বাধতে কলিঃ ॥৭৫॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" hari-nāma-parā ye cha ghore kali-yuge narāḥ<br />te eva kṛta-kṛtyāś cha na kalir bādhate hi tān [74]<br />hare keśava govinda vāsudeva jaganmaya<br />itīrayanti te nityaṁ na hi tān bādhate kaliḥ [75]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Bṛhan-nāradīya-purāṇa)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘Souls who devote themselves to the Name of the Lord in the dark Age of Kali are successful. Kali cannot obstruct them. Kali cannot obstruct those who constantly chant, “O Hari! O Keśava! O Govinda! O Vāsudev! O Jaganmay!”’"},{"class":"b97","text":" নারকী কীর্ত্তন করে ‘হরি’ ‘কৃষ্ণ’ বলি’ ।<br />হরিভক্ত হঞা যায় দিব্যধামে চলি’ ॥৭৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" nārakī kīrtana kare ‘hari’ ‘kṛṣṇa’ bali’<br />hari-bhakta hañā yāya divya-dhāme chali’ [76]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">nārakī</span>–The residents of hell [who] <span class=\\"e2\\">bali kīrtana</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kare</span>–chant <span class=\\"e2\\">‘hari’</span>–‘Hari’ [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">‘kṛṣṇa’</span>–‘Kṛṣṇa’, <span class=\\"e2\\">hari-bhakta</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">hañā</span>–become devotees of the Lord [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">chali’ yāya</span>–go <span class=\\"e2\\">divya-dhāme</span>–to the divine abode."},{"class":"b50","text":" “The residents of hell who chant ‘Hari’ and ‘Kṛṣṇa’ become devotees of the Lord and go to the divine abode."},{"class":"b97","text":" যথা যথা হরের্নাম কীর্ত্তয়ন্তি স্ম নারকাঃ ।<br />তথা তথা হরৌ ভক্তিমুদ্বহন্তো দিবং যয়ুঃ ॥৭৭॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" yathā yathā harer nāma kīrtayanti sma nārakāḥ<br />tathā tathā harau bhaktim udvahanto divaṁ yayuḥ [77]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Nṛsiṁha-purāṇa)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘The residents of hell chant the Name of the Lord, accordingly develop devotion to the Lord, and go to the divine abode.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" প্রারব্ধখণ্ডন কেবল হরিনামে হয় ।<br />জ্ঞানকর্ম্মে সেই ফল কভু না মিলয় ॥৭৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" prārabdha-khaṇḍana kevala hari-nāme haya<br />jñāna-karme sei phala kabhu nā milaya [78]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kevala</span>–Only <span class=\\"e2\\">hari-nāme</span>–by the Name of the Lord <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–are <span class=\\"e2\\">prārabdha-khaṇḍana</span>–the active reactions [to the soul’s sins] cut away. [The soul] <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">milaya</span>–never attains <span class=\\"e2\\">sei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">phala</span>–such a result <span class=\\"e2\\">jñāna-karme</span>–through [worldly] knowledge or action."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Only the Name of the Lord can cut away the active reactions to sins. Such a result is never attained through worldly knowledge or action."},{"class":"b97","text":" বিনা হরিকীর্ত্তন কভু কর্ম্মবন্ধ ।<br />খণ্ডন না হয়, মুমুক্ষুতা নহে লব্ধ ॥৭৯॥<br />যে মুক্তি লভিলে আর না হয় কর্ম্মসঙ্গ ।<br />রজস্তমোদোষহীন শূন্য মায়াসঙ্গ ॥৮০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" vinā hari-kīrtana kabhu karma-bandha<br />khaṇḍana nā haya, mumukṣutā nahe labdha [79]<br />ye mukti labhile āra nā haya karma-saṅga<br />rajas-tamo-doṣa-hīna śūnya māyā-saṅga [80]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">vinā</span>–Without <span class=\\"e2\\">hari-kīrtana</span>–chanting the Name of the Lord, <span class=\\"e2\\">karma-bandha</span>–entan­glement in karma <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–is <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nā</span>–never <span class=\\"e2\\">khaṇḍana</span>–cut away, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">mumukṣutā</span>–seekers of liberation <span class=\\"e2\\">labdha nahe</span>–never attain <span class=\\"e2\\">ye</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">mukti</span>–the liberation [in which,] <span class=\\"e2\\">labhile</span>–when [it] is attained, the soul] <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–has <span class=\\"e2\\">āra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nā</span>–no further <span class=\\"e2\\">karma-saṅga</span>–attachment to karma, [becomes] <span class=\\"e2\\">rajas-tamo-doṣa-hīna</span>–free from the faults of passion and ignorance, [and becomes] <span class=\\"e2\\">śūnya</span>–devoid of <span class=\\"e2\\">māyā-saṅga</span>–attachment to the illusory environment."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Without chanting the Name of the Lord, entanglement in karma is never cut away, and seekers of liberation never attain the liberation upon attaining which there is no further attachment to karma. They never become uncontaminated by passion and ignorance or free from attachment to the illusory environment."},{"class":"b97","text":" নাতঃ পরং কর্ম্মনিবন্ধকৃন্তনং<br />মুমুক্ষতাং তীর্থপদানুকীর্ত্তনাৎ ।<br />ন যৎ পুনঃ কর্ম্মসু সজ্জতে মনো-<br />রজস্তমোভ্যাং কলিলং ততোঽন্যথা ॥৮১॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" nātaḥ paraṁ karma-nibandha-kṛntanaṁ<br />mumukṣatāṁ tīrtha-padānukīrtanāt<br />na yat punaḥ karmasu sajjate mano-<br />rajas-tamobhyāṁ kalilaṁ tato ’nyathā [81]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Śrīmad Bhāgavatam: 6.2.46)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘There is no better means for those who desire liberation to cut away the bondage of karma than chanting the Name of the Lord because after chanting the mind does not become attached to karma again. After all other atonements, the mind again becomes polluted by passion and ignorance.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" ম্রিয়মাণ ক্লিষ্ট জন পড়িতে খসিতে ।<br />বিবশ হইয়া কৃষ্ণ বলে কোনমতে ॥৮২॥<br />কর্ম্মার্গলমুক্ত হঞা লভে পরা গতি ।<br />কলিকালে যাহা নাহি লভে অন্য মতি ॥৮৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" mriyamāṇa kliṣṭa jana paḍite khasite<br />vivaśa ha-iyā kṛṣṇa bale kona-mate [82]<br />karmārgala-mukta hañā labhe parā gati<br />kali-kāle yāhā nāhi labhe anya mati [83]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">mriyamāṇa</span>–A dying, <span class=\\"e2\\">kliṣṭa</span>–diseased <span class=\\"e2\\">jana</span>–soul, <span class=\\"e2\\">paḍite</span>–bedridden, <span class=\\"e2\\">khasite</span>–faltering, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">vivaśa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-iyā</span>–desperate [who] <span class=\\"e2\\">kona-mate</span>–somehow or other <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–chants <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span>–the Name of Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">karmārgala-mukta</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">hañā</span>–becomes free from the bondage of karma [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">labhe</span>–attains <span class=\\"e2\\">parā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">gati</span>–the supreme destination— <span class=\\"e2\\">yāhā</span>–which <span class=\\"e2\\">labhe nāhi</span>–souls cannot attain <span class=\\"e2\\">kali-kāle</span>–in the Age of Kali [by] <span class=\\"e2\\">anya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">mati</span>–any other means."},{"class":"b50","text":" “A dying, diseased, bedridden, faltering, desperate soul who somehow or other chants the Name of Kṛṣṇa becomes free from the bondage of karma and attains the supreme destination—which souls in the Age of Kali cannot attain by any other means."},{"class":"b97","text":" যন্নামধেয়ং ম্রিয়মাণ আতুরঃ<br />পতন্ স্খলন্ বা বিবশো গৃণন্ পুমান্ ।<br />বিমুক্তকর্ম্মার্গল উত্তমাং গতিং<br />প্রাপ্নোতি যক্ষ্যন্তি ন তং কলৌ জনাঃ ॥৮৪॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" yan-nāma-dheyaṁ mriyamāṇa āturaḥ<br />patan skhalan vā vivaśo gṛṇan pumān<br />vimukta-karmārgala uttamāṁ gatiṁ<br />prāpnoti yakṣyanti na taṁ kalau janāḥ [84]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Śrīmad Bhāgavatam: 12.3.44)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘In the Age of Kali, souls will not worship the Lord, by chanting whose Name even a dying, diseased, bedridden, faltering, desperate soul becomes free from the bondage of karma and attains the supreme destination.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" শ্রদ্ধা করি’ নাম লইলে অপরাধকোটী ।<br />ক্ষমা করে কৃষ্ণ, যদি না থাকে কুটিনাটী ॥৮৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" śraddhā kari’ nāma la-ile aparādha koṭī<br />kṣamā kare kṛṣṇa, yadi nā thāke kuṭināṭī [85]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">la-ile</span>–When souls chant the Name <span class=\\"e2\\">śraddhā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kari’</span>–faithfully, <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span>–Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">kṣamā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kare</span>–forgives <span class=\\"e2\\">koṭī aparādha</span>–millions of [their] offences <span class=\\"e2\\">yadi</span>–if <span class=\\"e2\\">kuṭināṭī thāke nā</span>–no deceit is present [in them]."},{"class":"b50","text":" “When souls chant the Name with faith, Kṛṣṇa forgives millions of their offences if they are free from deceit."},{"class":"b97","text":" ইহাতে বিশ্বাস যার না হয়, সে জন ।<br />বড়ই দুর্ভাগা, তার নাহিক মোচন ॥৮৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ihāte viśvāsa yāra nā haya, se jana<br />baḍa-i durbhāgā, tāra nāhika mochana [86]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">se</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">jana yāra viśvāsa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haya nā</span>–Those who do not have faith <span class=\\"e2\\">ihāte</span>–in this [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">baḍa-i</span>–extremely <span class=\\"e2\\">durbhāgā</span>–unfortunate. <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra mochana</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāhika</span>–They are not delivered."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Those who do not have faith in this are extremely unfortunate and will not be delivered."},{"class":"b97","text":" মম নামানি লোকেঽস্মিন্ শ্রদ্ধয়া যস্তু কীর্ত্তয়েৎ ।<br />তস্যাপরাধকোটিস্তু ক্ষমাম্যেব ন সংশয়ঃ ॥৮৭॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" mama nāmāni loke ’smin śraddhayā yas tu kīrtayet<br />tasyāparādha-koṭis tu kṣamāmy eva na saṁśayaḥ [87]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Viṣṇu-yāmala)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “[The Lord:]‘I forgive millions of offences committed by anyone in this world who chants My Name with faith. There is no doubt about this.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" মন্ত্র-তন্ত্র-ছিদ্র দেশ-কাল-বস্তু-দোষ ।<br />নামসঙ্কীর্ত্তনে যায়, পায় পরম সন্তোষ ॥৮৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" mantra-tantra-chhidra deśa-kāla-vastu-doṣa<br />nāma-saṅkīrtane yāya, pāya parama santoṣa [88]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-saṅkīrtane</span>–By chanting the Name, <span class=\\"e2\\">mantra-tantra-chhidra</span>–faults concerning mantras and procedures [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">deśa-kāla-vastu-doṣa</span>–flaws concerning time, place, and paraphernalia <span class=\\"e2\\">yāya</span>–go away, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">pāya</span>–one feels <span class=\\"e2\\">parama</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">santoṣa</span>–the greatest joy."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Chanting the Name removes all flaws or faults concerning mantras, procedures, time, place, and paraphernalia, and fills one with the greatest joy."},{"class":"b97","text":" সৎকর্ম্ম প্রধান নাম, তাহার আশ্রয়ে ।<br />অন্য সৎকর্ম্মের সিদ্ধি হইবে নিশ্চয়ে ॥৮৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sat-karma pradhāna nāma, tāhāra āśraye<br />anya sat-karmera siddhi ha-ibe niśchaye [89]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [Chanting] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–the Name [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">sat-karma</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">pradhāna</span>–the foremost auspicious practice, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">niśchaye</span>–for certain, <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">āśraye</span>–under its shelter, [all] <span class=\\"e2\\">anya</span>–other <span class=\\"e2\\">sat-karmera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">siddhi</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-ibe</span>–auspicious practices become successful."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Chanting the Name is the foremost auspicious practice, and under the Name’s shelter, all other auspicious practices certainly become successful."},{"class":"b97","text":" মন্ত্রতস্তন্ত্রতশ্ছিদ্রং দেশকালার্হবস্তুতঃ ।<br />সর্ব্বং করোতি নিশ্ছিদ্রং নামসঙ্কীর্ত্তনং তব ॥৯০॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" mantratas tantrataś chhidraṁ deśa-kālārha-vastutaḥ<br />sarvaṁ karoti niśchhidraṁ nāma-saṅkīrtanaṁ tava [90]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Śrīmad Bhāgavatam: 8.23.16)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘Chanting Your Name nullifies all flaws concerning mantras, procedures, time, place, participants, and paraphernalia.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" সর্ব্ববেদাধিক নাম, ইহাতে সংশয় ।<br />যে করে তাহার কভু মঙ্গল না হয় ॥৯১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sarva-vedādhika nāma, ihāte saṁśaya<br />ye kare tāhāra kabhu maṅgala nā haya [91]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–The Name [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-vedādhika</span>–superior to all the Vedas. <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–There is <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nā</span>–never <span class=\\"e2\\">maṅgala</span>–good fortune <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhāra ye</span>–for those who <span class=\\"e2\\">saṁśaya kare</span>–doubt <span class=\\"e2\\">ihāte</span>–this."},{"class":"b50","text":" “The Name is superior to all the Vedas. Those who doubt this never attain good fortune."},{"class":"b97","text":" প্রণব কৃষ্ণের নাম যাহা হৈতে বেদ ।<br />জন্মিল ব্রহ্মার মুখে বুঝ তত্ত্বভেদ ॥৯২॥<br />ঋক্-যজু-সামাথর্ব্ব সে কৈল পঠন ।<br />‘হরি’ ‘হরি’ যার মুখে শুনি’ অনুক্ষণ ॥৯৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" praṇava kṛṣṇera nāma yāhā haite veda<br />janmila brahmāra mukhe bujha tattva-bheda [92]<br />ṛk-yaju-sāmātharva se kaila paṭhana<br />‘hari’ ‘hari’ yāra mukhe śuni’ anukṣaṇa [93]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bujha</span>–Understand <span class=\\"e2\\">tattva-bheda</span>–the difference in nature [between the Vedas and] <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇera</span>–Kṛṣṇa’s <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–Name <span class=\\"e2\\">praṇava</span>–‘Om’, <span class=\\"e2\\">haite</span>–from <span class=\\"e2\\">yāhā</span>–which <span class=\\"e2\\">veda</span>–the Vedas <span class=\\"e2\\">janmila</span>–manifested <span class=\\"e2\\">brahmāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">mukhe</span>–in the mouth of Brahmā. <span class=\\"e2\\">se yāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">mukhe</span>–Those from whose mouth <span class=\\"e2\\">‘hari’</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">‘hari’</span>–‘Hari! Hari’ <span class=\\"e2\\">śuni’</span>–is heard <span class=\\"e2\\">anukṣaṇa</span>–always <span class=\\"e2\\">paṭhana kaila</span>–have recited <span class=\\"e2\\">ṛk-yaju-sāmātharva</span>–the <span class=\\"e33\\">Ṛg</span>-, <span class=\\"e33\\">Yajur</span>-, <span class=\\"e33\\">Sāma</span>-, and <span class=\\"e33\\">Atharva-veda</span>."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Understand the difference between the Vedas and Kṛṣṇa’s Name ‘Om’, from which the Vedas manifested in the mouth of Brahmā. Those from whose mouth ‘Hari! Hari!’ is always heard have already recited the <span class=\\"e3\\">Ṛg-</span>, <span class=\\"e3\\">Yajur-</span>, <span class=\\"e3\\">Sāma-</span>, and <span class=\\"e3\\">Atharva-veda</span>."},{"class":"b97","text":" ঋগ্বেদো হি যজুর্ব্বেদঃ সামবেদোপ্যঽথর্ব্বণঃ ।<br />অধীতস্তেন যেনোক্তং হরিরিত্যক্ষরদ্বয়ম্ ॥৯৪॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" ṛg-vedo hi yajur-vedaḥ sāma-vedo ’py atharvaṇaḥ<br />adhītas tena yenoktaṁ harir ity akṣara-dvayam [94]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Viṣṇu-dharma-purāṇa)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘Those who have uttered the two syllables ‘Ha-ri’ have certainly studied the <span class=\\"e3\\">Ṛg-</span>, <span class=\\"e3\\">Yajur-</span>, <span class=\\"e3\\">Sāma-</span>, and <span class=\\"e3\\">Atharva-veda</span>.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" ঋক্-যজু-সামাথর্ব্ব পঠ কি কারণ ?<br />‘গোবিন্দ’ ‘গোবিন্দ’ নাম করহ কীর্ত্তন ॥৯৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ṛk-yaju-sāmātharva paṭha ki kāraṇa?<br />‘govinda’ ‘govinda’ nāma karaha kīrtana [95]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">ki</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kāraṇa?</span>–What need [is there] <span class=\\"e2\\">paṭha</span>–to recite <span class=\\"e2\\">ṛk-yaju-sāmātharva</span>–the <span class=\\"e33\\">Ṛg</span>-, <span class=\\"e33\\">Yajur</span>-, <span class=\\"e33\\">Sāma</span>-, and <span class=\\"e33\\">Atharva-veda</span>? <span class=\\"e2\\">kīrtana karaha</span>–Chant <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–the Name: <span class=\\"e2\\">‘govinda’</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">‘govinda’</span>–‘Govinda! Govinda!’"},{"class":"b50","text":" “What need is there to recite the <span class=\\"e3\\">Ṛg-</span>, <span class=\\"e3\\">Yajur-</span>, <span class=\\"e3\\">Sāma-</span>, and <span class=\\"e3\\">Atharva-veda</span>? Just chant ‘Govinda! Govinda!’"},{"class":"b97","text":" মা ঋচো মা যজুস্তাত মা সাম পঠ কিঞ্চন ।<br />গোবিন্দেতি হরের্নাম গেয়ং গায়স্ব নিত্যশঃ ॥৯৬॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" mā ṛcho mā yajus tāta mā sāma paṭha kiñchana<br />govindeti harer nāma geyaṁ gāyasva nityaśaḥ [96]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Skanda-purāṇa)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘Do not recite the <span class=\\"e3\\">Ṛg-</span>, <span class=\\"e3\\">Yajur-</span>, or <span class=\\"e3\\">Sāma-veda</span> any more. Always sing the Lord’s Name ‘Govinda’.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" বিষ্ণুর প্রত্যেক নাম সর্ব্ববেদাধিক ।<br />‘রাম’-নাম জান সহস্র নামের অধিক ॥৯৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" viṣṇura pratyeka nāma sarva-vedādhika<br />‘rāma’-nāma jāna sahasra nāmera adhika [97]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">jāna</span>–Know [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">pratyeka</span>–every <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–Name <span class=\\"e2\\">viṣṇura</span>–of Viṣṇu [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-vedādhika</span>–superior to all the Vedas, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–the Name <span class=\\"e2\\">‘rāma’</span>–‘Rāma’ [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">adhika</span>–superior <span class=\\"e2\\">sahasra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmera</span>–to a thousand Names [of Viṣṇu]."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Know that every Name of Viṣṇu is superior to all the Vedas and that the Name ‘Rāma’ is superior to a thousand Names of Viṣṇu."},{"class":"b97","text":" বিষ্ণোরেকৈকনামাপি সর্ব্ববেদাধিকং মতম্ ।<br />তদৃক্ নামসহস্রেণ ‘রাম’-নামসমং স্মৃতম্ ॥৯৮॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" viṣṇor ekaika-nāmāpi sarva-vedādhikaṁ matam<br />tadṛk-nāma-sahasreṇa ‘rāma’-nāma-samaṁ smṛtam [98]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Padma-purāṇa)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘Every single Name of Viṣṇu is superior to all the Vedas, and the Name of Rāma is known to be equal to a thousand Names of Viṣṇu.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" সহস্র নাম তিনবার আবৃত্তি করিলে ।<br />যেই ফল হয় তাহা এক কৃষ্ণ-নামে মিলে ॥৯৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sahasra nāma tina-bāra āvṛtti karile<br />yei phala haya tāhā eka kṛṣṇa-nāme mile [99]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">eka</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-nāme</span>–By [chanting] one Name of Kṛṣṇa, <span class=\\"e2\\">mile</span>–the soul attains <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhā yei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">phala</span>–the result that <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–occurs <span class=\\"e2\\">āvṛtti</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">karile</span>–when they chant <span class=\\"e2\\">sahasra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–a thousand Names [of Viṣṇu] <span class=\\"e2\\">tina-bāra</span>–three times."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Once chanting the Name of Kṛṣṇa produces the same result as chanting a thousand Names of Viṣṇu three times."},{"class":"b97","text":" ‘কৃষ্ণ কৃষ্ণ কৃষ্ণ কৃষ্ণ কৃষ্ণ কৃষ্ণ কৃষ্ণ হে’ ।<br />এই নাম সর্ব্বক্ষণ ভক্ত সব কর হে ॥১০০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ‘kṛṣṇa kṛṣṇa kṛṣṇa kṛṣṇa kṛṣṇa kṛṣṇa kṛṣṇa he’<br />ei nāma sarva-kṣaṇa bhakta saba kara he [100]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">‘kṛṣṇa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa he’</span>–‘Kṛṣṇa, Kṛṣṇa, Kṛṣṇa, Kṛṣṇa, Kṛṣṇa, Kṛṣṇa, Kṛṣṇa!’ <span class=\\"e2\\">he</span>–O <span class=\\"e2\\">saba bhakta</span>–devotees! <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-kṣaṇa</span>–Constantly <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kara</span>–chant the Name!"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘Kṛṣṇa, Kṛṣṇa, Kṛṣṇa, Kṛṣṇa, Kṛṣṇa, Kṛṣṇa, Kṛṣṇa!’ O devotees! Constantly chant the Name!"},{"class":"b97","text":" ‘হরে কৃষ্ণ হরে কৃষ্ণ কৃষ্ণ কৃষ্ণ হরে হরে ।<br />হরে রাম হরে রাম রাম রাম হরে হরে’ ॥১০১॥<br />এই ষোল নামে সর্ব্বদিক্ বজায় রহিল হে ।<br />সর্ব্বফলসিদ্ধি লাভ এই ষোল নামে হইবে হে ॥১০২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ‘hare kṛṣṇa hare kṛṣṇa kṛṣṇa kṛṣṇa hare hare<br />hare rāma hare rāma rāma rāma hare hare’ [101]<br />ei ṣola nāme sarva-dik bajāya rahila he<br />sarva-phala-siddhi lābha ei ṣola nāme ha-ibe he [102]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ṣola</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāme</span>–By these sixteen Names, <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-dik</span>–all directions <span class=\\"e2\\">bajāya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">rahila he</span>–are maintained! <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ṣola</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāme</span>–By these sixteen Names, <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-phala-siddhi</span>–all perfection <span class=\\"e2\\">lābha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-ibe he</span>–will be attained!"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘Hare Kṛṣṇa Hare Kṛṣṇa Kṛṣṇa Kṛṣṇa Hare Hare Hare Rāma Hare Rāma Rāma Rāma Hare Hare’—by chanting these sixteen Names, everything is maintained! By chanting these sixteen Names, you will attain all perfection!"},{"class":"b97","text":" সহস্রনাম্নাং পুণ্যানাং ত্রিরাবৃত্ত্যা তু যৎ ফলম্ ।<br />একাবৃত্ত্যা তু কৃষ্ণস্য নামৈকং তৎ প্রযচ্ছতি ॥১০৩॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" sahasra-nāmnāṁ puṇyānāṁ trir-āvṛttyā tu yat phalam<br />ekāvṛttyā tu kṛṣṇasya nāmaikaṁ tat prayachchhati [103]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Brahmāṇḍa-purāṇa)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘Once chanting the Name of Kṛṣṇa produces the same result as chanting a thousand Holy Names of Viṣṇu three times.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" তীর্থযাত্রাপরিশ্রমে কিবা ফল হবে ।<br />‘হরে কৃষ্ণ’ নিত্য গানে সব ফল পাবে ॥১০৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" tīrtha-yātrā-pariśrame kibā phala habe<br />‘hare kṛṣṇa’ nitya gāne saba phala pābe [104]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kibā</span>–What <span class=\\"e2\\">phala</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">habe</span>–is the benefit <span class=\\"e2\\">tīrtha-yātrā-pariśrame</span>–of labouring to visit the holy places? <span class=\\"e2\\">pābe</span>–You will attain <span class=\\"e2\\">saba</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">phala</span>–all such benefits <span class=\\"e2\\">nitya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">gāne</span>–by constantly chanting <span class=\\"e2\\">‘hare</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa’</span>–‘Hare Kṛṣṇa’."},{"class":"b50","text":" “What is the benefit of labouring to visit the holy places? You will attain all such benefits by constantly chanting ‘Hare Kṛṣṇa’."},{"class":"b97","text":" কিবা কুরুক্ষেত্র, কাশী, পুষ্কর-ভ্রমণে ।<br />জিহ্বাগ্রেতে হরিনাম যাঁর ক্ষণে ক্ষণে ॥১০৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kibā kurukṣetra, kāśī, puṣkara-bhramaṇe<br />jihvāgrete hari-nāma yā̐ra kṣaṇe kṣaṇe [105]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kibā</span>–What [is the value] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhramaṇe</span>–of visiting <span class=\\"e2\\">kurukṣetra</span>–Kurukṣetra, <span class=\\"e2\\">kāśī</span>–Kāśī, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">puṣkara</span>–Puṣkara [for those] <span class=\\"e2\\">yā̐ra jihvāgrete</span>–on the tip of whose tongue <span class=\\"e2\\">hari-nāma</span>–the Lord’s Name [is present] <span class=\\"e2\\">kṣaṇe</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kṣaṇe</span>–moment by moment?"},{"class":"b50","text":" “What is the value of visiting Kurukṣetra, Kāśī, and Puṣkara for those on the tip of whose tongue the Lord’s Name is always present?"},{"class":"b97","text":" কুরুক্ষেত্রেণ কিং তস্য কিং কাশ্যা পুষ্করেণ বা ।<br />জিহ্বাগ্রে বসতি যস্য হরিরিত্যক্ষরদ্বয়ম্ ॥১০৬॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" kurukṣetreṇa kiṁ tasya kiṁ kāśyā puṣkareṇa vā<br />jihvāgre vasati yasya harir ity akṣara-dvayam [106]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Skanda-purāṇa)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘What are Kurukṣetra, Kāśī, and Puṣkara to those on the tip of whose tongue the two syllables ‘Ha-ri’ reside?’"},{"class":"b97","text":" কোটি শত কোটি সহস্র তীর্থে যাহা নয় ।<br />হরিনাম-কীর্ত্তনেতে সেই ফল হয় ॥১০৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" koṭi śata koṭi sahasra tīrthe yāhā naya<br />hari-nāma-kīrtanete sei phala haya [107]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">phala yāhā</span>–The result that <span class=\\"e2\\">naya</span>–is not [attained by visiting] <span class=\\"e2\\">koṭi</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">śata</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">koṭi</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sahasra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">tīrthe</span>–millions or billions of holy places <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–is [attained] <span class=\\"e2\\">hari-nāma-kīrtanete</span>–by chanting the Name of the Lord."},{"class":"b50","text":" “By chanting the Name of the Lord, the souls attain a result that is not attained by visiting millions or billions of holy places."},{"class":"b97","text":" তীর্থকোটিসহস্রাণি তীর্থকোটিশতানি চ ।<br />তানি সর্ব্বাণ্যবাপ্নোতি বিষ্ণোর্নামানুকীর্ত্তনাৎ ॥১০৮॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" tīrtha-koṭi-sahasrāṇi tīrtha-koṭi-śatāni cha<br />tāni sarvāṇy avāpnoti viṣṇor nāmānukīrtanāt [108]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Vāmana-purāṇa)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘By constantly chanting the Name of Viṣṇu, the soul attains the result of visiting millions and billions of holy places.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" কুরুক্ষেত্রে বসি’ বিশ্বামিত্র ঋষি বলে ।<br />‘শুনিয়াছি বহু তীর্থনাম ধরাতলে ॥১০৯॥<br />হরিনাম-কীর্ত্তনের কোটি-অংশতুল্য ।<br />কোন তীর্থ নাহি’—এই বাক্য বহু মূল্য ॥১১০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kurukṣetre basi’ viśvāmitra ṛṣi bale<br />‘śuniyāchhi bahu tīrtha-nāma dharā-tale [109]<br />hari-nāma-kīrtanera koṭi-aṁśa-tulya<br />kona tīrtha nāhi’—ei vākya bahu mūlya [110]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [Once,] <span class=\\"e2\\">basi’</span>–sitting <span class=\\"e2\\">kurukṣetre</span>–at Kurukṣetra, <span class=\\"e2\\">viśvāmitra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ṛṣi</span>–Viśvāmitra Ṛṣi <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–said, <span class=\\"e2\\">‘śuniyāchhi</span>–‘I have heard <span class=\\"e2\\">bahu</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">tīrtha-nāma</span>–the names of many holy places <span class=\\"e2\\">dharā-tale</span>–on the earth, [but] <span class=\\"e2\\">koṭi-aṁśa</span>–one ten-millionth [of the value] <span class=\\"e2\\">hari-nāma-kīrtanera</span>–of chanting the Name of the Lord <span class=\\"e2\\">nāhi</span>–is not <span class=\\"e2\\">tulya </span>–comparable [to] <span class=\\"e2\\">kona</span>–any <span class=\\"e2\\">tīrtha</span>–holy place. <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span>–This <span class=\\"e2\\">vākya</span>–statement [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">bahu</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">mūlya</span>–very valuable."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Once, sitting at Kurukṣetra, Viśvāmitra Ṛṣi said, ‘I have heard the names of many holy places on the earth, but none of them are comparable to even one ten-millionth of the value of chanting the Name of the Lord.’ This statement is very valuable."},{"class":"b97","text":" বিশ্রুতানি বহূন্যেব তীর্থানি বহুধানি চ ।<br />কোট্যংশেন নি তুল্যানি নামকীর্ত্তনতো হরেঃ ॥১১১॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" viśrutāni bahūny eva tīrthāni bahudhāni cha<br />koṭy-aṁśena na tulyāni nāma-kīrtanato hareḥ [111]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Viśvāmitra-saṁhitā)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘The various and numerous renowned holy places do not equal one ten-millionth of the value of chanting the Name of the Lord.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" বেদাগম বহু শাস্ত্রে কিবা প্রয়োজন ।<br />কেন করে লোক বহুতীর্থাদি ভ্রমণ ॥১১২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" vedāgama bahu śāstre kibā prayojana<br />kena kare loka bahu-tīrthādi bhramaṇa [112]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kibā</span>–What <span class=\\"e2\\">prayojana</span>–need [is there] <span class=\\"e2\\">vedāgama</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bahu</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">śāstre</span>–for the Vedas, Āgamas, and numerous other scriptures? [And] <span class=\\"e2\\">kena</span>–why <span class=\\"e2\\">loka bhramaṇa kare</span>–do people visit <span class=\\"e2\\">bahu-tīrthādi</span>–so many holy places?"},{"class":"b50","text":" “What need is there for the Vedas, Āgamas, and numerous other scriptures? And why do people visit so many holy places?"},{"class":"b97","text":" আত্মমুক্তিবাঞ্ছা যার, সেই সর্ব্বক্ষণ ।<br />‘গোবিন্দ’ ‘গোবিন্দ’ বলি’ করুক কীর্ত্তন ॥১১৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" ātma-mukti-vāñchhā yāra, sei sarva-kṣaṇa<br />‘govinda’ ‘govinda’ bali’ karuka kīrtana [113]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [Let] <span class=\\"e2\\">sei yāra</span>–those who <span class=\\"e2\\">ātma-mukti-vāñchhā</span>–desire their own liberation <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-kṣaṇa</span>–constantly <span class=\\"e2\\">kīrtana karuka</span>–chant <span class=\\"e2\\">‘govinda’</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">‘govinda’</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bali’</span>–‘Govinda! Govinda!’"},{"class":"b50","text":" “Let those who desire their own liberation constantly chant ‘Govinda! Govinda!’"},{"class":"b97","text":" কিন্তাত বেদাগমশাস্ত্রবিস্তরৈস্<br />তীর্থৈরনেকৈরপি কিং প্রয়োজনম্ ।<br />যদ্যাত্মনো বাঞ্ছসি মুক্তিকারণং<br />গোবিন্দ গোবিন্দ ইতি স্ফুটং রট ॥১১৪॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" kin tāta vedāgama-śāstra-vistarais<br />tīrthair anekair api kiṁ prayojanam<br />yady ātmano vāñchhasi mukti-kāraṇaṁ<br />govinda govinda iti sphuṭaṁ raṭa [114]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Laghu-bhāgavata)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘My child, what is the use of the Vedas, Āgamas, and other scriptures? What need is there for the numerous holy places? If you seek the means to your own liberation, then simply chant, “Govinda! Govinda!”’"},{"class":"b97","text":" সর্ব্বসৎকর্ম্মাধিক নাম জানহ নিশ্চয় ।<br />এই কথা বিশ্বাসিলে সর্ব্বধর্ম্ম হয় ॥১১৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sarva-sat-karmādhika nāma jānaha niśchaya<br />ei kathā viśvāsile sarva-dharma haya [115]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">jānaha</span>–Know <span class=\\"e2\\">niśchaya</span>–for certain [that chanting] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–the Name [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-sat-karmādhika</span>–superior to all pious activities. <span class=\\"e2\\">viśvāsile</span>–If you have faith <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kathā</span>–in this principle, <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-dharma</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–all [your] duties are [automatically] fulfilled."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Know for certain that chanting the Name is superior to all pious activities. If you have faith in this principle, all your duties are automatically fulfilled."},{"class":"b97","text":" সূর্য্য উপরাগে কোটি কোটি গরুদান ।<br />প্রয়াগেতে কল্পবাস মাঘেতে বিধান ॥১১৬॥<br />অযুত যজ্ঞাদি কর্ম্ম স্বর্গমেরুদান ।<br />শতাংশেতে হরিনামের না হয় সমান ॥১১৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sūrya uparāge koṭi koṭi garu-dāna<br />prayāgete kalpa-vāsa māghete vidhāna [116]<br />ayuta yajñādi karma svarga-meru-dāna<br />śatāṁśete hari-nāmera nā haya samāna [117]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">koṭi</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">koṭi</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">garu-dāna</span>–Donating billions of cows <span class=\\"e2\\">sūrya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">uparāge</span>–during a solar eclipse, <span class=\\"e2\\">kalpa-vāsa</span>–residing for billions of years <span class=\\"e2\\">prayāgete</span>–in Prayāg [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">vidhāna</span>–observing rites <span class=\\"e2\\">māghete</span>–during the month of Māgh, <span class=\\"e2\\">karma</span>–performing <span class=\\"e2\\">ayuta</span>–ten thousand <span class=\\"e2\\">yajñādi</span>–sacrifices, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">svarga-meru-dāna</span>–donating a Mount Sumeru’s worth of gold <span class=\\"e2\\">samāna haya nā</span>–does not equal <span class=\\"e2\\">śatāṁśete</span>–one one-hundredth [of the value] <span class=\\"e2\\">hari-nāmera</span>–of [chanting] the Name of the Lord."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Donating tens of millions of cows during a solar eclipse, residing at Prayāg for billions of years and observing rites during the month of Māgh, performing ten million sacrifices, and donating a Mount Sumeru’s worth of gold does not equal one one-hundredth of the value of chanting the Name of the Lord."},{"class":"b97","text":" গোকোটিদানং গ্রহণে খগস্য<br />প্রয়াগগঙ্গোদক-কল্পবাসঃ ।<br />যজ্ঞাযুতং মেরুসুবর্ণদানং<br />গোবিন্দকীর্ত্তের্ন সমং শতাংশৈঃ ॥১১৮॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" go-koṭi-dānaṁ grahaṇe khagasya<br />prayāga-gaṅgodaka-kalpa-vāsaḥ<br />yajñāyutaṁ meru-suvarṇa-dānaṁ<br />govinda-kīrter na samaṁ śatāṁśaiḥ [118]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Laghu-bhāgavata)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘Donating ten million cows during a solar eclipse, residing in the waters of the Ganges at Prayāg for billions of years, performing ten thousand sacrifices, and donating a Mount Sumeru’s worth of gold does not equal one one-hundredth of the value of chanting the Name of Govinda.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" ইষ্টাপূর্ত্ত কর্ম্ম বহু বহু কৃত হৈলে ।<br />তথাপি সে সব ভবহেতু শাস্ত্রে বলে ॥১১৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" iṣṭāpūrta karma bahu bahu kṛta haile<br />tathāpi se saba bhava hetu śāstre bale [119]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">śāstre</span>–The scriptures <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–say <span class=\\"e2\\">iṣṭāpūrta</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">karma</span>–public welfare works, [even if] <span class=\\"e2\\">se</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">saba kṛta</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haile</span>–they all are performed <span class=\\"e2\\">bahu</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bahu</span>–many [times], <span class=\\"e2\\">tathāpi</span>–still [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">hetu</span>–a cause [of bondage] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhava</span>–within the material world."},{"class":"b50","text":" “The scriptures say that public welfare works, even if they are performed many times, are a cause of bondage within the material world."},{"class":"b97","text":" হরিনাম অনায়াসে ভবমুক্তিধর ।<br />কর্ম্মফল নামের কাছে অকিঞ্চিৎকর ॥১২০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" hari-nāma anāyāse bhava-mukti-dhara<br />karma-phala nāmera kāchhe akiñchitkara [120]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">hari-nāma</span>–The Name of the Lord <span class=\\"e2\\">anāyāse</span>–easily <span class=\\"e2\\">bhava-mukti-dhara</span>–grants liberation from the material world. <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kāchhe</span>–Next to the Name, <span class=\\"e2\\">karma-phala</span>–the fruits of [pious] karma [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">akiñchitkara</span>–inconsequential."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Chanting the Name of the Lord easily grants liberation from the material world. Next to the Name, the fruits of pious karma are nothing."},{"class":"b97","text":" ইষ্টাপূর্ত্তানি কর্ম্মাণি সুবহূনি কৃতান্যপি ।<br />ভবহেতূনি তান্যেব হরের্নাম তু মুক্তিদম্ ॥১২১॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" iṣṭāpūrtāni karmāṇi subahūni kṛtāny api<br />bhava-hetūni tāny eva harer nāma tu mukti-dam [121]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Baudhāyana-saṁhitā)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘Public welfare works, even if performed many times, are a cause of bondage within the material world. Only chanting the Name of the Lord grants liberation.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" সাঙ্খ্য-অষ্টাঙ্গাদি যোগে কিবা আশা ধর ।<br />মুক্তি চাও—গোবিন্দ-কীর্ত্তন সদা কর ॥১২২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sāṅkhya-aṣṭāṅgādi yoge kibā āśā dhara<br />mukti chāo—govinda-kīrtana sadā kara [122]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kibā</span>–What <span class=\\"e2\\">āśā</span>–hope [do] <span class=\\"e2\\">dhara</span>–you have <span class=\\"e2\\">sāṅkhya-aṣṭāṅgādi</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">yoge</span>–in metaphysics, aṣṭāṅga-yoga, and so on? <span class=\\"e2\\">chāo</span>–You want<span class=\\"e2\\"> mukti</span>–liberation, [so] <span class=\\"e2\\">sadā</span>–always <span class=\\"e2\\">govinda-kīrtana kara</span>–chant the Name of Govinda."},{"class":"b50","text":" “What hope do you have in metaphysics and aṣṭāṅga-yoga? You want liberation, so just chant the Name of Govinda."},{"class":"b97","text":" মুক্তিও সামান্য ফল নামের নিকটে ।<br />হেলায় করিলে নাম জীবের মুক্তি ঘটে ॥১২৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" muktio sāmānya phala nāmera nikaṭe<br />helāya karile nāma jīvera mukti ghaṭe [123]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nikaṭe</span>–Next to the Name, <span class=\\"e2\\">muktio</span>–even liberation [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">sāmānya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">phala</span>–an insignificant fruit. <span class=\\"e2\\">jīvera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">mukti</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ghaṭe</span>–Souls attain liberation [even] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma karile</span>–when they chant the Name <span class=\\"e2\\">helāya</span>–negligently."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Next to the Name, even liberation is an insignificant attainment. Souls attain liberation even when they negligently chant the Name."},{"class":"b97","text":" কিং করিষ্যতি সাঙ্খ্যেন কিং যোগৈর্নরনায়ক ।<br />মুক্তিমিচ্ছসি রাজেন্দ্র কুরু গোবিন্দকীর্ত্তনম্ ॥১২৪॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" kiṁ kariṣyati sāṅkhyena kiṁ yogair nara-nāyaka<br />muktim ichchhasi rājendra kuru govinda-kīrtanam [124]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Garuḍa-purāṇa)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘O King, what will you do with metaphysics and yoga? You want liberation, O Emperor, so chant the Name of Govinda.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" শ্বপচ হইলেও দ্বিজশ্রেষ্ঠ বলি তারে ।<br />যাহার জিহ্বাগ্রে কৃষ্ণনাম নৃত্য করে ॥১২৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" śvapacha ha-ileo dvija-śreṣṭha bali tāre<br />yāhāra jihvāgre kṛṣṇa-nāma nṛtya kare [125]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">śvapacha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-ileo</span>–Even if they are outcasts, <span class=\\"e2\\">bali</span>–we consider <span class=\\"e2\\">tāre yāhāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">jihvāgre</span>–those on the tip of whose tongue <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-nāma</span>–the Name of Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">nṛtya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kare</span>–dances [to be] <span class=\\"e2\\">dvija-śreṣṭha</span>–the best of the twice-born."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Even outcasts are considered the best of brāhmaṇs when the Name of Kṛṣṇa dances on the tip of their tongue."},{"class":"b97","text":" সর্ব্বতপ কৈল সর্ব্বতীর্থে কৈল স্নান ।<br />সর্ব্ববেদ অধ্যয়নে আর্য মতিমান্ ॥১২৬॥<br />এই সব সাধনের বলে ভাগ্যবান্ ।<br />রসনায় সদা করে হরিনাম গান ॥১২৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sarva-tapa kaila sarva-tīrthe kaila snāna<br />sarva-veda adhyayane ārya matimān [126]<br />ei saba sādhanera bale bhāgyavān<br />rasanāya sadā kare hari-nāma gāna [127]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-tapa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kaila</span>–They have performed all austerities, <span class=\\"e2\\">snāna kaila</span>–bathed <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-tīrthe</span>–at all holy places, <span class=\\"e2\\">adhyayane</span>–studied <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-veda</span>–all scriptures, [and become] <span class=\\"e2\\">ārya matimān</span>–noble-minded. <span class=\\"e2\\">ei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">saba</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sādhanera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–With the strength produced by all these practices, <span class=\\"e2\\">bhāgyavān</span>–such fortunate souls <span class=\\"e2\\">sadā</span>–constantly <span class=\\"e2\\">gāna kare</span>–chant <span class=\\"e2\\">hari-nāma</span>–the Name of the Lord <span class=\\"e2\\">rasanāya</span>–with [their] tongue."},{"class":"b50","text":" “They have performed all austerities, bathed at all holy places, studied all scriptures, and become noble-minded. With the strength produced by all these practices, such fortunate souls constantly chant the Name of the Lord with their tongues."},{"class":"b97","text":" অহো বত শ্বপচোঽতো গরীয়ান্<br />যজ্জিহ্বাগ্রে বর্ত্ততে নাম তুভ্যম্ ।<br />তেপুস্তপস্তে জুহুবুঃ সস্নুরার্য্যা<br />ব্রহ্মানূচুর্নাম গৃণন্তি যে তে ॥১২৮॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" aho bata śvapacho ’to garīyān<br />yaj jihvāgre vartate nāma tubhyam<br />tepus tapas te juhuvuḥ sasnur āryā<br />brahmānūchur nāma gṛhṇanti ye te [128]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Śrīmad Bhāgavatam: 3.33.7)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘How glorious! An outcast on the tip of whose tongue Your Name appears is exalted. Those who chant Your Name have performed all austerities and sacrifices, bathed in all the holy places, become virtuous, and studied all the scriptures.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" সর্ব্ব-অর্থ-দাতা হরিনাম মহামন্ত্র ।<br />ফুকারিয়া বলে যত বেদাগমতন্ত্র ॥১২৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sarva-artha-dātā hari-nāma mahāmantra<br />phukāriyā bale yata vedāgama-tantra [129]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">yata</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">vedāgama-tantra</span>–All the Vedas, Āgamas, and Tantras <span class=\\"e2\\">phukāriyā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–proclaim [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">hari-nāma</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">mahāmantra</span>–the mahāmantra of the Lord’s Name [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-artha-dātā</span>–the giver of all desired ends."},{"class":"b50","text":" “The Vedas, Āgamas, Tantras, and other scriptures proclaim that the mahāmantra of the Lord’s Name grants all desired ends."},{"class":"b97","text":" হরিনামবলে সর্ব্বষড়্বর্গ-দমন ।<br />রিপুনিগ্রহণ আর অধ্যাত্ম-সাধন ॥১৩০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" hari-nāma-bale sarva-ṣaḍ-varga-damana<br />ripu-nigrahaṇa āra adhyātma-sādhana [130]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">hari-nāma-bale</span>–By the power of the Name of the Lord, <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-ṣaḍ-varga-damana</span>–destruction of all six vices, <span class=\\"e2\\">ripu-nigrahaṇa</span>–subduing of enemies, <span class=\\"e2\\">āra</span>–and <span class=\\"e2\\">adhyātma-sādhana</span>–realisation of the higher self [occur]."},{"class":"b50","text":" “The Name of the Lord vanquishes lust, anger, greed, madness, pride, and envy, subdues enemies, and produces self-realisation."},{"class":"b97","text":" এতৎ ষড়্বর্গহরণমং রিপুনিগ্রহণং পরম্ ।<br />অধ্যাত্মমূলমেতদ্ধি বিষ্ণোর্নামানুকীর্ত্তনম্ ॥১৩১॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" etat ṣaḍ-varga-haraṇam ripu-nigrahaṇaṁ param<br />adhyātma-mūlam etad dhi viṣṇor nāmānukīrtanam [131]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Skanda-purāṇa)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘Constantly chanting the Name of Viṣṇu destroys lust, anger, greed, madness, pride, and envy, completely subdues enemies, and produces realisation of the higher self.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" গুণজ্ঞ সারভুক্ আর্য্য কলিকে সম্মানে ।<br />সর্ব্বস্বার্থ লভি’ কলৌ নাম-সঙ্কীর্ত্তনে ॥১৩২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" guṇajña sāra-bhuk ārya kalike sammāne<br />sarva-svārtha labhi’ kalau nāma-saṅkīrtane [132]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">ārya</span>–The wise [who] <span class=\\"e2\\">guṇajña</span>–know the qualities <span class=\\"e2\\">kalike</span>–of the Age of Kali [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">sāra-bhuk</span>–appreciate its virtue <span class=\\"e2\\">sammāne</span>–honour [this age because] <span class=\\"e2\\">kalau</span>–in the Age of Kali <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-svārtha</span>–all desired ends <span class=\\"e2\\">labhi’</span>–are attained <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-saṅkīrtane</span>–by chanting the Name."},{"class":"b50","text":" “The wise who know the qualities of the Age of Kali and appreciate its virtue honour this age because in the Age of Kali all desired ends are attained by chanting the Name of the Lord."},{"class":"b97","text":" কলিং সভাজয়ন্ত্যার্য্যা গুণজ্ঞা সারভাগিনঃ ।<br />যত্র সঙ্কীর্ত্তনেনৈব সর্ব্বঃ স্বর্থোঽভিলভ্যতে ॥১৩৩॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" kaliṁ sabhājayanty āryā guṇajñā sāra-bhāginaḥ<br />yatra saṅkīrtanenaiva sarvaḥ svartho ’bhilabhyate [133]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Śrīmad Bhāgavatam: 11.5.36)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘The wise who know the qualities of the Age of Kali and appreciate its virtue praise this age in which all desired ends are attained simply by chanting the Name of the Lord.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" সর্ব্বশক্তিমান্ নাম কৃষ্ণের সমান ।<br />কৃষ্ণের সকল শক্তি নামে বর্ত্তমান ॥১৩৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sarva-śaktimān nāma kṛṣṇera samāna<br />kṛṣṇera sakala śakti nāme vartamāna [134]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–The Name [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-śaktimān</span>–all-powerful [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">samāna</span>–equal to Kṛṣṇa; <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sakala</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">śakti</span>–all of Kṛṣṇa’s power [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">vartamāna</span>–present <span class=\\"e2\\">nāme</span>–within the Name."},{"class":"b50","text":" “The Name is all-powerful and equal to Kṛṣṇa Himself; all of Kṛṣṇa’s power is present within the Name."},{"class":"b97","text":" দানব্রতস্তপস্তীর্থে ছিল যত শক্তি ।<br />দেবগণে কর্ম্মকাণ্ডে হইয়া বিভক্তি ॥১৩৫॥<br />রাজসূয়ে অশ্বমেধে আধ্যাত্মিক জ্ঞানে ।<br />সব আকর্ষিয়া কৃষ্ণ নিল আপন নামে ॥১৩৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" dāna-vratas-tapas-tīrthe chhila yata śakti<br />deva-gaṇe karma-kāṇḍe ha-iyā vibhakti [135]<br />rājasūye aśvamedhe ādhyātmika jñāne<br />saba ākarṣiyā kṛṣṇa nila āpana nāme [136]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span>–Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">ākarṣiyā</span>–has drawn <span class=\\"e2\\">saba yata</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">śakti</span>–all the power <span class=\\"e2\\">chhila</span>–that was present [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">vibhakti ha-iyā</span>–divided <span class=\\"e2\\">dāna-vratas-tapas-tīrthe</span>–within charity, rites, austerity, pilgrimage, <span class=\\"e2\\">deva-gaṇe</span>–[worshipping] the gods, <span class=\\"e2\\">karma-kāṇḍe</span>–[following] the codes for pious action in the Vedas, <span class=\\"e2\\">rājasūye</span>–coronations, <span class=\\"e2\\">aśvamedhe</span>–horse sacrifices, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">ādhyātmika</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">jñāne</span>–knowledge of the highest self, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">nila</span>–taken [it] <span class=\\"e2\\">āpana</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāme</span>–into His Name."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Kṛṣṇa has drawn all the power that was present and divided within charity, rites, austerity, pilgrimage, worshipping the gods, following the codes for pious action, coronations, horse sacrifices, and realisation of the higher self, and invested it in His Name."},{"class":"b97","text":" দানব্রততপস্তীর্থক্ষেত্রাদীনাঞ্চ যাঃ স্থিতাঃ ।<br />শক্তয়ো দেবমহতাং সর্ব্বপাপহরাঃ শুভাঃ ॥১৩৭॥<br />রাজসূয়াশ্বমেধানাং জ্ঞানমধ্যাত্মবস্তুনঃ ।<br />আকৃষ্য হরিণা সর্বাঃ স্থাপিতাঃ স্বেষু নামসু ॥১৩৮॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" dāna-vrata-tapas-tīrtha-kṣetrādīnāṁ cha yāḥ sthitāḥ<br />śaktayo deva-mahatāṁ sarva-pāpa-harāḥ śubhāḥ [137]<br />rājasūyāśvamedhānāṁ jñānam adhyātma-vastunaḥ<br />ākṛṣya hariṇā sarvāḥ sthāpitāḥ sveṣu nāmasu [138]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Skanda-purāṇa)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘The Lord has drawn out all the purifying power to remove sin situated within charity, rites, austerities, pilgrimage, worshipping the gods, serving the virtuous, coronations, horse sacrifices, and knowledge of the higher self, and placed it within His Names.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" দেবদেব শ্রীকৃষ্ণের সর্ব্ব অর্থ শক্তি ।<br />যুক্ত সব নাম, তঁহি মধ্যে যাতে অনুরক্তি ॥১৩৯॥<br />সেই নাম সর্ব্ব অর্থে যোজনা করিবে ।<br />সর্ব্ব অর্থ শক্তি হৈতে সকলই মিলিবে ॥১৪০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" devadeva śrī-kṛṣṇera sarva artha śakti<br />yukta saba nāma, ta̐hi madhye yāte anurakti [139]<br />sei nāma sarva arthe yojanā karibe<br />sarva artha śakti haite sakala-i milibe [140]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">saba</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–All [His] Names [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">yukta</span>–endowed [with] <span class=\\"e2\\">devadeva</span>–the God of gods <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-kṛṣṇera</span>–Śrī Kṛṣṇa’s <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva artha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">śakti</span>–power [to grant] all desired ends. <span class=\\"e2\\">yāte sei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–The Name to which [you are] <span class=\\"e2\\">anurakti</span>–attached <span class=\\"e2\\">ta̐hi</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">madhye</span>–amongst Them <span class=\\"e2\\">yojanā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">karibe</span>–will bring [you] <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva</span>–all <span class=\\"e2\\">arthe</span>–desired ends. <span class=\\"e2\\">haite</span>–Through [the Name’s] <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">artha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">śakti</span>–power [to grant] all desired ends, <span class=\\"e2\\">milibe</span>–You will attain <span class=\\"e2\\">sakala-i</span>–everything."},{"class":"b50","text":" “All the Names of the God of gods Śrī Kṛṣṇa are endowed with His power to grant all desired ends. Whichever Name amongst Them to which you are attached will bring you all desired ends. Through the Name’s power to grant all desired ends, you will attain everything."},{"class":"b97","text":" সর্ব্বার্থশক্তিযুক্তস্য দেবদেবস্য চক্রিণঃ ।<br />যচ্চাভিরুচিতং নাম তৎ সর্ব্বার্থেষু যোজয়েৎ ॥১৪১॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" sarvārtha-śakti-yuktasya deva-devasya chakriṇaḥ<br />yach chābhiruchitaṁ nāma tat sarvārtheṣu yojayet [141]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Brahmāṇḍa-purāṇa)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘For the attainment of all desired ends, chant your favourite Name of the God of gods, the carrier of the chakra, who has the power to grant all desired ends.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" হৃষীকেশ-সঙ্কীর্ত্তনে জগদানন্দিত ।<br />অনুরাগে হৃষ্টচিত্ত সর্ব্বদা সম্প্রীত ॥১৪২॥<br />দৈত্য রক্ষ ভীত হইয়া পলাইয়া যায় ।<br />সিদ্ধসঙ্ঘ সদা প্রণমিত তাঁর পায় ॥১৪৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" hṛṣīkeśa-saṅkīrtane jagad-ānandita<br />anurāge hṛṣṭa-chitta sarvadā samprīta [142]<br />daitya rakṣa bhīta ha-iyā palāiyā yāya<br />siddha-saṅgha sadā praṇamita tā̐ra pāya [143]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">hṛṣīkeśa-saṅkīrtane</span>–By the chanting of the Lord’s Name, <span class=\\"e2\\">jagad</span>–the world [becomes] <span class=\\"e2\\">ānandita</span>–joyful, [the people’s] <span class=\\"e2\\">chitta</span>–hearts <span class=\\"e2\\">sarvadā</span>–always [remain] <span class=\\"e2\\">hṛṣṭa</span>–happy and <span class=\\"e2\\">samprīta</span>–fulfilled <span class=\\"e2\\">anurāge</span>–through attachment [to the Lord,] <span class=\\"e2\\">daitya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">rakṣa</span>–the demons <span class=\\"e2\\">bhīta</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-iyā</span>–become afraid [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">palāiyā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">yāya</span>–flee, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">siddha-saṅgha</span>–the realised souls <span class=\\"e2\\">sadā</span>–continuously <span class=\\"e2\\">praṇamita</span>–bow <span class=\\"e2\\">tā̐ra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">pāya</span>–at His feet."},{"class":"b50","text":" “By the chanting of the Lord’s Name, the world becomes joyful, the people’s hearts always remain happy and fulfilled through attachment to the Lord, the demons become afraid and flee, and the realised souls continuously bow at the Lord’s feet."},{"class":"b97","text":" যেই কৃষ্ণ সেই নাম, নামের প্রভাব ।<br />উপযুক্ত বটে তাতে না থাকে অভাব ॥১৪৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" yei kṛṣṇa sei nāma, nāmera prabhāva<br />upayukta vaṭe tāte nā thāke abhāva [144]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sei yei</span>–He who [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span>–Kṛṣṇa [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–the Name, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmera</span>–the Name’s <span class=\\"e2\\">prabhāva</span>–influence <span class=\\"e2\\">vaṭe</span>–is [always] <span class=\\"e2\\">upayukta</span>–fitting. <span class=\\"e2\\">abhāva thāke nā</span>–There is no deficiency <span class=\\"e2\\">tāte</span>–within it."},{"class":"b50","text":" “The Name is Kṛṣṇa Himself, and the Name’s influence is always fitting. There is no deficiency within it."},{"class":"b97","text":" স্থানে হৃষীকেশ তব প্রকীর্ত্ত্যা<br />জগৎ প্রহৃষ্যত্যনুরজ্যতে চ ।<br />রক্ষাংসি ভীতানি দিশো দ্রবন্তি<br />সর্ব্বে নমস্যন্তি চ সিদ্ধসঙ্ঘাঃ ॥১৪৫॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" sthāne hṛṣīkeśa tava prakīrtyā<br />jagat prahṛṣyaty anurajyate cha<br />rakṣāṁsi bhītāni diśo dravanti<br />sarve namasyanti cha siddha-saṅghāḥ [145]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Śrīmad Bhagavad-gītā: 11.36)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘It is all fitting, O Master of the senses, that upon hearing the chanting of Your glories, the world rejoices and becomes attached to You, the demons flee in all directions, and the realised souls bow down.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" বর্ণাদি বিচার নাহি শ্রীনামসঙ্কীর্ত্তনে ।<br />দীক্ষাপুরশ্চর্য্যা বিধি বাধা নাই গণে ॥১৪৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" varṇādi vichāra nāhi śrī-nāma-saṅkīrtane<br />dīkṣā-puraścharyā vidhi bādhā nāi gaṇe [146]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">śrī-nāma-saṅkīrtane</span>–In chanting the Name, <span class=\\"e2\\">nāhi</span>–there is no <span class=\\"e2\\">vichāra</span>–consideration <span class=\\"e2\\">varṇādi</span>–of class or caste. <span class=\\"e2\\">vidhi</span>–The conventions <span class=\\"e2\\">dīkṣā-puraścharyā</span>–of [brahminical] initiation and preparatory rites <span class=\\"e2\\">gaṇe nāi</span>–are not counted <span class=\\"e2\\">bādhā</span>–as barriers."},{"class":"b50","text":" “In chanting the Name, there is no consideration of class or caste, and the conventions of brahminical initiation and preparatory rites are not barriers to it."},{"class":"b97","text":" নারায়ণ জগন্নাথ বাসুদেব জনার্দ্দন ।<br />যার মুখে সদা শুনি, পূজ্য গুরু সেই জন ॥১৪৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" nārāyaṇa jagannātha vāsudeva janārdana<br />yāra mukhe sadā śuni, pūjya guru sei jana [147]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">jana yāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">mukhe</span>–Those from whose mouth [we] <span class=\\"e2\\">sadā</span>–always <span class=\\"e2\\">śuni</span>–hear <span class=\\"e2\\">nārāyaṇa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">jagannātha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">vāsudeva</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">janārdana</span>–‘Nārāyaṇ!’, ‘Jagannāth!’, ‘Vāsudev!’, and ‘Janārdan!’ [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">pūjya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">guru</span>–worshippable Gurus."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Those from whose mouth we always hear ‘Nārāyaṇ!’, ‘Jagannāth!’, ‘Vāsudev!’, and ‘Janārdan!’ are worshippable Gurus."},{"class":"b97","text":" শয়নে স্বপনে আর চলিতে বসিতে ।<br />কৃষ্ণনাম করে যেই, পূজ্য সর্ব্ব মতে ॥১৪৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" śayane svapane āra chalite basite<br />kṛṣṇa-nāma kare yei, pūjya sarva mate [148]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">yei</span>–Those who <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-nāma</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kare</span>–chant the Name of Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">śayane</span>–while resting, <span class=\\"e2\\">svapane</span>–dreaming, <span class=\\"e2\\">chalite</span>–walking, <span class=\\"e2\\">āra</span>–and <span class=\\"e2\\">basite</span>–sitting [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">pūjya</span>–worshippable <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">mate</span>–in all respects."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Those who chant the Name of Kṛṣṇa while resting, dreaming, walking, and sitting are worshippable in all respects."},{"class":"b97","text":" নারায়ণ জগন্নাথ বাসুদেব জনার্দ্দন ।<br />ইতীরয়ন্তি যে নিত্যং তে বৈ সর্ব্বত্র বন্দিতাঃ ॥১৪৯॥<br />স্বপন্ ভুঞ্জন্ ব্রজংস্তিষ্ঠনুত্তিষ্ঠংশ্চ বদংস্তথা ।<br />যে বদন্তি হরের্নাম তেভ্যো নিত্যং নমো নমঃ ॥১৫০॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" nārāyaṇa jagannātha vāsudeva janārdana<br />itīrayanti ye nityaṁ te vai sarvatra vanditāḥ [149]<br />svapan bhuñjan vrajaṁs tiṣṭhan uttiṣṭhaṁś cha vadaṁs tathā<br />ye vadanti harer nāma tebhyo nityaṁ namo namaḥ [150]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Bṛhan-nāradīya-purāṇa)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘Those who always chant ‘Nārāyaṇ!’, ‘Jagannāth!’, ‘Vāsudev!’, and ‘Janārdan!’ are worshipped everywhere. Eternally, I bow again and again to those who chant the Name of the Lord while resting, eating, walking, sitting, standing, or talking.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" স্ত্রী-শূদ্র-পুক্কশ-যবনাদি কেন নয় ।<br />কৃষ্ণনাম গায়, সেও গুরু পূজ্য হয় ॥১৫১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" strī-śūdra-pukkaśa-yavanādi kena naya<br />kṛṣṇa-nāma gāya, seo guru pūjya haya [151]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kena naya</span>–Whether or not [they are] <span class=\\"e2\\">strī-śūdra-pukkaśa-yavanādi</span>–women, labourers, persons of mixed caste, outcasts, or otherwise, <span class=\\"e2\\">seo</span>–those [who] <span class=\\"e2\\">gāya</span>–chant <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-nāma</span>–the Name of Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–become <span class=\\"e2\\">pūjya guru</span>–worshippable Gurus."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Those who chant the Name of Kṛṣṇa, whether or not they are women, labourers, persons of mixed caste, outcasts, or otherwise, become worshippable Gurus."},{"class":"b97","text":" স্ত্রী শূদ্রঃ পুক্কশো বাপি যে চান্যে পাপযোনয়ঃ ।<br />কীর্ত্তয়ন্তি হরিং ভক্ত্যা তেভ্যোঽপীহ নমো নমঃ ॥১৫২॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" strī śūdraḥ pukkaśo vāpi ye chānye pāpa-yonayaḥ<br />kīrtayanti hariṁ bhaktyā tebhyo ’pīha namo namaḥ [152]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Nārāyaṇa-vyūha-stava)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘I bow again and again to those who chant the Name of the Lord with devotion, be they women, labourers, persons of mixed caste, or even outcasts.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" অন্যগতিশূন্য ভোগী পর-উপতাপী ।<br />ব্রহ্মচর্য্য-জ্ঞানবৈরাগ্যহীন পাপী ॥১৫৩॥<br />সর্ব্বধর্ম্মশূন্য নামজপী যদি হয় ।<br />তাহার যে সুগতি তাহা সর্ব্ব ধার্ম্মিকের নয় ॥১৫৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" anya-gati-śūnya bhogī para-upatāpī<br />brahmacharya-jñāna-vairāgya-hīna pāpī [153]<br />sarva-dharma-śūnya nāma-japī yadi haya<br />tāhāra ye sugati tāhā sarva dhārmikera naya [154]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">yadi</span>–If [those who are] <span class=\\"e2\\">anya-gati-śūnya</span>–shelterless, <span class=\\"e2\\">bhogī</span>–hedonistic, <span class=\\"e2\\">para-upatāpī</span>–harmful to others, <span class=\\"e2\\">brahmacharya-jñāna-vairāgya-hīna</span>–devoid of austerity, knowledge, and renunciation, <span class=\\"e2\\">pāpī</span>–sinful [or] <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-dharma-śūnya</span>–completely irreligious <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-japī</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–become chanters of the Name, [they attain] <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ye</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sugati</span>–an exalted destination <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhā</span>–that <span class=\\"e2\\">naya</span>–is not [attained] <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">dhārmikera</span>–by all pious persons."},{"class":"b50","text":" “If those who are shelterless, hedonistic, harmful to others, devoid of austerity, knowledge, and renunciation, sinful, or completely irreligious chant the Name, they attain an exalted destination that even the pious do not."},{"class":"b97","text":" অনন্যগতয়ো মর্ত্ত্যা ভোগিনোঽপি পরন্তপাঃ ।<br />জ্ঞানবৈরাগ্যরহিতা ব্রহ্মচর্য্যাদিবর্জ্জিতাঃ ॥১৫৫॥<br />সর্ব্বধর্ম্মোজ্ঝিতা বিষ্ণোর্নামমাত্রৈকজল্পকাঃ ।<br />সুখেন যাং গতিং যান্তি ন তাং সর্ব্বেঽপি ধার্ম্মিকাঃ ॥১৫৬॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" ananya-gatayo martyā bhogino ’pi parantapāḥ<br />jñāna-vairāgya-rahitā brahmacharyādi-varjitāḥ [155]<br />sarva-dharmojjhitā viṣṇor nāma-mātraika-jalpakāḥ<br />sukhena yāṁ gatiṁ yānti na tāṁ sarve ’pi dhārmikāḥ [156]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Padma-purāṇa)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘Regardless of whether they are shelterless, hedonistic, harmful to others, devoid of knowledge and renunciation, undisciplined, or completely irreligious, those who just once chant the Name of Viṣṇu happily attain a destination that even the pious do not.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" হরিনামগ্রহণে দেশকালের নিয়ম নাই ।<br />উচ্ছিষ্ট অশৌচে বিধি নিষেধ না পাই ॥১৫৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" hari-nāma-grahaṇe deśa-kālera niyama nāi<br />uchchhiṣṭa aśauche vidhi niṣedha nā pāi [157]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">hari-nāma-grahaṇe</span>–In chanting the Name of the Lord, <span class=\\"e2\\">nāi</span>–there are no <span class=\\"e2\\">niyama</span>–rules <span class=\\"e2\\">deśa-kālera</span>–regarding time and place, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">pāi nā</span>–we do not find <span class=\\"e2\\">vidhi</span>–any rules [or] <span class=\\"e2\\">niṣedha</span>–regulations <span class=\\"e2\\">uchchhiṣṭa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">aśauche</span>–regarding impurity produced by food remnants."},{"class":"b50","text":" “In chanting the Name of the Lord, there are no rules regarding time and place, and we do not find any rules or regulations regarding impurity produced by food remnants."},{"class":"b97","text":" ন দেশনিয়মস্তস্মিন্ ন কালনিয়মস্তথা ।<br />নোচ্ছিষ্টাদৌ নিষেধোঽস্তি শ্রীহরের্নাম্নি লুব্ধক ॥১৫৮॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" na deśa-niyamas tasmin na kāla-niyamas tathā<br />nochchhiṣṭhādau niṣedho ’sti śrī-harer nāmni lubdhaka [158]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Viṣṇu-dharma)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘O hunter! Neither are there rules regarding the time and place in chanting the Name of the Lord, nor are there regulations regarding food remnants.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" কৃষ্ণনাম সদা সর্ব্বত্র করহ কীর্ত্তন ।<br />অশৌচাদি নাহি মান, নাম স্বতন্ত্র পাবন ॥১৫৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kṛṣṇa-nāma sadā sarvatra karaha kīrtana<br />aśauchādi nāhi māna, nāma svatantra pāvana [159]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kīrtana karaha</span>–Chant <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-nāma</span>–the Name of Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">sadā</span>–always [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">sarvatra</span>–everywhere, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">māna nāhi</span>–do not be concerned <span class=\\"e2\\">aśauchādi</span>–about (external) impurity. <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–The Name [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">svatantra</span>–independently <span class=\\"e2\\">pāvana</span>–purifying."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Chant the Name of Kṛṣṇa always and everywhere, and do not be concerned about external purity. The Name is independently purifying."},{"class":"b97","text":" চক্রায়ুধস্য নামানি সদা সর্ব্বত্র কীর্ত্তয়েৎ ।<br />নাশৌচং কীর্ত্তনে তস্য স পবিত্রকরো যতঃ ॥১৬০॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" chakrāyudhasya nāmāni sadā sarvatra kīrtayet<br />nāśauchaṁ kīrtane tasya sa pavitrakaro yataḥ [160]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Skanda-purāṇa)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘The Name of the Lord, the carrier of the chakra, should be chanted always and everywhere. There is no impurity within the chanting of His Name because He Himself is purifying.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" যজ্ঞে দানে স্নানে জপে আছে কালের নিয়ম ।<br />কৃষ্ণকীর্ত্তনে কালাকালচিন্তা মহাভ্রম ॥১৬১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" yajñe dāne snāne jape āchhe kālera niyama<br />kṛṣṇa-kīrtane kālākāla-chintā mahābhrama [161]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">āchhe</span>–There are <span class=\\"e2\\">niyama</span>–rules <span class=\\"e2\\">kālera</span>–regarding the time <span class=\\"e2\\">yajñe</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">dāne</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">snāne</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">jape</span>–for [performing] sacrifice, [giving] charity, bathing, and [chanting] mantras, [but] <span class=\\"e2\\">kālākāla-chintā</span>–thinking [that there are] proper and improper times <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-kīrtane</span>–to chant the Name of Kṛṣṇa [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">mahābhrama</span>–a great mistake."},{"class":"b50","text":" “There are rules regarding the time to perform sacrifice, give charity, bathe, and chant mantras, but thinking that there are proper or improper times to chant the Name of Kṛṣṇa is a great mistake."},{"class":"b97","text":" দেশ-কাল-নিয়মাদি নামে কভু নাই ।<br />কৃষ্ণকীর্ত্তন সদা করহ সবাই ॥১৬২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" deśa-kāla-niyamādi nāme kabhu nāi<br />kṛṣṇa-kīrtana sadā karaha sabāi [162]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāi</span>–There are never <span class=\\"e2\\">deśa-kāla-niyamādi</span>–rules for the time and place <span class=\\"e2\\">nāme</span>–to [chant] the Name. <span class=\\"e2\\">sabāi</span>–Everyone <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-kīrtana</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">karaha</span>–should chant the Name of Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">sadā</span>–always."},{"class":"b50","text":" “There are never rules for the time and place to chant the Name. Everyone should always chant the Name of Kṛṣṇa."},{"class":"b97","text":" ন দেশনিয়মো রাজন্ ন কালনিয়মস্তথা ।<br />বিদ্যতে নাত্র সন্দেহো বিষ্ণোর্নামানুকীর্ত্তনে ॥১৬৩॥<br />কালোঽস্তি দানে যজ্ঞে চ স্নানে কালোঽস্তি সজ্জপে ।<br />বিষ্ণুসঙ্কীর্ত্তনে কালো নাস্ত্যত্র পৃথিবীতলে ॥১৬৪॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" na deśa-niyamo rājan na kāla-niyamas tathā<br />vidyate nātra sandeho viṣṇor nāmānukīrtane [163]<br />kālo ’sti dāne yajñe cha snāne kālo ’sti sajjape<br />viṣṇu-saṅkīrtane kālo nāsty atra pṛthivī-tale [164]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Vaiṣṇava-chintāmaṇi)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘O King, there are no rules regarding the time and place for chanting the Name of Viṣṇu. Of this there is no doubt. There are rules concerning the time for giving charity, performing sacrifices, bathing, and chanting mantras, but on this earth there are no rules regarding the time to chant the Name of Viṣṇu (the Name should be chanted at all times).’"},{"class":"b97","text":" সংসারে নির্ব্বিণ্ণচিত্ত অভয়পদ চায় ।<br />হেন যোগীর জন্য নাম একমাত্র উপায় ॥১৬৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" saṁsāre nirviṇṇa-chitta abhaya-pada chāya<br />hena yogīra janya nāma eka-mātra upāya [165]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">hena yogīra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">janya</span>–For the ascetics [who are] <span class=\\"e2\\">nirviṇṇa-chitta</span>–indifferent <span class=\\"e2\\">saṁsāre</span>–to the world [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">chāya</span>–desire <span class=\\"e2\\">abhaya-pada</span>–fearlessness, <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–the Name [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">eka-mātra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">upāya</span>–the one and only way."},{"class":"b50","text":" “For ascetics who are indifferent to the world and desire fearlessness, the Name is the one and only way."},{"class":"b97","text":" এতন্নির্ব্বিদ্যমানানামিচ্ছতামকুতোভয়ম্ ।<br />যোগিনাং নৃপ নির্ণীতং হরের্নামানুকীর্ত্তনম্ ॥১৬৬॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" etan nirvidyamānānām ichchhatām akuto-bhayam<br />yogināṁ nṛpa nirṇītaṁ harer nāmānukīrtanam [166]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Śrīmad Bhāgavatam: 2.1.11)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘O King, constantly chanting the Name of the Lord is prescribed for ascetics who are indifferent and desire total fearlessness.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" হরিনাম বিনা আর সহজ মুক্তিদাতা ।<br />কেহ নাহি ত্রিজগতে, নামই জীবের ত্রাতা ॥১৬৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" hari-nāma vinā āra sahaja mukti-dātā<br />keha nāhi trijagate, nāma-i jīvera trātā [167]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">keha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāhi</span>–No one <span class=\\"e2\\">trijagate</span>–throughout the three worlds <span class=\\"e2\\">vinā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">āra</span>–other than <span class=\\"e2\\">hari-nāma</span>–the Name of the Lord [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">sahaja</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">mukti-dātā</span>–an easy giver of liberation. <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-i</span>–The Name alone [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">trātā</span>–the deliverer <span class=\\"e2\\">jīvera</span>–of the soul."},{"class":"b50","text":" “No one throughout the three worlds other than the Name of the Lord easily grants liberation. The Name alone is the deliverer of the soul."},{"class":"b97","text":" একবার মুখে বলে ‘হরি’ দু’অক্ষর ।<br />সেই জন মোক্ষপ্রতি বদ্ধপরিকর ॥১৬৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" eka-bāra mukhe bale ‘hari’ du’akṣara<br />sei jana mokṣa-prati baddha-parikara [168]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">jana</span>–Those who <span class=\\"e2\\">eka-bāra</span>–once <span class=\\"e2\\">mukhe</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–chant aloud <span class=\\"e2\\">du’akṣara</span>–the two syllables <span class=\\"e2\\">‘hari’</span>–‘Ha-ri’ [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">baddha-parikara</span>–‘girdle-bound’ <span class=\\"e2\\">mokṣa-prati</span>–for liberation."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Those who once chant the two syllables ‘Ha-ri’ are bound to attain liberation."},{"class":"b97","text":" সকৃদুচ্চারিতং যেন হরিরিত্যক্ষরদ্বয়ম্ ।<br />বদ্ধঃ পরিকরস্তেন মোক্ষায় গমনং প্রতি ॥১৬৯॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" sakṛd uchchāritaṁ yena harir ity akṣara-dvayam<br />baddhaḥ parikaras tena mokṣāya gamanaṁ prati [169]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Skanda-purāṇa)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘Those who once chant the two syllables ‘Ha-ri’ are bound to attain liberation.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" জিতনিদ্র হঞা একবার ‘নারায়ণ’ বলে ।<br />শুদ্ধ-চিত্ত হঞা সেই নির্ব্বাণপথে চলে ॥১৭০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" jita-nidra hañā eka-bāra ‘nārāyaṇa’ bale<br />śuddha-chitta hañā sei nirvāṇa-pathe chale [170]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sei jita-nidra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">hañā</span>–Anyone who overcomes sleep [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">eka-bāra</span>–once <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–chants <span class=\\"e2\\">‘nārāyaṇa’</span>–‘Nārāyaṇ’ <span class=\\"e2\\">śuddha-chitta hañā</span>–becomes pure in heart [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">chale</span>–proceeds <span class=\\"e2\\">nirvāṇa-pathe</span>–on the path to liberation."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Anyone who overcomes sleep and once chants ‘Nārāyaṇ’ becomes pure in heart and proceeds on the path to liberation."},{"class":"b97","text":" সকৃদুচ্চারয়েদ্যস্তু নারায়ণমতন্দ্রিতঃ ।<br />শুদ্ধান্তঃকরণো ভূত্বা নির্ব্বাণমধিগচ্ছতি ॥১৭১॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" sakṛd uchchārayed yas tu nārāyaṇam atandritaḥ<br />śuddhāntaḥkaraṇo bhūtvā nirvāṇam adhigachchhati [171]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Padma-purāṇa)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘Anyone free from laziness who once chants the Name of Nārāyaṇ becomes pure in heart and attains liberation.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" এ ঘোর সংসারে, বলে বিবশে ‘হরে হরে’ ।<br />সদ্যোমুক্ত হয়, ভয় তারে ভয় করে ॥১৭২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" e ghora saṁsāre, bale vivaśe ‘hare hare’<br />sadyo-mukta haya, bhaya tāre bhaya kare [172]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [Souls] <span class=\\"e2\\">e</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ghora</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">saṁsāre</span>–in this frightening world [who] <span class=\\"e2\\">vivaśe</span>–desperately <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–call out <span class=\\"e2\\">‘hare</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">hare’</span>–‘O Lord! Lord!’ <span class=\\"e2\\">sadyo-mukta</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–are immediately liberated; [even] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaya</span>–Fear [himself] <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kare</span>–fears <span class=\\"e2\\">tāre</span>–Him."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Souls in this frightening world who desperately call out, ‘Hari! Hari!’ are immediately liberated; even Fear himself fears the Name."},{"class":"b97","text":" আপন্নঃ সংসৃতিং ঘোরাং যন্নাম বিবশো গৃণন্ ।<br />ততঃ সদ্যো বিমুচ্যেত যদ্বিভেতি স্বয়ং ভয়ম্ ॥১৭৩॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" āpannaḥ saṁsṛtiṁ ghorāṁ yan-nāma vivaśo gṛṇan<br />tataḥ sadyo vimuchyeta yad bibheti svayaṁ bhayam [173]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Śrīmad Bhāgavatam: 1.1.14)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘Souls entangled in the frightening world who desperately chant the Lord’s Name, whom Fear himself fears, are immediately liberated.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" মৃত্যুকালে বিবশে যে করে উচ্চারণ ।<br />তাঁর অবতার নাম লীলা বিড়ম্বন ॥১৭৪॥<br />বহুজন্মদুরিত সহসা ত্যাগ করি’ ।<br />যায় সে পরমপদে ভজে সেই হরি ॥১৭৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" mṛtyu-kāle vivaśe ye kare uchchāraṇa<br />tā̐ra avatāra nāma līlā viḍambana [174]<br />bahu-janma-durita sahasā tyāga kari’<br />yāya se parama-pade bhaje sei hari [175]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">se ye</span>–Those who <span class=\\"e2\\">mṛtyu-kāle</span>–at the time of death <span class=\\"e2\\">vivaśe</span>–desperately <span class=\\"e2\\">uchchāraṇa kare</span>–chant <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–the Names [that are] <span class=\\"e2\\">viḍambana</span>–allusions <span class=\\"e2\\">tā̐ra</span>–to His <span class=\\"e2\\">avatāra</span>–Avatārs [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">līlā</span>–Pastimes <span class=\\"e2\\">sahasā</span>–immediately <span class=\\"e2\\">tyāga</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kari’</span>–leave behind <span class=\\"e2\\">bahu-janma-durita</span>–many births’ worth of sin [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">yāya</span>–reach <span class=\\"e2\\">parama-pade</span>–the supreme abode. <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaje</span>–I serve <span class=\\"e2\\">sei hari</span>–this Lord."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Those who at the time of death desperately chant the Lord’s Names that describe His Avatārs and Pastimes immediately leave behind many births’ worth of sin and reach the supreme abode. I serve this Lord."},{"class":"b97","text":" যস্যাবতারগুণকর্ম্মবিড়ম্বনানি<br />নামানি যেঽসুবিগমে বিবশা গৃণন্তি ।<br />তেঽনেকজন্মশমলং সহসৈব হিত্বা<br />সংযান্ত্যপাবৃতামৃতং তমজং প্রপদ্যে ॥১৭৬॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" yasyāvatāra-guṇa-karma-viḍambanāni<br />nāmāni ye ’suvigame vivaśā gṛṇanti<br />te ’neka-janma-śamalaṁ sahasaiva hitvā<br />saṁyānty apāvṛtām ṛtaṁ tam ajaṁ prapadye [176]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Śrīmad Bhāgavatam: 3.9.15)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘Those who at the time of death desperately chant the Names of the Lord that describe His Avatārs, Qualities, and Pastimes immediately leave behind many births’ worth of sin and attain the uncovered Absolute. I surrender to that unborn Lord.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" চলিতে বসিতে স্বপ্নে ভোজনে শয়নে ।<br />কলিদমন কৃষ্ণোচ্চারে বাক্যের পূরণে ॥১৭৭॥<br />হেলাতেও করি’ নাম নিজ স্বরূপ পাঞা ।<br />পরমপদ বৈকুণ্ঠে যায় নির্ভয় হইয়া ॥১৭৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" chalite basite svapne bhojane śayane<br />kali-damana kṛṣṇochchāre vākyera pūraṇe [177]<br />helāteo kari’ nāma nija svarūpa pāñā<br />parama-pada vaikuṇṭhe yāya nirbhaya ha-iyā [178]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">chalite</span>–While walking, <span class=\\"e2\\">basite</span>–sitting, <span class=\\"e2\\">svapne</span>–dreaming, <span class=\\"e2\\">bhojane</span>–eating, <span class=\\"e2\\">śayane</span>–resting, [or] <span class=\\"e2\\">vākyera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">pūraṇe</span>–speaking, [those who] <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇochchāre</span>–chant the Name of Kṛṣṇa, <span class=\\"e2\\">kali-damana</span>–the subduer of Kali— [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">helāteo</span>–even [those who] neglect­fully <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma kari’</span>–chant the Name— <span class=\\"e2\\">nija</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">svarūpa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">pāñā</span>–realise the true self [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">nirbhaya</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">ha-iyā</span>–fearlessly <span class=\\"e2\\">yāya</span>–go [to] <span class=\\"e2\\">parama-pada</span>–the supreme abode <span class=\\"e2\\">vaikuṇṭhe</span>–of Vaikuṇṭha."},{"class":"b50","text":" “While walking, sitting, dreaming, eating, resting, or speaking, those who even neglectfully chant the Name of Kṛṣṇa, the subduer of Kali, realise the true self and fearlessly go to the supreme abode of Vaikuṇṭha."},{"class":"b97","text":" ব্রজংস্তিষ্ঠন্ স্বপন্নশ্নন্ শ্বসন্ বাক্যপ্রপূরণে ।<br />নামসঙ্কীর্ত্তনং বিষ্ণোর্হেলয়া কলিমর্ধনম্ ।<br />কৃত্বা স্বরূপতাং যাতি ভক্তিযুক্তঃ পরং ব্রজেৎ ॥১৭৯॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" vrajaṁs tiṣṭhan svapann aśnan śvasan vākya-prapūraṇe<br />nāma-saṅkīrtanaṁ viṣṇor helayā kali-mardhanam<br />kṛtvā svarūpatāṁ yāti bhakti-yuktaḥ paraṁ vrajet [179]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Liṅga-purāṇa)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘While walking, sitting, dreaming, eating, breathing, or speaking, those who even neglectfully engage in chanting Viṣṇu’s Name, the subduer of Kali, realise the true self, attain devotion, and go to the supreme abode.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" যেন তেন প্রকারেতে লয় কৃষ্ণনাম ।<br />তাকে প্রীতি করে কৃষ্ণ করুণা-নিদান ॥১৮০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" yena tena prakārete laya kṛṣṇa-nāma<br />tāke prīti kare kṛṣṇa karuṇā-nidāna [180]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span>–Kṛṣṇa, <span class=\\"e2\\">karuṇā-nidāna</span>–the reservoir of grace, <span class=\\"e2\\">prīti</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kare</span>–loves <span class=\\"e2\\">tāke</span>–those who <span class=\\"e2\\">laya</span>–chant <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-nāma</span>–the Name of Kṛṣṇa, <span class=\\"e2\\">yena</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">tena</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">prakārete</span>–howsoever [they do so]."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Kṛṣṇa, the reservoir of grace, loves those who chant His Name, howsoever they do so."},{"class":"b97","text":" মদ্যপানে ভূতাবিষ্ট বায়ু-পীড়া-স্থলে ।<br />হরিনামোচ্চারে মুক্তি তাঁর করতলে ॥১৮১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" madya-pāne bhūtāviṣṭa vāyu-pīḍā-sthale<br />hari-nāmochchāre mukti tā̐ra karatale [181]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">hari-nāmochchāre</span>–By chanting the Lord’s Name, [those who are] <span class=\\"e2\\">madya-pāne</span>–drunk, <span class=\\"e2\\">bhūtāviṣṭa</span>–bewitched, [or] <span class=\\"e2\\">vāyu-pīḍā-sthale</span>–diseased [find] <span class=\\"e2\\">mukti</span>–liberation <span class=\\"e2\\">tā̐ra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">karatale</span>–on the palm of their hand."},{"class":"b50","text":" “By chanting the Lord’s Name, even those who are drunk, bewitched, or diseased find liberation on the palm of their hand."},{"class":"b97","text":" বাসুদেবস্য সঙ্কীর্ত্ত্যা সুরাপো ব্যাধিতোঽপি বা ।<br />মুক্তো জায়েত নিয়তং মহাবিষ্ণুঃ প্রসীদতি ॥১৮২॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" vāsudevasya saṅkīrtyā surāpo vyādhito ’pi vā<br />mukto jāyeta niyataṁ mahāviṣṇuḥ prasīdati [182]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Varāha-purāṇa)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘By chanting the Name of Vāsudev, even drunk and diseased persons attain liberation, and Mahāviṣṇu becomes pleased.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" হরিনাম স্বতঃ পরমপুরুষার্থ হয় ।<br />উপেয়-মাঙ্গল্য-তত্ত্ব পরংধনময় ॥১৮৩॥<br />জীবনের ফল বস্তু কাশীখণ্ড বলে ।<br />পদ্মপুরাণেও তাহা কহে বহু স্থলে ॥১৮৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" hari-nāma svataḥ parama-puruṣārtha haya<br />upeya-māṅgalya-tattva paraṁ-dhanamaya [183]<br />jīvanera phala vastu kāśī-khaṇḍa bale<br />padma-purāṇeo tāhā kahe bahu sthale [184]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [Chanting] <span class=\\"e2\\">hari-nāma</span>–the Name of the Lord <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–is <span class=\\"e2\\">svataḥ</span>–itself <span class=\\"e2\\">parama-puruṣārtha</span>–the ultimate goal of life. <span class=\\"e2\\">kāśī-khaṇḍa</span>–The Kāśī-khaṇḍa (of the <span class=\\"e33\\">Skanda-purāṇa</span>) <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–says [that it is] <span class=\\"e2\\">upeya-māṅgalya-tattva</span>–the most sought-after auspiciousness, <span class=\\"e2\\">paraṁ-dhanamaya</span>–the supreme wealth, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">phala</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">vastu</span>–the fulfilment <span class=\\"e2\\">jīvanera</span>–of life. <span class=\\"e2\\">padma-purāṇeo</span>–The <span class=\\"e33\\">Padma-purāṇa</span> also <span class=\\"e2\\">kahe</span>–says <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhā</span>–this <span class=\\"e2\\">bahu</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sthale</span>–in many places."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Chanting the Name of the Lord is itself the ultimate goal of life. The Kāśī-khaṇḍa says that it is the most sought-after auspiciousness, the supreme wealth, and the fulfilment of life. The <span class=\\"e3\\">Padma-purāṇa</span> also says this in many places."},{"class":"b97","text":" ইদমেব হি মঙ্গল্যং এতদেব ধনার্জ্জনম্ ।<br />জীবিতস্য ফলঞ্চৈতদ্ যদ্দামোদরকীর্ত্তনম্ ॥১৮৫॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" idam eva hi maṅgalyaṁ etad eva dhanārjanam<br />jīvitasya phalañ chaitad yad dāmodara-kīrtanam [185]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Skanda-purāṇa, Padma-purāṇa)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘Chanting the Name of Dāmodar is true auspiciousness, true earning of wealth, and the fulfilment of life itself.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" সর্ব্ব মঙ্গলের হয় পরম মঙ্গল ।<br />চিত্তত্ত্ব-স্বরূপ সর্ব্ববেদবল্লীফল ॥১৮৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sarva maṅgalera haya parama maṅgala<br />chit-tattva svarūpa sarva-veda-vallī-phala [186]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">haya</span>–The Name is <span class=\\"e2\\">parama</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">maṅgala</span>–the most auspicious <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">maṅgalera</span>–of all auspicious things [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">chit-tattva</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">svarūpa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-veda-vallī-phala</span>–the spiritual fruit from the vine of all the Vedas."},{"class":"b50","text":" “The Name is the most auspicious of all auspicious things and the spiritual fruit produced by the vine of the Vedas."},{"class":"b97","text":" কৃষ্ণনাম লয় যেই শ্রদ্ধা বা হেলায় ।<br />নর-মাত্র ত্রাণ পায় সর্ব্ববেদে গায় ॥১৮৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kṛṣṇa-nāma laya yei śraddhā vā helāya<br />nara-mātra trāṇa pāya sarva-vede gāya [187]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-vede</span>–All the scriptures <span class=\\"e2\\">gāya</span>–sing [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">nara-mātra yei</span>–anyone who <span class=\\"e2\\">laya</span>–chants <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-nāma</span>–the Name of Kṛṣṇa, <span class=\\"e2\\">śraddhā</span>–faithfully <span class=\\"e2\\">vā</span>–or <span class=\\"e2\\">helāya</span>–neglectfully, <span class=\\"e2\\">pāya</span>–attains <span class=\\"e2\\">trāṇa</span>–deliverance."},{"class":"b50","text":" “All the scriptures sing that anyone who chants the Name of Kṛṣṇa, faithfully or negligently, attains deliverance."},{"class":"b97","text":" মধুরমধুরমেতন্মঙ্গলং মঙ্গলানাং<br />সকলনিগমবল্লীসৎফলং চিৎস্বরূপম্ ।<br />সকৃদপি পরিগীতং শ্রদ্ধয়া হেলয়া বা<br />ভৃগুবর নরমাত্রং তারয়েৎ কৃষ্ণনাম ॥১৮৮॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" madhura-madhuram etan maṅgalaṁ maṅgalānāṁ<br />sakala-nigama-vallī-sat-phalaṁ chit-svarūpam<br />sakṛd api parigītaṁ śraddhayā helayā vā<br />bhṛgu-vara nara-mātraṁ tārayet kṛṣṇa-nāma [188]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Prabhāsa-khaṇḍa)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘The Name of Kṛṣṇa, the sweetest of the sweet, the most auspicious of the auspicious, the eternal spiritual fruit from the vine of the Vedas, delivers a soul when He is chanted even once, faithfully or negligently.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" ভক্তির প্রকার যত শাস্ত্রে দেখা যায় ।<br />তঁহি মধ্যে নামাশ্রয় শ্রেষ্ঠ বলি’ গায় ॥১৮৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" bhaktira prakāra yata śāstre dekhā yāya<br />ta̐hi madhye nāmāśraya śreṣṭha bali’ gāya [189]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">gāya</span>–The scriptures sing [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmāśraya</span>–taking shelter of the Name <span class=\\"e2\\">śreṣṭha</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bali’</span>–is the best <span class=\\"e2\\">ta̐hi madhye</span>–amongst <span class=\\"e2\\">yata bhaktira</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">prakāra</span>–all the practices of devotion <span class=\\"e2\\">dekhā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">yāya</span>–found <span class=\\"e2\\">śāstre</span>–in the scriptures."},{"class":"b50","text":" “The scriptures sing that taking shelter of the Name is best amongst all the practices of devotion found in the scriptures."},{"class":"b97","text":" কষ্টেতে অষ্টাঙ্গ যোগে বিষ্ণুস্মৃতি সাধে ।<br />ওষ্ঠস্পন্দনেই শ্রেষ্ঠ কীর্ত্তন বিরাজে ॥১৯০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kaṣṭete aṣṭāṅga yoge viṣṇu-smṛti sādhe<br />oṣṭha-spandanei śreṣṭha kīrtana virāje [190]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">viṣṇu-smṛti</span>–Remembrance of Viṣṇu <span class=\\"e2\\">sādhe</span>–is practised <span class=\\"e2\\">kaṣṭete</span>–with difficulty <span class=\\"e2\\">aṣṭāṅga</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">yoge</span>–through aṣṭāṅga-yoga, [but] <span class=\\"e2\\">kīrtana</span>–chanting [His Name is practised] <span class=\\"e2\\">oṣṭha-spandanei</span>–by simply moving the lips; [chanting thus] <span class=\\"e2\\">virāje</span>–reigns <span class=\\"e2\\">śreṣṭha</span>–supreme."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Remembrance of Viṣṇu is practised with difficulty through aṣṭāṅga-yoga, but chanting His Name is practised simply by moving the lips; chanting thus reigns supreme."},{"class":"b97","text":" অঘচ্ছিৎ স্মরণং বিষ্ণোর্ব্বহ্বায়াসেন সাধ্যতে ।<br />ওষ্ঠস্পন্দনমাত্রেণ কীর্ত্তনন্তু ততো বরম্ ॥১৯১॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" aghachchhit smaraṇaṁ viṣṇor bahv-āyāsena sādhyate<br />oṣṭha-spandana-mātreṇa kīrtanan tu tato varam [191]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Vaiṣṇava-chintāmaṇi)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘Remembrance of Viṣṇu, which destroys sin, is practised with great exertion, but chanting Viṣṇu’s Name is practised simply by moving the lips. Chanting is thus superior to remembrance.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" দীক্ষাপূর্ব্বক অর্চ্চন যদি শত জন্ম করে ।<br />তাহার জিহ্বায় নিত্য হরিনাম স্ফুরে ॥১৯২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" dīkṣā-pūrvaka archana yadi śata janma kare<br />tāhāra jihvāya nitya hari-nāma sphure [192]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">hari-nāma</span>–The Name of the Lord <span class=\\"e2\\">nitya</span>–always <span class=\\"e2\\">sphure</span>–appears <span class=\\"e2\\">tāhāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">jihvāya</span>–on the soul’s tongue <span class=\\"e2\\">yadi</span>–when <span class=\\"e2\\">dīkṣā-pūrvaka</span>–they have accepted initiation [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">archana</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kare</span>–performed worship <span class=\\"e2\\">śata</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">janma</span>–for hundreds of births."},{"class":"b50","text":" “The Name of the Lord always appears on the tongue of those who have accepted initiation and performed worship for hundreds of births."},{"class":"b97","text":" যেন জন্মশতৈঃ পূর্ব্বং বাসুদেবঃ সমর্চিতঃ ।<br />তন্মুখে হরিনামানি সদা তিষ্ঠন্তি ভারত ॥১৯৩॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" yena janma-śataiḥ pūrvaṁ vāsudevaḥ samarchitaḥ<br />tan-mukhe hari-nāmāni sadā tiṣṭhanti bhārata [193]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Vaiṣṇava-chintāmaṇi)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘O King, the Names of the Lord are always present in the mouth of those who have fully worshipped Vāsudev for hundreds of previous births.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" সত্যযুগে বহুকালে যাহা তপোধ্যানে ।<br />যজ্ঞাদি যজিয়া ত্রেতায় যেবা ফল টানে ॥১৯৪॥<br />দ্বাপরে অর্চ্চনাঙ্গেতে পায় যেবা ফল ।<br />কলিতে হরিনামে পায় সে সকল ॥১৯৫॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" satya-yuge bahu-kāle yāhā tapo-dhyāne<br />yajñādi yajiyā tretāya yebā phala ṭāne [194]<br />dvāpare archanāṅgete pāya yebā phala<br />kalite hari-nāme pāya se sakala [195]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">se</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">sakala yāhā yebā yebā phala phala</span>–All the results <span class=\\"e2\\">ṭāne pāya</span>–attained <span class=\\"e2\\">satya-yuge</span>–in Satya-yuga <span class=\\"e2\\">bahu-kāle</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">tapo-dhyāne</span>–by long-term austerity and meditation, <span class=\\"e2\\">tretāya</span>–in Tretā-yuga <span class=\\"e2\\">yajñādi</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">yajiyā</span>–by conducting sacrifices, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">dvāpare</span>–in Dvāpar-yuga <span class=\\"e2\\">archanāṅgete</span>–by the practice of worship <span class=\\"e2\\">pāya</span>–are attained <span class=\\"e2\\">kalite</span>–in Kali-yuga <span class=\\"e2\\">hari-nāme</span>–by [chanting] the Name of the Lord."},{"class":"b50","text":" “All the results attained in Satya-yuga by long-term austerity and meditation, in Tretā-yuga by conducting sacrifices, and in Dvāpar-yuga by Deity worship are attained in Kali-yuga by chanting the Name of the Lord."},{"class":"b97","text":" ধ্যায়ন্ কৃতে যজন্ যজ্ঞৈস্ত্রেতায়াং দ্বাপরেঽর্চ্চয়ন্ ।<br />যদাপ্নোতি তদাপ্নোতি কলৌ সঙ্কীর্ত্ত্য কেশবম্ ॥১৯৬॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" dhyāyan kṛte yajan yajñais tretāyāṁ dvāpare ’rchayan<br />yad āpnoti tad āpnoti kalau saṅkīrtya keśavam [196]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Viṣṇu-purāṇa)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘Whatever is attained in Satya-yuga by meditation, in Tretā-yuga by sacrifice, and in Dvāpar-yuga by worship, is attained in Kali-yuga by chanting Keśava’s Name.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" কলিকালে মহাভাগবত বলি তারে ।<br />কীর্ত্তনে যে হরি ভজে এ ভব-সংসারে ॥১৯৭॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kali-kāle mahābhāgavata bali tāre<br />kīrtane ye hari bhaje e bhava-saṁsāre [197]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bali</span>–We consider <span class=\\"e2\\">tāre ye</span>–those who <span class=\\"e2\\">bhaje</span>–serve <span class=\\"e2\\">hari</span>–the Lord <span class=\\"e2\\">kali-kāle</span>–in the Age of Kali <span class=\\"e2\\">e</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">bhava-saṁsāre</span>–in this material world <span class=\\"e2\\">kīrtane</span>–by chanting [His Name to be] <span class=\\"e2\\">mahābhāgavata</span>–advanced devotees."},{"class":"b50","text":" “We consider those who serve the Lord in the Age of Kali in this material world by chanting His Name to be advanced devotees."},{"class":"b97","text":" মহাভাগবতা নিত্যং কলৌ কুর্ব্বন্তি কীর্ত্তনম্ ॥১৯৮॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" mahābhāgavatā nityaṁ kalau kurvanti kīrtanam [198]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Skanda-purāṇa)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘In the Age of Kali, great devotees always chant the Name of the Lord.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" চিদাত্মক হরিনাম বারেক উচ্চারে ।<br />শিব-ব্রহ্মা-অনন্ত তার ফল কহিতে নারে ॥১৯৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" chid-ātmaka hari-nāma bāreka uchchāre<br />śiva-brahmā-ananta tāra phala kahite nāre [199]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">śiva-brahmā-ananta</span>–Śiva, Brahmā, and Ananta <span class=\\"e2\\">nāre</span>–cannot <span class=\\"e2\\">kahite</span>–describe <span class=\\"e2\\">tāra</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">phala</span>–the result of <span class=\\"e2\\">bāreka</span>–once <span class=\\"e2\\">uchchāre</span>–chanting <span class=\\"e2\\">chid-ātmaka</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">hari-nāma</span>–the spiritual Name of the Lord."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Śiva, Brahmā, and Ananta cannot describe the result of once chanting the spiritual Name of the Lord."},{"class":"b97","text":" নামোচ্চারণমাহাত্ম্য অদ্ভুত বলি’ গায় ।<br />উচ্চারণমাত্রে নর পরমপদ পায় ॥২০০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" nāmochchāraṇa-māhātmya adbhuta bali’ gāya<br />uchchāraṇa-mātre nara parama-pada pāya [200]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">bali’ gāya</span>–The scriptures proclaim [that] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmochchāraṇa-māhātmya</span>–the glory of chanting the Name [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">adbhuta</span>–astounding: <span class=\\"e2\\">uchchāraṇa-mātre</span>–by just once chanting [the Name,] <span class=\\"e2\\">nara</span>–the soul <span class=\\"e2\\">pāya</span>–attains <span class=\\"e2\\">parama-pada</span>–the supreme abode."},{"class":"b50","text":" “The scriptures proclaim that the glory of chanting the Name is astounding: by just once chanting the Name, the soul attains the supreme abode."},{"class":"b97","text":" সকৃদুচ্চারয়ন্ত্যেব হরের্নাম চিদাত্মকম্ ।<br />ফলং নাস্য ক্ষমো বক্তুং সহস্রবদনো বিধিঃ ॥২০১॥<br />নামোচ্চারণমাহাত্ম্যং শ্রূয়তে মহদদ্ভুতম্ ।<br />যদুচ্চারণমাত্রেণ নরো যায়াৎ পরং পদম্ ॥২০২॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" sakṛd uchchārayanty eva harer nāma chid-ātmakam<br />phalaṁ nāsya kṣamo vaktuṁ sahasra-vadano vidhiḥ [201]<br />nāmochchāraṇa-māhātmyaṁ śrūyate mahad adbhutam<br />yad uchchāraṇa-mātreṇa naro yāyāt paraṁ padam [202]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Bṛhan-nāradīya-purāṇa)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘Thousand-mouthed Ananta Śeṣa and the creator Lord Brahmā cannot describe the result of chanting the Lord’s spiritual Name even once. We have heard that the glories of uttering the Name are greatly astounding: by just once chanting the Name, the soul attains the supreme abode.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" কৃষ্ণ বলে, ‘শুন অর্জ্জুন! বলিব তোমায় ।<br />শ্রদ্ধায় হেলায় জীব মম নাম গায় ॥২০৩॥<br />সেই নাম মম হৃদি সদা বর্ত্তমান ।<br />নামসম ব্রত নাই, নামসম জ্ঞান ॥২০৪॥<br />নামসম ধ্যান নাই, নামসম ফল ।<br />নামসম ত্যাগ নাই, নামসম বল ॥২০৫॥<br />নামসম পুণ্য নাই, নামসম গতি ।<br />নামের শক্তিগানে বেদের নাহিক শকতি ॥২০৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kṛṣṇa bale, ‘śuna arjuna! baliba tomāya<br />śraddhāya helāya jīva mama nāma gāya [203]<br />sei nāma mama hṛdi sadā vartamāna<br />nāma-sama vrata nāi, nāma-sama jñāna [204]<br />nāma-sama dhyāna nāi, nāma-sama phala<br />nāma-sama tyāga nāi, nāma-sama bala [205]<br />nāma-sama puṇya nāi, nāma-sama gati<br />nāmera śakti-gāne vedera nāhika śakati [206]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span>–Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–says, <span class=\\"e2\\">‘arjuna!</span>–O Arjuna, <span class=\\"e2\\">śuna</span>–listen [to what] <span class=\\"e2\\">baliba</span>–I will say <span class=\\"e2\\">tomāya</span>–to you. [When] <span class=\\"e2\\">jīva</span>–souls <span class=\\"e2\\">gāya</span>–chant<span class=\\"e2\\"> mama</span>–My <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–Name, <span class=\\"e2\\">śraddhāya</span>–faithfully [or] <span class=\\"e2\\">helāya</span>–negligently, <span class=\\"e2\\">sei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–their names <span class=\\"e2\\">vartamāna</span>–remain <span class=\\"e2\\">mama</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">hṛdi</span>–in My heart <span class=\\"e2\\">sadā</span>–forever. <span class=\\"e2\\">nāi</span>–There is no <span class=\\"e2\\">vrata</span>–rite <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-sama</span>–equal to [My] Name. [There is no] <span class=\\"e2\\">jñāna</span>–knowledge <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-sama</span>–equal to [My] Name. <span class=\\"e2\\">nāi</span>–There is no <span class=\\"e2\\">dhyāna</span>–meditation <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-sama</span>–equal to [My] Name. [There is no] <span class=\\"e2\\">phala</span>–attainment <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-sama</span>–equal to [My] Name. <span class=\\"e2\\">nāi</span>–There is no <span class=\\"e2\\">tyāga</span>–renunciation <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-sama</span>–equal to [My] Name. [There is no] <span class=\\"e2\\">bala</span>–strength <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-sama</span>–equal to [My] Name. <span class=\\"e2\\">nāi</span>–There is no <span class=\\"e2\\">puṇya</span>–piety <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-sama</span>–equal to [My] Name. [There is no] <span class=\\"e2\\">gati</span>–shelter <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-sama</span>–equal to [My] Name. <span class=\\"e2\\">vedera</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">śakati</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāhika</span>–The scriptures do not have the power <span class=\\"e2\\">śakti-gāne</span>–to sing about the power <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmera</span>–of [My] Name."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Kṛṣṇa says, ‘O Arjuna, listen to what I will say to you. When souls chant My Name, faithfully or negligently, their names remain in My heart forever. There is no rite equal to My Name. There is no knowledge equal to My Name. There is no meditation equal to My Name. There is no renunciation equal to My Name. There is no attainment equal to My Name. There is no strength equal to My Name. There is no piety equal to My Name. There is no shelter equal to My Name. The scriptures are unable to describe the power of My Name."},{"class":"b97","text":" নামই পরমা মুক্তি, নামই পরমা গতি ।<br />নামই পরমা শান্তি, নামই পরমা স্থিতি ॥২০৭॥<br />নামই পরমা ভক্তি, নামই পরমা মতি ।<br />নামই পরমা প্রীতি, নামই পরমা স্মৃতি ॥২০৮॥<br />জীবের কারণ নাম, নামই জীবের প্রভু ।<br />পরম আরাধ্য নাম, নামই গুরু প্রভু’ ॥২০৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" nāma-i paramā mukti, nāma-i paramā gati<br />nāma-i paramā śānti, nāma-i paramā sthiti [207]<br />nāma-i paramā bhakti, nāma-i paramā mati<br />nāma-i paramā prīti, nāma-i paramā smṛti [208]<br />jīvera kāraṇa nāma, nāma-i jīvera prabhu<br />parama ārādhya nāma, nāma-i guru prabhu’ [209]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [My] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-i</span>–Name alone [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">paramā</span>–the highest <span class=\\"e2\\">mukti</span>–liberation. [My] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-i</span>–Name alone [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">paramā</span>–the highest <span class=\\"e2\\">gati</span>–shelter. [My] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-i</span>–Name alone [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">paramā</span>–the highest <span class=\\"e2\\">śānti</span>–peace. [My] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-i</span>–Name alone [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">paramā</span>–the highest <span class=\\"e2\\">sthiti</span>–dedication. [My] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-i</span>–Name alone [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">paramā</span>–the highest <span class=\\"e2\\">bhakti</span>–devotion. [My] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-i</span>–Name alone [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">paramā</span>–the highest <span class=\\"e2\\">mati</span>–conception. [My] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-i</span>–Name alone [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">paramā</span>–the highest <span class=\\"e2\\">prīti</span>–love. [My] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-i</span>–Name alone [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">paramā</span>–the highest <span class=\\"e2\\">smṛti</span>–remembrance. [My]<span class=\\"e2\\"> nāma</span>–Name [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">jīvera</span>–the soul’s <span class=\\"e2\\">kāraṇa</span>–origin. [My] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-i</span>–Name alone [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">jīvera</span>–the soul’s <span class=\\"e2\\">prabhu</span>–Lord. [My] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–Name [is the soul’s] <span class=\\"e2\\">parama</span>–highest <span class=\\"e2\\">ārādhya</span>–object of worship. [My] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-i</span>–Name alone [is the soul’s] <span class=\\"e2\\">guru</span>–Guru [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">prabhu’</span>–Lord.’"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘My Name alone is the highest liberation. My Name alone is the highest shelter. My Name alone is the highest peace. My Name alone is the highest dedication. My Name alone is the highest devotion. My Name alone is the highest conception. My Name alone is the highest love. My Name alone is the highest remembrance. My Name alone is the soul’s origin. My Name alone is the soul’s master. My Name alone is the soul’s highest object of worship. My Name alone is the soul’s Guru and Lord.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" শ্রদ্ধয়া হেলয়া নাম রটন্তি মম জন্তবঃ ।<br />তেষাং নাম সদা পার্থ বর্ত্ততে হৃদয়ে মম ॥২১০॥<br />ন নামসদৃশং জ্ঞানং ন নামসদৃশং ব্রতম্ ।<br />ন নামসদৃশং ধ্যানং ন নামসদৃশং ফলম্ ॥২১১॥<br />ন নামসদৃশস্ত্যাগো ন নামসদৃশঃ শমঃ ।<br />ন নামসদৃশং পুণ্যং ন নামসদৃশী গতিঃ ॥২১২॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" śraddhayā helayā nāma raṭanti mama jantavaḥ<br />teṣāṁ nāma sadā pārtha vartate hṛdaye mama [210]<br />na nāma-sadṛśaṁ jñānaṁ na nāma-sadṛśaṁ vratam<br />na nāma-sadṛśaṁ dhyānaṁ na nāma-sadṛśaṁ phalam [211]<br />na nāma-sadṛśas tyāgo na nāma-sadṛśaḥ śamaḥ<br />na nāma-sadṛśaṁ puṇyaṁ na nāma-sadṛśī gatiḥ [212]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Ādi-purāṇa)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “[Kṛṣṇa:] ‘O Arjuna, the names of those who chant My Name, faithfully or negligently, always remain in My heart. There is no knowledge like My Name. There is no rite like My Name. There is no meditation like My Name. There is no attainment like My Name. There is no renunciation like My Name. There is no equanimity like My Name. There is no piety like My Name. There is no shelter like My Name."},{"class":"b97","text":" নামৈব পরমা মুক্তির্নামৈব পরমা গতিঃ ।<br />নামৈব পরমা শান্তির্নামৈব পরমা স্থিতিঃ ॥২১৩॥<br />নামৈব পরমা ভক্তির্নামৈব পরমা মতিঃ ।<br />নামৈব পরমা প্রীতির্নামৈব পরমা স্মৃতিঃ ॥২১৪॥<br />নামৈব কারণং জন্তোর্নামৈব প্রভুরেব চ ।<br />নামৈব পরমারাধ্যো নামৈব পরমো গুরুঃ ॥২১৫॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" nāmaiva paramā muktir nāmaiva paramā gatiḥ<br />nāmaiva paramā śāntir nāmaiva paramā sthitiḥ [213]<br />nāmaiva paramā bhaktir nāmaiva paramā matiḥ<br />nāmaiva paramā prītir nāmaiva paramā smṛtiḥ [214]<br />nāmaiva kāraṇaṁ jantor nāmaiva prabhur eva cha<br />nāmaiva paramārādhyo nāmaiva paramo guruḥ [215]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Ādi-purāṇa)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘My Name alone is the highest liberation. My Name alone is the highest shelter. My Name alone is the highest equanimity. My Name alone is the highest dedication. My Name alone is the highest devotion. My Name alone is the highest conception. My Name alone is the highest love. My Name alone is the highest remembrance. My Name alone is the soul’s origin. My Name alone is the soul’s master. My Name alone is the soul’s highest object of worship. My Name alone is the soul’s highest Guru.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" হরিনাম-মাহাত্ম্যের কভু নাহি পার ।<br />যে নাম শ্রবণে সদ্য পুক্কশ উদ্ধার ॥২১৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" hari-nāma-māhātmyera kabhu nāhi pāra<br />ye nāma śravaṇe sadya pukkaśa uddhāra [216]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kabhu</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāhi</span>–There is never <span class=\\"e2\\">pāra</span>–an end <span class=\\"e2\\">hari-nāma-māhātmyera</span>–to the glories of the Lord’s Name, <span class=\\"e2\\">ye</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–the Name which <span class=\\"e2\\">śravaṇe</span>–by hearing [even] <span class=\\"e2\\">pukkaśa</span>–outcasts [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">sadya</span>–immediately <span class=\\"e2\\">uddhāra</span>–liberated."},{"class":"b50","text":" “The glories of the Lord’s Name never end; even outcasts are immediately liberated upon hearing the Name."},{"class":"b97","text":" যন্নামসকৃচ্ছ্রবণাৎ <br />পুক্কশোঽপি বিমুচ্যতে সংসারাৎ ॥২১৭॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" yan-nāma sakṛch chhravaṇāt<br />pukkaśo ’pi vimuchyate saṁsārāt [217]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Śrīmad Bhāgavatam: 6.16.44)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “Even outcasts are liberated from saṁsāra by once hearing the Name of the Lord."},{"class":"b97","text":" স্বপনে জাগ্রতে যেবা জল্পে কৃষ্ণনাম ।<br />কলিতে সে কৃষ্ণরূপী, কৃষ্ণের বিধান ॥২১৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" svapane jāgrate yebā jalpe kṛṣṇa-nāma<br />kalite se kṛṣṇa-rūpī, kṛṣṇera vidhāna [218]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">se</span>–Those <span class=\\"e2\\">kalite</span>–in the Age of Kali <span class=\\"e2\\">yebā</span>–who <span class=\\"e2\\">jalpe</span>–chant <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-nāma</span>–the Name of Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">svapane</span>–in dreams [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">jāgrate</span>–while awake [attain] <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-rūpī</span>–a form like that of Kṛṣṇa. [This is] <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇera</span>–Kṛṣṇa’s <span class=\\"e2\\">vidhāna</span>–arrangement."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Those in the Age of Kali who chant the Name of Kṛṣṇa while dreaming or awake attain a form like that of Kṛṣṇa. This is Kṛṣṇa’s arrangement."},{"class":"b97","text":" কৃষ্ণ কৃষ্ণেতি কৃষ্ণেতি স্বপন্ জাগ্রদ্ ব্রজংস্তথা ।<br />যো জল্পতি কলৌ নিত্যং কৃষ্ণরূপী ভবেদ্ধি সঃ ॥২১৯॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" kṛṣṇa kṛṣṇeti kṛṣṇeti svapan jāgrad vrajaṁs tathā<br />yo jalpati kalau nityaṁ kṛṣṇa-rūpī bhaved dhi saḥ [219]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Varāha-purāṇa)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘While dreaming, waking, or walking, those who always chant, ‘Kṛṣṇa! Kṛṣṇa! Kṛṣṇa!’ in the Age of Kali attain a form like that of Kṛṣṇa Himself.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" কৃষ্ণ বলি’ নিত্য স্মরে সংসার-সাগরে ।<br />জলোত্থিত পদ্ম যেন নরকে উদ্ধরে ॥২২০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kṛṣṇa bali’ nitya smare saṁsāra-sāgare<br />jalotthita padma yena narake uddhare [220]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [The Lord] <span class=\\"e2\\">uddhare</span>–delivers <span class=\\"e2\\">narake</span>–from hell [anyone who,] <span class=\\"e2\\">yena</span>–like <span class=\\"e2\\">padma</span>–a lotus <span class=\\"e2\\">jalotthita</span>–arising from water, <span class=\\"e2\\">nitya</span>–always <span class=\\"e2\\">smare</span>–remembers [Him] <span class=\\"e2\\">bali’</span>–by chanting <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span>–the Name of Kṛṣṇa <span class=\\"e2\\">saṁsāra-sāgare</span>–within the ocean of material existence."},{"class":"b50","text":" “The Lord delivers from hell anyone who, like a lotus arising out of water, always remembers Him by chanting ‘Kṛṣṇa’ within the ocean of material existence."},{"class":"b97","text":" কৃষ্ণ কৃষ্ণেতি কৃষ্ণেতি যো মাং স্মরতি নিত্যশঃ ।<br />জলং ভিত্ত্বা যথা পদ্মং নরকাদুদ্ধরাম্যহম্ ॥২২১॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" kṛṣṇa kṛṣṇeti kṛṣṇeti yo māṁ smarati nityaśaḥ<br />jalaṁ bhittvā yathā padmaṁ narakād uddharāmy aham [221]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Nṛsiṁha-purāṇa)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “[The Lord:] ‘I deliver from hell anyone who, like a lotus cutting through water, always remembers Me by chanting ‘Kṛṣṇa! Kṛṣṇa! Kṛṣṇa!’ ’"},{"class":"b97","text":" কৃষ্ণনাম সর্ব্বমুখ্য জীবের আশ্রয় ।<br />অশেষ পাপ হরে, সদ্য পাপমুক্তিকর ॥২২২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" kṛṣṇa-nāma sarva-mukhya jīvera āśraya<br />aśeṣa pāpa hare, sadya pāpa-mukti-kara [222]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-nāma</span>–The Name of Kṛṣṇa [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">sarva-mukhya āśraya</span>–the foremost shelter <span class=\\"e2\\">jīvera</span>–of the soul. <span class=\\"e2\\">hare</span>–The Name removes <span class=\\"e2\\">aśeṣa</span>–innumerable <span class=\\"e2\\">pāpa</span>–sins [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">sadya</span>–immediately [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">pāpa-mukti-kara</span>–a granter of liberation from [all] sins."},{"class":"b50","text":" “The Name of Kṛṣṇa is the foremost shelter of the soul. The Name removes innumerable sins and immediately liberates the soul from all sins."},{"class":"b97","text":" নাম্নাং মুখ্যতরং নাম কৃষ্ণাখ্যং মে পরন্তপ ।<br />প্রায়শ্চিত্তমশেষাণাং পাপানাং মোচকং পরম্ ॥২২৩॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" nāmnāṁ mukhyataraṁ nāma kṛṣṇākhyaṁ me parantapa<br />prāyaśchittam aśeṣāṇāṁ pāpānāṁ mochakaṁ param [223]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Prabhāsa-purāṇa)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “[The Lord:] ‘Amongst My Names, ‘Kṛṣṇa’ is supreme. This Name atones for innumerable sins and grants the ultimate liberation.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" নাম চিন্তামণি, কৃষ্ণ, চৈতন্য-স্বরূপ ।<br />পূর্ণ, শুদ্ধ, নিত্যমুক্ত, নামনামী একরূপ ॥২২৪॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" nāma chintāmaṇi, kṛṣṇa, chaitanya-svarūpa<br />pūrṇa, śuddha, nitya-mukta, nāma-nāmī eka-rūpa [224]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–The Name [is] <span class=\\"e2\\">chintāmaṇi</span>–a wish-fulfilling jewel, <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa</span>–Kṛṣṇa [Himself. He is] <span class=\\"e2\\">chaitanya-svarūpa</span>–by nature spiritual, <span class=\\"e2\\">pūrṇa</span>–complete, <span class=\\"e2\\">śuddha</span>–pure, [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">nitya-mukta</span>–eternally liberated. <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-nāmī</span>–The Name and the possessor of the Name [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">eka-rūpa</span>–one being."},{"class":"b50","text":" “The Name is a wish-fulfilling jewel, Kṛṣṇa Himself. He is by nature spiritual, complete, pure, and eternally liberated. The Name and the possessor of the Name are one."},{"class":"b97","text":" নাম চিন্তামণিঃ কৃষ্ণশ্চৈতন্যরসবিগ্রহঃ ।<br />পূর্ণঃ শুদ্ধো নিত্যমুক্তোঽভিন্নত্বান্নামনামিনোঃ ॥২২৫॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" nāma chintāmaṇiḥ kṛṣṇaś chaitanya-rasa-vigrahaḥ<br />pūrṇaḥ śuddho nitya-mukto ’bhinnatvān nāma-nāminoḥ [225]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Padma-purāṇa)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘The Name is a wish-fulfilling jewel, Kṛṣṇa Himself, and the embodiment of spiritual joy. He is complete, pure, eternally liberated, and nondifferent from the possessor of the Name.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" বিষ্ণুনাম বিষ্ণুশক্তি যেই জন জানে ।<br />সুমতি প্রার্থনা করে অপ্রাকৃত জ্ঞানে ॥২২৬॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" viṣṇu-nāma viṣṇu-śakti yei jana jāne<br />sumati prārthanā kare aprākṛta jñāne [226]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">yei</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">jana</span>–Those who <span class=\\"e2\\">jāne</span>–know [the] <span class=\\"e2\\">sumati</span>–easily understandable <span class=\\"e2\\">viṣṇu-nāma</span>–Name of Viṣṇu [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">viṣṇu-śakti</span>–power of Viṣṇu <span class=\\"e2\\">prārthanā</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kare</span>–pray [to Him] <span class=\\"e2\\">aprākṛta</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">jñāne</span>–with supramundane knowledge."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Those who know the easily understandable Name and power of Viṣṇu pray to Him with supramundane realisation."},{"class":"b97","text":" ওঁ আস্য জানন্তো নাম চিদ্বিবক্তন্ ।<br />মহস্তে বিষ্ণো সুমতিং ভজামহে” ॥২২৭॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" o̐ āsya jānanto nāma chid-viviktan<br />mahas te viṣṇo sumatiṁ bhajāmahe” [227]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Ṛg-veda: 1.156.3)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘O Viṣṇu! Understanding Your spiritual, all-revealing, and easily intelligible Name, we serve You.’”"},{"class":"b97","text":" স্থানেশ্বরী কৃষ্ণদাস যোড় করি’ কর ।<br />বলে, “প্রভু, এক বস্তু প্রার্থনা হামার ॥২২৮॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" sthāneśvarī kṛṣṇa-dāsa yoḍa kari’ kara<br />bale, “prabhu eka vastu prārthanā hāmāra [228]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">sthāneśvarī</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kṛṣṇa-dāsa</span>–Kṛṣṇadās of Sthāneśvarī [then] <span class=\\"e2\\">yoḍa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kari’</span>–joined [his] <span class=\\"e2\\">kara</span>–palms [and] <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–said, <span class=\\"e2\\">“prabhu</span>–“O Lord, <span class=\\"e2\\">hāmāra eka</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">vastu</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">prārthanā</span>–I have one request."},{"class":"b50","text":" [Śrīman Mahāprabhu thus concluded His glorification of the Name.] Kṛṣṇadās of Sthāneśvarī then joined his palms and said, “O Lord, I have one request."},{"class":"b97","text":" এরূপ মাহাত্ম্য নামের শুনিনু শ্রবণে ।<br />সর্ব্বত্র সমান ফল নাহি হোয় কেনে” ॥২২৯॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" e-rūpa māhātmya nāmera śuninu śravaṇe<br />sarvatra samāna phala nāhi hoya kene” [229]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">śuninu</span>–I have heard [now] <span class=\\"e2\\">śravaṇe</span>–with [my own] ears <span class=\\"e2\\">e-rūpa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">māhātmya</span>–the glories <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmera</span>–of the Name, [but] <span class=\\"e2\\">samāna</span>–the same <span class=\\"e2\\">phala</span>–results <span class=\\"e2\\">hoya nāhi</span>–do not occur <span class=\\"e2\\">sarvatra</span>–everywhere. <span class=\\"e2\\">kene”</span>–Why?”"},{"class":"b50","text":" “I have now heard with my own ears the glories of the Name, but such results do not occur everywhere. Why?”"},{"class":"b97","text":" প্রভু বলে, “শ্রদ্ধা বিশ্বাস সকলের মূল ।<br />বিশ্বাস-অভাবে কেহ নাহি লভে ফল” ॥২৩০॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" prabhu bale, “śraddhā viśvāsa sakalera mūla<br />viśvāsa-abhāve keha nāhi labhe phala” [230]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">prabhu</span>–The Lord <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–said, <span class=\\"e2\\">“śraddhā viśvāsa</span>–Faith and conviction [are] <span class=\\"e2\\">mūla</span>–the basis <span class=\\"e2\\">sakalera</span>–of everything. <span class=\\"e2\\">viśvāsa-abhāve</span>–Because of a lack of faith, <span class=\\"e2\\">keha</span>–some <span class=\\"e2\\">labhe nāhi</span>–do not attain <span class=\\"e2\\">phala”</span>–the result.”"},{"class":"b50","text":" The Lord answered, “Faith and conviction are the basis of everything. Because they lack faith, some do not attain the result.”"},{"class":"b97","text":" প্রভু বলে, “অন্তর্য্যামী নাম ভগবান্ ।<br />বিশ্বাসানুসারে ফল করেন প্রদান ॥২৩১॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" prabhu bale, “antaryāmī nāma bhagavān<br />viśvāsānusāre phala karena pradāna [231]"},{"class":"b101","text":" <span class=\\"e2\\">prabhu</span>–The Lord <span class=\\"e2\\">bale</span>–said, <span class=\\"e2\\">“antaryāmī</span>–“Dwelling within [the heart,] <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma</span>–the Name, <span class=\\"e2\\">bhagavān</span>–the Lord [Himself,] <span class=\\"e2\\">pradāna karena</span>–grants [souls] <span class=\\"e2\\">phala</span>–results <span class=\\"e2\\">viśvāsānusāre</span>–according to [their] faith."},{"class":"b50","text":" The Lord continued, “Dwelling within the heart, the Name, the Lord Himself, grants souls results according to their faith."},{"class":"b97","text":" নামের মহিমা পূর্ণ বিশ্বাস না করে ।<br />নামের ফল নাহি পায়, নাম-অপরাধে মরে ॥২৩২॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" nāmera mahimā pūrṇa viśvāsa nā kare<br />nāmera phala nāhi pāya, nāma-aparādhe mare [232]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [Those who] <span class=\\"e2\\">pūrṇa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">viśvāsa</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kare nā</span>–do not have full faith <span class=\\"e2\\">mahimā</span>–in the glories <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmera</span>–of the Name <span class=\\"e2\\">pāya nāhi</span>–do not get <span class=\\"e2\\">phala</span>–the [proper] result <span class=\\"e2\\">nāmera</span>–of [chanting] the Name; <span class=\\"e2\\">mare</span>–they die <span class=\\"e2\\">nāma-aparādhe</span>–as a result of offences to the Name."},{"class":"b50","text":" “Those who do not have full faith in the glories of the Name do not get the proper result of chanting the Name; they die as a result of offences to the Name."},{"class":"b97","text":" অর্থবাদ করে ফলে বিশ্বাস ত্যজিয়া ।<br />ফল নাহি পায়, থাকে নরকে পড়িয়া” ॥২৩৩॥"},{"class":"b60","text":" arthavāda kare phale viśvāsa tyajiyā<br />phala nāhi pāya, thāke narake paḍiyā” [233]"},{"class":"b101","text":" [Those who] <span class=\\"e2\\">phale arthavāda</span> <span class=\\"e2\\">kare</span>–consider the result [of chanting the Name] to be exaggerated <span class=\\"e2\\">tyajiyā</span>–lose [their] <span class=\\"e2\\">viśvāsa</span>–faith [in the Name and] <span class=\\"e2\\">pāya nāhi</span>–do not get <span class=\\"e2\\">phala</span>–the [proper] result; <span class=\\"e2\\">paḍiyā thāke</span>–they fall and remain <span class=\\"e2\\">narake”</span>–in hell.”"},{"class":"b50","text":" “Those who consider the result of chanting the Name to be exaggerated lose their faith in the Name and do not get the proper result; they fall into hell and remain there.”"},{"class":"b97","text":" অর্থবাদং হরের্নাম্নি সম্ভাবয়তি যো নরঃ ।<br />স পাপিষ্ঠো মনুষ্যাণাং নিরয়ে পতন্তি স্ফুটম্ ॥২৩৪॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" arthavādaṁ harer nāmni sambhāvayati yo naraḥ<br />sa pāpiṣṭho manuṣyāṇāṁ niraye patanti sphuṭam [234]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Kātyāyana-saṁhitā)"},{"class":"b50","text":" “‘The sinners within human society who imagine the glories of the Name of the Lord to be exaggerated certainly fall into hell.’"},{"class":"b97","text":" যন্নামকীর্ত্তনফলং বিবিধং নিশম্য<br />ন শ্রদ্দধাতি মনুতে যদুতার্থবাদম্ ।<br />যো মানুষস্তমিহ দুঃখচয়ে ক্ষিপামি<br />সংসার-ঘোর-বিবিধার্ত্তিনিপীড়িতাঙ্গম্॥২৩৫॥"},{"class":"b59","text":" yan-nāma-kīrtana-phalaṁ vividhaṁ niśamya<br />na śraddadhāti manute yad utārthavādam<br />yo mānuṣas tam iha duḥkha-chaye kṣipāmi<br />saṁsāra-ghora-vividhārti-nipīḍitāṅgam [235]"},{"class":"b54","text":" (Brahma-saṁhitā)"},{"class":"b71","text":" “[The Lord:] ‘Those who hear about the various results attained by chanting My Name but have no faith in them and think them to be exaggeration—I throw such persons into the dark, troublesome material world after subjecting them to a myriad of miseries.’”"},{"class":"b178","text":" শ্রীশ্রীপ্রেমবিবর্ত্ত সমাপ্ত"},{"class":"b73","text":" śrī-śrī prema-vivarta samāpta"},{"class":"b65","text":" Thus ends <span class=\\"e3\\">Śrī Śrī Prema-vivarta</span>."}]},{"title":"The Ten Offences to the Holy Name","paragraphs":[{"class":"b46","text":"\\r"},{"class":"b47","text":" The Ten Offences <br />to the Holy Name"},{"class":"b42","text":" Summarised here on the basis of the verses in <br /><span class=\\"e3\\">Śrī Padma-purāṇa</span>* discussed in chapter nineteen."},{"class":"b50","text":" (1) Criticising sādhus."},{"class":"b50","text":" (2a) Considering Śiva or other gods to be independent of Kṛṣṇa."},{"class":"b50","text":" (2b) Considering Kṛṣṇa’s Name, Form, Qualities, or Pastimes to be distinct from Him."},{"class":"b50","text":" (3) Disobeying Śrī Guru."},{"class":"b50","text":" (4) Criticising the scriptures."},{"class":"b50","text":" (5) Considering the glories of the Name exaggerated praise."},{"class":"b50","text":" (6) Considering the Name imaginary."},{"class":"b50","text":" (7) Using the Name as a means to absolve oneself of sin."},{"class":"b50","text":" (8) Considering chanting the Name equivalent to pious worldly activities."},{"class":"b50","text":" (9) Instructing faithless persons in chanting the Name."},{"class":"b50","text":" (10) Remaining devoid of love for the Name and engrossed in the mentality of ‘I’ and ‘mine’ even after hearing the glories of the Holy Name."},{"class":"b55","text":" *In some editions of <span class=\\"e3\\">Śrī Padma-purāṇa</span>, the verses are found in chapter forty-eight of the Svarga-khaṇḍa and in other editions in chapter twenty-five of the Brahma-khaṇḍa."}]},{"title":"Glossary","paragraphs":[{"class":"b46","text":"\\r"},{"class":"b47","text":" Glossary"},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Āchārya</span> one who understands the purport of the scriptures, teaches it to others, and personally practises it."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Achyuta-gotra</span> ‘lit. the family of the Lord’. Vaiṣṇavas conceive of themselves in this way because they do not identify themselves with their paternal ancestry, or gotra. The name <span class=\\"e3\\">Achyuta</span> signifies ‘He who is infallible and inexhaustible’."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Aditi</span> the eldest daughter of Dakṣa, wife of Kaśyapa Muni, and mother of the twelve Ādityas: the eleven principal demigods—Sūrya, Aryamā, Pūṣā, Tvaṣṭā, Savitā, Bhaga, Dhātā, Vidhātā, Varuṇa, Mitra, and Indra—and Śrī Vāmandev, Lord Viṣṇu’s Avatār as a dwarf brāhmaṇ."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Advaita Āchārya</span> a principal associate of Śrīman Mahāprabhu and member of the Pañcha Tattva who participated in countless Pastimes of the Lord and played the role of inviting the Lord to descend to the earth. He is the Avatār of Mahāviṣṇu and Sadāśiva in the Pastimes of Śrīman Mahāprabhu."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Āgama</span> lit. ‘that which has come down’; scriptures spoken by Lord Śiva to Pārvatī Devī that describe creation, destruction, worship of deities, preparatory rites, methods of meditation, and other subjects."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Ajāmil</span> a fallen brāhmaṇ who at the time of death, while calling out to his son named Nārāyaṇ, happened to remember Lord Viṣṇu Himself and was thus protected by the attendants of Lord Viṣṇu from being taken to hell by the attendants of Yamarāj."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Anantadev (Ananta Śeṣa)</span> a partial Avatār of Lord Balarām in the form of a serpent who holds the planets on His innumerable heads and chants the glories of the Lord with his innumerable mouths. He also assumes the forms of all the paraphernalia required for the Lord’s service, such as the Lord’s umbrella, slippers, bed, pillow, clothing, resting chair, house, sacred thread, and throne. Because He serves the Lord in innumerable ways, He is known as ‘Ananta’ (‘Unending’), and because He reaches the ultimate limit of serving the Lord, He is known as ‘Śeṣa’ (‘the end’)."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">aparādha</span> an offence; an action that is contrary to the rules, principles, or mood of devotion to the Lord; an action that displeases the Lord; imperfect worship (apakṛṣṭa-ārādhana)."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">aprākṛta</span> lit. ‘not mundane’; supramundane, divine, spiritual; part of, or related to, the highest plane of spiritual existence, the land of Lord Kṛṣṇa’s Pastimes, which at times resembles the mundane world but is nevertheless ‘not mundane’."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">āśram</span> lit. ‘no fatigue’; a shelter; a residence where people practise spiritual life; the hermitage of a sage or guru; any of the four social orders: brahmacharya, gṛhastha, vānaprastha, and sannyās. Brahmachārīs are students whose duty is service to Śrī Guru; gṛhasthas are householders whose duty is maintaining others and performing worship; vānaprasthas are retired householders whose duty is performing austerities and realising the self; and sannyāsīs are renunciants whose duty is equanimity and nonviolence."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">aṣṭāṅga-yoga</span> the eightfold path of yoga practice taught by Patañjali comprised of rules for behaviour, codes of conduct, postures, breath regulation, restraint of the senses, concentration, meditation, and trance. Aṣṭāṅga-yoga is the dharma of the Age of Satya and the primary means to attain realisation of the Supersoul. It is impractical in the Age of Kali, though modified forms of it are practised at present as a means to pursue health, enjoyment, supernatural powers (siddhis), and impersonal liberation (sāyujya-mukti)."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Avatār</span> lit. ‘one who crosses down’; a form or role assumed by the Lord or one of His devotees when they descend from the spiritual world to the material world. In general, the Lord has six types of Avatārs: Puruṣa-avatārs (who maintain the creation), Līlā-avatārs (who perform special Pastimes), Guṇa-avatārs (who regulate the modes of material nature), Manvantara-avatārs (the fathers of mankind), Yuga-avatārs (who establish the dharma for each age), and Śaktyāveśa-avatārs (souls who are empowered to perform particular functions)."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">ātmā</span> the self, esp. the eternal soul. According to context, <span class=\\"e3\\">ātmā</span> may also refer to the Absolute (Brahma), the body, the mind, endeavour, steadiness, intelligence, or nature. As a name of the Supreme Lord, <span class=\\"e3\\">Ātmā</span> signifies ‘He who is all-pervasive and the source of everything’. See <span class=\\"e3\\">Supersoul</span>."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Balarām (Baladev)</span> the elder brother of Lord Kṛṣṇa; the first expansion of Kṛṣṇa; the source of Lord Nārāyaṇ and all other Avatārs. He appears as Śrī Nityānanda Prabhu in the Pastimes of Śrīman Mahāprabhu."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">banyan</span> <span class=\\"e3\\">Ficus benghalensis</span>; a sacred tree in the fig family whose branches produce aerial roots that expand into accessory trunks and sometimes span across acres in this manner. Banyan trees are found through the abodes of Lord Śrī Kṛṣṇa and Śrīman Mahāprabhu."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e12\\">Bhagavad-gītā</span> lit. ‘the Lord’s song’; Lord Kṛṣṇa’s guidance to the warrior Arjuna just prior to the Battle of Kurukṣetra, which appears in the <span class=\\"e3\\">Mahābhārata</span> compiled by Vedavyās. Within <span class=\\"e3\\">Bhagavad-gītā</span>, the soul, the Lord, reincarnation, action, knowledge, sacrifice, purity, devotion and surrender to the Lord are all clearly and concisely explained. <span class=\\"e3\\">Bhagavad-gītā</span> is thus renowned as the essential primary scripture for all spiritual practitioners."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Bilvamaṅgal Ṭhākur (Līlāśuka)</span> the author of <span class=\\"e3\\">Śrī Kṛṣṇa-karṇāmṛta</span>, a compilation of poems describing Śrī Kṛṣṇa’s madhura-rasa Pastimes which was greatly appreciated by Śrīman Mahāprabhu. Although he was a brāhmaṇ and scholar, Bilvamaṅgal once risked his life to meet with a prostitute in the middle of the night during a violent storm. After being admonished by the prostitute when he arrived, Bilvamaṅgal had an epiphany, and the next morning he went straight to the āśram of Somagiri, a renowned Vaiṣṇava in the lineage of Viṣṇu Swāmī, and took initiation. He stayed with his Guru for some time and began to compose poetry about Lord Kṛṣṇa. When Somagiri saw this, he gave him the name Līlāśuka (‘parrot of the Lord’s Pastimes’) and soon after conferred sannyās upon him. Bilvamaṅgal later departed for Śrī Vṛndāvan Dhām and spent the rest of his life there absorbed in serving the Lord and composing poetry describing His Pastimes."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Brahma (Brahman)</span> (1) the Absolute; a Name for the Supreme Lord which means, “<span class=\\"e3\\">Bṛhatvāt bṛhaṇatvāt iti Brahma</span>: He who is the greatest and always becoming greater”; (2) the bodily effulgence of the Supreme Lord; the infinite expanse of spiritual energy which makes up, surrounds, and pervades all living beings and all planes of existence."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Brahmā</span> the first being in the material universe, who is considered both self-born and the son of Lord Viṣṇu. Brahmā performs a variety of duties: creating all life forms within the material world using the material elements manifested by the energy of the Supreme Lord; regulating the mode of passion within the material world; revealing the Vedas to the ṛṣis; performing sacrifices for the satisfaction of the Supreme Lord; and overseeing the affairs of the demigods, the sages, and human beings. ‘Brahmā’ is a post occupied by a soul in each material universe, and each material universe manifests and dissolves with his birth and death."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">brāhmaṇ (brahmin)</span> lit. ‘knower of Brahma’; one who, as a result of realisation of Brahma, is endowed with twelve qualities: virtuousness, truthfulness, self-control, austerity, non-enviousness, humility, tolerance, non-maliciousness, expertise in sacrifice, charitableness, steadiness, and learning. One is not a brāhmaṇ simply by being born as the son of a brāhmaṇ; one must have the appropriate qualities and behaviour."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Chaitanya</span> lit. ‘consciousness’; a short name for Śrī Chaitanya Mahāprabhu."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Chaitanya Mahāprabhu (Śrī)</span> the Supreme Personality of Godhead; the combined form of Śrī Śrī Rādhā-Kṛṣṇa; the Absolute in His aspect as a devotee of Himself; the origin of all Avatārs, manifestations, and energies. He appeared on earth in the land of Bengal with His associates and divine abode (1486–1534) to spread prema-dharma, the religion of divine love, through Nām-saṅkīrtan, the chanting of the Lord’s Holy Names, and He is renowned for His compassion. He is also known as Nimāi, Viśvambhar, Gaurāṅga, Gaurahari, and Gaurasundar, amongst other names."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Chaṇḍī Dās</span> a pure devotee of Lord Kṛṣṇa who appeared at the beginning of the 15th century in a family of brāhmaṇs within the Birbhum district of West Bengal. His poetry describing the Pastimes of Śrī Śrī Rādhā-Kṛṣṇa is very dear to Śrīman Mahāprabhu."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Chāndrāyaṇ-vrata</span> a penance performed by eating only fifteen mouthfuls of food on the full-moon day, reducing the amount taken each day by one mouthful until the new moon, and then increasing the amount by one mouthful each day until the next full moon."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">dal</span> split pulses, esp. varieties of lentils."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">daśa-karma</span> ten rites performed throughout a person’s lifetime that are meant to purify them of sin and produce merits leading to a prosperous future. These include the rites performed when someone is given a name, when they begin their education, when they are married, and when they pass away."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">dharma</span> nature; inherent quality; religion; duty; occupation; law. In its purest sense, <span class=\\"e3\\">dharma</span> denotes the eternal service of the Supreme Lord."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Durvāsā Muni</span> a partial avatār of Lord Śiva who appeared as the son of Atri and Anasūya, and brother of Dattātreya; a powerful sage renowned for both his curses and boons. He plays a catalytic role in various Pastimes of Lord Kṛṣṇa and His Avatārs."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Dvāpar-yuga</span> the third of the four ages that the universe cycles through seventy-one times during each day of Brahmā. Dvāpar-yuga lasts approx. 864,000 years. The last Dvāpar-yuga ended about five thousand years ago, just after the Battle of Kurukṣetra and Lord Kṛṣṇa’s withdrawal from this world."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Dvārakā</span> the eternal abode of Lord Kṛṣṇa situated on the bank of the ocean, where He presides as the king of the Yadu dynasty. Dvārakā exists in the spiritual world in the lower portion of Goloka. When Lord Kṛṣṇa descended to the earth, Dvārakā manifested on an island just off the west coast of India in modern-day Gujarat."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">dvija</span> lit. ‘twice born’; an alternative name for a brāhmaṇ, drawn from the idea that receiving initiation into the Brahma gāyatrī mantra is a second birth."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Ekādaśī</span> the eleventh day of each lunar fortnight; the day during each fortnight that the Vaiṣṇavas fast and engage more deeply in devotional activities. Śrīman Mahāprabhu instructed that Ekādaśī should be observed only on days when the eleventh phase of the moon has begun before dawn (96 minutes before sunrise). Such days are known as Śuddhā Ekādaśī (‘pure Ekādaśī’)."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Gadādhar Paṇḍit</span> the Avatār of Śrīmatī Rādhārāṇī in Śrīman Mahāprabhu’s Pastimes; the most intimate devotee of Śrīman Mahāprabhu; a member of the Pañcha Tattva. He was a lifelong companion of the Lord who in particular served the Lord during His final Pastimes by reciting <span class=\\"e3\\">Śrīmad Bhāgavatam</span>. His humility, service, and love for the Lord are unparalleled."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Gadāi</span> a short name for Gadādhar Paṇḍit."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Gādigāchhā</span> a village within Godrumadwīp known at present as Svarūpgañj."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Gaṅgā</span> the sacred river Ganges; the consort of the Supreme Lord who serves Him in the form of a river. After washing the lotus feet of Lord Viṣṇu and filling the Causal Ocean, the Gaṅgā enters this material universe, flows through the heavenly planets, and descends to the earth after her fall is broken by Lord Śiva. From the Himalayas, the Gaṅgā flows across India into the Bay of Bengal, purifying and blessing all souls with devotion to the Lord."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Gauḍa Maṇḍal</span> lit. ‘the district of gur (a type of unrefined sugar)’; the land of sweetness: the land of Śrīman Mahāprabhu’s eternal Pastimes, which descended to the earth with the Lord. At present, Gauḍa Maṇḍal is a district in central West Bengal that is renowned for Vaiṣṇavism."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Gaura</span> lit. ‘gold’; a name of Śrīman Mahāprabhu that refers to His golden complexion."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Gaurachā̐d</span> lit. ‘golden moon’, a name of Śrīman Mahāprabhu."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Gaurahari</span> lit. ‘golden Lord’, a name of Śrīman Mahāprabhu."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Gaurāṅga</span> lit. ‘golden-formed’, a name of Śrīman Mahāprabhu."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Giridhārī</span> lit. ‘mountain holder’; a name of Lord Kṛṣṇa drawn from His Pastime of lifting Govardhan Hill."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Gokula</span> lit. ‘cow-herd’ or ‘cow-quarters’; the homeland of Lord Kṛṣṇa; the name of the village in Mahāvan where Kṛṣṇa lives as a boy before moving to Nanda Grām. <span class=\\"e3\\">Gokula</span> often refers to the abode of Kṛṣṇa revealed in the material world as opposed to Goloka, the abode of Kṛṣṇa in the spiritual world."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Goloka</span> lit. ‘cow-land’; the name of the eternal, spiritual abode of Kṛṣṇa, the topmost plane within the spiritual world where the Lord’s sweetest Pastimes take place. It contains three divisions: Dvārakā, Mathurā, and Vṛndāvan."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">gopa</span> lit. ‘maintainer of cows’; a cowherd boy or man; an inhabitant of Vṛndāvan and associate of Lord Kṛṣṇa in His eternal abode and Pastimes. Gopas serve Kṛṣṇa as servants (in dāsya-rasa), friends (in sakhya-rasa), and affectionate guardians (in vātsalya-rasa)."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">gopī</span> lit. ‘female maintainer of cows’; a cowherd girl or woman; an inhabitant of Vṛndāvan and associate of Kṛṣṇa in His eternal abode and Pastimes. Gopīs serve Kṛṣṇa as affectionate guardians (in vātsalya-rasa) or paramours (in parakīya-madhura-rasa). They are the greatest devotees of Lord Kṛṣṇa and the bodily expansions of Śrīmatī Rādhārāṇī."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Gopīnāth Āchārya</span> a highly respected brāhmaṇ of Nabadwīp who was the brother-in-law of Sārvabhauma Bhaṭṭāchārya. He hosted Śrīla Īśvara Purī at his home and participated in many of Śrīman Mahāprabhu’s Pastimes in Nadia. Gopīnāth Āchārya later moved to Jagannāth Purī and is best known for the convincing remarks he made to Sārvabhauma Bhaṭṭāchārya about the divinity of Śrīman Mahāprabhu when the Lord first arrived in Purī."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Gorā</span> lit. ‘gold’; a Name of Śrīman Mahāprabhu."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Gorāchā̐d</span> lit. ‘golden moon’, a name of Śrīman Mahāprabhu."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Govinda</span> lit. <span class=\\"e3\\">vinda</span>, possessor, of <span class=\\"e3\\">go</span>, which can mean cows, Vedas, senses, world, and other things; a name of Lord Kṛṣṇa given to him by Indra after He lifted Govardhan Hill."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Govinda Ghoṣ</span> an eternal associate of the Lord who appeared in Agradwīp, West Bengal. He and his two younger brothers, Vāsudev Ghoṣ and Mādhava Ghoṣ, were renowned kīrtanīyās."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Guṇḍichā</span> a Temple about two miles northeast of the Temple of Lord Jagannāth in Purī that is said to be named after the wife of Indradyumna Mahārāj, the King of Purī who built both of the Temples. Śrīman Mahāprabhu saw the Guṇḍichā Temple as a form of Vṛndāvan and would personally clean the Temple each year on the day prior to the Ratha Yātrā, the festival in which Kṛṣṇa, in the form of Lord Jagannāth, travels to Guṇḍichā as a way of fulfilling the devotees’ desire for Him to return to Vṛndāvan from Dvārakā. The yearly cleansing of the Guṇḍichā Temple demonstrates the necessity of purifying the heart so that the Lord can be received and served within it."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Guru</span> lit. ‘heavy’; master; teacher; he who dispels darkness; the form the Supreme Lord assumes to distribute divine knowledge."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Hari</span> lit. ‘He who takes away’; the Supreme Lord."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Haribol</span> lit. ‘chant ‘Hari’’; ‘chant the Name of the Lord’."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Haridās Ṭhākur</span> the close associate of Śrīman Mahāprabhu who is renowned as the foremost Āchārya of chanting the Holy Name (the Nāmāchārya). After Lord Brahmā offended Lord Kṛṣṇa in Vṛndāvan and performed austerities in Antardwīp, Lord Kṛṣṇa blessed him to accept the form of an outcast to fulfil his desire to humbly chant the Lord’s Name and serve in the Lord’s association. He thus became Haridās Ṭhākur."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Hari-vāsar</span> lit. ‘the Lord’s day’; days throughout the year on which Vaiṣṇavas fast and engage more deeply in devotional activities. Such days include pure Ekādaśīs, special Dvādaśīs, and appearance days of the Lord, such as Janmāṣṭamī and Gaura Pūrṇimā."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">hlādinī-śakti</span> lit. ‘pleasing energy’; the pleasure potency of the Supreme Lord; the energy by which the Lord feels pleasure and gives pleasure to all souls. The hlādinī-śakti appears to conditioned souls as sense pleasure, to liberated souls as the pleasure of Brahma, and to souls devoted to the Lord as rasa. The essence of the hlādinī-śakti is divine love, and its ultimate personification is Śrīmatī Rādhārāṇī."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Jagannāth</span> lit. ‘Lord of the universe’; the renowned Deity of the Supreme Lord situated in Śrī Puruṣottam Dhām in Odisha; a peculiar form Lord Kṛṣṇa assumes when He is overwhelmed by feelings of separation from the devotees of Vṛndāvan."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Jagannāth Miśra</span> the father of Śrīman Mahāprabhu. He is Nanda Mahārāj in the Pastimes of Lord Kṛṣṇa."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Jagannāth Purī</span> the name of the city on the bank of the Indian ocean in Odisha where Lord Jagannāth resides."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Jagannāth Vallabha garden</span> a garden near the Guṇḍichā Temple in Jagannāth Purī that Lord Jagannāth visits throughout the year to perform various Pastimes. Śrīman Mahāprabhu and His devotees also performed numerous Pastimes here."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">japa</span> recitation of a mantra, either by mentally chanting it, murmuring it, or speaking it aloud. Japa is typically counted on a mālā and done a set number of times."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Jayadev Goswāmī</span> the author of <span class=\\"e3\\">Śrī Gīta-govinda</span>; a renowned Vaiṣṇava poet whose writings were deeply appreciated by Śrīman Mahāprabhu and His associates, as well as Lord Jagannāth and the Vaiṣṇavas throughout the ages."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">jñān</span> knowledge; consciousness; calculation; speculation; the pursuit of liberation; knowledge of the soul; knowledge of Brahma; knowledge of the Supreme Lord, His energies, and their relationships (sambandha-jñān)."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">jñāna-yoga</span> the pursuit of liberation through the cultivation of knowledge."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">jñānī</span> a practitioner of jñāna-yoga; a seeker of liberation; a person of great learning."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">kachu śāk</span> a dish made from the corms and leaves of taro plants."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Kali</span> lit. ‘the personification of quarrel’; the personification of the current age, who was allotted five places to reside by Mahārāj Parīkṣit: those of intoxication, illicit sex, slaughter, money, and gaming (gambling, dice, cards, chess, etc. (as explained by Śrīla Bhakti Siddhānta Saraswatī Ṭhākur in his commentary on SB 1.17.38))."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Kali-yuga</span> the fourth (and current) of the four ages of the material universe (Satya, Tretā, Dvāpar, and Kali). Known as the age of quarrel and comparable to a dark winter, Kali-yuga lasts 427,000 years and began about 5,000 years ago, just after the battle of Kurukṣetra and the disappearance of Lord Kṛṣṇa. Kali-yuga is characterised by degradation of the fundamental virtues—honesty, cleanliness, compassion, and austerity—and a predominance of gaming, intoxication, illicit sex, slaughter, and hoarding of wealth. It is nonetheless considered the most desirable of all ages by the sages and scriptures because during that time the prescribed means to serve the Lord—chanting His Name—is the easiest, the most purifying, and the most joyful of all spiritual practices."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Kāmyavan</span> the fourth of the twelve forests of Vraja, located on the western side of the Dhām."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">karma</span> action; reactions to previous actions; worldly action; action performed to attain its fruit; action performed as a profession or duty; action performed according to scriptural directives; destiny."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">karma-yoga</span> the pursuit of enjoyment, both in the earthly and heavenly planes, by practising selfless action according to the directives in the scriptures; propitiating the Lord and the demigods by performing one’s duty, acting virtuously, being charitable, engaging in sacrifices, conducting ceremonies, and offering worship."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">karmī</span> a practitioner of karma-yoga; a worker; a materialistic person."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Kāśī Miśra</span> the head priest at the Temple of Lord Jagannāth in whose home Śrīman Mahāprabhu resided during His Pastimes in Jagannāth Purī."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Kavi Karṇapūr</span> the youngest son of Śivānanda Sen, who, by the special grace of Śrīman Mahāprabhu, was able to compose Sanskrit poetry about Lord Kṛṣṇa at just seven years of age. In his maturity, he composed numerous Sanskrit texts describing the Pastimes of Lord Kṛṣṇa, Śrīman Mahāprabhu, and Their associates."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">kīrtan</span> glorification; chanting, speaking, writing, and so on of the Names, Forms, Qualities, and Pastimes of the Supreme Lord and His associates; the spiritual practice prescribed for the Age of Kali; the best of all practices of devotion."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Kṛṣṇa</span> the Supreme Personality of Godhead; He who is all-attractive (kṛṣ) and gives ecstasy (ṇa); the original Name and form of the Supreme Lord in which He has unparalleled qualities and Pastimes."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Kṛṣṇa Chaitanya</span> lit. ‘Kṛṣṇa consciousness’; the sannyās name of Śrīman Mahāprabhu."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">kṣīr</span> (1) condensed milk; (2) sweet rice pudding."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">līlā</span> Pastimes; the transcendental activities of the Supreme Lord and His devotees; their eternal play of love."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">mahāmantra</span> lit. ‘supreme mantra’; the Hare Kṛṣṇa mahāmantra: Hare Kṛṣṇa Hare Kṛṣṇa Kṛṣṇa Kṛṣṇa Hare Hare, Hare Rāma Hare Rāma Rāma Rāma Hare Hare. Śrīman Mahāprabhu established the chanting of this mantra as the primary way to practise the religion of the Age of Kali: chanting the Name of the Lord."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">mahāmāyā</span> lit. ‘great illusion’; the material world; the energy of the Supreme Lord known as His illusory energy, material energy, and external energy; another name of the goddess of illusion, Māyā Devī."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Mahāprabhu</span> lit. ‘supreme master’; a Name of Śrī Kṛṣṇa Chaitanya, prophesied in the <span class=\\"e3\\">Muṇḍaka-upaniṣad</span>."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">mahāprasād</span> lit. ‘great kindness’; the remnants of offerings made to the Lord or Śrī Guru, esp. the remnants of the foods or other articles that were physically consumed by them or placed directly before them."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">mālā</span> a string of beads used for chanting japa, typically consisting of 108 beads; a garland; a necklace."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">mānachāki</span> a dish made from ground taro."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">mantra</span> lit. ‘that which delivers by being meditated upon’; a hymn, prayer, instruction, incantation, or principle composed in concise and metric Sanskrit, typically originating from a Vedic scripture."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">markaṭa-vairāgya</span> lit. ‘monkey renunciation’; outwardly presenting oneself as a renunciant while privately pursuing material enjoyment. Such behaviour is comparable to that of a monkey, who outwardly lives like a renunciant (wears no clothes, has no house, begs for food), but inwardly seeks only food, comfort, and the opposite sex."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">māyā</span> lit. ‘that which is not’; illusion; forgetfulness of the Lord and the self; identification with a material body and attachment to its paraphernalia."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Māyā Devī</span> the goddess of illusion, who serves the Supreme Lord by detaining souls who are averse to the Lord within the material world and subjecting them to the law of karma. Her purpose is to completely remove all forms of aversion to the Lord from the hearts of the conditioned souls. When souls fully surrender to the Lord and become indifferent to her temptations, she considers her purpose fulfilled and happily releases them. She is the consort of Lord Śiva and known by numerous names, such as Pārvatī, Durgā, and Kālī."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Māyāpur</span> the village at the centre of Śrī Nabadwīp Dhām on the island of Antardwīp where Śrīman Mahāprabhu takes birth and resides during His youth."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">māyāvād</span> lit. ‘illusionism’; the theory that the eternal spiritual existence of the Lord, His energies, His personal forms, His abodes, the souls (devotees of the Lord), and devotion to the Lord are all an illusion. Māyāvād is the ultimate antithesis of Vaiṣṇavism and claims that the highest aim in life is to merge into Brahma. Māyāvād was propagated by Lord Śiva in the form of Śaṅkar Āchārya on the order of Lord Kṛṣṇa to attract dissenting persons back to the Vedic scriptures. Māyāvād and ideas similar to it are also known as Advaitavād, Vivartavād, and Nirviśeṣavād."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">mṛdaṅga</span> lit. ‘clay body’; the double-headed drum prescribed by Śrīman Mahāprabhu for Hari-nām-saṅkīrtan."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">mukti</span> liberation; liberation from material existence; liberation from ignorance of the self, the Lord, and their relationship; realisation of one’s true nature as an eternal servant of the Lord. The scriptures describe five types of liberation: sālokya (residing in the Lord’s abode), sārūpya (having a form like the Lord’s), sārṣṭi (having opulence like the Lord’s), sāmīpya (having the association of the Lord), and sāyujya (absorption into the body or effulgence of the Lord). Vaiṣṇavas may accept the first four of these for the sake of service to the Lord, but they never accept sāyujya-mukti, in which knowledge, the object of knowledge, and the knower (jñān, jñeya, and jñātā) are all demolished. Such liberation is sought by jñānīs and is often awarded to demons who attack the Supreme Lord or His devotees, but devotees shun it because it denies one the opportunity to serve the Lord eternally."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Nabadwīp</span> lit. ‘nine islands’; the eternal abode of Śrīman Mahāprabhu, nondifferent from Śrī Vṛndāvan, which He brought with Him to the earth during His Pastimes here. The region known as Nabadwīp is the centre of Śrī Gauḍa Maṇḍal and is divided by tributaries of the Ganges, Yamunā, Saraswatī, and other sacred rivers into nine islands—Sīmantadwīp, Godrumadwīp, Madhyadwīp, Koladwīp, Ṛtudwīp, Jahnudwīp, Modadrumadwīp, Rudradwīp, and Antardwīp. At present, <span class=\\"e3\\">Nabadwīp</span> also refers to the town on the western bank of the Ganges within Koladwīp in West Bengal, India."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Nadia</span> the land of Śrīman Mahāprabhu’s eternal Pastimes. <span class=\\"e3\\">Nadia</span> once referred specifically to the town of Nabadwīp, but at present refers to the district in which Nabadwīp is located."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Nāma</span> lit. ‘name’; the Name of the Supreme Lord; the personal form of the Lord as His Name, nondifferent from the Lord Himself. The Name is chanted in three forms within the material world: (1) Śuddha-nām, as the pure Name Himself, (2) Nāmābhās, as a semblance of the Name, and (3) Nāmāparādha, a form of the Name covered by offences."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Nāmābhās</span> lit. ‘a semblance of the Name’; chanting the Name impurely. Nāmābhās is comparable to a fog of ignorance and to clouds made up of selfish desires, offences, and weakness of heart. These cover the soul so that the light of the pure Name, comparable to a bright sun, is only faintly visible. There are four types of Nāmābhās listed in order from least to most gross (SB: 6.2.14): (1) saṅketa, indirect chanting, as in the case of Ajāmil, who called out to his son named Nārāyaṇ, or in the case of persons who speak other languages and utter the syllables of the Name with intentions unrelated to the Lord; (2) parihāsa, chanting jokingly, as in the case of the non-Hindus who jokingly chanted the Name during the lunar eclipse at the time of Śrīman Mahāprabhu’s appearance; (3) stobha, chanting mnemonically, as in the case of <span class=\\"e3\\">Śrī Hari-nāmāmṛta-vyākaraṇa</span>, in which the Names of the Lord are used as part of a system of grammatical terminology, and (4) helā, chanting neglectfully, that is, without respect or affection but also without disdain, as in the case of calling out the Name to shake off lethargy. Nāmābhās can give the soul piety, wealth, enjoyment, freedom from active and inactive karmic reactions, deliverance from hell, liberation, and sukṛti. It cannot, however, give the soul divine love for Kṛṣṇa. Nāmābhās, as a semblance of the Name, is further understood to be either a shadow of the Name, as in the case of those who chant the Name in the four ways mentioned above, or a reflection of the Name, as in the case of māyāvādīs or materialists who intentionally chant the Name with a conception and purpose contrary to the soul’s nature of being an eternal servant of Kṛṣṇa. The benefits of Nāmābhās listed above apply only to those who chant the shadow form of the Name; those who chant the reflected form make offences to the Name and are not benefitted by their practices."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Nārad (Devarṣi Nārad)</span> a Śaktyāveś-avatār of the Lord delegated to travel throughout the material and spiritual worlds as a devotee sage, constantly chanting the Lord’s glories to the music of his vīnā. He takes part in countless Pastimes of the Lord in many of the Lord’s appearances in the world and gives guidance to numerous sages, kings, and devotees throughout the ages."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Nārāyaṇ</span> lit. ‘the shelter of all beings’; the Lord of Śrī Vaikuṇṭha Dhām; the four-armed form of the Lord who presides over His eternal majestic abode of awe-inspired worship. Nārāyaṇ is an expansion of Śrī Balarām and the source of Mahāviṣṇu and all the Avatārs of the Lord in the material world."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">neem</span> <span class=\\"e3\\">Azadirachta indica</span>; margosa; referred to as <span class=\\"e3\\">nimba</span> in the scriptures."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Nimāi</span> a name given to Śrīman Mahāprabhu at His birth because He was born under a neem tree and because the name <span class=\\"e3\\">Nimāi</span>, like neem itself, protects one from ill fate."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Nitāi, Nityānanda</span> a principal associate of Śrīman Mahāprabhu and member of the Pañcha Tattva who is the first expansion of the Lord Himself. He is Lord Balarām in the Pastimes of Lord Kṛṣṇa and the origin of Lord Nārāyaṇ, Lord Viṣṇu, Lord Śeṣa, and all other Avatārs of the Lord. As the embodiment of unconditional mercy, He is always joyful and eager to engage souls, even the most fallen, in the service of Śrīman Mahāprabhu."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Nṛsiṁhānanda</span> an eternal associate of Śrīman Mahāprabhu who appeared in the village of Piyārīgañj near Kalna. The Lord was very pleased with the service Nṛsiṁhānanda performed in meditation, and at times the Lord personally appeared in Nṛsiṁhānanda’s heart, spoke to people through his mouth, and exhibited ecstasy in his body."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">pānā</span> sherbet; a beverage typically prepared from fruit juices with added sugar, salt, or spices."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">pāpa</span> sin; inauspicious karma; actions that produce suffering. Such actions may be divided into the following categories: (1) violence, (2) cruelty, (3) duplicity, (4) madness, (5) falsity, (6) disobeying superiors, (7) covetousness, (8) selfishness, (9) impurity, (10) uncivil behaviour, and (11) destructive behaviour. The consequences of such actions are also called <span class=\\"e3\\">pāpa</span> and exist in three forms: aprārabdha, inactive, prārabdha, active, and bīja, seed. Inactive sin refers to sin that will take effect in future births, active sin refers to sin that will effect in this birth, and the seed form of sin refers to the desire to commit sin. Devotion can destroy all three forms of pāpa, as well as their root cause, avidyā, ignorance, misunderstanding of the self."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Pāpa-puruṣ</span> lit. ‘personification of sin’; the <span class=\\"e3\\">Padma-purāṇa</span> (7.22.1–52) explains that the Lord gave the Pāpa-puruṣ the special dispensation to take shelter in grains on the day of Ekādaśī, and thus anyone who consumes grains on Ekādaśī becomes implicated in the sum total of all sins. While the true purpose of observing Ekādaśī is endeavouring to satisfy the Lord without any selfish motivation of being freed from sin, it is also Śrīman Mahāprabhu’s order that everyone fast from grains on Ekādaśī and avoid contact with the Pāpa-puruṣ."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">paramānna</span> lit. ‘great rice’; sweet rice pudding; rice cooked in milk with sugar."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">paṭol</span> pointed gourd; <span class=\\"e3\\">trichosanthes dioica</span>."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">pīṭhā (piṭhe)</span> a general term for speciality items such as pancakes, doughnuts, steamed cakes, and dumplings. They are typically sweet, made with rice flour, and filled with date syrup and coconut, though there are countless varieties."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Prabhu</span> master; lord. <span class=\\"e3\\">Prabhu</span> was traditionally used as a title for Śrī Guru and for the Supreme Lord (esp. Mahāprabhu, Nityānanda Prabhu, and Advaita Prabhu). Śrīla Bhakti Siddhānta Saraswatī Ṭhākur started the practice of referring to his disciples as <span class=\\"e3\\">Prabhu</span> because he saw them as extensions of his Gurudev, and he also encouraged his disciples to adopt this practice. Thus <span class=\\"e3\\">Prabhu</span> is used within the Sāraswat Gauḍīya–Vaiṣṇava sampradāya as a respectful address for initiated, male devotees of all ages, with the exception of sannyāsīs."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">prasād</span> lit. ‘grace, kindness’; the mercy of the Lord, Śrī Guru, and the Vaiṣṇavas; the remnants of offerings made to them, such as fragrances, flowers, and especially foods."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">prāyaśchitta</span> atonement for sin; the numerous penances prescribed in the scriptures—such as fasting, begging, and performing unusual austerities—to absolve oneself of sins. Such acts can remove the inauspicious karma that is produced by committing sin, but they cannot remove the desire or susceptibility to commit sin in the future, and they cannot absolve the soul of offences against the Lord’s Name or His devotees."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">prema</span> divine love; intense desire to please the Lord; the goal of life and perfection of the soul."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">phalgu-vairāgya</span> useless renunciation; rejecting as mundane anything that is favourable to the Lord’s service; making a show of detachment but internally pursing selfish ends, esp. liberation. The term comes from the appearance of the Phalgu River near Gaya in India which for part of the year appears to be a dry bed of sand but always has water running within it just below the surface."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Puruṣottam</span> lit. ‘the Supreme Person’; the Supreme Lord Kṛṣṇa; Lord Jagannāth."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Puruṣottam Āchārya</span> the name of Śrīla Svarūp Dāmodar Prabhu prior to his acceptance of sannyās."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Puruṣottam Kṣetra</span> the land of Lord Jagannāth; Jagannāth Purī and its surrounding area."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Rādhā (Rādhikā, Rādhārāṇī)</span> lit. ‘She whose worship is supreme’; Lord Kṛṣṇa’s eternal consort, the embodiment of the highest service and sacrifice to the Lord; the female aspect of the Supreme Absolute Truth."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Rādhā Kuṇḍa</span> the lake made by Śrīmatī Rādhārāṇī and Her companions beside Śyāma Kuṇḍa near Govardhan Hill; the site of Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa’s most confidential Pastimes; the most exalted holy place for all Rūpānuga Vaiṣṇavas."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Raghunāth Dās Goswāmī</span> a principal follower of Śrīman Mahāprabhu whose intense standard of service and renunciation greatly satisfied the Lord and deeply inspired all devotees. After receiving the blessings of Śrīman Nityānanda Prabhu in Bengal, he resided in Jagannāth Purī for the last sixteen years of Śrīman Mahāprabhu’s Pastimes as the personal assistant of Śrī Svarūp Dāmodar. He participated in many of the Lord’s confidential Pastimes, and his personal accounts of these Pastimes form the foundation of <span class=\\"e3\\">Śrī Chaitanya-charitāmṛta</span>. Raghunāth Dās eventually went to Vṛndāvan, found new life in the company of Śrī Rūpa and Śrī Sanātan, and spent his final days at Śrī Rādhā Kuṇḍa. He is revered within the Gauḍīya–Vaiṣṇava sampradāya as the Āchārya of prayojan-tattva, as he illuminated the highest attainment of the soul in the service of Śrīmatī Rādhāraṇī under the guidance of Śrī Rūpa Mañjarī."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Rāmānanda Rāy</span> the intimate associate of Śrīman Mahāprabhu whom the Lord regarded as His Guru in rāga-mārg service to Śrī Kṛṣṇa. Rāmānanda was the first to perceive the innermost identity of Śrīman Mahāprabhu—that of Śrī Śrī Rādhā-Kṛṣṇa combined—and the first to speak the essential teachings that the Lord descended to distribute to the world. He first met the Lord in South India while serving as the governor of the Godāvarī region, but at the Lord’s request he resigned and spent the rest of his life with the Lord in Jagannāth Purī, serving Him intimately during His later Pastimes by reciting verses that suited His intense feelings of separation for Kṛṣṇa. Śrīman Mahāprabhu praised his scholarship, worldly detachment, and expertise in rasa as unparalleled. He is Śrī Viśākhā Devī in the Pastimes of Śrī Śrī Rādhā-Kṛṣṇa and is held in the highest regard by all Gauḍīya–Vaiṣṇavas."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">rasa</span> pleasure; the inconceivable, wonderful substance tasted in the hearts of pure devotees; the dispositions in which souls serve the Supreme Lord, which are of five primary types: adoration, servitorship, friendship, affectionate guardianship, and paramour love."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Rāsa Dance</span> a style of dance performed by Lord Śrī Kṛṣṇa with the gopīs of Vṛndāvan which should never be imitated or imagined."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Śachī Devī</span> the mother of Śrīman Mahāprabhu. The Lord’s associates in Nadia often call her ‘Āi’, a non-Sanskrit vernacular title meaning ‘respectable lady’ or ‘mother’. She is Yaśodā Devī in the Pastimes of Lord Kṛṣṇa."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">sādhu</span> a holy man; one who is adherent to Truth."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">sāk</span> green leafy vegetables; cooked greens; a favourite preparation of Śrīman Mahāprabhu."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">śakti</span> energy, power; a name of the Supreme Lord’s consort or the consort of a demigod."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">saṁsāra</span> lit. ‘through motion’; transmigration; the perpetual cycle of repeated birth and death in which souls pass from one body to the next within the material world according to their desires, pushed by the forces of time, karma, and material nature. The soul may assume the form of an inanimate object, a plant, an animal, a human form, or a heavenly form such as that of god or sage. Souls wander indefinitely around this wheel of saṁsāra until they attain the association of souls who are engaged in the Lord’s service and surrender to the Lord. <span class=\\"e3\\">Saṁsāra</span> also connotes the material world itself, the range of experiences the soul undergoes within it, esp. suffering, and the pursuit of worldly happiness, esp. that of family life."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Sanātan Goswāmī</span> a principal follower of Śrīman Mahāprabhu and the elder brother of Śrīla Rūpa Goswāmī. He was shown the highest respect by everyone, including Śrīman Mahāprabhu Himself. According to the Lord’s instructions, he discovered lost holy places, re-established the worship of Deities, compiled numerous scriptures, and cared for the whole community of devotees in Vṛndāvan."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Sanat Kumār</span> lit. ‘eternal youth’; the eldest of the first four sons of Lord Brahmā. At the beginning of creation, he refused to obey Brahmā’s order to create progeny and instead engaged in the service of the Lord exclusively. He is revered as the founder of a number of spiritual lineages, and his teachings are recorded in many of the scriptures."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Śaṅkar</span> lit. ‘he who is beneficent’; a name of Lord Śiva."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">saṅkīrtan</span> congregational glorification of the Name, Form, Qualities, Pastimes, associates, and paraphernalia of the Lord; the prescribed religious practice for the Age of Kali."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">sāṅkhya</span> lit. ‘enumeration’; discrimination between spirit and matter, the self and the non-self; systematic analysis of the elements within the material creation. The Lord taught the process of sāṅkhya in various Avatārs, such as that of Kapiladev, as a means to understand the self, the creation, and the soul’s purpose within the creation to ultimately awaken devotion within the heart of the soul. Non-devotional and even atheistic forms of sāṅkhya are also practised by philosophers, of whom the most well-known is also (confusingly) named Kapila."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">sannyās</span> lit. ‘complete abandonment’; the renounced order of life; the fourth āśram in Vedic society; the practice of giving up selfish action and fully dedicating oneself to the Lord, primarily by preaching the principles of pure devotion. Formally, this entails celibacy, withdrawal from family, wearing the robes of a renunciant, and engaging one’s speech, thought, and action exclusively in the Lord’s service."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">sannyāsī</span> one who has accepted the order of sannyās."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Sārvabhauma Bhaṭṭāchārya (Vāsudev Sārvabhauma)</span> the most widely renowned scholar in India during the time of Śrīman Mahāprabhu. As an avatār of Bṛhaspati, he left his position in heaven and appeared on earth as a scholar to serve Śrīman Mahāprabhu in Jagannāth Purī."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Satyabhāmā</span> one of the principal queens of Lord Kṛṣṇa during His Pastimes in the city of Dvārakā."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Satya-yuga</span> the age of truth, which lasts 1,728,000 years and is characterised by honesty, austerity, and meditative devotion. Satya-yuga is the first of the four ages that cycle throughout the existence of the material universe (Satya, Tretā, Dvāpar, and Kali)."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Śaunaka</span> a renowned sage who led the sages assembled at Naimiṣ­āraṇya in hearing <span class=\\"e3\\">Śrīmad Bhāgavatam</span> narrated by Śrī Sūta Goswāmī."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Śikṣāṣṭakam</span> lit. ‘eight verses of instruction’; the only poem known to be composed by Śrīman Mahāprabhu Himself. Within it, all the Lord’s teachings are summarised in these eight verses describing the chanting of the Holy Name."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Śiva</span> lit. ‘the auspicious one’; a unique expansion of the Supreme Lord who performs numerous functions: regulating the mode of ignorance in the material world, cyclically destroying the material world, infusing the material world with souls, satisfying the desires for enjoyment and liberation of those who are averse to the Supreme Lord, supporting the demigods in their management of the material world, bearing the Ganges river on his head as she descends from Dhruvaloka, protecting the devotees of the Supreme Lord, and setting a paramount example of pure devotion to the Supreme Lord."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Śivānanda Sen</span> an exemplary householder devotee of Śrīman Mahāprabhu who on the order of the Lord took care of all the devotees each year during their pilgrimage to Jagannāth Purī from Bengal. He engaged his entire family and all his wealth in the Lord’s service and was a recipient of special affection from both Śrīman Mahāprabhu and Śrīman Nityānanda Prabhu."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">smārta</span> a follower of the smṛti scriptures, in particular, one who rigidly follows the codes of conduct and rules for worship given therein."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">smṛti</span> lit. ‘that which is remembered’; the scriptures compiled by Vedavyās and other sages that illuminate the śruti. These include the Purāṇas, Nīti-śāstras, Itihāsas, <span class=\\"e3\\">Mahābhārata</span>, <span class=\\"e3\\">Rāmāyaṇa</span>, and law books such as that of Manu."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Śrī Kṣetra</span> the land of Lord Jagannāth; Jagannāth Purī and its surrounding area."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e12\\">Śrīmad Bhāgavatam</span> the essence of all Vedic literature. Written by Śrīla Vyāsadev as the fruit of his meditation on the four verses spoken by Lord Kṛṣṇa to Lord Brahmā at the beginning of creation, <span class=\\"e3\\">Śrīmad Bhāgavatam</span> is Vyāsadev’s natural commentary on the <span class=\\"e3\\">Vedānta-sūtra</span>, the foremost of all the Purāṇas, and the conclusion of all the Vedic literatures. The text is comprised of 18,000 verses and explains ten subjects: (1) the creation: the manifestation of the material elements, (2) the sub-creation: the manifestation of the life-forms within the creation, (3) position: the Lord’s rule over the creation, (4) nourishment: the Lord’s mercy upon His devotees, (5) conditioning: the impressions created by actions, (6) the Manus: the establishment of proper dharma, (7) discussion of the Lord: narrations of the activities of the Lord’s Avatārs and Their devotees; (8) the destruction: the souls laying at rest (after the dissolution of the material elements), (9) liberation: realisation of the true self, and (10) the shelter: the Supreme Being. Śrī Chaitanya Mahāprabhu accepted <span class=\\"e3\\">Śrīmad Bhāgavatam</span> as the purest and most authoritative revelation of the Absolute as it describes the dharma of the paramahaṁsas, is dearmost to the Vaiṣṇavas, explains the highest engagement of liberated souls, establishes Lord Śrī Kṛṣṇa as the Supreme Personality of Godhead, and shows divine love for Him to be the ultimate attainment."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Śrīvās Ṭhākur</span> a principal associate of Śrīman Mahāprabhu and member of the Pañcha Tattva who lives near the Lord in Māyāpur and participates in countless Pastimes of the Lord. Śrīman Mahāprabhu is eternally present in his courtyard. There, the Lord performs kīrtan every night with His intimate associates and once revealed Himself as the Supreme Lord for twenty-one hours."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">śruti</span> lit. ‘that which is heard’; the Vedas, Upaniṣads, and other scriptures revealed to (heard by) the ṛṣis."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Śukadev </span> lit. ‘divine parrot’; a liberated soul from birth who appeared as the son of Vedavyās and spoke <span class=\\"e3\\">Śrīmad Bhāgavatam</span> in the assembly of Mahārāj Parīkṣit. His testimony serves as the principal evidence that the Pastimes of Lord Kṛṣṇa are supramundane and attract even the liberated souls."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">sukṛti</span> lit. ‘proper action’; merits; actions that lead to favourable future results. There are three types of sukṛti: those that lead to enjoyment, to liberation, and to devotion. Chiefly, <span class=\\"e3\\">sukṛti</span> refers to merits that lead the soul to devotion, in other words, to that which gives the soul the capacity to appreciate Truth and inspires the soul to seek the Absolute (<span class=\\"e3\\">puṇya</span> typically refers to merits that lead to enjoyment). Here, <span class=\\"e3\\">sukṛti</span> denotes service rendered knowingly or unknowingly to the Lord, that which is His own, or those who are dear to Him. The opportunity to render such service comes to the soul by good fortune and fructifies (typically over the course of a number of lifetimes) as association with sādhus, by whose grace the soul develops faith and progresses on the path of devotion."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Supersoul</span> standard English rendering of <span class=\\"e3\\">Paramātmā</span>; the all-pervading Soul who functions as the observer, permitter, maintainer, supporter, and supreme master of all beings in the material creation; the infinitesimal animating principle within every particle of material energy; the third Puruṣ-avatār Kṣīrodakaśāyī Viṣṇu."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Sūta Goswāmī</span> the disciple of Vedavyās who recited <span class=\\"e3\\">Śrīmad Bhāgavatam</span> and other Purāṇas at the assembly of 60,000 sages in Naimiṣāraṇya."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Svarūp Dāmodar</span> the constant companion of Śrīman Mahāprabhu who was regarded as the leader of all the Lord’s devotees and a second manifestation of the Lord Himself. He participated in the Pastimes of the Lord in Nabadwīp, accepted sannyās after the Lord did, and then joined Him in Śrī Purī Dhām. Both his scholarship and his singing were unparalleled amongst the Lord’s servants, and he served Śrīman Mahāprabhu night and day, personally caring for the Lord during His fits of divine madness. He screened all compositions that were brought to the Lord, and his writings about the identity and Pastimes of the Lord are renowned as the most profound and authoritative representation of Śrīman Mahāprabhu. He is Śrī Lalitā Devī in the Pastimes of Śrī Śrī Rādhā-Kṛṣṇa and the guardian of all Gauḍīya–Vaiṣṇavas."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Śyām</span> lit. ‘dark’; blackish; dark blue, grey, or green; resembling the colour of a dark cloud; a Name of Lord Śrī Kṛṣṇa describing His complexion."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">tīrtha</span> a holy place; a place of pilgrimage; a place visited or inhabited by the Lord or His devotees."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Toṭā Gopīnāth</span> lit. ‘Garden Gopīnāth’; the strikingly beautiful Deity of Lord Kṛṣṇa found by Śrīman Mahāprabhu in the garden near the Temple of Yameśvar in Śrī Purī Dhām. The Lord gave this Deity to Śrīla Gadādhar Paṇḍit to worship, and when Gadādhar grew old and became unable to reach up and garland the Deity, Gopīnāth sat down to accept his service. Toṭā Gopīnāth is thus known for His unique, graceful sitting posture."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Tretā-yuga</span> the second of the four ages that cycle throughout the existence of the material universe (Satya, Tretā, Dvāpar, and Kali). Tretā-yuga lasts 1,296,000 years and is best known for being the period of Lord Rāmachandra’s appearance. Fire sacrifice is the dharma of the age, and people in general at that time are virtuous and versed in the Vedas."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Tulasī</span> lit. ‘she who is incomparable’; Lord Kṛṣṇa’s favourite plant. Without her leaves, Kṛṣṇa will not accept any offering. Tulasī is a form of the gopī Vṛndā Devī, the personal expansion of Śrīmatī Rādhārāṇī who serves as the mistress of Vṛndāvan: she who distributes devotion to the Lord, gives entrance into Vraja, and makes arrangements for Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa’s Pastimes."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Tulasī Paḍichhā</span> the superintendent of the Jagannāth Temple at the time of Śrīman Mahāprabhu’s Pastimes in Śrī Purī Dhām."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Vaikuṇṭha</span> lit. ‘that which has no limit’ or ‘where there is no anxiety’; the spiritual world; the eternal abode of the Supreme Lord; the portion of the spiritual world presided over by Lakṣmī and Nārāyaṇ, where the Lord’s majesty is predominant and devotees serve the Lord with awe and reverence."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">vairāgya</span> renunciation; lit. ‘devoid of attachment’ or ‘intense attachment’. For a Vaiṣṇava, both senses are applicable—detachment from the mundane and attachment to the Lord—though in common speech, the word is used in the first sense."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">vairāgī</span> one who has or practises vairāgya."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Vaiṣṇava</span> lit. ‘one who is devoted to Viṣṇu’; a servant of the Supreme Lord; a member of one of the four Vaiṣṇava sampradāyas."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Vakreśvar Paṇḍit</span> an eternal associate of Śrīman Mahāprabhu who accompanied the Lord in Nabadwīp and Jagannāth Purī and greatly pleased Him with his tireless dancing."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">varṇa</span> the occupational divisions within society created by the Lord: the brāhmaṇs, kṣatriyas, vaiśyas, and śūdras. These divisions are differentiated by their functions and the modes of nature predominant within them, and strictly speaking an individual should be accepted as a member of one of them according to their character, not their heredity (though in recent history this is largely misunderstood). Brāhmaṇs study and teach the scriptures, perform worship for themselves and on behalf of others, and accept and give charity. They are situated in the mode of goodness. Kṣatriyas govern society, collect taxes, and engage in warfare. They also perform many of the duties of brāhmaṇs and are situated in a mixture of the modes of goodness and passion. Vaiśyas engage in agriculture, animal husbandry, and commerce. They also perform the duties of brāhmaṇs and are situated in a mixture of the modes of passion and ignorance. Śūdras engage in service to the other three varṇas. They are situated in the modes of ignorance."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">varṇāśram-dharma</span> the social and occupational orders established by the Lord consisting of the four varṇas (brāhmaṇ, kṣatriya, vaiśya, and śūdra) and the four āśrams (brahmacharya, gṛhastha, vānaprastha, and sannyās). When souls observe their duties within this system according to their nature as a means to serve the Supreme Lord, they gradually transcend the modes of material nature and satisfy the Lord. When souls consider the orders within the system to be determined by birth and use the system to pursue material gain or liberation, however, they do not attain any spiritual benefit."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">vāsanā</span> desires; material desires; the impressions in the subtle body produced by past experiences."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Vāsudev Ghoṣ</span> an eternal associate of Śrīman Mahāprabhu who appeared in Tamluk, West Bengal. He and his two elder brothers, Govinda Ghoṣ and Mādhava Ghoṣ, were renowned kīrtanīyās, and both Śrīman Mahāprabhu and Nityānanda Prabhu would dance to their singing with great satisfaction."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Veda</span> lit. ‘knowledge’; the knowledge revealed by the Supreme Lord through Lord Brahmā and the ṛṣis that explains the proper way for all souls to live and serve the Lord; the body of eternal knowledge recorded in separate scriptures at the beginning of Kali-yuga by Vedavyās, made up of the <span class=\\"e3\\">Ṛg-veda</span>, <span class=\\"e3\\">Sāma-veda</span>, <span class=\\"e3\\">Yajur-veda</span>, and <span class=\\"e3\\">Atharva-veda</span>, the Upaniṣads, and other texts."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Vidyāpati</span> a renowned devotee of Lord Kṛṣṇa who appeared approximately one hundred years before Śrīman Mahāprabhu in a brāhmaṇ family of scholars and ministers in Mithila in North India. His poems describing the Pastimes of Śrī Śrī Rādhā-Kṛṣṇa, and in particular his songs describing separation, were very dear to Śrīman Mahāprabhu."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Viṣṇu</span> lit. ‘the all-pervading Lord’; the maintainer of the universe; a Name of the Supreme Lord and His expansions that preside over spiritual and material worlds."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Viṣṇudūta</span> the attendants of Lord Viṣṇu who resemble Him in appearance."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Vraja</span> lit. ‘corral’; the eternal abode of Lord Kṛṣṇa; the 168-square-mile circular district that encompasses Vṛndāvan, Govardhan, and the other sites of Lord Kṛṣṇa’s Pastimes with the gopas and gopīs. Often used synonymously with <span class=\\"e3\\">Vṛndāvan</span>."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">vrata</span> lit. ‘vow’; an act of abstention; a rite, typically consisting of subjecting oneself to some form of austerity and performing specified actions to propitiate a deity."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Vṛndāvan</span> lit. ‘forest of Tulasī’; the eternal homeland of Lord Kṛṣṇa; the supreme abode in the spiritual world where love and devotion reach their zenith. Vṛndāvan appeared on earth with Lord Kṛṣṇa in what is known today as the Mathurā district of Uttar Pradesh in Northern India."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Vyāsadev (Vedavyās)</span> the Śaktyāveś-avatār of the Lord who compiled the Vedic literatures (the four Vedas, the Upaniṣads, the Purāṇas, <span class=\\"e3\\">Mahābhārata</span>, and other texts) and ultimately revealed Lord Śrī Kṛṣṇa as the Absolute Truth in <span class=\\"e3\\">Śrīmad Bhāgavatam</span>."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Yamadūta</span> the attendants of Yamarāj. They seize souls at the time of death and bring them to be judged by Yamarāj."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Yamarāj</span> lit. ‘master of regulation’; the god of justice who maintains order within the material world. He is revered as one of the twelve mahājans and a devotee of the Supreme Lord. He judges souls after death on the basis of the record of their actions kept by his assistant Chitragupta, and administers punishments or rewards as are appropriate in the form of the soul’s future body, destination, and fortune. He presides over Patalaloka, the lower region of the universe, and is also known as Kāla (Time), Dharma or Dharmarāj (Order or the Lord of order), and Mṛtyu (Death)."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">Yaśodā</span> the mother of Lord Kṛṣṇa and the queen of the cowherd people of Vraja."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">yoga</span> (1) union; the union of the soul with the Lord; (2) a path; a means to attain a goal; (3) a practice; (4) aṣṭāṅga-yoga; (5) a conjunction; an auspicious astrological circumstance."},{"class":"b50","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">yogī</span> a practitioner of yoga, esp. of haṭha- or aṣṭāṅga-yoga; one who seeks connection with the Absolute."},{"class":"b55","text":" <span class=\\"e32\\">yukta-vairāgya</span> lit. ‘proper renunciation’; using anything favourable to the Lord’s service in His service without personal attachment to it; recognising Śrī Guru, the Name, the Deity, the scriptures, and mahāprasād as spiritual, seeing everything in connection to the Lord, fully dedicating all of one’s available energy and resources to the Lord’s service, and accepting no less and no more than is necessary for oneself to engage in the Lord’s service."}]}]}')}}]);
